INSERT INTO `forums_posts` VALUES (43782,5600,84499,'2012-07-04 00:58:42','Congratulations! You have found a bug!  :chase: \n\nTo tell us about it we need specific information:  :borg: \n\n[*][b]The page url[/b] For example the url for the browse torrents page is [code]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php[/code] which when written in a post becomes: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php\n[*][b]What is wrong[/b] Tell us what the problem is, and if applicable the way you expect it to work.\n[*][b]How to reproduce it[/b] Please include enough information so that we can reproduce the bug ourselves. Reproduce it yourself first if possible, and make a note of what actions produce the bug.\n\nUse a title that gives some idea of what the bug is about, and [u]don\'t[/u] prefix it with \'BUG\' or anything else - lanz or I will do that once we have checked it out.\n\nThanks for your hard work! \n\n :bugchases: ',84499,'2012-07-05 21:13:22'),(43783,5601,84499,'2012-07-04 02:09:25','User profile page:\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=84499\n\nImages in the user profile which are too big for the column stretch over the edge of the box. It should probably be automatically scaled to fit.\n\nTo reproduce put an image in your profile that is wider than the column ( ~710px with a 1600x1200 display)\n\n[mcom]\n[b]Status:[/b] Confirmed Bug (originally reported by usb on previous test tracker)\n[b]FIXED[/b] - all images should scale appropriately now\n[/mcom]\n',84499,'2012-07-05 18:38:55'),(43785,5602,48010,'2012-07-04 17:01:50','assdafrgfdhg\n\nadd to this as a test\n\nEdit another test to make sure !',48010,'2012-07-05 17:08:30'),(43786,5601,48010,'2012-07-04 17:21:32','looks ok to me',NULL,NULL),(43787,5601,1,'2012-07-04 22:54:29','for me not. dave, a image its over the left sidebar\r\nprobably depends on the OS/browser we use',NULL,NULL),(43790,5605,47234,'2012-07-05 09:55:48','Ok found a few issues with BBCode now im working on my guide.\n\nFirstly is Anchor links\n\nAnchor link names can not include Caps as i found out to my frustration\n[mcom][b]Fixed[/b] - mifune\nits an oversight that they were not allowed before.[/mcom]\n\nThe BBCode guide suggests [code][#=name][/#][/code] at the anchor location.  The [code][/#][/code] is completely redundant and it works without it.  I didnt use it in my guide.\n[mcom][b]Confirmed Bug (kind of)[/b] - This works by accident, I will probably just make it so under the hood it automatically adds a close tag so the html is properly formed.\n[b]FIXED[/b] - it will now automatically close this tag for you in the html[/mcom]\n\n\n\n[b]mifune: moved other issue to [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2606]new thread[/url][/b]',84499,'2012-07-05 20:45:28'),(43791,5601,48010,'2012-07-05 17:04:33','this what i see\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=60CE_4FF5C8DC][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=60CE_4FF5C8DC[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(43792,5605,84499,'2012-07-05 17:47:59','[b]Allowing Caps in achor links[/b] - fixed. its an oversight that they were not allowed before. \n[b]\nNot closing anchor tags[/b]: well... there is no gaurantee that an unclosed tag will not break the page. You end up with an unclosed <a> tag in the html and how browsers handle badly formed html is undefined. Luckily most browsers wont choke but they might, probably it should either not recognise the tag (ie. you would just see [code][#=name][/code] unparsed) or automagically include a close tag :hmmm: \n\nEDIT:\nIn fact... whilst fixing this I notice that it does in fact slightly break the page when you dont close the tag! The text for about 3 paragraphs from \"Its not really just a seedbox its actually a dedicated server \" is incorrectly formatted bold and large because of this. No matter I have added a check that adds a close tag for you if you use the format [code][#=name][/code] so dont change the article, it will fix itself when the code gets updated ;)\n',84499,'2012-07-05 21:05:09'),(43793,5601,84499,'2012-07-05 17:53:23','Haha, you need to go to the link to see the problem, the staff comment thing is not an example of the bug - it really is a staff comment ;) (okay you might think its weird that I put a staff comment in my own post but that is the way I intend to format the bug reports so I thought I would give an example lol).\n\nheres what I see btw (with browser shrunk to induce smallest possible width):\n\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/aaeVyrUy][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/aaeVyrUy.jpg[/IMG][/URL] ',84499,'2012-07-05 18:48:01'),(43795,5601,84499,'2012-07-05 18:40:14','\r\n\r\nI fixed this, hopefully [u]all[/u] images will now be scaled to fit the container they are in. If you see otherwise let us know! (allow a day or so for the test tracker to be updated with the fix though)',NULL,NULL),(43796,5606,84499,'2012-07-05 20:40:40','[originally posted by [user=clownius]clownius[/user]]\n\nSecond is the delicate bit.  Over at Emp.me this would have worked fine\n\n[code][size=2][b][u]Test[/b][/size][/u][/code]\n\nHere it will produce\n\n[size=2][b][u]Test[/b][/size][/u]\n\nYou will have to edit it in the exact right order like this\n\n[code][size=2][b][u]Test[/u][/b][/size][/code]\n\nto produce\n\n[size=2][b][u]Test[/u][/b][/size]\n\nNot sure if thats an easy fix but i can see lots of presentations and forum threads getting messed up when they get moved\n\n[mcom][b]Kind of a Bug[/b] - You are right about stuff getting messed up... so it is a problem. But there is no way to fix this as such as this functionality is a consequence of a sloppy parser. I wouldnt exactly call it a feature, more like an unintended consequence :sad:\nHaving said all that maybe we can strip orphaned closing tags from the outputted text :hmmm: let me ponder on the consequences...\n[b] (removed experimental fix)[/b] - under consideration...[/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-06 15:27:28'),(43797,5606,84499,'2012-07-05 20:46:16','\r\nUntil PKorus raised this same issue it never occured to me it was a problem, in a commercial project I would blame it on the brief not being accurate :lol: . I\'m not sure the outcome would be have been any different even if we had thought of this though... essentially the reason that badly formed bbcode can work on the current site is the same reason that there are errors in the bbcode on the current site. The bbocde parser that comes with gazelle is much more robust and making it work in exactly the same way as the parser on emp.me would mean scrapping a very well coded parser and replacing it with a slightly crappy one.',NULL,NULL),(43798,5606,84499,'2012-07-05 20:54:53','\r\n\r\nActually we can easily strip out any (and all) orphaned closing tags from the outputted text... this is a bandaid but would probably fix most issues with badly formed tags from being reflected in the page. \r\n\r\nI am running this at home and trying to find if there are any unintended consequences. One thing is it would mean that if you want to write something in the format [pre][/*anything at all in here*][/pre] you couldnt (without putting it in something like a code tag) :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(43806,5605,47234,'2012-07-06 00:26:24','Thanks Mifune',NULL,NULL),(43807,5606,47234,'2012-07-06 00:50:40','This is all beyond this clowns understanding.... i will let you and Lanz decide the best solution',NULL,NULL),(43809,5607,1507,'2012-07-06 07:30:45','[b]I gave myself some slots and noticed that only Double Seed button appears and Free Leech is no longer available...  So, if there are no Free Leech slots, the bonus shoppe has to be corrected where is says:\n\n[quote]A slot will give you the option to either [color=red]freeleech[/color] or doubleseed a torrent. [color=red]Freeleech will allow you to download the torrent without counting the downloaded amount[/color], while doubleseed will count the uploaded amount times 2.[/quote]\n\nNot a bug, but needs correcting....\n\nusb[/b]\n\n[mcom][b]BUG:[/b] The error is actually that there is no freeleech available for some torrents[/mcom]\n\n:usb:',84499,'2012-07-06 15:31:24'),(43810,5608,1366,'2012-07-06 07:39:12','I am using internet explorer and the search center is open and only says Open Search center(no Close Search Center) I cannot close the search center\n\n\n\n[mcom][b]FIXED[/b] - stupid stupid IE - bodged up a workaround,  [/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-17 04:06:36'),(43811,5609,1507,'2012-07-06 07:39:30','[b]I just gave myself 100GB download amount...  It registers in the staff notes box, but doesn\'t show under up/down at the top of the page...  I refreshed the page several times (I remembered this time  :laugh: ), but it doesn\'t register...\n\nusb[/b]\n\n:usb:\n\n[mcom][b]FIXED:[/b] doh a stupid spelling mistake was preventing the cache from being cleared when you adjusted up/down[/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-06 15:57:46'),(43813,5609,1507,'2012-07-06 08:05:52','[b]I\'ve just noticed that it shows correctly in the user info field, but not at the top of the page...   :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb [/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(43814,5609,1507,'2012-07-06 08:20:12','[b]It is working now, so I don\'t know if it was fixed or it just took a long time to update...\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(43815,5609,1507,'2012-07-06 08:25:02','[b]Subtracting download amount doesn\'t register correctly at the top either...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(43816,5610,6203,'2012-07-06 08:34:13','the color attribute doesn\'t work correctly. when i try to assign the color orange to a font it shows up as broken bbcode. otherwise, when i use the hex code #FFBF00 instead of the word orange it works.\n\n\n\n[mcom][b]A Good Idea[/b] - orange is not in the named color attributes and probably should be... I will add it later[/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-06 16:01:10'),(43817,5611,6203,'2012-07-06 08:36:01','when i try to change some bbcode i cannot submit the chnages. it got the error in the subject field.\n\n\n[mcom][b]confirmed bug[/b] - ony mods can edit torrents doh!\n[b]-FIXED[/b] authors can edit torrents without being a mod now![/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-06 18:45:02'),(43820,5614,47234,'2012-07-06 14:06:05','I just passed the URL of the test tracker to \"yamchan07bb\".  He cant login with current username and pass.  One more login and it claims it will ban him.\r\n\r\nI have had to reset passwords before for deadmanwanking and others for the same reason.  I think we have a bug and its major.  Somehow usernames and/or passwords are not transferring right when you import the database.\r\n\r\nIf you start inviting people without fixing this expect a lot of PM\'s and a huge cleanup.\r\n\r\nUnless of course you did something to break this on purpose.  But broken it is',NULL,NULL),(43821,5614,6203,'2012-07-06 14:26:35','yes, i had several times the same problem. lanz reseted my pass two times.',NULL,NULL),(43822,5614,47234,'2012-07-06 14:27:52','Add barumba to the list of couldnt sign in with current username and pass.',NULL,NULL),(43823,5615,47234,'2012-07-06 15:10:50','Ok so im seeing 200GB+ torrents not set as freeleech.  Obviously that part of the database isnt working ;)',NULL,NULL),(43824,5616,6203,'2012-07-06 15:15:10','the red disk besides the torrent title in the overview shows up for me but i never DL it. same problem at my own torrent i uploaded. it says that i am leeching it. :D\n\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=1419_4FF700BD[/img]\n\n\n[mcom][b]confirmed bug[/b]\n[b]FIXED[/b] - seems to have been fixed at some point :D[/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-14 20:23:43'),(43825,5617,47234,'2012-07-06 15:18:15','Im still seeing the What.CD favicon? on my test tracker tabs instead of a Empornium e :)\n\nDeluge also still has no favicon for the test tracker :)\n\nIf you need screens to explain what i mean yell.\n\n[mcom][b]FIXED:[/b] include favicon[/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-07 02:35:10'),(43826,5618,129045,'2012-07-06 15:24:36','See: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35137\n\nClick on [ quote ], the comment should be inserted in the reply box, the result is the handle appears correctly [quote = username], but the contents appear as \"null\"\n\n[i][b]EDIT:[/b][/i] Scratch that, it seems like a site wide issue, please update the thread title :hmmm:\n\n[quote=yamchan07bb]        null\n\n        null\n        					\nnull\n[/quote]\n\nQuoting my forum post.\n\n[mcom][b]confirmed bug[/b] just took a quick look at this and I can see exactly how I broke it lol... will fix later\n[b]FIXED[/b] - quote should work everywhere on the site now (threads, torrent comments, collage comments, request comments)[/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-06 22:24:43'),(43827,5608,84499,'2012-07-06 15:34:47','\r\n\r\nI cant confirm the bug right now until I reboot into windoze, but just to check have you got cookies enabled for this site/that page?\r\n\r\nAlso if anyone else can confirm this bug that would be helpful to us.\r\n\r\n(please tell us what browser you are using if you post re: this)\r\n',NULL,NULL),(43828,5608,47234,'2012-07-06 15:40:28','Well it works fine in FF 13.01 on Kubuntu 11.10\n\nEdit: Add Chromium 18.0.1025.168 under Kubuntu 11.10 working fine.\n\n\nLooks like yet another case of IE being a PITA and not conforming to the same standard of every other browser in the world.  MS is good at that trick',47234,'2012-07-06 16:17:41'),(43829,5608,129045,'2012-07-06 15:42:28','Opera 12 here (64bit, Windows 7), works fine.\n\nEDIT: Opera 12 under Ubuntu works fine too.\n\nEDIT: Indeed, using [color=#FF0000]Internet Explorer 9.0[/color] here, the button doesn\'t work. Search appears expanded as default, while the button says \"Open search center\", clicking on it really does nothing.',129045,'2012-07-06 15:49:19'),(43830,5619,70679,'2012-07-06 15:54:26','ok it worked for me so I am now here\n\nEdit by Clownius: Barumba couldnt login with normal pass but the pass reset link did work :)',47234,'2012-07-06 15:58:20'),(43831,5610,84499,'2012-07-06 16:01:55','\r\n\r\ncurrent valid colors are:\r\n\r\n\'aqua\', \'aquamarine\', \'magenta\', \'darkmagenta\', \'slategrey\', \'pink\', \'hotpink\', \'black\', \'wheat\', \'midnightblue\', \'forestgreen\', \'blue\', \'lightblue\', \'fuchsia\', \'lightgreen\', \'green\', \'grey\', \'lightgrey\', \'lime\', \'maroon\', \'navy\', \'olive\', \'khaki\', \'darkkhaki\', \'gold\', \'goldenrod\', \'darkgoldenrod\', \'purple\', \'violet\', \'red\', \'crimson\', \'firebrick\', \'gainsboro\', \'silver\', \'teal\', \'linen\', \'aliceblue\', \'lavender\', \'white\', \'whitesmoke\', \'lightyellow\', \'yellow\',\r\n\r\nI dont think we want to add a huge number more but we can add a few more; orange should be one, any others?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(43832,5611,84499,'2012-07-06 16:04:23','\r\n\r\nneed more information: what url were you on and what actions do we need to take to reproduce it?',NULL,NULL),(43833,5610,47234,'2012-07-06 16:06:53','Moved to suggestions.  Tool appears to work well :)',NULL,NULL),(43834,5615,84499,'2012-07-06 16:07:18','\r\n\r\n[mcom]TODO: put a line in import routines to set FL for imported torrents >20gb (or perhaps we should just transfer the current FL status from emp? :hmmm:)[/mcom]',NULL,NULL),(43835,5615,47234,'2012-07-06 16:09:46','I think transfer current at least.  As for the 20GB thing consistency say set anything over 20GB that isnt too :hmm:\r\nBut if its FL now taking it off FL would be kinda mean',NULL,NULL),(43836,5620,47234,'2012-07-06 16:11:41','I see we have shedloads of cool new smilies and im sure people would love to know the Code for them.  Can we have somewhere we cabn look up the smilies please.\r\n\r\nUnless i missed it somewhere obvious',NULL,NULL),(43837,5615,1243,'2012-07-06 16:18:58','The best way to go would be to import the old freeleech torrents as is and then use the new system from now on.',NULL,NULL),(43838,5615,47234,'2012-07-06 16:20:28','Works for me we have always gone with the rule applies from today thing and doesnt apply to anything before this with other things like for example Image hosts.  Why not for FL too?',47234,'2012-07-06 16:20:52'),(43839,5621,47234,'2012-07-06 16:23:36','Refers to an IRC pass thingymabob like What.CD uses still.  Would be nice to see this work like current emp and open an IRC page/chat or better yet a chat like another site we staff use ;)',NULL,NULL),(43840,5622,47234,'2012-07-06 16:25:46','How about a TODO forum section for things other staff (maybe even users) can do for Lanz and Mifune with current tools towards getting things finished?  Might help with some of the workload and let us know whats in need of doing :)',NULL,NULL),(43841,5617,129045,'2012-07-06 16:27:33','Tested a minute after mifune edited the post. Slanted \"[size=4]e[/size]\" favicon showing up fine on IE, Firefox and Opera.',NULL,NULL),(43843,5615,1243,'2012-07-06 16:35:56','Updated the import script to set the correct freeleech torrents.',NULL,NULL),(43844,5617,47234,'2012-07-06 16:36:42','Fixed here now too for FF. \r\n\r\nNeed a test tracker only torrent for my seedbox to test Deluge.  Due to Deluge not playing nice (and me being too lazy to work out why) I have every torrent seeding in Deluge for emp and ktorrent for emp.beta',NULL,NULL),(43845,5615,47234,'2012-07-06 16:37:58','You guys dont mess around do you :lol:\r\n\r\nFind a bug and its fixed minutes later :)',NULL,NULL),(43846,5617,1243,'2012-07-06 16:39:22','favicon added',NULL,NULL),(43847,5611,6203,'2012-07-06 17:15:42','the error appears when i am intended to change the bbcode from a torrent. i press \"preview\" and that works. to submit the changes is not possible caused of the above mentioned error message i received.',NULL,NULL),(43848,5611,1507,'2012-07-06 17:23:59','[b]I tagged NG\'s upload for deletion, and he got the same error....\r\n\r\n[url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35132]Check Me...[/url]\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(43849,5623,1507,'2012-07-06 17:26:54','[b]I found this in NovaGent\'s torrent cumments:\r\n\r\n[quote]#51381 NovaGent (Good Perv) 6 hours and 21 mins a