,5624,129045,'2012-07-06 17:57:07','Opera 12 here and it works: hovering anywhere over \"Torrents uploaded: RankingNumber\" will show a tooltip under the mouse cursor displaying the number of torrents uploaded (61 in my case)\r\n\r\nIt just seems a little redundant, as the ranking list is between Stats and Community, where it already shows each value in plain sight.\r\n\r\nEDIT: Tested under IE 9.0 and it also shows up fine.\r\n',129045,'2012-07-06 18:01:35'),(43857,5625,84499,'2012-07-06 18:01:01','btw:\n\nlinks work in the format [code][link=/top10.php?type=users]top10 users[/link][/code]\n\n[link=/top10.php?type=users]top10 users[/link]\n\n\nbut you know... perhaps they should work with (still local only) longform urls as well and just trim that bit off :hmmm:\n\n',84499,'2012-07-06 18:59:02'),(43858,5622,129045,'2012-07-06 18:04:59','Can\'t find anything wrong under simple use.\r\n\r\nBrowsing, downloading, commenting, adding tags, voting tags, toggling user settings, adding a signature, editing posts all seem to work as intended. Only odd thing I could find was at the tag rules page, here: http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=tag\r\n\r\nThe tags list link leads to [color=red][i][b]trackerdev.mooo.com[/b][/i][/color][b][i]/torrents.php?action=tag_synomyns[/i][/b] rather than [i][b]empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=tag_synomyns[/b][/i]\r\n\r\nShould I post it under Bugs?\r\n\r\n[mcom]No need, fixed it, thanks for pointing it out.[/mcom]\r\n\r\n[s][b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b] What about labelling the quick search boxes? A simple \"Quick search\" to the left or maybe a simple icon:\r\n\r\nIcon > [URL]http://i.imgbox.com/aamconoO.png[/URL]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=B8CF_4FF73862][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-B8CF_4FF73862.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\n[quote]What about labelling the quick search boxes? A simple \"Quick search\" to the left or maybe a simple icon:\r\n\r\nIcon > [URL]http://i.imgbox.com/aamconoO.png[/URL]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=B8CF_4FF73862][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-B8CF_4FF73862.jpg[/img][/url][/quote][/s]\r\n\r\n\r\nEh, I\'m pretty sure I posted that as a new post, rather than editing my first post  :confused: \r\n\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT2: Is this thread locked or something?[/i][/b]\r\n\r\n[i][b]EDIT3: Gah, nevermind, I\'m slow, this is probably automerge at work, I just wanted to bump the thread :P[/b][/i]',129045,'2012-07-09 18:44:19'),(43859,5625,84499,'2012-07-06 18:13:35','\r\n\r\nokay what is happening is that the top10 here uses 5 GB as the minimum download instead of 1 GB....\r\n\r\n\r\nit could be changed :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(43860,5626,6203,'2012-07-06 18:33:37','when i deactivate the \"Tags in lists: Hide tags in lists\" in the settings the tags show up, what they shouldn\'t. :P\n\n\n[mcom][b]FIXED[/b][/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-06 18:43:55'),(43861,5623,84499,'2012-07-06 18:42:40','\r\n\r\nI entered [code]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=9130_4FF64C1D[/code] and it works.\r\n\r\n\r\ndunno?',NULL,NULL),(43862,5625,1243,'2012-07-06 18:45:41','Yeah it should be changed imo',NULL,NULL),(43863,5626,129045,'2012-07-06 18:47:30','Same here.\r\n\r\nOdd, because I\'m pretty sure the first time I accessed the Browse page, the tag list was hidden by default.',NULL,NULL),(43864,5627,6203,'2012-07-06 19:07:25','clicking on description text of the check boxes in the settings section triggers an activation of the first check box\r\n:P',NULL,NULL),(43865,5627,1243,'2012-07-06 19:20:37','Thanks for the report, fixed.',NULL,NULL),(43866,5628,84499,'2012-07-06 20:22:22','\n\n[b]EDIT: The discussion around this has ended up [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2635]in this thread[/url]  :smile1: [/b]\n \n[hr]\n\nThe goal of the bonus system is \n\n1) To encourage seeding\n\n2) To distribute some free GB to help out users with bad upload speeds\n\n3) To encourage site participation\n\n\nIf buyGB is too cheap then there is no incentive to seed as you can just buy your dl away instead, if its too expensive then its too hard to get the credits and its not worth the effort...\n\nThe new system counts up to 60 torrents at once for bonus credits, and no weekly max. So... if you seed 60 * 24 * 7 then you get 10,080 credits. But this max will be harder to reach, no more seeding 1000 torrents at once!\n\nFor those that are credit rich, we have some bling that will be available to buy (actual images will change im sure), but the main thing for balance is the buy GB costs, what should they be?\n\n\n\n',84499,'2012-07-17 16:43:30'),(43867,5607,1243,'2012-07-06 21:00:41','It\'s fixed anyway ;)',NULL,NULL),(43868,5607,1507,'2012-07-06 21:22:49','[quote=Lanz]        null\r\n\r\n        null\r\n        					\r\nnull\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]Thank you Lanz...\r\n\r\nI could kiss you, but you\'d probably whup my ass...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :tease: ',1507,'2012-07-06 21:27:14'),(43869,5608,1243,'2012-07-06 21:27:15','We should just ban IE on the spot. :laugh:\r\n\r\nHate that damn browser and all the problems it cause when making web pages. ',NULL,NULL),(43870,5629,1507,'2012-07-06 21:33:09','[url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2607&page=1#post23868]mouseover bug[/url]\r\n\r\n[b]I\'m using Opera, and in this particular thread, when I mouseover my user name to get the drop down menu, the staff message and my quoted message overlays the drop down menu so you cannot access those links and the drop down abruptly closes...\r\n\r\nIt only has done this on this one thread so far and if I move to a different page it doesn\'t happen...\r\n\r\nNothing serious but just wanted to report it....\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[/b]',NULL,NULL),(43871,5629,1507,'2012-07-06 21:36:29','\r\n[b]Click image to enlarge...[/b]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/aagdE7w3][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/aagdE7w3.jpg[/IMG][/URL] \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-06 21:37:34'),(43872,5629,1243,'2012-07-06 21:50:47','[mcom]Should be fixed now[/mcom]',NULL,NULL),(43873,5629,129045,'2012-07-06 21:53:17','Confirmed on Opera, IE and Firefox.\r\n\r\nThe hover menu will appear behind the post contents.\r\n\r\nProblem seems worse on Opera, as the line spacing seems too excessive in comparison to Firefox or IE.\r\n\r\nEDIT: Oops, indeed it\'s fixed, still, the line spacing seems odd in Opera when compared to other browsers.',129045,'2012-07-06 21:54:59'),(43874,5629,1243,'2012-07-06 21:56:56','Yeah I looked at it before and it doesn\'t make any sense, I\'ll take a closer look when more pressing things are out of the way.',NULL,NULL),(43876,5629,129045,'2012-07-06 22:08:11','Playing around here:\r\n\r\n[color=#FF0000]#stats_block ul li, #header_bottom ul li [/color] and its line-height seems to be the one governing the line space, 18px is too excessive, setting to [color=#FF0000]1[/color] seems to work fine for Opera and Firefox.\r\n\r\nEDIT: It still too spaced out in comparison to Firefox, but it will cut its length considerably. Using less than 1 may cause some cramming on other browsers... But I\'m not sure, tried 0.7 and it seemed fine on Firefox, can\'t test on IE, because I don\'t know how to use it lol\r\n\r\nEDIT2: Oh shit, 1 is the safest value, just noticed the stats at the top right corner are affected by it too, anything lower and it\'ll become hard to read.\r\n\r\nEDIT3: Nevermind, setting the value individually for [color=#FF3300]#header_bottom ul li[/color] will fix it :)',129045,'2012-07-06 22:50:27'),(43877,5630,129045,'2012-07-06 22:21:38','I PM\'d the staff, but better be safe than sorry :P\n\n[quote]Lanz seems to have updated the buttons successfully based on redmax1 comment here: [url=/torrents.php?id=35137][/url], but the comment box is still titled \"Post reply\". To avoid confusion, wouldn\'t be better to rename it to \"Post comment\" or maybe \"Add a comment\" like current EMP.me?[/quote]\n\nOpinions?',84499,'2012-07-07 00:20:22'),(43878,5630,84499,'2012-07-06 22:57:49','\r\n\r\nI have changed that, and also reflected the changes in the post comment boxes in collages and requests.\r\n\r\nI dont mind changing it again if we come to a consensus on there being better alternatives, I think it should be whatever is clearest to most people, and thats a hard thing for me to judge...\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(43879,5630,129045,'2012-07-06 23:34:35','Well then, I guess it should be \"Add a comment\". Since that\'s what\'s being used on current EMP and I really don\'t see a reason to change. It\'s clear enough.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(43880,5625,84499,'2012-07-07 00:26:27','[quote=mifune]btw:\r\n\r\nlinks work in the format [code][link=/top10.php?type=users]top10 users[/link][/code]\r\n\r\n[link=/top10.php?type=users]top10 users[/link]\r\n\r\n\r\nbut you know... perhaps they should work with (still local only) longform urls as well and just trim that bit off :hmmm:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nactually it occurs to me that the link tag is superfluous, and its better to have the functionality of link in the url tag, it should be a bit simpler this way, there are just url tags and it works out what to do with them based on the form of the url.\r\n\r\nIts better to use the form [code]/top10.php?type=users[/code] rather than [code]http://empornium.mooo.com/top10.php?type=users[/code] because when the url changes when we go live links in the first format will still work, whereas links in the longer format will be broken. Obviously on the forums it dosent matter as all these posts will probably be nuked, but for articles etc. it will make a difference!',NULL,NULL),(43881,5631,78812,'2012-07-07 00:27:06','if you look at my torrent:\n\n[url=/torrents.php?id=33969&torrentid=6063][/url]\n\nu\'ll see the images are stuck together .. its a but ugly. I think that everyone will agree that the space bewteen images should stay the same as in the previous BBCode of EMP.me V1\n\nfurthermore the font that I coded with [size=1] is really really small.. and the one with [size=2} is the same size as the normal one before in V1\n\nalso I would like to add that IMHO we should use the old logo that has always been around..\n\nalso I would like to know what the max width for images now is .. so I can recalibrate my Photoshop actions..\n\n\nmy 2 cents\n\n\n[mcom][b]FIXED[/b] Im going to call this fixed as lanz fixed the space issue and the size thing has been changed.\n-any outstanding issues please post again thanks[/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-08 01:19:52'),(43882,5631,129045,'2012-07-07 00:58:35','Uh... what? Using Opera here, this is what I see:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=E756_4FF78955][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=E756_4FF78955[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nAs far as I remember that\'s exactly how it showed up on the other EMP.\r\n\r\nAbout the font sizes... yeah, that seems inconsistent as of now, Size=3 on the other EMP would result in size=10 here :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[size=2]size=2[/size] [size=3]size=3[/size] [size=4]size=4[/size] [size=5]size=5[/size] [size=6]size=6[/size] [size=7]size=7[/size] [size=8]size=8[/size] [size=9]size=9[/size] [size=10]size=10[/size]\r\n\r\nEDIT: And dang, someone need to rethink the tag box position.\r\n\r\nEDIT2: Firefox also shows it the same way... the images aren\'t stuck together  :confused: ',129045,'2012-07-07 01:13:36'),(43883,5631,1243,'2012-07-07 01:21:23','That\'s because I changed it earlier ;)\n\nAnd we have a plan for the font size',1243,'2012-07-07 01:22:28'),(43884,5631,84499,'2012-07-07 01:49:49','[quote=PKorus]if you look at my torrent:\n\n[url=/torrents.php?id=33969&torrentid=6063][/url]\n\nu\'ll see the images are stuck together .. its a but ugly. I think that everyone will agree that the space bewteen images should stay the same as in the previous BBCode of EMP.me V1\n\nfurthermore the font that I coded with [size=1] is really really small.. and the one with [size=2} is the same size as the normal one before in V1\n\nalso I would like to add that IMHO we should use the old logo that has always been around..\n\nalso I would like to know what the max width for images now is .. so I can recalibrate my Photoshop actions..\n\n\nmy 2 cents[/quote]\n\n\nI do not see butt ugly images stuck together... [EDIT: because Lanz already fixed it lol]\n\n\nFont Size: we have changed the size so that size=1 is the normal text size and size=0 is the tiny text size. the bigger sizes are smaller than emps but its better to have more text size levels than there are at emp so there is no getting round that, but it wont be \'broke\' as such just some of the larger text from the old site will be smaller (but still larger than normal).\n\n\nLogo: :hmmm: we\'ll think about this later\n\n\nMax Width: All Images will be resized to fit if they are too large for the page.\nI have added an absolute width attribute to the bg tag to help with presentations: if you use the format [code][bg=500px]Your code here[/bg][/code] you will get a fixed width column. It will default align to the center but you can use [code][bg=500px,left][/code] or change left to right/center to specify an alignment (You can also specify a bg color to this tag with format [code][bg=500px,left,red][/code] where the color attribute is a named color or a hex value). The maximum width you can use in this is 920px, which I *think* wont break the page even on the narrowest screen resolution, but it needs more testing. See the [url=/articles.php?topic=bbcode]bbCode guide[/url] for more details in the examples at the bottom. There are also table tags you can use for a more structured layout (the same attributes work for tables as for bg tags).\n\n',84499,'2012-07-07 02:04:13'),(43885,5631,129045,'2012-07-07 01:54:33','I think he meant \"bit\" not \"butt\"  :laugh: \r\n\r\nSo Lanz fixed it... [i]Jeez, so much efficiency. We can\'t even bitch about problems without having someone quickly fixing it[/i]. Where\'s the fun in that  :tongue: ',NULL,NULL),(43886,5631,84499,'2012-07-07 01:56:43','\r\n\r\nlol yeah lanz ninja fixed it :ninja:',NULL,NULL),(43887,5631,129045,'2012-07-07 02:08:02','And mang, those new bbcodes are pretty awesome. I was breaking my head before, trying to place images with text right above them while keeping them centered in the description area, now it seems pretty simple using the new codes :D\r\n\r\nEDIT: Eh... nevermind. Spoke too soon, this seems even more complicated to handle... is it possible to set two [bg] elements side by side?\r\nWith a result similar to what I did here: http://torrents.empornium.me/details.php?id=24481 , otherwise I\'ll need to resort to - or _ instead of spaces to compensate the distances and then hide them using color codes...\r\n\r\nEDIT2: Yeah, a little too much work, but it works :) http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=24481\r\n\r\nNow just waiting the color codes to get sorted out.\n\nWill try tomorrow, now off to catch some Z\'s',129045,'2012-07-07 05:09:08'),(43888,5619,67255,'2012-07-07 02:22:48','Yes the same happened to me',NULL,NULL),(43889,5632,67255,'2012-07-07 02:34:42','The user apparition made a post about tags on http://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=1611\r\n\r\nThis post is very good in terms of the guide it offer, any possibility after the bugs are squash to include a couple of this examples?\r\n\r\nExample, a drop down menus with the different options set on this guide, it will help clarify a set standard and agreed upon way to write tags, making them much more effective.',NULL,NULL),(43891,5633,77214,'2012-07-07 03:15:09','I\'ve used Bit Tornado T-0.3.18 on the current Empornium without problems, but get this error message on this test site:\r\n\"got bad file info - bad bencoded data\".\r\nThe torrent I\'m trying to download does works just fine on UTorrent 3.1.3 client.\r\nHere\'s the torrent:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35136&page=1#post51390\r\n\r\nNo problem just using Utorrent from here on out, but I\'m curious to know what would cause the error message.\r\n     Good luck with everything!!!!!!!!!',NULL,NULL),(43893,5634,47234,'2012-07-07 03:18:44','Still setup for What.CD by the look of things ;-)  Doesnt actually go anywhere but an error page on paypal in any case.',NULL,NULL),(43894,5633,47234,'2012-07-07 03:21:31','Well i can confirm that torrent works fine with Deluge and KTorrent...\r\n\r\nIm looking at Bit Tornado for having an issue.....',NULL,NULL),(43895,5633,77214,'2012-07-07 03:28:57','Thanks for the reply.\r\nBit Tornado also won\'t work with torrents at torsky.org, which caused me to seek out another client..... looks like my old friend Bit Tornado will have to be put down after all these years. ',NULL,NULL),(43896,5635,129045,'2012-07-07 03:35:34','Visit it here: http://empornium.mooo.com/bonus.php (you can find it by hovering your username and then selecting \'Bonus\' on the list, [i]your username located at the top right side of every page[/i])\r\n\r\nCredits are obtained at the same rate as before and it isn\'t capped at 3360 anymore, there\'s some interesting options but prices for the usual bonuses went up. [b][i]Your opinions?[/i][/b]\r\n\r\nIMO, the jump seems a little too steep. e.g. The bonus to slash -10Gb went from [color=#009900]2500[/color] to [color=#FF3300]8000[/color] credits.\r\n\r\nI don\'t mind the raise in price for a custom title or the current prices for the custom icons\\plates, but the bonuses that affect ratio in any way could use some discounts :)',129045,'2012-07-07 03:41:12'),(43897,5636,77214,'2012-07-07 03:41:53','What decided the big increase in rates? ',NULL,NULL),(43898,5635,1243,'2012-07-07 03:43:16','Nothing is fixed in stone when it comes to the prices. But you need to remember that the max credit is 60 torrents at any moment, so roughly 10,000 credits per week. We also do not have the the ratio value here, you ALWAYS get 1 credit for one torrent.\r\n\r\nBut we are open for suggestions.',NULL,NULL),(43899,5636,47234,'2012-07-07 03:44:31','Im guessing the big increase in possible earnings but its certainly to be adjusted yet :)\r\n',NULL,NULL),(43900,5635,84499,'2012-07-07 03:46:00','[quote=yamchan07bb]Visit it here: http://empornium.mooo.com/bonus.php (you can find it by hovering your username and then selecting \'Bonus\' on the list, [i]your username located at the top right side of every page[/i])\n\nCredits are obtained at the same rate as before and it isn\'t capped at 3360 anymore, there\'s some interesting options but prices for the usual bonuses went up. [b][i]Your opinions?[/i][/b]\n\nIMO, the jump seems a little too steep. e.g. The bonus to slash -10Gb went from [color=#009900]2500[/color] to [color=#FF3300]8000[/color] credits.\n\nI don\'t mind the raise in price for a custom title or the current prices for the custom icons\\plates, but the bonuses that affect ratio in any way could use some discounts :)[/quote]\n\n\nthat is true, the prices have gone up.\n\nThe amount you can earn a week has also gone up though, it will count 60 torrents at once which you can do all week (there is no longer a seperate weekly maximum) to give you 60 * 7 * 24 = 10,080 credits. This is harder to earn than it used to be in some ways but you can earn more... but we might need to balance the costs for -gb a bit.\n',84499,'2012-07-07 03:46:52'),(43901,5636,84499,'2012-07-07 03:48:45','\r\nsee [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2635]this thread[/url] for discussion  :smile1: ',NULL,NULL),(43902,5637,67255,'2012-07-07 03:56:05','Where: In the setting page for your username\nWhat is wrong: When clicking preset for setting paranoia level; nothing happens\nAlso where is the option to hide the email?\n\n[mcom][b]FIXED:[/b] preset button for paranoia button on edit user settings page dosent work[/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-23 04:58:44'),(43903,5635,88669,'2012-07-07 03:56:54','A double seed slot that would cost half its price, but last for half the time. This is because for me after uploading to 2 or 3 peers 100%, their speed is so greater then mine that my upload drops to 3 kb/s.\r\nEven small torrents could benefit from a smaller double-seed. However, they could be \"sold\" in a pack of two, to maintain is price.',NULL,NULL),(43904,5635,129045,'2012-07-07 03:56:59','So I\'m overreacting at the prices  :tongue: \r\n\r\nOn the other EMP I reached  224 days worth of seed time this week, how much would that translate to if it didn\'t have the 3360 limit set? Or using the old formula you had posted still works for this too? [i](140 x 24 = 3360)[/i]\r\n\r\nThat would put me raking around 5000 per week :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(43905,5638,88669,'2012-07-07 04:07:53','I\'m using Opera 12 x64 on win7 x64, 1920x1800.\r\n\r\nThis is how it looks\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=66AA_4FF7B509][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=66AA_4FF7B509&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n\r\nAnd this is my suggestions (paintbrush work)\r\n\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=79C5_4FF7B509][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=79C5_4FF7B509&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nCenter align the text and tick box, remover border between text and tick box and remove unnecessary text warp.\r\nThis phenoma seems to happen on the \"post new thread\" too... the \"body isn\'t centered though looks ok.',88669,'2012-07-07 04:08:40'),(43906,5637,84499,'2012-07-07 04:13:41','\r\n\r\nre: email no-one (but staff) can see your email address  :tinfoil: ',NULL,NULL),(43907,5635,77214,'2012-07-07 04:14:39','Ooops!! Sorry about starting the other thread.... all this porn is making me blind and didn\'t see this!\r\nSomething to consider when adjusting the credit rates is some folks may not have the drive space to run 60 torrents at once and me for me personally, I can\'t run the \'puter anywhere near 24/7 anyway (power outages from tropical storms, others on my computer...). The credit thing is a lot of fun and can really get pervs out of the hole with slower connections, but I actually feel bad to argue about it since my ratio is fine. I\'m sure whatever it ends up being will be fair and not frustrating. \r\n     The \"Free Leech\" thing is also great to help get the ratio up if the credits are out of reach.... hope that continues as well.',NULL,NULL),(43908,5637,129045,'2012-07-07 04:14:40','Confirmed. Using Opera 12 and Firefox 13.\r\n\r\nDisabling each option individually also doesn\'t seem to have any effect (e.g. \"Last seen\" still show up in the profile page)\r\n\r\nSeconded: Option to actually hide the email and passkey from showing up.\r\n\r\nEDIT: Seems like all browsers are affected by it, just tested IE 9.0 here.',129045,'2012-07-07 04:17:19'),(43909,5639,88669,'2012-07-07 04:16:48','For me, they both sit too close to each other. Would be nice to add a css:hover, so highlighting what we\'re about to click erases any doubt.\r\n\r\nOk, so seems like using the EMP skin this issue has been addressed. :)',88669,'2012-07-07 04:21:06'),(43910,5639,129045,'2012-07-07 04:21:52','Seems ok for me, they show up with a safe distance here, about 7px distant of each other: Username > Settings > Logout. (Seeing it under Opera, Firefox and IE)\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\nEDIT: The distance is similar or equal between stylesheets, Light simply has a very weak glow when hovering. Just aim for the \"t\" when wanting to sign out :P',129045,'2012-07-07 04:25:50'),(43911,5638,84499,'2012-07-07 04:29:27','\r\n\r\n[mcom]yeah that looks better... done  :gjob: [/mcom]',NULL,NULL),(43912,5640,88669,'2012-07-07 04:30:43','If i type anal on that box, to [b]search for [/b]anal [b]torrents[/b] the url gets like this:\n\n[code]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?searchstr=anal[/code]\n\nBut the results are simply all torrents, not only anal ones.\n\nWhat do works, is using the search box on the search center:\n\n[code]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?setdefault=Make+Default&order_by=time&order_way=desc&searchtext=anal&search_type=1&taglist=&tags_type=1[/code]\n\n[mcom][b]FIXED[/b][/mcom]\n',84499,'2012-07-07 04:42:49'),(43913,5639,88669,'2012-07-07 04:44:26','How it looks:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=7162_4FF7BE87][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=7162_4FF7BE87&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n\r\nMy suggestions:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=8084_4FF7BE87][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=8084_4FF7BE87&jpg[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(43914,5640,129045,'2012-07-07 04:54:23',':hmmm:\r\n\r\nDon\'t know from where you pulled [color=#FF3300]searchstr=[/color], but the default string I get here: [color=#FF3300]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=advanced&groupname=[/color] leads nowhere\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?searchtext=test [color=#009900]OK[/color]\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?filelist=test [color=#009900]OK[/color]\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?taglist=brunette [color=#009900]OK[/color]\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=advanced&groupname=test [color=#FF0000]Not.Ok[/color]',NULL,NULL),(43915,5639,129045,'2012-07-07 05:06:42',':hmmm:\r\n\r\nSeems easily fixable through the stylesheet :)',NULL,NULL),(43917,5640,84499,'2012-07-07 05:10:57','\r\n\r\nwhere do you get the default string http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=advanced&groupname= ??\r\n\r\n\r\nif you type something in the torrent search bar you will now get http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?searchtext=yourtext but until it was fixed it had searchstr instead of the correct field name.',NULL,NULL),(43918,5640,129045,'2012-07-07 05:15:00','Click on first box (\'Torrent\'), type and hit Enter.\r\n\r\nUsing Opera and Firefox, both result in http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=advanced&groupname=test that\'s why I asked where he got \"searchstr=\" as I can\'t get that or any of the correct ones :hmmm:\r\n\r\nEDIT: It\'s not a cache problem from my browsers, just purged everything here and I still