n\r\nFAQ page needs underlined hyper text activated:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=faq\r\n\r\nI\'m using Firefox 13.0.1\r\n\r\nProbably more in the Rules section, might need to check.',NULL,NULL),(43924,5643,47234,'2012-07-07 07:24:24','Yeah i dont think we have started never mind finished a lot of the rules/help section.\r\n\r\nIts most certainly on the TODO list.  Maybe any interested staff could cover this one instead of just Mifune and Lanz ;)  I will hit what i can when i have time',NULL,NULL),(43925,5631,78812,'2012-07-07 09:08:52','thanks for the fixes.. but now I see [b] [/size]-[/b]- [/b] at the end of a couple of lines.. we spoke about this earlier and you told me that my bbcode was a little bit messy.. does this mean I have to fix everything manually ?',78812,'2012-07-07 09:09:34'),(43926,5644,70679,'2012-07-07 12:28:52','I noticed I get logged out after a certain time. This did not happen with the actual site and should not happen with this one or at least be configurable. I did not see it in profile settings.',NULL,NULL),(43927,5645,70679,'2012-07-07 12:37:51','I know this is not up to the site but... the Greasemonkey script \"Empornium Quick Thumbnail Preview 0.2\" is really handy with the actual site... if any script crack could maybe give it a look and have a fix would be nice.\r\n\r\nI tried to contact the author on the actual site few times but.... no response....',NULL,NULL),(43928,5646,70679,'2012-07-07 13:35:25','title says all....',NULL,NULL),(43933,5641,129045,'2012-07-07 17:27:21','Same here. There really seems to have a huge delay, but yesterday it actually updated the value after some hours seeding a single torrent :hmmm:\r\n\r\nThe problem seems to affect credit spending too, I just tested buying a custom title twice, the values were debted and logged perfectly in the profile page, but the top bar does not reflect the change.\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b] Not only credits, but the [b][i]Down[/i][/b] values also didn\'t get updated after I used a -1Gb bonus. So all values are probably affected by this. (Ratio is confirmed, as it didn\'t change to the infinity symbol)\r\n\r\n[i][b]EDIT2:[/b][/i] Downloaded amount and Ratio got updated here, credit values are still stuck.',129045,'2012-07-07 17:51:29'),(43934,5635,1507,'2012-07-07 17:46:29',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]A half day DS slot for half the price sounds pretty cool....  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nWe will discuss the prices and I\'m sure that no matter what is decided, someone will not like the final decision....\r\n\r\nBut, we are open to suggestions so keep them cumming...  :smile1:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:smile1:',NULL,NULL),(43935,5647,129045,'2012-07-07 17:49:25','On top of this behavior http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2641, the values are not really debted from the user.\r\n\r\n1 - As of now you can buy all the available bonuses as many times as you want (icons and I guess plaques too, are one time only. Self -1, -5 and -10Gb are available as long as your DL amount is higher than 0.00)\r\n2 - Your profile will start listing [i]negative values for credits[/i]. Currently -445,664.50 :D\r\n3 - Custom title [b]does not[/b] appears besides the username on posts, but it shows correctly on the profile page (maybe I made it too long?)\r\n\r\nAs for their effects, they seem to be working as intended. Icons shows up in the profile page and under the user avatar, slots are made available and the Downloaded amount is knocked out accordindgly while displaying a clear warning of the actual values it\'ll remove.\r\n\r\nI just need confirmation from other users to see if they received the Credit gifts I sent.\r\n\r\n[i][b]EDIT:[/b][/i] Seems to be working correctly now.\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT2:[/i][/b] Yep [b]Mifune[/b], working as intended. Credits are removed accordingly and items become unavailable as soon as you drop below the required value.  :gjob: \r\n\r\n[mcom][b]confirmed bug[/b] - the cached user values are not clearing after actions in the bonus shop changes them, current credits is tested against the cached value so this leads to the observed behaviour\r\n[b]FIXED[/b] stupid spelling mistake + missed one of the cache value[/mcom]',129045,'2012-07-08 16:24:25'),(43936,5643,1507,'2012-07-07 17:51:39','[quote=slobray]Avatar page \"Click Here\" needs hyperlink:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=avatar\r\n\r\nFAQ page needs underlined hyper text activated:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=faq\r\n\r\nI\'m using Firefox 13.0.1\r\n\r\nProbably more in the Rules section, might need to check.[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=slobray]Avatar page \"Click Here\" needs hyperlink:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=avatar\r\n\r\nFAQ page needs underlined hyper text activated:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=faq\r\n\r\nI\'m using Firefox 13.0.1\r\n\r\nProbably more in the Rules section, might need to check.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]Yeah, we still need to import those tutorials over here and then we can link them.....  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(43937,5647,1507,'2012-07-07 18:06:09','[quote=yamchan07bb]On top of this behavior http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2641, the values are not really debted from the user.\r\n\r\n1 - As of now you can buy all the available bonuses as many times as you want (icons and I guess plaques too, are one time only. Self -1, -5 and -10Gb are available as long as your DL amount is higher than 0.00)\r\n2 - Your profile will start listing [i]negative values for credits[/i]. Currently -445,664.50 :D\r\n3 - Custom title [b]does not[/b] appears besides the username on posts, but it shows correctly on the profile page (maybe I made it too long?)\r\n\r\nAs for their effects, they seem to be working as intended. Icons shows up in the profile page and under the user avatar, slots are made available and the Downloaded amount is knocked out accordindgly while displaying a clear warning of the actual values it\'ll remove.\r\n\r\n[color=magenta]I just need confirmation from other users to see if they received the Credit gifts I sent.[/color][/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]Unfortunately, no one will know if they got your gift if the system doesn\'t send a notification.....  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nLuckily, I stumbled on this and checked your account and saw that you gifted me, but I received no notification....  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nand you ran a deficit in bonus credits....  :laugh:\r\n\r\n[quote]Credits: -445,664.25[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nGood find...  :smile1:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]',1507,'2012-07-07 18:06:37'),(43938,5647,129045,'2012-07-07 18:07:22','Now I\'m royally screwed :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(43939,5648,67255,'2012-07-07 18:10:05','The page url: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35140\r\nWhat is wrong: It should have been made freeleech automatically when I uploaded it yesterday to the new tracker\r\n    ',NULL,NULL),(43940,5647,1507,'2012-07-07 18:10:47','[quote=yamchan07bb]Now I\'m royally screwed :laugh:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n:laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]I would fix your credits now, but I think it\'s best to wait for the guys to pop in, see this, and check it for the bug(s) before your credits get reset...  :smile1:\r\n\r\nGood find tho\'...  :thumbsup:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:smile1:',NULL,NULL),(43941,5631,84499,'2012-07-07 18:20:59','[quote=yamchan07bb]And mang, those new bbcodes are pretty awesome. I was breaking my head before, trying to place images with text right above them while keeping them centered in the description area, now it seems pretty simple using the new codes :D\n\nEDIT: Eh... nevermind. Spoke too soon, this seems even more complicated to handle... is it possible to set two [bg] elements side by side?\nWith a result similar to what I did here: http://torrents.empornium.me/details.php?id=24481 , otherwise I\'ll need to resort to - or _ instead of spaces to compensate the distances and then hide them using color codes...\n\nEDIT2