like the other system capping things at [color=#3333FF]140days[/color]\\[color=#3333FF]3360cr[/color]).\n\nRunning a max of 60 torrents 24\\7, really seems a bit too hard to achieve on a regular basis :hmmm:\n\n\nEMP.me made me spoiled  :tongue: ',129045,'2012-07-07 19:42:13'),(43945,5635,88669,'2012-07-07 20:12:20','Not so hard... you can download, or even upload a lot of small torrents:\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?order_way=asc&order_by=size&\r\n\r\nEven larger torrents like 1.2 GB video perday, is normal.',NULL,NULL),(43946,5635,87179,'2012-07-07 20:33:21','It seems that 8000c for 10 gb is too much.....more than double of today....! An opinion!',NULL,NULL),(43947,5635,129045,'2012-07-07 20:35:32','[i]It is hard[/i]. You\'re limited to 60 torrents and you need to keep them running [i]24 hours nonstop[/i] in order to reach the top 10080cr, a little less to buy a -10Gb bonus (8000cr).\r\n\r\nYou can\'t run 100 torrents, since the system in place will not count the extra 40, so you don\'t have an edge.\r\n\r\nFor comparison, it would be like having to run 20 torrents for 24 hours, during 7 days to achieve 3360 credits on the other EMP. But since the system is more lenient there, I can run 68 torrents simultaneously and achieve the same seeding time in a much shorter time (e.g. I can seed a higher number of torrents for 10 hours per day or less, rather than keep the computer running nonstop, limited to only [color=#FF6600][i]xx[/i][/color] torrents).',NULL,NULL),(43948,5649,129045,'2012-07-07 20:41:21','Since this new tracker supports a custom external stylesheet, I\'ll be using DropBox.com to host the files and see how can we change its looks.\r\n\r\nPlease, post here your opinions and suggestions. This is mostly for fun, since I don\'t really have any experience on this :P\r\n\r\n[s]Will start tomorrow.[/s]\r\n\r\n\r\n[s][b]Please, could the Staff correct the thread title? Since I goofed, please Remove [i]\" - An EMP taulored\"[/i] or update it to [i]\" - An EMP tailored for you\"[/i].[/b][/s] [b][i][color=#FF6600]Thank you![/color][/i][/b]\r\n\r\nOk, this is just a copy of the standard EMP stylesheet, only changed the font (no more Verdana), removed the gradients, changed a little the stats \\ links at the top right corner (font spacing) and added some icons.\r\n\r\nPlease try:\r\n\r\n[url=http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/EMPstyle.css]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/EMPstyle.css[/url]\r\n\r\nand if you use Opera:\r\n\r\n[url=http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/EMPstyleOP.css]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/EMPstyleOP.css[/url] (this will reduce the spacing between items in the menu that appears when you hover your username)\r\n\r\n[img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/emplogo.png[/img]\r\n[img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/upload.png[/img] [img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/donate.png[/img] [img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/settings.png[/img] [img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/logout.png[/img]\r\n[bg=#000000,120px,left][img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/uploadw.png[/img] [img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/donatew.png[/img] [img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/settingsw.png[/img] [img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/logoutw.png[/img][/bg]\r\n[bg=#DDDDDD,26px,left][img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/mglass10op.png[/img][/bg]\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/aacAIh7H.png[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]Good new is that the feature works flawlessly. No bugs here as far as I can see.[/b]',129045,'2012-07-27 00:51:47'),(43949,5647,84499,'2012-07-08 01:06:48','[quote=yamchan07bb]Now I\'m royally screwed :laugh:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nI gave you some credits to play with, and removed your badges so you can buy them again and check it works properly :D',NULL,NULL),(43950,5641,84499,'2012-07-08 01:11:59','[quote=Clownius]Just thought id see if this was a bug or an update period issue\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=0D1E_4FF7C5A5][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=0D1E_4FF7C5A5&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nWhen i go to my account  details i see this\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=A1A0_4FF7C5A5][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=A1A0_4FF7C5A5&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nThe bit at the top doesnt seem to update that i have noticed.  But i havn\'t been looking all that hard to be honest[/quote]\r\n\r\nwhere did those +365 points come from? ',NULL,NULL),(43951,5645,84499,'2012-07-08 01:48:03','\r\n\r\niirc greasemonkey is a wrapper for javascript based scripts :hmmm:\r\n\r\ncan you post the code here?\r\n\r\nI doubt lanz or I will be doing anything with it anytime soon but maybe someone else could help?\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(43952,5641,1243,'2012-07-08 01:53:17',' :hmmm: \n\nEarned credits is updated every hour now. Moderated credits and bonus shop updates correctly.',1243,'2012-07-08 02:58:29'),(43953,5634,1243,'2012-07-08 03:04:44','We will need Alex\'s input on how we should handle the donations.',NULL,NULL),(43954,5645,70679,'2012-07-08 12:57:18','here is the link to it:\n\n[url=http://userscripts.org/scripts/show/124820]Empornium Script Link[/url]\n\nclick on the source code tab for the code list.\n\n\n\n',70679,'2012-07-15 21:36:40'),(43956,5650,47234,'2012-07-08 13:19:29','First i got a 404 and now it redirects to the browse page....\r\n\r\nIs it supposed to do something else.  I was expecting a log of changes to the torrent by the name',NULL,NULL),(43957,5651,104290,'2012-07-08 16:29:04','Not sure if this is simply a facet of all content from the current site getting moved over to the new site, but my inbox is not up-to-date.  My most recent messages viewable are from over a week ago, so messages sent to me over the past week are not showing up.',NULL,NULL),(43958,5651,129045,'2012-07-08 16:40:34','[quote=ButterGroove]Not sure if this is simply a facet of all content from the current site getting moved over to the new site ... [/quote]\r\nIndeed it is.\r\n\r\nI wouldn\'t worry (too much), most likely, data will be 1:1 when they do the definitive move to the new tracker.',129045,'2012-07-08 16:44:29'),(43959,5635,88669,'2012-07-08 17:28:18','I currently seed almost 20/7 (thats it I close utorrent to play online game), about 13 torrents uploaded my self.\r\nWhat I think should be takken into account is the number of seeds, this is: the less seeds on a torrent, more credits you get.\r\nSo if you\'r the only on seeding, you would get maybe 5% more credits or so.',NULL,NULL),(43960,5635,1243,'2012-07-08 20:43:03','We could set the prices to what they where, limit the credit system to max 30 torrents. That would make things slightly more generous and a balance between the old and the new.\n\nLimiting the torrent numbers further is probably the right thing to do and lower the prices to the previous level or close to the previous levels.\n\nI don\'t think we will make it free to start a huge number of torrents like you can do on the current site and then stop seeding after a day and still get max credits though.\n\nThat goes against the core idea of the credit system and some people are taking advantage of it.\n\nStill, this is just a suggestion and all input are more than welcomed. :gjob:',1243,'2012-07-08 20:43:39'),(43961,5651,1243,'2012-07-08 20:51:29','Yes the data was imported to this tracker about a week ago so that looks right to me.',NULL,NULL),(43962,5635,47234,'2012-07-09 03:37:44','I like that idea Lanz.  Should help make people happier.\r\n\r\nAs the credit system has changed the max torrents seeded for a shorter period thing wont work as it stands.\r\n\r\nPeople should be even happier as the points are handed out more often rather than at the end of the week',NULL,NULL),(43963,5635,67255,'2012-07-09 05:24:01','One question calculating the points given more frequently won\'t stress the server too much?\r\n\r\nI said it, due to the tags cloud before, that had to be scrapped due to the intensity of the continuous calculation',NULL,NULL),(43964,5635,129045,'2012-07-09 13:36:06','[i]Jeez, can\'t even exploit the system anymore :([/i]\r\n\r\nI\'m fine with that, didn\'t try to look from that angle before... but rewarding people that actually seed full time is the logical thing to do.',NULL,NULL),(43965,5635,1243,'2012-07-09 15:04:43','[quote=elkid]One question calculating the points given more frequently won\'t stress the server too much?\r\n\r\nI said it, due to the tags cloud before, that had to be scrapped due to the intensity of the continuous calculation[/quote]\r\n\r\nNo, the current system is actually a lot more easy on the server than the old system and one of the reasons we changed it.',NULL,NULL),(43966,5635,103720,'2012-07-09 17:46:46','Having a max of 60 torrents is ok, i guess, but there were people that seeded a whole lot more than 60. as in, more than 300 or so. Seedbox users keep alive a lot of torrents, and limiting them to 60 will result in some dying out, or having less down speed....\r\n\r\nNot having a week cap is better. I admit to stopping my emp torrents, once i had reached the max, to ease utorrent with other torrents i seeded, or when uploading something.\r\nNow, we\'ll get what we seed, so the more we seed the more we get. \r\nI think the only thing needing some tuning is the prices in the bonus shop.\r\nA lot of users won\'t be able to seed 24/7. I won\'t, for one. \r\n10GB is 8000 credits, and seeding max torrents 24/7 gives 10000. My idea is to make 10GB cost 5000 credits. So people who seed 12/7 can still get 10GB worth of credits.\r\n\r\nBut I \'m happy there is a bonus system, no matter what the prices are.\r\nA tracker I was in, nuked the upload amount bought with karma points. 90% of its members got demoted, not to mention the TBs some are in debt (I had only downloaded 167MB of books, so no debt for me. pheeewww). They nuked it because, despite seeding 24/7 for a month gave out about 2TB worth of points, some users kept complaining about the system \"cheating\" them out of upload/points. Now, the points amassed enable members to download simultaneously more torrents than their respective user class. But no bonus upload. Only what has been actually seeded.\r\n\r\nSo, I guess I don\'t have a real problem with it here. It\'s a bonus, we should treat it as such. Whatever is given, is welcome.\r\nMy suggestion is to wait until the new tracker goes live, and see what other members say.',NULL,NULL),(43967,5635,84499,'2012-07-09 21:05:15','\r\n\r\n[quote=Lanz]We could set the prices to what they where, limit the credit system to max 30 torrents. That would make things slightly more generous and a balance between the old and the new.\r\n\r\nLimiting the torrent numbers further is probably the right thing to do and lower the prices to the previous level or close to the previous levels.\r\n\r\nI don\'t think we will make it free to start a huge number of torrents like you can do on the current site and then stop seeding after a day and still get max credits though.\r\n\r\nThat goes against the core idea of the credit system and some people are taking advantage of it.\r\n\r\nStill, this is just a suggestion and all input are more than welcomed. :gjob:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI like the max being 40 or above, that means you can seed 12/7 - which is probably more realistic for a lot of users - and still get 3360+ a week. \r\n\r\nFor prices... how about:\r\n\r\n[table=300px,left]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -1 GB  [/td][td] 500 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -5 GB [/td][td] 2000 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -10 GB [/td][td] 4000 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -1 GB to other [/td][td] 600 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -5 GB to other [/td][td] 2200 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -10 GB to other [/td][td] 4200 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[/table]\r\n\r\n\r\nI dont have a problem with lowering the prices and keeping it at 60 max myself, some people will get richer quicker than the old system but then we have always had the issue that the people with the most credits need them for buying down their gb the least. At least now there is bling for them to spend their credit hoards on  :pimp: \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=eimaimpala]Having a max of 60 torrents is ok, i guess, but there were people that seeded a whole lot more than 60. as in, more than 300 or so. Seedbox users keep alive a lot of torrents, and limiting them to 60 will result in some dying out, or having less down speed....\r\n\r\n...\r\n\r\nSo, I guess I don\'t have a real problem with it here. It\'s a bonus, we should treat it as such. Whatever is given, is welcome.\r\nMy suggestion is to wait until the new tracker goes live, and see what other members say.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nSeedbox owners who keep alive a lot of torrents dont do it for the credits imo, if that were the case then logically they would only seed 20 at a time as that would be enough to max out their bonus on emp.me. \r\n\r\nWe can fine tune the system after we are live but once a system is being used it gains inertia... I am trying to say we should get it as right as possible before we go live as things tend not to change once users are used to them.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(43968,5635,103720,'2012-07-09 21:57:10','yeah, seedbox users don\'t do it for the credits, as they don\'t need them.\r\nI mentioned them because with no limit to how many torrents we can seed, they seed (and keep alive) a lot.\r\nNow they\'ll be restricted to 60.\r\nbut that\'s a good number too....',NULL,NULL),(43969,5635,84499,'2012-07-09 22:39:44','\r\n\r\nthey are not restricted to 60, they can seed as many as they want, it will just only count 60 towards their bonus.',NULL,NULL),(43970,5652,129045,'2012-07-09 22:55:26','Even at lower resolutions (1024x768 or 800x600) thing will show up ok on Windows, the top search boxes will appear a little wider than the [b]Home\\Torrent\\Collages...[/b] menu (30px or so), so if the resolution is lower or the window is resized to accommodate only the site \'body\' (e.g. the forum and torrents descriptions, just before the horizontal scrollbar kicks in), the search boxes will end \'invading\' the stats area, no big deal as it doesn\'t seem to overlap anything.\n\nBut in Ubuntu the top search boxes are rendered differently for some reason (way wider), under the same conditions above, the boxes will overlap the logo and part of the stats, Firefox:\n\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=7CC8_4FFB3C32][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=7CC8_4FFB3C32&jpg[/img][/url]\n\nOpera (to a lesser extent) will present the same behavior, the boxes will reach the \"U\" in the logo and cover part of \"Slots\" on the stats side. Both browsers are running with default settings under Ubuntu.\n\n\nI know it\'s early to be whining about those minor things... but better be safe than sorry :P',129045,'2012-07-09 23:10:30'),(43971,5652,84499,'2012-07-10 00:02:50','\r\n\r\nI changed the width of the search boxes to scale with the page, I think that works :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(43972,5652,129045,'2012-07-10 00:30:27','Just tested here, looking fine (tested on IE 9.0, Firefox 13, Opera 12 and Chrome 20.0.1132.47m) :gjob: ',129045,'2012-07-10 00:35:18'),(43973,5635,1243,'2012-07-10 00:48:00','another option I\'ve been experimenting with is to use a diminishing return formula:\r\n\r\nFirst value here is the number of torrents you seed, second the number of credits you would earn per hour.\r\n1 - 2\r\n2 - 3\r\n3 - 5\r\n4 - 6\r\n5 - 7\r\n6 - 8\r\n7 - 9\r\n8 - 10\r\n9 - 11\r\n10 - 12\r\n11 - 13\r\n12 - 14\r\n13 - 15\r\n14 - 16\r\n15 - 16\r\n16 - 17\r\n17 - 18\r\n18 - 19\r\n19 - 19\r\n20 - 20\r\n.\r\n.\r\n30 - 26\r\n40 - 31\r\n50 - 36\r\n100 - 54\r\n150 - 68\r\n200 - 80\r\n300 - 100\r\n400 - 117\r\n500 - 132\r\n\r\nThe formula is scaled to 20 in this example but can be set to any value.\r\nThe sql I\'ve set up seems to be relatively quick for this, still just one query but needs more speed testing.',NULL,NULL),(43974,5653,6203,'2012-07-10 01:05:09','the link leads me to a blank page instead to the wiki article.',NULL,NULL),(43975,5654,6203,'2012-07-10 01:24:03','in some cases a vote of a tag is double counted. e.g. i vote for a tag that has already 9, the counter doubled my vote to 11. is that a bug?',NULL,NULL),(43976,5655,6203,'2012-07-10 01:29:21','i can add big.breasts or big.boobs although already big.tits was listed. do i misunderstood something of the functioning of the synomyn replacer?',NULL,NULL),(43977,5634,1,'2012-07-10 01:35:23','just like on current site, to tell users send me a PM',NULL,NULL),(43978,5656,1,'2012-07-10 01:37:23','I know we currently have a problem with some torrents and some versions of rtorrent,\r\ndo someone have a seedbox to try the new tracker ?',NULL,NULL),(43979,5653,1,'2012-07-10 01:42:33','will be fixed',NULL,NULL),(43980,5628,1,'2012-07-10 01:52:25','1k = 1gb ?',NULL,NULL),(43981,5654,117367,'2012-07-10 02:12:46','I noticed it only doubles your votes when you add.  When you subtract, it removes correctly.  ',NULL,NULL),(43982,5635,84499,'2012-07-10 02:38:50','\r\n\r\n :yes2: \r\n\r\n\r\nI like the method it feels good  :gjob: My only reservation is that because theres no cap it makes the top end more profitable (even with the diminishing returns). If you seed <20 torrents at once you get a bit more credit per torrent but you are still getting no more than 3360 a week, over 20 although you get less per torrent you can potentially earn quite a bit more, ie. if you have a few hundred to seed all week you can make >20k credits... so I\'m not sure where that leaves us with pricing :hmmm: \r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(43983,5654,1243,'2012-07-10 02:46:09','This is correct, it vote up adds two, vote down removes one. It might have been added to give up votes more value than down votes because of politics and bad behavior amongst users. But I\'ll take the risk and set it to count both to be just as valuable.\r\n\r\nSo FIXED(?) :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(43984,5655,84499,'2012-07-10 02:58:24','\r\n\r\nthere are no synomyns in the list of synomyns yet :D\r\n\r\nThe list is here: [url=/torrents.php?action=tag_synomyns]tags and synomyns[/url]',NULL,NULL),(43985,5628,84499,'2012-07-10 03:05:36','\r\n\r\nThe discussion around this has ended up [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2635]in this thread[/url]  :smile1: ',NULL,NULL),(43986,5655,1243,'2012-07-10 03:18:37','...and I just picked the top list that made somewhat sense to get us going with something.',NULL,NULL),(43987,5635,1243,'2012-07-10 04:09:02','Well we can still cap it of course and I did a couple of experiments. We have 14,699 seeding users on the server that have a total of 351,746 seeding torrents so I set up the db with 15,000 users with 360,000 peers (24 torrents each).\n\nHere are the results:\n\n[b]Current count of 60 torrents[/b]\n1.1399 sek\nUPDATE users_main SET Credits = Credits + (\nSELECT IF( COUNT( * ) >60, 60, COUNT( * ) ) * 0.25\nFROM xbt_files_users\nWHERE users_main.ID = xbt_files_users.uid\nAND xbt_files_users.remaining =0\nAND xbt_files_users.active =1\n)\n\n[b]Diminishing return with no cap[/b]\n1.3036 sek\nUPDATE users_main SET Credits = Credits + (\nSELECT ROUND( (\nSQRT( 8.0 * ( COUNT( * ) /20 ) + 1.0 ) - 1.0 ) / 2.0 *20\n) * 0.25\nFROM xbt_files_users\nWHERE users_main.ID = xbt_files_users.uid\nAND xbt_files_users.remaining =0\nAND xbt_files_users.active =1\n)\n\n[b]Diminishing return capped at 60 torrents[/b]\n1.5001 sek\nUPDATE users_main SET Credits = Credits + (\nSELECT ROUND( (\nSQRT( 8.0 * ( IF( COUNT( * ) >60, 60, COUNT( * ) ) /20 ) + 1.0 ) - 1.0 ) / 2.0 *20 ) * 0.25\nFROM xbt_files_users\nWHERE users_main.ID = xbt_files_users.uid\nAND xbt_files_users.remaining =0\nAND xbt_files_users.active =1\n)\n\nAll three are within acceptable time frames for a query that is only executed once every 15 minutes, so the complexity of the query should not be a factor IMO.',1243,'2012-07-10 04:17:03'),(43988,5653,84499,'2012-07-10 04:54:37','\r\n\r\nThe IRC chat is now working and I am not sure we even need an irc tutorial, if we do have one then we will add the link back in until then I\'ve removed it.',NULL,NULL),(43989,5635,47234,'2012-07-10 04:57:56','[quote=mifune]For prices... how about:\r\n\r\n[table=300px,left]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -1 GB  [/td][td] 500 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -5 GB [/td][td] 2000 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -10 GB [/td][td] 4000 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -1 GB to other [/td][td] 600 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -5 GB to other [/td][td] 2200 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -10 GB to other [/td][td] 4200 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[/table][/quote]\r\n\r\nHmm just out of interest why are we sticking with it costs more to bail out others thing?\r\n\r\nI like those numbers but how about make it the same to buy other as buy own?\r\n\r\nEncourages people to be helpful.  Or at least stops punishing those that are for helping others',NULL,NULL),(43990,5656,47234,'2012-07-10 05:01:49','My seedbox is already seeding 45 odd torrents here no problems.  That said im using Deluge or Ktorrent (mix of both as im seeding both trackers and it wasnt playing nice doing the same files in Deluge for both trackers).\r\n\r\nI dont have rTorrent installed though.',NULL,NULL),(43991,5621,84499,'2012-07-10 05:19:36','\r\n\r\ndone  :smile1: ',NULL,NULL),(43992,5651,104290,'2012-07-10 05:29:06','Gotcha, makes sense now.  That\'s why my ratio on here looks like what it did a week ago on the current site.  Thanks for clarifying this guys.',NULL,NULL),(43993,5657,129045,'2012-07-10 16:12:05','[s]I had added a test filter containing a few common tags and waited for a new upload to hit, since it didn\'t, I uploaded something myself. Still, no notification appeared on http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=notify\r\n\r\nTorrent in question: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35141 [i](slightly OT, but why does it show a lonely [color=#FF3300]\'[/color] at the bottom of the \"Torrent Info\"? Did I forget to fill something during the upload? No other torrent seems to have it.)[/i]\r\n\r\nThe tags used in the filter:\r\n[quote]brunette blonde test oral anal blowjob big.boobs big.butt big.ass hardcore handjob straight facial natural.tits small.tits[/quote]\r\n\r\n[i]\"At least one of these tags\"[/i] should\'ve worked, as the upload contained the tag \'blonde\'.\r\n\r\nNow, I understand if this is by design, the filter ignores the user\'s own uploads :hmmm:[/s]\r\n\r\n[b][i][color=#FF0000]EDIT: Nevermind, Rometheus uploaded a torrent and it triggered a notification [/color][/i][/b]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35145\r\n\r\n[s]One other thing, having to click on \'Notifications\' and then on \'View\' can get a bit tiresome, so when users go to the menu and hit \"Notifications\", wouldn\'t be better to send them direct to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=notify rather than http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?action=notify ?\r\n\r\nJust place a warning in the page, saying that the user has no filters set yet. \'Inconvenience\' for them, but it\'s better to people who actually want to see their notifications.[/s]\r\n\r\n[b][i][color=#FF6600]EDIT2: Clarified and moved to its own thread, under Suggestions:[/color][/i][/b] http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2678',129045,'2012-07-14 18:33:01'),(43994,5658,129045,'2012-07-10 16:40:40','Clicking on [b]Slots[/b] at the top bar sends the user to the Bonus page, rather than this page http://empornium.mooo.com/userhistory.php?action=token_history or http://empornium.mooo.com/userhistory.php?action=token_history[color=#FF6600]&userid=XXXXXX[/color]\n\n\nThat link can only be reached by using the \"Slots\" link in the profile\'s stats area. It lists the torrents and their activation time correctly, but it doesn\'t list an expiration date or what type of slots are being used.\n\n\n[b]When using the slots[/b], the button text will be \'grayed out\', but the button will still [i]work[/i].\nIf the user clicks again and confirms the warning, another slot will be used. He can do this as long as he has slots available. Can\'t say if the effects are cumulative as [i]no expiration date[/i] is informed.\n\n[mcom][b]confirmed bug[/b] - CACHE ISSUE: slots are not correctly checking if they are already in use, affects interface (slots in use not showing) and users can consume slots on a torrent when they already have one for that torrent. - All is well once the cache updates\nAlso: expiration date?[/mcom]\n',84499,'2012-07-10 18:21:00'),(43995,5635,103720,'2012-07-10 17:16:55','[quote=mifune]they are not restricted to 60, they can seed as many as they want, it will just only count 60 towards their bonus.[/quote]\r\n\r\noh, :slap:  then all is good.  :happy2: ',NULL,NULL),(43996,5658,84499,'2012-07-10 17:33:37','\r\n\r\nhaha, you know I can remember when I added the slots info to the user stats, as I was copy pasting the link I thought \"must remember to change the slots link to something more apt\" :lol:\r\n\r\n\r\nre: the rest yeah there is something funky going on with slots, we need to take a look at it.\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=yamchan07bb]\r\n[b]When using the slots[/b], the button text will be \'grayed out\', but the button will still [i]work[/i].\r\nIf the user clicks again and confirms the warning, another slot will be used. He can do this as long as he has slots available. Can\'t say if the effects are cumulative as [i]no expiration date[/i] is informed.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nI cannot find any greyed out buttons? What page is this on? \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(43997,5635,84499,'2012-07-10 17:54:38','[quote=Clownius][quote=mifune]For prices... how about:\r\n\r\n[table=300px,left]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -1 GB  [/td][td] 500 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -5 GB [/td][td] 2000 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -10 GB [/td][td] 4000 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -1 GB to other [/td][td] 600 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -5 GB to other [/td][td] 2200 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[tr]\r\n[td] -10 GB to other [/td][td] 4200 credits [/td]\r\n[/tr]\r\n[/table][/quote]\r\n\r\nHmm just out of interest why are we sticking with it costs more to bail out others thing?\r\n\r\nI like those numbers but how about make it the same to buy other as buy own?\r\n\r\nEncourages people to be helpful.  Or at least stops punishing those that are for helping others[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nI dunno, I cant think of a really good reason. I feel like there ought to be some cost to tranferring credits to prevent \'gaming\', except there is nothing really to game, we dont plan on giving out badges for simply having credits or anything so... I dunno I still want there be some cost I just cant justify why  :demon: ',NULL,NULL),(43998,5658,129045,'2012-07-10 17:55:09','Buy some slots and go to [b][i]any[/i][/b] torrent page to download.\r\n\r\nThe torrent page will present 3 buttons, [color=#0099FF]blue[/color] for normal download, [color=#00CC00]green[/color] for freeleech and [color=#FF9900]orange[/color] for doubleseed.\r\n\r\nThe text in the buttons is white by default, once you click and activate one of the effects (freeleech or doubleseed), the text will turn [color=grey]grey[/color].\r\n\r\nOn EMP.me, once you activated a slot, the button would disappear and the area would display the information related to that slot (freeleeching or the expiration date of the doubleseed effect).\r\n\r\nWhat I\'m refering to is that now the white text simply turns [color=grey]grey[/color], the button remains in place and the user can still click on it to activate the same effect (e.g. use 5 slots to activate Doubleseed on the same torrent), problem is, [b]the effect isn\'t clear[/b]. There\'s no information about expiration dates or anything, it could be cumulative ([b]effect x 5[/b]) or not ([b]the user ends wasting slots[/b]).\r\n\r\nAlso, the only visual information the user has about the active slots, is that the button text turns grey.',129045,'2012-07-10 18:01:25'),(43999,5658,84499,'2012-07-10 17:58:44','\r\n\r\noh that is a css bug I think, its just the visited link color changing (which is inappropriate).\r\n\r\nYou can only use one FL and one DS slot at once on a torrent, the buttons shouldnt appear if you already have a slot of that type in use. It needs fixing :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(44000,5658,129045,'2012-07-10 18:06:47','[color=#FF3300]Sorry, no, scratch that. The text was turning grey because I set it in the external CSS file.[/color]\r\n\r\nThe current css (the Empornium stylesheet) doesn\'t contain any code to change the text color. So the text color remains white, but the problem is the same.\r\n\r\nEDIT: Or was, just F5\'d here and the buttons are now gone.\r\n\r\nEDIT2: I\'m slow, yeah, now only a notification informing the expiration date\\effect is needed :gjob:',129045,'2012-07-10 18:09:15'),(44001,5650,129045,'2012-07-10 18:18:21','Should it send the user to this page? Or something similar? http://empornium.mooo.com/log.php\r\n\r\n\"[b]View History[/b]\" will lead to an Error 404 page.',NULL,NULL),(44002,5658,84499,'2012-07-10 18:19:42','\nlol well I assumed the visitor link css must have been in the emp style sheet, glad to hear its on your end.\n\nAha yeah I see, its (surprise surprise) another cache issue. When a slot is used its not updating/clearing the cache, once the cache does update then the slot in use is detected and it behaves properly.',84499,'2012-07-23 06:39:10'),(44003,5635,48010,'2012-07-10 20:15:06','So to help costs you - that\'s not the way to go\r\n\r\nI did it before and thought \"I give you credits for 10GB and it costs me more - if you pay me back it costs you too\" Not the best way to do it IMHO',NULL,NULL),(44004,5659,70679,'2012-07-10 22:05:03','If you set a filter and do a make default then you take out the check mark and do a browser refresh or click on torrents the filter is not reset/removed.\r\n\r\nAlso on the actual site clicking browse removes the filter so I think it should be the same here.',NULL,NULL),(44005,5660,70679,'2012-07-10 23:27:54','[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=8EFF_4FFC9EB7[/img]\n\n\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=FDCC_4FFC9BFE[/img]\n\n :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: \n\nsorry could not resist... \n\n :devil:  :devil:  :devil: ',70679,'2012-07-10 23:31:02'),(44006,5659,129045,'2012-07-11 00:27:56',':hmmm:\r\n\r\nIsn\'t that the whole purpose of \"[b]Make Default[/b]\"? It makes your selections sticky. \"[b]Clear Default[/b]\" will revert your selections to nothing and \"[b]Reset[/b]\" will clear the whole selection, but will not override \"[b]Make Default[/b]\". ([i]this is using \"Advanced Search\"[/i])\r\n\r\n\r\n[s][i][b][color=#FF0000]Now the problems I\'m experiencing here:[/color][/b][/i]\r\n\r\n- On [b][i]Basic Search[/i][/b], after you select the categories and use \"[b]Make Default[/b]\", \"Reset\" will not work (it will not clear the search boxes or the selected categories)\r\n\r\n- After using \"[b]Make Default[/b]\" on \"[b]Basic Search[/b]\", if you change your Settings to use \"[b]Advanced[/b]\" search as default, it\'ll be borked too. (same behavior as Basic Search, Reset will not work)\r\n\r\n- Using \"[b]Make Default[/b]\" on \"[b]Advanced Search[/b]\" [b]will override your Settings[/b], so if you change it later to use \"Simple\" search as default, it\'ll not work, you\'ll be stuck with Advanced Search until you use \"Clear Default\".\r\n\r\n\r\n- [b]Both[/b] types of search present this problem: [b]sticky search terms[/b]. Anything you search will activate \"Make Default\" somehow. So everytime you return to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php, it\'ll have the torrents filtered by the last keywords you used. You need to use \"[b]Clear Default[/b]\" to reset things back to normal.[/s]\r\n\r\n[color=#FF6600][i][b]Sorry, clarified and carried to its own thread:[/b][/i][/color] http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2666',129045,'2012-07-12 22:20:19'),(44007,5660,1243,'2012-07-11 03:10:05','Damn, I misspelled that one :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(44008,5649,88669,'2012-07-11 05:39:41','I would suggest, that for after launch, or before, EMP could do a competition!\r\nSo users would would send their custom CSS, and the top 5 would  be on the dropdown menu.\r\nUsers can still use their own, or the defaul.\r\nOf course, winners could get some prize :)',NULL,NULL),(44009,5661,88669,'2012-07-11 05:46:02','I mean, some tutorials and rules could be translated to other languages, this would gather more users and thus make sure everyone understands the rules! I sure some users might have shit because they had poor English.\r\n\r\nAlso, explaining in a precise way what exactly fits in to each of the \"torrents Types\": megapack, softcore, etc.\r\nOk this seems to obvious for most of us I believe, but I found many friends are unsure about BBW or big boos, and so on.\r\nAgain the users with poor english have a very hard time understanding when it\'s a megapack or siterip...\r\n\r\nThis said, I offer my help to crate this guide, and also translate it to portugueseBR',NULL,NULL),(44010,5649,1507,'2012-07-11 06:52:19',' :gjob: \r\n\r\n[b]That\'s kind of cool yam...  nice job....   :smile1: \r\n\r\nNow, how do you make the background pink (magenta) instead of that grayish/white....???   :hmmm: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :tongue: ',NULL,NULL),(44011,5660,1507,'2012-07-11 06:56:12',' :laugh: \r\n\r\n[b]I changed the category to \"Praysite\" back on Emp.me some time back...\r\n\r\nI thought we were going to do away with that category altogether...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44012,5660,1243,'2012-07-11 08:34:33',':dunno:\n\nwtf! 3 million smiles on the tracker and no :dunno:  :no: ',1243,'2012-07-11 08:36:32'),(44015,5660,84499,'2012-07-11 11:50:55','\r\n\r\n[quote=Lanz]:dunno:\r\n\r\nwtf! 3 million smiles on the tracker and no :dunno:  :no:[/quote]\r\n\r\n[img]http://www.emporniumforums.com/images/smilies/icon_dunno.gif[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:lol: okay thats weird, I blame usb for not including it in the smiley thread  :mad: ',NULL,NULL),(44017,5649,47234,'2012-07-11 13:35:05','[quote=usillyboy]:gjob: \r\n\r\n[b]That\'s kind of cool yam...  nice job....   :smile1: \r\n\r\nNow, how do you make the background pink (magenta) instead of that grayish/white....???   :hmmm: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :tongue:[/quote]\r\n\r\nJust no usb no',NULL,NULL),(44018,5662,47234,'2012-07-11 13:38:07','Just noticed when quoting anything on the forums i get 2 blanks lines above the quote included for no reason i can think of.\r\n\r\nIs there a reason behind this or just a bug?\r\n\r\nAnnoying having to go delete them constantly',NULL,NULL),(44019,5662,84499,'2012-07-11 14:48:14','\r\n\r\nyes i deliberatly added them so if you quote something into a post that already has some text it seperates them, but I think your right its annoying, I\'ll remove them.',NULL,NULL),(44020,5649,84499,'2012-07-11 14:48:57','\r\n\r\nyeah anyone who tells usb how to do that gets a ban from me :lol:',NULL,NULL),(44021,5662,47234,'2012-07-11 15:57:08','Maybe make it one line instead?',NULL,NULL),(44022,5650,84499,'2012-07-11 16:16:43','\r\n\r\nOkay I connected the grouplog page which was a little neglected for some reason. It is a bit unnessecary for the system to be logging stuff in 2 places but as its already doing this we may as well actually present the data somewhere!\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44023,5662,84499,'2012-07-11 16:57:50','\r\nIn fact I will try and be clever and have it detect if there is any text already there, and if there is add one in front and one at the end, lets see how that feels.',NULL,NULL),(44024,5662,47234,'2012-07-11 17:12:08','Wow that would be nice but i wouldnt have a clue how you do that sort of thing',NULL,NULL),(44025,5649,48010,'2012-07-11 20:24:57','\r\n\r\n[quote=mifune]yeah anyone who tells usb how to do that gets a ban from me :lol:[/quote]\r\n\r\ncome on it\'s his trademark :grin:',NULL,NULL),(44026,5662,84499,'2012-07-11 20:37:14','\r\n\r\nIts done, I think thats better?',NULL,NULL),(44027,5649,1507,'2012-07-11 22:24:41',' :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(44028,5660,1507,'2012-07-11 22:29:09','[quote=mifune][quote=Lanz]:dunno:\r\n\r\nwtf! 3 million smiles on the tracker and no :dunno:  :no:[/quote]\r\n\r\n[img]http://www.emporniumforums.com/images/smilies/icon_dunno.gif[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:lol: okay thats weird, I blame usb for not including it in the smiley thread  :mad:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]That\'s one of my fav smilies, and I asked you to include it when we were in chat and you asked which one(s) I wanted to have here...  I guess I forgot to also include it in the thread...  [img]http://www.emporniumforums.com/images/smilies/icon_dunno.gif[/img]\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n[img]http://www.emporniumforums.com/images/smilies/icon_dunno.gif[/img]',NULL,NULL),(44029,5663,48010,'2012-07-11 22:39:50','Are we still going forward with this?\r\n\r\nIf so I will upload and request for some tests on it\r\nDave',NULL,NULL),(44030,5660,70679,'2012-07-11 22:44:04','glad could help fix this extremely important smiley issue....  :laugh:  :clap: \r\n\r\n[IMG]http://i1261.photobucket.com/albums/ii581/barumba1/2B0E42FA47EA78F7.gif[/IMG]',NULL,NULL),(44031,5663,84499,'2012-07-11 23:27:50','\r\nyes absolutely. It should in theory all be working... (there will be bugs)',NULL,NULL),(44032,5660,84499,'2012-07-11 23:49:21','[quote=usillyboy][quote=mifune][quote=Lanz]:dunno:\r\n\r\nwtf! 3 million smiles on the tracker and no :dunno:  :no:[/quote]\r\n\r\n[img]http://www.emporniumforums.com/images/smilies/icon_dunno.gif[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:lol: okay thats weird, I blame usb for not including it in the smiley thread  :mad:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]That\'s one of my fav smilies, and I asked you to include it when we were in chat and you asked which one(s) I wanted to have here...  I guess I forgot to also include it in the thread...  [img]http://www.emporniumforums.com/images/smilies/icon_dunno.gif[/img]\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n[img]http://www.emporniumforums.com/images/smilies/icon_dunno.gif[/img][/quote]\r\n\r\nlol, yeah usb! you didnt remind me for the tenth time, and when I said I was adding all the common ones from the chat you believed me too! It really is your fault.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44033,5662,47234,'2012-07-12 00:19:40','[quote=mifune]Its done, I think thats better?[/quote]\r\n\r\nLooks fine to me now :)',NULL,NULL),(44034,5660,1507,'2012-07-12 00:49:06',' :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: \r\n\r\n[b]yeah, it\'s my fault...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nat least you know now to add it...   :tongue: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :yes2: ',NULL,NULL),(44035,5663,1507,'2012-07-12 00:50:52',' :chase: ',NULL,NULL),(44036,5639,84499,'2012-07-12 01:00:09','\r\n\r\nI changed it to 7px margin; lets see how it looks.',NULL,NULL),(44037,5639,1507,'2012-07-12 03:45:14',':hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(44038,5635,1507,'2012-07-12 03:55:53',':hmmm:\r\n[b]I agree...  don\'t penalize for helping others out...  keep them the same price I think...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(44039,5664,1507,'2012-07-12 04:00:22',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]Is it possible to give the new posts icon a different color than what they are now...???\r\n\r\nI see a white for read/no new posts, and a bluish for unread/new posts in the forums and I can barely make out the color difference...   :sad: \r\n\r\nMaybe make it a darker color like red or something..???  something that stands out a little more, otherwise I have to click on every link as I cannot tell if it is new or not...   :no2: \r\n\r\nThank you...\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(44040,5664,129045,'2012-07-12 05:37:10','Holy shit, so many badges ( ê’ªâŒ“ê’ª)\r\n\r\n\r\nSeems like you need... [i]an EMP tailored for you[/i] ;)\r\n\r\nGo to [b]Settings[/b] and in the [i]\"External CSS\"[/i] box, paste this: http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/usb.css\r\n\r\nThe unread icon will be darker and visited links will show up as... [color=magenta][i]magenta[/i][/color] lol, hard to miss them this time.',129045,'2012-07-12 05:38:38'),(44041,5664,1507,'2012-07-12 06:10:03',':thumbsup:\r\n\r\n[b]Cool beans yamchan07bb...  :thumbsup:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/aaquJLhO.png[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI like the magenta and I can see the darker icons...  :thumbsup:\r\n\r\nThanks for that...  :smile1:\r\n\r\nAs for the medals/badges, I\'m just testing it to see how it messes things up when you have too many of them...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-12 06:10:48'),(44043,5635,70679,'2012-07-12 15:59:40',' :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: \r\n\r\nUSB one more medal or award and we will all go blind from the unbearable shine.... like looking in the sun.\n\nSeriously ... question .... would it be possible when you buy GB for other that the credit goes over zero? So you can give some positive credits to somebody? On the actual site goes only to zero if negative.',70679,'2012-07-12 16:02:15'),(44044,5635,84499,'2012-07-12 19:18:05','[quote=barumba]:laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: \r\n\r\nUSB one more medal or award and we will all go blind from the unbearable shine.... like looking in the sun.\r\n\r\nSeriously ... question .... would it be possible when you buy GB for other that the credit goes over zero? So you can give some positive credits to somebody? On the actual site goes only to zero if negative.[/quote]\r\n\r\nDo you mean for the download to go negative (never going to happen, for many logical and technical reasons) ? Or something else?',NULL,NULL),(44045,5635,70679,'2012-07-12 19:46:42','nope let see.... an user has say 250MB upload and 11GB download and obviously shitty ratio and gets blocked. This on the actual site...\r\n\r\nYou give him a first -10GB and he goes to 1GB download.\r\n\r\nThe you give another -10GB and he goes to zero download and 9GB are lost. Not sure if this a feature or a bug... but would be better\r\n\r\nif the download goes to zero and the rest, in this case 9GB gets applied to the uploaded so that he gets 9.25GB.\r\n\r\nSo when the download goes to zero no does not go to negative - Illogical - would say Mr. Spock.... but the rest is applied, added to the uploaded number. \r\n\r\nSo you can dig somebody that comes and asks nicely in IRC for example out of the shithole with your credits and also prop him a bit.\r\n\r\nHope I was able to explain.... ',NULL,NULL),(44046,5635,84499,'2012-07-12 21:11:48','\r\n\r\nI understand, but I dont think its a good idea - sorry :D\r\n\r\nBecause required ratio is always below 1.0 it makes uploaded more valuable than downloaded in terms of how much you can download before you are limited. So to me its logical that you can only buy down your download. \r\n\r\nAnd with the smaller quantities available to buy you can just give him -1GB instead of the second -10GB. I think thats a better solution.',NULL,NULL),(44048,5666,129045,'2012-07-12 22:18:53','If the user tries to use the Advanced or Simple search on http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php, these are the results:\n\n- On [b][i]Basic Search[/i][/b], after you use \"[b]Make Default[/b]\", \"Reset\" will not work (it will not clear the search boxes or the selected categories)\n\n- \"[b]Make Default[/b]\" [b]will override your [i]Settings[/i][/b]. So if you change it later to use a different search type, no change will occur until you use \"Clear Default\". (This one is probably the expected behavior)\n\n- [b]Both[/b] types of search present this problem: [b]sticky search terms[/b]. Anything you search will activate \"[b]Make Default[/b]\" somehow. So everytime you return to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php, it\'ll have the torrents filtered by the last keywords and categories you used. You need to click on \"[b]Clear Default[/b]\" to reset things back to normal.\n\n[mcom][b]Confirmed Bug:[/b] Sticky search results if as described :[/mcom]\n[quote=yamchan07bb][b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b] [color=#FF0000]Oh shit, the bug only kicks in when the user select categories \\ search for something by typing and pressing [b]Enter[/b]. If he select categories and type something (or not) and then click on \"Filter torrents\", it\'ll not trigger the bug.[/color]\n\n[b][i]EDIT2:[/i][/b]\n\n[color=#0066FF]Well, now I know why it happens, one of those \"[b][i]D\'oh![/i][/b]\" moments. If you click on any of the search boxes, you will see that the focus will be given to the \"Make Default\" button, that\'s why hitting Enter will trigger the \"bug\", test it now:\n\n- Click on any of them (Search term, File list or Tags) and pay attention to the \"Make Default\" button, now click somewhere else on the page and you will see the button losing focus.[/color]\n\n[color=#009900][b][i]So to be clear:[/i][/b] This happens because whenever you click on the search boxes to type something, focus will be given to the \"[b]Make Default[/b]\" button, instinctively hitting [i][b]Enter[/b][/i] will of course, activate the button. Thus triggering the \"bug\"[/color]\n\n[b][i]Possible solution:[/i][/b] [color=#0066FF]Force the focus to the \"Filter Torrents\" button instead.[/color]\n[/quote]\n\nOn the other hand, the search box at the top bar behaves \'[i]normally[/i]\', it\'ll obey your search type choice in [i]Settings[/i] and it\'ll always return results filtered only by the keyword(s) used, ignoring anything previously set by \"[b]Make Default[/b]\".',84499,'2012-07-19 21:47:26'),(44049,5635,70679,'2012-07-12 22:35:39','AH OK I see it .... more granularity OK that makes sense.',NULL,NULL),(44050,5666,47234,'2012-07-13 02:22:19','[quote=yamchan07bb]- [b]Both[/b] types of search present this problem: [b]sticky search terms[/b]. Anything you search will activate \"[b]Make Default[/b]\" somehow. So everytime you return to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php, it\'ll have the torrents filtered by the last keywords and categories you used. You need to click on \"[b]Clear Default[/b]\" to reset things back to normal.\r\n\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, the search box at the top bar behaves \'[i]normally[/i]\', it\'ll obey your search type choice in [i]Settings[/i] and it\'ll always return results filtered only by the keyword(s) used, ignoring anything previously set by \"[b]Make Default[/b]\".[/quote]\r\n\r\nThat bit drove me insane for a while but i forgot how i fixed uit.  Thanks for the follow up yamchan.  Let me add that will drive anyone insane as even with the search centre closed i had the sticky search result when i chose the torrents link',NULL,NULL),(44051,5667,47234,'2012-07-13 16:39:50','Thanks Mifune for setting up the IRC link thingy but i was wondering about our use of EFnet\r\n\r\nSeen quite a few users on IRC who use EFnet IRC already and have established nick\'s on it.  Would it be worth considering an Emp specific IRC server?  Maybe throw it on the Empforums server?\r\n\r\nJust thinking that way everyone can use their emp nicks.\r\n\r\nLet me know what you guys think.  Im unsure as to whats involved to be honest',NULL,NULL),(44052,5656,167879,'2012-07-13 16:47:50','I use rtorrent. I run the current stable 0.9.2/0.13.2 and have access to a box running 0.8.9/0.12.9 if you need me to test something. I will run some stuff and let you know if I have any issues.\n\nEDIT: So far im not getting any errors from the tracker.',167879,'2012-07-13 17:20:20'),(44053,5668,167879,'2012-07-13 17:19:27','Torrents.php shows instantly updates but on the torrent description page the amount of seeders/leechers has not updated as of being on the torrent for 30mins+ \r\n\r\nWhen clicking on the peerlist of the torrent it however does show me leeching.\r\n[img]http://picpit.net/images/oOVvD.png[/img]\r\n\r\nOn the torrents.php it reports fine\r\n[img]http://picpit.net/images/xIX0u.png[/img]\r\n\r\nIm not sure about the cache times set but I would think it would be set under 20 mins. I jumped on 2 torrents and they both are reporting fine on the torrents.php but no under the description\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35142\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35141\r\n\n\nFinally showed me leeching at around the 45min-50min mark. I also completed one of the torrents and it updated to 2 seeders right away. So I guess there is a issue lying in memcached some where?',167879,'2012-07-13 17:44:32'),(44055,5669,48010,'2012-07-13 19:25:36','What is the point in those links in white in the rounded box ? and they don\'t work anyway\n\nThey are mostly just dupes of the bar above except logs and users (which should be moved to tools ?)\n\n\n[mcom][b]Search Bars?[/b] - Search Bars are a little bit mystical\n[b]FIXED?[/b] - hopefully now its more obvious![/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-14 20:08:38'),(44056,5670,48010,'2012-07-13 19:47:34','Hi all testers\r\n\r\nI can\'t seed it all the time as said in description but what I want is the following tested by staff and non staff too\r\n\r\nthe torrent is [url]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35142[/url]\r\n\r\nadd tags (please add something like \"this.is.shit\" and any improvement tag too)\r\n\r\nmake comments especially some abusive ones are welcome to test the staff procedures \r\ndon\'t worry it doesn\'t affect you ! \r\ntype something like \"this torrent is fucking crap\" (you will probably get warned to test that too !) but it\'s part of the process to test warning and reports to staff.\r\n\r\nNote a warning on here means nothing here (does not affect you on the main site emp.me) and you may even get rewarded !\r\n\r\n@mifune and lanz edit this if needed',NULL,NULL),(44057,5669,84499,'2012-07-13 19:49:27','\r\n\r\n:D\r\n\r\nthey are search bars, I did add tooltips saying \"Search X\" but its obviously not obvious enough :hmmm:\r\n\r\nI dunno if there is anything more we can do with the interface (if anyone can think of a way to make it more obvious what those bars do please say!) but perhaps we need to write a \"Whats new\" article for when we switch that can explain stuff like that?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44058,5669,129045,'2012-07-13 19:52:57','[s]... are you talking about the search boxes (Torrents) (Requests) (Forums) (Log) (Users) ?[/s]\r\n\r\nEDIT: Gah, [b]add a magnifying glass icon somewhere or everywhere[/b] :P\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=B8CF_4FF73862][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-B8CF_4FF73862.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=C201_50007076][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=C201_50007076&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nBut yeah, the article\\FAQ thing may be the most sensible solution. Or just make an announcement... \"Welcome blah blah, now you can use the boxes at the top bar to quick search ...\"\r\n\r\n\r\nOne thing I noticed, the tooltip actually pops up real fast on IE, but other browsers seems to take some milliseconds or a full second to actually show the tooltip.',129045,'2012-07-13 21:14:45'),(44059,5656,84499,'2012-07-13 19:54:36','\r\n\r\n\r\nthe bug where torrents made in utorrent 3.1.2 cannot be opened through the rutorrent interface (rtorrent is actually okay with them if it loads them through the watch folder) is fixed in the latest build of rutorrent. Many seedboxes will not be using the latest version so will still need to use the watch folder workaround, but I dont see anything the tracker (we) can do about this issue  :sorry: ',NULL,NULL),(44060,5669,48010,'2012-07-13 20:33:40','ok I see the tool tips but I think it will not be clear to many that it\'s a search (as I miseed it :grin:)',NULL,NULL),(44061,5669,84499,'2012-07-13 23:26:50','\r\nactually we could do this:\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/aasrXm9T.png[/img]',NULL,NULL),(44062,5669,129045,'2012-07-13 23:47:01','That works too  :tongue: \r\n\r\nI was thinking, could the lack of a \"Go\" or \"Search\" button share some responsibility in the confusion? :hmmm:\r\n\r\nThis is just speculation, as I have no idea how many people use their mouses or whatever to click on \"Search\" rather than hitting Enter.',NULL,NULL),(44063,5669,84499,'2012-07-14 00:02:42','or\n\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/aac3aS9Q.png[/img]',84499,'2012-07-14 00:04:18'),(44064,5670,1507,'2012-07-14 02:14:51','[b]I left a couple of cumments, a couple of tags, and am using a DS slot to test...  \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb: :chase:',1507,'2012-07-14 02:15:03'),(44065,5671,1507,'2012-07-14 02:21:42','[b]I may have found a bug...\n\nI clicked around on the Browse page and picked this one at random:\n\n\n[url]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35144[/url]\n\n\nI went into Boshie\'s settings and looked under \"Recent Uploads\" and this one didn\'t appear....\n\n\n[url]http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=138108[/url]\n\n\nI think I\'ve found a bug....   :yaydance: \n\nusb[/b]\n\n:usb:  :chase:\n\n[mcom][b]not a bug[/b] - changed so all recent uploads show...\n[b]TOFO[/b] sort out text/layout issues[/mcom]\n\n\n',84499,'2012-07-29 01:13:08'),(44066,5671,1507,'2012-07-14 02:26:19','[b]Same with Dave:\r\n\r\n\r\n[url]http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=48010[/url]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nBut not with Rometheus:\r\n\r\n\r\n[url]http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=118746[/url]\r\n\r\n\r\nwho happens to have one that shows...  \r\n\r\nas does yamchan07bb:\r\n\r\n\r\n[url]http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=129045[/url]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',1507,'2012-07-14 02:32:24'),(44067,5669,1507,'2012-07-14 02:37:35','\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/aac3aS9Q.png[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n:thumbsup:\r\n\r\n[b]I like that....  :smile1:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',1507,'2012-07-14 02:38:12'),(44068,5669,1507,'2012-07-14 02:40:44','[quote=yamchan07bb]... One thing I noticed, the tooltip actually pops up real fast on IE, but other browsers seems to take some milliseconds or a full second to actually show the tooltip.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]What \"tooltip\"....???  I don\'t see anything that says that...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',1507,'2012-07-14 02:41:13'),(44069,5669,1507,'2012-07-14 02:42:11','[b]why did it just strike out my quote of yam...???  I corrected it but it struck it out for some reason...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44070,5669,129045,'2012-07-14 02:53:57','Place your mouse cursor over any of the search boxes and wait a second. Under the cursor, a tooltip will appear saying \"Search _______\"',129045,'2012-07-14 02:54:22'),(44071,5671,129045,'2012-07-14 02:59:57','Really seems random :hmmm:\r\n\r\nQuick look at them and I thought that maybe the lack of seeding could be triggering the problem, but NovaGent http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=71038 has an inactive torrent and it shows up fine under Recent Uploads...\r\n\r\nAnyway, will try to replicate it by stop seeding my own upload :P\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT: Scratch that, inactivity does not trigger the issue.[/i][/b]',129045,'2012-07-14 15:58:33'),(44072,5669,1507,'2012-07-14 03:15:29','[quote=yamchan07bb]Place your mouse cursor over any of the search boxes and wait a second. Under the cursor, a tooltip will appear saying \"Search _______\"[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:thumbsup:\r\n\r\n[b]Thank you yamchan07bb...  I\'ve never even noticed that....  :smile1:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(44073,5635,1507,'2012-07-14 03:19:28',' :gunshot: ',NULL,NULL),(44074,5672,47234,'2012-07-14 03:59:20','Yeah its broken.  Its giving a 404 instead of linking to the tutorial articles of which we have a few now :)\r\n\r\nThis is the Help link at the top of the page between Rules and Staff.  All those other links are working fine',NULL,NULL),(44075,5672,1243,'2012-07-14 04:04:08','Yeah someone has removed the article with the \"tutorials\" id, which is the link to the help section.',NULL,NULL),(44076,5672,84499,'2012-07-14 04:40:45',' \r\n\r\nwho clicked the delete link? :alcapone:',NULL,NULL),(44077,5672,47234,'2012-07-14 04:41:08','Chances are it was me... I have been working on Articles a bit :slap:  Sort of thing i would manage\n\nEdit;  When im home for work i promise to repopulate the Tutorials Link with Links to current tutorials',47234,'2012-07-14 04:42:14'),(44078,5672,84499,'2012-07-14 04:47:24','\r\n\r\nNah all the links appear automatically at the bottom. IIRC all it said on that page was \"Here be noobs\" (unless someone changed it recently) :hmmm: we should probably think of something more apt for that page... it just needs to be there to act as a portal to the help section.',NULL,NULL),(44079,5673,47234,'2012-07-14 05:02:12','Hitting the torrents link takes me to this now.  Not a torrent in sight\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=B920_5000E0DA][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=B920_5000E0DA&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nI even tried searching blonde (because its super common) and got nothing as well.\r\n\r\nAre you guys doing something or did the database fall over or?',NULL,NULL),(44080,5673,103390,'2012-07-14 05:03:59','The same thing is happening to me too. Did a search for hardcore and nothing showed up.\n\nAlso, the torrents I\'m seeding/leeching are giving me \"couldn\'t connect to server errors,\"',103390,'2012-07-14 05:06:13'),(44081,5673,1243,'2012-07-14 06:07:49','The Server had rebooted for unknown reason. Not all services starts automatically so that was the problem.',NULL,NULL),(44084,5674,1783,'2012-07-14 10:37:24','Hey guys,\n\nA small bug, if you even want to call it that, in IE the link for the Tools drop down menu has a gap between the link and the drop down box. So every time you try to drag your mouse down into the drop down to select a link the box disappears before your able to. The drop down to a users profile & account info is flush to the bottom of the user\'s username. This is how the tools drop down should be too, however it isn\'t. \n\n \n[mcom][b]confirmed bug[/b] - gap under tools menu in IE (css snafu)\n[b]fixed?[/b] - please test[/mcom]',84499,'2012-08-14 16:29:00'),(44085,5675,89443,'2012-07-14 11:03:12','The \'View History\' tab inside a torrent page comes up as Error 404 - You just tried to go to a page that doesn\'t really exist.\n\nI\'m not sure what this \'View History\' thing is supposed to be but I\'m pretty sure it\'s not supposed to do what it\'s doing now.  :wink: \n\nP.S. I tried to find this topic in the forum but was unsuccessful. So, apologies in advance if this has already been reported.\n\n[mcom][b]confirmed bug[/b] - view history links to a page dosent really exist error\n[b]FIXED[/b] - all functionality is now in view log, removed view history button[/mcom]\n',84499,'2012-07-14 20:06:11'),(44086,5676,89443,'2012-07-14 11:18:37','I like this idea but there is just one problem with the execution. Whenever you click on a \'plus\' or a \'minus\' the page has to re-load. When the torrent page contains a lot of high quality images it can take a while for the whole thing to re-load (especially if you are downloading stuff at a high speed, or if your internet connection sucks). Is it possible to make it so that when you rate a tag you see the result change without having the whole page re-load?',NULL,NULL),(44087,5669,129045,'2012-07-14 17:09:40','Ok, I see the changes rolled in.\r\n\r\nSince \"Search ______\" is in plain sight now, what about changing the tool tip to something like \"[i]Type the keyword(s) and press Enter[/i]\" ?',NULL,NULL),(44089,5678,129045,'2012-07-14 18:26:04','Point it to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=notify\r\n\r\nRather than http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?action=notify\r\n\r\nHaving to click on \'[b][i]Notifications[/i][/b]\' and then on \'[b][i]View[/i][/b]\' can get a bit tiresome, so when users go to the menu and hit \"Notifications\" they should be greeted with the notifications list, rather than the Filters configuration page.\r\n\r\nThe default message could be changed too, just to be extra clear.\r\nIf the user has no filters set, instead of \"[i]No new notifications found! [b]Edit notification filters (link)[/b][/i]\" it could display \"[i]No filters set! [b]Add a filter (link)[/b][/i]\" :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[s]EDIT: Gah, thread title should say \"[b][i]Changing the \"Notifications\" [color=#FF0000]link[/color] destination[/i][/b]\", could somebody fix it, please?[/s] Thank you!',129045,'2012-07-14 18:36:47'),(44091,5678,47234,'2012-07-14 18:33:13','Title changed',NULL,NULL),(44092,5669,48010,'2012-07-14 18:37:45','It\'s clear now - good work and thanks\r\nDave',NULL,NULL),(44093,5672,48010,'2012-07-14 18:40:35','worked ok for me - I see\r\n\r\nOther tutorials\r\nTitle 	Additional Info\r\nUploading with uTorrent for Dummies 	A small guide on how to download with uTorrent\r\nBoolean Search 	A guide on how to use boolean operators for a more refined search\r\nConnectability Checker 	How to use the Connectability Checker to check you are connectable through your torrent client\r\nbbCode 	A guide to bbcode\r\nSeedbox setup on a Kimsufi 2G 	A step by step guide on a couple of methods of turning a cheap Kimsufi 2G into a Seedbox\r\nAvatar 	How to add an Avatar\r\n\r\nhope that\'s right Clownius\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44094,5670,48010,'2012-07-14 18:47:01','[quote=usillyboy][b]I left a couple of cumments, a couple of tags, and am using a DS slot to test...  \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb: :chase:[/quote]\r\nthanks usb',NULL,NULL),(44095,5672,47234,'2012-07-14 18:47:17','Thats the current one im still adjusting and adding to articles.  Avatar Tutorial is new today for example :)',NULL,NULL),(44096,5674,48010,'2012-07-14 19:30:36','[quote=iigreatoneii]Hey guys,\r\n\r\nA small bug, if you even want to call it that, in IE the link for the Tools drop down menu has a gap between the link and the drop down box. So every time you try to drag your mouse down into the drop down to select a link the box disappears before your able to.[/quote]\r\n\r\nworks ok for me in FF\r\n\r\n[quote]The drop down to a users profile & account info is flush to the bottom of the user\'s username. This is how the tools drop down should be too, however it isn\'t.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI don\'t see that ?????',NULL,NULL),(44097,5675,48010,'2012-07-14 19:35:43','confirmed - same here on my upload and 2 others I checked',NULL,NULL),(44098,5671,48010,'2012-07-14 19:52:33','confirmed - I see the same as usb',NULL,NULL),(44099,5619,88640,'2012-07-14 19:55:27','This happened to me when I used Firefox, but when I switched to Explorer it worked fine.',NULL,NULL),(44100,5676,118418,'2012-07-14 19:57:04','Something like Like/Not like in youtube, right? Yeah, I miss something like this too. Well, of course it stills awesome this way, but would be better without refreshing all the content (since some of our guys doesn\'t cache the images). Anyway, nice idea! It can keep the tag most present on the video(s) focused!',NULL,NULL),(44101,5675,84499,'2012-07-14 19:59:27','\r\n\r\nOkay after some investigation the view log button now provides all the history... the view history button is a relic from when torrents and torrent groups and artists were seperate entities, I will remove the history button!\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44102,5674,84499,'2012-07-14 20:12:48','\r\n\r\nDave you must see the dropdown menu under your name... with Inbox, Staff Inbox, etc at the top and Conn-Checker at the bottom of the menu?',NULL,NULL),(44103,5619,84499,'2012-07-14 20:17:59','[quote=hobobobo]This happened to me when I used Firefox, but when I switched to Explorer it worked fine.[/quote]\r\n\r\nJust to clarify: do you mean you were able to login without resetting your password in IE? (when it wouldnt work in FF)',NULL,NULL),(44104,5648,84499,'2012-07-14 20:21:52','\r\n\r\nI think Lanz fixed this one a while ago... needs testing but should be good now  :gjob: ',NULL,NULL),(44106,5676,84499,'2012-07-14 20:29:06','\r\n\r\n :hmmm: \r\n\r\nI agree it would be better that way...\r\n\r\nI will investigate but no promises, (I made a \'small change\' yesterday that took about 12 hours to get working lol) if it really is a small thing I might change it.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44107,5619,88640,'2012-07-14 20:36:18','[quote=mifune][quote=hobobobo]This happened to me when I used Firefox, but when I switched to Explorer it worked fine.[/quote]\n\nJust to clarify: do you mean you were able to login without resetting your password in IE? (when it wouldnt work in FF)[/quote]\nNo, I still had to reset password using IE, but the email link redirected properly in IE.  In FF the email link would redirect me to Step 1 which is to enter your email address, so in FF it was essentially just looping me over and over again. (I just checked and since the reset in IE, I can now log in properly in FF, meaning I don\'t have to try and reset password in FF).',88640,'2012-07-14 20:39:53'),(44109,5679,84499,'2012-07-14 21:05:33','\r\n\r\nIf you want some credits or slots to play with just post here and a staff member will give you a bundle  :gjob: ',NULL,NULL),(44110,5674,1783,'2012-07-14 21:13:52','Yeah, I\'ve only experienced this in [b]Internet Explorer[/b]. \n\nHere is what it looks like:\n\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=5997_5001C3D6][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=5997_5001C3D6[/img][/url]\n\nWhen the two drop downs are compared side by side, that gap under the tools one doesn\'t allow you to access the links inside it. It should be a quick fix as it appears to be just coding since the other drop down performs as it should.',1783,'2012-07-14 21:20:42'),(44111,5668,84499,'2012-07-14 21:41:36','\r\n\r\ndoes updating your torrent client manually make any difference?',NULL,NULL),(44112,5667,1246,'2012-07-14 22:15:56','I\'m 100% for an EMP specific server, primarily because if we set up our own then we could have hostmasking. The \'being able to use our full usernames\' thing is a bonus.',NULL,NULL),(44113,5680,129045,'2012-07-14 23:04:19','Since their function is in plain sight now ([i]\"Search ______ \"[/i]), why not change the tooltip to something else, instead of having it present the same info \"[i]Search ______ [/i]\"?\r\n\r\nDue to the lack of a \"Go\" or \"Search\" button, changing the tooltip to something like \"Type your search terms and press Enter\" would clarify things right away IMO (even though the speed seems to vary between browsers... so the user actually need to stop the cursor over the box to actually see the tooltip) :hmmm: ',NULL,NULL),(44114,5681,129045,'2012-07-14 23:26:37','Access it here: http://empornium.mooo.com/requests.php or by clicking on \"Requests\" at the top bar.\r\n\r\nThings that seems to work just fine (but please, test it):\r\n\r\n[color=#009900]- Creating requests\r\n- Voting\r\n- Filling (and receiving the bounty)\r\n- Unfilling (bounty is taken back)\r\n- Filtering\\Search\r\n- Bookmarking\r\n- System notification once the Request is filled\\unfilled\r\n[/color]\r\n\r\n:excl:[size=3][b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b] When filling requests pay attention to its category: ([color=#6633FF]Request > [color=#FF0000][b][i]Category[/i][/b][/color] > Request title[/color]), it appears below the top bar.\r\n[color=#FF3300][b]The torrent you upload or use to fill it must be in the same category[/b][/color]. Doesn\'t matter if the content matches what the user requested, if the category isn\'t the same, the page will give you an error.\r\n[/size]\r\n\r\n:excl:[size=3][b][i]EDIT2:[/i][/b] Can you spot any option to [b][i]Update \\ Edit[/i][/b] your Requests? I can\'t see any here :hmmm:[/size]\r\n\r\n\r\n:excl:[size=3][b][i]EDIT3:[/i][/b] Seems like I can fill any request and claim the bounty by using the torrent of another user. [color=#FF3300]Wouldn\'t that lead to abuse?[/color]\r\nIn case the torrent is already upped on EMP, users should point it out in the comments section or by PM, rather than going ahead and claiming the bounty.[/size]\r\n\r\n[b][i]Please, report anything weird here:[/i][/b] http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2693',129045,'2012-07-16 13:19:32'),(44115,5682,129045,'2012-07-14 23:48:30','[i][b][color=#FF0000][size=2]No notification is sent or received for any of the Bonus gifts\\purchases.[/size][/color][/b][/i]\n\nBack when I was testing the Bonus shop and its features, one thing that USB brought up is that he didn\'t receive any notifications about the credit gifts I sent, [i][b]even though the user\'s profile page seems to keep a precise log about it[/b][/i].\n\n[s](This is an assumption, as mine logged every Bonus purchase, gifts and each time Mifune set my credits value. So I guess USB, Clownius, barumba, cyberavatar and slobray also have the gifts logged on their profile\'s page)[/s] [color=#FF6600]Confirmed, thanks for dropping by :)[/color]\n\n[mcom][b]FIXED[/b] in as much as it now sends a PM when you get a gift from another in the shop.\nIf anyone wants other notifications adding please post[/mcom]\n',84499,'2012-07-15 20:54:50'),(44116,5683,129045,'2012-07-14 23:58:08','Since there\'s no option to toggle under [i][b]Settings[/b][/i], I guess this is simply not inplemented yet :hmmm:\r\nWould be nice to have this feature like EMP.me\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44117,5684,129045,'2012-07-15 00:57:04','[i][b][color=#FF0000]!You\'ll need some Slots[/color], check this thread:[/b][/i] http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2679\r\n\r\n\r\nRegarding the quick links: Download [b][DL][/b], Freeleech [b][FL][/b] and Report [b][RP][/b] ([i]why the lack of a Doubleseed option?[/i])\r\n\r\nSome torrents will not present the [b][FL][/b] link, see:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php?id=1\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php?id=2\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php?id=3\r\n\r\n[color=#0000FF]\"Neighbor.Affair.15\"[/color], [color=#003300]\"BigTitsAtSchool - Franceska Jaimes\"[/color], [color=#CC00FF]\"BigTitsAtSchool - Persia Black\"[/color], [color=#993300]\"Don\'t Cum Inside Me\"[/color], [color=#CC66FF]\"Kayden Kros Megapack\"[/color] and [color=#999900]\"Blumpkin Blowjobs 3\"[/color] lack it in the list, even though the torrent\'s page have the Freeleech button available.\r\n\r\nAlso it doesn\'t have a clear pattern, some are old and unseeded, others are newer and seeded :hmmm:\r\n\r\n\r\nAnd this is most likely a cache issue, some torrents doesn\'t seem to update to the correct # of torrents in the collage, while others show up instantly. Some examples, see:\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=32831 (Should be listing 9, only shows 1)\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=30780 (Should be listing 5, only shows 3)',129045,'2012-07-15 01:23:25'),(44118,5671,6203,'2012-07-15 00:58:13','confirmed, i have the same problem since some days.',NULL,NULL),(44119,5685,1246,'2012-07-15 01:29:00','This is a test post to see whether or not my signature in this post will change from what is was before (a few smilies) to what I changed it to 3 minutes ago (a still gif).\n\n\nAfter I changed my signature in Settings, I went to view one of my old posts, but saw that the signature was unchanged.\n\n[mcom][b]buggy buggy bum bum[/b] - it will update eventually.... but its semi random as to how long that will take and not really expected behaviour... yeah i guess i will fix this annoying as it is lol - mifune\n[b]FIXED[/b] - this should be fixed now, update your sig and it will be instantly reflected in all your posts etc.[/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-15 23:37:56'),(44120,5685,129045,'2012-07-15 01:41:42','I\'m pretty sure it\'s retroactive, it just may take a while to update :hmmm:\r\n\r\nRight now I see [i][b]allguys.gif[/b][/i].',NULL,NULL),(44121,5670,86439,'2012-07-15 05:22:46','I wiped my bum on your torrent.',NULL,NULL),(44122,5670,1246,'2012-07-15 05:49:38','I found your used toilet paper. Prepare foe an unconventional stocking stuffer this xmas.',NULL,NULL),(44123,5670,86439,'2012-07-15 07:08:53','[quote=borkb0rkbork]I found your used toilet paper. Prepare foe an unconventional stocking stuffer this xmas.[/quote]\r\nDid you reuse it?, it was supersoft.',NULL,NULL),(44124,5682,47234,'2012-07-15 09:02:35','i Can confirm seeing the gift on my logs but no id did not receive a message telling me where they came from.  In fact it was a while until i even noticed them arrive.\r\n\r\nIt would be a nice feature to have back',NULL,NULL),(44125,5686,89443,'2012-07-15 09:54:03','Perhaps this is something that bothers only a minority of users, perhaps not. I feel as though the most (or at least one of the most) important parts of a movie/scene is the \'finish\'. A lot of torrents don\'t specify what happens at the end. E.g. facial, cum-in-mouth (swallow or spit, swapping), cum-on-tits/ass, etc. \r\nA lot of uploaders do provide such info but a lot don\'t. It would be nice if there was some kind of box where you can check off what happens at the end of the scene (if applicable of course) when uploading. Just my two cents. I don\'t know if too many people care about this stuff but for me it usually is the difference between downloading and not downloading a torrent.\r\n\r\nAlso, I\'ve never seen such a thing on any porn-torrent site so it\'s something that would make Empornium unique.\r\n\r\nThanks for reading.',NULL,NULL),(44126,5687,47234,'2012-07-15 09:54:24','As most of our invited testers dont actually test anything and the server is lets face it likely more powerful than the current Emp server how many more should we invite?\n\nIm happy to send Invites out.  I can handle copy and paste.\n\nSo to Lanz and Mifune post here how many more testers you want and when and i can handle the Invites.\n\nMy suggestion is 200 more testers.  Maybe then we will get 20 or 30 people who will break things\n\nI swear maybe 1 in 10 actually do much more than look and say cool :lol:\n',47234,'2012-07-15 09:55:05'),(44127,5687,1507,'2012-07-15 10:02:00','[quote=Clownius]As most of our invited testers dont actually test anything and the server is lets face it likely more powerful than the current Emp server how many more should we invite?\r\n\r\nIm happy to send Invites out.  I can handle copy and paste.\r\n\r\nSo to Lanz and Mifune post here how many more testers you want and when and i can handle the Invites.\r\n\r\n[color=magenta]My suggestion is 200 more testers.  Maybe then we will get 20 or 30 people who will break things[/color]\r\n\r\nI swear maybe 1 in 10 actually do much more than look and say cool :lol:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(44131,5687,1246,'2012-07-15 10:25:49','I did a break-shit dance today. Nothing broke.\r\n\r\nI\'m doing my part!\r\n\r\n :w00t:  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(44135,5679,48010,'2012-07-15 13:47:33','no takers - most of these testers are lame\r\n\r\ngive me 2 slots and a shed load of credits so I can play around (possibly I could add them to myself but that is not fair on the members if staff manipulate their own account)',NULL,NULL),(44136,5681,48010,'2012-07-15 13:48:32','added request',NULL,NULL),(44137,5670,48010,'2012-07-15 14:17:07','[quote=knickers]I wiped my bum on your torrent.[/quote]\n\nthanks knickers you got a one week warning - if it doesn\'t clear let me know (but I\'m watching) and thanks for testing and I gave you a slot on the main site as compensation',48010,'2012-07-15 14:17:42'),(44139,5690,48010,'2012-07-15 14:20:40','don\'t take it seriously he did what I asked and I gave him a slot on emp.me\n\nI see other staff extended the warning - thats cool as a test\n\nnow we need to warn another 2 willing victims but this time one gets a week extension but the others stands and [b]no one adds to it[/b] to check it clears\n\nany suggestions for a guinea pig ? me ? a normal user would be better tho\n\nAlso should I reduce knickers ban as a test ? but really we shouldn\'t over-rule another staff members decison to to it ?\n\n',48010,'2012-07-16 18:29:16'),(44140,5676,48010,'2012-07-15 14:31:05','I understand the community tagging thing and mifune I\'m not anti tags but I noticed the following\r\n\r\nOn my upload I didn\'t get notified of tags added or voted up/down (and this was tested) - not a big deal but for me but for some it might be\r\n\r\non the other hand I got no notification of tag changes so do we need to keep telling uploaders of tag changes by PM ? I think this will annoy a lot of them but at the end of the day the uploader sets the tags and others change them. I don\'t really like that.\r\n\r\nI like the current emp.me system where members politely request tags in a comment',NULL,NULL),(44141,5681,86439,'2012-07-15 14:50:17','harrrgggllllbl blarrrrgghh',86439,'2012-07-15 14:54:13'),(44142,5670,86439,'2012-07-15 14:51:37','That warning could easily go unnoticed. I logged in, looked around a little and didnt notice i has a message until I saw your post here. Not sure if Id notice it more if I was more familiar with the site, or not,\n\n[spoiler=spoilered to keep forums SFW for mifune][url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-22B7_5002BC0C.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-22B7_5002BC0C.gif[/img][/url][/spoiler]\n',84499,'2012-07-19 20:13:38'),(44143,5672,48010,'2012-07-15 15:13:43','[quote=Clownius]Thats the current one im still adjusting and adding to articles.  Avatar Tutorial is new today for example :)[/quote]\r\nso it looks ok then :grin:',NULL,NULL),(44144,5686,86439,'2012-07-15 15:14:17','Dude, you just cum in your own mouth, ending is always the same then.',NULL,NULL),(44145,5675,48010,'2012-07-15 15:15:04','cool - good work mifune',NULL,NULL),(44146,5691,86439,'2012-07-15 15:16:13','I just posted a comment in a forum thread, the wrong thread, and noticed I dont have the option to simply delete my own post. I can only edit it. Might be a handy feature to have, especially for me lol.\r\n\r\nHavent noticed if same can be done for torrent comments too.',NULL,NULL),(44147,5692,86439,'2012-07-15 15:31:54','I just tried to add an image to use in my sig, it tested fine in the \'toggle preview\' mode, but when I clicked \'save profile\' I got this error message\n\n Signature field: http://www.freeimage.us/image-22B7_5002BC0C.gif is not on an approved pichost.\n\n\n[mcom][b]Fixed[/b] Added www.freeimage.us to whitelist[/mcom]',84499,'2012-07-15 18:18:44'),(44148,5685,86439,'2012-07-15 15:35:12','Working fine for me. I see 4 cupcakes and a donut.',NULL,NULL),(44150,5682,48010,'2012-07-15 16:04:37','agreed I just got slots from mifune for testing and nearly didn\'t notice them\r\n\r\nsome notification would be good for credits given or other stuff awarded by members or staff',NULL,NULL),(44151,5693,129045,'2012-07-15 16:04:44','Things that doesn\'t seem to work\\inconsistencies:\r\n\r\n[size=2][color=#FF0000]- [b]Requests Updates\\Edits[/b][/color] are absent, [b][i]the user cannot update the request in any way (e.g. descriptions updates, category changes or tag additions)[/i][/b][/size]\r\n[color=#FF0000]- When reporting a request[/color], the guidelines will reference using \"[b][i][Requests Update][/i][/b]\".\r\n[color=#FF0000]- When the user tries to create a new request[/color] http://empornium.mooo.com/requests.php?action=new The tag guidelines will contain this (What.CD residues?):\r\n\r\n[quote]There is a list of official tags to the left of the text box. Please use these tags instead of \'unofficial\' tags (eg. use the official \'[color=#006600]drum.and.bass[/color]\' tag, instead of an unofficial \'[color=#FF0000]dnb[/color]\' tag.)[/quote]\r\n[color=#FF3300]\r\n- [size=2]As of now, users can fill requests by providing [b][i]any[/i][/b] torrent already upped on EMP (e.g. the torrent of different users) and claim the bounty.[/size][/color]\r\n[color=#FFFFFF]--[/color]Wouldn\'t be better to block users from doing so? The system will already stop the user from filling a request if the categories don\'t match, so to avoid such undesirable situation, the system could block\r\n[color=#FFFFFF]--[/color]the user informing that he isn\'t the owner of the torrent he is trying to supply.\r\n[color=#FFFFFF]--[/color]In this case, the correct course of action could be linking it in the comments and then flagging the request somehow (report?), so the Staff could delete\\lock it and any bounty\\votes would be returned to\r\n[color=#FFFFFF]--[/color]their owners.\r\n\r\n\r\nThings that work:\r\n\r\n[color=#009900]- Creating requests\r\n- Voting\r\n- Filling (and receiving the bounty)\r\n- Unfilling (bounty is taken back)\r\n- Filtering\\Search\r\n- Bookmarking\r\n- System notification once the Request is filled\\unfilled\r\n[/color]\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b] IF you need help to test your request, visit this thread: http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2681',129045,'2012-07-16 13:19:40'),(44152,5674,48010,'2012-07-15 16:09:40','[quote=mifune]Dave you must see the dropdown menu under your name... with Inbox, Staff Inbox, etc at the top and Conn-Checker at the bottom of the menu?[/quote]\ngot that but not the users profile & account info - is that something differenrt ?',48010,'2012-07-15 16:14:38'),(44153,5681,129045,'2012-07-15 16:26:01','OP updated.\r\n\r\n[quote=Dave]added request[/quote]\r\n\r\nI was thinking more in general terms, nothing too specific, just to see if the whole system is working properly. Try posting something easier and I\'ll try to fill :P',129045,'2012-07-15 16:30:32'),(44154,5694,129045,'2012-07-15 16:41:36','Access it here: http://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php or [s]by clicking on \"Collages\" at the top bar.[/s] [color=#FF0000]The Collages link now has moved to the user menu, it\'s located to the left of [b]Settings[/b] and [b]Logout[/b]. Hover your username and you\'ll find the \"Collages\" link there.[/color] \r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=CB96_500AC0FB][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-CB96_500AC0FB.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nAlso, see if you experience any of this: http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2684',129045,'2012-07-21 16:49:01'),(44157,5696,86439,'2012-07-15 17:02:29','I uploaded a torrent.\r\n\r\n:grin:',NULL,NULL),(44158,5676,84499,'2012-07-15 17:05:51','\r\n\r\n[quote=Dave]I understand the community tagging thing and mifune I\'m not anti tags but I noticed the following\r\n\r\nOn my upload I didn\'t get notified of tags added or voted up/down (and this was tested) - not a big deal but for me but for some it might be\r\n\r\non the other hand I got no notification of tag changes so do we need to keep telling uploaders of tag changes by PM ? I think this will annoy a lot of them but at the end of the day the uploader sets the tags and others change them. I don\'t really like that.\r\n\r\nI like the current emp.me system where members politely request tags in a comment[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nThe way I see it is this: on this site tags are not part of your presentation. Tags are just an aid to searching - in fact they are nothing more than searchable keywords. The uploader may or may not add the correct tags, or may only add a couple - when for effective searching it could do with a few more. The community tagging system is a way of trying to get appropriate and useful tags on every torrent without draconian tag rules for uploaders and without having staff whos only job is to tag stuff (a solution I have seen on other sites).\r\n\r\nSo I see no reason for uploaders to be defensive about the tags on their uploads changing. Tags are not for uploaders, they are for pervs trying to find stuff. Don\'t be upset if your tags change, be glad that more pervs can find your upload now. \r\n\r\nAs far as telling uploaders of tag changes by PM... I dunno I have changed a few tags on emp.me and I never PM\'d anyone :lol: If that upset anybody then... I dunno maybe they shouldnt be so butthurt when their crappy tags get corrected?? Technically we could have notifications sent to the uploader but I dont like the idea, firstly it will generate a large volume of PM traffic saying very little - internal junkmail imo - and secondly it gives credence to this idea that the uploader has some ownership of the tags for their upload, when really they dont, they just set the initial state but then the tags belong to the tracker community - which is as it should be in my eyes.\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44159,5676,86439,'2012-07-15 17:54:34','[quote=mifune]\nThe way I see it is this: on this site tags are not part of your presentation. Tags are just an aid to searching - in fact they are nothing more than searchable keywords. The uploader may or may not add the correct tags, or may only add a couple - when for effective searching it could do with a few more. The community tagging system is a way of trying to get appropriate and useful tags on every torrent without draconian tag rules for uploaders and without having staff whos only job is to tag stuff (a solution I have seen on other sites).\n\nSo I see no reason for uploaders to be defensive about the tags on their uploads changing. Tags are not for uploaders, they are for pervs trying to find stuff. Don\'t be upset if your tags change, be glad that more pervs can find your upload now. \n\nAs far as telling uploaders of tag changes by PM... I dunno I have changed a few tags on emp.me and I never PM\'d anyone :lol: If that upset anybody then... I dunno maybe they shouldnt be so butthurt when their crappy tags get corrected?? Technically we could have notifications sent to the uploader but I dont like the idea, firstly it will generate a large volume of PM traffic saying very little - internal junkmail imo - and secondly it gives credence to this idea that the uploader has some ownership of the tags for their upload, when really they dont, they just set the initial state but then the tags belong to the tracker community - which is as it should be in my eyes.[/quote]\n\nI was with ya all the way, it all makes perfect sense and seems the most useful method of using tags,\n\nuntil I read this\n\n[quote=mifune]... having staff whos only job is to tag stuff (a solution I have seen on other sites).\n\n[/quote]\n\nNow Im convinced, there should be one mod to keep it all level, USB.',86439,'2012-07-15 17:55:43'),(44160,5692,84499,'2012-07-15 17:57:36','\r\n\r\nwhy is that image on [b]www[/b].freeimage.us and not [b]xxx[/b].freeimage.us ?\r\n\r\nanyway thats why... probably the www version should be added :hmmm: ',NULL,NULL),(44161,5692,86439,'2012-07-15 18:02:24','Doh!!',NULL,NULL),(44162,5691,84499,'2012-07-15 18:12:55','\r\n\r\n\r\nCan users delete their own posts at emp atm?\r\n\r\n\r\nI am not sure users generally should be able to delete their posts... I mean in your case you had a good reason but on the whole I think its bad ettiquette to go deleting posts after they have been responded to etc. I would rather have it as a staff only function and if something like what you did happens you can just report your post saying \"posted in wrong place pls delete\" and the staff can delete it.\r\n\r\nThats my gut feeling anyway.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44163,5691,129045,'2012-07-15 18:17:45','[quote=mifune]Can users delete their own posts at emp atm?\r\n\r\n\r\nI am not sure users generally should be able to delete their posts... I mean in your case you had a good reason but on the whole I think its bad ettiquette to go deleting posts after they have been responded to etc. I would rather have it as a staff only function and if something like what you did happens you can just report your post saying \"posted in wrong place pls delete\" and the staff can delete it.\r\n\r\nThats my gut feeling anyway.[/quote]\r\n\r\nEMP.mooo is the same thing as EMP.me, users cannot delete anything. Apart from their own torrents :hmmm:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44164,5691,86439,'2012-07-15 18:21:02','[quote=mifune]Can users delete their own posts at emp atm?\r\n\r\n\r\nI am not sure users generally should be able to delete their posts... I mean in your case you had a good reason but on the whole I think its bad ettiquette to go deleting posts after they have been responded to etc. I would rather have it as a staff only function and if something like what you did happens you can just report your post saying \"posted in wrong place pls delete\" and the staff can delete it.\r\n\r\nThats my gut feeling anyway.[/quote]\r\nNo, we cant delete posts there either, but not being able to encourages people to just edit to, nvm or similar. Makes sense when folks have responded though I can see that. Maybe a time limit to delete (10 mins), unless a response (relevant or not) has been posted after it within that 10 mins.\r\n\r\nAnd yes, im glad Im not the one coding all this.  You should be too, I code like a monkey.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44165,5697,129045,'2012-07-15 18:31:35','When the user tries to edit a torrent, he only has access to:\n\n- Category\n- Cover\n- Description\n- Edit summary (reason)\n\nNo way to update the torrent [b][i]title[/i][/b]. [color=#FF6600]Or [b][i]tags[/i][/b] as knickers brought up...[/color]\n\nAlso, the [b][i]Edit[/i][/b] page will have a small section at the bottom, called \"[b][i]Other[/i][/b]\", housing a lonely \"[b]Edit[/b]\" button that doesn\'t seem to do anything important, it simply kicks you back to the torrent\'s page :hmmm:\n\n[mcom][b]FIXED[/b] - \'Other\' heading should not be visible to non staff on torrent edit page\n[b]DONE[/b] - Should uploaders be able to edit titles? Should uploaders be able to add with votes=9/delete their own tags after upload? A: yes[/mcom]\n',84499,'2012-07-24 23:24:22'),(44166,5682,84499,'2012-07-15 18:37:13','\r\n\r\n\r\nI will confess I hate hate hate the bonus shop notifications on emp.me so neglected to add them when I coded up the bonus shop here :lol:\r\n\r\nHowever... that is not a great reason in itself not to have them. \r\n\r\nAre we talking about notifications for your own actions in the shop? which I think we can probably live without; you do get a record in your own bonus log and if you are buying it in the shop yourself you shouldnt need reminding that you have just done that!\r\n\r\nBut notifications (ie. a PM) when you get given something from the shop, that makes perfect sense to me, I will add that.\r\n\r\nIf some of you do feel strongly that you should get notifications of your own actions in the shop then you can try and persuade me to include them...\r\n\r\n\r\nNotifications when a staff member moderates your profile (to give you credits/slots/badges/change your stats etc) is more difficult. The straightforward way to implement that is to just automatically send a PM whenever a staff changes anything on that page, but that might not be appropriate for some of the actions on there. :hmmm: Its not impossible to come up with a better system for this but how much of a priority is it?',NULL,NULL),(44167,5697,86439,'2012-07-15 18:37:37','Also cant edit tags as original uploader either (std +9), but the OP can add tags as a non-uploader (std +2). I assume these values are counts of thumbs up or down for the particular tag, with the OP\'s tags having a decent start count to counter some imbalance. When adding tags, the OPs dont have that weighting.',86439,'2012-07-15 18:39:36'),(44168,5682,129045,'2012-07-15 18:41:21','Yeah, sorry, I just brought that up because it\'s the current behavior on EMP.me, but you\'re right about omiting the self notifications, as the profile\'s log does a better job at that.',NULL,NULL),(44169,5697,129045,'2012-07-15 18:43:28','[quote=knickers]Also cant edit tags as...[/quote]\r\n\r\nReading mifune opinion on the other thread, I don\'t think that will change. But yeah, thanks for bringing that up, forgot to add it :(',NULL,NULL),(44170,5698,86439,'2012-07-15 18:47:39','Not sure if this is desirable or not, but it can generate conversations in threads. At the bottom of a thread, a list of members viewing a thread at the time? With an option in your profile to not show you as active if you so choose.\r\n\r\nThis can increase traffic in a thread as seeing a number of members you find interesting hanging out in a thread attracts people to stay in it. Thus generating conversation in almost real time.',NULL,NULL),(44171,5699,129045,'2012-07-15 18:52:16','While testing http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2693 , I experienced this: \r\n\r\n[quote][color=#FF3300]\r\n- [size=2]As of now, users can fill requests by providing [b][i]any[/i][/b] torrent already upped on EMP (e.g. the torrent of different users) and claim the bounty.[/size][/color]\r\n[color=#FFFFFF]--[/color]Wouldn\'t be better to block users from doing so? The system will already stop the user from filling a request if the categories don\'t match, so to avoid such undesirable situation, the system\r\n[color=#FFFFFF]--[/color]could block the user informing that he isn\'t the owner of the torrent he is trying to supply.\r\n[color=#FFFFFF]--[/color][b]In this case[/b], the correct course of action could be linking it in the comments and then flagging the request somehow (report?), so the Staff could delete\\lock it and any bounty\\votes would be\r\n[color=#FFFFFF]--[/color]returned to their owners.[/quote]\r\n\r\nThoughts? The rules page is pretty strict, so I doubt such thing would go unnoticed and left for the Staff to fix each time it happened :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(44172,5661,129045,'2012-07-15 19:01:03','Sounds good.\r\n\r\nDoing an announcement on EMP.me to recruit any users interested to do the translations could work pretty well :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(44173,5699,86439,'2012-07-15 19:02:21','Reading the quoted text, wouldnt it be easier in the long run just to assign say 50% (or whatever) of the bounty to the member name listed as uploader on the torrent linked, and the remainder becomes a spotters fee added to the person who linked it.\n\nThat way if they were the same person, they would get 100% of the offer and its automated. That way people are encouraged to find such things without having to rely on the original uploader to read the request?\n\nI have no idea of the difficulties of coding such a thing, so that was not even considered by me. Or am I missing the point here?',86439,'2012-07-15 19:02:51'),(44174,5699,129045,'2012-07-15 19:05:50','That solution sounds good too :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(44175,5700,129045,'2012-07-15 19:16:29','[b][color=#0066FF][DL][/color][/b] = Normal Download\r\n[b][color=#009900][FL][/color][/b] = Use slot to activate Freeleech Download\r\n[b][color=#FF6600][DS][/color][/b] = Use slot to activate Doubleseed Download\r\n[b][color=#FF0000][RP][/color][/b] = Report\r\n\r\nWould that be welcome or not?\r\n\r\nCurrent:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php > Only lists quick DL\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php?id=3 > Lists DL, FL and RP (sometime [FL] is absent http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2684)\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/top10.php > Only lists quick DL\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/bookmarks.php?type=torrents  > Lists DL, FL and RP (sometime [FL] is absent http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2684)\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?type=uploaded&userid=129045 > Only lists quick DL and RP (to check your own list, hover your username under the topbar and then click on \"Uploads\")\r\n\r\nPlease, post if you find any other places not listed here.',129045,'2012-07-15 19:18:15'),(44176,5661,86439,'2012-07-15 19:19:29','I can translate into English\r\n\r\n\r\nand Yobbo.',NULL,NULL),(44177,5701,70679,'2012-07-15 19:22:14','Seen it before but now I know for sure.... example is here:\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2645&page=1#post23954\r\n\r\nIf I try to do a new post and the last post in the thread is mine then it appends it as an edit in the last post instead of generating a new entry.',NULL,NULL),(44178,5701,86439,'2012-07-15 19:31:21','Yeah thats freaky. A side effect of the merge feature to prevent double posts, with the added benefit of preventing bumps too.\n\nBut in that case, the bump is appropriate, but fails to bump.',86439,'2012-07-15 19:32:02'),(44179,5685,84499,'2012-07-15 21:06:47','\r\n\r\nYou know when you go back and look at the code you wrote when you first started on a project, and you think why the fuck did I do it that way? Why would you store the sig with the post instead of caching it with each users general info? I mean thats the obviously correct way to do it, the user info is going to get pulled anyway for the avatar and such. Then you beat your head against the keyboard repeatedly.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44180,5701,84499,'2012-07-15 21:13:20','\r\n\r\nsextreme\'s and above have the option to double post, there should be a checkbox in the quick reply box you can uncheck to not merge.\r\n\r\nI have extended this permission to good pervs too, may be different when we go live but for now good pervs should also be able to uncheck the merge post checkbox and be able to double post.',NULL,NULL),(44181,5685,86439,'2012-07-15 21:27:08','[quote=mifune]You know when you go back and look at the code you wrote when you first started on a project, and you think why the fuck did I do it that way? Why would you store the sig with the post instead of caching it with each users general info? I mean thats the obviously correct way to do it, the user info is going to get pulled anyway for the avatar and such. Then you beat your head against the keyboard repeatedly.[/quote]\r\nSo that would also be why when a sig is changed, it only changes from that post on, all previous posts retain the old sig etc?',NULL,NULL),(44182,5685,84499,'2012-07-15 21:35:44','well without boring you with how the caching system works old posts will update their signature eventually, either when something that is stored in the same place is updated or after about a month otherwise :lol:\n\nbut I\'m going to change it.',84499,'2012-07-15 21:36:27'),(44183,5645,70679,'2012-07-15 21:36:46','Revisiting this.... one feature of the script, namely being able to download without opening one entry is already implemented.\r\n\r\nThe other nice feature maybe could be to.... namely getting to open pictures in the entry by just hovering with the mouse over the category icon and being able to move forward and backwards with left and right key.\r\n\r\nMaybe?\r\n\r\n[IMG]http://i1261.photobucket.com/albums/ii581/barumba1/23_31_4.gif[/IMG]',NULL,NULL),(44184,5701,70679,'2012-07-15 21:38:04','Jep saw it now and it works but... it could confuse people...\r\n\r\nmaybe putting that option in red to make it more noticeable?',NULL,NULL),(44185,5702,70679,'2012-07-15 21:43:24','I think it could be better:\n\nTopic           Author        Views    Replies    Last Post\n                                     ^Nr.      ^Nr.      ',70679,'2012-07-16 20:53:20'),(44186,5679,84499,'2012-07-15 21:43:35','\r\n  :fiesta: ',NULL,NULL),(44187,5703,70679,'2012-07-15 21:45:34','not sure if it is a feature or bug but tabs and multiple spaces do not work. Tabs would be better like of you want to line up things.',NULL,NULL),(44188,5696,86439,'2012-07-15 21:50:39','Warnings received\r\n\r\n1st unrelated to the torrent, rsulted in one system message in inbox. (7 days)\r\n\r\n\r\n2nd warning is related to the torrent, resulted in 4 messages in inbox, 2 system, 2 USB (28 days)\r\n\r\nQuoted below in order they are listed in my inbox.\r\n\r\n[quote]Your above torrent was reported but not deleted.\r\n\r\nReason: The releases on the Do Not Upload list (on the upload page) are currently forbidden from being uploaded from the site. Do not upload them unless your torrent meets a condition specified in the comment.\r\nThis has resulted in a 4 week warning.\r\n\r\nLog Message: No log message (Torrent wasn\'t deleted)\r\n\r\n\r\nReport was handled by usillyboy. [/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote]When you received your latest warning (Set to expire on 2012-08-12), you already had a different warning (Set to expire on 2012-07-22).\r\n\r\nDue to this collision, your warning status will now expire at 2012-08-19 14:10:46.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote]You uploaded the above torrent, it has been reported for the reason: Specifically Banned\r\n\r\ndammit... \"ban hammer\" - usb hahaha.... - usb [/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote]You uploaded the above torrent, it has been reported for the reason: Specifically Banned\r\n\r\nomg... where\'s my ban hamer...?? - usb [/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44189,5703,84499,'2012-07-15 22:00:24','\r\n\r\nits a feature inherited from gazelle...\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\nI am sort of ambivalent about this, opinions?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44190,5703,86439,'2012-07-15 22:31:29','Sometimes it helps to lay out.\r\n\r\nAre we talking forum or torrents?\r\n\r\nDoesnt matter, Id use it occasionally in both.',NULL,NULL),(44191,5704,86439,'2012-07-15 23:10:53','May not be a bug, Im unsure.\n\n[url]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35149[/url]\n\nThe torrent I upped to be reported, was reported, then cleared and not deleted. The message in the torrent that explains the report to me, is gone, but on the browse list it still shows the red \'reported\' designation.\n\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-FD7D_500330FC.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-FD7D_500330FC.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-7F64_500330FC.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-7F64_500330FC.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nWhile on the subject. Wouldnt it be easier if the site picked up words on the banned list when i uploaded it/edit it? That way they never make it to the browse list unless hidden deliberately? I deliberately used tags and title that should ID it as banned content.\n\nOr is that too resource intensive?',86439,'2012-07-15 23:13:23'),(44192,5704,1507,'2012-07-15 23:13:31',':hmm:\r\n\r\n[b]I addressed that report and thought that I marked it for deletion...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nI most likely missed a step....\r\n\r\nlet\'s try again....  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\n\n:thumbsup:\r\n\r\n[b]Okay, second time it did delete automatically...  Most likely I messed up with my first attempt, but this time I accidentally did it correctly....  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',1507,'2012-07-15 23:18:08'),(44193,5705,70679,'2012-07-15 23:29:26','ability to edit own thread title... but I guess there are many reasons against this...',NULL,NULL),(44194,5697,84499,'2012-07-15 23:29:33','\r\n\r\nWe can have this stuff however we want it... but I am not sure what the desired behaviour is. \r\n\r\nCurrently only mods can edit torrent titles.\r\nWe are not going to add another tag interface, but perhaps we could have it so the uploader can add tags with 9 votes instead of 2 after the torrent is up :hmmm: Maybe even the uploader could remove their own tags too... again I am not sure what the best way to have it is.\r\n\r\nThe other thing at the bottom shouldnt be there (unless you are a mod, and then it has the freeleech options under it) we will fix that.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44195,5704,86439,'2012-07-15 23:32:58','Yeah cool. But I wasnt looking at whether it was deleted or not, just the fact it appeared to clear in the torrent details but the browse page still showed it as reported.\r\n\r\nOr is that because it was going to be deleted? I would have thought if you clear the report message (address it without deleting it), the browse page should drop the Report message too. Or can only I see that Reported message on the browse page? But still, not sure why it remains.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAdditionally, I reported your torrent http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35146 , plus one of Yamchans and in the torrent details page I could see the details of my report(s), but they never showed as reported on the browse page.\r\n\r\nI dont know if these are bugs, or just some other reason, for example not allowing me to report due to my warnings to prevent me getting upity and reporting everything to annoy mods etc.',NULL,NULL),(44196,5706,70679,'2012-07-15 23:37:21','ok do not kill me but.... I like the Deviloid feature where you get \"new\" on torrents stored in your data and that you are able to reset it yourself so that you can see in the torrents list the news and you have the ability once you checked them to reset it. Find it VERY useful.',NULL,NULL),(44197,5705,84499,'2012-07-15 23:45:41','\r\n\r\nAnd just for some extra meta comment about this I have changed the title of this thread to better reflect the topic :lol:\r\n \r\n ',NULL,NULL),(44198,5707,86439,'2012-07-15 23:48:27','OK, this one is a bug.\r\n\r\nThe torrent being discussed here  \r\n[url]http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2704&page=1#post24191[/url]\r\n\r\nand here\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2696&page=1#post24188\r\n\r\nhas resulted in an expected warning period. However, as it wasnt deleted, and USB had to deal with it a second time, the system sent me another 4 week warning which its added to the earlier one. So it punished me twice for the same reported torrent.\r\n\r\n\r\nOriginal message which explained as I was under a current 7 day warning (unrelated), the 4 week warning associated with the torrent would be added to it,\r\n\r\n[quote]When you received your latest warning (Set to expire on 2012-08-12), you already had a different warning (Set to expire on 2012-07-22).\r\n\r\nDue to this collision, your warning status will now expire at 2012-08-19 14:10:46. [/quote]\r\n\r\nAs can be seen, the 4 week period was added. But then the necessary second dealing with the same torrent resent the same warning period, but added it to the already applied one making it 8 weeks total for that torrent. \r\n\r\n[quote]When you received your latest warning (Set to expire on 2012-08-12), you already had a different warning (Set to expire on 2012-08-19).\r\n\r\nDue to this collision, your warning status will now expire at 2012-09-16 14:10:46. [/quote]',NULL,NULL),(44199,5707,84499,'2012-07-16 00:19:18','\r\n\r\nto be honest this one I dont think is a bug so much as a result of a report being dealt with twice. When a mod clicks on the \'resolve\' button it applies whatever settings are checked on the report interface, in the (hopefully) rare case when a report has to be resurrected and dealt with again its up to the staff to check/uncheck the settings as appropriate. There is no easy way for the system to track if a warning has already been issued by any specific thing.\r\n\r\nIt has to be said the torrent reports system is probably the most complex interface for the staff... its a pretty good system but bits of it are not very intuitive (we inherited it from gazelle), probably we need to do some staff training :lol: :lol:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44200,5703,1246,'2012-07-16 01:25:47','I\'ve always wanted to be able to tab and multispace in my posts, but I\'ve just dealt with not being able to do it in phpbb and now here. If it\'s possible, I\'d like it, I\'d use it. If it\'s a real pain in the ass, it\'s probably not worth it.  :evilbunny: ',NULL,NULL),(44201,5676,84499,'2012-07-16 02:58:47','\r\n\r\nokay I made it so you can vote \'in page\'. It wont reorder the list until you reload the page but it does update the num of votes etc so I think its probably okay.',NULL,NULL),(44202,5676,118418,'2012-07-16 03:55:24','Nice mifune! Just like we wanted it to be ... perfect! ;) Btw, the green box presenting the vote wasn\'t asked here but was smoothly implemented! Good work! :)',NULL,NULL),(44203,5704,1243,'2012-07-16 04:06:42','Cache keys did not update correctly. Fixed.',NULL,NULL),(44204,5608,1366,'2012-07-16 04:30:58','Still can\'t close the Search center and yes cookies are enabled.......running xp with IE8',1366,'2012-07-16 04:32:50'),(44205,5608,1783,'2012-07-16 07:51:50','Also experiencing this issue. Although, you\'re already well aware of it anyways! :)',NULL,NULL),(44206,5697,47234,'2012-07-16 09:01:01','Im for leaving title edits to Staff only sorry.  People remember titles and changing them is annoying.  \r\n\r\nAs for tags leave them alone we have the vote system.  Dont see why the uploader should have more votes than others once they have placed the original tags.  Just let the crowd take over at that point IMO',NULL,NULL),(44207,5707,47234,'2012-07-16 09:02:51','Staff training what is that?\r\n\r\nIm used to Emp.me style where training starts and ends with good luck and we make it up as we go along',NULL,NULL),(44208,5608,47234,'2012-07-16 09:05:27','Can we have a page that comes up if you try and log into emp.me with IE.\r\n\r\nIt says get a real browser if you want to use emp.me and offers links to download ff or chrome :laugh:  :laugh:  :mad: ',NULL,NULL),(44209,5696,47234,'2012-07-16 09:07:43','You should have a warning from me now too',NULL,NULL),(44210,5696,86439,'2012-07-16 11:00:29','Hmmm, considers next sig gif ....\r\n\r\n\r\n*looks in box of goodies.\r\n\r\nHa!',NULL,NULL),(44211,5608,86439,'2012-07-16 11:22:06','Is this where we get our balloons?',86439,'2012-07-16 11:22:19'),(44212,5696,129045,'2012-07-16 13:41:44','Got a warning...\r\n\r\n[quote][size=2][i]This has resulted in a [b]x week(s) warning[/b].[/i][/size][/quote]\r\n\r\n[b]x week(s) warning[/b] is a link, it leads to: http://empornium.mooo.com/wiki.php?action=article&id=218\r\n\r\nBut the link doesn\'t load here (blank page, no error) :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(44213,5696,84499,'2012-07-16 13:42:27','\r\n\r\nwhere did you see that text yamchan?',NULL,NULL),(44214,5696,129045,'2012-07-16 13:45:20','The PM the system sent me.\r\n\r\n[quote][i]Your above torrent[/i] (link) was reported and has been deleted.\r\n\r\n Reason: The torrent was determined to be infected with a virus/trojan. In the future, please scan all potential uploads with an antivirus program such as AVG, Avast, or MS Security Essentials.\r\n This has resulted in a [i][color=#FF0000]1 week warning[/color][/i] (link).\r\n\r\n Log Message: deleted torrent for the reason: Contains Virus. ( knickers test 3 )\r\n\r\n\r\n Report was handled by usillyboy.[/quote]',NULL,NULL),(44215,5608,84499,'2012-07-16 14:03:12','\r\n\r\nI have made a change but I cant test it right now... there is about a 50% chance it is now working in IE  :bombie: ',NULL,NULL),(44216,5608,129045,'2012-07-16 14:33:34','[quote=mifune]I have made a change but I cant test it right now... there is about a 50% chance it is now working in IE  :bombie:[/quote]\r\n\r\nIt works... But the text is inverted. (Testing with IE 9.0)\r\n\r\nIt says \'Open Search Center\' when it\'s already expanded and \'Close Search Center\' when it\'s retracted.\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b] [b][i]Seems to be hit and miss[/i][/b] :hmmm:\r\n\r\n- If you go to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php , the search will be expanded, saying \"[b][i]Open Search Center[/i][/b]\", after you click on it to close, it\'ll say \"[b][i]Close Search Center[/i][/b]\".\r\n\r\n- While the search is expanded, Reloading the page or clicking again on \"Torrents\' at the top bar will not fix the text.\r\n\r\n- If you click on it to retract the search and then reload or visit it again by clicking on \"Torrents\", it\'ll display the correct text (incorrectly at first, but after you click on it to retract, the correct text will appear). [b][i]But it\'s \'temporary\'[/i][/b], as soon as you close the page and visit the Torrents page, it\'ll behave incorectly again.\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT2:[/i][/b]\r\n\r\nFirst visit (wrong text)\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=2F1F_50041014][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=2F1F_50041014[/img][/url] [url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=EB85_50041014][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=EB85_50041014[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nWorkaround (retract search, reload or revisit the Torrents link - wrong text at first, but if you contract and then expand, the text will be fixed)\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=3D7A_50041014][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=3D7A_50041014[/img][/url] [url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=24CE_50041014][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=24CE_50041014[/img][/url]',129045,'2012-07-16 15:07:13'),(44217,5696,86439,'2012-07-16 14:47:38','Hes right, my warning does the same thing. The text \'4 weeks warning\' is a link that goes to a blank page. \n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/wiki.php?action=article&id=218\n\nIm guessing the details of the wiki isnt done yet? I completely missed that.\n\n\n\nI reported that torrent for a virus. (obviously there was none ...well I never actually tested it, or even attempted to dl it)',86439,'2012-07-16 14:50:24'),(44218,5608,103720,'2012-07-16 14:59:36','[quote=Clownius]Can we have a page that comes up if you try and log into emp.me with IE.\r\n\r\nIt says get a real browser if you want to use emp.me and offers links to download ff or chrome :laugh:  :laugh:  :mad:[/quote]\r\n\r\nCouldn\'t agree more! :hooray:\r\nFF is free, chrome is free, Opera is free. \r\nThere\'s absolutely no reason to be using IE anymore. \r\nOr is there? :hmmm: ',NULL,NULL),(44219,5608,86439,'2012-07-16 15:04:02','Dont want to open a new thread and its search related so I thought Ill pop this here. Its probably not an issue anyway, just for me.\n\nWhen I click advanced search, I get a search page so similar to the basic one (seems to add boolean help and \'File list\') its confusing. Once worked out its easy enough but could be clearer.\n\nMaybe the option to switch between basic/advanced should be near the search terms fields. And the heading just define where you currently are, as opposed to where you will go to if you click it. Either that or the title could be \'Advanced Filter\', and \'Basic Filter\' with the option to switch where it is. Seems unnecessarily confusing is all Im saying.\n\nAdvanced Search Page\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-E70F_50041086.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-E70F_50041086.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nBasic Search Page\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-94DC_50041086.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-94DC_50041086.jpg[/img][/url]\n\none more browse related\r\n\r\nWhen I open the browse page I see a list of torrents, with page range numbers, next, last, across the top as normal with the last page range being 51-100, \r\n\r\n1-50 | 51-100 | Next > Last >>\r\n\r\nwhen I click \'last\', I get the last page listed 1-50, 51-100, so here I will get to page range 50-100 but then the page number ranges now include 101-150, so im only on the next page range, not last.\r\n\r\n<< First < Prev | 1-50 | 51-100 | 101-150 | 151-200 | Next > Last >>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI just kept clicking last, and each time was taken to the second to last page range page ending like this.\r\n\r\n<< First < Prev | 1-50 | 51-100 | 101-150 | 151-200 | 201-250 | [b][u]251-300[/u][/b] | 301-350 | Next > Last >>\r\n\r\n\r\nI then clicked on page range 151-200, and the next screen appeared like this.\r\n\r\n<< First < Prev | 1-50 | 51-100 | 101-150 | [b][u]151-200[/u][/b] | 201-250 | Next > Last >>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nNot sure if bug, or just the source of the torrent list creating that event as each time I click last, I get an extra range of pages added to the options.',86439,'2012-07-16 15:19:28'),(44220,5608,129045,'2012-07-16 15:29:45','[quote=eimaimpala][quote=Clownius]Can we have a page that comes up if you try and log into emp.me with IE.\r\n\r\nIt says get a real browser if you want to use emp.me and offers links to download ff or chrome :laugh:  :laugh:  :mad:[/quote]\r\n\r\nCouldn\'t agree more! :hooray:\r\nFF is free, chrome is free, Opera is free. \r\nThere\'s absolutely no reason to be using IE anymore. \r\nOr is there? :hmmm:[/quote]\r\n\r\nIE is free and comes pre-installed with Windows :P\r\n\r\n[spoiler=EMP statistics]\r\n\r\n[img]http://chart.apis.google.com/chart?cht=p&chs=750x400&chf=bg,s,FFFFFF00&chco=8A00B8&chl=Windows%20%20(74.67%)|Mac%20OS%20X%20(14.67%)|iPhone%20(4.00%)|Ubuntu%20(3.33%)|Linux%20(2.67%)|Other%20(0.67%)&chd=e:vxJYCjCIBtAb&.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n[img]http://chart.apis.google.com/chart?cht=p&chs=750x400&chf=bg,s,FFFFFF00&chco=008AB8&chl=Firefox%20(39.33%)|Chrome%20(30.00%)|Internet%20Explorer%20(15.33%)|Safari%20(6.00%)|Opera%20(4.67%)|Safari%20Mobile%20(4.67%)&chd=e:ZKTMJzD1C.C.&.jpg[/img]\r\n[/spoiler]\r\n\r\n[quote=knickers]Dont want to open a new thread and its search related so I thought Ill pop this here.\r\n\r\n[spoiler=Its probably not an issue anyway, just for me.]\r\n\r\nWhen I click advanced search, I get a search page so similar to the basic one (seems to add boolean help and \'File list\') its confusing. Once worked out its easy enough but could be clearer.\r\n\r\nMaybe the option to switch between basic/advanced should be near the search terms fields. And the heading just define where you currently are, as opposed to where you will go to if you click it. Either that or the title could be \'Advanced Filter\', and \'Basic Filter\' with the option to switch where it is. Seems unnecessarily confusing is all Im saying.\r\n\r\nAdvanced Search Page\r\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-E70F_50041086.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-E70F_50041086.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nBasic Search Page\r\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-94DC_50041086.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-94DC_50041086.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n[/spoiler]\r\n\r\n[spoiler=one more browse related]\r\nWhen I open the browse page I see a list of torrents, with page range numbers, next, last, across the top as normal with the last page range being 51-100, \r\n\r\n1-50 | 51-100 | Next > Last >>\r\n\r\nwhen I click \'last\', I get the last page listed 1-50, 51-100, so here I will get to page range 50-100 but then the page number ranges now include 101-150, so im only on the next page range, not last.\r\n\r\n<< First < Prev | 1-50 | 51-100 | 101-150 | 151-200 | Next > Last >>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI just kept clicking last, and each time was taken to the second to last page range page ending like this.\r\n\r\n<< First < Prev | 1-50 | 51-100 | 101-150 | 151-200 | 201-250 | [b][u]251-300[/u][/b] | 301-350 | Next > Last >>\r\n\r\n\r\nI then clicked on page range 151-200, and the next screen appeared like this.\r\n\r\n<< First < Prev | 1-50 | 51-100 | 101-150 | [b][u]151-200[/u][/b] | 201-250 | Next > Last >>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nNot sure if bug, or just the source of the torrent list creating that event as each time I click last, I get an extra range of pages added to the options.\r\n[/spoiler]\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nBetter open a new thread under \"Suggestions\"\r\n\r\nAs for the browsing list, yes it seems like a bug, [b]Next[/b] and [b]Last[/b] [color=#FF0000][b]will always link to the same destination[/b][/color] :hmmm:  ([b]First[/b] and [b]Prev[/b] behaves correctly)\r\n\r\ne.g. If you\'re on page 1, both will send you to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?page=2 , [b]Last[/b] should actually send you to something like http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?page=last (just an example, the link doesn\'t actually work)\r\n\r\nOr have it like EMP.me and present the first and the last few result pages:\r\n\r\n[quote]1 - 25 | 26 - 50 | 51 - 75 | ... | 31726 - 31750 | 31751 - 31775 | 31776 - 31787[/quote]',129045,'2012-07-16 15:47:54'),(44221,5608,103720,'2012-07-16 15:44:13','Yes, it\'s free, but it\'s so buggy.... :laugh:\r\nWhy would someone drive a Lada Niva if he was granted access to the Batmobile? :wub:',NULL,NULL),(44222,5608,84499,'2012-07-16 16:17:24','\r\n\r\nknickers - actually that would be much better in its own thread :lol: \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=yamchan07bb][quote=mifune]I have made a change but I cant test it right now... there is about a 50% chance it is now working in IE  :bombie:[/quote]\r\n\r\nIt works... But the text is inverted. (Testing with IE 9.0)\r\n\r\nIt says \'Open Search Center\' when it\'s already expanded and \'Close Search Center\' when it\'s retracted.\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b] [b][i]Seems to be hit and miss[/i][/b] :hmmm:\r\n\r\n- If you go to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php , the search will be expanded, saying \"[b][i]Open Search Center[/i][/b]\", after you click on it to close, it\'ll say \"[b][i]Close Search Center[/i][/b]\".\r\n\r\n- While the search is expanded, Reloading the page or clicking again on \"Torrents\' at the top bar will not fix the text.\r\n\r\n- If you click on it to retract the search and then reload or visit it again by clicking on \"Torrents\", it\'ll display the correct text (incorrectly at first, but after you click on it to retract, the correct text will appear). [b][i]But it\'s \'temporary\'[/i][/b], as soon as you close the page and visit the Torrents page, it\'ll behave incorectly again.\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT2:[/i][/b]\r\n\r\nFirst visit (wrong text)\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=2F1F_50041014][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=2F1F_50041014[/img][/url] [url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=EB85_50041014][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=EB85_50041014[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nWorkaround (retract search, reload or revisit the Torrents link - wrong text at first, but if you contract and then expand, the text will be fixed)\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=3D7A_50041014][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=3D7A_50041014[/img][/url] [url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=24CE_50041014][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=24CE_50041014[/img][/url][/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nWhats happening is when you click on the button it sets it correctly, but the bit of code that is meant to read the cookie to find out your last state dosent fire in IE (  :argh: stupid proprietry loaddom events, stupid stupid IE  :banghead: )... \r\n\r\n\r\nbah, stupid gazelle coders too  :ras: I dont think that bit of js has ever worked with IE!\r\n\r\n\r\nI have been bashing my head against this for a while today and am not getting anywhere fast... I\'ll have to come back to this ie thing later.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44223,5697,84499,'2012-07-16 16:19:25','\r\nI fixed the interface niggle anyway.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44224,5696,84499,'2012-07-16 16:25:35','\r\n\r\nThe wiki system does not exist anymore.\r\n\r\nInstead we have articles :D\r\n\r\nI will try and hunt down where that text gets written.\r\n\r\n\r\nnote: If I forget its your own faults for not putting this in a bug thread  :borg: ',NULL,NULL),(44226,5608,86439,'2012-07-16 16:53:26','[quote=mifune]knickers - actually that would be much better in its own thread :lol: \n\n\n\n[/quote]\nDagnabbit. :laugh:\n\nI just dont want to clutter up the area with useless things. I though for example on the last page thing it was only that way due to something like the test site only using 100 torrents for test purposes and grabbing the rest off the running site when requested. Thus last page behaved like next page instead as it is never actually the last page it can find, only the last one it does find but always has another to load thus we see a new last page in the list each time I click it.\n\nMake sense? Yeah, probably not.',86439,'2012-07-16 17:14:53'),(44227,5708,129045,'2012-07-16 17:03:03','Just so no one forgets :P\r\n\r\n[quote][i]Your above torrent[/i] (link) was reported and has been deleted.\r\n\r\n Reason: The torrent was determined to be infected with a virus/trojan. In the future, please scan all potential uploads with an antivirus program such as AVG, Avast, or MS Security Essentials.\r\n [b]This has resulted in a [i][color=#FF0000]1 week warning[/color][/i] (link).[/b]\r\n\r\n Log Message: deleted torrent for the reason: Contains Virus. ( knickers test 3 )\r\n\r\n\r\n Report was handled by usillyboy.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\"1 week warning\" (or whatever number given) will link to http://empornium.mooo.com/wiki.php?action=article&id=218 (inexistent destination, blank page, no error given)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=knickers]Hes right, my warning does the same thing. The text \'4 weeks warning\' is a link that goes to a blank page. \r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/wiki.php?action=article&id=218\r\n\r\nIm guessing the details of the wiki isnt done yet? I completely missed that.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI reported that torrent for a virus. (obviously there was none ...well I never actually tested it, or even attempted to dl it)[/quote]\r\n[quote=mifune]The wiki system does not exist anymore.\r\n\r\nInstead we have articles :D\r\n\r\nI will try and hunt down where that text gets written.\r\n\r\n\r\nnote: If I forget its your own faults for not putting this in a bug thread  :borg:[/quote]',129045,'2012-07-16 17:03:51'),(44228,5709,86439,'2012-07-16 17:09:18','\n[mcom][b]NOT A BUG:[/b]  It\'s a way for the system to limit results based on user class.[/mcom]\n\n\nNOTE: \"1-50 | 51-100 | Next > Last >>\" is just highlighted from screen, copy (in full) and paste, youre seeing exactly what I see.\n\n\n\n\n\nWhen I open the browse page I see a list of torrents, with page range numbers, next, last, across the top as normal with the last page range being 51-100, \n\n1-50 | 51-100 | Next > Last >>\n\nThat is the default layout when i first visit the page. \n\n\n\nHowever, when I click \'last\', the browser (FF) navigates to the last page listed [b][u]51-100[/u][/b], but then the page number ranges now include 101-150, so Im only on the next page range, not last.\n\n\nThe layout now looks like this\n\n<< First < Prev | 1-50 | [b][u]51-100[/u][/b] | 101-150 |  Next > Last >>\n\nSo the last is never the last.\n\n\n\nFurther testing, I just kept clicking last a few more times, and each time was taken to the second to last page range ending like this.\n\n<< First < Prev | 1-50 | 51-100 | 101-150 | 151-200 | 201-250 | [b][u]251-300[/u][/b] | 301-350 | Next > Last >>\n\nNote, there is always one more range of pages added to the options. \n\n\n\nI then clicked on page range 151-200, and the next screen appeared like this.\n\n<< First < Prev | 1-50 | 51-100 | 101-150 | [b][u]151-200[/u][/b] | 201-250 | Next > Last >>\n\n301-350 has now disappeared from the selectable options, but 201-250 still exists as an option, while Im viewing page range 151-200\n\n\n\nThe reason I wasnt sure if it was a bug or not was due to the source of the torrents its indexing. I assume they arent all upped here on the test site, and some are just borrowed from the current main site on demand. Id hate to send someone puling their hair out looking for something that actually wasnt broken, and was perfectly normal just odd due to other circumstances.\n\n\nHope that makes sense.',1243,'2012-07-24 05:48:01'),(44229,5608,84499,'2012-07-16 17:11:14','\r\n\r\nI cannot reproduce the last page issue... for me it looks fine...  but now we are off-topic lol (and this site has its own database, thats not anything to do with it).\r\n\r\n\r\nthe only thing is if bugs are hidden away in threads that titles do not reflect them then we will lose them, with one bug per thread we have a fighting chance of catching them  :chase: ',NULL,NULL),(44230,5710,86439,'2012-07-16 17:12:17','When I click advanced search, I get a search window so similar to the basic one (seems to add boolean help and \'File list\') its confusing. Once worked out its easy enough but could be clearer.\r\n\r\n\r\nMaybe the option to switch between basic/advanced should be near the search terms fields (red ?). And the heading just define where you currently are, as opposed to where you will go to if you click it. Either that or the title could be \'Advanced Filter\', and \'Basic Filter\' with the option to switch where it is in smaller text. Seems unnecessarily confusing as is, is all Im saying.\r\n\r\nAdvanced Search Page\r\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-E70F_50041086.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-E70F_50041086.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nBasic Search Page\r\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-94DC_50041086.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-94DC_50041086.jpg[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(44232,5709,129045,'2012-07-16 17:20:47','[b][i]Confirmed here.[/i][/b] Same behavior across different browsers, so I have no idea why Mifune couldn\'t replicate it :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[quote=yamchan in the other thread]As for the browsing list, yes it seems like a bug, [b]Next[/b] and [b]Last[/b] [color=#FF0000][b]will always link to the same destination[/b][/color] :hmmm:  ([b]First[/b] and [b]Prev[/b] behaves correctly)\r\n\r\ne.g. If you\'re on page 1, both will send you to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?page=2 , [b]Last[/b] should actually send you to something like http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?page=last (just an example, the link doesn\'t actually work)\r\n\r\nOr have it like EMP.me and present the first and the last few result pages:\r\n\r\n[quote]1 - 25 | 26 - 50 | 51 - 75 | ... | 31726 - 31750 | 31751 - 31775 | 31776 - 31787[/quote][/quote]\r\n\r\nGo to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php and copy their links, you\'ll see that [b]Next[/b] and [b]Last[/b] both point to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?page=2 (if you were on page 3, both would point to page 4 and so forth and so on)\r\n\r\nAs for the range, I don\'t really understand what you tried to explain, but it\'ll be wider as the the number of pages go higher, see: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?page=17',NULL,NULL),(44234,5681,48010,'2012-07-16 17:24:41','[quote=yamchan07bb]OP updated.\r\n\r\n[quote=Dave]added request[/quote]\r\n\r\nI was thinking more in general terms, nothing too specific, just to see if the whole system is working properly. Try posting something easier and I\'ll try to fill :P[/quote]\r\n\r\ngive me a suggestion as to something you have and I\'ll do it',NULL,NULL),(44235,5694,48010,'2012-07-16 17:27:03','There was some talk about whether we need this or not - not sure a decision was made tho',48010,'2012-07-16 17:27:25'),(44236,5708,86439,'2012-07-16 17:27:25','Dmanit, I was off doing this too, now there two threads.',NULL,NULL),(44237,5679,48010,'2012-07-16 17:28:24','thanks for the slots - I\'ll start to play around with them tomorrow',NULL,NULL),(44238,5608,86439,'2012-07-16 17:32:13','[quote=mifune]I cannot reproduce the last page issue... for me it looks fine...  but now we a