it\'ll be wider as the the number of pages go higher, see: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?page=17[/quote]\r\n\r\nOn the main site, \r\n\r\n1 - 25 | 26 - 50 | 51 - 75 | ... | 31876 - 31900 | 31901 - 31925 | 31926 - 31937\r\nÂ« Prev      Next Â»\r\n\r\nis the default. Its what I get when I first look at the browse page, ellipsis included, with the and range of torrents already there. The absence of that ellipsis and the range of pages in the 10\'s of thousands led me to believe that maybe the test site was only looking at a limited number of torrents, but if requested could go to the main site and pull down some more.\r\n\r\nmifune (that other thread) said that the test site has its own db so its unlikely, but at the time, I did not know that. I just wanted to put a theory out there as to why, even if it was an uneducated guess. I didnt want to be responsible for someone looking for a fault, that didnt actually exist, it just seemed like one did. The lack of the ellipsis and the other end of the range available led me to believe it was looking at a limited db. Thus if I was correct (Im not), last and next would be the same in value (coincidentally, not intentional), I think.',NULL,NULL),(44242,5709,129045,'2012-07-16 17:43:40','Using Win7 here\r\n\r\nOpera, Chrome, Firefox and IE present the same behavior, it only goes up to page=20 (1000 torrents listed, not the 30000+ like current EMP.me)\r\n\r\nNo external stylesheet enabled.\r\n\r\nUbuntu with Firefox and Opera also presents the same probem.\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b] This is what I see, across all browsers (on page 18, [color=#FF6600]Last[/color] should be =last or page=20, but as you can see in the statusbar, it\'s showing page=19 when I hover the link)\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=446A_50043B97][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-446A_50043B97.jpg[/img][/url]',129045,'2012-07-16 18:09:06'),(44243,5709,86439,'2012-07-16 17:44:50','FF 12\r\nXP Pro\r\n\r\nI have no idea about style sheet. Ill a