u can use \n\n[code][url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2714]Your link text here[/url][/code]\n\nto get:\n[url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2714]Your link text here[/url]\n\nthe advantadge of using the /page.php format is that local links formatted like that will still work when we change to the proper url, whereas any links to [pre]http://empornium.mooo.com/[/pre] will be dead. (Not so important in these threads but very useful if you are writing text for an article).\n\n',84499,'2012-07-16 19:39:36'),(44275,5716,47234,'2012-07-16 19:38:07','Also needs a tag.......',NULL,NULL),(44276,5709,86439,'2012-07-16 19:38:36','Gimme a minute, Im having issues with the image host\n\n\n\n\n\nNot sure if this helps. but heres some screens\n\nFirst is default page (ie: when I first click browse from the forums)\n\n[URL=http://hotchyx.com/][IMG]http://hostingb.hotchyx.com/adult-image-hosting-20/699ScreenShot075.jpg[/IMG][/URL][URL=http://hotchyx.com/]Adult Image Hosting[/URL]\n\n\nThe next is same page with the code highlighted in the bottom left for \'last\' (note pointer on last) as mentioned by Ymanchan.\n\n[URL=http://hotchyx.com/][IMG]http://hostingb.hotchyx.com/adult-image-hosting-20/2679ScreenShot076.jpg[/IMG][/URL][URL=http://hotchyx.com/]Adult Image Hosting[/URL]\n\n\nThe next is as above, except \'next\' is highlighted\n\n[URL=http://hotchyx.com/][IMG]http://hostingb.hotchyx.com/adult-image-hosting-20/3613ScreenShot077.jpg[/IMG][/URL][URL=http://hotchyx.com/]Adult Image Hosting[/URL]\n\n\nthe next one is after clicking \"last\" 6 times, again last is highlighted\n\n[URL=http://hotchyx.com/][IMG]http://hostingb.hotchyx.com/adult-image-hosting-20/831ScreenShot079.jpg[/IMG][/URL][URL=http://hotchyx.com/]Adult Image Hosting[/URL]\n\n\nsame again, \'next\' highlighted\n\n[URL=http://hotchyx.com/][IMG]http://hostingb.hotchyx.com/adult-image-hosting-20/2313ScreenShot080.jpg[/IMG][/URL][URL=http://hotchyx.com/]Adult Image Hosting[/URL]\n\n \n\n\n',86439,'2012-07-16 19:49:19'),(44278,5703,84499,'2012-07-16 19:48:15','[quote=knickers]Sometimes it helps to lay out.\r\n\r\nAre we talking forum or torrents?\r\n\r\nDoesnt matter, Id use it occasionally in both.[/quote]\r\n\r\nForums, comments, posts and articles all use the same bbcode engine.\r\n\r\n[quote=borkb0rkbork]I\'ve always wanted to be able to tab and multispace in my posts, but I\'ve just dealt with not being able to do it in phpbb and now here. If it\'s possible, I\'d like it, I\'d use it. If it\'s a real pain in the ass, it\'s probably not worth it.  :evilbunny:[/quote]\r\n\r\nOkay I changed it so it preserves (most) whitespace, lets see if anyone hates it                                                             :worm: \r\n',NULL,NULL),(44279,5709,184595,'2012-07-16 19:57:48','\nYep from this account I get the same results as knickers et all...\n\n\n:wtfsign: \n\n\nIt looks like the sphinx search behaves differently for users and staff... \n\nLanz are you there? :D\n\n:backingout: ',84499,'2012-07-16 20:00:45'),(44280,5718,86439,'2012-07-16 20:01:23','How many you need, Ive just sent about 10. From forums, not torrents, you want torrent reports?',NULL,NULL),(44281,5719,48010,'2012-07-16 20:01:27','seems we can only resolve them - no option to leave it for discussion ?\n\nsame as emp.me and no way to edit them ?\n\ncan someone check if I\'m missing something\n\nTIA Dave\n\nEDIT what is the update time ?\n\nI just cleared all of knickers reports but not showing in reports that I cleraed any of them\n\nlast resolved in 24 hours only shows usb - do I have to wait 24 hours for it to update ?',48010,'2012-07-16 21:25:19'),(44282,5718,48010,'2012-07-16 20:03:19','[quote=knickers]How many you need, Ive just sent about 10. From forums, not torrents, you want torrent reports?[/quote]\r\n\r\nyes I want all of them',NULL,NULL),(44283,5720,48010,'2012-07-16 20:04:36','please start to contact staff\r\n\r\nagian it can be bullshit but start to hassle us \r\n\r\n@knickers - not too many mate please',NULL,NULL),(44284,5716,48010,'2012-07-16 20:06:01','[quote=Clownius]Also needs a tag.......[/quote]\r\nnice addition - I didn\'t get that far',NULL,NULL),(44285,5714,48010,'2012-07-16 20:14:43','you got it mifune\n\nlike you I type url tags and the same if I want to add words to it\n\njust confused me a bit as the url didn\'t work \n\n[quote=mifune]And... should I carry on :hmmm: fuck it... :D If you want to be real fancy for local links you can use\n[b][url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2714]Your link text here[/url][/b] [/quote]\n\nI know that already how to add text to the link just seems confusing to those not up on BB code who only add the http and no title\n\nyou missed the point but you got it now :wink: :thumbsup:',48010,'2012-07-16 20:16:34'),(44286,5716,84499,'2012-07-16 20:17:14','\r\nWhat do you think the desired behaviour should be?\r\n\r\nI guess if you are specifying a specific file tags might be superfluous from the requesters/fillers POV, but then if someone is later searching for requests of that specific girl/fetish/whatever wouldnt it be useful to have them tagged properly?\r\n\r\nCategories are subjective but still shouldnt stuff be in a category just for the purposes of searching, so if someone wants to look at all requests in a certain category they dont have to remember to check the \'unspecified\' category too?',NULL,NULL),(44287,5720,86439,'2012-07-16 20:21:03','Now you tell me, I just sent about 20 reports from forums and same from torrents.',NULL,NULL),(44288,5716,48010,'2012-07-16 20:24:17','we are talking about requests not searches - so why do need to put a category or tags?\r\n\r\nyou may never get what you want - example I want an asian lesbian scene so I have to choose one category not both - limits my chances of getting it \r\n\r\nkeep it like emp.me - just request what you want without category but tags may or not be useful \r\n',NULL,NULL),(44289,5716,84499,'2012-07-16 20:28:00','\nbecause requests are searchable...\n\n\nbut yeah, I see your point. What if you didnt have to strictly match the category when filling a request?',84499,'2012-07-16 20:30:48'),(44290,5716,129045,'2012-07-16 20:32:41','Dave, it\'s for organization \\ searching purposes, which is understandable.\r\n\r\nThe only thing that bothers me, as I said in that post: Doesn\'t matter if the content matches, the Request system will not accept it if it\'s not in the same category.\r\n\r\nSo ultimately the Request will dictate the category of the torrent you upload to fill it, even if it doesn\'t seem optimal (e.g. Latina does Anal and some fetish, set under \"Straight\")\r\n\r\nEDIT: Oh I\'m slow.',129045,'2012-07-16 20:34:06'),(44291,5703,70679,'2012-07-16 20:56:40','I  :love: it!!   :cheer: \r\n\r\nBut is not WYSIWYG... I had to move around the second line on my forum list column suggestion to get the proper alignment with the line above....\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2702 ',NULL,NULL),(44292,5716,48010,'2012-07-16 21:13:27','[quote=mifune]because requests are searchable...\n\n\nbut yeah, I see your point. What if you didnt have to strictly match the category when filling a request?[/quote]\nthat\'s an improvement\n\n@mifune while testing I am trying to wear the dunce cap not my staff one - I am trying to find the stuff the rank and file will see and not see it from my staff perspective (except for staff tests of course)',48010,'2012-07-16 21:20:28'),(44293,5703,84499,'2012-07-16 21:19:04','\r\n\r\nit still trims the first space in a line, but to change that would be extremely not straightforward... I can live with it as is  :pythfoot: ',NULL,NULL),(44294,5681,129045,'2012-07-16 23:32:30','[s]Somebody nuked all the requests?[/s]\r\n\r\nNevermind, probably maintenance or something :hmmm:\r\nThe torrents list is also gone.',129045,'2012-07-16 23:44:18'),(44295,5702,1243,'2012-07-17 03:00:14','use a table instead.',NULL,NULL),(44296,5702,70679,'2012-07-17 03:43:12','nah too complicated sorry but that was not the purpose of this post... or... maybe I did not explain myself clearly Lanyz? It was meant as a suggestion for this:\n\n[img]http://img62.imageshack.us/img62/9227/snap98.jpg[/img]\n',70679,'2012-07-17 03:49:18'),(44297,5608,1366,'2012-07-17 03:58:08','[size=2]Looks like the Search Center is working fine for me now. What was all the wining about? I knew you guys could fix it! Great Job!!![/size]',NULL,NULL),(44298,5608,84499,'2012-07-17 04:05:23','\nokay cool, I added a very clunky workaround... but if it works it works  :gjob: ',84499,'2012-07-17 04:05:38'),(44299,5668,167879,'2012-07-17 04:47:51','No it doesn\'t. I manually updated a couple times too.',NULL,NULL),(44300,5681,47234,'2012-07-17 06:47:18','The server this is on has crashed badly at least twice today :banghead: ... Hard lockup both times....  Required a manual reboot.  I saw the emails about it when i got home just them....\r\n\r\nOVH has detected and kickstarted it twice that is looking at the graphs i think its had more issues than just that :sigh:  I think we got a dodgy server... If it continues to crash i may harass OVH for a server swap.',NULL,NULL),(44301,5702,1243,'2012-07-17 07:52:37','Perhaps I could have explained it better too. What I meant was that using white spaces to form nice columns using a font with variable character width is futile. It will also most likely not look the same on different operating systems either since they usually do not share exactly the same fonts. So for stuff like that, tables are really the only viable option.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44302,5707,1507,'2012-07-17 08:10:50',':laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]Well, the added warning got tacked on for something he was going to do, and so it is a deterrent...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44303,5676,89443,'2012-07-17 09:03:30','Nice work!',NULL,NULL),(44304,5702,70679,'2012-07-17 09:04:50','still you miss the point of THIS thread my dear.... sigh....',NULL,NULL),(44305,5676,48010,'2012-07-17 09:36:41','[quote=mifune][quote=Dave]I understand the community tagging thing and mifune I\'m not anti tags but I noticed the following\r\n\r\nOn my upload I didn\'t get notified of tags added or voted up/down (and this was tested) - not a big deal but for me but for some it might be\r\n\r\non the other hand I got no notification of tag changes so do we need to keep telling uploaders of tag changes by PM ? I think this will annoy a lot of them but at the end of the day the uploader sets the tags and others change them. I don\'t really like that.\r\n\r\nI like the current emp.me system where members politely request tags in a comment[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nThe way I see it is this: on this site tags are not part of your presentation. Tags are just an aid to searching - in fact they are nothing more than searchable keywords. The uploader may or may not add the correct tags, or may only add a couple - when for effective searching it could do with a few more. The community tagging system is a way of trying to get appropriate and useful tags on every torrent without draconian tag rules for uploaders and without having staff whos only job is to tag stuff (a solution I have seen on other sites).\r\n\r\nSo I see no reason for uploaders to be defensive about the tags on their uploads changing. Tags are not for uploaders, they are for pervs trying to find stuff. Don\'t be upset if your tags change, be glad that more pervs can find your upload now. \r\n\r\nAs far as telling uploaders of tag changes by PM... I dunno I have changed a few tags on emp.me and I never PM\'d anyone :lol: If that upset anybody then... I dunno maybe they shouldnt be so butthurt when their crappy tags get corrected?? Technically we could have notifications sent to the uploader but I dont like the idea, firstly it will generate a large volume of PM traffic saying very little - internal junkmail imo - and secondly it gives credence to this idea that the uploader has some ownership of the tags for their upload, when really they dont, they just set the initial state but then the tags belong to the tracker community - which is as it should be in my eyes.[/quote]\r\nthanks for the explanation and no objections from me with that\r\n\r\nI like the idea of USB being tag monitor tho :grin:',NULL,NULL),(44306,5681,48010,'2012-07-17 09:47:04','[quote=Clownius]The server this is on has crashed badly at least twice today :banghead: ... Hard lockup both times....  Required a manual reboot.  I saw the emails about it when i got home just them....\r\n\r\nOVH has detected and kickstarted it twice that is looking at the graphs i think its had more issues than just that :sigh:  I think we got a dodgy server... If it continues to crash i may harass OVH for a server swap.[/quote]\r\n\r\nanything in the logs to give so idea why it crashed - what was the lastthing it was trying to do?\r\n\r\nI doubt we are overloading the server\r\n\r\nYears ago I saw a log file that kept appending the same error - the log file became so obscenely large that it kept crashing the server - check free space and log file sizes just in case',NULL,NULL),(44309,5721,48010,'2012-07-17 10:01:12','under my nick I see a way to view comments but not forum posts\r\n\r\nI messed around with the forum search and got a list using my nick in the body search\r\n\r\nIf I didn\'t put my name in the post it\'s not on the list\r\n\r\nsometimes I forget where I post and want to check for updates - yes I know I could subscribe but I really don\'t want to do that on every post I think I may need to check later\r\n\r\nI would like to see my posts and threads marked as new (like on other sites)\r\n\r\nI tried to hack myposts in the url but no joy',NULL,NULL),(44310,5681,47234,'2012-07-17 10:15:37','It sounds hardware related as it stopped responding to pings and even when OVH plugged the crash cart into it they got no response.  They report basically pulling the power to it and waiting to restart it.\r\n\r\nLanz may be able to check the logs though before i blow OVH up too badly :lol:\r\n\r\n\r\nBut yeah its got a nasty habit of rebooting itself randomly too.  That doesnt sound like Ubuntu thats for sure.  Even my desktops have uptimes in the weeks and months....\r\n\r\nIm thinking something is a bit dodgy.  PSU maybe or RAM?  Worst case its the mobo.\r\n\r\nNice triple post btw ;)',NULL,NULL),(44311,5681,48010,'2012-07-17 10:21:10','sorry about the dupes - connection was up and down - cleared them now',NULL,NULL),(44312,5703,70679,'2012-07-17 11:07:03','OK Lanz THIS is the place... LOL\r\n\r\nnow yes indeed using multiple space is a stupid way to align columns. One should ALWAYS use tabulators. But when they are not available... then multiple spaces can do, not as good of course. But it appears that tabulators cannot be implemented. ',NULL,NULL),(44313,5722,89443,'2012-07-17 11:42:56','none of the torrents are loading screens/pictures? Is this on purpose?\r\n\r\nAlso, what\'s up with the old site?',NULL,NULL),(44314,5722,48010,'2012-07-17 11:54:27','[quote=pistonsfan]none of the torrents are loading screens/pictures? Is this on purpose?\r\n\r\nAlso, what\'s up with the old site?[/quote]\r\nemp.me has been down for the last few hours\r\n\r\nxxxfreeimage is hosted on the same server so it is down too (I tried to get to both and no joy)',NULL,NULL),(44315,5722,86439,'2012-07-17 11:59:43','Are you looking at torrents hosted at freeimage? If you are, if you click the links for the screens they dont load either.\n\nThe main site appears down, has been for some time. I was on there 2 or so hours ago and it just timed out. Just tried a few minutes ago, same thing.\n\nI was also having issues with freeimage yesterday so maybe they are related.\n\n\n\nI just looked at this torrent using imgbox as its host, pics loaded fine.\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35141\n\n\nMaybe we killed it with the tug o war.\n\n\n\nDamn ninjas. Wait ...5 minute