end here http://empornium.mooo.com/userhistory.php?action=posts&userid=48010\r\n\r\nClick on \"Show all posts\" to view them and then you have the option to click on \"Show all posts (grouped)\", this will show only the thread titles.\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=5247_5005590A][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-5247_5005590A.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nEDIT: Now I\'m confused, Search works fine here...\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=search&search=&type=body&user=dave\r\n\r\nIgnore \"Search for\" and use the \"Username\" box instead. Selecting \"Post bodies\" should show all your posts :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=4F83_50055F0A][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-4F83_50055F0A.jpg[/img][/url]',129045,'2012-07-17 14:56:33'),(44321,5703,84499,'2012-07-17 14:42:15','\r\nIF you want aligned columns use a table\r\n\r\n[align=center][b][size=2]\r\n[table=nball]\r\n[tr] [td]  t  [/td][td] [/td][td]     [/td][td]     [/td][/tr]\r\n[tr] [td]  a  [/td][td] [/td][td]     [/td][td]     [/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]  b  [/td][td] [/td][td]  r   [/td][td]     [/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]  l  [/td][td]     [/td][td]  e   [/td][td]     [/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]  e  [/td][td]  a  [/td][td]  a   [/td][td]     [/td]][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]  s  [/td][td]  l  [/td][td]  l  [/td][td]  g   [/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]     [/td][td]  i  [/td][td]     [/td][td]  o   [/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]     [/td][td]  g  [/td][td]     [/td][td]  o   [/td][/tr]\r\n[tr][td]     [/td][td]  n  [/td][td]     [/td][td]  d   [/td][/tr][/table][/size][/b][/align]\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44322,5702,84499,'2012-07-17 14:54:57','\r\n\r\nI think what barumba is suggesting is that we add number of views to and re-order the columns displayed on the forums pages. Instead of it showing \'Latest (has topic and last poster in it) - Replies - Author\' he wants it to be \'Topic - Author - Views - Replies - Last Post\'.',NULL,NULL),(44323,5721,48010,'2012-07-17 14:55:53','[quote=yamchan07bb]Got to your Profile http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=48010 > Check the Community box (right side, bottom) > Forum Posts: xxxx [color=#FF0000]View[/color] < Click , you\'ll end here http://empornium.mooo.com/userhistory.php?action=posts&userid=48010\n\nClick on \"Show all posts\" to view them and then you have the option to click on \"Show all posts (grouped)\", this will show only the thread titles.\n\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=5247_5005590A][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-5247_5005590A.jpg[/img][/url][/quote]\n\nthanks for that - EDIT  it doesnt work\n\nhowever it is not up to date and probably not the easiest way to do it too\nas I said before I am wearing the dunce cap - trying to represent the basic (dumb) user on the site',48010,'2012-07-17 15:38:04'),(44324,5719,48010,'2012-07-17 14:58:55','I closed mifunes report - again no option as to why I did that\r\n\r\nthis needs more work ?',NULL,NULL),(44325,5721,129045,'2012-07-17 15:03:46','Looks up to date to me  :confused: ',NULL,NULL),(44326,5721,84499,'2012-07-17 15:27:34','\r\n\r\n\r\nsubscriptions (from your drop down menu under your name) --> show all posts \r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adgC9TH9.png[/img]\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/advG19pC.png[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\nis a quicker way of getting to the same place. I dont know what you mean by its not up to date... it should be totally up to date, it is for me.\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44327,5721,48010,'2012-07-17 15:40:11','[quote=yamchan07bb]Looks up to date to me  :confused:[/quote]\n\ni dont see it up to date !\n\n@mifune I said I dont want to subscribe to every forum thread i post in - i just want to see my posts in a link or drop down\n\nsorry if i am being an asshole but others will report the same later for sure - we all have our own habits and that\'s one of mine on other sites\n\nEdIT added screens \n\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=7CB4_50056CA3][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=7CB4_50056CA3[/img][/url]\n\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=D7F1_50056CA3][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=D7F1_50056CA3[/img][/url]',48010,'2012-07-17 15:47:43'),(44328,5719,84499,'2012-07-17 15:56:01','\r\n\r\nAh I see... you havent found the torrents reports. Gazelle has two seperate reports systems; \r\n\r\n1) A VERY simple reports system that only allows you to resolve reports about users/comments/posts/anything you can report that is not a torrent. \r\n2) A very sophisticated (and complicated when you have never used it before) torrents reporting system, that allows you to \'grab\' reports and assign them to yourself, gives you a bunch of automated options for dealing with it so you just check the options and press the button and it carries out the actions specificed and is very spiffy.\r\n\r\nI did post somewhere recently that the reports interface was not the easiest to understand!\r\n\r\nHere is an abbreviated guide to the torrents reports section. (called reportsv2 by gazelle):\r\n\r\n[b]When you click on the torrent reports number in the header you go to the Reportsv2->Views page, this gives a summary of what reports are waiting to be dealt with plus some stats on who has dealt with what[/b]\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/abhmbfap.png[/img]\r\n\r\n[b]The Reportsv2->Assign Page is where staff can \'grab\' reports. This takes reports out of the unassigned list, so if you grab them deal with them! (You can give back reports to put them back in the unassigned list too).[/b]\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/abek2AzK.png[/img]\r\n\r\n[b]The Reportsv2->Unassigned Reports Page is all the unassigned reports, you can deal with reports here but DONT - grab them instead that way there will be no collisions of 2 staff dealing with the same report!\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adrHWzEt.png[/img][bg=lightgrey,100%][bg=white,97%] If the report pictured above were to be resolved as is :\r\n[*]The Torrent WOULD be deleted\r\n[*]The uploader would NOT be warned\r\n[*]The uploaders uploading rights would NOT be disabled\r\n[*]The reporter WOULD be paid the standard bounty\r\n[*]A Standard PM WOULD be sent to the uploader\r\n[*]A Standard PM WOULD be sent to the reporter (as the bounty was paid)[/bg] [/bg][/b]\r\n\r\nOnce you have grabbed a report you can deal with it. To view/deal with reports you have grabbed click on the Reportsv2->Mine Page. Old (dealt with) reports are on the Reportsv2->Old Page.\r\n\r\nAt some point I or someone else should write a guide to dealing with torrents reports... but basically when you press resolve (or multi-resolve be careful!) each report automatically carries out whatever actions are specified on the form. These actions can be warnings, deleting torrents, PM\'s sent to the uploader, bonus payments to the reporter, lots of serious stuff can be carried out at the press of a button so be sure what you are doing!\r\n\r\nThe advantadge to all this is that once you have got the hang of the system you can deal with torrent reports very quickly, and with standardised replies and actions etc.\r\n\r\nRe: the other reports. Yes, they are very very simple... perhaps too simple? :hmmm: I wonder if we could do something clever and make the other reports (non torrents reports) mesh with the staff messaging system, if those reports were instead staff messages we would have a much better system to deal with them which is hooked up to the message templates etc.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44329,5721,84499,'2012-07-17 16:11:33','\r\n\r\nBut you are using the forum search!! Thats a seperate thing... but as an aside - when I use forum search to seach for posts by you I seem to get all of your posts, maybe there is a lag for really new ones, I will test it some more. But thats a seperate issue! forget about the forum search now.\r\n\r\n \r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adgC9TH9.png[/img]\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/advG19pC.png[/img]\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\nBecause I am talking about your post history. To get to your post history click on subscriptions (as pictured) - YES! I know you havent subscribed to all your posts... thats okay, bear with me! Now once you are in your subscriptions you can click on \"Show All Posts\" and you get your COMPLETE post history, not just subscriptions.\r\n\r\nYou can also get to the same place following the links in your user page that Yamchan described:\r\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-5247_5005590A.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\nClick on Forum Posts-\'View\' to get there from your user page. (This box is on the right hand side under the other boxes)\r\n\r\n I was just showing a way of getting to the same place from the drop down menu.',NULL,NULL),(44330,5721,129045,'2012-07-17 16:12:00','This is what I see, searching \"Post bodies\" and using your username:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=0D7E_500571A6][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=0D7E_500571A6[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nOdd :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[i][b]EDIT:[/b][/i] Even more odd, [b][i]mifune[/i][/b], are you on the right page?\r\n\r\nWhen I visit \'Subscriptions\'. I get to the subscribed threads list (empty as of now) so I need to click on \"Go to post history\" in order to see that screen you posted. Same thing with clicking on \"Comments\", I still need to click on \"Go to post history\".\r\n\r\nIn other words, it\'s quicker, but Subscriptions does not send you directly to http://empornium.mooo.com/userhistory.php?action=posts',129045,'2012-07-17 16:19:24'),(44331,5721,84499,'2012-07-17 16:21:06','\r\n\r\nPerhaps we should have a link saying \'Post History\' in the drop down menu? \r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\nThere is a tension between having too many junk links in that drop down that no-one will ever use, and needing places to put links to stuff...\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44332,5681,184595,'2012-07-17 16:24:48','test',NULL,NULL),(44333,5721,84499,'2012-07-17 16:27:50','[quote=yamchan07bb]This is what I see, searching \"Post bodies\" and using your username:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=0D7E_500571A6][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=0D7E_500571A6[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nOdd :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[i][b]EDIT:[/b][/i] Even more odd, [b][i]mifune[/i][/b], are you on the right page?\r\n\r\nWhen I visit \'Subscriptions\'. I get to the subscribed threads list (empty as of now) so I need to click on \"Go to post history\" in order to see that screen you posted. Same thing with clicking on \"Comments\", I still need to click on \"Go to post history\".\r\n\r\nIn other words, it\'s quicker, but Subscriptions does not send you directly to http://empornium.mooo.com/userhistory.php?action=posts[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nBah you are right, but it gets you to the right place.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44334,5702,70679,'2012-07-17 16:32:15','[size=10][color=#FF0000][b]YES![/b][/color][/size]',NULL,NULL),(44335,5721,129045,'2012-07-17 16:45:04','[quote=mifune]Perhaps we should have a link saying \'Post History\' in the drop down menu? \r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\nThere is a tension between having too many junk links in that drop down that no-one will ever use, and needing places to put links to stuff...[/quote]\r\n\r\nThe menu lenght is only a problem on Opera, as the spacing is all fucked up, so it ends occupying over half the screen height here :\\\r\n\r\nI guess, [b]Bonus[/b] and [b]Sandbox[/b] could find a home in plain sight, like in the same line as Upload, Donate, Settings and Logout :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(44336,5721,86439,'2012-07-17 16:51:37','Can a sub menu pop out off that menu item (subscriptions)? Give it a better heading because if I was looking for my post history I would probably not look in subscriptions if I dont subscribe to threads.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44337,5719,48010,'2012-07-17 17:28:59','ok I\'ll play with this\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44338,5721,48010,'2012-07-17 17:33:10','oh shit what have I done now :grin:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44339,5703,70679,'2012-07-17 19:01:13','ok then.... still think is overkill and too complicated for the average user but I understand that implementing tabulators would be VERY complicated an