:fiesta: \r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b] oops typo',129045,'2012-07-26 22:53:49'),(44371,5655,84499,'2012-07-18 21:04:18','\r\n\r\nhaha yeah I was just checking something out..\r\n\r\nI will have a go at adding a bunch of synomyns in the next few days, I am just tweaking the interface for adding them to speed up the work a bit!',NULL,NULL),(44372,5725,84499,'2012-07-18 21:23:33','\r\n\r\nCurrently the auto-delete function is switched off, so it can time them out and nothing happens. For staff if you go to the torrent\'s detail page you can view the staff review logs to see who marked it as \'delete\' and why, and if the user has responded or not etc.',NULL,NULL),(44373,5655,48010,'2012-07-18 21:31:38','[quote=mifune]haha yeah I was just checking something out..\n\nI will have a go at adding a bunch of synomyns in the next few days, I am just tweaking the interface for adding them to speed up the work a bit![/quote]\ngive me some main tags and i can work on synonyms to help you\n\nor make a post and let everyone do the work :grin:',48010,'2012-07-18 21:32:16'),(44374,5725,48010,'2012-07-18 21:37:36','[quote=mifune]Currently the auto-delete function is switched off, so it can time them out and nothing happens. For staff if you go to the torrent\'s detail page you can view the staff review logs to see who marked it as \'delete\' and why, and if the user has responded or not etc.[/quote]\r\n\r\nok see that\r\n\r\nwhen are we going to test auto delete ? all we need to do is put up some torrents and leave them unseeded\r\n\r\nis that low priority and an overload on what you are doing now ? (I mean that respectfully not sarcastically)',NULL,NULL),(44375,5655,6203,'2012-07-18 21:44:04','i mailed mifune a list of some suggestions i worked at.',NULL,NULL),(44376,5727,70679,'2012-07-18 22:46:22','I think that it would be useful to add to the uploader name also his level. If not directly by mouse hover on both name and the title.\r\n\r\nThis can give information about the reliability of the upload.',NULL,NULL),(44377,5725,84499,'2012-07-19 00:06:37','\r\n\r\nseeded status does not directly affect the torrents review system (marked for deletion). There is a seperate thing in the scheduler for unseeded torrents, it sends a pm to the uploader warning them and then deletes sometime afterwards. The marked for deletion status that gives the pink bar is only from staff setting it to \'marked for deletion\' via the staff review system.\r\n\r\nTo test the auto-delete for the torrents review system we just need some torrents that we can delete :smile1:\r\n\r\nYou can change the options here: (staff only!) [url=/tools.php?action=marked_for_deletion]Marked for Deletion Manager[/url] to change the time allowed for the user to fix it and to switch the auto deleter on and off (and to see a summary of torrents that are currently warned and how long they have etc.) If a staff uploads a torrent they can be both warnee and warner, but it would be a good idea to test it thoroughly in more realistic scenarios (ie. the uploader is not a staff/the reviewer).',NULL,NULL),(44378,5725,129045,'2012-07-19 00:12:32','So you guys need a target? A shitty torrent? Well then, this one can be sacrificed for the cause: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35150',NULL,NULL),(44379,5655,84499,'2012-07-19 01:10:48','\r\n\r\nWe can expand the list hexen has already done ready for when we switch, but there isnt much point entering more than we need too to test the synomyn system as the process will have to be repeated when we reimport the existing data from emp.me. I doubt there is a good way round this, the process of turning a tag into a synomyn changes the tag data both in the torrent data and in seperate tag data tables, but those tables dont exist until the torrents are imported, and I think we will have to reimport all the user and torrent data fresh (some things like articles we can keep because they are new bits of data unrelated to the stuff we are importing).',NULL,NULL),(44380,5683,84499,'2012-07-19 04:41:45','\r\nAdded :evilbunny: ',NULL,NULL),(44381,5724,47234,'2012-07-19 05:50:59','Wow you work fast Mifune.  Soon you will fix the bugs before we get around to reporting them :lol:',NULL,NULL),(44382,5686,1507,'2012-07-19 06:40:05',' :slap: ',NULL,NULL),(44383,5721,1507,'2012-07-19 06:44:03',':chase:\r\n\r\n[b]Nice job with that fix mifune...   :gjob: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(44384,5666,1507,'2012-07-19 07:12:48',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]I\'ve just noticed that after I made a search on the browse page, the search term never clears when I delete the term and click filter...  It will clear and show all of the new torrents and act normally, but when I return again, the search term will display only what was last searched for even tho\' I had cleared it out....\r\n\r\nMy example is:\r\n\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adozqgVp.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/acpSDapr.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adxZFCUR.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44385,5729,47234,'2012-07-19 08:21:55','I couldnt work out how to edit this page you have to agree to before the IRC page loads.  But can we have something big and bold saying we dont have people watching IRC 24/7 and our response time may be more than the 2 minutes (or less) most people seem to wait *sigh*',NULL,NULL),(44386,5666,86439,'2012-07-19 08:35:32','Your cache maybe?\r\n\r\nI just tried same thing, it was cleared. I searched for porcupine (and got one hit  WTF), then cleared the term, hit filter and got full list again. I then closed the search centre, reopened it and it was still clear, I closed the browse page, then reopened browse, still clear.\r\n\r\nIs that what you did?\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-10B3_5007AA24.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-10B3_5007AA24.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44387,5666,129045,'2012-07-19 12:44:16','Bug bug bug bug : http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2666\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44388,5729,70679,'2012-07-19 14:29:33','I second that as lotsa plebs do not seem in clear with the IRC concept. double *sigh*\r\n\r\nIDLE is the name of the game.',NULL,NULL),(44389,5730,6203,'2012-07-19 15:20:28','this is not really a bug, but normally features like the notification filters have a max. limit on other sites. sometimes this could be a security issue, when an asshole trying to create unlimited filters which causes senseless server load. :D',NULL,NULL),(44390,5731,84499,'2012-07-19 17:17:58','\r\nRandom snag fixes: (please test)\r\n\r\n[*]Block PM\'s - implemented allow PM\'s options as per emp.me\r\n[*]Staff Messages - added some extra info to the view conversation page so its easier to tell who initiated (user or staff) and made it so users can only resolve conversations they initiated.\r\n[*]Logs should now correctly show as red when it is a delete log (was showing them as blue if it was a torrent delete log)\r\n[*]Added a check on entering tags to strip dots from the start and end.\r\n[*]staff only: Added Groups link for staff tools, staff can access groups and use the stuff there.\r\n[*]staff only: Made a few changes to synomyns to make the interface a bit more bulletproof.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44391,5729,129045,'2012-07-19 17:34:38','Kind of related to the topic...\r\n\r\n[quote]/mode nickname +x[/quote]\r\n\r\nDoes this thing work on the #empornium channel? Should I activate it?\r\n\r\nXChat will show my nick+ip everytime I join a room, but Opera never showed it... :hmmm:',129045,'2012-07-19 17:38:32'),(44392,5729,70679,'2012-07-19 18:13:43','nope efnet is a bitch when it comes to anonymity so no IP masking and one can locate you in a second.\n\nOnly way is to use an IRC proxy (normal HTTP ones do not work) again a bitch. I use kproxy but is a pay service and you need few tricks to get it to work properly.\n\nTor is also rejected from efnet servers, or you can use a buoncer but need to have, run, find one.',70679,'2012-07-19 18:16:22'),(44393,5729,129045,'2012-07-19 18:29:54','Well, shit. Thanks for the info.\r\n\r\nNow I remember, it was you who posted this thread: http://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=2464\r\n\r\n[quote=borkb0rkbork][b]I was told.....\r\n\r\nThat when the new site goes live, host-masking will be implemented for the IRC, along with some other privacy features we currently don\'t really need, but which would be nice.[/b][/quote]\r\n\r\nIs this still in the plans? :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(44394,5729,70679,'2012-07-19 18:34:06','not if we keep using efnet, yes if we move to a private irc server. But I am not privy of the internal plan.\r\n\r\nHeck I did run at some point an XBNC on my seedbox and promptly efnet blacklisted me and had to bet them to whitelist me back.... but then prefer to use a proxy.',NULL,NULL),(44395,5670,129045,'2012-07-19 19:11:22','Ok, mifune added the PM notifications for comments received. Dave, did you receive one?\r\n\r\nOr please, post a comment in one of those torrents:\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35152\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35150\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35141\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b] [color=#009900]Working![/color], thanks Hexen for dropping the comment.',129045,'2012-07-19 19:25:35'),(44396,5683,129045,'2012-07-19 19:17:01','Working, now it ignores the uploader own comments, so that\'s extra nice :)',NULL,NULL),(44397,5676,6203,'2012-07-19 19:23:40','[quote=mifune][quote=Dave]I understand the community tagging thing and mifune I\'m not anti tags but I noticed the following\r\n\r\nOn my upload I didn\'t get notified of tags added or voted up/down (and this was tested) - not a big deal but for me but for some it might be\r\n\r\non the other hand I got no notification of tag changes so do we need to keep telling uploaders of tag changes by PM ? I think this will annoy a lot of them but at the end of the day the uploader sets the tags and others change them. I don\'t really like that.\r\n\r\nI like the current emp.me system where members politely request tags in a comment[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nThe way I see it is this: on this site tags are not part of your presentation. Tags are just an aid to searching - in fact they are nothing more than searchable keywords. The uploader may or may not add the correct tags, or may only add a couple - when for effective searching it could do with a few more. The community tagging system is a way of trying to get appropriate and useful tags on every torrent without draconian tag rules for uploaders and without having staff whos only job is to tag stuff (a solution I have seen on other sites).\r\n\r\nSo I see no reason for uploaders to be defensive about the tags on their uploads changing. Tags are not for uploaders, they are for pervs trying to find stuff. Don\'t be upset if your tags change, be glad that more pervs can find your upload now. \r\n\r\nAs far as telling uploaders of tag changes by PM... I dunno I have changed a few tags on emp.me and I never PM\'d anyone :lol: If that upset anybody then... I dunno maybe they shouldnt be so butthurt when their crappy tags get corrected?? Technically we could have notifications sent to the uploader but I dont like the idea, firstly it will generate a large volume of PM traffic saying very little - internal junkmail imo - and secondly it gives credence to this idea that the uploader has some ownership of the tags for their upload, when really they dont, they just set the initial state but then the tags belong to the tracker community - which is as it should be in my eyes.[/quote]\r\n\r\none question i have in mind regarding the tags that will be added from other members. do the syno- replacer control them too? if not, you will have double triple thousands similar tags again. ',NULL,NULL),(44398,5731,129045,'2012-07-19 19:24:19','[quote=mifune]Random snag fixes: (please test)\r\n\r\n[*]Block PM\'s - implemented allow PM\'s options as per emp.me [color=#009900]Working![/color] (According to this thread http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2723 , unless something changed)\r\n[*]Staff Messages - [color=#FF6600]1 - added some extra info to the view conversation page so its easier to tell who initiated (user or staff)[/color] and [color=#FF0000]2 - made it so users can only resolve conversations they initiated.[/color] [color=#009900]1 - Working[/color], can\'t test [color=#FF0000]2[/color]\r\n[*]Logs should now correctly show as red when it is a delete log (was showing them as blue if it was a torrent delete log) [color=#009900]Working![/color]\r\n[*]Added a check on entering tags to strip dots from the start and end. [color=#009900]Working![/color]\r\n[/quote]',129045,'2012-07-19 20:49:44'),(44399,5732,6203,'2012-07-19 19:28:39','i ask me why a normal member have the ability to watch the logs? isnt that more an admin/ mod tool?',NULL,NULL),(44400,5666,6203,'2012-07-19 19:34:29','confirmed. i have the same error when i use the advanced search (file name)\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44401,5666,129045,'2012-07-19 19:43:08','Is this different somehow?\r\n\r\nThe bug I reported was because everything you searched (not using the box at the top bar), would activate \"Make Default\" (it overrides everything, you need to use \"Clear Default\" to reset things to normal). So, as knickers tested, if he searches something and then search again with no terms (blank box), he is just working around the issue, not really solving, as \"Make Default\" would still be active.\r\n\r\nThis doesn\'t only apply for search terms, but for the categories selected as well.\r\n\r\nEDIT:\r\n\r\n[color=#009900][size=3]This happens because whenever you click on the search boxes to type something, focus will be given to the \"[b]Make Default[/b]\" button, instinctively hitting [i][b]Enter[/b][/i] will of course, activate the button. Thus triggering the \"bug\"[/size][/color]\r\n\r\nQuoting myself from the other thread:\r\n\r\n[quote][size=2][b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b][/size] [color=#FF0000]Oh shit, the bug only kicks in when the user select categories \\ search for something by typing and pressing [b]Enter[/b]. If he select categories and type something (or not) and then click on \"Filter torrents\", it\'ll not trigger the bug.[/color]\r\n\r\n[size=2][b][i]EDIT2:[/i][/b]\r\n\r\n[color=#0066FF]Well, now I know why it happens, one of those \"[b][i]D\'oh![/i][/b]\" moments lol\r\n\r\nIf you click on any of the search boxes, you will see that the focus will be given to the \"Make Default\" button, that\'s why hitting Enter will trigger the \"bug\", test it now:\r\n\r\n- Click on any of them (Search term, File list or Tags) and pay attention to the \"Make Default\" button, now click somewhere else on the page and you will see the button losing focus.[/color]\r\n\r\n[b][i]Possible solution:[/i][/b] [color=#0066FF]Force the focus to the \"Filter Torrents\" button instead.[/color]\r\n[/size]\r\n[/quote]\r\n\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',129045,'2012-07-19 20:33:13'),(44402,5666,129045,'2012-07-19 20:03:26','[quote=mifune][mcom][b]Confirmed Bug:[/b] Sticky search results [color=#FF0000][i]if you have default search settings saved[/i][/color][/mcom][/quote]\n\n[s]That\'s incorrrect, you don\'t need to do anything apart from using any of the search boxes at http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php\n\nThe bug will happen on both Search types (basic or advanced), anything you search will activate \"Make Default\", that\'s what\'s making the search terms [i]sticky[/i].\n\nThe biggest problem with this, is that users can\'t actually make proper use of \"Make Default\", as their choices will be overwritten on the next time they search something.\n\ne.g. If the user made legit use of \"Make Default\", for example leaving the search boxes blank and marking some categories to filter all the torrents, that choice would be lost as soon as he used any keyword on the search boxes, as the bug would kick in and activate \"Make Default\". So instead of having [color=#0033FF]selected categories + blank search boxes[/color] as default (this would filter all torrents based on category), now he would have [color=#FF0033]selected categories + keyword[/color] (this would filter by category, only the torrents matching the keyword).[/s]\n\n[size=2][b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b] [color=#FF0000]Oh shit, the bug only kicks in when the user select categories \\ search for something by typing and pressing [b]Enter[/b]. If he select categories and type something (or not) and then click on \"Filter torrents\", it\'ll not trigger the bug.[/color][/size]\n\n[size=2][b][i]EDIT2:[/i][/b]\n\n[color=#0066FF]Well, now I know why it happens, one of those \"[b][i]D\'oh![/i][/b]\" moments. If you click on any of the search boxes, you will see that the focus will be given to the \"Make Default\" button, that\'s why hitting Enter will trigger the \"bug\", test it now:\n\n- Click on any of them (Search term, File list or Tags) and pay attention to the \"Make Default\" button, now click somewhere else on the page and you will see the button losing focus.[/color][/size]\n\n[color=#009900][size=3][b][i]So to be clear:[/i][/b] This happens because whenever you click on the search boxes to type something, focus will be given to the \"[b]Make Default[/b]\" button, instinctively hitting [i][b]Enter[/b][/i] will of course, activate the button. Thus triggering the \"bug\"[/size][/color]\n\n[size=3][b][i]Possible solution:[/i][/b] [color=#0066FF]Force the focus to the \"Filter Torrents\" button instead.[/color]\n[/size]',84499,'2012-07-19 21:45:39'),(44403,5676,84499,'2012-07-19 20:19:27','\r\n oh ye of little faith...\r\n\r\n :robot: \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44404,5732,84499,'2012-07-19 20:33:43','\nThe idea of having recent logs (<28 days) viewable to normal members appeals to my sense of openness and transparency. It used to be like that on the old old emp, and its like that on some other sites.\n\nThere is some practical use too... users looking for their deleted torrent or whatever will be able to find the reason without bothering the staff, or when they post in the forums bleating other users will solve it for them etc. \n :chairspin: ',84499,'2012-07-26 02:10:17'),(44405,5666,1507,'2012-07-19 21:20:18',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]hmmmm....\r\n\r\nwhat I did was leave everything unchecked (categories) in the advanced search...  I typed in \"underwatersex\" in the search term box and then clicked on \"filter torrents\"...  the results came in...  I then deleted the search term, left everything unchecked still, clicked \"filter torrents\" again, and this time everything showed as normally it does...  I then closed Opera out, relaunched Opera, went to the browse page and only torrents with \"underwatersex\" were displayed and the search term \"underwatersex\" was back in the search box...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nI then deleted everything from the search box, typed in \"hardcore\", left everything unchecked, clicked on \"filter torrents\", the contents for hardcore then displayed...  I then deleted \"hardcore\" form the search box, clicked on \"filter torrents\", and everything displayed normally again...  I then closed Opera again, re-launched Opera, and it displayed \"underwatersex\" once again where I thought it would display \"hardcore\" since that was my last search and should have been shown if it was a cache issue I thought...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nSo, everytime I go to browse, I get the search for \"underwatersex\", and I have to delete it from the search box, click \"filter torrents\", and then can use the browse as normal...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nI think it is a bug or a setting not clearing, but I am not a coder and am only reporting what steps I\'ve taken to make this happen...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44406,5666,129045,'2012-07-19 21:24:47','Well, I can\'t replicate it here. Do you see a \"Clear Default\" button somewhere when you visit the torrents page?\r\n\r\n[i][b]EDIT:[/b][/i] Tried IE, Firefox, Chrome and of course Opera, can\'t replicate it in any of them. [b]Clicking[/b] on \"Filter Torrents\" will filter the torrents like it should, but the settings aren\'t retained (visiting \"Torrents\" http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php again will have the boxes blank)\r\n\r\nWell, shit. And I thought I had finally found the source of the problem :laugh:\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',129045,'2012-07-19 21:30:29'),(44407,5666,1507,'2012-07-19 21:29:59','[quote=yamchan07bb]Well, I can\'t replicate it here. Do you see a \"Clear Default\" button somewhere when you visit the torrents page?[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n :gjob:  :gjob:  :gjob: \r\n\r\n[b]Thanks yam...  I clicked on it before but nothing happened, but this time I clicked onit and it actually worked and removed the \"underwatersex\" issue...   :yaydance: \r\n\r\nI guess I didn\'t get a good click on it before...   :hmmm:  :hmmm:  :hmmm: \r\n\r\nNow, it seems to work as it\'s supposed to...  :gjob:\r\n\r\nLet\'s see if I can make it screw up again...   :hmmm: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44408,5666,1507,'2012-07-19 21:31:25',' :hooray: \r\n\r\n[b]Yep, that did it...\r\n\r\nThanks...  :smile1:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44409,5723,1507,'2012-07-19 21:36:35',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]You can block staff pm\'s...???  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nThat\'s not a good feature...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nStaff pm\'s should never be allowed to be blocked...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(44410,5666,129045,'2012-07-19 21:37:17','To be clear:\r\n\r\nDid you type something and [b][i]CLICKED[/i][/b] on the \"Filter Torrents\" button?\r\n\r\nOr you typed something and pressed Enter\\Return or the keyboard?\r\n\r\nClicking on the button shouldn\'t trigger the problem, if you saw the \"Clear Default\" button there, then you probably either used \"Make Default\" or made a search by typing and then pressing Enter\\Return.\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44411,5666,86439,'2012-07-19 21:37:29','[quote=usillyboy]:hmmm:\n\n[b]hmmmm....\n\nwhat I did was leave everything unchecked (categories) in the advanced search...  I typed in \"underwatersex\" in the search term box and then clicked on \"filter torrents\"...  the results came in...  I then deleted the search term, left everything unchecked still, clicked \"filter torrents\" again, and this time everything showed as normally it does...  I then closed Opera out, relaunched Opera, went to the browse page and only torrents with \"underwatersex\" were displayed and the search term \"underwatersex\" was back in the search box...  :hmmm:\n\nI then deleted everything from the search box, typed in \"hardcore\", left everything unchecked, clicked on \"filter torrents\", the contents for hardcore then displayed...  I then deleted \"hardcore\" form the search box, clicked on \"filter torrents\", and everything displayed normally again...  I then closed Opera again, re-launched Opera, and it displayed \"underwatersex\" once again where I thought it would display \"hardcore\" since that was my last search and should have been shown if it was a cache issue I thought...  :hmmm:\n\nSo, everytime I go to browse, I get the search for \"underwatersex\", and I have to delete it from the search box, click \"filter torrents\", and then can use the browse as normal...  :hmmm:\n\nI think it is a bug or a setting not clearing, but I am not a coder and am only reporting what steps I\'ve taken to make this happen...  :laugh:\n\nusb[/b]\n\n:usb:[/quote]\n\nOk, I did exactly what you said when I tested it in the first place, and Ive just checked it again, no change. Im using FF, not Opera (had an issue with Opera a week or so ago, decided to uninstall and now the install refuses to install so Ive given up until I replace this system in the next couple of weeks, but I digress).\n\nWith what Yamchan was saying in regard to the default box being highlighted when you click in the search fields, that doesnt happen to mine when I click the search fields. Not in basic, or advanced.\n\n\nEdit: Oh fine, fix it while im typing and rechecking to be sure :laugh:\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',86439,'2012-07-19 21:39:18'),(44412,5732,86439,'2012-07-19 21:42:44','So, ...laziness basically :lol:',NULL,NULL),(44413,5666,1507,'2012-07-19 21:42:51','[quote=yamchan07bb]To be clear:\r\n\r\nDid you type something and [b][i]CLICKED[/i][/b] on the \"Filter Torrents\" button?\r\n\r\nOr you typed something and pressed Enter\\Return or the keyboard?\r\n\r\nClicking on the button shouldn\'t trigger the problem, if you saw the \"Clear Default\" button there, then you probably either used \"Make Default\" or made a search by typing and then pressing Enter\\Return.\r\n\r\n:hmmm:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]Yep, I\'ve tried it both ways and I must have hit \"Enter\" before without realizing it as it only does this when I hit \"Enter\" and not if I just click on \"filter torrents\"...  :slap:\r\n\r\nSo my \"bug\" was actually me clicking on \"Enter\" and not realizing that I did it....  :slap:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :sigh: \n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44414,5666,129045,'2012-07-19 21:45:21','Well, sorry, just tested here and you\'re right.\r\n\r\nIt doesn\'t show up on Firefox or Chrome, but Opera and IE will show the change of focus on the fly, by clicking on the search boxes and then outside of it (on the background or the top bar)\r\n\r\nStill, the effect is true. By default hitting Enter will activate \"Make Default\"\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44415,5723,84499,'2012-07-19 21:49:11','\r\n\r\nno, you cannot block staff PM\'s. You can have staff on your blocked list... but it dosent stop staff from sending you PM\'s. ',NULL,NULL),(44416,5666,86439,'2012-07-19 21:54:24','[quote=yamchan07bb]Well, sorry, just tested here and you\'re right.\r\n\r\nIt doesn\'t show up on Firefox or Chrome, but Opera and IE will show the change of focus on the fly, by clicking on the search boxes and then outside of it (on the background or the top bar)\r\n\r\nStill, the effect is true. By default hitting Enter will activate \"Make Default\"[/quote]\r\nOk just for clarity, I read the alterations to this thread after I posted, tested it now using keyboard only, still doesnt highlight the default box in FF. Ive upgraded to v14 from the v12 I was using a few days ago, also mentioned for clarity in case it makes a difference.\r\n\r\nJust tried again, in both advanced and basic, clicked all over the fieldss, selected and deselected checkboxes, clicked around (but not on) the buttons themselves, in the bar with advanced serach/basic search toggle, etc. I mean I clicked all over the place.\r\n\r\nAt no point does make default highlight as active.\r\n\r\nJust reading your last line, I wasnt sure if you meant in Opera, or included FF in that enter reference. So thought Id make sure i was being clear.\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44417,5723,86439,'2012-07-19 21:57:07','Burn them, theyre witches.',NULL,NULL),(44418,5666,129045,'2012-07-19 22:01:36','Ok, but the behavior, did you test it?\r\n\r\nType something and hit Enter. It should activate \"Make Default\", you should see \"Clear Default\" appearing on its side ([i]Reset > Make Default > [b]Clear Default[/b][/i])\r\n\r\nClick on \"Clear Default\" and then try again, type something and hit Enter. The result should be the same :hmmm:\r\n\r\nTesting here, looking at the page source code, adding\r\n\r\n[code]<input style=\"display:none\" type=\"submit\" value=\"Filter Torrents\" />[/code]\r\n\r\nbefore the code for the other buttons seems to make sure focus isn\'t given to \"Make Default\", it\'ll activate \"Filter Torrents\" instead, producing the correct behavior.\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',129045,'2012-07-19 22:15:20'),(44419,5666,86439,'2012-07-19 22:13:20','Yeah I did. But the default button is not highlighted, ever. When the screen reloads after hitting enter, I do get a new button, clear default, but I dont have to click it to clear the default.\n\nAll i have to do is delete the search term I entered (highlight ,and click delete to leave blank, or retype a new word to change the term) and it does what I expect it to do. Search for only the \'string\' even if blank, in the field. \n\nIve then closed the torrent page, reopened and the only difference is the clear default button is still present, but all torrents are showing.  (well, the 2 pages we see by default due to that next/last page issue)\n\nIll close ff now, and see if that makes a difference.\n\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',86439,'2012-07-19 22:21:37'),(44420,5666,86439,'2012-07-19 22:21:48','I just clicked clear default, which is a different bug to what USB reported and which I was replying to. At no time is make default highlighted, nor do my searches go awry. They behave as expected.\n\n\nHowever, when i click clear default instead of just re-entering a string or leaving it blank, it does just remove the clear default button when the screen reloads, but the results page looks like it did prior to clicking it. That is, still limits torrents shown to the string which is still shown in the field.\n\nBased on that, being uneducated, I think it just fails to clear the search field. Because like I said, if its meant to clear defaults, I dont have any defaults set. Leaving that button alone, the system works as it should. But I imagine if the clear defaults button also cleared the search string field, then I would see what I do the other way of doing it, all torrents as the field would be blank.\n\ni could be wrong on that though.\n\n\nedit: Clicking enter, always brings up the reset defaults button, with a string, or left blank in the search field, but doesnt seem to do anything else. Nothing is highlighted though.\n\nI closed the browse page, reopened it, the clear default button is there still, but so are all torrents. Thats because I cleared the string field and hit enter. If I dont clear the string field, then whatever I typed last is the way the page opens.\n\nBut what USB was saying is that the first term he entered reappears despite searching for something else last. That doesnt happen to me.\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',86439,'2012-07-19 22:31:47'),(44421,5666,129045,'2012-07-19 22:28:49','What the hell... :hmmm:\r\n\r\nIgnore the focus\\highlight thing I was talking about earlier.\r\n\r\nSearch \"test\" and hit Enter. From here, go to \"Torrents\" http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php (open it in a new tab), the search term \"test\" should be there.\r\n\r\nClose all Torrents tabs, close Firefox, launch it again and visit http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php, the search term should still be there.\r\n\r\nAnother way to check this, instead of hitting Enter, simply type something (or leave it all blank) and then click on \"Make Default\", the results should be the same you were getting before by hitting Enter.\r\n\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',129045,'2012-07-19 22:35:07'),(44422,5666,86439,'2012-07-19 22:36:34','Check my edit, was doing similar while you were typing.\n\n\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',86439,'2012-07-19 22:43:05'),(44423,5666,86439,'2012-07-19 22:43:13','So I just rebooted FF, as above, test being the last phrase typed in the field, and it still was there when I closed, and was still there when i reopened FF.\r\n\r\nBut If I clear the search field, ie: search on a blank field, all torrents reappear, and that is the way it boots up again too. The Clear default button is there, until I hit that button, but the torrents are all there.\r\n\r\nit appears to me it remembers the last search it did.\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44424,5666,129045,'2012-07-19 22:51:32','Ok, from what I get, USB somehow activated the \"bug\" by hitting Enter (thus activated \"Make Default\") without knowing, that\'s why he had the \"Clear Default\" option there, using \'Filter Torrents\' in this case wouldn\'t override what \"Make Default\" had set (\'sexunderwater\'), so everytime he came back, that was the search term that appeared there.\r\n\r\nNow follow me on this: [color=#FF0000]Why users should search with blank fields in order to see all torrents again?[/color] Why were you doing this? [i]That\'s a work around, not really a solution.[/i] It\'s still activating \"Make Default\" (which will make whatever search term or categories you chose stick, until you do a new search or hit \"Clear Default\").\r\n\r\nWhat I\'m talking about: [b]this is the wrong behavior[/b], the default action (hittin Enter) should activate \"Filter Torrents\" instead of \"Make Default\" (this is what I was referring to as \'focus\' or \'highlight\', IE and Opera shows it, Firefox and Chrome does not).\r\n\r\nHere, how it shows up on Opera:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1CD1_5008743C][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-1CD1_5008743C.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n\"Make Default\" is focused as the default action, hit Enter and it\'ll be activated, thus creating all this mess. \"Filter Torrents\" should be the default action, it would return the results to the user without making any categories or search terms stick. While other browsers don\'t show the focus, they all perform the same action.\r\n\r\nRight now, if you have the \'Clear Default\' button available, click on it. On further searches, don\'t use Enter, but simply click on \'Filter Torrents\', you\'ll never experience this problem again, because this is how it should be working in the first place.\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1BE5_50087970][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-1BE5_50087970.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=2B54_50087970][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-2B54_50087970.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nThis is just an example, dirty fix applied (only tested on Opera), \"Make Default\" will not receive the focus anymore, so hitting Enter will be the same as clicking on \"Filter Torrents\" :)\r\n\r\nHope you understood what I meant.\r\n\r\nNow, I gotta go, this ADSL roller coaster is killing me, up-down-up-down-down-down, fucking shitty signal D:\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',129045,'2012-07-19 23:27:22'),(44425,5666,86439,'2012-07-19 23:19:08','The reason I search a blank string, is the list is filtered by whatever I type. If I want to do another search, i need to change it. That would include returning the browse page to show everything, thus blank.\r\n\r\nIt would annoy me if the next day I opened FF and came to the site to look through anything uploaded, nothing specific, but anything, and I only got what I looked for yesterday and had to clear it to see everything, so that aspect is going to need addressing.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSo to establish a simple test. \r\n\r\nI just tried to search for \'troll\' (again some hits, WTF is up with that?) and did so by hitting enter. I then cleared the field, and mouse clicked filter torrents. Closed, then Reopened the browse page, and there it was, \'troll\'. I guess that answers the question.\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44426,5666,129045,'2012-07-19 23:42:45','[quote=knickers]The reason I search a blank string, is the list is filtered by whatever I type. If I want to do another search, i need to change it. That would include returning the browse page to show everything, thus blank.\r\n\r\nIt would annoy me if the next day I opened FF and came to the site to look through anything uploaded, nothing specific, but anything, and I only got what I looked for yesterday and had to clear it to see everything, so that aspect is going to need addressing.\r\n\r\nSo to establish a simple test. \r\n\r\nI just tried to search for \'troll\' (again some hits, WTF is up with that?) and did so by hitting enter. I then cleared the field, and mouse clicked filter torrents. Closed, then Reopened the browse page, and there it was, \'troll\'. I guess that answers the question.[/quote]\r\n\r\n[b][i]Ok, just to be clear:[/i][/b]\r\n\r\nThat\'s the \'bug\' kicking in. Using [b][i]Enter[/i][/b] will activate \"[b]Make Default[/b]\", so your last search terms and categories (if you selected any) will stick until you do a new search (in your case, using blank fields) or click on \"[b]Clear Default[/b]\".\r\n\r\nNow, as I said, make sure you click on \"[b]Clear Default[/b]\" if the button is available and on future searches, instead of hitting [b]Enter[/b], simply click on \"[b]Filter Torrents[/b]\" and you\'ll never face this problem again (this way, everytime you go to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php, the torrents will be unfiltered, so all of them will be listed.)\r\n\r\nAnd now I\'m out of here, before this stupid ADSL drives me mad.   :nasher: \n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',129045,'2012-07-19 23:44:40'),(44427,5666,84499,'2012-07-20 00:14:42','\r\n\r\nthis thread is way way too complicated for what is a very simple bug :lol:\r\n\r\n\r\nyamchan is right about this stuff.... anyway I implemented his fix and it seems to be working  :gjob: \n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'BUG : On Browse Page, Search Term never clears\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44431,5735,84499,'2012-07-20 00:55:29','teset11',NULL,NULL),(44432,5735,84499,'2012-07-20 00:56:03','\r\n\r\nanother test\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]merged from thread[/i][br]\'test22\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(44433,5667,84499,'2012-07-20 02:24:16','\r\n\r\nlets do it.\r\n\r\nI have no idea whats involved... or anything. But I really hate the fact that efnet broadcasts my ip!',NULL,NULL),(44434,5729,84499,'2012-07-20 02:26:14','\r\n\r\n[quote=yamchan07bb]Well, shit. Thanks for the info.\r\n\r\nNow I remember, it was you who posted this thread: http://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=2464\r\n\r\n[quote=borkb0rkbork][b]I was told.....\r\n\r\nThat when the new site goes live, host-masking will be implemented for the IRC, along with some other privacy features we currently don\'t really need, but which would be nice.[/b][/quote]\r\n\r\nIs this still in the plans? :hmmm:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nWell I have no idea where bork got that information from... I am all for it but have no idea whats involved. Dunno if Lanz has any plans or whether that is misinformation...',NULL,NULL),(44435,5737,84499,'2012-07-20 03:46:29','\r\n\r\nShould there be a thanks button for torrents like there is at emp? Or is it just a waste of space?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso if you think there should be, where should it be on the torrent details page?',NULL,NULL),(44436,5737,88640,'2012-07-20 04:30:30','I think there should be one.  Sometimes if I can\'t think of anything better than thanks I\'ll just click the thanks button.  I think just above the comments is a good place, like on emp.  Unless you\'re worried people will see it and stop there instead of continuing down to leave a comment.',NULL,NULL),(44437,5737,67255,'2012-07-20 05:19:10','Yeah I like them',NULL,NULL),(44438,5729,67255,'2012-07-20 05:22:05','That could be one of the reasons people feel apprehensive when thinking about joining the irc\r\nThis should be implemented or a guide posted on how to do it',NULL,NULL),(44439,5667,47234,'2012-07-20 08:21:08','Speak to MrRandom who runs the current one.  He claims to know.  I got him signed up to empforums with some help from Lanz :)',NULL,NULL),(44440,5729,47234,'2012-07-20 08:25:06','I private IRC is being looked into.  I for one have no idea whats actually involved.  So i asked people who might know lol',NULL,NULL),(44441,5729,70679,'2012-07-20 08:55:41','it involves using one\'s own irc server instead of using a public one. I know other sites that do it. And indeed it is being looked into.',NULL,NULL),(44442,5729,47234,'2012-07-20 09:02:50','I meant more on the server setup and requirements end Barumba',NULL,NULL),(44443,5737,89443,'2012-07-20 09:30:02','What about a +/- system?',NULL,NULL),(44444,5619,152838,'2012-07-20 12:07:22','I also had to \"reset\" my password, using Firefox 14.0.1 .\r\nThe reset process worked without problems* and I was able to reset my password. Although I took the same password as before and now it works just fine.\r\n\r\n(* the mail went to the spam folder on my mail providers server, so I couldn\'t directly access it, but thats a problem on my side.)',NULL,NULL),(44445,5738,86439,'2012-07-20 13:20:45','\n\nOK, so I received a message for a reported post as part of the fls system. Being new to these tools and these tools themselves being new, Im not sure how to interpret it. So im looking for clarity in this post mostly while taking the opportunity to explain my experience.\n\n\nThe post reported was not mine, it was one of yamchans, and the message indicates it was sent to yamchan, not me, but assigned to fls thus I also got it? Yep, clear as mud.\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-D447_50092C5A.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-D447_50092C5A.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-E148_50093CE1.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-E148_50093CE1.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nSo if I read this right, someone reported the post, and then Mifune assigned it to fls, or Mifune reported it, and the system assigned it first to fls?\n\nIt also says \'your post #\' and Im wondering if that should just read \'post #\' or is it showing me what it sent to yamchan? The message heading bar also indicates it was sent to Yamchan and not me.\n\n\n\nI selected \'common answers\' and there was only one option, rant at user, \n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-373F_50093DF1.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-373F_50093DF1.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-04B7_50093DF1.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-04B7_50093DF1.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n\nThere does appear to be an option to create a new \'common answer\' or edit the current one. Im not sure if that edit will simply edit the one communication, or edit the preset itself, I havent tried yet. But I have added a couple of new ones which appear to have saved to the list.\n\nI sent one of them, but no idea who it went to. Or is this just something like a bulletin board, and all staff will see it? A staff discussion if you like. It appears to me, that I would read the message, and decide if it was bogus or not, if not, then I would assign to staff/admin depending on type of report? If bogus, just resolve it. Leaving staff to deal with actual issues and not waste time with nonsense? A filter if you will.\n\nIm I getting this right?',84499,'2012-07-20 17:52:52'),(44446,5738,47234,'2012-07-20 13:34:23','Hmm as this is staff related do we need to get the fls testers onto the staff forum section?\n\nI couldnt work out how to add the forum properly.  Maybe mifune or lanz could help with that.  I see add forum section on the user settings but it didnt seem to do anything last time i tried it.',47234,'2012-07-20 13:35:32'),(44447,5729,70679,'2012-07-20 13:50:15','in MrR we trust  :clap2: ',NULL,NULL),(44448,5738,86439,'2012-07-20 13:50:43','\n\n[img]http://ismoketoomuch.com/pics/i%20has%20a%20bucket.jpg[/img]\n\n',86439,'2012-07-20 14:22:58'),(44449,5738,47234,'2012-07-20 14:04:07','Good idea knickers :)\r\n\r\nI suggest you PM mifune at this point and ask the question or point to my post',NULL,NULL),(44450,5619,39588,'2012-07-20 14:12:53','Reset took the same pass for me as well, Chrome 20.',NULL,NULL),(44452,5619,94804,'2012-07-20 14:22:23','I\'m using win7 64bit with Chrome(latest build) and it happened to me, too',NULL,NULL),(44453,5740,94804,'2012-07-20 14:32:52','hi, \r\nI\'m missing all messages in my inbox from 3th of July \'till now',NULL,NULL),(44454,5740,47234,'2012-07-20 14:34:15','This tracker is using a copy of thae database around that old its not linked to the current site beyond a certain date.  Im guessing thats about it :)',NULL,NULL),(44455,5740,94804,'2012-07-20 14:37:02','oow',NULL,NULL),(44456,5619,84973,'2012-07-20 14:38:10','On Firefox (windows vista) it didn\'t take my password, I reset to the same one and it worked fine.',NULL,NULL),(44457,5741,94804,'2012-07-20 14:42:42','why did the price for slots rise so much? harder to buy \'em now, which is a shame:(',NULL,NULL),(44458,5741,47234,'2012-07-20 14:46:31','Ahhh the joys of breaking new testers in :lol:\r\n\r\nCatch up on the forums a bit :)\r\n\r\nThe whole credit system is changing.  The current one does nasty things to server load.',NULL,NULL),(44460,5741,94804,'2012-07-20 15:06:17','haha woops will read',NULL,NULL),(44461,5741,86439,'2012-07-20 15:10:18','GFC, European markets ... and two divorces',86439,'2012-07-20 15:11:13'),(44462,5742,94804,'2012-07-20 15:23:30','[mcom][b]FIXED[/b] - I broke a regex in the validator with a rouge smiley code  :slap: the description length error should be gone now\n[b]FIXED[/b] also fixed a snafu whereby the error msg would render html (whoops!)[/mcom]\n\n\nI\'ve a prob uploading when I try that it returns to the original uploadscreen but w/o torrent and category (those are blank again), and it didn\'t upload\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-09E0_50096A93.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-09E0_50096A93.jpg[/img][/url]\nusing Chrome 20.0.1132.57 \n\noow, one more thing, it says \"amature\"when you selected \"amateur\" at category\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-1240_50095CE4.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-1240_50095CE4.jpg[/img][/url]',84499,'2012-07-20 20:50:37'),(44463,5742,86439,'2012-07-20 15:32:51','Mate, edit out the passkey in the announce url on that screencap (top url). i dont know if those are set here permanently, but its never wise to post your passkeys.\n\nDoes it give you any error messages. I was getting similar when i left out