ill not count stuff inside tags like urls etc... you actually need a text description!\r\n\r\nif you can copy and paste the bbcode you are trying to enter as the description inside code tags I can check it out.\r\n\r\n[code][code]your bbcode here[/code][/code]',NULL,NULL),(44473,5738,84499,'2012-07-20 17:51:52','\r\n\r\nOkay I moved this thread to staff testing and added the staff testing forum id to knickers permitted forums... he should be able to see this forum now.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44475,5738,84499,'2012-07-20 17:57:31','\r\n[quote=mifune]Okay you are looking at the staff side of the staff messaging system. \r\n\r\nWhen a user sends a staff message they select whether it is for FLS - or Mods - or Admins. The default is FLS. This is the level the message is at. When a message is initiated by staff I think it will always be at FLS level. All the staff at a particular level can see the staff messages at their level and lower.\r\n\r\nThat particular message was started by staff (me) and sent to yamchan, so requires no action until he replies - and then it probably just needs closing (resolving). Staff Messages started by users can be resolved by themselves but if started by a staff then someone on the staff side (FLS, Mod whoever has permission to access that message) has to resolve it.\r\n  \r\nThe common message stuff - anything you do on the edit/save page just edits the common messages, eventually there will be a bunch of common messages staff/FLS can select when replying to staff messages.\r\n\r\nI suggest you generate a few as a user (goto the staff page or user inbox to compose a staff message, the compose forum will probably caution you that you are a staff but you can ignore that and just send them, then you can pick them up from the other side as staff.\r\n\r\nEr, we need to find a way to discuss this in a better forum - PM\'s is inappropriate and I dont have time to write tutorials for every part of the website right now.... I am going to see if i can figure out whats up with the gazelle forum permissions (looks like its fubar) - hopefully in a few hours time i can add you to the staff forum or something and we can put this discussion there...[/quote]\r\n\r\npermissions field works it just takes forum ID\'s (deduce from the urls - its not actually displayed anywhere even in the toolbox) instead of their names.\r\n\r\n\r\nSO.....  \r\n\r\nTalk about the staff messaging system in here - hopefully its figurable out :D but if not I will return with better explanations!\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44476,5735,48010,'2012-07-20 18:00:10','voted but way merge polls - are we really going to get the same ones?\r\n\r\nmy suggestion is forget polls anyway as most of them on other sites are rubbish :grin:\r\n\r\npoll\r\nDo you prefer blonde or brunette - FFS what is the point in it ?\r\n\r\ncould be useful for site decisions though so the members can vote and express their opinion',NULL,NULL),(44477,5670,48010,'2012-07-20 18:02:32','[quote=yamchan07bb]Ok, mifune added the PM notifications for comments received. Dave, did you receive one?\r\n\r\nOr please, post a comment in one of those torrents:\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35152\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35150\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35141\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b] [color=#009900]Working![/color], thanks Hexen for dropping the comment.[/quote]\r\nyes i got it and i posted to confirm in the torrent too',NULL,NULL),(44478,5744,84499,'2012-07-20 18:06:32','\r\n:welcome3: \r\n\r\nHi, welcome new FLS.\r\n\r\n\r\nSay hi and ask any questions you have here.\r\n\r\n\r\nI can answer the first one... \r\n\r\nQ: what do FLS do?\r\nA: we dont know yet.\r\n\r\n\r\n:lol:\r\n\r\nPart of this testing is for us to work out what FLS should do, what powers they should have etc.\r\n\r\nTo start with... FLS can read and respond to staff messages that are not specifically assigned to a higher level, we havent got any right now (perhaps someone could post a thread in test requests asking for staff messages to be generated?) but you could check out the old messages and see if the system makes sense.\r\n\r\nWhat other powers and responsibilities should FLS have? Opinions needed!\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44479,5738,86439,'2012-07-20 18:09:01','Yep, I see.\r\n\r\nI will come back to this tomorrow, atm, someones waiting for me.',NULL,NULL),(44480,5735,84499,'2012-07-20 18:09:11','\r\n\r\nhaha sorry this was not asking anything , i just wanted somehwere to try merging a thread with a poll to see if it switched the poll to the new thread id  :blush: \r\n\r\n\r\nyou will be glad to know the merge thread tool works okay :D',NULL,NULL),(44481,5732,48010,'2012-07-20 18:22:14','[quote=knickers]So, ...laziness basically :lol:[/quote]\nno it\'s efficiency - cuts down the crap for us staff to deal with - they can see why their torrent was nuked or other things like new uploads\n\nI asked a long time ago on the current site for an irc announce of new torrents (like other sites do) but not possible on the current efnet - this solves that problem too\n\n',48010,'2012-07-20 18:22:47'),(44482,5667,84499,'2012-07-20 18:22:57','\r\n\r\nOkay I PM\'d MrRandom on emp and I have invited him to this thread (I gave him permission for this staff testing forum).\r\n\r\nHopefully we can get this sorted :)\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44483,5737,48010,'2012-07-20 18:26:03','yes but most won\'t use it\r\n\r\nit is a feature i see and use on emp.me and other sites\r\n\r\nat least the uploader knows they are appreciated but regular uploaders probably dont check to see :wink: as it\'s not too important to them',NULL,NULL),(44484,5742,94804,'2012-07-20 18:38:15','yeah, I tried it with what I got in the first image (the one with the now-blurred-out passkey)\n\nso this [code][u][b][color=#006699]Description[/color][/b][/u]\r\n!The lovely Mae Olson doing anal and taking a big facial in the end, what more can I say?\r\n\r\n[u] [b][color=#006699] Own Notes[/color][/b][/u]\r\nPlease seed, and feel free to leave a comment!\r\n\r\n[u][b][font=Verdana][size=2][color=#006699]Screenshots[/color][/size][/font][/b][/u]![url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=418C_5009534A][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=418C_5009534A&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[u][b][color=#006699]My profile and other uploads[/color][/b][/u]\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=D27F_4FF9FDB9][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=D27F_4FF9FDB9&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n[/code]',94804,'2012-07-20 18:42:13'),(44485,5737,6203,'2012-07-20 18:46:39','i say no. i very rarely read who said thanks.',NULL,NULL),(44486,5667,85636,'2012-07-20 18:46:53','Ok, I\'m here so what you want to know?',85636,'2012-07-20 18:47:26'),(44487,5729,48010,'2012-07-20 18:56:34','+1 MrR is the man',NULL,NULL),(44488,5742,84499,'2012-07-20 19:07:48','\r\n\r\nbugger\r\n\r\nI am pretty mystified as to why the text validator has stopped working... :hmmm:\r\n\r\nIt must have been working a few hours ago, so its the commit I made recently... fuck me thats strange.\r\n\r\nbugger\r\n\r\ngood catch anyway! :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(44489,5667,84499,'2012-07-20 19:15:28','\r\n\r\n[quote=MrRandom]For moving the IRC Channel all that would be required is deciding where it should be (have a few suggestions on where), moving the IRC Bots (all I need to do is edit a line in the config), and notify people about the move by changing the channel topic so say \"Hey we moved to #empornium @ irc.blahblahblah.org\" and edit the forum topic about IRC and make an announcement.\r\n\r\nAs for a place to put the channel I was talking to Clownius about having one of his servers link to my IRC Server to set up a network you could use and have operator powers on. If you want to just have a channel a place that is a little easier to manage (EFNet is a fucking pain to manage a channel on) you could try p2p-network but that do not provide any webchat features which I can be setup on my server ( e.g. http://webchat.digitalwizardry.org/ << mine).\r\n\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nWhat do the other staff think we should do?\r\n\r\nLanz/Clownius? You know anything about setting up an IRC server or whether thats a good idea? (presumably it would be on the empforums server?)\r\n\r\nI am ignorant about these things but can probably learn enough to do stuff if needed.\r\n\r\nIdeas? Opinions?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44490,5741,48010,'2012-07-20 19:22:00','problem in new prices\n\nthe maths dont add up :wink:\n\nGive Away 500 Credits 	If you have more credit than you could possibly have a use for, then why not share it with a friend? Give away 500 credits. COST=600 !!!\n\nso \n-1GB to other 	Do you know a friend or perhaps someone else who has a shitty ratio? Here you can give someone a happy surprise by taking away 1GB from the person\'s downloaded traffic! COST=505 !! \n\ncost to remove 1GB=500c\n\nwhy is it more expensive to help a friend than a member you don\'t know ? unless you invited them :wink:\n\nEDIT hope this is clear to mifune and coders to check the maths',48010,'2012-07-20 19:22:41'),(44491,5743,48010,'2012-07-20 19:24:07','good catch PJ',NULL,NULL),(44492,5667,85636,'2012-07-20 19:29:08','If you want help I can help set it up. If you want Lanz/Clownius to run it.',85636,'2012-07-20 19:39:22'),(44493,5729,85636,'2012-07-20 19:42:19','[quote=Dave]+1 MrR is the man[/quote]\r\n[quote=barumba]in MrR we trust  :clap2:[/quote]\r\n\r\nThank you\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44494,5735,48010,'2012-07-20 19:43:46','cool - good work \r\n\r\nsorry i didnt get it',NULL,NULL),(44495,5744,48010,'2012-07-20 19:45:09','OMG mifune\r\n\r\nlets see if they agree to be FLS :wink:',NULL,NULL),(44496,5738,48010,'2012-07-20 19:46:49','[quote=knickers]Yep, I see.\r\n\r\nI will come back to this tomorrow, atm, someones waiting for me.[/quote]\r\ngood luck knickers !!',NULL,NULL),(44497,5744,85636,'2012-07-20 19:53:30','FLS could also deal with help requests on IRC since we get a few people in there asking for help.',NULL,NULL),(44498,5745,48010,'2012-07-20 20:47:57','Hi all testers\r\n\r\nI got a reminder saying I\'m staff so not to post to staff trying to test a post to FLS (that\'s good) :grin:\r\n\r\ncan someone post to FLS - see the staff link to the page for who they are (they have no role yet but try anyway)\r\n\r\n@FLS team can you test and see if you get the red message too\r\n\r\nthanks Dave\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44499,5742,84499,'2012-07-20 20:53:24','\r\n\r\nOkay I fixed both issues...\r\n\r\nThe description length thing is working again (a smiley code I added broke something... dont ask)\r\n\r\nThe error message if you put html into any of the fields wont spaz out anymore   :slap: ',NULL,NULL),(44500,5744,129045,'2012-07-20 20:57:59','Can\'t access the \"Tools\" menu. It does have the dropdown arrow, but it seems to not work for me :hmmm:\r\n\r\nAccessing http://empornium.mooo.com/tools.php will only give me a \"Public Sandbox\" thingy (blank page, no error or anything)\r\n\r\nTried Opera, IE, Firefox and Chrome.',NULL,NULL),(44501,5744,48010,'2012-07-20 21:17:45','[quote=yamchan07bb]Can\'t access the \"Tools\" menu. It does have the dropdown arrow, but it seems to not work for me :hmmm:\n\nAccessing http://empornium.mooo.com/tools.php will only give me a \"Public Sandbox\" thingy (blank page, no error or anything)\n\nTried Opera, IE, Firefox and Chrome.[/quote]\ntools is for staff not FLS as i understand it\n\nsome changes may be needed ?',48010,'2012-07-20 21:18:22'),(44502,5745,84499,'2012-07-20 21:19:00','\r\n\r\njust to be clear do not PM them, use the staff messaging system. If you click on the Staff link at the top and then click on the red button on that page it will open a staff message form.\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/acnusm6m.png[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\nIf you want to recreate typical staff messages they mostly go something like \r\n[quote=random perv]Hi, I seed 24/7 but it never does anything!\r\nOn all my other trackers I seed plenty, what is wrong with this site??\r\nNow I have been download disabled! How can I seed if I cant downlaod??!?!?\r\nPls advise[/quote]\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44503,5744,84499,'2012-07-20 21:27:55','\r\nHmm, well its like this... every possible tool is checked against the permissions settings. If FLS have no permissions (like right now) then what they see is an empty menu :hmmm:\r\n\r\nIf we know FLS will have at least one permission... and I think its likely, then that menu will make sense (and there will be something in the drop down). I will add articles permissions for FLS right now, and think about it a bit more in terms of making the menu not appear if no tools are available.',NULL,NULL),(44504,5666,129045,'2012-07-20 21:40:31','[quote=mifune]this thread is way way too complicated for what is a very simple bug :lol:\r\n\r\nyamchan is right about this stuff.... anyway I implemented his fix and it seems to be working  :gjob: \r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nI wish it was simple :(\r\n\r\nFirefox and Opera will work just fine with the fix, but IE and Chrome will still use \"[b]Make Default[/b]\" as the default action when users press [b]Enter[/b].\r\n\r\n[color=#FF0000]Also, this is a separate issue[/color], still needs to be looked into:\r\n[quote]- On [b][i]Basic Search[/i][/b], after you use \"[b]Make Default[/b]\", \"Reset\" will not work (it will not clear the search boxes or the selected categories)[/quote]',NULL,NULL),(44505,5744,129045,'2012-07-20 21:44:12','Yep, Articles popped up in the menu.',NULL,NULL),(44506,5666,84499,'2012-07-20 22:06:28','\r\n\r\n:bombie:\r\n\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\nokay I am going to try something else...\n\n\r\n\r\nTry it now, I am hopeful that IE and Chrome will now not use make default as the default action.',84499,'2012-07-20 22:20:36'),(44507,5667,47234,'2012-07-20 22:07:14','I has no idea how to setup an IRC server to be honest.  But one without IP addresses would certainly be nice lol',NULL,NULL),(44508,5738,47234,'2012-07-20 22:08:58','Ah-hah you add the forum number :)',NULL,NULL)