le of hours of having a >1.05 ratio :smile1:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44597,5746,1243,'2012-07-21 16:04:19','[quote=iamstoopid][quote=yamchan07bb][quote=iamstoopid][quote=mifune]:hmm:\r\n\r\nhow annoying...\r\n\r\nthanks for the catch! :gjob:[/quote]\r\n\r\nYeh I had a similar problem when resizing the window on Chrome. \"Staff\" hyperlink gets pushed down and ratio info on top right overlaps a little >>\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=065E_5009EDAC][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=065E_5009EDAC[/img][/url][/quote]\r\n\r\nWell, this one I can\'t replicate, I had talked about a similar problem here http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2652\r\n\r\nBut after mifune corrected the Search boxes, the text didn\'t overlap anymore :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=C258_5009EF98][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-C258_5009EF98.jpg[/img][/url][/quote]\r\n\r\nyeh same thing happens in all my browsers.. starts overlapping at anything below [u]1140px[/u] window width. \r\n\r\n\r\ntop to bottom >> Chrome, Safari and Firefox. \r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=3641_5009F383][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=3641_5009F383[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nim using a Macbook btw with default resolution of 1440x900.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYou haven\'t increased the default font size or something? They look too big to be the default size.',NULL,NULL),(44598,5713,1243,'2012-07-21 16:14:08','That thing sticks out like a sore thumb to me. I didn\'t think it was even possible to NOT see/notice it. :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(44599,5713,129045,'2012-07-21 16:29:09','Is it supposed to behave differently for Staff messages and reports?\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=F005_500ABC34][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-F005_500ABC34.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nNo redbar anywhere :\\\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44600,5694,129045,'2012-07-21 16:49:10','[quote=Pornjacker]are the collages removed from the header? \r\nyesterday it was there now its gone.. http://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php\r\n[url=http://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php?id=1]\r\n[img]http://hostinga.imagecross.com/image-hosting-18/9965Untitled-1.jpg[/img][/url][/quote]\r\n\r\nUpdated the OP, the Collages link is now located in the user menu (hover your username).',NULL,NULL),(44601,5713,84499,'2012-07-21 16:49:31','\r\n\r\nyeah that is deliberate... we assume staff would rather have no redbar and simply be dilligent about checking the header :D\r\n\r\n\r\nwould you rather have the redbar? :hmmm: its not beyond the realms of possibility that there could be a user setting for staff/FLS to turn that on and off...\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44602,5713,129045,'2012-07-21 16:54:11','Thanks for the confirmation. Well, I\'m fine with any of them  :hmmm: ',NULL,NULL),(44603,5755,86439,'2012-07-21 16:58:16','[b]FAQ[/b]\nPedantic.\n\nWith the demise of yet another large porntracker (Cheggit) we wish to welcome all the new members who migrated from there.\n\nMaybe add, too, to the end.\n\n\n[b]FAQ[/b]\nPedantic.\nWe now have a unique opportunity to build a new community of pornlovers! This will however require patience from members from all the three old sites, and a positive attitude that we along the way can find the best solutions for the whole community.\n\nWe now have a unique opportunity to build a new community of pornlovers! This will however require patience from members from all three old sites, and a positive attitude that we along the way can find the best solutions for the whole community.\n\n\n[b]FAQ[/b]\nDo keep in mind that this site sometimes are upgraded and to keep up with whats going on (bugs/updates-functionality) be sure to regularly check the Current upgrades, Fixes and bugs Topic in the Forums.\n\nDo keep in mind that sites are sometimes upgraded and to keep up with whats going on be sure to regularly check the Current upgrades, Fixes and bugs Topic in the Forums (bugs/updates-functionality).\n\n\n[b]FAQ[/b]\nBefore you do anything here at empornium\n\n    You have to read and understand the - rules!\n\nunderline of \'rules\' goes back to incorporate the dash too. Same for the \'Help and Support\' line in the same section.\n\n    And the torrents.empornium.me user agreement.\n\n\'user agreement\' looks like it should be a hyperlink, but isnt.\n\n\n[b]FAQ[/b]\nInconsistent use of Capital in BitTorrent, Bittorrent\nWhat is this bittorrent all about anyway? How do I get the files? : Show\nWhen show is clicked, the line;\n BitTorrent it\'s about sharing and exchanging files. \n\nShould be \n BitTorrent - it\'s about sharing and exchanging files.    OR\n BitTorrent is about sharing and exchanging files.\n\n\n\n[b]FAQ[/b]\nUser information:\n  Original\n  What does the letters and numbers on the top bar mean? : Show\n\n  Correction\n  What do the letters and numbers on the top bar mean? : Show\n\n  Plus alignment issue in show field, and most spaces after \'=\' sign\n  [url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-30FF_500A9F11.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-30FF_500A9F11.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n  Re: slots line, maybe use \'number\' instead of \'amount\'.\n\n  Re: Ratio line. Space issue between \"is - Total\" and superfluous period after \'is\'.\n  \"current ratio is.-Total Upload/To\"\n\n\n\nSo, what\'s MY ratio? : Show\n  Your ratio is the amount you\'ve uploaded divided by the amount you\'ve downloaded. \n\n  Maybe add in that this is different from the RR.\n\n\n\n\nWhat are the bonus credits and \"slots\" for and [b]how can it be used?[/b] : Show\n\n  correction\n  how they can be used?\n\n\n  \'Show\' field\n  Space missing between bonus and credits, superfluous \'s\' and \'.\', and \'more\' should be replaced with \'additional\', and the addition of \'opportunity\' as credits dont automatically give you those, they must first be purchased. I do see the further explanation further down, but I think this keeps it clear.\n  \n  Original\n  Bonuscredits gives you 2 more download/seeding alternatives.!\n \n  Correction\n  Bonus credits give you the opportunity to purchase 2 additional download/seeding alternatives!   OR\n  Bonus credit gives you the opportunity to purchase 2 additional download/seeding alternatives!\n\n  NEXT SECTION\n  For clarity I would add \'The Standard\', and \'Two additional options\' to this.\n\n  [color=#FF0000]The standard[/color]\n  Regular Download:\n\n  (Always available with a good ratio)\n  Use this download link to download the torrent in the normal way.\n  All download / upload activity will be reported normally to the tracker.\n\n  [color=#FF0000]And two extra options[/color]\n  Free Leech and Double Upload Slots  (Freeleech in this context is not the same thing as Freeleech torrents. See below for further clarification) \n\n\n  Space missing between bonus and credits.\n\n  These can be purchased with your collected [color=#FF0000]bonuscredits[/color].\n\n\n***Notice!***\nThe Freeleech and Doubleseed Download buttons are only displayed\nnext to the regular download button after purchasing a Free/Double slot.\n\n\n\nFreeleech Slot:\n\nLine break\n\nOriginal\nOnce chosen this torrent will be Freeleech for 14 days\nand can be resumed or started over using the regular download link.\nDoing so will result in one Freeleech Slot being taken away from your total.\n\nCorrection\nOnce chosen this torrent will be Freeleech for 14 days and can be resumed or started over using the regular download link.\nDoing so will result in one Freeleech Slot being taken away from your total.\n\n\nMissing dash at \'Only\', and a space between the \'-\' and will, mixed use of capitals and lower case in beginning of those same lines.\nOriginal\nWhen you use this slot your download activity (for the choosen torrent)\n-will not be reported to the tracker\nOnly the upload activity would be reported.\n\nCorrection\nWhen you use this slot your download activity (for the choosen torrent)\n- will not be reported to the tracker\n- only the upload activity would be reported.\n\n\nMaybe some additional Information\n\nDo not confuse this concept of Freeleech with the other form of Freeleech here at EMPornium. They have the same name because they operate in the same manner in essence, but the manner in which they are available is completely different. The difference is this one mentioned here is generated by the member and applies to any torrent they choose. The other is system generated and applies to specific torrents that fit a specific criteria. System generated Freeleech never expires unless the sites rules change.\n\n\n\nDoubleseed Slot:\n\nLine breaks, some added info, and missing space between \'tracker,\' and \'but\', added \'at\' in the line 2 times the actual uploaded amount (DS section), and \'choosen\' should be \'chosen\', and some syntax corrections such as \'restarted\' as opposed to \'started over\'\n\nOriginal\nOnce chosen this torrent will be Doubleseed for 14 days\nand can be resumed or started over using the regular download link.\nDoing so will result in one Freeleech Slot being taken away from your total.\n\nWhen you use this download link it will report your download activity\nnormally to the trac[color=#FF0000]ker,bu[/color]t this time, your uploaded amount\n(on the [color=#FF0000]choosen[/color] torrent) will be reported [color=#FF0000](missing \'at\')[/color] 2 times of the actual uploaded amount to the tracker.\n\n\nCorrection\nOnce chosen this torrent will be Doubleseed for 14 days and can be resumed or restarted using the regular download link if you should ever need to do so.\nUsing this option will result in the removal of one Freeleech Slot from your total.\n\n([color=#FF0000]Im assuming that the DS link does not mandate the need to also click DL, its just if you decided to reseed or similar? If Im wrong, ignore that part of the correction \'if you should ever need to do so.\')[/color]\n\nWhen you use this download link it will report your download activity normally to the tracker, but this time your uploaded amount (on the chosen torrent) will be reported at 2 times the actual uploaded amount to the tracker.\n\n\n\n\nMissing spaces between \'bonus\' and \'points\', and the comma and \'or improve\'\n\nOriginal\nYou can also give away [color=#FF0000]bonuspoints,or improve[/color] your own or others ratios.\nA custom title and some forum bling can also be purchased.\n\nCorrected\nYou can also give away bonus points, or improve your own or others ratios.\nA custom title and some forum bling can also be purchased.\n\n\n\n\nBonuscredits,How does it work? : Hide\nMissing spaces between bonus credits, and after the comma which should be a full stop.\n\nOriginal\nBonuscredits,How does it work? : Hide\n\nCorrection\nBonus credits. How does it work? : Hide\n\n    What is a credit?\n\n\n    Original\n    Credits are distributed as a bonus to people who are seeding torrents.\n    You can find your total credit amount at the [color=#FF0000]top of this page[/color],\n    or on your user details page.\n\n    Correction (I think)\n    Credits are distributed as a bonus to people who are seeding torrents.\n    You can find your total credit amount at the top of any page in the top right corner, \n    or on your user details page.\n\n\n\nHow is the credit calculated? : Hide\n\nIs this one dangerous? If the formula has a quality element and whatnot that wont be factored into any calculation example? Will it? Or is that element gone now? Anyway, based on what I see before me here goes.\n\n\nI am seeding a partially downloaded torre[color=#FF0000]nt,bu[/color]t im not getting any credits? : Hide\nMissing space, lower case i in Im and missing apostrophe. Superfuous line break, \'credited\' implies ratio as well to some, so \'bonus credits\' seems more apt.\n\n    Remember that with partially downloaded torrents, \n    when seeding them you wont get credited with bonus,\n    Because the tracker will only see you as a leech!!\n    We recommend downloading the full torrent if you want to get credited.\n\nCorrection\nI am seeding a partially downloaded torrent, but I\'m not getting any credits? : Hide\n\n    Remember that with partially downloaded torrents, when seeding them you wont get credited with bonus,\n    Because the tracker will only see you as a leech!!\n    We recommend downloading the full torrent if you want to get bonus credits on that torrent.\n\n\n\n\nI registered an account but did not receive the confirmation e-mail! : Hide\nLine breaks.\n\n    All accounts are auto confirmed.\n    You will receive an email only if you reset your password.\n    Note though that if you didn\'t receive the email the first time\n    it will probably not succeed the second time either\n    so you should really try another email address.\n\n   Correction\n    All accounts are auto confirmed.\n    You will receive an email only if you reset your password.\n    Note though that if you didn\'t receive the email the first time it will probably not succeed the second time either so you should really try another email address.\n\n\nCan you rename my account? : Hide\n  Missing space before dash\n    (you need a good rea[color=#FF0000]son)- Se[/color]nd a message to admin\n\n\n\n\nMy IP address is dynamic. How do I stay logged in? : Hide\nSuperfluous line breaks\n    You do not have to anymore.\n    All you have to do is make sure you are logged in with your actual IP\n    when starting a torrent session. After that, even if the IP changes mid-session,\n    the seeding or leeching will continue and the statistics will update without any problem.\n\n   Correction\n    You do not have to anymore.\n    All you have to do is make sure you are logged in with your actual IP when starting a torrent session. After that, even if the IP changes mid-session, the seeding or leeching will continue and the statistics will update without any problem.\n\n\n\nWhy am I listed as not connectable? (And why should I care?) : Hide\nSuperfluous line breaks, or are these needed for alignment issues and lack of tab ability? Fuck, I just realised that might be the reason for them. How many times have i typed that now? Hope its not for naught.\n\n    The tracker has determined that you are firewalled or NATed and cannot accept incoming connections.\n\n    This means that other peers in the swarm will be unable to connect to you, only you to them.\n    Even worse, if two peers are both in this state they will not be able to connect at all.\n    This [color=#FF0000]has obviously[/color] a detrimental effect on the overall speed.\n\n    The way to solve the problem involves opening the ports used for incoming connections\n    (the same range you defined in your client) on the firewall\n    and/or configuring your NAT server to use a basic form of NAT for that range instead of NAPT\n    (the actual process differs widely between different router models.\n    Check your router documentation and/or support forum.\n    You will also find lots of information on the subject at http://portforward.com\n\n\n   Correction\n    \n    This obviously has a detrimental effect on the overall speed.\n\n    The way to solve the problem involves opening the ports used for incoming connections (the same range you defined in your client) on the firewall\n    and/or configuring your NAT server to use a basic form of NAT for that range instead of NAPT (the actual process differs widely between different router models.\n    Check your router documentation and/or support forum.\n    You will also find lots of information on the subject at http://portforward.com\n\n\nHow do I add an avatar to my profile? : Hide\nSuperfluous line breaks, and should xxx.freeimage be a hyerlink?\n\n    First, find an image that you like, and that is within the rules.\n    Then you will have to find a place to host it,\n    such as our own image hosting xxx.freeimage.us.\n    All that is left to do is to copy the image location to the avatar field in your profile.\n\n   Correction\n   