AT/ICS, or using a proxy), and some of the persons you share it with are also users, you may occasionally see their torrents listed in your profile.\n(If they start a torrent session from that IP and you were the last one to visit the site the torrent will be associated with you).\nNote that now torrents listed in your profile will always count towards your total stats.\n\nTo make sure your torrents show up in your profile you should visit the site immediately before starting a session.\n\n(The only way to completely stop foreign torrents from showing in profiles is to forbid users without an individual IP from accessing the site.\nYes, that means you. Complain at your own risk.)[/quote]\n\n\n\nQuestion, is this still valid. I thought I read somewhere the site doesnt rely on IP anymore for this stuff?\n\nThe next FAQ seems to confirm my suspicion.\n\nIf it doesnt someone more knowledgeable might need to look over the Multiple IP\'s and NAT/ISC topics (next two down from this one) too for same issues re: IP. Im not versed enough to say one way or the other.',86439,'2012-07-22 05:08:34'),(44685,5755,86439,'2012-07-22 04:45:17','[quote=yamchan07bb][quote=knickers]Can you fix this URL?\n\nIts in the spoiler under FAQ > Uploading > \nIs there any content thats not allowed to be Uploaded?\n\n[url=/articles.php?topic=forbidden[color=#FF0000]%20[/color]content]Forbidden Content[/url].[/quote]\nRemove that [color=#FF0000]%20[/color] and it\'ll be fixed:\n\n[url=/articles.php?topic=forbiddencontent]Forbidden Content[/url]\n\nAlso, who tried to edit the Upload rules article http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=upload ? External links need the [code]http://[/code] prefix:\n\n[code][url]xxx.freeimage.us[/url][/code] [color=#FF0000]will not work =[/color] [url]xxx.freeimage.us[/url]\n[code][url]http://xxx.freeimage.us[/url][/code] [color=#009900]will work =[/color] [url]http://xxx.freeimage.us[/url][/quote]\n\nThat was me, but Ive edited it back out, when I tested I saw i