owed the instructions in Clownius\'s Tracker Beta Test message that suggested resetting the password if it didn\'t work.  If it was a problem with FF, which it may be since the reset did work with IE, I\'ll never know if the original password would have worked with IE.  I did reset it to the exact same password, and that worked fine.',NULL,NULL),(44696,5755,47234,'2012-07-22 09:14:35','Wow you lot have been busy.  Now im trying to work out whats done and what needs work lol\n\nOk i think i caught up with everything i could fix.  If you spot anything i missed yell.\n\nAs for guides for multiple torrent clients we would need someone to write them up from scratch i think :(  Dont really have the time or knowledge to do that atm.',47234,'2012-07-22 10:49:49'),(44697,5769,90004,'2012-07-22 09:59:49','Hey all,\r\nI have some ideas about placing contents to be more simple, and more user-friendly. This one is really easy for the designers: The mini-userinfos on the top-right should be more user-friendly: In this way, users can easily see what\'s the situation.\r\n[img]http://i49.tinypic.com/23uek3r.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\nPlease, give a look at it, and think about it,while I making demonstrations to my other ideas.\r\nGreetings',NULL,NULL),(44698,5769,94804,'2012-07-22 10:24:37','may be asked already, but searching for \"user info\" or \"required\" returned no results, but was is \"required\" in mini-userinfo?',94804,'2012-07-22 10:25:15'),(44700,5753,85111,'2012-07-22 13:53:50','[quote=Lanz]same thing even after a ctrl/command+f5? Perhaps better to just widen that form though.[/quote]\r\n\r\nhey i can confirm its... drum rolls... FIXED!! Looks great!! here\'s what [u]torrents[/u] page looks like now >>\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=8FD1_500BE796][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=8FD1_500BE796[/img][/url] \r\n\r\nnote: the font is a little bigger on requests.php search box, would be pro if you guys could get it the same as the fixed torrents.php page... for continuity sake. heres what it looks like >>\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=9FE9_500BE796][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=9FE9_500BE796[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nkeep up the good work guys site is really coming along.',NULL,NULL),(44701,5769,86439,'2012-07-22 14:03:16','Required, is the Ratio you will be required to maintain to stay off the limiter. I believe.\n\n\n[quote=hapci]Hey all,\nI have some ideas about placing contents to be more simple, and more user-friendly. This one is really easy for the designers: The mini-userinfos on the top-right should be more user-friendly: In this way, users can easily see what\'s the situation.\n[img]http://i49.tinypic.com/23uek3r.jpg[/img]\n\nPlease, give a look at it, and think about it,while I making demonstrations to my other ideas.\nGreetings[/quote]\nAm I missing something there, did you actually state what your suggestion specifically is?\n\nIt would help the coders if they knew exactly what you thought needed changing.',86439,'2012-07-22 14:06:58'),(44702,5763,85636,'2012-07-22 14:14:35','[size=3][b][color=#FF0000]Moved as is to Help in its own chapter - need to decide if it stays there or goes to staff operator reference - Delete after double check[/color][/b][/size]\n\n\n[b][u]ChanServ Commands[/u][/b]\n\nChanServ allows you to register and control various aspects of channels. ChanServ can often prevent malicious users from â€œtaking overâ€ channels by limiting who is allowed channel operator privileges. Available commands are listed below; to use them, type [quote]/msg ChanServ command[/quote]. For more information on a specific command, type [quote]/msg ChanServ HELP command[/quote]\n \n[b]REGISTER[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  REGISTER channel password description\n \n Registers a channel in the ChanServ database.  In order\n to use this command, you must first be a channel operator\n on the channel you\'re trying to register.  The password\n is used with the IDENTIFY command to allow others to\n make changes to the channel settings at a later time.\n The last parameter, which must be included, is a\n general description of the channel\'s purpose.\n \n When you register a channel, you are recorded as the\n \"founder\" of the channel.  The channel founder is allowed\n to change all of the channel settings for the channel;\n ChanServ will also automatically give the founder\n channel-operator privileges when s/he enters the channel.\n See the ACCESS command (/msg ChanServ HELP ACCESS) for\n information on giving a subset of these privileges to\n other channel users.\n \n NOTICE: In order to register a channel, you must have\n first registered your nickname.  If you haven\'t,\n /msg ChanServ HELP for information on how to do so.[/quote]\n\n[b]IDENTIFY[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  IDENTIFY channel password\n \n Authenticates you to ChanServ as the founder of the given\n channel.  Many commands require you to use this command\n before using them.  The password should be the same one\n you sent with the REGISTER command.[/quote]\n \n[b]LOGOUT[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  LOGOUT channel nickname\n \n This command will log the selected nickname out meaning they\n would have to reidentify themselves to regain their access.\n \n If you are the founder of the channel, you can log out anybody,\n else you can only log out yourself.[/quote]\n \n[b]DROP[/b]\n[/quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ DROP channel\n \n Unregisters the named channel.  Can only be used by\n channel founder, who must use the IDENTIFY command first.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel option parameters\n \n Allows the channel founder to set various channel options\n and other information.\n \n Available options:\n \n     FOUNDER       Set the founder of a channel\n     SUCCESSOR     Set the successor for a channel\n     PASSWORD      Set the founder password\n     DESC          Set the channel description\n     URL           Associate a URL with the channel\n     EMAIL         Associate an E-mail address with the channel\n     ENTRYMSG      Set a message to be sent to users when they\n                      enter the channel\n     BANTYPE       Set how Services make bans on the channel\n     MLOCK         Lock channel modes on or off\n     KEEPTOPIC     Retain topic when channel is not in use\n     OPNOTICE      Send a notice when OP/DEOP commands are used\n     PEACE         Regulate the use of critical commands\n     PRIVATE       Hide channel from LIST command\n     RESTRICTED    Restrict access to the channel\n     SECURE        Activate ChanServ security features\n     SECUREOPS     Stricter control of chanop status\n     SECUREFOUNDER Stricter control of channel founder status\n     SIGNKICK      Sign kicks that are done with KICK command\n     TOPICLOCK     Topic can only be changed with TOPIC\n     XOP           Toggle the user privilege system\n \n Type /msg ChanServ HELP SET option for more information on a\n particular option.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET FOUNDER[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel FOUNDER nick\n \n Changes the founder of a channel.  The new nickname must\n be a registered one.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET SUCCESSOR[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel SUCCESSOR nick\n \n Changes the successor of a channel.  If the founder\'s\n nickname expires or is dropped while the channel is still\n registered, the successor will become the new founder of the\n channel.  However, if the successor already has too many\n channels registered (<num>), the channel will be dropped\n instead, just as if no successor had been set.  The new\n nickname must be a registered one.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET PASSWORD[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel PASSWORD password\n \n Sets the password used to identify as the founder of the\n channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET DESC[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel DESC description\n \n Sets the description for the channel, which shows up with\n the LIST and INFO commands.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET URL[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel URL <url>\n \n Associates the given URL with the channel.  This URL will\n be displayed whenever someone requests information on the\n channel with the INFO command.  If no parameter is given,\n deletes any current URL for the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET EMAIL[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel EMAIL [address]\n \n Associates the given E-mail address with the channel.\n This address will be displayed whenever someone requests\n information on the channel with the INFO command.  If no\n parameter is given, deletes any current E-mail address for\n the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET ENTRYMSG[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel ENTRYMSG [message]\n \n Sets the message which will be sent via /notice to users\n when they enter the channel.  If no parameter is given,\n causes no message to be sent upon entering the channel.[/quote]\n\n[b]SET BANTYPE[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel BANTYPE bantype\n \n Sets the ban type that will be used by services whenever\n they need to ban someone from your channel.\n \n bantype is a number between 0 and 3 that means:\n \n 0: ban in the form *!user@host\n 1: ban in the form *!*user@host\n 2: ban in the form *!*@host\n 3: ban in the form *!*user@*.domain[/quote]\n\n[b]SET KEEPTOPIC[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel KEEPTOPIC {ON | OFF}\n \n Enables or disables the topic retention option for a\n channel.  When topic retention is set, the topic for the\n channel will be remembered by ChanServ even after the\n last user leaves the channel, and will be restored the\n next time the channel is created.[/quote]\n\n[b]SET TOPICLOCK[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel TOPICLOCK {ON | OFF}\n \n Enables or disables the topic lock option for a channel.\n When topic lock is set, ChanServ will not allow the\n channel topic to be changed except via the TOPIC\n command.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET MLOCK[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel MLOCK modes\n \n Sets the mode-lock parameter for the channel. ChanServ\n allows you to define certain channel modes to be always\n on, off or free to be either on or off.\n \n The modes parameter is constructed exactly the same way\n as a /MODE command; that is, modes followed by a + are\n locked on, and modes followed by a - are locked off. Note,\n however, that unlike the /MODE command, each use of\n SET MLOCK will remove all modes previously locked before\n setting the new!\n \n Warning:  If you set a mode-locked key, as in the second\n example below, you should also set the RESTRICTED option for\n the channel (see HELP SET RESTRICTED), or anyone entering\n the channel when it is empty will be able to see the key!\n \n Examples:\n \n     SET #channel MLOCK +nt-iklps\n         Forces modes n and t on, and modes i, k, l, p, and\n         s off.  Mode m is left free to be either on or off.\n \n     SET #channel MLOCK +knst-ilmp my-key\n         Forces modes k, n, s, and t on, and modes i, l, m,\n         and p off.  Also forces the channel key to be\n         \"my-key\".\n \n     SET #channel MLOCK +\n         Removes the mode lock; all channel modes are free\n         to be either on or off.\n		 [/quote]\n[b]SET PEACE[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel PEACE {ON | OFF}\n \n Enables or disables the peace option for a channel.\n When peace is set, an user won\'t be able to kick,\n ban or remove a channel status of an user that has\n a level superior or equal to his via ChanServ commands.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET PRIVATE[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel PRIVATE {ON | OFF}\n \n Enables or disables the private option for a channel.\n When private is set, a /msg ChanServ LIST will not\n include the channel in any lists.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET RESTRICTED[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel RESTRICTED {ON | OFF}\n \n Enables or disables the restricted access option for a\n channel.  When restricted access is set, users not on\n the access list will instead be kicked and banned from the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET SECURE[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel SECURE {ON | OFF}\n \n Enables or disables ChanServ\'s security features for a\n channel.  When SECURE is set, only users who have\n registered their nicknames with ChanServ and IDENTIFY\'d\n with their password will be given access to the channel\n as controlled by the access list.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET SECUREOPS[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel SECUREOPS {ON | OFF}\n \n Enables or disables the secure ops option for a channel.\n When secure ops is set, users who are not on the userlist\n will not be allowed chanop status.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET SECUREFOUNDER[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel SECUREFOUNDER {ON | OFF}\n \n Enables or disables the secure founder option for a channel.\n When secure founder is set, only the real founder will be\n able to drop the channel, change its password, its founder and its\n successor, and not those who are IDENTIFY\'d with ChanServ.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET SIGNKICK[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel SIGNKICK {ON | LEVEL | OFF}\n \n Enables or disables signed kicks for a\n channel.  When SIGNKICK is set, kicks issued with\n ChanServ KICK command will have the nick that used the\n command in their reason.\n \n If you use LEVEL, those who have a level that is superior\n or equal to the SIGNKICK level on the channel won\'t have their\n kicks signed. See /msg ChanServ HELP LEVELS for more information.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET XOP[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel XOP {ON | OFF}\n \n Enables or disables the xOP lists system for a channel.\n When XOP is set, you have to use the AOP/SOP/VOP\n commands in order to give channel privileges to\n users, else you have to use the ACCESS command.\n \n Technical Note: when you switch from access list to xOP\n lists system, your level definitions and user levels will be\n changed, so you won\'t find the same values if you\n switch back to access system!\n \n You should also check that your users are in the good xOP\n list after the switch from access to xOP lists, because the\n guess is not always perfect... in fact, it is not recommended\n to use the xOP lists if you changed level definitions with\n the LEVELS command.\n \n Switching from xOP lists system to access list system\n causes no problem though.[/quote]\n \n[b]SET OPNOTICE[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SET channel OPNOTICE {ON | OFF}\n \n Enables or disables the op-notice option for a channel.\n When op-notice is set, ChanServ will send a notice to the\n channel whenever the OP or DEOP commands are used for a user\n in the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]AOP[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  AOP channel ADD nick\n         AOP channel DEL {nick | entry-num | list}\n         AOP channel LIST [mask | list]\n         AOP channel CLEAR\n \n Maintains the AOP (AutoOP) list for a channel. The AOP\n list gives users the right to be auto-opped on your channel,\n to unban or invite themselves if needed, to have their\n greet message showed on join, and so on.\n \n The AOP ADD command adds the given nickname to the\n AOP list.\n \n The AOP DEL command removes the given nick from the\n AOP list.  If a list of entry numbers is given, those\n entries are deleted.  (See the example for LIST below.)\n \n The AOP LIST command displays the AOP list.  If\n a wildcard mask is given, only those entries matching the\n mask are displayed.  If a list of entry numbers is given,\n only those entries are shown; for example:\n\n    AOP #channel LIST 2-5,7-9\n       Lists AOP entries numbered 2 through 5 and\n       7 through 9.\n \n The AOP CLEAR command clears all entries of the\n AOP list.\n \n The AOP ADD and AOP DEL commands are limited to\n SOPs or above, while the AOP CLEAR command can only\n be used by the channel founder. However, any user on the\n AOP list may use the AOP LIST command.\n \n This command may have been disabled for your channel, and\n in that case you need to use the access list. See\n /msg ChanServ HELP ACCESS for information about the access list,\n and /msg ChanServ HELP SET XOP to know how to toggle between\n the access list and xOP list systems.[/quote]\n \n[b]HOP[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  HOP channel ADD nick\n         HOP channel DEL {nick | entry-num | list}\n         HOP channel LIST [mask | list]\n         HOP channel CLEAR\n \n Maintains the HOP (HalfOP) list for a channel. The HOP\n list gives users the right to be auto-halfopped on your\n channel.\n \n The HOP ADD command adds the given nickname to the\n HOP list.\n \n The HOP DEL command removes the given nick from the\n HOP list.  If a list of entry numbers is given, those\n entries are deleted.  (See the example for LIST below.)\n \n The HOP LIST command displays the HOP list.  If\n a wildcard mask is given, only those entries matching the\n mask are displayed.  If a list of entry numbers is given,\n only those entries are shown; for example:\n\n    HOP #channel LIST 2-5,7-9\n       Lists HOP entries numbered 2 through 5 and\n       7 through 9.\n \n The HOP CLEAR command clears all entries of the\n HOP list.\n \n The HOP ADD, HOP DEL and HOP LIST commands are\n limited to AOPs or above, while the HOP CLEAR command\n can only be used by the channel founder.\n \n This command may have been disabled for your channel, and\n in that case you need to use the access list. See\n /msg ChanServ HELP ACCESS for information about the access list,\n and /msg ChanServ HELP SET XOP to know how to toggle between\n the access list and xOP list systems.[/quote]\n \n[b]SOP[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  SOP channel ADD nick\n         SOP channel DEL {nick | entry-num | list}\n         SOP channel LIST [mask | list]\n         SOP channel CLEAR\n \n Maintains the SOP (SuperOP) list for a channel. The SOP\n list gives users all rights given by the AOP list, and adds\n those needed to use the AutoKick and the BadWords lists,\n to send and read channel memos, and so on.\n \n The SOP ADD command adds the given nickname to the\n SOP list.\n \n The SOP DEL command removes the given nick from the\n SOP list.  If a list of entry numbers is given, those\n entries are deleted.  (See the example for LIST below.)\n \n The SOP LIST command displays the SOP list.  If\n a wildcard mask is given, only those entries matching the\n mask are displayed.  If a list of entry numbers is given,\n only those entries are shown; for example:\n\n    SOP #channel LIST 2-5,7-9\n       Lists AOP entries numbered 2 through 5 and\n       7 through 9.\n \n The SOP CLEAR command clears all entries of the\n SOP list.\n \n The SOP ADD, SOP DEL and SOP CLEAR commands are\n limited to the channel founder. However, any user on the\n AOP list may use the SOP LIST command.\n \n This command may have been disabled for your channel, and\n in that case you need to use the access list. See\n /msg ChanServ HELP ACCESS for information about the access list,\n and /msg ChanServ HELP SET XOP to know how to toggle between\n the access list and xOP list systems.[/quote]\n \n[b]VOP[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  VOP channel ADD nick\n         VOP channel DEL {nick | entry-num | list}\n         VOP channel LIST [mask | list]\n         VOP channel CLEAR\n \n Maintains the VOP (VOicePeople) list for a channel.\n The VOP list allows users to be auto-voiced and to voice\n themselves if they aren\'t.\n \n The VOP ADD command adds the given nickname to the\n VOP list.\n \n The VOP DEL command removes the given nick from the\n VOP list.  If a list of entry numbers is given, those\n entries are deleted.  (See the example for LIST below.)\n \n The VOP LIST command displays the VOP list.  If\n a wildcard mask is given, only those entries matching the\n mask are displayed.  If a list of entry numbers is given,\n only those entries are shown; for example:\n\n    VOP #channel LIST 2-5,7-9\n       Lists VOP entries numbered 2 through 5 and\n       7 through 9.\n \n The VOP CLEAR command clears all entries of the\n VOP list.\n \n The VOP ADD, VOP DEL and VOP LIST commands are\n limited to AOPs or above, while the VOP CLEAR command\n can only be used by the channel founder.\n \n This command may have been disabled for your channel, and\n in that case you need to use the access list. See\n /msg ChanServ HELP ACCESS for information about the access list,\n and /msg ChanServ HELP SET XOP to know how to toggle between\n the access list and xOP list systems.[/quote]\n \n[b]ACCESS[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  ACCESS channel ADD nick level\n         ACCESS channel DEL {nick | entry-num | list}\n         ACCESS channel LIST [mask | list]\n         ACCESS channel CLEAR\n \n Maintains the access list for a channel.  The access\n list specifies which users are allowed chanop status or\n access to ChanServ commands on the channel.  Different\n user levels allow for access to different subsets of\n privileges; /msg ChanServ HELP ACCESS LEVELS for more\n specific information.  Any nick not on the access list has\n a user level of 0.\n \n The ACCESS ADD command adds the given nickname to the\n access list with the given user level; if the nick is\n already present on the list, its access level is changed to\n the level specified in the command.  The level specified\n must be less than that of the user giving the command, and\n if the nick is already on the access list, the current\n access level of that nick must be less than the access level\n of the user giving the command.\n \n The ACCESS DEL command removes the given nick from the\n access list.  If a list of entry numbers is given, those\n entries are deleted.  (See the example for LIST below.)\n \n The ACCESS LIST command displays the access list.  If\n a wildcard mask is given, only those entries matching the\n mask are displayed.  If a list of entry numbers is given,\n only those entries are shown; for example:\n\n    ACCESS #channel LIST 2-5,7-9\n       Lists access entries numbered 2 through 5 and\n       7 through 9.\n \n The ACCESS CLEAR command clears all entries of the\n access list.[/quote]\n \n[b]ACCESS LEVELS[/b]\n[quote] User access levels\n \n By default, the following access levels are defined:\n \n    Founder   Full access to ChanServ functions; automatic\n                      opping upon entering channel.  Note\n                      that only one person may have founder\n                      status (it can be given using the\n                      ACCESS command and using level 9999).\n         10   Access to AKICK command; automatic opping.\n          5   Automatic opping.\n          3   Automatic voicing.\n          0   No special privileges; can be opped by other\n                      ops (unless secure-ops is set).\n         <0   May not be opped.\n \n These levels may be changed, or new ones added, using the\n LEVELS command; type /msg ChanServ HELP LEVELS for\n information.[/quote]\n\n[b]AKICK[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  AKICK channel ADD {nick | mask} [reason]\n         AKICK channel STICK mask\n         AKICK channel UNSTICK mask\n         AKICK channel DEL {nick | mask | entry-num | list}\n         AKICK channel LIST [mask | entry-num | list]\n         AKICK channel VIEW [mask | entry-num | list]\n         AKICK channel ENFORCE\n         AKICK channel CLEAR\n \n Maintains the AutoKick list for a channel.  If a user\n on the AutoKick list attempts to join the channel,\n ChanServ will ban that user from the channel, then kick\n the user.\n \n The AKICK ADD command adds the given nick or usermask\n to the AutoKick list.  If a reason is given with\n the command, that reason will be used when the user is\n kicked; if not, the default reason is \"You have been\n banned from the channel\".\n When akicking a registered nick the nickserv account\n will be added to the akick list instead of the mask.\n All users within that nickgroup will then be akicked.\n \n The AKICK STICK command permanently bans the given mask\n on the channel. If someone tries to remove the ban, ChanServ\n will automatically set it again. You can\'t use it for\n registered nicks.\n \n The AKICK UNSTICK command cancels the effect of the\n AKICK STICK command, so you\'ll be able to unset the\n ban again on the channel.\n \n The AKICK DEL command removes the given nick or mask\n from the AutoKick list.  It does not, however, remove any\n bans placed by an AutoKick; those must be removed\n manually.\n \n The AKICK LIST command displays the AutoKick list, or\n optionally only those AutoKick entries which match the\n given mask.\n \n The AKICK VIEW command is a more verbose version of\n AKICK LIST command.\n \n The AKICK ENFORCE command causes ChanServ to enforce the\n current AKICK list by removing those users who match an\n AKICK mask.\n \n The AKICK CLEAR command clears all entries of the\n akick list.[/quote]\n \n[b]LEVELS[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  LEVELS channel SET type level\n         LEVELS channel {DIS | DISABLE} type\n         LEVELS channel LIST\n         LEVELS channel RESET\n \n The LEVELS command allows fine control over the meaning of\n the numeric access levels used for channels.  With this\n command, you can define the access level required for most\n of ChanServ\'s functions.  (The SET FOUNDER and SET PASSWORD\n commands, as well as this command, are always restricted to\n the channel founder.)\n \n LEVELS SET allows the access level for a function or group of\n functions to be changed.  LEVELS DISABLE (or DIS for short)\n disables an automatic feature or disallows access to a\n function by anyone other than the channel founder.\n LEVELS LIST shows the current levels for each function or\n group of functions.  LEVELS RESET resets the levels to the\n default levels of a newly-created channel (see\n HELP ACCESS LEVELS).\n \n For a list of the features and functions whose levels can be\n set, see HELP LEVELS DESC.[/quote]\n \n[b]INFO[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  INFO channel [ALL]\n \n Lists information about the named registered channel,\n including its founder, time of registration, last time\n used, description, and mode lock, if any. If ALL is\n specified, the entry message and successor will also\n be displayed.\n \n By default, the ALL option is limited to those with\n founder access on the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]LIST[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  LIST pattern\n \n Lists all registered channels matching the given pattern.\n (Channels with the PRIVATE option set are not listed.)\n Note that a preceding \'#\' specifies a range, channel names\n are to be written without \'#\'.[/quote]\n \n[b]OP[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  OP [#channel [nick]]\n \n Ops a selected nick on a channel. If nick is not given,\n it will op you. If channel and nick are not given,\n it will op you on all channels you\'re on, provided you\n have the rights to.\n \n By default, limited to AOPs or those with level 5 access\n and above on the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]DEOP[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  DEOP [#channel [nick]]\n \n Deops a selected nick on a channel. If nick is not given,\n it will deop you. If channel and nick are not given,\n it will deop you on all channels you\'re on, provided you\n have the rights to.\n \n By default, limited to AOPs or those with level 5 access\n and above on the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]VOICE[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  VOICE [#channel [nick]]\n \n Voices a selected nick on a channel. If nick is not given,\n it will voice you. If channel and nick are not given,\n it will voice you on all channels you\'re on, provided you\n have the rights to.\n \n By default, limited to AOPs or those with level 5 access\n and above on the channel, or to VOPs or those with level 3\n and above for self voicing.[/quote]\n \n[b]DEVOICE[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  DEVOICE [#channel [nick]]\n \n Devoices a selected nick on a channel. If nick is not given,\n it will devoice you. If channel and nick are not given,\n it will devoice you on all channels you\'re on, provided you\n have the rights to.\n \n By default, limited to AOPs or those with level 5 access\n and above on the channel, or to VOPs or those with level 3\n and above for self devoicing.[/quote]\n \n[b]HALFOP[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  HALFOP [#channel [nick]]\n \n Halfops a selected nick on a channel. If nick is not given,\n it will halfop you. If channel and nick are not given,\n it will halfop you on all channels you\'re on, provided you\n have the rights to.\n \n By default, limited to AOPs and those with level 5 access\n and above on the channel, or to HOPs or those with level 4\n and above for self halfopping.[/quote]\n \n[b]DEHALFOP[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  DEHALFOP [#channel [nick]]\n \n Dehalfops a selected nick on a channel. If nick is not given,\n it will dehalfop you. If channel and nick are not given,\n it will dehalfop you on all channels you\'re on, provided you\n have the rights to.\n \n By default, limited to AOPs and those with level 5 access\n and above on the channel, or to HOPs or those with level 4\n and above for self dehalfopping.[/quote]\n \n[b]PROTECT[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  PROTECT [#channel [nick]]\n \n Protects a selected nick on a channel. If nick is not given,\n it will protect you. If channel and nick are not given,\n it will protect you on all channels you\'re on, provided you\n have the rights to.\n \n By default, limited to the founder, or to SOPs or those with\n level 10 and above on the channel for self protecting.[/quote]\n \n[b]DEPROTECT[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  DEPROTECT [#channel [nick]]\n \n Deprotects a selected nick on a channel. If nick is not given,\n it will deprotect you. If channel and nick are not given,\n it will deprotect you on all channels you\'re on, provided you\n have the rights to.\n \n By default, limited to the founder, or to SOPs or those with\n level 10 and above on the channel for self deprotecting.[/quote]\n \n[b]OWNER[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  OWNER [#channel]\n \n Gives you owner status on channel. If channel is not\n given, it will give you owner status on all channels you\'re\n on, provided you have the rights to.\n \n Limited to those with founder access on the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]DEOWNER[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  DEOWNER [#channel]\n \n Removes your owner status on channel. If channel is\n not given, it will remove your owner status on all channels\n you\'re on, provided you have the rights to.\n \n Limited to those with founder access on the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]INVITE[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  INVITE channel\n \n Tells ChanServ to invite you into the given channel.\n \n By default, limited to AOPs or those with level 5 and above\n on the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]UNBAN[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  UNBAN channel\n \n Tells ChanServ to remove all bans preventing you from\n entering the given channel.\n \n By default, limited to AOPs or those with level 5 and above\n on the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]KICK[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  KICK [#channel [nick [reason]]]\n \n Kicks a selected nick on a channel. If nick is not given,\n it will kick you. If channel and nick are not given,\n it will kick you on all channels you\'re on, provided you\n have the rights to.\n \n By default, limited to AOPs or those with level 5 access\n and above on the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]BAN[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  BAN [#channel [nick [reason]]]\n \n Bans a selected nick on a channel. If nick is not given,\n it will ban you. If channel and nick are not given,\n it will ban you on all channels you\'re on, provided you\n have the rights to.\n \n By default, limited to AOPs or those with level 5 access\n and above on the channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]TOPIC[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  TOPIC channel [topic]\n \n Causes ChanServ to set the channel topic to the one\n specified. If topic is not given, then an empty topic\n is set. This command is most useful in conjunction\n with SET TOPICLOCK. See /msg ChanServ HELP SET TOPICLOCK\n for more information.\n \n By default, limited to those with founder access on the\n channel. [/quote]\n \n[b]CLEAR[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  CLEAR channel what\n \n Tells ChanServ to clear certain settings on a channel.  what\n can be any of the following:\n \n      MODES    Resets all modes on the channel (i.e. clears\n                   modes i,k,l,m,n,p,s,t).\n      BANS     Clears all bans on the channel.\n      EXCEPTS  Clears all excepts on the channel.\n      INVITES  Clears all invites on the channel.\n      OPS      Removes channel-operator status (mode +o) from\n                   all channel operators.\n      HOPS     Removes channel-halfoperator status (mode +h) from\n                   all channel halfoperators, if supported.\n      VOICES   Removes \"voice\" status (mode +v) from anyone\n                   with that mode set.\n      USERS    Removes (kicks) all users from the channel.\n \n By default, limited to those with founder access on the\n channel.[/quote]\n \n[b]GETKEY[/b]\n[quote] Syntax: /msg ChanServ  GETKEY channel\n \n Returns the key of the given channel. This is a command\n mainly intended to be used by bots and/or scripts, so\n the output is in the following way:\n \n KEY <channel> <key>\n \n key is \"NO KEY\" if no key is set.[/quote]',70679,'2012-09-11 15:40:13'),(44703,5770,51383,'2012-07-22 18:02:24','[font=Arial][size=2][color=#0000FF]title search / phrase search / file search\r\n\r\n[b]title search[/b]\r\nCheckbox \"search in titles only\"\r\n\r\n[b]phrase search[/b]\r\n[url=http://support.google.com/websearch/bin/answer.py?hl=en&answer=136861&ctx=cb&src=cb&cbid=-q5qm00k5vv11]http://support.google.com/websearch/bin/answer.py?hl=en&answer=136861&ctx=cb&src=cb&cbid=-q5qm00k5vv11[/url]\r\n[url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phrase_search]http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phrase_search[/url]\r\n\r\n[b]file search[/b]\r\nSearch in Filelist[/color][/size][/font]',NULL,NULL),(44704,5767,48010,'2012-07-22 18:05:19','[quote=tmarkey]:unsure: Seems we cannot change the title of our torrents? Am I missing a button somewhere? Used to be able to do that. Often we will do a title wrong and need to fix that, so that is an important part of edit function. Thanks.\r\n\r\nI\'m also having trouble figuring out how to add a cover image :hmmm:[/quote]\r\n\r\nTo edit the title click on the torrent then edit torrent - do you see this at the top of the page\r\n\r\n[Edit Torrent] [Bookmark] [View log] [Report] [Remove] \r\n\r\nyou then see rename title - just edit it and hit rename\r\n\r\nworks for me\r\n\r\nI haven\'t tried cover images so can\'t help there\r\n\r\nplease confirm here that it works for you',NULL,NULL),(44705,5767,129045,'2012-07-22 18:54:52','Only Staff can edit the titles, it was discussed here: http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2697\r\n\r\nIt\'s still to be determined if users will have that ability again.',129045,'2012-07-22 19:19:14'),(44706,5770,129045,'2012-07-22 19:07:30','[quote=shifted22][font=Arial][size=2][color=#0000FF]title search / phrase search / file search\r\n\r\n[b]title search[/b]\r\nCheckbox \"search in titles only\"\r\n\r\n[b]phrase search[/b]\r\n[url=http://support.google.com/websearch/bin/answer.py?hl=en&answer=136861&ctx=cb&src=cb&cbid=-q5qm00k5vv11]http://support.google.com/websearch/bin/answer.py?hl=en&answer=136861&ctx=cb&src=cb&cbid=-q5qm00k5vv11[/url]\r\n[url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phrase_search]http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phrase_search[/url]\r\n\r\n[b]file search[/b]\r\nSearch in Filelist[/color][/size][/font][/quote]\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=search\r\n\r\nChange to [i][b]Advanced Search[/b][/i] and you\'ll be able to search in the [b]file list[/b].\r\n\r\n[b]Phrase search[/b] is already in, use double quotes: [color=#FF0000]\"[/color]exact match[color=#FF0000]\"[/color] (Note: Article needs editing.)\r\n\r\nI guess, [b]title search only[/b] is the only thing that isn\'t available\r\n\r\n[i][b]EDIT:[/b][/i] You used the old section imported from EMP.me, the correct [b]Suggestions[/b] section, is this one: http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewforum&forumid=18',129045,'2012-07-22 19:11:13'),(44707,5619,84499,'2012-07-22 20:11:59','\r\n[quote=Lanz]Well I\'ve looked it over several times, obviously I\'m blind to the bug but I\'m gonna take another look and see what I can find.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nI have also looked at this in the code and I\'ll be buggered if I can even see anywhere a bug could get in... there really isnt much code inbetween entering the pw and checking it against the hash.. and we know the hashes themselves are correct (if you hash your pw you get whats stored in the db). Its a strange one!\r\n\r\n :bugchases: ',NULL,NULL),(44708,5769,84499,'2012-07-22 20:51:58','[quote=hapci]Hey all,\r\nI have some ideas about placing contents to be more simple, and more user-friendly. This one is really easy for the designers: The mini-userinfos on the top-right should be more user-friendly: In this way, users can easily see what\'s the situation.\r\n[img]http://i49.tinypic.com/23uek3r.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\nPlease, give a look at it, and think about it,while I making demonstrations to my other ideas.\r\nGreetings[/quote]\r\n[img]http://i49.tinypic.com/23uek3r.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\nyeah I think I prefer it your way too... still what do others think? opinions?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44709,5769,84499,'2012-07-22 20:53:39','[quote=knickers]Required, is the Ratio you will be required to maintain to stay off the limiter. I believe.\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=hapci]Hey all,\r\nI have some ideas about placing contents to be more simple, and more user-friendly. This one is really easy for the designers: The mini-userinfos on the top-right should be more user-friendly: In this way, users can easily see what\'s the situation.\r\n[img]http://i49.tinypic.com/23uek3r.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\nPlease, give a look at it, and think about it,while I making demonstrations to my other ideas.\r\nGreetings[/quote]\r\nAm I missing something there, did you actually state what your suggestion specifically is?\r\n\r\nIt would help the coders if they knew exactly what you thought needed changing.[/quote]\r\n\r\nCompare his pic to the top right of the current page - he has rearranged the user info.',NULL,NULL),(44710,5767,84499,'2012-07-22 21:30:48','[quote=tmarkey]:unsure: Seems we cannot change the title of our torrents? Am I missing a button somewhere? Used to be able to do that. Often we will do a title wrong and need to fix that, so that is an important part of edit function. Thanks.\r\n\r\nI\'m also having trouble figuring out how to add a cover image :hmmm:[/quote]\r\n\r\nTitles... yeah I am not sure what we are going to do about that.\r\n\r\n\r\nCover Image - you should see this when you edit your torrent: \r\n(and there is a similar input field on the upload page)\r\n\r\nenter the url for your image and you should be good to go :smile1:\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adl501vq.png[/img]',NULL,NULL),(44711,5771,129045,'2012-07-22 21:46:10','[*] Moving the [b]Tag list[/b] above the \"[b]100+ Results[/b]\" text (number of torrents found)\r\n[*] [b]Tweaking the Tag list usage, so every time an user adds a tag [i](by clicking on it in the list)[/i], the focus would go to the last tag added[/b]. As of now, if the user adds too many tags, he\'ll not be able to see the tags added beyond the visible area, in order to see them, he needs to click on the search field and use the [b]Left Arrow[/b] or the [b]End[/b] key.\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=AB5E_500C5561][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=AB5E_500C5561[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[b]Ah, at least something good came out of that bloody search problem[/b] lol.\r\nMoving the [b]Tag list[/b] to under the Tag search field feels natural, but it\'s spoiled by having the [i]number of torrents found[/i] laying there between them :hmmm:',129045,'2012-07-22 21:59:25'),(44712,5769,94804,'2012-07-22 21:50:06','I.M.O everyting is handy right now except for that \"required\" part, coild auto-PM someone if he/she\'s in the dangerzone',NULL,NULL),(44713,5772,94804,'2012-07-22 22:11:21','250000 and 100000 are too similar i.m.o. 250000 should be changed into something else? for instance\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-85FF_500C5E3C.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-85FF_500C5E3C.gif[/img][/url]\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-BC5E_500C5E3C.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-BC5E_500C5E3C.jpg[/img][/url]\n',94804,'2012-07-22 22:12:32'),(44714,5697,94804,'2012-07-22 22:21:09','By reading this I was quite amazed, why change it (it\'s working now, isn\'t it?) editable titles seem good to me.............\n\nI agree with Clownius, changing\'s annoying to say the least, but we can do it now, right? why change that?',94804,'2012-07-22 22:23:45'),(44715,5767,94804,'2012-07-22 22:27:34','I think that cover-image\'s really nice, and you should keep it, but a line explaining what kind of URL is required for insertion (sounds dirtier than it actually is ;) would be nice',94804,'2012-07-22 22:28:09'),(44716,5773,94804,'2012-07-22 22:35:22','when browsing torrents I get the options \"FL\" &\"DS\" even if they\'re not my own uploads, can\'t be good, right?',NULL,NULL),(44717,5773,129045,'2012-07-22 22:57:16','Do you have any Slots available? (in the top bar, it should be listed to the left of your [b]Credits[/b], under the [b]Up[/b] amount)\r\n\r\nAre you seeing it in the browsing list? Can you take a screenshot? Some lists will show [DL] [FL] and [RP], never saw a [DS] one.\r\n\r\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-BC28_500C6AD6.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\nOr you mean this:\r\n\r\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-18FB_500C6890.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\nIf you have any slots, then it\'s normal for that to show up :hmmm:',129045,'2012-07-22 23:05:06'),(44720,5773,94804,'2012-07-22 23:14:45','oow nevermind, saw it\'s like that on the old site as well. Sorry',NULL,NULL),(44722,5767,84499,'2012-07-22 23:26:39','\r\n\r\ngood idea I added some text :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(44723,5771,84499,'2012-07-22 23:47:43','\r\n\r\nokay done :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(44724,5768,84499,'2012-07-22 23:59:32','\r\n\r\n[quote=ArtaraBlue]Hello everyone again, I decided to test out the Custom Title feature here and I noticed that the long message I wanted to input on purpose did not get posted after two tries and this wasting credits. It appears that the dialog box has unlimited characters but I don\'t know where it cuts off. Any admin know what the character limit is so no one gets surprised if they decide to input a long message and lose credits? :o\r\n\r\nEDIT: Oops nevermind, it doesn\'t show next to the person\'s name in the forums. You have to click on their profile to see it lol.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYou bring up a good point... we really dont want pervs to have silly long titles so I\'ve set the max to 32 characters.',NULL,NULL),(44725,5768,129045,'2012-07-23 00:25:24','(ãƒŽ`Ð”Â´)&#12494\r\n\r\nlol\r\n\r\nNow my title is broken ;_;\r\n\r\n(ãƒŽ`Ð”Â´)ãƒŽå½¡â”»â”â”» [b][i]Damn you Unicode characters![/i][/b]\r\n',129045,'2012-07-23 00:40:06'),(44726,5768,84499,'2012-07-23 00:46:16','\r\nsorry bout that :D',NULL,NULL),(44727,5637,92503,'2012-07-23 02:18:07','Ditto, FF 14.',NULL,NULL),(44728,5637,85636,'2012-07-23 03:28:47','Same in Chromium 18',NULL,NULL),(44729,5637,84499,'2012-07-23 04:57:59','\r\n\r\nshould be fixed now  :borg: ',NULL,NULL),(44730,5708,84499,'2012-07-23 05:52:32','\r\n\r\nshould be fixed, I removed the last few wiki links so you shouldnt see any anywhere now  :pythfoot: ',NULL,NULL),(44731,5768,115474,'2012-07-23 06:06:04','[quote=mifune][quote=ArtaraBlue]Hello everyone again, I decided to test out the Custom Title feature here and I noticed that the long message I wanted to input on purpose did not get posted after two tries and this wasting credits. It appears that the dialog box has unlimited characters but I don\'t know where it cuts off. Any admin know what the character limit is so no one gets surprised if they decide to input a long message and lose credits? :o\r\n\r\nEDIT: Oops nevermind, it doesn\'t show next to the person\'s name in the forums. You have to click on their profile to see it lol.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYou bring up a good point... we really dont want pervs to have silly long titles so I\'ve set the max to 32 characters.[/quote]\r\nYay! I do know that someone would eventually do that lol. Cool, i\'ll change it back to my old title. Not that it matters anyway lol.',NULL,NULL),(44732,5678,84499,'2012-07-23 06:34:14','\r\n\r\ndone, except the \'no new notifications\' bit of the message has to stay as if you have filters set but no notifications yet that is also the message you get.',NULL,NULL),(44733,5709,84499,'2012-07-23 06:36:55',' :evilbunny: ',NULL,NULL),(44734,5747,84499,'2012-07-23 06:37:02',' :evilbunny: ',NULL,NULL),(44735,5674,84499,'2012-07-23 06:37:13',' :evilbunny: ',NULL,NULL),(44736,5693,84499,'2012-07-23 06:37:35',' :evilbunny: ',NULL,NULL),(44737,5671,84499,'2012-07-23 06:37:47',' :evilbunny: ',NULL,NULL),(44738,5684,84499,'2012-07-23 06:38:03',' :evilbunny: ',NULL,NULL),(44739,5658,84499,'2012-07-23 06:38:59',' :evilbunny: ',NULL,NULL),(44740,5746,84499,'2012-07-23 06:40:17',' :evilbunny: ',NULL,NULL),(44741,5697,84499,'2012-07-23 06:41:49',' :evilbunny: ',NULL,NULL),(44742,5774,89443,'2012-07-23 11:09:31','(Sorry, I couldn\'t think of a better thread title)\r\n\r\nI think it would be good if there was a way to show a user that the thread where they posted has had new replies.\r\n\r\nAnother problem is that you can\'t tell which threads are new and which are old.\r\n\r\nThoughts?',NULL,NULL),(44743,5746,85111,'2012-07-23 11:23:10','[quote=Lanz] You haven\'t increased the default font size or something? They look too big to be the default size.[/quote]\r\n\r\nnah i havent its default atm at medium size, times 16, page zoom 100% in chrome.. ill try and see if same thing happens at my imac at work in different browsers when i get in, that will confirm its a mac problem and not just isolated incident.',NULL,NULL),(44744,5697,85111,'2012-07-23 11:30:34','my vote goes to editable tags at least.. sometimes users comment like the name of a pornstar when i didnt know her name. instantly adding tags will only benefit users at a more speedy rate. as for titles im 50/50.. i change the titles of my torrents sometimes as i do a lot of typo\'s but i understand clownius when he says changing them is annoying. guess i\'ll just have to pay extra careful attention before pressing that upload torrent button. ',NULL,NULL),(44745,5697,47234,'2012-07-23 11:37:43','When people remember a pornstar name they can always add the tag themselves under the system here.  Im all for leaving tags well alone to be honest.  I dont think my opinion on that will change\r\n\r\nAt least give it time to see if its working :)\r\n\r\nAs for title i could be swayed on that one',NULL,NULL),(44746,5775,85111,'2012-07-23 13:32:46','Not really a suggestion but something to think about. \n\nAs of now everyone can add and delete torrents to a particular collage. Now what if a troll decides to go on a collage and remove torrents just for kicks or add non related torrents to it.. shouldn\'t there be someone who moderates this stuff who isn\'t one of us very trust worthy citizens? Just thought I\'d throw it out there. Maybe only the creator of the collage should have access to removal rights or something along those lines.',85111,'2012-07-23 13:38:49'),(44747,5775,47234,'2012-07-23 13:42:07','Hmmm im guessing that sort of thing would lead to a swift kick up the backside by the first staff member alerted to it......  Not to mention a sudden loss of editing rights.\r\n\r\nBut maybe we could bump it to Sextreme and above?',NULL,NULL),(44748,5774,129045,'2012-07-23 14:24:41','Odd :hmmm:\r\n\r\nI\'m pretty sure, users could see these icons changing:\r\n\r\n[code]http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/read.png[/code][img]http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/read.png[/img]\r\n[code]http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/unread.png[/code][img]http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/unread.png[/img]\r\n\r\n[s]But looking here now, everything is showing up as \"Read\"[/s]\r\n\r\nAlso, this will most likely be fixed soon, I wouldn\'t worry too much :)',129045,'2012-07-23 16:44:48'),(44749,5775,85111,'2012-07-23 14:32:35','[quote=Clownius]Hmmm im guessing that sort of thing would lead to a swift kick up the backside by the first staff member alerted to it......  Not to mention a sudden loss of editing rights.\r\n\r\nBut maybe we could bump it to Sextreme and above?[/quote]\r\n\r\nyeh because I just removed one of the london.keys torrent from a collage with no problems. If i was a dickhead I could just go through every single collage and remove all of them just for laughs..  I\'d be pretty pissed if my awesome London Keys collage with 50+ torrents got screwed up by some wanker... also there\'s no way to track the culprit (unless your an admin I\'d presume) so normal users wouldn\'t be able to report him anyway.. \r\n\r\ni think only giving Removal rights to the Collage creator/Sextreme users would be better... also would mean staff wouldn\'t have to be policing as much.',NULL,NULL),(44750,5619,41468,'2012-07-23 14:38:07','logged in 1st try.\r\nwith user and password  :smile1: \r\nno problem at all.\r\n\r\nwin 7 64bit (running cracked bios loader) \r\nfirefox v14.0.1\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44752,5697,49532,'2012-07-23 14:50:50','There is one reason, why I\'m for being able to edit everything.  ERRORS!!!\r\nI\'m dyslexic and I can\'ttype worth shit.   I would really like to be abl;e to fix things beforeer too many poeplwe see themn.  Do you really want the to be a torrent titled \"Barea Benttit Nega-Park\"?\r\n\r\n-C',NULL,NULL),(44753,5635,49532,'2012-07-23 15:24:48','As I see it the main point of a bonus system is to encourage as many people as possible to seed as long as possible.   Having a cap of 60 gives a subliminal suggestion that you should only seed 60 torrents. \r\n\r\n Also, I think it would be better to add to the upload rather than remove from the download, psychologically people respond more to getting a positive rather than removing a negative.\r\n\r\nOne other thing, I think the bonus should be higher for seeding older or less seeded torrents. ',NULL,NULL),(44754,5775,129045,'2012-07-23 15:33:43','Yeah... changes doesn\'t seem to be tracked in the Logs http://empornium.mooo.com/log.php\r\n\r\nJerks always spoiling everything D:\r\n\r\n\r\nLeaving it to only be changed by the creator or special users (above Good Perv) and Staff could work. But that would rely on the fact that the creator would like to spend time mantaining the Collage. Other users can drop comments pointing to related torrents to be added etc, but if the creator stop paying attention to it, that\'s will still result in extra work for someone else (Staff or special users).\r\n\r\n:hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(44755,5774,84499,'2012-07-23 15:34:26','\r\n\r\nthe read/unread icons work for me.',NULL,NULL),(44756,5774,129045,'2012-07-23 15:45:36','I must be confusing it, sorry :hmmm:\r\n\r\nI can\'t see any changes on http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php (all icons show up as \"Read\")\r\n\r\nBut in each section (Suggestions, Bugs, etc) the icon will show up ok for threads with unread posts. Will pay extra attention on the next time.\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b] Yeah, they are ok. My bad :(',129045,'2012-07-23 16:44:36'),(44757,5776,49532,'2012-07-23 16:00:23','Heres a way to make uploading screenshots easier, and at the same time reduce the problem of unauthorized image host:  \n\nIn the torrent upload form include fields to upload images xxx.freeimage.us, and automaticly insert the image bbcode into the decscription field.',49532,'2012-07-23 16:01:23'),(44758,5777,129045,'2012-07-23 16:13:06','[*]In blue, that\'s the wasted space\r\n[*]In red, that\'s the area covers will always occupy (5 covers side by side, regardless of display choice - 10, 25, 50, 100 or All)\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=F159_500D56F4][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=F159_500D56F4&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat I\'m proposing, make it more like the \"Recent Uploads\" covers display:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=968A_500D57D2][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=968A_500D57D2&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nIt makes better use of the whole space and the images keep their aspect ratios :)',NULL,NULL),(44759,5671,129045,'2012-07-23 16:17:41','[size=2][color=#FF0000]Could somebody check this:[/color] It will only affect uploads without cover images[/size]\r\n\r\nI noticed it while browsing Collages http://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php?id=3 , it\'ll display the title in plain text for uploads without cover images.\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, \"Recent Uploads\" section in the user\'s profile page, will only display uploads that contain a cover image.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[b][color=#FF0000]EDIT:[/color][/b] From what I tested here, that really seems to be the cause.\r\n\r\nCheck \"[b]Recent Uploads[/b]\" in my profile: http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=129045\r\n\r\nOnly 3 uploads showing up, all 3 have cover images:\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35141&torrentid=30028\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35152&torrentid=30039\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35165&torrentid=30052\r\n\r\n2 missing, no cover images:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35150&torrentid=30037\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35164&torrentid=30051',129045,'2012-07-23 16:41:37'),(44760,5755,129045,'2012-07-23 16:27:05','This is probably WIP and will be updated correctly later (that\'s why I\'m not opening a thread on Bugs), but was \"[b]Do not upload from the following list[/b]\" present before on http://empornium.mooo.com/upload.php ? I don\'t remember seeing it before\r\n\r\nRight now it\'s empty. Should it be linking or displaying the same info as http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=forbiddencontent ?\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=A2AE_500D5EAD][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=A2AE_500D5EAD&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n:hmmm:',129045,'2012-07-23 16:27:48'),(44762,5778,49532,'2012-07-23 16:37:03','Ok this is just a little suggestion: add \"FAQ\" to the menu at the top of the page.  If space is an issue relocate \"Top 10\" ',NULL,NULL),(44763,5778,129045,'2012-07-23 16:53:36','Or swap \"Rules\" http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=rules\r\n\r\nto\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=faq\r\n\r\n\r\nOr they could be merged, \"Rules\" could easily fit inside FAQ the introduction :hmmm:',129045,'2012-07-23 16:54:02'),(44764,5779,49532,'2012-07-23 16:54:06','When entering forum posts, comments or descriptions, sometimes the text doesn\'t wrap correcty, and part of it gets hidden at the end of the line beyond the width of the input box.\r\n\r\nI am currently using firefox 14 on a OSX 10.7 (Lion) with Lucida Grande 18 as my proportional font and Menlo 18 as my monospaced font. The problem is intermittent, but also occurs when I change the proportional font to anything that size or bigger.',NULL,NULL),(44765,5779,129045,'2012-07-23 16:56:41','Can you post a screenshot of the problem?',129045,'2012-07-23 16:56:56'),(44766,5779,49532,'2012-07-23 17:32:08','[quote=yamchan07bb]Can you post a screenshot of the problem?[/quote]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1C28_500D6E39][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=1C28_500D6E39&jpg[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(44767,5755,84499,'2012-07-23 17:43:02','\r\n\r\nThe DNU list has always been there :D\r\n\r\nI filled it with the stuff from the rules, if I have missed anything or if any staff wants to correct it the link to edit it is in the tools dropdown.',NULL,NULL),(44769,5779,129045,'2012-07-23 17:52:27','Thanks. That sure is odd.\r\n\r\nSince you use a Mac, can you check [i]iamstoopid[/i] screens on these threads, to see if experience the same things? (it\'s also related to font sizes)\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2746\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2753',NULL,NULL),(44770,5778,84499,'2012-07-23 17:58:42','\r\n\r\nI would rather relocate essential topics within the faq to be individual help articles. That way the help section can be more of a one stop call for pervs needing help, rather than having to root around individual topics looking for sub headings.\r\n\r\n(also space in the menu is an issue and there is nowhere really appropriate for the top10 link but there.)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44771,5779,84499,'2012-07-23 18:11:46','\r\n\r\n :hmm: \r\n\r\nstupid macs\r\n\r\n\r\ncan you tell me if you go to this torrents edit page: [url=/torrents.php?action=editgroup&groupid=10467]edit page for a torrent you uploaded[/url]\r\ndo you see the same error with the text in the description textbox (if you can set your font so it will definitely manifest on threads) or is it wrapped correctly?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44773,5755,48010,'2012-07-23 18:25:24','DNU list looks ok - do we need to add the other banned content from current site (specified actresses etc)?',NULL,NULL),(44774,5780,48010,'2012-07-23 18:45:47','See the browse page\n\nI marked 2 torrents one nearly 4 days ago and the other 5 days ago and they are still there\n\n[url=/torrents.php?id=35146][/url]\n\n[url=/torrents.php?id=35144][/url]\n\nthere are others on the browse page that I can test for no seeding if they can be fixed\n\nI put this in bugs as it is one - I could put it in staff but want others who are non-staff to check too - could be another bug where staff see one thing and members don\'t\n\nthanks - Dave',84499,'2012-07-23 18:49:20'),(44775,5697,67255,'2012-07-23 18:52:29','Having editable titles is a must and also the ability to edit tags. More power to the uploader. It can only be a good thing\r\nHaving control of this things is easy for the tracker coder and it means a lot to the uploaders.\r\nThat is why I don\'t upload to other trackers, here I feel that I have control and if I make a mistake or remember something it later, it will be an easy fix by me',NULL,NULL),(44777,5780,129045,'2012-07-23 18:53:44','When I visited http://empornium.mooo.com/tools.php?action=marked_for_deletion\r\n\r\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-AD33_500D8149.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n:hmmm:',129045,'2012-07-23 18:54:45'),(44778,5780,84499,'2012-07-23 18:56:00','\r\n\r\nThe auto-deleter is turned off at the moment... if you want to turn it on just go to the \'Marked for Deletion\' page under the tools dropdown, right now all staff have permissions set to turn the deleter on and off.\r\n\r\nI marked as okay the two torrents that have a seed, and marked a couple of older ones with a 24 hr time period. If you want to test it on newly marked torrents quicker than that you can also change the marked for deletion period on the same tools page (iirc 1 hr is the smallest time you can set).\r\n\r\nI imagine the auto deleter will always be on and the time period will never change once we go live, but its useful for testing if they can be changed.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44779,5780,48010,'2012-07-23 18:59:31','@yamchan - i missed that completely\n\nIf we keep the current emp.me rules they have 24 hours to fix or it goes\n\n[quote=mifune]I imagine the auto deleter will always be on and the time period will never change once we go live, but its useful for testing if they can be changed.[/quote]\n\nHope so :grin:\n\nHowever we may need to extensions sometimes - ISPs drop our or members have RL issues - if they come up with something valid an extension should be an option but NOT\nthe dog ate my HDD \nor the dog ate my torrent type of crap :wink:',48010,'2012-07-23 19:05:35'),(44780,5780,84499,'2012-07-23 19:07:53','\r\n\r\nalmost certainly it should be on when we are live, when are testing... depends. It was useful to have it turned off when I was testing all the aspects of that system apart from the delete mechanism because it takes time to upload a torrent, even a test one!\r\n\r\nIf you are sure its okay to delete the torrents then turn it on... I have done so now anyway, so be aware any torrents marked for deletion will be going bye bye if they time out without a response from the uploader (or after a response has been rejected by the staff so it is again ahs \'marked for deletion\' status instead of \'pending\' or \'okay\').',NULL,NULL),(44781,5780,84499,'2012-07-23 19:10:22','[quote=Dave]@yamchan - i missed that completely\r\n\r\nIf we keep the current emp.me rules they have 24 hours to fix or it goes\r\n\r\n[quote=mifune]I imagine the auto deleter will always be on and the time period will never change once we go live, but its useful for testing if they can be changed.[/quote]\r\n\r\nHope so :grin:\r\n\r\nHowever we may need to extensions sometimes - ISPs drop our or members have RL issues - if they come up with something valid an extension should be an option but NOT\r\nthe dog ate my HDD \r\nor the dog ate my torrent type of crap :wink:[/quote]\r\n\r\nThe site settings on the marked for deletion page apply to all torrents. To stop individual torrents being deleted they can be marked okay, if you still want them to marked for deletion but with a time extension then set it to okay and then reset the marked for deletion status which should reset the clock.\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44782,5749,87267,'2012-07-23 19:16:10','[quote=mifune]You can add a picture in the description area using bbcode.\n\nThe Cover Art area is for cover art of the torrents you collate in your collage.[/quote]\n\n[s]I tried in this one http://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php?id=1#post8 but the pics do not show up.\nThis friday they did show up but I don\'t see them anymore.[/s]\n\nNevermind I double tested with another browser and it was Adblocker that messed it up. Sorry.\n',87267,'2012-07-23 19:19:41'),(44783,5749,84499,'2012-07-23 19:19:52','\nI see them once I refreshed the page... probably a imghost thing :dunno:\n\nhaha, np ninja editer :ninja:',84499,'2012-07-23 19:20:35'),(44784,5782,67255,'2012-07-23 19:44:51','There should be a link to collages in the top banner for access\r\nIf people cannot see it they will not use it\r\nThanks!',NULL,NULL),(44785,5780,48010,'2012-07-23 19:51:39','[quote=mifune][quote=Dave]@yamchan - i missed that completely\n\nIf we keep the current emp.me rules they have 24 hours to fix or it goes\n\n[quote=mifune]I imagine the auto deleter will always be on and the time period will never change once we go live, but its useful for testing if they can be changed.[/quote]\n\nHope so :grin:\n\nHowever we may need to extensions sometimes - ISPs drop our or members have RL issues - if they come up with something valid an extension should be an option but NOT\nthe dog ate my HDD \nor the dog ate my torrent type of crap :wink:[/quote]\n\nThe site settings on the marked for deletion page apply to all torrents. To stop individual torrents being deleted they can be marked okay, if you still want them to marked for deletion but with a time extension then set it to okay and then reset the marked for deletion status which should reset the clock.[/quote]\n\nI don\'t have time to play with it right now as it\'s getting late\n\nwill test it tomorrow',48010,'2012-07-23 19:52:01'),(44786,5782,129045,'2012-07-23 19:55:41','It was there before, but mifune remove it and placed it in the user menu (hover your username v).\r\n\r\nI don\'t thing he will revert it\'s position :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(44787,5783,129045,'2012-07-23 19:57:24','[i]I\'m not sure if I should report this. I think [b]barumba[/b] posted something about how the login sessions expire after some inactivity, [s]but I can\'t find the thread or post at this moment.[/s] here: http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2644\r\nSo, when sessions start to be handled like EMP.me, I guess this will be a non issue. :hmmm:[/i]\r\n\r\n\r\nI may need to do more tests, but this is basically how it goes:\r\n\r\n[b]Problem 1:[/b]\r\n[b]The user\'s session has expired[/b]. Without knowing it, if the user tries to perform some actions, he\'ll not be redirected to http://empornium.mooo.com/login.php , instead, a login prompt will appear in the area he was accessing (e.g. Editing a comment or post or when tying to access the Peer list of a torrent - see images).\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]Problem 2:[/b]\r\nIf the user actually uses that login prompt, there will be some odd results, in my tests, these happened at least once:\r\n\r\n- I Got redirected to http://empornium.mooo.com/index.php\r\n- I Got Redirected to http://empornium.mooo.com/login.php\r\n- Trying to edit a comment I ended with this link instead http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=takeedit\r\n- Trying to access the torrent\'s peer list I ended with this link instead http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=peerlist&torrentid=30049\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]Problem 3:[/b]\r\nWhenever that login prompt appears, seems like it\'ll apply the same stylesheet from http://empornium.mooo.com/login.php , causing visual inconsistencies (it clashes with the Empornium and Light CSS - see images)\r\n\r\n\r\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/acfrOYV8][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/acfrOYV8.jpg[/IMG][/URL] [URL=http://imgbox.com/abgiJmfp][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/abgiJmfp.jpg[/IMG][/URL] [URL=http://imgbox.com/acjRjo8B][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/acjRjo8B.jpg[/IMG][/URL] [URL=http://imgbox.com/acnvqCva][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/acnvqCva.jpg[/IMG][/URL] [URL=http://imgbox.com/abnHTOH8][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/abnHTOH8.jpg[/IMG][/URL] ',129045,'2012-07-31 22:55:37'),(44788,5783,84499,'2012-07-23 20:32:41','\r\n\r\n\r\nstrange...\r\n\r\n\r\nwhen I time out it redirects me to the login page :hmmm:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44790,5783,129045,'2012-07-23 20:50:56','I don\'t mean hitting F5 or clicking on a link to visit another page. If my session has expired and I do that, I\'ll be redirected to the login page just like you.\r\n\r\nI don\'t get redirected anywhere automatically, after the session has expired :hmmm:\r\n\r\nWhat I tried to described is a result of that, since the page looks normal and I don\'t know that my session has expired, if I try to edit a post for example, the login prompt will appear in it\'s place.',NULL,NULL),(44791,5679,71158,'2012-07-23 21:01:31','So um...can I get some credits?',NULL,NULL),(44792,5778,86439,'2012-07-23 21:08:59','[quote=mifune]I would rather relocate essential topics within the faq to be individual help articles. That way the help section can be more of a one stop call for pervs needing help, rather than having to root around individual topics looking for sub headings.\r\n\r\n(also space in the menu is an issue and there is nowhere really appropriate for the top10 link but there.)[/quote]\r\nI have to agree with that. As there is so much stuff in them it can be hard for a new user to find information. It can be overwhelming and they just end up asking in the forms for something that is available but cant find as they just get lost.\r\n\r\nI remember when i first started torrenting I would get lost trying to find information between Help, FAQ and Rules etc. I dont know, you just start to get confused clicking pages trying to hunt down whatever.\r\n\r\nMake sense?',NULL,NULL),(44793,5783,42827,'2012-07-23 21:35:28','I had the same experience today. My session expired when I left it inactive for about twenty minutes while on another browser doing other searches.\r\n\r\nNow you guys said you wanted input, right? well, here it is: honestly, I think the old look was much cleaner and easier to read. On a single page you get the feeling of there being just too much clutter. Perhaps, as I use the new site more that impression will fade. I\'ll keep you guys updated.  :worm:  ',NULL,NULL),(44794,5778,49532,'2012-07-23 21:45:24','[quote=knickers][quote=mifune]I would rather relocate essential topics within the faq to be individual help articles. That way the help section can be more of a one stop call for pervs needing help, rather than having to root around individual topics looking for sub headings.\r\n\r\n(also space in the menu is an issue and there is nowhere really appropriate for the top10 link but there.)[/quote]\r\nI have to agree with that. As there is so much stuff in them it can be hard for a new user to find information. It can be overwhelming and they just end up asking in the forms for something that is available but cant find as they just get lost.\r\n\r\nI remember when i first started torrenting I would get lost trying to find information between Help, FAQ and Rules etc. I dont know, you just start to get confused clicking pages trying to hunt down whatever.\r\n\r\nMake sense?[/quote]\r\n\r\nYes it makes sence, and it\'s a better solution. The goal is to have everything easily accessible and findable.',NULL,NULL),(44795,5779,49532,'2012-07-23 22:18:22','[quote=mifune]:hmm: \r\n\r\nstupid macs\r\n\r\n\r\ncan you tell me if you go to this torrents edit page: [url=/torrents.php?action=editgroup&groupid=10467]edit page for a torrent you uploaded[/url]\r\ndo you see the same error with the text in the description textbox (if you can set your font so it will definitely manifest on threads) or is it wrapped correctly?[/quote]\r\n\r\nMore like stupid Firefox.\r\nAfter an update to Firefox 14.0.1 I am no longer able to reproduce the problem, but I will post again if it reoccurs\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44796,5784,37338,'2012-07-23 22:51:08','I don\'t know if this is possible or if will require a lot of time to implement but the use of the \"tags\" in searches could be a lot better. When searching for a random thing like (Black Lesbians) I have to select the \"Black\" check box along with the \"Lesbian\" check box only to get all Lesbian and Black results, where I have an all white lesbian movie and not an all black or even a black actress in it.\r\n\r\nI did this with an torrent I uploaded and I did the same type of search only for it to show up in the lez category or the black one never by itself.',NULL,NULL),(44797,5785,37338,'2012-07-23 22:58:02','Location: http://empornium.mooo.com/bonus.php\r\n\r\nThe amount of credits from the old site are showing this:\r\n\r\nYou have 12198 credits to spend.\r\n\r\nNext bonus update is Jul 24 2012, 09:18 PM\r\n\r\nNo need to reproduce seeing that logging in and out still shows the same amount',NULL,NULL),(44798,5679,37338,'2012-07-23 23:02:22','I\'ll take some also',NULL,NULL),(44799,5785,86439,'2012-07-23 23:10:23','Im fairly certain the stats here are exclusive to here for testing purposes only, the old site stats will be transferred over when this site goes live. ',NULL,NULL),(44800,5784,84499,'2012-07-23 23:21:41','\r\n\r\nsounds like you are confusing tags and categories, leave the categories blank (all unchecked) and just type \"black lesbian\" in the tag search field.\r\n\r\n[url=/torrents.php?order_by=time&order_way=desc&searchtext=&search_type=1&action=basic&taglist=black&#43;lesbian&tags_type=1]Search for tags \'black\' and \'lesbian\'[/url]\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44801,5679,84499,'2012-07-23 23:22:26','[quote=LatexRyan]So um...can I get some credits?[/quote]\r\n[quote=Wallabe99]I\'ll take some also[/quote]\r\n\r\ndone :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(44802,5784,86439,'2012-07-23 23:22:36','I have a habit of reading these things wrong, but it sounds like your confusing search terms as per non tag sites, with the use of tags.\n\nblack lesbians would be black.lesbians as a tag, if such a tag exists, yet. I did look through the list of tags and did not see one.\n\nIm assuming that because you havent typed the items as a tag in your post. It looks to me like youre searching for black and lesbians so will get results for both, not the combined phrase exclusively.\n\nAnyway, the main point I was making is a tag for black lesbians would be black.lesbians.\n\n\nEdit: And i was ninja\'d',86439,'2012-07-23 23:25:20'),(44803,5786,49532,'2012-07-23 23:50:49','I testing uploads with various types of errors, and each time, when I was returned to the [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/upload.php]upload form[/url] with an error message, the \'Torrent File\' field was blank.  The torrent location should be retained and not have to be reselected each time. \r\n',NULL,NULL),(44804,5679,49532,'2012-07-24 00:05:14','I\'ll take 1 billion credits.   :grin: ',NULL,NULL),(44805,5679,100662,'2012-07-24 00:15:52','Please give me a bottle of credits, and take a glass yourself! Always like to give away thingies :-)',NULL,NULL),(44806,5786,84499,'2012-07-24 01:11:01','\r\n\r\nBrowsers specifically ignore any starting values for file input controls as a security precaution. In other words there is nothing we can do about that, sorry.',NULL,NULL),(44807,5737,84499,'2012-07-24 01:12:45','\r\nAdded thanks button.',NULL,NULL),(44808,5787,49532,'2012-07-24 02:24:47','in another thread knickers was talking about searching for black.lesbians, which got me thinking....\n\nthere are many situations where someone is looking for specific combinations of tags and subsets of tags. for instance suposse someone wants only videos of Eva Evangelina before she got implants but doesn\'t care about the breastsize of any other actress. at the same time other people want to find all videos of Eva Evangelina.  Or suppose someone wants only videos that have Lexi.Belle when she was a teen and other people want all videos that have Lexi Belle.  \n\nOne solution would be to create composit tags that will match searches for any included tag in a regular search, but will only match only the composit if the search uses composit operator (e.g. ..)\n\nsome examples:\nthe tag [b]lexi.belle..teen[/b] will be found in searches for [b]lexi.belle[/b], [b]teen[/b] or  [b]lexi.belle..teen[/b].  However a search for  [b]lexi.belle..teen[/b], will not match [b]lexi.belle[/b], or [b]teen[/b]\n\nthe tag [b]eva.evangelista..small.tits[/b] will be found in searches for [b]eva.evangelista[/b], [b]small.tits[/b] or  [b]eva.evangelista..small.tits[/b].  However a search for  [b]eva.evangelista..small.tits[/b], will not match [b]eva.evangelista[/b], or [b]small.tits[/b]\n\nBetter yet would be to allow any combinaion of composit elements:\n\nthe tag [b]eva.evangelista..small.tits..glasses[/b] will be found in searches for [b]eva.evangelista [/b],  [b]small.tits[/b], [b]glasses[/b], [b]eva.evangelista..glasses[/b],  [b]eva.evangelista..small.tits[/b] or  [b]eva.evangelista..small.tits..glasses[/b].  However a search for  [b]eva.evangelista..small.tits..glasses[/b], will not match [b]eva.evangelista [/b], [b]small.tits[/b],[b]glasses[/b], [b]eva.evangelista..glasses[/b], or [b]eva.evangelista..small.tits[/b]\n\n\n',49532,'2012-07-24 02:25:56'),(44809,5787,37338,'2012-07-24 02:38:42','http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2784\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44810,5787,84499,'2012-07-24 02:39:52','maybe I am being dense but how is this any different from the way the tag search works already?\n\nIf you search for the tags \"lexi.belle teen\" you will only get matches for torrents that have both tags\n\n[url=/torrents.php?order_by=time&order_way=desc&searchtext=&action=advanced&filelist=&taglist=lexi&#46;belle&#43;teen]Tag search for \'lexi.belle teen\'[/url]\n\nIf you want more complex searches where you can say match tags a + b but only where not c, use boolean operators in the advanced search.\n\n[url=/articles.php?topic=search]Advanced Search operators[/url]\n',84499,'2012-07-24 04:39:28'),(44811,5784,37338,'2012-07-24 02:44:16','The reason I asked that was because I have friends that search on this site and they use the method I said above. The way you guys explained it sounds very simple but even I didn\'t know I could do all of that until it was explain. So now the real question is will there be an explanation when making torrents or some FAQ that explains this search method. Either way a first time user of this site is automatically do such said search and not pull the results they were looking for.\n\nMifune I did the search you said do and yet white lesbian movies still popped up with no black actresses in them. I understand that most of this is depending on the OP making the correct tags and what not. ',37338,'2012-07-24 02:57:22'),(44812,5785,37338,'2012-07-24 02:44:57','Thanks for the info',NULL,NULL),(44814,5787,49532,'2012-07-24 03:10:11','[quote=mifune]maybe I am being dense but how is this any different from the way the tag search works already?\n\nIf you search for the tags \"lexi.belle teen\" you will only get matches for torrents that have both tags\n\n[url=/torrents.php?order_by=time&order_way=desc&searchtext=&action=advanced&filelist=&taglist=lexi.belle+teen]Tag search for \'lexi.belle teen\'[/url]\n\nIf you want more complex searches where you can say match tags a + b but only where not c, use boolean operators in the advanced search.\n\n[url=/articles.php?topic=search]Advanced Search operators[/url][/quote]\n\nNo they don\'t work like this already. \n\nif you had the tags [b]lexi.belle.teen[/b] you would not match [b]teen.lexi.belle[/b] and you would still have to have a separate [b]lexi.belle[/b] tag and a separate [b]teen[/b] tag or else the video wouldn\'t come up in searches for [b]lexi.belle[/b] or [b]teen[/b].\n\nlets take it further: It would take 22 tags under the current system to acomplish what the the compsit tag [b]lexi.belle..long.hair..teen..lesbain..reality.king\n[/b]  does.\n\nThe current advanced search features also don\'t do the same thing.  [b]lexi.bell&teen[/b] would match lexi belle at any age, and anybody who is a teen.\n\n',49532,'2012-07-24 03:28:41'),(44815,5780,1507,'2012-07-24 03:11:50',' :yes2: \r\n\r\n[b]I have marked my Real Couples torrent for deletion oto test if the auto-deletion is working or not...\r\n\r\n[url]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35146[/url]\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(44816,5788,1507,'2012-07-24 03:20:13',' :yes2: \r\n\r\n\r\n[b]I found this when I was testing the auto-deletion:\r\n\r\nFrom the pm the system sent me:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote]System 5 mins ago - [color=magenta](Quote) [/color]\r\n\r\nYour upload Real Couples - Victoria and Ridge does not meet our standards for uploading and has been marked for deletion.\r\n\r\nIt will be automatically deleted if you do not fix your upload in the next 1 day  (Jul 25 2012, 03:09).\r\n\r\nReason:  testing auto-deletion\r\n\r\nPlease make sure you read the Upload Rules\r\nYou will find useful guides in the Tutorials section\r\n[color=magenta]If you need further help please post in the Help & Support Forum[/color] [/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFirst, the \"Quote\" is a link that does nothing...\r\n\r\nNext, the link for \"Help and Support\" actually directs you to the Bugs forum and not H&S and needs to have the correct link put in place...\r\n\r\nSo, not so much a bug but a need to be fixed thingy...    :smile1: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-24 03:22:16'),(44817,5784,86439,'2012-07-24 03:24:13','\'Rules\' at the top of the page has a section within it at the bottom, \"Other Rules\' which includes a link for the FAQ\r\nThere is also a \'Help\' option at the top of the page which contains a tutorial for \'Boolean Search\' which will allow you to add terms together, and to restrict it I believe. You can also get to the Boolean Search information page by switching to advanced search in the browse page, and theres a link to it there.\r\n\r\nI believe entering in the search field black AND lesbian or black & lesbian should get you the result you want. I cant test it now as many torrents use freeimage as host and it seems to be down ATM. I saw some that definitely included at least one black star from their descriptions. I dont know if this aspect of the site has been thoroughly tested either.',NULL,NULL),(44818,5737,1507,'2012-07-24 03:31:58',' :gjob: ',NULL,NULL),(44819,5784,49532,'2012-07-24 03:39:22','[quote=knickers]\'Rules\' at the top of the page has a section within it at the bottom, \"Other Rules\' which includes a link for the FAQ\r\nThere is also a \'Help\' option at the top of the page which contains a tutorial for \'Boolean Search\' which will allow you to add terms together, and to restrict it I believe. You can also get to the Boolean Search information page by switching to advanced search in the browse page, and theres a link to it there.\r\n\r\nI believe entering in the search field black AND lesbian or black & lesbian should get you the result you want. I cant test it now as many torrents use freeimage as host and it seems to be down ATM. I saw some that definitely included at least one black star from their descriptions. I dont know if this aspect of the site has been thoroughly tested either.[/quote]\r\n\r\nNo, it wouldn\'t. It would also match videos with white lesbians and black straights.',NULL,NULL),(44820,5775,1507,'2012-07-24 03:44:05',' :hmmm: \r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-24 03:45:41'),(44821,5774,1507,'2012-07-24 03:49:25',' :yes2: \r\n\r\n[b]Yeah, I have that problem because I am fucking color blind/blind and the icons all look the same to me..  But someone, I think it was yam, made a css that works for me as it darkens the icons so that I can see them now...  :gjob:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44822,5775,84499,'2012-07-24 03:55:19','\r\n\r\nWe can potentially add logging and access rights easily enough... dunno what the best solution is though.',NULL,NULL),(44823,5635,1507,'2012-07-24 03:55:34',' :dunno: \r\n\r\n[b]I still want to see my random rewards idea, where the system randomly picks torrents and bumps the bonus for seeding it 5, 10, 25, 50, or maybe 100 times the regular bonus credit amounts for seeding it...  no one will know what torrent(s) have the greatest bonus amounts so that they will just keep seeding them all...   :dunno: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :bugchases: \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-24 03:56:42'),(44824,5775,1507,'2012-07-24 03:59:42','[quote=mifune]We can potentially add logging and access rights easily enough... dunno what the best solution is though.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]make a log entry so that staff can check to see who is screwing around, and if they are, ban the dick head...   :judge: \r\n\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :blink: ',NULL,NULL),(44825,5767,1507,'2012-07-24 04:03:50',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]uploader\'s cannot edit their titles....???  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nnot a good idea....  we\'ll have a lot of deleted uploads as the uploader will have to delete and re-up if they want to make title changes because they\'ve misspelled something or whatever...  or staff will be busy editing titles...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44826,5784,84499,'2012-07-24 04:04:59','[quote=Wallabe99]Mifune I did the search you said do and yet white lesbian movies still popped up with no black actresses in them. I understand that most of this is depending on the OP making the correct tags and what not.[/quote]\n\nBut there isnt much more we can do... all the torrents in that search result have both the tag black and the tag lesbian. You can try searching for a more specific tag like black.lesbians, but if torrents are not specifically tagged there is not a lot we can do about it. Oh and for this specific search try [url=/torrents.php?order_by=time&order_way=desc&searchtext=&search_type=1&action=basic&taglist=ebony&#43;lesbian&tags_type=1]Search for tags \'ebony\' and \'lesbian\'[/url]',84499,'2012-07-24 04:06:15'),(44827,5772,1507,'2012-07-24 04:09:35',':hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(44828,5756,1507,'2012-07-24 04:15:03',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]Nice job, but SysOp Lanz really loves :wub: [color=magenta]pink[/color] :wub: ...\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :sigh:  :sigh:  :sigh:  :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh:  :slap:  :slap:  :slap: ',1507,'2012-07-24 04:22:44'),(44829,5787,84499,'2012-07-24 04:23:31','\r\nI never said anything about lexi.belle.teen, I said the tags lexi.belle & teen.\r\n\r\nSearching for the tagstring \'lexi.belle + teen\' on advanced search or \'lexi.belle teen\' with the default \'all\' option selected in basic mode will get you only results that are tagged with both of the tags. \r\n\r\nDid you try it? That search gives you 24 results, all of which have both those tags. Do you really need to narrow the search more?\r\n\r\nYour system would require taggers to put more effort in, which is not realistic imo, and I still dont see what better results it will get you. \r\n',NULL,NULL),(44830,5787,1507,'2012-07-24 04:28:27','[quote=mifune]I never said anything about lexi.belle.teen, I said the tags lexi.belle & teen.\r\n\r\nSearching for the tagstring \'lexi.belle + teen\' on advanced search or \'lexi.belle teen\' with the default \'all\' option selected in basic mode will get you only results that are tagged with both of the tags. \r\n\r\nDid you try it? That search gives you 24 results, all of which have both those tags. Do you really need to narrow the search more?\r\n\r\n[color=magenta]Your system would require taggers to put more effort in[/color], which is not realistic imo, and I still dont see what better results it will get you.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n :sigh: \r\n\r\n[b]Don\'t complicate things and make them harder for the uploaders....  :sigh:\r\n\r\nWe have enough problems just getting them to do a damn basic presentation, so adding something else will just cause more confusion and headaches...  :slap:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44831,5789,77802,'2012-07-24 04:44:18','<< First < Prev | 451-500 | 501-550 | 551-600 | 601-650 | 651-700 | 701-750 | 751-800 | 801-850 | 851-900 | 901-950 | 951-1000 | Next > Last >>\r\n\r\nLast>> only moves the torrent list to the next page.',NULL,NULL),(44832,5772,86439,'2012-07-24 04:49:29','Rather than start a thread Ill just ask int his somewhat generic thread going by its title.\r\n\r\nIs 24hr Freeleech gone? I noticed its not there but wondered if intentional or an oversight.',NULL,NULL),(44833,5789,86439,'2012-07-24 04:56:29','Yeah, its been noted already. I believe its being worked on (put in a queue) as the bug thread title hasnt been changed to FIXED yet.\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2709&page=1#post24733',NULL,NULL),(44835,5772,1507,'2012-07-24 05:02:28','[quote=knickers]Rather than start a thread Ill just ask int his somewhat generic thread going by its title.\r\n\r\nIs 24hr Freeleech gone? I noticed its not there but wondered if intentional or an oversight.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]I\'m told it is gone for good...\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44837,5772,86439,'2012-07-24 05:26:23','Cool\r\n\r\nI wonder if many people off the main site will read this, and a frenzy of spending credits on 24 freeleech will follow.',NULL,NULL),(44838,5790,86439,'2012-07-24 05:32:35','The list of tags within a torrent (on each torrent page) arent sorted alphabetically. Some it doesnt matter because they are short but on mega-packs etc they can be quite substantial.\n\nIs it possible to make them sort alphabetically so people can scan them easier? Might help with voting them down etc. Or is the official list not going to get much bigger?\n\nI just noticed one torrent that had a huge list of tags.',86439,'2012-07-24 05:34:15'),(44839,5709,1243,'2012-07-24 05:46:48','This is NOT a bug, but a way for the system to limit the results. It can be defined for each user class. I\'ve added it to all classes but apprentice and perv for now.\n\nEdit: \"Can go past low limit of search results.\" in the user classes',1243,'2012-07-24 05:50:42'),(44840,5790,1243,'2012-07-24 05:59:16','They are sorted by number of votes atm. We could perhaps add this as an option, alphabetically or by score.',NULL,NULL),(44841,5709,86439,'2012-07-24 06:09:19','OK, that changed things for me.',NULL,NULL),(44842,5619,86853,'2012-07-24 06:35:42','Win7 64, Firefox 14.0.1...logged in first try.',NULL,NULL),(44843,5619,128757,'2012-07-24 07:15:51','For what it\'s worth, same login prob hit me on FF v14.0.1 using Mac OS. \r\nReset pw and here I am. But it\'s no biggie, not worth worrying about. It seems to be kinda random and user/browser-related NOT code failure.',NULL,NULL),(44844,5791,86853,'2012-07-24 07:39:45','http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php\r\n\r\nNot a big deal, but I have noticed the preview window that pops up while hovering over posted torrent names hangs on the mouse pointer, anywhere I move the mouse. Seems to happen when clicking an a post, and then clicking back. And it doesn\'t always do it. Just sometimes. Firefox 14.0.1\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-9D6A_500E3468.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-9D6A_500E3468.jpg[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(44845,5772,1507,'2012-07-24 07:53:16',' :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: \r\n\r\n[b]wait until they find out that we are taking away all of their credits and slots as well...   :panic:  :panic:  :panic: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-24 07:55:38'),(44848,5792,76943,'2012-07-24 08:28:32','When doing a search there is a link called \"View Tags\" it shows all tags (or maybe the most common ones).  It would be nice to have the same in the \"Add/Edit Notification filters\" screen(http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=notify).\n\nthanks',76943,'2012-07-24 08:28:55'),(44849,5767,1635,'2012-07-24 08:46:21','[quote=usillyboy]:hmmm: [b]uploader\'s cannot edit their titles....??? :hmmm: not a good idea.... we\'ll have a lot of deleted uploads as the uploader will have to delete and re-up if they want to make title changes because they\'ve misspelled something or whatever... or staff will be busy editing titles... :hmmm: usb[/b] :hmmm:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI absolutely agree with my friend [color=#FF0099][b]u-sillyboy![/b][/color] :thumbsup: :thumbsup: :thumbsup:\r\n\r\nThe Admin and Mods, in my opinion, probably don\'t have the time to answer hundreds of pms requesting changing or editing of titles of their presented torrents.  To the best of my knowledge, I have always had this benefit?  If it is at all possible, we should have the ability to edit titles of our torrents posted.  Thanks for everybodys input here and thanks for listening to my opinion:)',NULL,NULL),(44851,5791,94484,'2012-07-24 09:00:31','i am olso a windows 7 user and have been getting the same as described above..',NULL,NULL),(44852,5679,47234,'2012-07-24 09:01:06','Throwing 100k credits and 10 slots each at Apparition and Cladiron',NULL,NULL),(44853,5767,47234,'2012-07-24 09:10:26','Can we remove the delete upload option and replace it with remove uploaders name.  It is an issue when people leave and delete all their uploads.... Leaves more than a few people stranded.\r\n\r\nYeah your right we likely dont need the extra workload that would come with editing torrent names all the time.',NULL,NULL),(44855,5787,49532,'2012-07-24 09:29:11','[quote=mifune]I never said anything about lexi.belle.teen, I said the tags lexi.belle & teen.\n\nSearching for the tagstring \'lexi.belle + teen\' on advanced search or \'lexi.belle teen\' with the default \'all\' option selected in basic mode will get you only results that are tagged with both of the tags. \n\nDid you try it? That search gives you 24 results, all of which have both those tags. Do you really need to narrow the search more?\n\nYour system would require taggers to put more effort in, which is not realistic imo, and I still dont see what better results it will get you.[/quote]\n\nYes they would get both tags, but the teen tag does not necessarily refer to Lexi Belle when SHE was a teen.  If Lexi Belle was 23 and Jessi Andrews was 19.  Then the video would show up in the search.  \n\nBack when I made a torrent site, it didn\'t have tags (The idea had never crossed my mind back then) but it had a table where you added a row for each actress. For each actress, you had input fields for name and age, and pulldowns for breasts, hair color, hair length, bodytype, tatoos, piercings, pubic hair.  \n\nMy GF\'s suggestion was an attempt to get the same degree of specificity and more.\n\nWe\'re not here to debate the issue though, if there isn\'t support for this idea then it won\'t get implemented. \n\nI still applaud her efforts to suggest this, if only to get more ideas out there and get people thinking.  \n\nHowever, it appears to me that the idea is not well understood, and probably will not be utilized to it\'s potential even if it were implemented. \n',49532,'2012-07-24 10:06:17'),(44856,5776,47234,'2012-07-24 09:31:47','Nope i dont like it as it forces people to use xxx.freeimage.us\r\n\r\nMany uploaders upload at a few sites.  Forcing them to use freeimage may just mean they decide not to upload at Emp as they dont wish to upload the material twice to image hosts.',NULL,NULL),(44857,5777,47234,'2012-07-24 09:32:55','Eww the aspect ratio yeah that needs looking at.',NULL,NULL),(44858,5782,47234,'2012-07-24 09:35:17','Hmm i agree considering how many people seem interested in Collages it may be worth having the link back somehwere.\r\n\r\nTo be honest they almost got removed as we didnt think people would use them but half the suggestions seem to be about collages... so people must want them.',NULL,NULL),(44859,5671,1243,'2012-07-24 09:37:25','yes only those with cover images will show up. Been planning to change that but haven\'t had the time to do it lately. It\'s not a bug but done so buy the what.cd people.',NULL,NULL),(44860,5774,89443,'2012-07-24 09:43:16','The grey and blue icons show up for me too. But my original point was that it could be changed to make it more clear/noticeable. As well as having some special icon signifying that you posted in that thread.',NULL,NULL),(44861,5635,47234,'2012-07-24 09:46:16','[quote=apparition]As I see it the main point of a bonus system is to encourage as many people as possible to seed as long as possible.   Having a cap of 60 gives a subliminal suggestion that you should only seed 60 torrents. [/quote]\r\n\r\nCurrently its 20 torrents so i say gainign credit for up to 60 torrrents 24/7 is an improvement.\r\n\r\n[quote]Also, I think it would be better to add to the upload rather than remove from the download, psychologically people respond more to getting a positive rather than removing a negative. [/quote] \r\n\r\nLets not reinvent the wheel here.  Emp has removed downloads not added uploads for some time.  Plus another bonus for removing down is the fact it reduces our required ratio as well.\r\n\r\n[quote]One other thing, I think the bonus should be higher for seeding older or less seeded torrents.[/quote]\r\n\r\nWe moved to this bonus credit system because the old one was too hard on the server.  The more variables we throw at this the heavier the load.  We then need more expensive servers to run EMP and damnit this show runs on the smell of an oily rag.....\r\n\r\nWe are not Webop we dont run $2k a month servers and if we did EMP would be long gone.  I mean this test tracker runs on a 40Euro a month server and could in all likelihood handle the entire EMP userbase and then a few more times that.  Thats the way it needs to stay or the site will collapse due to lack of funds or start having to run massive donation drives all the time.\r\n\r\nAnother option with bonus systems that load the hell out of the server is one that was taken a few months back.  You shut the bonus system down because its too costly in computer time.  No one likes that.\r\n\r\nThankfully the guys managed to get the server beefed up and somehow managed to get it running again on that server.  But its not a long term solution.',NULL,NULL),(44862,5775,47234,'2012-07-24 09:50:05','[quote=usillyboy]:hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]make a log entry so that staff can check to see who is screwing around, and if they are, ban the dick head...   :judge: \r\n\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :blink:[/quote]\r\n\r\nYeah its something we would need to monitor somehow.  I just assumed it was logged i didnt check :lol:\r\n\r\nIf some ass-hat did start doing this sort of thing we would really need to apply the :judge:\r\n\r\nIm thinking Sextreme or above only editing or maybe good perv but i dont think we want emp apprentices playing with this.  Or people with throw away accounts.',NULL,NULL),(44863,5756,47234,'2012-07-24 09:52:24','Yeah we blieve you USb its Lanz who likes Pink not our favourite tag lover :)',NULL,NULL),(44864,5697,47234,'2012-07-24 10:01:44','You could still easily fix the tags under the current system.  Just add them like other users can.\r\n\r\nWhat i dont want to see is people adding tags and the uploader (who hates tags) removing the lot because they can or adding tags with a high vote later just because they can.\r\n\r\nI thought the whole idea of voting tags was to let the crowd decide as it makes both the uploader and the tag nazis happy about the tagging system....\r\n\r\nIf you want to just do one tag do so and others will add them for you....',NULL,NULL),(44865,5783,47234,'2012-07-24 10:03:15','To be honest automatic log outs drive me insane anywhere........',NULL,NULL),(44866,5776,49532,'2012-07-24 10:12:15','[quote=Clownius]Nope i dont like it as it forces people to use xxx.freeimage.us\n\nMany uploaders upload at a few sites.  Forcing them to use freeimage may just mean they decide not to upload at Emp as they dont wish to upload the material twice to image hosts.[/quote]\n\nIt doesn\'t force anything; anyone can still can manually add image code to the description the same as it is now.   This is merely a shortcut, that will help save effort, and enable newbies to be able to add images when they don\'t yet know what code to put in the description, to get the images to show up correctly.',49532,'2012-07-24 10:18:17'),(44867,5784,1243,'2012-07-24 10:12:57','This is actually where BOTH categories AND tags can help out. Categories can help to pick out the MAIN theme of the torrent.\r\n\r\nCheck the category lesbian and enter the following in the tags field:\r\n\"(ebony or black) and not white\" without the quotes in the advanced search form.\r\n\r\nThis can be tweaked further of course. I bet you can not find a better system than this anywhere else.\r\n',1243,'2012-07-24 11:01:25'),(44868,5776,1243,'2012-07-24 10:15:30',':hmm: need to think about that.',1243,'2012-07-24 10:16:37'),(44869,5783,1243,'2012-07-24 10:26:42','[quote=bongorum]I had the same experience today. My session expired when I left it inactive for about twenty minutes while on another browser doing other searches.\r\n\r\nNow you guys said you wanted input, right? well, here it is: honestly, I think the old look was much cleaner and easier to read. On a single page you get the feeling of there being just too much clutter. Perhaps, as I use the new site more that impression will fade. I\'ll keep you guys updated.  :worm:[/quote]\r\n\r\nYes this is information we really want to hear. But we want detailed rants, what pages, what makes it feel cluttered to you, etc etc. The more info you give the easier it is to follow up and see if we need to change something.',NULL,NULL),(44872,5791,1243,'2012-07-24 10:44:48','This happens when you click on the torrent link and while the torrent details page load, you move your mouse cursor away from the list. It is then stuck when you go back again.',NULL,NULL),(44873,5793,76180,'2012-07-24 10:53:28','So, my stats do match the stats on the regular emp site.  Here are my stats on the original site:\r\n\r\n  Ratio: 24.63  Up: 292.08 GB  Down: 11.86 GB  Credits: 22792\r\n\r\nAnd on the beta:\r\n\r\n  Up: 267.93 GB\r\n  Down: 11.67 GB\r\n  Credits: 16,884\r\n  Ratio: 22.94\r\n\r\nPerhaps, this could be fixed?  Or is it un-synchronized intentionally for a reason?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44874,5793,86439,'2012-07-24 10:56:10','And they wont, this is still a test site.\r\n\r\nWhen it goes live, your stats will be imported over. Dont panic.',NULL,NULL),(44875,5793,47234,'2012-07-24 10:57:27','This is an old copy of the database just here for testing purposes.  What happens here stays here.  Once the test is over and things go live we import the latest data.\r\n\r\nIt lives ona  different server in a different country to the current emp site :)',NULL,NULL),(44876,5791,1243,'2012-07-24 10:57:54','Can only replicate it in FF so far. Not tested with IE.',NULL,NULL),(44877,5697,86439,'2012-07-24 11:00:45','When I mentioned tags, I only meant within a few minutes of uploading. Not days later. Its just easy to leave one out, hit submit and then go bugger!\r\n\r\nI dont know how hard that is to do but plenty of sites do this with post edits etc.',NULL,NULL),(44878,5756,1243,'2012-07-24 11:04:19','[quote=Pornjacker]What is the required pix size for the header? Then I\'ll give it a shot as well.[/quote]\r\n\r\nIt should fit on where the current one is exact size is not that important. The current one is also transparent and used on both the themes we have atm but not important.',NULL,NULL),(44879,5755,47234,'2012-07-24 11:10:50','Added DrkNess\'s rtorrent guide [s]and about to add seeding guide to tutorials[/s]\n\nRealised how current Emp specific it is so removed it again\n\n\nAdded Vuze upload guide',47234,'2012-07-24 11:30:35'),(44880,5790,86439,'2012-07-24 11:11:58','Sounds perfect.\n\nIf its not too much trouble.',86439,'2012-07-24 11:12:19'),(44881,5635,49532,'2012-07-24 11:30:09','[quote=Clownius][quote=apparition]As I see it the main point of a bonus system is to encourage as many people as possible to seed as long as possible.   Having a cap of 60 gives a subliminal suggestion that you should only seed 60 torrents. [/quote]\r\n\r\nCurrently its 20 torrents so i say gainign credit for up to 60 torrrents 24/7 is an improvement.\r\n\r\n[quote]Also, I think it would be better to add to the upload rather than remove from the download, psychologically people respond more to getting a positive rather than removing a negative. [/quote] \r\n\r\nLets not reinvent the wheel here.  Emp has removed downloads not added uploads for some time.  Plus another bonus for removing down is the fact it reduces our required ratio as well.\r\n\r\n[quote]One other thing, I think the bonus should be higher for seeding older or less seeded torrents.[/quote]\r\n\r\nWe moved to this bonus credit system because the old one was too hard on the server.  The more variables we throw at this the heavier the load.  We then need more expensive servers to run EMP and damnit this show runs on the smell of an oily rag.....\r\n\r\nWe are not Webop we dont run $2k a month servers and if we did EMP would be long gone.  I mean this test tracker runs on a 40Euro a month server and could in all likelihood handle the entire EMP userbase and then a few more times that.  Thats the way it needs to stay or the site will collapse due to lack of funds or start having to run massive donation drives all the time.\r\n\r\nAnother option with bonus systems that load the hell out of the server is one that was taken a few months back.  You shut the bonus system down because its too costly in computer time.  No one likes that.\r\n\r\nThankfully the guys managed to get the server beefed up and somehow managed to get it running again on that server.  But its not a long term solution.[/quote]\r\n\r\nOne of the difficulties of sharing my GF\'s account is that our opinions aren\'t looked at separately. \r\n\r\nI mostly agree with Clownius here, but I think he overestimates the increase in the server load from her suggestion.',NULL,NULL),(44882,5697,1243,'2012-07-24 11:44:32','It\'s frankly stupid to not let the uploader edit the title of the torrent, and as pointed out here will just lead to more work for the staff.\n\nYou should now be able to rename the title under edit.',1243,'2012-07-24 11:48:57'),(44883,5697,1243,'2012-07-24 11:48:25','Regarding tags. Tags on many other sites are much more simpler than what we currently have here, and it is sort of a bitch to enabled tag editing as with the old empornium because of it. If this is REALLY wanted, we can try and sort it out but I would prefer not to tbh.',NULL,NULL),(44884,5635,1243,'2012-07-24 12:00:09','[quote=apparition]One of the difficulties of sharing my GF\'s account is that our opinions aren\'t looked at separately. \r\n\r\nI mostly agree with Clownius here, but I think he overestimates the increase in the server load from her suggestion.[/quote]\r\n\r\nTrue, it wont change the server load that much with just rewarding older torrents more, it will require a more complex database query though and that needs to be tested IF we want to go that route.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44885,5756,85111,'2012-07-24 12:42:32','[quote=Lanz][quote=Pornjacker]What is the required pix size for the header? Then I\'ll give it a shot as well.[/quote]\r\n\r\nIt should fit on where the current one is exact size is not that important. The current one is also transparent and used on both the themes we have atm but not important.[/quote]\r\n\r\nfor anyone else who wants to try, the current one on this site is 170x32 and exported in png-24 for complete transparency. \r\n\r\nhaha would like to see submitters upload a pink version just for laughs.',NULL,NULL),(44886,5709,84499,'2012-07-24 12:49:07','\r\n\r\n:D\r\n\r\nI am so happy right now',NULL,NULL),(44887,5756,47234,'2012-07-24 12:58:54','A pink version ewwww where my banhammer :judge:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44889,5776,84499,'2012-07-24 13:11:06','\r\n\r\nThere are pros and cons, but for technical reasons I am against it. ',NULL,NULL),(44892,5709,129045,'2012-07-24 13:26:45','Class limitation explains how the user could only see a 1.000 torrents... but [b]Next[/b] and [b]Last[/b] always having the same destination (next page) is the correct behavior?',129045,'2012-07-24 13:28:20'),(44894,5709,1243,'2012-07-24 13:30:00','That code frankly doesn\'t make sense to me or mifune. We will not use it for any of the classes when we go live.\r\n\r\nBut yes, the code first limits you to 100 results, but increase it by 50 for each time you click on last page. ',NULL,NULL),(44897,5791,129045,'2012-07-24 13:49:31','This is a hard one to replicate :hmmm:\n\nCan\'t replicate it on IE 9.0 or Chome 20.0.1132.57m\n\nBut Opera 12 will also present the bug.\n\n[b]EDIT:[/b] It\'s not limited to Win7.\n\nFirefox on Ubuntu will also behave the same.\n\nOpera 12 on the other hand will lose the popup completely until you Refresh the page.',129045,'2012-07-24 14:16:52'),(44902,5619,65471,'2012-07-24 14:40:09','I use Firefox, and I had to reset my password to get in too.',NULL,NULL),(44906,5746,129045,'2012-07-24 16:24:46','yay :)\r\n\r\nStealth fixed!',NULL,NULL),(44908,5772,94804,'2012-07-24 16:34:02','[quote=usillyboy]:laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: \r\n\r\n[b]wait until they find out that we are taking away all of their credits and slots as well...   :panic:  :panic:  :panic: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:[/quote]\r\nThat\'s just EVIL',NULL,NULL),(44909,5746,84499,'2012-07-24 16:35:28','\r\nlol I couldnt find which thread this one was in when I updated the fix, we rearranged the details page, hopefully this works for everyone.',NULL,NULL),(44911,5794,94804,'2012-07-24 16:40:46','At risk of being a dumbass, how do css stylesheets work (in settings) and where can I find some?',NULL,NULL),(44912,5794,129045,'2012-07-24 16:58:34','You need to create one or modify the site\'s default:\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/style.css\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/light/style.css\r\n\r\nAfter that, just host it somewhere, then paste the link in the box and save. e.g.:\r\n\r\nhttp:\\\\yoursite.com\\yourcssfile.css\r\n\r\nI use DropBox.com to host mine, it\'s free and they allow hotlinking, so it works fine. There\'s also Google Drive, but I don\'t know their policy about hotlinking.\r\n\r\nActually, about DropBox, they will not support Public folders for new accounts after July 31th, so I guess that eliminates hotlinking, but anyone signing up before that date should be good to go :hmmm:',129045,'2012-07-24 16:59:08'),(44913,5794,84499,'2012-07-24 17:02:38','\r\natm there are two stylesheets you can select in the dropdown, empornium and light. Select, save your settings (button at bottom of settings page) and you should instantly see it change.\r\n\r\nIs it possible to enter the url for an externally hosted stylesheet. It has to be specifically written to work with the site, there are some css writing pervs knocking around the site and at least one alternative css has been made I think (if you are lucky they might sees this and give you the url...)\r\n\r\nIf you want to make one you are welcome but we do not (and will not) officially offer support for external stylesheets. It is possible that we might add some more official stylesheets at some point in the future but its a low priority right now.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44915,5746,129045,'2012-07-24 17:14:42','Tested on Win7: working fine on IE 9.0, Chrome, Firefox and Opera\r\n\r\nTested on Ubuntu: working fine on Firefox and Opera',NULL,NULL),(44916,5770,51383,'2012-07-24 17:54:07','[quote=yamchan07bb]Change to [i][b]Advanced Search[/b][/i] and you\'ll be able to search in the [b]file list[/b].\n\n[b]Phrase search[/b] is already in, use double quotes: [color=#FF0000]\"[/color]exact match[color=#FF0000]\"[/color] (Note: Article needs editing.)[/quote]\n[font=Arial][size=2][color=#0000FF]That\'s good. Now we are moving forward.[/color][/size][/font] [img]http://www.greensmilies.com/smile/smiley_emoticons_thumbs1.gif[/img]',51383,'2012-07-24 17:54:33'),(44917,5795,171777,'2012-07-24 18:06:14','As the title says. Once you are inserting info for an upload the Img button does nothing.',NULL,NULL),(44918,5796,171777,'2012-07-24 18:15:50','Since this is a part of the site where I spent A LOT of time it is also the part where I first started looking into what can be done.\r\n\r\n-Make the \"Do not upload from the following list\" and \"Approved Imagehosts\" collapsable (if not always then add some kind of trigger. Say a good perv can collapse them). Reason: Added scrolling since if you click preview for a torrent layout you then have to scroll all the way down to where you can make the edits.\r\n-Tags: right above where you select a tag is says \"No category selected.\" This is a confusing place. I know it changes into auto adding a tag. It might be better to exclude the category from the tags list all together and get rid of the line I quoted. Reason: Less confusion.\r\n-Tags: Probably done on purpose but if you add 720p as a tag then also do 540 and 1080 since those are the most used resolution indicators.\r\n-Preview: Why force people to click a new button (make changes) if they want to once again edit the description. Just stick with the preview button and keep the code part so people can tweak (might be an idea to insert a sandbox window at the top or bottom of the description once you click preview that shows what will be in the description). Reason: Easier editing of torrent descriptions. On the old site I always had a sandbox open because it did just what I described and allowed for far easier editing of the torrents. The only disadvantage back there is that you had to open the sandbox in a seperate window.\r\n-Torrent creation error message: Place this all the way at the top. Even above the \"Do not upload from the following list\" and \"Approved Imagehosts\" lists. Reason: If you get the same page as before without seeing the red error bar you might think all went well and leave the page. Resulting in a lot of irritation later on.\r\n-Forbidden content list: Add something like \"Or anything else mentioned on the list located at: http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=forbiddencontent\". Reason: Makes it harder to say you didn\'t know then if there is only a small link at the very bottom of the page.\r\n-Error message \"You must enter at least one tag. Maximum length is 200 characters.\" should contain the word \"additional\" since it is already stated that he category counts as a tag on it\'s own\r\n-Error message \"Your Description must be more than 20 characters long. (counted:9 all:9)\" remove the all:9 part. This has no added value what so ever.\r\n-Torrent upload errors: Checking if there is an actual torrent file happens last of everything. I dare say that this is actually the most important part.\r\n-After forcing me to check quite literally everything in the description the site itself does not check whether the torrent actually contains the correct tracker (I uploaded a torrent from pussytorrents.org to test this and it was accepted with no additional changes)\r\n\r\n\r\nSo much for the upload part.\r\nNow just 1 thing in general. We live in 2012. A lof of people have some serious real estate in terms of monitor size. Allow for different widths to be used. Right now half of my screen is blank.',NULL,NULL),(44919,5795,84499,'2012-07-24 18:22:34','\r\non the upload page the img button and preview both work for me :dunno:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44920,5795,84499,'2012-07-24 18:23:09','\r\nso perhaps thats not what you mean..... so:\r\n\r\nwhat page?\r\n\r\nexactly what steps do you have to take to reproduce the error?\r\n\r\nwhat do you expect the behaviour to be?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44921,5795,129045,'2012-07-24 18:29:09','On this http://empornium.mooo.com/upload.php\r\n\r\nThe IMG button, located above the description area, Opera and Chrome fail to bring up the IMG popup to insert an image.\r\n\r\nFirefox works fine, on IE, the popup appears, but it\'s always at the top left corner of the window.\r\n\r\nNow, the IMG button located above the comment\\post area works fine on all of them :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b] The problem also affects Opera and Chrome on http://empornium.mooo.com/requests.php?action=new\r\n\r\nWhile http://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php?action=new works fine for all browsers',129045,'2012-07-24 18:47:45'),(44923,5796,84499,'2012-07-24 19:02:36','[quote=DrkNess]Since this is a part of the site where I spent A LOT of time it is also the part where I first started looking into what can be done.\r\n\r\n-Make the \"Do not upload from the following list\" and \"Approved Imagehosts\" collapsable (if not always then add some kind of trigger. Say a good perv can collapse them). Reason: Added scrolling since if you click preview for a torrent layout you then have to scroll all the way down to where you can make the edits.\r\n[/quote]\r\nThey do collapse, once you have made an upload they should then be collapsed until the lists change.\r\n[quote]\r\n-Tags: right above where you select a tag is says \"No category selected.\" This is a confusing place. I know it changes into auto adding a tag. It might be better to exclude the category from the tags list all together and get rid of the line I quoted. Reason: Less confusion.\r\n[/quote]\r\nOnce you pick a category - which you have to do - the message becomes much more relevant and is in the appropriate place. Its a lot of hassle to change that to be 2 different messages in 2 places for something that should be obvious once you select a category.\r\n[quote]\r\n-Tags: Probably done on purpose but if you add 720p as a tag then also do 540 and 1080 since those are the most used resolution indicators.\r\n[/quote]\r\nThe official tag list and synonyms are placeholders - we just made the top so many tags official for the moment, in any event they will need to be regenerated when we go live.\r\n[quote]\r\n-Preview: Why force people to click a new button (make changes) if they want to once again edit the description. Just stick with the preview button and keep the code part so people can tweak (might be an idea to insert a sandbox window at the top or bottom of the description once you click preview that shows what will be in the description). Reason: Easier editing of torrent descriptions. On the old site I always had a sandbox open because it did just what I described and allowed for far easier editing of the torrents. The only disadvantage back there is that you had to open the sandbox in a seperate window.\r\n[/quote]\r\nYou like it that way, but if you have a long presentation I\'m not so sure its better. I would like to hear the opinions of other uploaders about this before considering any change.\r\n[quote]\r\n-Torrent creation error message: Place this all the way at the top. Even above the \"Do not upload from the following list\" and \"Approved Imagehosts\" lists. Reason: If you get the same page as before without seeing the red error bar you might think all went well and leave the page. Resulting in a lot of irritation later on.\r\n[/quote]\r\nYou might be right about this... I think we will try returning them to an anchor on the page just below the lists though but you are right they should see the error msg straight away.\r\n[quote]\r\n-Forbidden content list: Add something like \"Or anything else mentioned on the list located at: http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=forbiddencontent\". Reason: Makes it harder to say you didn\'t know then if there is only a small link at the very bottom of the page.\r\n-Error message \"You must enter at least one tag. Maximum length is 200 characters.\" should contain the word \"additional\" since it is already stated that he category counts as a tag on it\'s own\r\n-Error message \"Your Description must be more than 20 characters long. (counted:9 all:9)\" remove the all:9 part. This has no added value what so ever.\r\n[/quote]\r\nthose values are not always the same! try using some bbcode and they will be different. They might well be removed anyway before we go live... they are really just for error checking anyway although i thought it might be of some use when users wonder why there massive presentation is only counted as <20 characters.\r\n[quote]\r\n-Torrent upload errors: Checking if there is an actual torrent file happens last of everything. I dare say that this is actually the most important part.\r\n[/quote]\r\nI actually put it as the last check for a very good reason... as the torrent file cannot be reinserted into the page it is a massive PITA if you are trying to solve some other presentation issue and you have to keep selecting the file every time.\r\n[quote]\r\n-After forcing me to check quite literally everything in the description the site itself does not check whether the torrent actually contains the correct tracker (I uploaded a torrent from pussytorrents.org to test this and it was accepted with no additional changes)\r\n\r\n\r\nSo much for the upload part.\r\nNow just 1 thing in general. We live in 2012. A lof of people have some serious real estate in terms of monitor size. Allow for different widths to be used. Right now half of my screen is blank.[/quote]\r\nThe width does scale slightly... but other widescreen users prefer the page to have a narrower max width.',NULL,NULL),(44924,5795,84499,'2012-07-24 19:06:25','\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\nstrange... its literally the same code in all of those places... I will look into it.\r\n\r\n\r\nthanks for the report :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(44925,5697,86439,'2012-07-24 19:11:50','In that case, leave tag edits as they are.',86439,'2012-07-24 19:12:16'),(44926,5784,37338,'2012-07-24 19:21:09','Trust me Lanz I\'ve been with you guys before you made the move to the .me, I\'ve built a large spank bank from you guys. I just thought outside the box for a second and wanted to see if something could be tweaked a little. Thanks for the hard work guys, without you I would have to find time to talk to my girlfriend. ',NULL,NULL),(44927,5796,1243,'2012-07-24 19:25:29','[quote=DrkNess]\r\n-After forcing me to check quite literally everything in the description the site itself does not check whether the torrent actually contains the correct tracker (I uploaded a torrent from pussytorrents.org to test this and it was accepted with no additional changes)\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nThis is not a bug. The site will replace the announce url with the appropriate url + user passkey every time someone download the file. So it doesn\'t care what you add in it. Of course if you do add the correct information, you do not have to download the torrent file from the site but can use the one you generated directly.',NULL,NULL),(44929,5787,37338,'2012-07-24 19:30:56','[quote=apparition]\r\n\r\nYes they would get both tags, but the teen tag does not necessarily refer to Lexi Belle when SHE was a teen.  If Lexi Belle was 23 and Jessi Andrews was 19.  Then the video would show up in the search.  \r\n\r\nBack when I made a torrent site, it didn\'t have tags (The idea had never crossed my mind back then) but it had a table where you added a row for each actress. For each actress, you had input fields for name and age, and pulldowns for breasts, hair color, hair length, bodytype, tatoos, piercings, pubic hair.  \r\n\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nAll of this is too much. My question was to make it simple for the dev\'s and mods to control it but also give the end user a more controlled search to where more results would show up and giving them a chance to explore more torrents. This is turn will help torrents be seeded more instead of having a dead torrent sitting in a search result.',NULL,NULL),(44930,5784,37338,'2012-07-24 19:31:36','All of this is too much. My question was to make it simple for the dev\'s and mods to control it but also give the end user a more controlled search to where more results would show up and giving them a chance to explore more torrents. This is turn will help torrents be seeded more instead of having a dead torrent sitting in a search result.',NULL,NULL),(44931,5798,129045,'2012-07-24 19:38:23','[i]Look, I don\'t use IE... but this is for testing purposes, if Lanz want to go ahead and ban IE, you have my vote[/i] :laugh:\n\nProbably not even a bug, it\'s just IE being IE :P\n\nUsing IE 9.0, only buttons that bring up a popup [i]and Size setting[/i] seems to behave correctly, everything else will either insert the bbcode after OR before the highlighted word(s):\n\n[table=nball,600px,left]\n[tr]\n[td][b]Examples:[/b] [i]CR[/i], [i]FF[/i], [i]OP[/i]\n[code][b]word[/b][/code]\n[code][color=#FF0000]word1 word2[/color][/code]\n[code][bg=#FF0000]word[/bg][/code]\n[/td]\n[td][i]IE[/i]\n[code]word[b][/b][/code]\n[code][color=#FF0000][/color]word[/code]\n[code][bg=#FF0000][/bg]word1 word2[/code]\n[/td][/tr]\n[/table]\nConvenience is lost.\n\nRegarding the popup that appears (Anchor, IMG, Video, Flash, Spoiler, etc), on IE it\'ll always appear at the top left corner, while other browsers will make it appear at the middle of the window (horizontal wise, not vertical).\n\n:hmmm:\n\n\n[b]EDIT:[/b] Oops, meant to post \"only buttons that bring up a popup [i]and Size setting[/i]\" and forgot.',129045,'2012-07-24 21:46:42'),(44932,5784,1243,'2012-07-24 19:50:54','[quote=Wallabe99]All of this is too much. My question was to make it simple for the dev\'s and mods to control it but also give the end user a more controlled search to where more results would show up and giving them a chance to explore more torrents. This is turn will help torrents be seeded more instead of having a dead torrent sitting in a search result.[/quote]\r\nIt\'s somewhat of an oxymoron to both want it to be simple and to give you a more controlled search. If you can come up with a way that give you the control we have now in a simpler way, then I\'m all for adding it.\r\n\r\nI do hover agree that we need more information about the search function, as a programmer it\'s easy to be blind to the problems other people might have with the search. ',NULL,NULL),(44933,5798,1243,'2012-07-24 20:00:03','Ihatethatbrowsersomuch :gunshot: \r\n',NULL,NULL),(44935,5798,84499,'2012-07-24 20:03:09','meh. IE is stupid with its non compliant javascript. We will try and fix the selection code at some point.',84499,'2012-07-24 20:03:41'),(44936,5796,84499,'2012-07-24 20:14:02','[quote=DrkNess]\r\n-Torrent creation error message: Place this all the way at the top. Even above the \"Do not upload from the following list\" and \"Approved Imagehosts\" lists. Reason: If you get the same page as before without seeing the red error bar you might think all went well and leave the page. \r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nIf you are returned to the upload page I made it so it closes the lists - so the error bar should be plainly visible :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(44937,5798,105266,'2012-07-24 20:20:26','The same it happend to me in IE  :mad:  but until now seems in chrome no problem  :smile1: ',NULL,NULL),(44938,5796,84499,'2012-07-24 20:23:05','\r\n[quote=DrkNess]\r\n-Forbidden content list: Add something like \"Or anything else mentioned on the list located at: http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=forbiddencontent\". Reason: Makes it harder to say you didn\'t know then if there is only a small link at the very bottom of the page.\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\ngood idea, done   :cigarpuff: ',NULL,NULL),(44941,5767,48010,'2012-07-24 20:38:47','[quote=Clownius][b]Can we remove the delete upload option and replace it with remove uploaders name.  It is an issue when people leave and delete all their uploads.... Leaves more than a few people stranded.[/b]\n\nYeah your right we likely dont need the extra workload that would come with editing torrent names all the time.[/quote]\nthis should be in a new thread ',48010,'2012-07-24 20:39:13'),(44942,5776,49532,'2012-07-24 20:39:44','[quote=mifune]There are pros and cons, but for technical reasons I am against it.[/quote]\n\nCan you elaborate on those techical reasons?\n\n\n\n',49532,'2012-08-01 20:23:52'),(44943,5775,48010,'2012-07-24 20:43:27','I agree with the last 2 posts - nice one usb and Clownius',NULL,NULL),(44944,5746,85111,'2012-07-24 20:49:33','Does anyone use a mac? cos my ratio stuff on top right still overlaps a little on the Light Stylesheet..the Dark Stylesheet is fine.',NULL,NULL),(44945,5790,48010,'2012-07-24 20:54:07','[quote=knickers]Sounds perfect.\r\n\r\nIf its not too much trouble.[/quote]\r\npersonally when I upload I first describe the main content then add other tags\r\n\r\nfor eaxmple I would start with Asian or Lesbian \r\n\r\nthen add others as I think of them such as dildo strap-on anal actress.name(s)',NULL,NULL),(44946,5772,1507,'2012-07-24 20:55:35',' :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(44947,5756,1507,'2012-07-24 20:56:48',' :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(44948,5784,84499,'2012-07-24 20:56:59','\r\n\r\nYeah, lets expand the search article in help to cover \'how to search\' basic and advanced as well as boolean search terms :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(44949,5772,48010,'2012-07-24 20:58:08','[quote=knickers]Cool\r\n\r\nI wonder if many people off the main site will read this, and a frenzy of spending credits on 24 freeleech will follow.[/quote]\r\nhow can you spend credits on an option that isn\'t there in the Bonus Shop?',NULL,NULL),(44951,5784,37338,'2012-07-24 21:01:59','[quote=mifune]Yeah, lets expand the search article in help to cover \'how to search\' basic and advanced as well as boolean search terms :gjob:[/quote]\r\n\r\nI agree and thank you guys.',NULL,NULL),(44952,5767,94804,'2012-07-24 21:02:02','[quote=mifune]good idea I added some text :gjob:[/quote]\r\ngreat! thanks,but uhm still nothing (like an explanatory line) (in most recent Chrome)\r\nand I agree with u-sillyboy\r\n',NULL,NULL),(44954,5772,94804,'2012-07-24 21:13:22','[quote=Dave][quote=knickers]Cool\r\n\r\nI wonder if many people off the main site will read this, and a frenzy of spending credits on 24 freeleech will follow.[/quote]\r\nhow can you spend credits on an option that isn\'t there in the Bonus Shop?[/quote]\r\nimaginary credits, I guess;)\n\nbut returning to the purpose of this thread, don\'t you guys agree that 100,000 and 250,000 look too similar?',94804,'2012-07-24 21:16:35'),(44955,5793,48010,'2012-07-24 21:13:32','do testers fully read the PM they get or just click the link?\n\nor do they forget the PMs content asap ?',48010,'2012-07-24 21:14:32'),(44957,5772,129045,'2012-07-24 21:28:06','What 250.000?\n\nI can only see 100.000 (Bling - medal) and 200.000 (Plaque), they aren\'t similar :hmmm:',129045,'2012-07-24 21:28:53'),(44959,5793,47234,'2012-07-24 21:36:04',':lol: Dave  I actually didnt bother to make the link clickable.  Hoped they would ready it that way.',NULL,NULL),(44960,5798,47234,'2012-07-24 21:38:59','Oh i beg of you please ban IE .....  I swear you spend half your bug squashing time on bugs that only affect IE...',NULL,NULL),(44962,5799,49532,'2012-07-24 21:55:08','When I tried to add an avatar with the url:\r\nhttp://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=289E_500EF870 \r\nI got the error:\r\n[b]You did not enter a valid avatar url.[/b]\r\n\r\nThe same error occured using: \r\nhttp://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=289E_500EF870 and\r\nhttp://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=289E_500EF870',NULL,NULL),(44964,5799,129045,'2012-07-24 22:00:49','You need to supply a [s]proper[/s] direct link. It\'s not a bug, the system is working correctly.\r\n\r\nRead this http://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=avatartutorial\r\n\r\nTry http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-289E_500EF870.jpg\r\n\r\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-289E_500EF870.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n',129045,'2012-07-24 23:21:28'),(44965,5746,129045,'2012-07-24 22:10:07','[quote=iamstoopid]Does anyone use a mac? cos my ratio stuff on top right still overlaps a little on the Light Stylesheet..the Dark Stylesheet is fine.[/quote]\r\n\r\nBetter open a new thread for Mac interface related problems :hmmm:\r\n\r\nOr it could be specified a different font family for the top menu, like Lanz said, on the images you posted, the font appears too large.',NULL,NULL),(44966,5619,87020,'2012-07-24 22:17:07','I use Google Chrome on a Windows 7 64 Ultimate and I also had to reset my password. I am positive that I used the same password as on the main site. Good luck =)',NULL,NULL),(44967,5772,94804,'2012-07-24 22:25:40','? \r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=4C0E_500F04AA][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=4C0E_500F04AA&jpg[/img][/url] I meant this......',NULL,NULL),(44968,5635,94804,'2012-07-24 22:31:56','oow yeah, being altruistic is being punished it seems, when you wanna improve someelse\'s ratio you gotta pay more than when it\'s for yourself. Why?\n\njust noticed Mifune having no answer to that, why not change it then?',94804,'2012-07-24 22:39:57'),(44969,5772,129045,'2012-07-24 22:36:47','Well, I don\'t have that one.\r\n\r\nI guess it\'s hidden because I don\'t have enough credits, but even then, that doesn\'t explain why other items are still available, but in red :hmmm:\r\n\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=12B7_500F0749][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-12B7_500F0749.jpg[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(44971,5799,49532,'2012-07-24 22:44:22','This is a bug, because the behavior should be changed. There is no need to require the addition of .jpg; images can be displayed just fine without it.  Besides that won\'t nessesarily work with other image hosts.  ',NULL,NULL),(44972,5772,94804,'2012-07-24 22:49:41','yeah, got that, too.\r\nbut between 100 & 200 = 250 (so much fir sequenciality)(= that even a word?)',NULL,NULL),(44973,5635,84499,'2012-07-24 23:01:25','[quote=schlager]oow yeah, being altruistic is being punished it seems, when you wanna improve someelse\'s ratio you gotta pay more than when it\'s for yourself. Why?\r\n\r\njust noticed Mifune having no answer to that, why not change it then?[/quote]\r\n\r\nThere is a 1% tax on giving... think of it as insurance against possible credit scams I havent yet thought of.',NULL,NULL),(44974,5772,84499,'2012-07-24 23:05:24',' :demon: \n\nWell the reason is simple... I just havent told anyone yet :lol:\n\n\nThe blue ribbon bling medals are a ranked set - you have to own the lower ranked one before you can buy the higher ranked one. The plaques are all unique items, so you can buy them individually.\n\nOf course this information will all be on the [url=/bonus.php?action=awards]Awards and Badges[/url] page... once we get round to sorting out the badges :D\n',84499,'2012-07-24 23:07:17'),(44975,5772,87267,'2012-07-24 23:08:55','Awesomey huge Collection...  The non-buyable ribbons are the best.\nand the Gay ribbons should be rainbow colored :D',87267,'2012-07-24 23:13:07'),(44976,5800,49532,'2012-07-24 23:12:49','On the [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=8075&torrentid=6651]detail page[/url] of a torrent. The description diplays under the tag list/. When there is a large list of tags, the description can be pushed offscreen.  The description should apppear to the left of the tag list instead.\n\n\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=A202_500F0C93][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=A202_500F0C93[/img][/url]',49532,'2012-07-24 23:13:15'),(44978,5772,86439,'2012-07-24 23:22:22','[quote=Dave][quote=knickers]Cool\r\n\r\nI wonder if many people off the main site will read this, and a frenzy of spending credits on 24 freeleech will follow.[/quote]\r\nhow can you spend credits on an option that isn\'t there in the Bonus Shop?[/quote]\r\nNo, I meant spending them on the main site, on 24 freeleech. Its to my opinion, probably one of the better bonus options..',NULL,NULL),(44980,5767,84499,'2012-07-24 23:22:52','\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adjAqZfB.png[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\nwhat else do you want to know?',NULL,NULL),(44981,5635,86439,'2012-07-24 23:24:45','There are only two guarantees in torrenting\r\n\r\nError 500\'s and taxes.',NULL,NULL),(4498