t as the unread ones. I use the \'read\' state of a torrent to mark how far back to browse, so it\'d be nice if the new site allowed us to distinguish between read and unread torrents. Or another way I\'ve seen is to explicitly show torrents and \"new\" and have the user take an action that marks them all as \'read\'.',NULL,NULL),(45006,5799,49532,'2012-07-25 06:42:31','[quote=yamchan07bb]:hmmm:\r\n\r\nIt\'s not simply adding [color=#FF0000].jpg[/color], the article describes how to edit the URL to gain access to the image without having it served through PHP, in other words: [b]direct link[/b]\r\n\r\nFrom what I understand, the system will only accept direct links. What\'s the problem with that?\r\n\r\n[quote]Besides that won\'t nessesarily work with other image hosts.[/quote]\r\nWhat other hosts? If they supply a direct link to the file, it\'ll work just fine.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI explained this to her, she gets it now',NULL,NULL),(45009,5803,47234,'2012-07-25 07:00:25','Interesting thats something i hadnt even noticed.  Hmm',NULL,NULL),(45010,5634,47234,'2012-07-25 07:06:43','Thats because Paypal likes freezing accounts of anything porn or torrent related.  If you have a direct link you just know it wont last very long at all....',NULL,NULL),(45011,5804,171777,'2012-07-25 07:06:50','I noticed that there is a catch up button same as there was one on the old site however there is no \"view unread\" button. I used that feature a lot (once I noticed it existed on the old forums) so it would be nice to have something similar on the new boards as well.',NULL,NULL),(45012,5793,47234,'2012-07-25 07:10:38','Should have seen something on the home page too\r\n\r\n[quote=Invite]2) Whatever happens on the test tracker stays on the test tracker. Meaning that no upload or download will affect your account on empornium.me[/quote]\r\n\r\nThats about as close as the Invite comes.  Mentioning stats are not linked\r\n\r\n[quote=News]What happens on the test tracker stays on the test tracker!  :shutup2:\r\n- Meaning that all stats on the test tracker will be wiped out when we go live. Therefore anything downloaded, uploaded, credits gained/spent, anything and everything to do with individual user stats and torrents will be reset to the current main site stats when we go live.[/quote]\r\n\r\nThats what the News says.\r\n\r\nMaybe we should reword it to say none of the stats will ever be related or something :dunno:',NULL,NULL),(45013,5805,171777,'2012-07-25 07:38:18','Using any of the search options (so from torrent overview or from the search bar at the top of the page), if I search for the term Freeleech, no torrents with a coin show up. The only results are from torrents that have the term Freeleech somewhere in their description. There is however a Freeleech torrent of (at moment of writing) 11 hours old that does not show up at all in the search. It looks like the part that is added to the torrent title (Freeleech! + coin symbol) is not used in the search indexing.\r\n\r\nTested this on Google Chrome (latest versions)',NULL,NULL),(45014,5635,171777,'2012-07-25 07:45:46','As I already mentioned on the old board, helping out someone else is penalized. Helping out someone else should be cheaper then helping out yourself (encourages activity on forums so people will like you enough to help). If you are afraid of this being abused just put a timer on it. You can not help the same user more then say 10 gigs each half year (excluding yourself offcourse).\r\n\r\nThe plaques are a bit overkill if you ask me. The medals are nice but to add plaques for doing basically the same thing but just a tiny bit more expensive is bogus. It feels like those were added just to add something expensive to the list.\r\n\r\nThe Bling medals. Are they seperate? So if I buy all 4 will I retain all 4 or do they cancel each other out? No matter which one but this probably should be mentioned in their info.',NULL,NULL),(45015,5774,171777,'2012-07-25 07:52:00','[quote=pistonsfan]The grey and blue icons show up for me too. But my original point was that it could be changed to make it more clear/noticeable. As well as having some special icon signifying that you posted in that thread.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI too have to say that it is pretty much impossible to differentiate between the 2 colors that the forum icons can have.\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=93C5_500F8921][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=93C5_500F8921&jpg[/img][/url]\r\nIt does depend on how my screen is positioned though. Monitor viewing angles make these colors too similair. Changing the unread one to say dark blue (to stay in theme with the empornium colors) would make the difference a lot more obvious.',NULL,NULL),(45016,5806,171777,'2012-07-25 08:07:28','[img=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=A11C_500F8BBD]\r\n\r\nAs the image shows there is an image in the torrent description and it still counts it as a bug. True the use of the BB code tag is different but it still is a valid BB tag. To test that this is actually a valid BB tag i posted the above image using an identical type of link.\r\n\r\nIn the above torrent description if I click preview the tag IS correctly implemented and the preview shows an image on the correct location.\r\n\r\nNoticed this in the latest Google Chrome for windows\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45018,5807,171777,'2012-07-25 08:42:28','I just copy pasted a descr to see how long it was and hit 77 pages in MS Word. There is no way that I want to scroll through that everytime I check up on a torrent. Other information about a torrent can be hidden so why not the description itself?',NULL,NULL),(45020,5619,79684,'2012-07-25 10:02:42','I had the same issue on Firefox. ',NULL,NULL),(45023,5743,171777,'2012-07-25 10:36:15','Probably should also remove the part about no adds since they are now present.',NULL,NULL),(45024,5743,47234,'2012-07-25 10:55:21','That link comes straight from What.CD lol\r\n\r\nPaypal and Emp havent gotten along in the past.  These days you need to PM admin to donate and he gives instructions.\r\n\r\nSo we need to edit it to reflect that i guess.....',NULL,NULL),(45025,5808,49532,'2012-07-25 11:03:48','I don\'t know if this is a bug or a feature, but the the description (including screenshot BBcode) is limited to 64K characters, but wasn\'t on the old site.\n\nI discovered this because I re-uploaded the littemutt siterip with it\'s very long list of titles and screenshots for every video.  I noticed that the screenshots didn\'t all appear, and the description source was truncated.\n\ncompare \n[url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35173]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35173[/url] and\n[url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=21028]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=21028[/url] with\n[url=http://torrents.empornium.me/details.php?id=21028]http://torrents.empornium.me/details.php?id=21028[/url]',49532,'2012-07-25 11:06:24'),(45028,5809,49532,'2012-07-25 11:21:27','The upload form gives an error, if you attempt to add more than 200 characters in the tags field.  I think that limit is too low.  That limit doesn\'t seem to be the maximum limit for all tags, since you can exceed it, by adding tags later.\r\n\r\nWhy not make the limit, on the upload form, the same as the maximum limit, for the torrent?',NULL,NULL),(45030,5808,47234,'2012-07-25 12:22:10','Im calling bug as we dont go out of our way to limit descriptions.\r\n\r\nAlthough that is an extreme presentation and very hard on users when they load the page.  But i have seen bigger :lol:\r\n\r\nI once saw one so large we had to remove it and PM the user as it was crashing web browsers.....  Im talking well over 1GB of RAM in use to load the page :lol:\r\n\r\nSo maybe a limit but not too small',NULL,NULL),(45032,5810,49532,'2012-07-25 12:42:03','One thing that fucking annoys the shit out of me, is when people put multiple versions of the same videos in a torrent. I would guess the reason the do this is they don\'t want to make multiple presentations/uploads. \r\n\r\nother people spend alot of time making multiple uploads, when they would rather spend that time rubbing their clit/cock.\r\n\r\nIt would be much better if they could add separate .torrent files for each version (resolution/codec/etc),to the same upload form, and the detail page would have a download button for each .torrent file. \r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45034,5810,47234,'2012-07-25 12:52:33','Interesting idea imm just trying to get my head around how it would work\r\n\r\nIm thinking gazelle would be more than capable of doing it as on What.CD you usually have multiple formats of the same CD.  For example FLAC, V2 and VO.\r\n\r\nWould we need to standardise for example for an upload have 1080, 720, 540, lower Res (i not sure on common resolutions below that) options?\r\n\r\nFor now the obvious workaround many uploaders use is copy the BBCode of the Presentation and paste it and only change for example the fact its called 1080 to 720.\r\n\r\nCould this be a better system?  Is there enough demand for it?',NULL,NULL),(45043,5808,49532,'2012-07-25 13:59:28','Yeah, this was definitly way fucking extreme, but I was trying my best to break something (a girl has to have her fun)  :yaydance: \n\nThere\'s no fucking way I\'d do that when this goes live.  I don\'t think anyone should NEED more that 64K to make a decent presentation. :rolleyes: \n\n',49532,'2012-07-25 14:00:01'),(45044,5808,47234,'2012-07-25 14:01:36','Breaking things is good.  Its not the number of characters i have a problem with but too many screens ina  presentation and the load time can get right up there...........',NULL,NULL),(45045,5805,129045,'2012-07-25 14:05:28','[quote]It looks like the part that is added to the torrent title (Freeleech! + coin symbol) is not used in the search indexing.[/quote]\r\n\r\nThis, it\'s not really a \'bug\'. It\'s just something that isn\'t implemented yet :hmmm:\r\n\r\nOn EMP.me people already suggested making FL torrents searchable, but I didn\'t follow the discussion, so I don\'t know if they reached any conclusion.',NULL,NULL),(45046,5806,49532,'2012-07-25 14:13:24','This isn\'t a bug. There\'s an error in your bbcode. Try: [b][code][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=EA16_4FDD4C29[/img][/code][/b]',NULL,NULL),(45047,5806,47234,'2012-07-25 14:21:13','Hmm hes right it works.  But yeah thats a nasty way to write BBcode.....',NULL,NULL),(45048,5805,47234,'2012-07-25 14:23:00','Moved to suggestions and renamed.\r\n\r\nIt would be a really nice feature to make an easy way to search for FL torrents.',NULL,NULL),(45049,5806,129045,'2012-07-25 14:23:54','I guess they could add an exception, as long as it meets either format: [code][img=][/code] or [code][img][/img][/code]\r\n\r\n[quote=Clownius]Hmm hes right it works.  But yeah thats a nasty way to write BBcode.....[/quote]\r\nWith xxx.freeimage.us (image served through PHP), the system will throw an error when using the [b]Img[/b] button, saying it only accepts PNG, GIF, JPG and JPEG, but if you try a second time it\'ll wrap the URL just fine.\r\n\r\nOne way or the other, there would be some hiccups :P',129045,'2012-07-25 14:31:50'),(45050,5763,85636,'2012-07-25 14:36:04','[size=3][b][color=#FF0000]Already in Help - Delete after double check[/color][/b][/size]\n\n\n[b][u]How to connect with xchat (this tutorial also works for clients based off of xchat such as HexChat)[/u][/b]\n\nFirstly we need to get xchat installed. For linux users it should be in your repository e.g. ubuntu is \"sudo apt-get install xchat\". If you are on windows you can grab it from [url=http://www.silverex.org/download/]here http://www.silverex.org/download/[/url].\n\nWhen you first run xchat you will be presented with a server connect list.\n\n[align=center][img]http://xchat.org/docs/start/xchat-1-servlist.png[/img][/align]\n\nChange your nickname and real name settings. Then click add to add a new IRC network and change the name to \"Empornium IRC\" and hit enter. \n\n[align=center][img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/xchat_server_edit.PNG[/img][/align]\n\nClick edit double click on \"newserver/6667\" and change it to \"irc.digitalwizardry.org/6697\", click the check boxes on Use SSL and Accept invalid SSL Certificate, and if you registered your nickname enter the password you resisted with.\n\n[align=center][img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/xchat_server_edit2.PNG[/img][/align]\n\nClick the close button, then click connect and that\'s you you should be connected to Empornium IRC over secure SSL.\n\nIf you have any problems feel free to drop by #empornium-help.',70679,'2012-09-10 19:47:16'),(45051,5810,129045,'2012-07-25 14:42:42','Didn\'t put much thought on this... but how would the torrent be managed? (Numbers of peers, snatches, its \'health\' etc)',NULL,NULL),(45052,5805,49532,'2012-07-25 14:45:50','[quote=Clownius]Moved to suggestions and renamed.\n\nIt would be a really nice feature to make an easy way to search for FL torrents.[/quote] Probably the easiest way, would be to generate a freeleech (or maybe free.leech) tag, for all freeleech  torrents. Then it\'s just a regular tag search.',49532,'2012-07-25 14:47:44'),(45053,5806,171777,'2012-07-25 14:45:53','[quote=Clownius]Hmm hes right it works.  But yeah thats a nasty way to write BBcode.....[/quote]\r\n\r\nNever said it was pretty code. It IS however correct BBcode.',NULL,NULL),(45055,5806,47234,'2012-07-25 14:53:49','Correct BBCode is whatever Mifune says it is here :lol:\n\nSeriously you should only be using = inside the [] when your also closing it later.\n\n[code][img=whatever][/img][/code]  You need to close the tag or bbcode gets all pissy.  Especially i have found on this site.',47234,'2012-07-25 14:54:40'),(45056,5806,84499,'2012-07-25 14:56:19','\r\noh, yeah I forgot about the [img=] format of displaying images.\r\n\r\nstupid mifune.\r\n\r\ngood catch :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(45057,5811,53597,'2012-07-25 15:00:48','i\'m not sure if its a bug or my fault, but i tried to add an image to my request w/o success. i used freeimage.us i tried every link it gave me, including just the url of the pic. i always get the error message \"[link] doesn\'t seem to be a direct link to an image\"\r\n\r\nas i sais, maybe i did somethin wrong, but tried everything i could think of. if it\'s not a bug, there should be some info what qualifies as an acceptible link.',NULL,NULL),(45058,5806,47234,'2012-07-25 15:02:44','Oh and another pro tip make sure you bbcode is in order it hates out of order bbcode too :sigh:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45059,5763,85636,'2012-07-25 15:06:45','[size=3][b][color=#FF0000]moved to Help - Delete after double check[/color][/b][/size]\n\n\n[b][u]IRSSI (Linux and Mac only but there is a windows version in beta)[/u][/b]\n\n[b]Getting Connected[/b]\n\nThe first step is to start irssi. Run from your shell:\n\n[quote]irssi[/quote]\nYou should now see Irssi in its default stateâ€“disconnected, with some blue bars at the top and bottom.\n\nIn Irssi, there are three important connection-related commands: /server, /connect, and /disconnect. Irssi can handle multiple IRC connections simultaneously, thus it is possible to be active in channels on different networks at the same time. The first command, /server, will connect to the specified server on the current network. On the other hand, /connect will open a new network connection and connect to the specified server on the new network.\n\nFor example, typing /connect irc.foo.com will open a new network connection and connect to irc.foo.com. If you then type /connect irc.bar.com, there will be two network connections open, one for irc.foo.com, one for irc.bar.com. Typing /server irc.baz.com while the network connection for irc.bar.com is active will disconnect the client from irc.bar.com and connect to irc.baz.com on that network connection. You can use Ctrl-X to switch between network connections. You can see what the active network is by looking at the status bar, which looks something like this:\n\n[align=center][img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/irssi_connect.PNG[/img][/align]\n\n(05:23:10) (irssi-test[+Tiwxz]) (1:SilentZombies (change with ^X))\n\nAt this point you should have a just-opened instance of Irssi, with no connections to any server. Connect to an IRC server by typing:\n\n[quote]/connect -ssl irc.digitalwizardry.org 6697[/quote]\n\nand change your nickname with:\n\n[quote]/nick [you][/quote]\n\nIf everything connected fine, join a channel by typing:\n\n[quote]/join #empornium[/quote]\n\n[align=center][img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/irssi_channel_join.PNG[/img][/align]\n\n[b]Switching Windows[/b]\n\nYou should now notice that the â€œstatusâ€ window is now hidden, and youâ€™re looking at the channel you just joined. You should also notice that your status bar says â€œ2:#emporniumâ€. This means that the window for #empornium is assigned window number 2. The status window is by default window number 1. To switch between windows in Irssi, use Alt-#, where # is 0-9. Windows start at number 1, and Alt-0 goes to window number 10. You can use Alt-q through Alt-o for windows 11 to 19. It is possible to have more than 19 windows. Use Alt with the arrow keys to scroll through the windows.\n\nTip: If youâ€™re trying to get to end windows past 19, start at window 1, and then use Alt with the left arrow key.\n\nAdvanced note: use /help bind to learn about the /bind command. It can be used to assign keyboard shortcuts to windows past 19.\n\nTo get support for auto-identifying you to nickserv you will need to get an external plugin for irssi:[url=http://scripts.irssi.org/scripts/nickserv.pl]http://scripts.irssi.org/scripts/nickserv.pl[/url]. Adding and managing plugins is beyond the scope of this tutorial but there are guides on how to do it on the IRSSI website.',70679,'2012-09-10 21:12:17'),(45060,5811,129045,'2012-07-25 15:19:07',':hmmm:\r\n\r\nOdd, it should behave the same as the Cover area on Uploads.\r\n\r\nThis really needs some fixin\'\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b] [b]Workarounds[/b]\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/requests.php?action=view&id=15\r\n\r\nRight click over the fullsize image in xxx.freeimage.us and copy its address\\link\\url\r\n\r\nThe resulting URL should contain xxx.freeimage.us[color=#FF0000]/image.php[/color], ignore thumb.php and share.php they will not work with this method.\r\n\r\ne.g. xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=XXXX_00000000\r\n\r\nEdit the URL replacing [color=#FF0000].php?id=[/color] with a hyphen [color=#FF0000]-[/color] and then append [color=#FF0000].jpg[/color]:     xxx.freeimage.us/image[color=#FF0000]-[/color]XXXX_00000000[color=#FF0000].jpg[/color]\r\n\r\nOR\r\n\r\nSimply append [color=#FF0000]&.jpg[/color] to the link:     xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=XXXX_00000000[color=#FF0000]&.jpg[/color]',129045,'2012-07-25 19:44:37'),(45061,5802,84499,'2012-07-25 15:30:33','\r\n\r\nI dunno, it dosent do anything malicious afaik - just looks fucked up. And if someone wants to use it in their sig or something I dont see the particular harm... if someone abuses it we could deal with it on a case by case basis. \r\n\r\n\r\nIf we want to prevent it automagically I guess we could remove any text not in the \'standard\' unicode range  :hmmm: \r\n',NULL,NULL),(45062,5772,94804,'2012-07-25 15:33:10','allright, but my objection to the 100,000/250,000cdts-badge still stands.',NULL,NULL),(45063,5805,47234,'2012-07-25 15:33:22','I have manually done the same when i have made torrents freeleech on Emp now.  But having it done automagically would be nice',NULL,NULL),(45064,5802,129045,'2012-07-25 15:33:52','As long as that allows me to keep funny faces lol (à¹‘ï½¥â—¡ï½¥)\r\n\r\nYou already destroyed my custom title, let me have those at least :laugh:',129045,'2012-07-25 16:19:34'),(45065,5805,129045,'2012-07-25 15:37:00','For extra convenience, it should append \"Freeleech\" to the description area, that way a quick search from the top bar will also bring them up',129045,'2012-07-25 15:38:36'),(45067,5810,84499,'2012-07-25 15:44:01','\r\nThis idea isnt a bad idea, there are a lot of pros, although there are cons too (added complexity for users and policing the system). However whatever the merits or downsides its not going to happen, we made a decision early on to go with one torrent uploads only and its just too late in the day to change. Maybe emp.me v3?\r\n\r\nbtw: Multiple versions of the same file in one torrent are not allowed on emp anymore, so you shouldnt be seeing them.',NULL,NULL),(45068,5812,49532,'2012-07-25 16:01:01','As an altenative to Cassie\'s multi-torrent upload suggestion, I have a much simpler one:\r\n\r\nMake a \"Clone\" button, which would open an upload form with all of the fields preloaded with the data from the original. This will make things easier to upload another resolution, not only for the original uploader, but also anyone else.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45069,5807,84499,'2012-07-25 16:12:04','\r\n\r\nYou make a valid point... is hiding the description with a toggle (hide)-(View) link better than having a link that shoots you down the page to the thanks/comments section?',NULL,NULL),(45070,5802,85636,'2012-07-25 16:17:31','Â¬_Â¬',NULL,NULL),(45071,5806,84499,'2012-07-25 16:27:43','[quote=Clownius]Correct BBCode is whatever Mifune says it is here :lol:\r\n\r\nSeriously you should only be using = inside the [] when your also closing it later.\r\n\r\n[code][img=whatever][/img][/code]  You need to close the tag or bbcode gets all pissy.  Especially i have found on this site.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nsorry actually with img tags it does not quite work that way lol. With an img tag you can use either [code][img]content[/img][/code] or [code][img=whatever][/code] This is the way the bbcode from emp (and every other forum) works, I blame the internet.\r\n\r\nThe reason you have to close say a url tag is because there is [code][url=attrib]content[/url][/code] functionality. Img tags can only have one bit of info so its possible to have a single tag version, most tags cant work like this.',NULL,NULL),(45073,5812,94804,'2012-07-25 17:08:14','yrah',NULL,NULL),(45074,5807,94804,'2012-07-25 17:11:33','[s]or limit the description[/s]\nnah, then there\'s the problem limit it at what length, hide = better',94804,'2012-07-25 17:11:56'),(45075,5813,94804,'2012-07-25 17:15:54','This\'s great fun, but when will the site go live? Just curious (so when is decided \"this is the best we can do\", bugs will always arise, even after test has been cancelled)',NULL,NULL),(45076,5813,129045,'2012-07-25 17:24:39','[align=center][img]http://i.imgur.com/4zpq8.gif[/img]\r\n[size=4][i]Between now and a billion years![/i][/size][/align]\r\n\r\nIIRC, I read Clownius posting something about the server being contracted for 3 months, so I guess there\'s no hurry... even though those weeks are flying real fast :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(45077,5813,84499,'2012-07-25 17:49:57','\r\n\r\nwhen we feel its ready.\r\n\r\nor\r\n\r\nin 2 weeks.\r\n\r\n\r\n(one of these answers is always correct)\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45078,5619,94551,'2012-07-25 17:56:50','Same issue using IE. Password recovery worked without a problem though.',NULL,NULL),(45079,5807,86439,'2012-07-25 18:57:16','Toggle\n\nCan the toggle button float and follow you down the page? Just so you dont have to scroll back up when youre say half way down.',86439,'2012-07-25 18:58:49'),(45080,5807,84499,'2012-07-25 19:20:16','\r\n\r\nDescription is now collapsable.',NULL,NULL),(45081,5807,84499,'2012-07-25 19:20:33','[quote=knickers]Toggle\r\n\r\nCan the toggle button float and follow you down the page? Just so you dont have to scroll back up when youre say half way down.[/quote]\r\n\r\ner, no. well, you can fix elements to the viewport, so they stay in one place on the screen, but then its there wherever you are on the page not just when you are over the description. ',NULL,NULL),(45082,5774,84499,'2012-07-25 19:22:35','\r\nI made them a bit darker.',NULL,NULL),(45084,5811,53597,'2012-07-25 19:26:16','i tried both methods in this req http://empornium.mooo.com/requests.php?action=view&id=14 and this picture http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=F58F_50102B62\r\n\r\nnone of them worked. i don\'t get the error message, but in the cover section there is just the name of the image but no image.',NULL,NULL),(45085,5807,86439,'2012-07-25 19:35:05','Awww bugger, that wouldnt be very friendly.',NULL,NULL),(45086,5811,129045,'2012-07-25 19:35:19','Sorry, I should be clearer:\r\n\r\nYou need to use the link that has [b]image.php[/b] in the url, [i]thumb.php[/i] and [i]share.php[/i] will not work.\r\n\r\nVisit http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=F58F_50102B62 , right click over the full size image and there should be a \"Copy image address\" option in the context menu or something similar, use it.\r\n\r\nThe resulting link should be this one: http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=F58F_50102B62\r\n\r\nThen you replace its parts like I said or append [color=#FF0000]&.jpg[/color] to it.\r\n\r\n\r\nAnyway, this should behave like the Cover area in torrent uploads, it accepts the imge.php link without forcing the user to edit it :)',129045,'2012-07-25 19:49:20'),(45087,5774,86439,'2012-07-25 19:41:29','Yeah I noticed them being darker. Thought it might be just me.\r\n\r\nIf you cant differentiate between them now, may I suggest a new monitor, change the angle, see a doctor.',NULL,NULL),(45088,5787,53597,'2012-07-25 19:44:00','i agree that the suggested search-feature would be terrific. i regularly check torrent sites for lexi doing anal. i always get resutls, because lexi performs in vidz were other girls do anal. i would love to directly look for lexi belle getting fucked in the ass. so i think this feature would be a great enhancement.\r\n\r\nbut i understand the reservations against making tagging more complex.',NULL,NULL),(45089,5807,129045,'2012-07-25 19:46:36','Time to put the [b][i]Home[/i][/b] and [b