dn\'t even notice the quote box extending all the way down...  :hmmm:\n\nusb[/b]\n\n:hmmm:[/quote]\nPLUS CERTAIN THINGS MAKE YOU GO BLIND(wwoops capslock)[/quote]\n\nhuh? when I click \"post reply\"\nit posts it inside that gray area, like it\'s part of tyhat last post while it\'s actually a new post. using latest Chrome\n\n\n\n[EDIT: fixed fucked up quote tag - mifune]\n\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]split from thread[/i][br]\'deadline?\'[/size][/align]',84499,'2012-07-26 01:01:00'),(45115,5805,48010,'2012-07-25 21:00:42','fuck you pinkie\r\n[quote=mifune]I agree we need to do something... the auto tag approach might well be the best way.\r\n\r\nwe are definitely not adding a freeleech category (pink or not) :D[/quote]\r\nand never a pink category :grin:',NULL,NULL),(45116,5811,129045,'2012-07-25 21:01:11','[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=2397_5010428D][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=2397_5010428D&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=FAF6_5010428D][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=FAF6_5010428D&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nNo this affects everybody, the [b]Image[/b] box will only accept direct links, so using http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=F58F_50102B62&jpg will not work\r\n\r\nWhile the Cover feature on http://empornium.mooo.com/upload.php (\"Cover Image\") will accept it just fine, so the problem is:\r\n\r\n[size=3]While they serve the same purpose, they work differently[/size].\r\n\r\nAnd there\'s no reason for that, so there\'s no need for all this confusion, it should simply behave the same as the Cover feature on torrent uploads.',NULL,NULL),(45117,5815,84499,'2012-07-25 21:01:15','\r\nthat is a bug.',NULL,NULL),(45118,5811,48010,'2012-07-25 21:05:21','I\'ll leave that to the coders :grin:',NULL,NULL),(45119,5815,84499,'2012-07-25 21:11:33','\r\nwhen did you get that message? :hmmm:\r\n\r\nit must have been missing a variable in the config but I think its okay now.',NULL,NULL),(45120,5811,84499,'2012-07-25 21:2