824,84499,'2012-07-26 02:41:16','\r\nWhen you create a blog post it creates a thread for it automagically if you dont fill in the thread id field... thats fine except you get no choice over which forum its created in! \r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2823\r\n\r\nI wondered why ppl were posting threads about blog posts in usbs random forum :lol:',NULL,NULL),(45205,5763,85636,'2012-07-26 03:18:15','[size=3][b][color=#FF0000]All now in Help - Delete after double check[/color][/b][/size]\n\nWork in Progress.\n\n[b][u]Chatzilla[/u][/b]\n\n[b]Getting Chatzilla.[/b]\n\nTo get chatzilla all you need is a mozilla browser such as Firefox. First start up firefox and then get chatzilla from the addon\'s site [url=https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/chatzilla/]here https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/chatzilla/[/url], you may need to restart firefox after you install chatzilla.\n\n[img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/chatzilla-install.png[/img]\n\n[b]Setting up chatzilla[/b]\n\nTo start chatzilla click on tools, then chatzilla. The chatzilla client window will popup\n\n[img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/chatzilla-fresh-installed.png[/img]\n\nto connect to Empornium IRC enter:\n\n[quote]/sslserver irc.emprn.tk 6697[/quote]\n\n[img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/chatzilla-connect.png[/img]\n\nto add empornium IRC as a default network [url=http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/faq/#networks]please read this guide.[/url]\n\nWhen you connect you will be warned that the server has an invalid certificate, click \"add exeption\" and remember to change your nickname to the one you use on the site:\n\n[quote]/nick [you][/quote]\n\nFinally to join a channel simply enter:\n\n[quote]/join #empornium[/quote]\n\n[img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/chatzilla-in-channel.png[/img]\n\nThe different symbols and colored blobs to the left of each user in the userlist indicate their respective status within the channel. Available levels, from most to least powerful are:\n\n[img]http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/common/image/userlist-founder-symbol.png[/img][size=1]/[/size][img]http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/common/image/userlist-founder-graphic.png[/img] - Founder - ultimate power. Can do anything to the channel and those within it. Usually represents the user who registered the channel. Only certain networks support founders.\n[img]http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/common/image/userlist-admin-symbol.png[/img][size=1]/[/size][img]http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/common/image/userlist-admin-graphic.png[/img] - Admin - a normal operator, but protected from being kicked by anyone except the founder. Only certain networks support admins.\n[img]http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/common/image/userlist-op-symbol.png[/img][size=1]/[/size][img]http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/common/image/userlist-op-graphic.png[/img] - Operator (op) - the user can grant and revoke operator, half-operator and voice status, change the topic, kick other users and generally control the channel.\n[img]http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/common/image/userlist-halfop-symbol.png[/img][size=1]/[/size][img]http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/common/image/userlist-halfop-graphic.png[/img] - Half-operator (half-op) - the user has the power to moderate the channel, change the topic and kick people, but cannot kick other half-operators nor higher-ranking users, nor can he/she create new operators/half-operators. Only certain networks support half-operators.\n[img]http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/common/image/userlist-voice-symbol.png[/img][size=1]/[/size][img]http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/common/image/userlist-voice-graphic.png[/img] - Voice - the user can talk in the channel when it is moderated. Often used to mark people as trusted or helpful without giving them any real power.\n[size=1]/[/size][img]http://chatzilla.hacksrus.com/common/image/userlist-no-graphic.png[/img] - Normal - the user has no special status.\n',70679,'2012-09-10 20:09:33'),(45206,5824,84499,'2012-07-26 03:27:25','\r\n\r\nadded a selection box and some error checking to stop threads from being created with no valid forumid.',NULL,NULL),(45210,5814,129045,'2012-07-26 03:43:19','Nah, I don\'t know. I mentioned the game jokingly, I really just wanted more threads listed there :\\',NULL,NULL),(45212,5814,84499,'2012-07-26 03:57:43','we dont always get what we want [img]http://s4.tinypic.com/242tp1z_th.gif[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n:lol:\r\n\r\n\r\nyeah I dunno, I\'m not sure I want it any bigger... anyone else care?',NULL,NULL),(45213,5783,129045,'2012-07-26 03:59:36','Well, that never happened to me either :P\r\n\r\nI had opened multiple threads and forgot them in the background, when I clicked back to read them, I tried to fix one of my posts, that\'s how I triggered it the first time (trying to edit a post).\r\n\r\nGot it a couple more times, but for the screenshots I had to force the situation by opening various EMP threads\\torrent pages and then logging out.',NULL,NULL),(45214,5814,129045,'2012-07-26 04:03:25',' :ignore: \r\n  :ras:\r\n\r\nI gotta go catch some Z\'s, [i]I\'ll dream of having a bajillion threads listed under \"[b]Latest forum topics[/b]\", it\'ll be glorious [/i] lol\r\n\r\nK bye :)',NULL,NULL),(45216,5814,86439,'2012-07-26 04:18:27','Yeah, I think its too short. Not now so much, but when the site is live it will be kind of pointless, unless youre sitting there waiting for a reply and hitting refresh every 20 seconds. Well, maybe slight exaggeration.\r\n\r\n\r\nNo option for a separate page that in real time pops up links to latest threads posted in? One forum I frequent used to have this, it came in handy when the joint was hopping. Or even just a page with all the new posts listed. I havent found one of those yet either. But you know, apparently it does make you go blind.',NULL,NULL),(45218,5827,84499,'2012-07-26 04:50:20','\r\n\r\nIf you could all vote for the tags on any torrents you check out... and add tags, and if you are the uploader you can add tags with a higher score and delete your own tags as well.\r\n\r\nthanks    :chase: ',NULL,NULL),(45220,5828,84845,'2012-07-26 04:59:35','UPDATE - I hadn\'t noticed that advanced search supports [b]boolean[/b] searches.  That IS significant.  Please close this bug.  Thanks.\n\nMicrofine\n\n***************\n\nHi,\n\nI notice the difference between basic search and advanced search is one field (I\'ll double check this after posting as maybe the field names changed on two of the fields I feel are duplicate).  If the difference is only one field, we should think about combining them into a single unified search page.\n\nIt\'s more of an annoyance than anything - not above a priority 3 in my opinion.\n\nDouble checking now.\n\nMicrofine',84845,'2012-07-26 05:01:36'),(45221,5747,84845,'2012-07-26 05:14:26','I\'m not sure if this is related or not.  I opened search center and went to Advanced search, selected some variables and set them as my default.  I then searched for a term (puke AND Big.tits).  No results were found.  I closed search center expecting to see the list of Torrents for browsing. This is not the case.  I had to open search center, clear my terms, search (or is it called \"filter\"?), all torrents display.  I then close search center and browse torrents.  However, I took it another step and went to the forum.  I looked at one post, then clicked the Torrents link at the very top of the page.  I was taken to Torrents, but search center was open and my last search terms (puke AND big.tits) were in the search field and there were NO RESULTS.  I had to clear the search terms and click search (or filter) again.  This bug is reproducible.\r\n\r\nLet me know if you have any questions or need me to re-test.  Thanks.\r\n\r\nMicrofine',NULL,NULL),(45222,5827,86439,'2012-07-26 05:22:24','Lady Ginga torrent   http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35177\n\nVoted down lady.ginga (was 3) (now 2)\nVoted down dildo (was 8) (now 7)  then tried to vote it up, no change\nVoted up anal (was 8) (now 9)\nAdded porcupine (added at +3)\n\nJust noticed the green bar telling me my vote was counted or some such\nAdded ginger.megs (added at +3) green bar states \"your tag ginger.megs added\" or some such. It disappears after a few seconds, maybe 2 or so.\n\nAdded tag, mifune.spanked\n\nGot red error bar stating already voted on lady.ginga when I tried to up the vote on that tag. That red error bar appears to stay, not time out.',86439,'2012-07-26 05:24:42'),(45223,5829,84845,'2012-07-26 05:23:04','At the bottom of each page in both the old tracker and the new tracker, the torrent numbers display (1-25, 26-50, 51-75, etc.) as hyperlinks.  The design flaw is that (in Firefox at least), I can\'t tell which page I\'m on, until I mouse over each page and find the page that isn\'t a hyperlink.\r\n\r\nThe suggestion is to somehow identify the \"current\" page (underline, bold, make larger, etc.).  Thanks.\r\n\r\nMicrofine.',NULL,NULL),(45225,5747,86439,'2012-07-26 05:35:29','See this thread too. It seems related.\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2666',86439,'2012-07-26 05:37:05'),(45227,5827,86439,'2012-07-26 06:08:54','How long does a torrent take to appear in the browse list?\r\n\r\n\r\nI just tried (15 minutes ago thereabouts) to up one, full of terrible tags and not categorised correctly. 1 screen for about 6 clips. I entered everything it asks for, including the screen but when I hit \'upload torrent\' I just got a blank browser page (FF Win XP). I page backed the page, and now i see everything there, but \'upload torrent\' is dulled. I can only preview and make changes.\r\n\r\nI go from entering details page, and this is what i get next http://empornium.mooo.com/upload.php , its blank. No error messages, no opportunity to fix errors, nadda, but I cant see it listed in the torrents page.\r\n\r\nI just tried again, same issue.',NULL,NULL),(45229,5812,49532,'2012-07-26 06:47:46','[quote=mifune]I think it has some merits... it takes about 9 clicks/keys to acheive what that 1 click would do.\r\n\r\nBut... I dont think we would let you \'rip\' someone elses presentation. [/quote]\r\n\r\nDo you think people are that possessive of their presentations? I copy peoples presentations on most of my uploads, it\'s just more work than this.\r\n\r\nWell you could make the presentation be credited to it\'s source, by adding an uneditable line - e.g.:[quote]This presentation was cloned from [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35169]Hentai Pack 5 [/url] uploaded by [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=3027]splinter[/url][/quote]',NULL,NULL),(45230,5830,49532,'2012-07-26 07:04:24','sometimes people change there mind about a tag, and sometimes they just click wrong.  it would be great if we could change our votes.\r\n\r\nit would work like this: if I voted +, I could click - to remove the vote,  and have my voted status removed. Then if I want to vote -, it would be like a fresh vote. Of course it would work the other way around too.\r\n\r\nIf that is too complicated you could make it: \r\nif I voted +, then change my mind, I would click - and it would subtract 2.\r\n\r\nI think that you should be able to reverse your vote an infinate number of times.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45231,5820,171777,'2012-07-26 07:12:44','I don\'t even remember quoting anything there and still my own post is emtpy aswell so this is might not be a faulty BB tag.',NULL,NULL),(45232,5807,171777,'2012-07-26 07:14:35','Thank you',NULL,NULL),(45233,5798,171777,'2012-07-26 07:29:56','[quote=Clownius]Oh i beg of you please ban IE .....  I swear you spend half your bug squashing time on bugs that only affect IE...[/quote]\r\n\r\nIt gets even better. The same bug does not effect all versions of IE so the total list of IE bugs is even longer overal :P',NULL,NULL),(45234,5831,49532,'2012-07-26 07:30:52','I share this account with my 2 lovers, but it would be nice if we could have our  own identities for posting in the forums and making comments.  I\'m sure there are others in this same situation.\r\n\r\nAlso, it would be great for Staff members to have one identity, to post there personal thoughts as a user, and another to post in there roll as staff (e.g. Clownius, LordClownius).\r\n\r\nThe easiest way I can think of it to have username aliases: In the profile there would be input fields for adding aliases, then on forum and comment add/edit forms, there would be a pulldown menu to select which Alias it will be posted as.\r\n\r\nThis should be on both add and edit forms, because it\'s easy to forget to select one.',NULL,NULL),(45235,5807,49532,'2012-07-26 07:36:15','if the description is collapsed, does that stop screensots from loading?',NULL,NULL),(45236,5807,171777,'2012-07-26 07:49:08','[quote=apparition]if the description is collapsed, does that stop screensots from loading?[/quote]\r\nNope. All images are still loaded in the hidden part.',NULL,NULL),(45237,5798,49532,'2012-07-26 08:10:56','[quote=Clownius]Oh i beg of you please ban IE .....  I swear you spend half your bug squashing time on bugs that only affect IE...[/quote]\r\n+1 for banning IE.\r\n\r\nBut in the other hand, IE is only on MS Windows. People with real operating systems don\'t need to worry. :smartass:',NULL,NULL),(45238,5832,49532,'2012-07-26 08:17:14','The smiley images are reversed \r\n\r\n[code]:smart:[/code] :smart: \r\n\r\n[code]:smartass:[/code] :smartass:',NULL,NULL),(45240,6042,94804,'2012-07-26 09:27:08','[quote=yamchan07bb]Wankers, don\'t you guys try to come here showing good intention trying to find where shit went wrong, you know you fucked it up :laugh:[/quote][i][size=1]Anyway... I went back and found where usb had put a bold tag and then not closed it in his first quoting post... which everyone else then also quoted... so there were about 6 unclosed bold tags on the page![/size][/i]\nso it was usb!:)\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]split from thread[/i][br]\'deadline?\'[/size][/align]',94804,'2012-07-26 09:28:12'),(45241,5833,171777,'2012-07-26 09:41:16','Looking through the rules pages I found that the different pages use different layouts. Since they are however all rules this should technically be all the same. The ones that are very obvious are:\r\nRequests\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=requests\r\nClients\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=clients\r\nAvatars\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=avatar\r\nForum\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/articles.php?topic=forum_guidelines\r\n\r\nAlso I noticed a small spelling error in the rules overview:\r\nApproved Image hosts	 This is a [b]liost[/b] of all the approved image hosts to be used at Empornium',NULL,NULL),(45242,5774,89443,'2012-07-26 09:52:00','Definitely way better now but it would probably be even better if the title of the thread (that has been viewed) was a bit lighter in shade as well.\n\nAlso, any thoughts on my other suggestion? The one about having some sort of icon next to a thread that you have posted in so that you can easily see that thread. \n\nEdit: I noticed that an arrow shows up if you view a thread. I guess that\'s basically what I was suggesting except it would be a bit more specific.',89443,'2012-07-26 09:56:55'),(45243,5834,171777,'2012-07-26 10:04:30','For the sake of testing the reporting function I was trying to upload a random torrent. I used the same info as I have done a few times before (while testing removal of torrents) but now I keep getting \"HTTP error 500\"\r\n\r\nInfo:\r\nBrowser: Google Chrome latest version\r\nLocation of error: http://empornium.mooo.com/upload.php\r\n\r\nError has happened 7 times so far. all between 09:45 and 10:00 local time (I am writing this at 10:03 as a reference so roughly 15 minutes before this was posted).\r\nInformation used while trying to upload:\r\nCategory: Anal\r\nTag: 720p\r\ndescr:\r\n[code][align=center]\r\n[img=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=EA16_4FDD4C29]\r\n[size=4]Anal Queen Alysa - Photosets[/size]\r\n[/align]\r\n\r\nThis pack contains all the photo sets for an earlier uploaded torrent.\r\nThe torrent in question can be found at [url]http://torrents.empornium.me/details.php?id=32859[/url] and was uploaded by DeSaRieD.\r\n\r\n[size=3]A quick overview of the different episodes[/size]\r\n\r\n[img=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=D029_4FDD7E72]\r\n\r\n[size=3]Sample pictures[/size]\r\n\r\n[img=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=F317_4FDD4D0C]\r\n[img=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=D8C0_4FDD4D0C]\r\n[img=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=6E97_4FDD4D0C]\r\n[img=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=BA58_4FDD4D0C]\r\n[img=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=9523_4FDD4A34]\r\n\r\n[size=3]Requests[/size]\r\n\r\nIf you have any specific scene from the 21sectury network, or any model of which you want all scenes, please let me know and I\'ll see what can do for you. Just be nice. If you request things atleast also help seed them as long as you can.\r\n\r\n[size=3]Brought to you by[/size]\r\n\r\n[url=http://torrents.empornium.me/userdetails.php?id=171777][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=AC68_4FD5055B&gif[/img][/url] Click picure for my other torrents.\r\n\r\n[size=2]Like the torrent? Drop a comment or thank you if you please.[/size][/code]\r\n(yes the preview shows this correctly and this is also literally something currently in use on the old website).\r\n\r\nThe torrentfile I am using is somewhat bigger. The file is also actively in use on the old website (http://torrents.empornium.me/details.php?id=35437). The file shows to be uploaded correctly. The browser states that it is waiting for an answer from the site and nothing happens.',NULL,NULL),(45244,6042,1507,'2012-07-26 10:43:05','[quote=schlager][quote=yamchan07bb]Wankers, don\'t you guys try to come here showing good intention trying to find where shit went wrong, you know you fucked it up :laugh:[/quote][i][size=1]Anyway... I went back and found where usb had put a bold tag and then not closed it in his first quoting post... which everyone else then also quoted... so there were about 6 unclosed bold tags on the page![/size][/i]\r\nso it was usb!:)[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]was there any doubt....???  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]split from thread[/i][br]\'deadline?\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(45245,5831,1238,'2012-07-26 10:56:08',' :group: ',NULL,NULL),(45246,5834,86439,'2012-07-26 11:00:14','So its not just me then? This is likely the same as I posted earlier but wasnt sure if it was my own error so was waiting for a reply before listing a bug.\r\n\r\n[quote=knickers]How long does a torrent take to appear in the browse list?\r\n\r\n\r\nI just tried (15 minutes ago thereabouts) to up one, full of terrible tags and not categorised correctly. 1 screen for about 6 clips. I entered everything it asks for, including the screen but when I hit \'upload torrent\' I just got a blank browser page (FF Win XP). I page backed the page, and now i see everything there, but \'upload torrent\' is dulled. I can only preview and make changes.\r\n\r\nI go from entering details page, and this is what i get next http://empornium.mooo.com/upload.php , its blank. No error messages, no opportunity to fix errors, nadda, but I cant see it listed in the torrents page.\r\n\r\nI just tried again, same issue.[/quote]\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2827&page=1#post25227',NULL,NULL),(45250,5812,47234,'2012-07-26 11:33:42','[quote=apparition]Do you think people are that possessive of their presentations? [/quote]\r\n\r\nShort answer is some sure as hell are :lol:\r\n\r\nI was thinking copy and paste your own uploads not someone elses.  The idea you could or would didnt even enter my mind to be honest.  So if was your own post you could got to edit and copy and paste everything including the BBCode.  Im sure some users do already if they wish to save them self work when uploading multiple Resolutions of the same Video',NULL,NULL),(45251,5833,47234,'2012-07-26 11:37:21','Lol Make more work for me DrkNess :(\r\n\r\nI will have a look at it tomorrow or the next day.\r\n\r\nCurrently different sections have been done by different people.  Some sections are even still from What.CD (requests anyone) but didnt need a change.\r\n\r\nIt would be nice to clean it all up though.\r\n\r\nI would love to say i would look at it and fix it all sometime but yeah... I dont even know what im working in 2 days time atm.',NULL,NULL),(45252,5818,53597,'2012-07-26 11:44:42','good thing i kept my bounty moderate. i hope those guys giving some tb to test the system were in on it ^^\r\n\r\nthere should be a warning of sorts. it\'s one thing to be willing to give your gigs for a fulfilled request and quite another for merely the meager chance of fulfillment.',NULL,NULL),(45253,5835,53597,'2012-07-26 11:52:56','before changing to .me only, there was a search bar plugin for emp for you browser. you could search for tags and titles and it was very useful to me and maybe some others.\r\n\r\nyou could find and install it on http://mycroft.mozdev.org/search-engines.html. it think you can create your own search tools right there. if anyone got a handle on that, it would be great to have that search function back for the new emp.',NULL,NULL),(45254,5835,129045,'2012-07-26 14:09:42','You mean been able to do a quick search directly from the addressbar?\r\n\r\nI think most browsers offer an option to create a custom search engine using an operator, if you visit http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php and right click inside one of the search boxes, the context menu will probably have that option.\r\n\r\nBut there will be no option to look into titles only (the basic search will always look in the title and description) :hmmm:\r\n\r\nAdd a custom search engine using those addresses:\r\n\r\n[b]Tags[/b] (keyword\\operator example [color=#FF0000]e1[/color]) > [code]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=advanced&taglist=%s[/code] \r\n\r\n[b]Title, Descriptiom[/b] (keyword\\operator example [color=#FF0000]e2[/color]) > [code]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=advanced&text=%s[/code] \r\n\r\n[b]File list[/b] (keyword\\operator example [color=#FF0000]e3[/color]) > [code]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=advanced&filelist=%s[/code] \r\n\r\nAnd you will be able to do searches directly from the addressbar, example: Typing [color=#FF0000]e1 big.boobs[/color] will return all torrents with tag',129045,'2012-07-26 14:10:43'),(45257,5836,94804,'2012-07-26 14:48:58','I\'m not that into IRC so I could be wrong, but isn\'t # supposed to be succeeded by a channel name?\r\nthird bullet: Do not link shock sites or anything NSFW (not safe for work) without a warning. If in doubt, ask a staff member in # about it.',NULL,NULL),(45258,5837,129045,'2012-07-26 14:51:49','[size=2][i]This is just an interface \'problem\' and only appears when the system tries to truncate some text and its last charater happens to be a special character.\r\nSpeaking with [b]mifune[/b], he made a good point: [b]the solution may not be worth it[/b]. Anyway, he asked for a thread to be made.[/i][/size]\r\n\r\n\r\n[b][i]What I\'m talking about:[/i][/b]\r\nSimple example, look at my user title, while you see a single character [color=#FF0000]ãƒŽ[/color] , it\'s actually a code comprised of 8 characters [size=4][b]&#12494[color=#000000];[/color][/b][/size]\r\nIf you copy that code and try to post it, you will see that your browser will replace it automatically with ãƒŽ, just try it, paste it in the post box and hit preview.\r\n\r\n(ãƒŽ`Ð”Â´)ãƒŽå½¡â”»â”â”»\r\n\r\nSince the limit for user titles are 32 characters (my title had quite a few of special characters), what appeared to be 11 characters were actually over 50 characters total, that\'s why it\'s appears cut now.\r\n\r\n[b][i]Problem:[/i][/b]\r\nThose special characters need their full code intact in order to appear correctly, that means from the ampersand ([color=#FF0000]&[/color]) to the semicolon ([color=#FF0000];[/color]), if one of them gets cut, the browser will simply see them as plain text (e.g. an apostrophe or single quote will not appear as \', but broken as [color=#FF0000]&#39[/color])\r\n\r\n[b]This affects thread titles on the Forum\'s front page[/b], where titles are truncated at 50 characters, so while you see 47 characters: [color=#FF0000]BUG: Expired Session - Login prompt Interface \'[/color] http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2783 the system is accounting for 51 characters, truncating will eliminate the semicolon from the [size=4][color=#FF0000]\'[/color][/size] code, so it\'ll appear broken.\r\n\r\nThis doesn\'t really break anything as far as I can tell (threads will still work just fine), but it will not be fixed simply by increasing the character limit, as long as the special character is the last character, truncating it will trigger this isse.\r\n\r\nSo don\'t freak out if you see some odd code appearing in the Forum\'s front page :P',129045,'2012-07-26 14:54:14'),(45259,5836,171777,'2012-07-26 15:01:34','read the # symbol as the word channel. Sort of IRC slang.',NULL,NULL),(45260,5838,171777,'2012-07-26 15:05:23','Right now if I try to look at uploaded torrents by a user and he has his paranoia setting to high I get an error 403: You just tried to go to a page that you don\'t have enough permission to view.\r\n\r\nThe reason is most likely the paranoia but should it then not say something along the lines of: The user does not wish to share this information. Right now it is rather confusing as to what is going wrong.\r\n\r\nSpecific example: \r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?type=uploaded&userid=94804\r\nfor the user [b]schlager [/b](http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=94804)',NULL,NULL),(45261,5747,129045,'2012-07-26 15:10:27','[quote=microfine][color=#FF0000]I\'m not sure if this is related or not.  I opened search center and went to Advanced search, selected some variables and set them as my default.  I then searched for a term (puke AND Big.tits).[/color]  No results were found.  I closed search center expecting to see the list of Torrents for browsing. This is not the case.  I had to open search center, clear my terms, search (or is it called \"filter\"?), all torrents display.  I then close search center and browse torrents.  However, I took it another step and went to the forum.  I looked at one post, then clicked the Torrents link at the very top of the page.  I was taken to Torrents, but search center was open and my last search terms (puke AND big.tits) were in the search field and there were NO RESULTS.  I had to clear the search terms and click search (or filter) again.  This bug is reproducible.\r\n\r\nLet me know if you have any questions or need me to re-test.  Thanks.\r\n\r\nMicrofine[/quote]\r\n\r\nDid you type [color=#FF0000]puke AND Big.tits[/color] [b]BEFORE[/b] or [b]AFTER[/b] clicking on \"[b]Make Default[/b]\"?\r\n\r\nIf you selected the categories and typed the tags and [b]THEN[/b] clicked on \"[b]Make Default[/b]\", it\'s not a bug, it\'s the expected behavior.\r\n\r\n\"[b]Make Default[/b]\" will do exactly what it says, it basically [b]saves[/b] whatever you searched. Look at it\'s side, you should see \"[b]Clear Default[/b]\", click on it and things will be back to normal.\r\n\r\n[b]An example of correct usage would be selecting your favorite categories along with some tags or keywords to be excluded[/b]. That way everytime you came back to http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php ALL the torrents would be filtered only showing your favorite things.\r\n\r\nDon\'t use it for random searches, if you just want to do a simple search, type the tags\\keywords and click on [b]Filter[/b]\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]Now[/b], if you used \"Make Default\" with the search fields empty and it still saved the tags you used afterwards, then it\'s a bug :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(45262,5836,94804,'2012-07-26 15:15:15','aah',NULL,NULL),(45263,5838,129045,'2012-07-26 15:16:20','I guess you\'re right, let\'s stress test it, try to access mine: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?type=uploaded&userid=129045\r\n\r\nI have everything disabled, post the results and I will enable the Uploaded stats.\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b] I can access his list normally, but it\'s most likely because I was added to First Line Support :hmmm:',129045,'2012-07-26 15:19:16'),(45264,5827,49532,'2012-07-26 15:40:34','[url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35169]Hentai Pack 5[/url]:\r\n\r\nI voted down tag dmitrysfutaeliashottieshentaideviljigglygirls, to 0 but it still appears in the [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php]main torrent list[/url] ',NULL,NULL),(45266,5839,49532,'2012-07-26 15:53:10','here\'s a weird one. my avatar stopped showing up in my posts to [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2760]The Last Person To Post Wins[/url] thread, but it still appears everywhere else.\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2760&postid=25239#post25239\n',49532,'2012-07-26 15:53:31'),(45267,5827,1243,'2012-07-26 16:04:03','Looks like yet another cache problem.',NULL,NULL),(45268,5839,129045,'2012-07-26 16:05:14','Showing up here, you sure it wasn\'t just xxx.freeimage.us having some hiccups?',NULL,NULL),(45269,5671,49532,'2012-07-26 16:05:27','I say keep it.  It will be be an incentive to include covers',NULL,NULL),(45270,5827,84499,'2012-07-26 16:05:38','\r\n\r\nno, what happens is tags are only deleted every 15 mins or so in the scheduler. But that action does not update the taglist (!)\r\n\r\nJust lazy programming by the gazelle team  :nasher: \r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45271,5827,84499,'2012-07-26 16:09:27','\r\n\r\nWould it be better if tags were deleted when they actually get voted down below 0? I think so... and I am much happier to make the adjustment to each torrents taglist at that point (looping through a bunch of torrents in the scheduler is a bad idea imo, and taglist has to be read adjusted and then set back you cannot make the needed change in sql)...\r\n\r\nit will be done!\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45272,5818,84499,'2012-07-26 16:15:50','\r\n\r\nare you talking about losing bounties on the test tracker??\r\n\r\nthe test tracker where all your stats will be wiped out when we go live?\r\n\r\n\r\nyou realise what happens on this tracker is irrelevant to your main site stats right?',NULL,NULL),(45274,5839,49532,'2012-07-26 16:25:00','No, if it were a xxx.freeimage.us problem, then my earlier post, on the same page, wouldn\'t have an avatar, but it does. \n\nNo matter how often I refresh the page, relaunch Firefox, flush the cache, it still doesn\'t have an avatar, neither does my [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2760&postid=25265#post25265]post[/url] this morning, in that thread.\n\n\nI just tested it in Safari, and the avatar is showing up there. Like I said, it\'s a really weird one.',49532,'2012-07-26 16:33:57'),(45275,5671,129045,'2012-07-26 16:26:14','[quote=apparition]I say keep it.  It will be be an incentive to include covers[/quote]\r\n[quote]Note: Do not add a thumbnail image as cover, rather leave this field blank if you don\'t have a good cover image or an image of the actor(s).[/quote]\r\n\r\nPlain text listed there is better than having a bad image that doesn\'t quite say anything about the upload.',NULL,NULL),(45276,5839,129045,'2012-07-26 16:31:57','Using Firefox, Chrome and Opera here, they will show fine. Well, no idea then :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(45277,5832,84499,'2012-07-26 16:32:39','\r\n\r\nthey are the same way they are on emp.me :dunno:',NULL,NULL),(45278,5834,84499,'2012-07-26 16:40:37','\nbah!\n\nI am about 99% sure I know why this is... and the upload will be fubar until its fixed.\n\n\n\n\r\n\r\nFIXED\r\n\r\n\r\nsorry bout that... that was a stupid one.',8