',NULL,NULL),(45345,5812,49532,'2012-07-27 07:49:46','Ok, so then what I hear you saying, is that it is more important to you, not to steal someones presentation, of stolen images and text, for a stolen video, than it is to make other relsolutions available for download.   \r\n\r\nI have no problem with that.  This is your house, we play by your rules :beer2: ',NULL,NULL),(45346,5833,171777,'2012-07-27 08:49:12','Already working on it as we speak.',NULL,NULL),(45347,5815,1507,'2012-07-27 10:58:09','[quote=mifune]I changed the forum link to the H&S forum.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]I just got another pm from the system saying my upload was auto-deleted, and the link to H&S still points to Bugs...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nSo, that link needs to be changed..  :smile1:\r\n\r\nIt didn\'t screw up with the urls this time so you did fix that bug...  :thumbsup:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-27 10:59:45'),(45348,5838,171777,'2012-07-27 12:04:07','[quote=mifune]changed but i am not positive i got them all.[/quote]\r\nIf I happen to find one I\'ll let you know.',NULL,NULL),(45349,5847,171777,'2012-07-27 12:07:48','Right now you get the following standard PM:\r\n\r\n[quote]Your upload Reporting test: bullshit torrent does not meet our standards for uploading and has been marked for deletion.\r\n\r\nIt will be automatically deleted if you do not fix your upload in the next 1 day  (Jul 28 2012, 11:53).\r\n\r\nReason:  Description does not match content of torrent.\r\n\r\nPlease make sure you read the Upload Rules\r\nYou will find useful guides in the Tutorials section\r\nIf you need further help please post in the Help & Support Forum[/quote]\r\n\r\nIt might be a good idea to add reminder that once you have fixed the torrent you also have to click the button in the torrent that says that you fixed it. Yes I know there is a button in the torrent but once you get the PM you usually assume that the message in the torrent is identical so you don\'t read it.',NULL,NULL),(45350,5848,171777,'2012-07-27 12:11:03','Right now the [code][code][/code][/code] tags do what you think they do: they write everything that was written inside appear literally as it was written. For inline typing as I am doing right now this is find but if you want to post a set of commands it is always nicer to have those commands boxed. Right now you can do this by abusing the quote functionality a bit e.g.:\r\n[quote][code]\r\n[b][/b]\r\n[i][/i]\r\n[u][/u]\r\n[/code][/quote]\r\nBut I am not sure that abusing other tags is the way to go for this. Perhaps a new BB button for code boxes?',NULL,NULL),(45352,5842,1507,'2012-07-27 13:23:51',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]I don\'t know why they cannot offer up credits, upload, slots, or whatever else they may have...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nSomething for further discussion maybe...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-27 13:24:13'),(45353,5838,1507,'2012-07-27 13:29:16',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]I don\'t get a 403 error...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nand I may be the most paranoid guy around...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-27 13:29:59'),(45354,5770,91522,'2012-07-27 15:37:35','I think a good search is the most important feature of a tracker.\nHere are my suggestions to further improve the situation:\n\n- [b]Phrased search[/b]\nSeems to work only in advanced mode.\nIs this intended?\n\n- Why is there a [b]basic mode[/b] anyway?\nI think it would be better to unite both modes\nand use the \'all\' and \'any\' radiobuttons as default values if there is no boolean operator present\nso for example\n\'-hello \"perv world\"\' with \'all\' selected would mean (NOT \'hello\') AND \'perv world\'\nThis way all users could use the same powerful search\n\n- [b]Search in title[/b] would be great\n\n- Description of advanced search could need a small explanation of the input boxes.\n\n- The terms \'search term\' and \'file list\' in advanced search is confusing,\nbecause you also put search terms into the file list box.\nso the heading should be search terms and then the name of the boxes\n\'description\', \'file list\' and \'tags\'',91522,'2012-07-27 15:52:53'),(45355,5838,184595,'2012-07-27 15:49:38','as staff you automatically override anyones paranoia settings...',NULL,NULL),(45356,5763,70679,'2012-07-27 18:02:59','[size=3][b][color=#FF0000]Already in Help - Delete after double check[/color][/b][/size]\n\n\nFirst thanks to MrRandom for this great thread. I have been asked to mention mIRC as a client so here it is\n\nWork in Progress <- will edit this out once is more or less in good shape.\n\n[b][size=2]mIRC[/size][/b]\n\nmIRC is a fully fledged mature IRC client with tons of features. Worth mentioning is logging and scripting ability.\n\n[b][color=#FF0000]Is Windows only and is not for free[/color][/b]\n[b][size=2]\nGetting mIRC.[/size][/b] \n\nyou can use it for 30 days to see how you like it after that you need to register it and it is $20. Or.... well you know how to use torrents  :wink: \n\nyou can get mIRC here : [url=http://www.mirc.com/get.html]Download mIRC[/url]\n\nAfter that read the guide (no point in duplicating it, is good) : [url=http://www.mirc.com/install.html]Link to first use guide[/url]\n\nthen use the commands shown in the other guides to connect to to our IRC channel.\n\nI will post more info later but this should help you going and feel free to explore this client and try things and also has a pretty good help feature.\n\nHere is a screen shot of my (heavily customized) mIRC connected to our channels:\n\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-2BEB_5012C0D9.jpg[/img]\n\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=2BEB_5012C0D9]Link to bigger image[/url]',70679,'2012-09-10 19:46:15'),(45357,5829,48010,'2012-07-27 19:09:58','confirmed in FF 13.0.1\n\nit\'s a litte confusing but you could look at the browse bar but deep in the list some maths would be needed\n\nA simple colour showing the current would be good',48010,'2012-07-27 19:12:14'),(45358,5831,48010,'2012-07-27 19:16:08','[quote=apparition]I share this account with my 2 lovers, but it would be nice if we could have our  own identities for posting in the forums and making comments.  I\'m sure there are others in this same situation.\n\n[b]Also, it would be great for Staff members to have one identity, to post there personal thoughts as a user, and another to post in there roll as staff (e.g. Clownius, LordClownius).[/b]\n\nThe easiest way I can think of it to have username aliases: In the profile there would be input fields for adding aliases, then on forum and comment add/edit forms, there would be a pulldown menu to select which Alias it will be posted as.\n\nThis should be on both add and edit forms, because it\'s easy to forget to select one.[/quote]\n\nI have no need for that :wink:',48010,'2012-07-27 19:16:32'),(45359,5815,84499,'2012-07-27 19:24:30','\r\nI missed one (I had fixed it in the first pm you get sent).\r\n\r\nfixed now.',NULL,NULL),(45360,5846,48010,'2012-07-27 19:38:00','another who didn\'t read the PM invite to the test site :grin:',NULL,NULL),(45361,5798,48010,'2012-07-27 19:46:33','[quote=apparition][quote=Clownius]Oh i beg of you please ban IE .....  I swear you spend half your bug squashing time on bugs that only affect IE...[/quote]\r\n+1 for banning IE.\r\n\r\nBut in the other hand, IE is only on MS Windows. People with real operating systems don\'t need to worry. :smartass:[/quote]\r\nCan\'t they use FF or Chrome or another browser - it\'s really not difficult but for some it might be',NULL,NULL),(45362,5671,48010,'2012-07-27 19:49:11','[quote=yamchan07bb][quote=apparition]I say keep it.  It will be be an incentive to include covers[/quote]\r\n[quote]Note: Do not add a thumbnail image as cover, rather leave this field blank if you don\'t have a good cover image or an image of the actor(s).[/quote]\r\n\r\nPlain text listed there is better than having a bad image that doesn\'t quite say anything about the upload.[/quote]\r\nnot all uploads will have a cover too - eg praysite webrip or webcam',NULL,NULL),(45363,5849,48010,'2012-07-27 20:12:40','Sorry but 2 problems in one :grin:\n\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=9F1D_5012D96B][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=9F1D_5012D96B[/img][/url]\n\nFirst see the irrelevant tags like is this the with  etc.\n\nSecond I did not report this - I looked at the report of both as dupes and it added \"Dave reported..\" I diddn\'t (maybe this should be in staff too ?)',48010,'2012-07-27 20:13:03'),(45364,5850,71859,'2012-07-27 20:33:55','Sorry if this has been posted before but the old empornium allowed you to have a password under 6 characters so for example mine was 5 so I tried logging in to the new test empornium site just now and it wouldn\'t work...tried 100 times kept getting error. So I had to reset pass to get over it. \r\n\r\nThe new emp test site you need at least 6 characters for your pass to login.\r\nOld emp you could have less than 6 characters for your pass to login.\r\n\r\nDon\'t know how to fix this but just wanted to give heads up.',NULL,NULL),(45365,5679,71859,'2012-07-27 20:40:07','I can haz creditz to play around with ? \r\n\r\nEdit: Thanks for the 200k...sadly I can\'t buy the one I wanted...awesome mutha :)\r\nWould be sweet if it was named \'\'BAD MUTHAF\'\' lol pulp fiction style.',71859,'2012-07-27 21:13:41'),(45366,5851,71859,'2012-07-27 20:45:27','Hi guys, I don\'t know if this is the place or time for this but...is it possible to have an alternative skin ? I\'d love to create 1 or more if possible and it\'s not that much trouble for you guys. I was thinking about an erotic silver dark - shiny black or a blue one like the main bar color expect expand it to cover the entire site background. The current one is nice but I surf on this site a lot late when it\'s dark and the color of the current background - white - is painful to my eyes after a while and especially in the dark.\r\n\r\nOh and I\'d like to offer my services with photoshop if needed. I think i\'m capable of doing some decent stuff and I\'d love to help out in any shape or form. ',NULL,NULL),(45367,5806,84499,'2012-07-27 20:45:58','\r\n[quote=DrkNess][img=http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=A11C_500F8BBD]\r\n\r\nAs the image shows there is an image in the torrent description and it still counts it as a bug. True the use of the BB code tag is different but it still is a valid BB tag. To test that this is actually a valid BB tag i posted the above image using an identical type of link.\r\n\r\nIn the above torrent description if I click preview the tag IS correctly implemented and the preview shows an image on the correct location.\r\n\r\nNoticed this in the latest Google Chrome for windows[/quote]\r\n\r\nfixed :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(45368,5851,84499,'2012-07-27 20:54:53','\r\nyou can make an external css stylesheet and use that (also there is already an alternative stylesheet - look under settings).\r\n\r\nsee these threads:\r\n[url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2649][/url]\r\n[url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2794][/url]\r\n\r\nI am prepared to make good ones into official stylesheets, but it will probably have to wait until after we go live.',NULL,NULL),(45369,5635,71859,'2012-07-27 21:01:14','Seeding 60 torrents make little sense because everyone just downloads and seeds torrents that have no seeders. Pointless.\r\nIt\'s like you get credits for doing nothing essentially. If only the leechers were substantially larger so max seeding would be achieved much easier. I think the credits should be doubled imo...the more credits people have the more they\'ll share and it come around full circle creating a better balance.\r\n\r\nAn option to donate credits to uploaders would be nice. Basically a thank you in credits.\r\nOr/And an extra 1000 or such for sharing a torrent with certain rules like the more seeders the more credits and encourage seeding and also add some rules to encourage people don\'t share awful ones just to collect credits.',NULL,NULL),(45370,5635,1243,'2012-07-27 22:36:32','[quote=onigami][quote=mifune]well it is actually beyond my resources to add user based FL (the backend that would provide 24hr FL or PFL)... the tracker code is written in c++ and while I could brush up on my c++ that would take time (of my limited spare time) and thats time not working on bugs, and its time I havent really got to spare (LOL). Also I hate c++. I would guess Lanz has even less time available unfortunately.[/quote]\r\n\r\nSo, wait, what\'s the original tracker\'s code?  This is more a curiosity than anything else.[/quote]\r\n\r\nOriginal tracker can use both the old php style announcer, xbt or ocelot. xbt and ocelot is written in c++. We use ocelot here.\r\n\r\nI\'ve added 24 hour freeleech to the tracker now.',NULL,NULL),(45371,5635,1243,'2012-07-27 22:41:10','[quote=Typhoon20]Seeding 60 torrents make little sense because everyone just downloads and seeds torrents that have no seeders. Pointless.\nIt\'s like you get credits for doing nothing essentially. If only the leechers were substantially larger so max seeding would be achieved much easier. I think the credits should be doubled imo...the more credits people have the more they\'ll share and it come around full circle creating a better balance.\n\nAn option to donate credits to uploaders would be nice. Basically a thank you in credits.\nOr/And an extra 1000 or such for sharing a torrent with certain rules like the more seeders the more credits and encourage seeding and also add some rules to encourage people don\'t share awful ones just to collect credits.[/quote]\n\nThey keep the torrents alive and earn some credits for it which is great for people with bad upload speed, that\'s far from pointless IMO.\n',1243,'2012-07-27 22:45:34'),(45372,5850,1243,'2012-07-27 22:54:40','I\'ve changed it so you can login using 5 characters, that might help with some of the problems people have been having using their old passwords.',NULL,NULL),(45373,5802,1243,'2012-07-27 23:13:27','[quote=mifune]I dunno, it dosent do anything malicious afaik - just looks fucked up. And if someone wants to use it in their sig or something I dont see the particular harm... if someone abuses it we could deal with it on a case by case basis. \r\n\r\n\r\nIf we want to prevent it automagically I guess we could remove any text not in the \'standard\' unicode range  :hmmm:[/quote]\r\n\r\nYeah I looked in to it, and the solution is more invasive than the zalgo text so not worth it imo.',NULL,NULL),(45374,5847,84499,'2012-07-27 23:31:07','\r\nI added a line telling them to click on the green button at the top of the torrent page.',NULL,NULL),(45375,5848,84499,'2012-07-27 23:32:51','\r\n[codeblock][codeblock][b]your text here[/b][/codeblock][/codeblock]',NULL,NULL),(45376,5768,129045,'2012-07-28 00:37:01','[b]Note to self:[/b] Do not compliment mifune hardwork ever again. :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(45377,5829,129045,'2012-07-28 00:46:32','Seems to affect only the Light stylesheet (so it doesn\'t matter the browser), the Empornium stylesheet on the other hand will actually show the actual page of results as black and other links as blue.',NULL,NULL),(45378,5671,129045,'2012-07-28 01:00:11','Ok, now torrents without covers appear under \"[b]Recent Uploads[/b]\", but since it appears as the [b]ALT attribute[/b] inside a broken\\inexistent [b]IMG[/b] with a set width, it may need some tweaks (or somehow mimic the same behavior from [b]Collages[/b] http://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php?id=3 )\n\nSee my profile for example: http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=129045\n\nDifferent browsers will handle the [b]IMG ALT[/b] attribute differently:\n\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=6870_50132B2A[/img]\n\n- [b]Opera[/b] will display the text obeying the set width (truncating)\n- [b]Chrome[/b] and [b]IE[/b] will have a similar behavior, both will obey the set width, but will not display any text: http://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=16734\n- [b]Firefox[/b] will display the text in full, ignoring the set width',129045,'2012-07-28 02:02:08'),(45379,5830,84499,'2012-07-28 02:12:02','\r\n\r\nimplemented :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(45380,5852,49532,'2012-07-28 02:29:48','We have been using the emporium stylesheet, after logging off and loging back on, the stylesheet reverted to light.\r\n\r\nthis happened only once and I could not replicate it by logging off and logng back on\r\n\r\n[Just my opinion: the emporium stylsheet should be the default]',NULL,NULL),(45381,5830,49532,'2012-07-28 02:39:33','Ok, small correction needed:\n\nWhen removing a down vote, by clicking up, it says [b]removing up vote[/b]. It should say [b] removing down vote[/b] \n\nWhen removing an up vote by, clicking down, it says[b] removing down vote[/b]. It  should say [b] removing up vote[/b] ',49532,'2012-07-28 02:41:14'),(45382,5853,49532,'2012-07-28 03:45:01','A lot of things rarely get tagged, that I think are important.  I would like to see the folowing on the upload form:\r\n\r\n[quote]Whenever possible, please tag the following:\r\n[*]the year(s) of release (eg. 2009, 2007-2011)\r\n[*]production company or website: (e.g. ftvgirls.com, vivid.video,)\r\n[*]names for all known performers. (e.g. brea.bennett, jenna.haze, sensi.pearl)\r\n[*]language (eg. english, portugese, german)\r\n[*]video codecs (eg. wmv, xvid, mp4)\r\n[*]Audio codec (eg. mp3,aac,wma)\r\n[*]video resolutions (eg. 480p, 720p, 1080i)\r\n[*]source type (e.g. site.rip, dvd,vhs, web.clip) [/quote]',NULL,NULL),(45383,5747,84845,'2012-07-28 04:59:49','Yamchan, \r\n\r\nYou are right.  I didn\'t realize I had typed in \"puke AND big.tits\" [i][u]before[/u][/i] hitting the \"Make Default\" button.  I just tested further and it\'s working fine (I [u]removed[/u] \"puke AND big.tits\", selected Make Default and navigated to other pages, came back and \"puke and Big.tits\" did [b]not[/b] appear by default).  \r\n\r\nWorking as designed.  Bug can be closed.  Thanks!\r\n\r\nMicrofine',NULL,NULL),(45384,5854,1243,'2012-07-28 07:20:45','Hey all, I implemented 24 hour leech yesterday since that was wanted by a lot of people. It needs to be tested though. Please buy a 24 hour leech in the bonus shop and download some things that isn\'t freeleech already and keep track of your download stats. So far only the most basic functions for it is implemented so input is appreciated.  :smile1: ',NULL,NULL),(45386,5848,171777,'2012-07-28 10:48:36','ah ok so it is accepted by the site but just not present in the button list. never mind then.',NULL,NULL),(45387,5849,171777,'2012-07-28 10:56:09','Well the question is whether or not staff would mark a torrent for deletion in 24 hours or just down right delete it if the reason is something that is downright against the rules and not fixable.\r\n\r\nareyou as a mod not able to delete the irrelevant tags?',NULL,NULL),(45389,5854,171777,'2012-07-28 12:25:26','for testing purposes you might want to make it a bit cheaper. It is either that or people need to be given a lot more credits just to test the functionality.',NULL,NULL),(45390,5679,171777,'2012-07-28 12:26:32','could I have some test credits? Been saving up a lot on the old site but only a small part was transferred to the test site :P',NULL,NULL),(45391,5856,171777,'2012-07-28 12:30:06','[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=3405_5013BF45][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=3405_5013BF45&jpg[/img][/url]\r\nAs you can see the form still says you are entering a value in MB even though I selected GB.\r\n\r\nAlso how hard is it to add TB in the dropdown? Not that I see that part used too often but you never know.',NULL,NULL),(45393,5679,47234,'2012-07-28 14:07:33','Just threw a shitload your way DrkNess',NULL,NULL),(45394,5854,47234,'2012-07-28 14:08:09','Credits are being given out like Candy if people ask :)\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45395,5854,1243,'2012-07-28 14:23:35','I gave everyone 10,000 slots and 5 million credits, that should take care of that! :laugh:\n',1243,'2012-07-28 14:26:32'),(45396,5679,1243,'2012-07-28 14:25:32','I just flooded the server with credits and slots so I think this thread just became pointless...  :worm:  :wink: ',NULL,NULL),(45398,5679,171777,'2012-07-28 15:12:00','well then either you 2 managed to cancel each other out or there is a max of 5 million credits that people can have at any given time.',NULL,NULL),(45399,5854,171777,'2012-07-28 15:13:36','Freeleech is not working. I can click the link but I am not getting the freeleech. Also no credits are substracted.',NULL,NULL),(45400,5857,171777,'2012-07-28 15:15:39','Would it be an idea to send a reminder PM once a torrent is 6 hours or so away from deletion?',NULL,NULL),(45401,5854,129045,'2012-07-28 15:39:29','[quote=DrkNess][color=#FF0000]1 - Freeleech is not working. I can click the link but I am not getting the freeleech.[/color] [color=#FF0000]2 - Also no credits are subtracted.[/color][/quote]\r\n\r\n1 - Similar? http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2658\r\n\r\n2- Buying something in the Bonus Shop isn\'t subtracting for you?\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b] Started a test here, simple FL slot, but since stats are updated hourly now, it\'ll probably take a while to confirm. Buying something from the Bonus shop here subtracted the credits normally (old bug thread here: http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2647 ) unless you mean something else.',129045,'2012-07-28 15:45:43'),(45402,5854,171777,'2012-07-28 15:45:23','[quote=yamchan07bb][quote=DrkNess][color=#FF0000]1 - Freeleech is not working. I can click the link but I am not getting the freeleech.[/color] [color=#FF0000]2 - Also no credits are substracted.[/color][/quote]\r\n\r\n1 - Similar? http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2658\r\n\r\n2- Buying something in the Bonus Shop isn\'t subtracting for you?[/quote]\r\nno other things are sub