nd download and getting that \"unregistered torrent\" error...??\r\n\r\nSomething to do with rTorrent not being able to identify the .torrent file corrctly...???  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nOr am I confused again...???  :dunno:\r\n\r\nhttp://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=903\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-28 20:33:35'),(45440,5805,48010,'2012-07-28 20:33:39','[quote=Lanz]Added filter for freeleech.[/quote]\n\nworks for me - i see 5 FL torrents on a blank search just by checking the \"Filter freeleech torrents\" option (hope that is right)',48010,'2012-07-28 20:37:23'),(45441,5805,129045,'2012-07-28 20:40:24','Yep, that\'s what I get also.\r\n\r\n3 were set manually, while the top 2 are tests to see the System setting them as FL automatically.\r\n\r\nAccording to this thread http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2615 , things should normalize on the definitive move, all FL torrents will appear as intended :)',NULL,NULL),(45442,5858,129045,'2012-07-28 20:42:35','You may be on to something there, it\'s not the first time I hear utorrent creating some broken ass torrent files.\r\n\r\nReading his description, seems like he pulled the torrent file from a public tracker, so who knows the state of it (or he means only the video...?)',NULL,NULL),(45443,5849,48010,'2012-07-28 20:46:52','[quote=mifune][quote=Dave][quote=mifune]\r\n1) bad tags. what do you expect to happen?\r\n\r\n2) I cannot reproduce this. What exactly did you click/page did you go to? What actions precisely need to be taken to reproduce it?[/quote]\r\n\r\n1) yes it\'s a test so ok\r\n\r\n2) this is weird - the \"Dave reported it\" is not now showing in the torrent - as far as i recall i just clicked on the torrent and it appeared \"i reported it\" so i took the screenshot. Not much help but\'s all i remember doing[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nI still dont know what you expect to happen about those tags... there is no mechanism to stop users adding stupid stuff like \'and\' \'this\' - do you expect there to be? maybe there should be... but Im not sure what you are driving at?\r\n\r\nAs it is users can vote those tags down and they will be removed when there score is < 1. Or staff can delete them.[/quote]\r\n\r\nno prob with the tags - i\'m not driving at something but maybe a block list may be useful if possible and also for banned tags (see staff forum on emp.me)\r\n\r\nthe real worry was that fake \"dave reported it\" which has gone now and can\'t be replicated - a glitch? anyway forget that for now - if happens again i\'ll add another screenshot',NULL,NULL),(45444,5859,48010,'2012-07-28 20:51:50','[quote=yamchan07bb]See here: http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2658\r\n\r\nCache issue, give it some time and the buttons will disappear from the Torrent page (e.g. if you used both FL and DS, both will be gone), the Torrent list will also display the correct information (Personal Freeleech \\ Doubleseed) besides the torrent title.[/quote]\r\n\r\nok i\'ll wait and see - but if you are stupid and forgot you added FL or DS or had to go and make a coffee or something it will take the slots away - anyway i lost the slot (no big deal on the test site but will be when we go live) so i\'m waiting to see if the slot will be returned when the cache updates',NULL,NULL),(45445,5859,129045,'2012-07-28 20:56:36','The Slot will not be returned.\r\n\r\nWhat I was referring to is that the correct behavior will only kick in after some time (the buttons should disappear instantly after use, but due to the cache issue they stay there causing this problem)',NULL,NULL),(45446,5859,1243,'2012-07-28 20:59:47','There are several problems with the slot code, it needs to be rewritten in some parts. I\'ll look into it as soon as I have some free time for it.',NULL,NULL),(45447,5859,48010,'2012-07-28 20:59:57','[quote=yamchan07bb]The Slot will not be returned.\r\n\r\nWhat I was referring to is that the correct behavior will only kick in after some time (the buttons should disappear instantly after use, but due to the cache issue they stay there causing this problem)[/quote]\r\n\r\nThis needs to be made more clear when they buy the slots - something like \"wait a while for it to take effect and update your slots\"\r\n\r\nI\'ll work out the words later or someone else will',NULL,NULL),(45448,5854,1243,'2012-07-28 21:03:45','[quote=usillyboy]:thumbsup:\r\n\r\n[b]Welcum back 24hr FL slot...  :thumbsup:\r\n\r\nNow if we can only get that 1 Week FL slot put into place....  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:[/quote]\r\n\r\nBuy 24 hour several times, they are cumulative. I will probably add mod tools for it too so you can abuse the pfl to the max :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(45449,5859,1243,'2012-07-28 21:07:36','That\'s one of the things that needs to be looked over. If it worked as it should, the button would be removed directly after you selected freeleech or double seed.',NULL,NULL),(45450,5777,1243,'2012-07-28 21:58:19','it would probably be better to just make it as a list and use an image popup like on the browse page.',NULL,NULL),(45451,5775,85111,'2012-07-28 23:18:06','has this been implemented yet?  or is it forgotten? lol',NULL,NULL),(45452,5758,85111,'2012-07-28 23:20:22','yeh erm.. this should be implemented if it hasn\'t been already.. wonder if admins noticed haha',NULL,NULL),(45453,5854,1507,'2012-07-28 23:27:45','[quote=Lanz][quote=usillyboy]:thumbsup:\r\n\r\n[b]Welcum back 24hr FL slot...  :thumbsup:\r\n\r\nNow if we can only get that 1 Week FL slot put into place....  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:[/quote]\r\n\r\nBuy 24 hour several times, they are cumulative. I will probably add mod tools for it too so you can abuse the pfl to the max :laugh:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]Thank you...  :smile1:\r\n\r\nI was thinking that I would like to be able to give away a week of Free Leech to members for contests and such for instance...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45454,5858,171777,'2012-07-28 23:34:44','[quote=yamchan07bb]You may be on to something there, it\'s not the first time I hear utorrent creating some broken ass torrent files.\r\n\r\nReading his description, seems like he pulled the torrent file from a public tracker, so who knows the state of it (or he means only the video...?)[/quote]\r\nIt is also not the first time I am having this (also noticed it on the old tracker a few times but didn\'t really think anything of it). \r\n\r\nIs this problem uTorrent based or rTorrent? (ergo can I fix it by updating myself or am I dependant on other people)?',NULL,NULL),(45455,5805,1507,'2012-07-28 23:36:02',':dunno:\r\n\r\n[b]Free Leech category, stick them all into that category, check mark in FL category for search, submit and all of the Free Leech torrents should appear..  :dunno:\r\n\r\nYou can use tags, key words then to narrow your search of the Free Leech torrents from there I think...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nI may be talking out of my ass tho\'...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45456,5858,1507,'2012-07-28 23:39:10',':dunno:\r\n\r\n[b]I thought this was a problem with the updated uTorrent 3.(whatever) crap, and that they finally fixed it with the later updates, but the .torrents made with that borked version of uT are all screwy...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45457,5853,1507,'2012-07-28 23:42:19',' :sigh: ',NULL,NULL),(45458,5858,171777,'2012-07-28 23:42:54','[quote=usillyboy]:dunno:\n\n[b]I thought this was a problem with the updated uTorrent 3.(whatever) crap, and that they finally fixed it with the later updates, but the .torrents made with that borked version of uT are all screwy...  :dunno:\n\nusb[/b]\n\n:usb:[/quote]\n\naccording to that topic you linked it is fixable by using the \"watch\" folder from rtorrent. Gonna test that now. Will update in a bit.\n\nedit: succesfully downloading with the \"watch folder\" work around.\n\nErgo the problem is not tracker based. Case closed I suppose.',171777,'2012-07-28 23:44:59'),(45459,5858,1507,'2012-07-28 23:49:06',':thumbsup:\r\n\r\n[b]Good to hear that it was the uTorrent 3.(whatever) buggy thingy...  :thumbsup:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45460,5853,85636,'2012-07-28 23:49:16','Stuff like that should either be in the title or in the description. Tags are for finding what is in the content NOT when it was made, the source of the copy, etc. Thats my 2 cents',NULL,NULL),(45461,5805,84499,'2012-07-28 23:49:20','[quote=usillyboy]:dunno:\r\n\r\n[b]Free Leech category, stick them all into that category, check mark in FL category for search, submit and all of the Free Leech torrents should appear..  :dunno:\r\n\r\nYou can use tags, key words then to narrow your search of the Free Leech torrents from there I think...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nI may be talking out of my ass tho\'...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:[/quote]\r\n\r\nLanz has already added an option on the search to filter freeleech torrents...what more need is there?\r\n\r\nAlso categories already serve a purpose and are differentiated by the type of content, FL really dosent fit into what categories represent.',NULL,NULL),(45462,5854,84499,'2012-07-28 23:53:42','\r\n\r\nisnt a week of FL a bit much? :sigh: :lol:',NULL,NULL),(45463,5853,171777,'2012-07-28 23:53:52','[quote=MrRandom]Stuff like that should either be in the title or in the description. Tags are for finding what is in the content NOT when it was made, the source of the copy, etc. Thats my 2 cents[/quote]\r\n+1',NULL,NULL),(45464,5854,171777,'2012-07-28 23:55:08','[quote=mifune]isnt a week of FL a bit much? :sigh: :lol:[/quote]\r\n\r\nlet\'s wait until we hear about the first \"death due to too much porn\" before we call it too much :P',NULL,NULL),(45465,5758,86439,'2012-07-28 23:59:25','They probably have noticed it, will get to it eventually, there are likely more pressing issues to focus on until then. No-one here has a bad ratio, or at least a need to. You have credits coming out the waazoo.',NULL,NULL),(45466,5805,1507,'2012-07-29 00:00:13','[quote=mifune][quote=usillyboy]:dunno:\r\n\r\n[b]Free Leech category, stick them all into that category, check mark in FL category for search, submit and all of the Free Leech torrents should appear..  :dunno:\r\n\r\nYou can use tags, key words then to narrow your search of the Free Leech torrents from there I think...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nI may be talking out of my ass tho\'...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:[/quote]\r\n\r\nLanz has already added an option on the search to filter freeleech torrents...what more need is there?\r\n\r\nAlso categories already serve a purpose and are differentiated by the type of content, FL really dosent fit into what categories represent.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:slap:\r\n\r\n[b]It might help if I fucking read before I respond...  :slap:\r\n\r\nMy bad...   :slap: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45467,5858,129045,'2012-07-29 00:05:46','[quote=DrkNess]\r\nIt is also not the first time I am having this (also noticed it on the old tracker a few times but didn\'t really think anything of it). \r\n\r\nIs this problem uTorrent based or rTorrent? (ergo can I fix it by updating myself or am I dependant on other people)?[/quote]\r\n\r\nhttp://code.google.com/p/rutorrent/issues/detail?id=710\r\n\r\nReading there and this thread on EMP http://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=600&page=p4102#4102, saying to move the torrent file to the \"[b]Watch[/b]\" folder and it would be added without problems.\r\n\r\nIt also says it was fixed on rutorrent version 3.4\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b] lol was digging the other thread. Glad you sorted it out.',129045,'2012-07-29 00:07:33'),(45468,5860,94952,'2012-07-29 00:06:08','Since I got a crapton of bonus points I wanted to give some away but I didn\'t know any names. So I thought \"Aww.. Screw it!\" \r\n\r\nBut then I got to browsing the forum and clicked around on some profiles and thought I want to donate to this guy. And that was kinda annoying. \r\n\r\nSo my suggestion: Give away buttons on profiles. And better feed back that someone got the gift now it only shows that I lost some points, if I look for it.\r\n\r\n//Mobbo',NULL,NULL),(45469,5671,171777,'2012-07-29 00:06:57','Still not working correctly for me. I am using the blue theme and this is what my recent uploads looks like (according to Yam this is standard behaviour for chrome though):\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=FDA2_5014621C][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=FDA2_5014621C&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nAs a suggestion. Right now if you look in the overview for torrents that have no image you see the following:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=8E27_50146225][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=8E27_50146225&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nQuestion is: How hard is it to add that \"no image available\" thing as a standard cover when nothing is provided. Thiw way all torrents basically have a cover and no problems arise on the site because of the lack of covers.',NULL,NULL),(45470,5854,1507,'2012-07-29 00:08:57','[quote=mifune]isnt a week of FL a bit much? :sigh: :lol:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:laugh: :laugh: :laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]Not really...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nWill get them to pop into the forums and participate...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(45471,5671,129045,'2012-07-29 00:30:23','Having 4 \"NO IMAGE AVAILABLE\" side by side doesn\'t seem much better.\r\n\r\n\r\nReading Lanz comment here http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2777&postid=25450#post25450\r\n[quote=Lanz]it would probably be better to just make it as a list and use an image popup like on the browse page.[/quote]\r\nHaving a short list instead would solve this problem too. All the necessary info available and if the user was interested, he could hover to get that popup.\r\n\r\n:hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(45472,5818,94952,'2012-07-29 00:37:22','I found the wording(or math) to be confusing. I wanted to add a 10 GB bounty and understood it as I would lose 10 GB when/if the request was filled instead the I lost 10 GB immediately  and the bounty was set at 9 GB. Afterwards I understood the thinking but it wasn\'t very clear before I set up my req and \"lost\" my 10 GB.\r\n\r\nI feel this should be addressed before live. I sense a lot of drama over this.  :banghead: ',NULL,NULL),(45473,5671,84499,'2012-07-29 01:11:55','\r\nI will fix the text issue. ',NULL,NULL),(45474,5853,47234,'2012-07-29 01:27:13','Only if the uploader has a button next to them where they can choose that says \"like i give a crap\" so we dont create too much work for them :P',NULL,NULL),(45475,5853,84499,'2012-07-29 01:41:28','I dont think we want to be too proscriptive about what tags [i]should[/i] be added by the uploader. And of that list only porn star names , and to a lesser extent the first two types are what I would call \'really useful\' tags, but thats just my opinion. \n\nThe beauty of the tag system is that you can always add whatever tags you think are appropriate and if the swarm agree they will vote them up... its survival of the fittest, time will tell what the good tags are.',84499,'2012-07-29 01:41:43'),(45480,5754,1507,'2012-07-29 04:59:42',':dunno:\r\n\r\n[b]I\'ve checked everything in my paranoia level...  Can [i]they[/i]  :cool: still see me.....???  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-29 05:00:06'),(45481,5754,67255,'2012-07-29 05:15:08','If a user like the perceived anonymity that that \"paranoia\' level get them, and this make them want to upload more, the better. \r\nYou can still look for torrents you like trough search\r\nThe benefit of the doubt should be to the uploader.',NULL,NULL),(45484,5754,84499,'2012-07-29 05:44:47','\r\n[quote=l3af]Regarding the paranoia lvl, I have to ask if a user can hide it\'s uploaded torrents? For me it\'s kind of important to see uploads from specific users. I think it should be viewable by default and impossible to hide.\r\n\r\nps: someone can check if he can see what torrents i have upped, thx.[/quote]\r\n\r\nIf an uploader wants to not have stuff listed under their profile thats up to them I think, we dont have anonymous uploading so the benefit is debateable but if they want to hide it they can. They will lose some hits but most hits are through the browse and search anyway. And I suspect the vast majority of uploaders want their uploads to be as visible as possible.\r\n\r\n...its slightly off topic but we should probably have a guide to the paranoia settings in the help section explaining exactly what they do and dont hide :hmmm: Not that its particularly hard to understand but its good to spell stuff out. \r\n',NULL,NULL),(45485,5648,1243,'2012-07-29 06:56:14','It should be set to 20BG already.',NULL,NULL),(45486,5805,1243,'2012-07-29 07:05:08',' :goldstars: :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(45487,5754,1243,'2012-07-29 07:12:31','[quote=mifune][quote=l3af]Regarding the paranoia lvl, I have to ask if a user can hide it\'s uploaded torrents? For me it\'s kind of important to see uploads from specific users. I think it should be viewable by default and impossible to hide.\r\n\r\nps: someone can check if he can see what torrents i have upped, thx.[/quote]\r\n\r\nIf an uploader wants to not have stuff listed under their profile thats up to them I think, we dont have anonymous uploading so the benefit is debateable but if they want to hide it they can. They will lose some hits but most hits are through the browse and search anyway. And I suspect the vast majority of uploaders want their uploads to be as visible as possible.\r\n\r\n...its slightly off topic but we should probably have a guide to the paranoia settings in the help section explaining exactly what they do and dont hide :hmmm: Not that its particularly hard to understand but its good to spell stuff out.[/quote]\r\n\r\nPerhaps we should have anonymous uploads using a checkbox on the upload page. :hmmm: ',NULL,NULL),(45488,5754,84499,'2012-07-29 07:38:05','\r\n\r\nI am not sure how I feel about it, it\'s like I shouldnt object in principle but I worry it could change the culture of emp in a bad way maybe... I am probably prejudiced by it being used on some really crappy sites but I dont have a good opinion of anonymous uploading.\r\n\r\nA more practical issue is it has a lot of ramifications in the code... I dont relish the idea of tracking down all the unforseen ways in which you can associate a user with an upload  :sorry: ',NULL,NULL),(45490,5648,86439,'2012-07-29 08:40:18','[quote=Lanz]It should be set to 20BG already.[/quote]\nBigger Gytes? :D  :smartass: \n\n\nOh fine, Im going ...Im going.',86439,'2012-07-29 08:40:49'),(45493,5648,1243,'2012-07-29 08:48:40','[quote=knickers][quote=Lanz]It should be set to 20BG already.[/quote]\r\nBigger Gytes? :D  :smartass: \r\n\r\n\r\nOh fine, Im going ...Im going.[/quote]\r\n:laugh: oops',NULL,NULL),(45494,5859,49532,'2012-07-29 09:11:28','One thing some people do is click on a button/link again if their browser is slow to respond.  I tested double clicking, and 2 slots were used.  it would be nice to prevent this as well',NULL,NULL),(45495,5754,1507,'2012-07-29 09:15:51',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]If you decide to do it, maybe make it for certain classes and allow staff to be able to see who it actually is...  gives everyone another reason to reach that promotion....  :dunno:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:dunno:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45496,5805,1507,'2012-07-29 09:19:13',':laugh:\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45497,5853,49532,'2012-07-29 09:31:05','[quote=MrRandom]Stuff like that should either be in the title or in the description. Tags are for finding what is in the content NOT when it was made, the source of the copy, etc. Thats my 2 cents[/quote]\r\n\r\nthese are for finding the content.  for example if you are looking for videos of brea bennett when she was 18 searching for [b]brea.bennett[/b] [b]2006[/b] would be very  usefull if the videos had a date tag.  \r\n\r\nIf, like me, you care more about the dialog, than what positions they fuck in, the [b]english[/b] tag is far much more usefull than the cowgirl tag.\r\n\r\nIf something has the tags [b]russian teen[/b] I know not to download it, because there is a good changce, that there is an underage girl, or one who was coorced into doing porn. \r\n\r\nWithout those tags I end up download shit that I don\'t want, and even shit I\'ll delete the moment I discover it, no matter whether it fucks my ratio, or even gets me banned',NULL,NULL),(45498,5860,49532,'2012-07-29 09:52:12','I\'m not sure if you mean buttons on the giver\'s profile, or the reciever\'s profile?\r\n\r\nI\'d make it work like this:\r\nEveryone would have options in their settings to put [b]give donation[/b] button on their profile and/or an [b]ask for donation[/b] button on their profile.\r\n\r\nif someone clicks the [b]give donation[/b] button, a dialog would pop up and ask for the amount, which would be transfered, when they click [b]ok[/b].\r\n\r\nif someone clicks the [b]ask for donation[/b] button, a dialog would pop up and ask for the amount, which would send a request message, when they click [b]ok[/b].\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45499,5857,49532,'2012-07-29 09:54:49','I got one, with an 8 hour reminder.',NULL,NULL),(45501,5648,47234,'2012-07-29 10:01:38','Whos got a 20.1-49.9GB torrent to upload and test with?',NULL,NULL),(45502,5861,49532,'2012-07-29 10:04:57','to me it seems like there needs to be more activity in the beta test (am I wrong?)\r\n\r\nIf the beta test was opened to evrybody:\r\n1. the staff wouln\'t have to tsake the time to ivite people. \r\n2. there would be a chance that there would be more torrents uploaded.\r\n3. when it goes live, and people start complaining about it not being like the old site. They could be told, that they had the opportunity to give input, and since they didn\'t, they have nothing to complain about.',NULL,NULL),(45503,5861,86439,'2012-07-29 10:21:06','Well, if that were true, might as well just go live as is and fix it on the run I would have thought. More activity at times might be good, but theres likely such a thing as too much activity.\n\nWell over 200 people have been invited, most aint doing shit. While a dedicated few (I dont include myself in that) appear to be putting a lot of time into it.\n\nI cant imagine being swamped with hundreds of threads stating the stats arent up to date is going to be helpful. Exaggeration? Maybe.',86439,'2012-07-29 10:22:31'),(45504,5861,47234,'2012-07-29 11:01:03','Actually the invites are over 300 at the moment.\r\n\r\nFor now i havent invited more for two reasons\r\n\r\nOne the bugs are still coming thick and fast\r\n\r\nTwo its a PITA to invite more :lol:\r\n\r\nWhen the bugs start to slow down a bit i will likely send out a few more invites (think 1-200) and see if the bugs start cropping up in bulk again.\r\n\r\nAgreed at one point it will go open for a load test but i dont think the beta is at that stage yet.  But at the end of the day those doing the Code will decide not me.',NULL,NULL),(45505,5648,86439,'2012-07-29 11:07:18','Done. (23 gig)\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35212\n\nAnd I see a spinning gold coin at the top of the uploaded torrents page which suggests it works.\n\n\nedit: Well theres an interesting thing, it appears in the browse list, but only if I filter for freeleech. An open search does not list it.\n\nBug thread started http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2862',86439,'2012-07-29 11:30:05'),(45506,5861,49532,'2012-07-29 11:07:42','[quote=knickers]Well, if that were true, might as well just go live as is and fix it on the run I would have thought. More activity at times might be good, but theres likely such a thing as too much activity.\r\n\r\nWell over 200 people have been invited, most aint doing shit. While a dedicated few (I dont include myself in that) appear to be putting a lot of time into it.\r\n\r\nI cant imagine being swamped with hundreds of threads stating the stats arent up to date is going to be helpful. Exaggeration? Maybe.[/quote]\r\n\r\nyou are definitely one of the dedicated few   :strongbench: \r\n\r\nif opened up, there might be maybe 500 more people not doing shit\r\nand maybe 20 more who do shit. the rest won\'t even login once. \r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45507,5805,49532,'2012-07-29 11:23:28',' I\'d recommend changing [b]Filter freeleech torrents[/b] to [b] Include only freeleech torrents[/b].\r\n\r\nSome people night interpret [b]Filter freeleech torrents [/b], as filter [i]out[/i] freeleech torrents.',NULL,NULL),(45508,5862,86439,'2012-07-29 11:28:28','It appears freeleech torrents are only visible when filtered. I just upped a 23 gig torrent to test the auto list feature as requested in thread http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2648\r\n\r\n\r\nIve waited (20 mins) to see if it was just slow to update the tracker, it doesnt appear to be the case. When i filter freeleech, there it is. Uncheck the box, click filter again, still not there. Reload the browse page, still nothing. Filter for freeleech, and its listed there.',NULL,NULL),(45509,5862,1243,'2012-07-29 12:01:09','yeah blame me for stupid coding, fixed now.',NULL,NULL),(45510,5805,1243,'2012-07-29 12:05:45','Changed.',NULL,NULL),(45511,5861,1243,'2012-07-29 12:20:02','Yes I think we might open the doors at a later time, but for now I prefer just doing small invites. ',NULL,NULL),(45512,5854,1243,'2012-07-29 12:25:25','24 hour freeleech is still a great gift on it\'s own and frankly more than enough for someone to pop in and say hi in the forum IMO :worm: ',NULL,NULL),(45513,5853,48010,'2012-07-29 13:11:52','[quote=apparition][quote=MrRandom]Stuff like that should either be in the title or in the description. Tags are for finding what is in the content NOT when it was made, the source of the copy, etc. Thats my 2 cents[/quote]\r\n\r\nthese are for finding the content.  for example if you are looking for videos of brea bennett when she was 18 searching for [b]brea.bennett[/b] [b]2006[/b] would be very  usefull if the videos had a date tag.  \r\n\r\nIf, like me, you care more about the dialog, than what positions they fuck in, the [b]english[/b] tag is far much more usefull than the cowgirl tag.\r\n\r\nIf something has the tags [b]russian teen[/b] I know not to download it, because there is a good changce, that there is an underage girl, or one who was coorced into doing porn. \r\n\r\nWithout those tags I end up download shit that I don\'t want, and even shit I\'ll delete the moment I discover it, no matter whether it fucks my ratio, or even gets me banned[/quote]\r\n\r\nyou are over over-obsessed with tags - most members do not think or use the site the same way as you :wink:',NULL,NULL),(45514,5805,48010,'2012-07-29 13:17:39','[quote=Lanz]Changed.[/quote]\r\nworks for me - good job',NULL,NULL),(45515,5862,86439,'2012-07-29 13:22:35',' :broccolidance:  :cavitysearch: ',NULL,NULL),(45516,5859,48010,'2012-07-29 13:45:42','[quote=apparition]One thing some people do is click on a button/link again if their browser is slow to respond.  I tested double clicking, and 2 slots were used.  it would be nice to prevent this as well[/quote]\r\nThanks for the confirmation Apparition\r\n\r\nI didn\'t click again immediately but good point - I did click a while later (trying to break it) and noticed the problem\r\n\r\nAnyway Lanz is aware of it so it will be dealt with',NULL,NULL),(45517,5863,47234,'2012-07-29 14:45:44','Now a case came to my attention on the current site where someone got a ban.  Now they claim to be running seedboxes to generate the speed which is possible.\r\n\r\nBut our tools over there only show IP\'s that have logged into Emp.me not seeboxes.  I can confirm that as i cant see my current seedbox on this list over on current site.  Can we see where people are seeding from over here?\r\n\r\nAlso what tools are being looked into to catch cheats now?  In my experience we have quite a few of them on emp.  I would love to be able to sort the cheats from the others.......\r\n\r\nBanning those doing the right thing would suck IMO.  missng those who cheat is bad too but not as bad as false bans.  Thats why i always currently err on the side of if im not sure they get away.  Would rather be sure one way or the other.\r\n\r\nAlso would love a staff note section where we could record if people let us know if they are seedboxing.  Putting it into the general log just seems to guarantee the note will be lost in the noise.  Especially with changes to the users profile taking up so much space',NULL,NULL),(45518,5863,171777,'2012-07-29 15:41:13','Well I know of a very easy to set up cheat tool called ratiomaster. This tool is usually used out of the box so some settings can make it very easy to detect. Example:\r\nUnless you specifically set the client to stop seeding unless there are only very few leechers it will keep reporting upload speeds of several MB to the tracker (even if there is only 1 leecher downloading at 10 KB/s). Finding torrents on which such forms of cheating happen is a matter of looking at the total up and down reported to the tracker. Once these start to truly differ the torrent most likely has a fake reporter on the app..\r\n\r\nAnother thing that often happens: People download a torrent with the latest torrent client but the upload all of a sudden switches to a different client (because the client file for that newest version of whatever download client was used has not yet been written).\r\n\r\nOff course like this you only find the stupid cheaters but it is a point to start.',NULL,NULL),(45519,5860,171777,'2012-07-29 15:50:22','[quote=apparition]I\'m not sure if you mean buttons on the giver\'s profile, or the reciever\'s profile?\r\n\r\nI\'d make it work like this:\r\nEveryone would have options in their settings to put [b]give donation[/b] button on their profile and/or an [b]ask for donation[/b] button on their profile.\r\n\r\nif someone clicks the [b]give donation[/b] button, a dialog would pop up and ask for the amount, which would be transfered, when they click [b]ok[/b].\r\n\r\nif someone clicks the [b]ask for donation[/b] button, a dialog would pop up and ask for the amount, which would send a request message, when they click [b]ok[/b].[/quote]\r\nA button to give donations to a user on that users profile I can agree with but a button to beg? That is the same thing as when you win the lottery. All of a sudden everybody that wants money starts sending you letters and such demanding money because they have to pay for an expensive operation for their non-existant child.... I\'d say just a give button is more then enough.',NULL,NULL),(45520,5860,94952,'2012-07-29 15:54:20','I was thinking of a easier way to spend bonus points on others, not open the door for begging.',NULL,NULL),(45521,5863,47234,'2012-07-29 15:56:31','We find plenty of stupid cheaters already.  Some like to claim 500TB+ up day 1 for example :lol:\r\n\r\nI believe our current most experienced on this sort of thing is GaryE.  Im certainly not.\r\n\r\nSeriously though we only catch the complete knob jockies atm.  Do we have better tools here or comming?',NULL,NULL),(45522,5863,1243,'2012-07-29 17:30:36','No we don\'t have any good tools for finding cheaters atm. I\'ve planned on spending more time working on this later on, with the help of Gary and others.',NULL,NULL),(45523,5860,49532,'2012-07-29 17:57:37','[quote=DrkNess][quote=apparition]I\'m not sure if you mean buttons on the giver\'s profile, or the reciever\'s profile?\r\n\r\nI\'d make it work like this:\r\nEveryone would have options in their settings to put [b]give donation[/b] button on their profile and/or an [b]ask for donation[/b] button on their profile.\r\n\r\nif someone clicks the [b]give donation[/b] button, a dialog would pop up and ask for the amount, which would be transfered, when they click [b]ok[/b].\r\n\r\nif someone clicks the [b]ask for donation[/b] button, a dialog would pop up and ask for the amount, which would send a request message, when they click [b]ok[/b].[/quote]\r\nA button to give donations to a user on that users profile I can agree with but a button to beg? That is the same thing as when you win the lottery. All of a sudden everybody that wants money starts sending you letters and such demanding money because they have to pay for an expensive operation for their non-existant child.... I\'d say just a give button is more then enough.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYeah, I don\'t like the idea of opening the door to begging.  But if someone wants to open themselves to beggers, by chooosing to put a begging button on their profile; then I have no objections to giving them a mechanism, to invite such headaches on themselves. :pickme: ',NULL,NULL),(45524,5864,75827,'2012-07-29 18:06:06','It would be nice when someone comments on a torrent that you could have a reply button and have that reply directly under it. So if the uploader wants to answer a question every body can clearly see it\r\n\r\nLike this \r\n\r\n_________________________________________________________________________________________\r\nWhat that girls name?\r\n\r\n_________________________________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n_________________________________________________________________________________________\r\n    Her name is Sasha Grey.\r\n_________________________________________________________________________________________\r\n\r\n\r\nMake any sense? lol I`m lil hung over.',NULL,NULL),(45525,5853,49532,'2012-07-29 18:06:06','[quote=Dave]\nyou are over over-obsessed with tags - most members do not think or use the site the same way as you :wink:[/quote]\n\nTrue, but I\'m not the only cheggit refugee here.\n\n[or girl... either reason expains it]  :laugh: ',49532,'2012-07-29 18:09:23'),(45526,5864,49532,'2012-07-29 18:07:30','yes, it makes sense',NULL,NULL),(45527,5864,75827,'2012-07-29 18:13:35','[quote=apparition]yes, it makes sense[/quote]\r\n\r\n[b]Right on [/b]',NULL,NULL),(45528,5853,1243,'2012-07-29 19:03:35','Perhaps a better way to say that is that we encourage tagging but we don\'t enforce them. I\'m actually quite excited to see IF (yeah people are lazy and don\'t give a fuck about anything) community tagging will work.',NULL,NULL),(45529,5864,1243,'2012-07-29 19:05:22','My initial thought was to say use the quote function, but I guess you mean something else?',NULL,NULL),(45530,5864,129045,'2012-07-29 19:42:30','[quote=Lanz]My initial thought was to say use the quote function, but I guess you mean something else?[/quote]\r\n\r\nHe wants a simple reply function, where the reply would appear under the original comment.\r\n\r\nExample lifted from Google:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=53F7_50157580][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image-53F7_50157580.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n\r\nCould be nice I guess, even more if the user received a notification when his comments received a reply.',NULL,NULL),(45531,5854,1507,'2012-07-29 21:25:05',':hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(45532,5864,1507,'2012-07-29 21:26:36',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]Yeah, I think they did that back on the old Chegg...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45533,5853,1507,'2012-07-29 21:33:23',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]It probably will, especially with those members who adore tags...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(45534,5853,49532,'2012-07-29 21:37:30','[quote=Lanz]Perhaps a better way to say that is that we encourage tagging but we don\'t enforce them.[/quote]\nMy suggestion has always been about enouraging, not enforcing.  That\'s why I phrased it as a request (\"Whenever possible, please tag the following: \"), and not a damand(\"You [b]MUST[/b] incluide the all of following, if at all possible\"), but I guess we could soften it even more,\"we recommend including tags for the following:\". \n\nAnd if the list, I gave above, is too much, how about just language and date\n[quote=Lanz]\nI\'m actually quite excited to see IF (yeah people are lazy and don\'t give a fuck about anything) community tagging will work.[/quote] If you want to see if anyone gives a fuck about community taging , secretly tell the major uploaders NOT to tag [b]anal[/b], [b]facial[/b] and [b]big.tits[/b] :laugh: ',49532,'2012-07-29 21:39:00'),(45535,5853,1507,'2012-07-29 21:40:55',':laugh: :laugh: :laugh:\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-07-29 21:41:42'),(45536,5863,171777,'2012-07-29 22:17:06','Some examples of anti spoof scripts (very simple ones):\n\nhttp://www.sb-innovation.de/f59/bittorrent-tracker-analysis-swedvdr-15172/\nhttp://www.sb-innovation.de/f59/bittorrent-tracker-analysis-what-cd-14576/\nhttp://www.sb-innovation.de/f59/bittorrent-tracker-analysis-softmp3-14711/\n\n[b]Edit[/b]: Is it possible to generate a file detailing what users are active on what torrent and how much they uploaded and downloaded on that torrent (and I mean for every active torrent on the website)? If so writing a small program to detect anomalies in such a file would be a small matter and I would happily do that for you people.',171777,'2012-07-29 22:20:41'),(45537,5864,1243,'2012-07-29 23:13:53','Being a bit cynical here; It\'s not hard finding a comment when there are max 3 comments on a torrent.. Lot of work for little gain IMO.',NULL,NULL),(45538,5864,84499,'2012-07-29 23:28:55','\r\nyeah it would be \'nice\' - I think its a superior system. But it would mean some pretty major changes to the way the db is structured and to the comments code. And its a lot of work to be adding at this stage, and as Lanz says for relatively little gain...  imo its a non starter.',NULL,NULL),(45539,5864,86439,'2012-07-30 00:13:14','While it has merits to keep a conversation grouped, on cheggit where this was done, often a fresh comment gets lost in the comments. I recall people responding to comments made weeks ago but no comment appears at the end. Its just highlighted in a red box but hidden in among older posts.\r\n\r\nyou had to scroll through all the comments and keep an eye for the red ones.',NULL,NULL),(45540,5864,49532,'2012-07-30 00:56:23','[quote=mifune]yeah it would be \'nice\' - I think its a superior system. But it would mean some pretty major changes to the way the db is structured and to the comments code. And its a lot of work to be adding at this stage, and as Lanz says for relatively little gain...  imo its a non starter.[/quote]\n\nWell maybe this is one to be put on the todo [i]later[/i] list.',49532,'2012-07-30 00:57:02'),(45541,5865,49532,'2012-07-30 01:23:48','Sometimes sommeone wants to put an attachment to a PM or forum post that isn\'t an image e.g. (css file, greasmonkey script, .torrent, binary,etc), There should be aproved hosts for those as well (better yet, allow attachments).',NULL,NULL),(45542,5864,75827,'2012-07-30 01:47:08','Well it`s a suggestion..\r\nMaybe all make post on Emp.me and see if there is any \"want\" for this  ',NULL,NULL),(45543,5866,49532,'2012-07-30 02:19:43','There are over 100,000 members,  of there was a one time membership fee of $1 that would give Emp $90,000 after paypal micropayment fees.\r\n\r\nThat would cover the costs of running empornium, and maybe even allow the staff to get paid a token salery.\r\n\r\nOf course, that membership might drop to below 50,000, once all the kids who, can\'t make paypal payments get eliminated. (I was 12 when I joined the original Empornium :baby:  )',NULL,NULL),(45545,5866,85111,'2012-07-30 04:53:42','lol i wonder how much emp makes from donations? out of all the private trackers out there tho emp is prob the only one i\'d pay a dollar for.. but seems kinda gay to pay then still have to deal with shit like ratio.. its like buying an iphone app and still get annoying ads/popups\n\nedit. wtf happened i pressed that post button once n it made a dupe post\n\n[mcom]no idea but I deleted the dupe![/mcom]',51063,'2012-08-03 21:24:01'),(45546,5867,49532,'2012-07-30 06:30:19','\r\n\r\nThis is the 21st century there is no need to use the [i]\"web-safe\"[/i] fonts, that most people have on their computer. Verdana Arial and Helvetica are ugly. Plus they render differently depending on which version you have (some people get word wrapping in bad palaces).  It doesn\'t matter what font anyone has on their system, since you can embed fonts into the webpage using google fonts.\r\n\r\nI\'d recommend the Ubuntu font, but other good choices are PT Sans, Open Sans, Droid Sans, and many of the other 500+ google fonts.  \r\n\r\nIt\'s as easy as as adding this to the css file:\r\n \r\n[code]\r\n@import url(http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Ubuntu:400,400italic,500,500italic,700,700italic,300,300italic);\r\n@import url(http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Ubuntu+Mono:400,400italic,700,700italic);\r\n...\r\nbody {\r\n    width: 100%;\r\n    background: #0261a3;\r\n    font-family:\"Ubuntu\",sans-serif;\r\n    font-size: 9pt;\r\n    color: #000000;\r\n}\r\n....\r\ncode {\r\n    font-family: \"Ubuntu Mono\", monospace;\r\n}[/code]',NULL,NULL),(45547,5868,94952,'2012-07-30 13:48:15','URL: [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35212]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35212[/url]\n\nWhat\'s wrong: My only downloading torrent is Knickers FL-test and still my \"Down\" stat is slowly creeping upwards. I zeroed out my Down stat with the free bonus points and so far it has recorded 960 MB downloaded in 18 hours or so. Not huge amount but still not free.\nPossible interference on my end, I have PEX and DHT activated. And I do have 10 other torrents seeding\n\nReproduce: Reset your downloaded stat and freeleech something. I\'m going to kill off all other torents I have active and re-download knickers torrent. \n\n[mcom][b]fixed?:[/b] freeleech automatically set is still counting the download[/mcom]\nFixed!',94952,'2012-08-04 16:49:52'),(45548,5867,85111,'2012-07-30 13:49:18','this might sort out overlapping bugs that i have been experiencing on my macs.. ',NULL,NULL),(45549,5868,129045,'2012-07-30 14:47:16','[quote]Possible interference on my end, I have PEX and DHT activated. And I do have 10 other torrents seeding[/quote]\r\n\r\nYou have it enabled on the torrent in question?\r\n\r\nAnyway, jumped on it to test. Can\'t spare too much bandwidth, but I\'ll grab the screens, that should add at least 15Mb against me :hmmm:',129045,'2012-07-30 14:48:13'),(45550,5868,94952,'2012-07-30 15:04:14','I have confirmed it. Download-stat now at 208 MB and I have downloaded about 230 MB (0.99%)\nWith no other torrents active on this tracker and with PEX and DHT disabled. \nI\'m running Transmission 1.92 I know it\'s old but I have a seedbox set up at home  :grin: ',94952,'2012-07-30 15:06:22'),(45551,5868,129045,'2012-07-30 15:11:39','[s]So far still at zero here.\r\n\r\nDown: 0.00 B\r\nRatio: âˆž[/s]\r\n\r\n[quote]I\'m running Transmission 1.92 I know it\'s old but I have a seedbox set up at home[/quote]\r\nI doubt the client could screw something like this, FL is all handled on the server side :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\r\n\r\nYeah, Auto FL is borked, the system just added 16Mb agains me :\\\r\nOdd, because [b]FL slots[/b] and the [b]24h FL[/b] works just fine, what could be so different between them? :hmmm:\r\nAnd I\'m pretty sure the other FL torrents (set manually) works just fine too, otherwise this problem would have been brought up before.\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT2:[/b]\r\n[quote=mifune]Okay I think I fixed this but it needs testing (by new uploads over 20gb) :smile1:[/quote]\r\nYep, working fine now.\r\n\r\n',129045,'2012-07-31 16:11:34'),(45552,5867,49532,'2012-07-30 15:26:41','[quote=iamstoopid]this might sort out overlapping bugs that i have been experiencing on my macs..[/quote]\r\n\r\nthat\'s the point.',NULL,NULL),(45553,5854,49532,'2012-07-30 15:31:47','I can confirm that my DL hasn\'t moved, and my upload has.',NULL,NULL),(45554,5869,49532,'2012-07-30 15:41:04','[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=5A09_50168EA5][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=5A09_50168EA5[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(45555,5869,129045,'2012-07-30 15:59:53','Well, that\'s new :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]iamstoopid[/b] was having a similar problem ([b]running on Mac[/b]), fonts appear too big, so it was overlapping over the other elements (Menu and search boxes).\r\n\r\nAre you running a Mac too by any chance? I tried Ubuntu and Win7, both render those fonts in a \'normal\' size\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b] Does that happen on both stylesheets?\r\n[b]EDIT2:[/b] Just read his comment on the other thread, I guess both are borked.',129045,'2012-07-30 16:07:09'),(45556,5775,5825,'2012-07-30 16:50:35','How about this: everyone good perv and up can create collages and they are initially the only ones who can edit it and if they feel like having some help, they could give other good pervs and up access to make modifications',NULL,NULL),(45557,5866,171777,'2012-07-30 17:42:22','Not only would this get rid of people not able to pay via paypal (and that includes countries where it is just impossible), it would also get rid of people like me that refuse to pay for a torrent website when there are a lot of free ones out there. \r\n\r\nWe live in 2012 these days. If it exists digitally then you can get it for free if you search around a bit.\r\n\r\nOf course donations are a different matter since those are voluntary, but forcing people to pay anything (no matter how small) will most likely destroy the community IMHO.',NULL,NULL),(45558,5867,171777,'2012-07-30 18:07:21','[quote=iamstoopid]this might sort out overlapping bugs that i have been experiencing on my macs..[/quote]\r\n\r\ngetting rid of the mac would also help :P\r\n\r\nStill I can see the wisdom of this even if it would be hell on earth to find 1 font that everybody likes.',NULL,NULL),(45559,5866,84499,'2012-07-30 18:15:17','\r\n\r\nnever gonna happen',NULL,NULL),(45560,5867,1243,'2012-07-30 19:26:11','[quote=DrkNess][quote=iamstoopid]this might sort out overlapping bugs that i have been experiencing on my macs..[/quote]\r\n\r\ngetting rid of the mac would also help :P\r\n\r\nStill I can see the wisdom of this even if it would be hell on earth to find 1 font that everybody likes.[/quote]\r\n\r\nGood idea, as a test I\'ve set the light stylesheet to use the PT sans web font. Tell me how that looks regarding the the huge font size on macs.',NULL,NULL),(45561,5866,1243,'2012-07-30 19:40:02','Yeah that\'s never gonna happen as long as I have something to say on the matter. It\'s just.. wrong. They tried to pull that stunt on the old emp and it ended with a shit storm (rightfully so) and they had to back off.',NULL,NULL),(45562,5866,1507,'2012-07-30 21:48:18',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]Yeah, I don\'t see that happening here either....  A donation is one thing, given freely and by choice, while a fee is not voluntary and you have no choice...  I don\'t see it happening...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nTho\', if you want to charge a fee, you might think of starting your own group, charging a buck to join your group, and the fees would be used to purchase a membership to a paysite of the group\'s choosing, who then rips the site and makes it available for the group/cummunity, or something like that....  tho\' this is not something I am saying you can do, but is just an idea...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45563,5866,171777,'2012-07-30 21:52:31','[quote=usillyboy]:hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]Yeah, I don\'t see that happening here either....  A donation is one thing, given freely and by choice, while a fee is not voluntary and you have no choice...  I don\'t see it happening...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nTho\', if you want to charge a fee, you might think of starting your own group, charging a buck to join your group, and the fees would be used to purchase a membership to a paysite of the group\'s choosing, who then rips the site and makes it available for the group/cummunity, or something like that....  tho\' this is not something I am saying you can do, but is just an idea...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:[/quote]\r\n\r\nYou know I actually see the group rips of a website as a nice idea :P ',NULL,NULL),(45564,5866,49532,'2012-07-30 23:17:26','\r\n[quote=apparition]There are over 100,000 members,  of there was a one time membership fee of $1 that would give Emp $90,000 after paypal micropayment fees.\r\n\r\nThat would cover the costs of running empornium, and maybe even allow the staff to get paid a token salery.\r\n\r\nOf course, that membership might drop to below 50,000, once all the kids who, can\'t make paypal payments get eliminated. (I was 12 when I joined the original Empornium :baby:  )[/quote]\r\nI\'d never go for a membership fee, but Jenny was not totally wrong.  It\'s true that most people here give money if they can get everythng free, but won\'t think twice about spending $1. The problem is everythig they could get for $1 here they can get for free elesewhere.  \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=DrkNess][quote=usillyboy]:hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]Yeah, I don\'t see that happening here either....  A donation is one thing, given freely and by choice, while a fee is not voluntary and you have no choice...  I don\'t see it happening...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nTho\', if you want to charge a fee, you might think of starting your own group, charging a buck to join your group, and the fees would be used to purchase a membership to a paysite of the group\'s choosing, who then rips the site and makes it available for the group/cummunity, or something like that....  tho\' this is not something I am saying you can do, but is just an idea...  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:[/quote]\r\n\r\nYou know I actually see the group rips of a website as a nice idea :P[/quote]\r\n\r\nHow about doing premium torrent buy-ins.\r\n\r\nI used to belong to a tracker for entrepeneurs, that had ebooks, audio and vidoe for things like, business,marketing, personal growth, hypnosis, etc.\r\n\r\nWhenever there was a request, people could buy into the purhcase of the requested item, for $1-5 dollars (depending opn the item). The site would buy it, when the buy-in target was met, and everyone who, who paid towards it, would be able to download from the initial seed and it would be freeleech, once they have been seeded it would be made public. \r\n',NULL,NULL),(45565,5866,85636,'2012-07-30 23:52:48','[quote=apparition]How about doing premium torrent buy-ins.[/quote]\r\n\r\nA site I\'m on for ebooks does something similar where the new releases are only available to donators for the first week or two, then they are opened up to the rest of the site. Something like that for premium or rare content might entice the wallets to open.',NULL,NULL),(45566,5867,85111,'2012-07-31 00:07:23','everything is perfect  :gjob:  except that filter button.. Here\'s a screen of torrents.php \r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=45E1_50170136][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=45E1_50170136[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nNot sure why but the font for the categories on requests.php is still huge but still works fine enough to call functional i guess >> \r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=404F_50170136][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=404F_50170136[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nI just reformatted all my macs with the new Mountain Lion OS which released 2 days ago.. thats what it looks like with NO browser customisations whatsoever. Same look on safari firefox and chrome which I just installed literally like 5minutes ago. \r\n\r\nAt least the ratio doesn\'t overlap anymore which i thought you lot would never fix  :yaydance:  :laugh: \r\n\r\nI\'ll never get rid of my mac.. had about 3 crashes in 5 years.. windows.. 5 crashes in 3 hours.. anyway now im going to watch some Breaking Bad.. :D\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45567,5869,49532,'2012-07-31 00:15:43','yes this is on a mac\n\nI\'ve Isolated the problem to the NoSquint firefox extension, \r\n\r\nIt happens on ubuntu with the same noSquint settings.\r\nWhen I set the NoSquint text only  scaling to 100% the problem doesn\'t happen',49532,'2012-07-31 00:27:00'),(45568,5870,85636,'2012-07-31 00:25:19','I have seen this on a few sites and might be useful for people who use seedboxes to download and seed content. The Add to RSS button adds that torrent to a RSS feed for a seedbox to get the torrent from. This is not like the notifications, it is a button on the torrent page its self so that only torrents that are clicked are on the RSS list.',NULL,NULL),(45569,5867,49532,'2012-07-31 00:54:27','[quote=Lanz][quote=DrkNess][quote=iamstoopid]this might sort out overlapping bugs that i have been experiencing on my macs..[/quote]\n\ngetting rid of the mac would also help :P\n\nStill I can see the wisdom of this even if it would be hell on earth to find 1 font that everybody likes.[/quote]\n\nGood idea, as a test I\'ve set the light stylesheet to use the PT sans web font. Tell me how that looks regarding the the huge font size on macs.[/quote]\n\nOn my machine the huge font turned out to be caused by the NoSquint extention. I had text scalling at 120% and fullpage salling at 100%.  when I set both to 100 the problem was fixed. \n\n\nThe PTsans looks much better than Verdana, but I still like Ubuntu better.  Why is the size 11pt in the light theme?\n\nMaking the stats a slightly smaller font than the rest of the page would be a good Idea though   the sats look too crowded still.',49532,'2012-07-31 01:10:56'),(45570,5869,85111,'2012-07-31 01:28:36',' :sigh: dark theme was perfect until now. dno what changed but now i get a tiny overlap on ratio too. \r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=F0FF_501718B4][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=F0FF_501718B4[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nfirefox, chrome and safari - no add ons',NULL,NULL),(45571,5867,85111,'2012-07-31 01:38:29','crowded i can live with but overlapping is just crap.. i dont have any extensions on my browsers yet but i still get the bugs.\r\n\r\nme and yamchan tried troubleshooting this last week in this thread\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2746\r\n\r\nand came up with a couple of possible fixes. At the end of the day all we can do is inform the admins, i think they probably hate me now cos im always posting up bugs that they thought they fixed lol. ',NULL,NULL),(45572,5871,85636,'2012-07-31 02:30:37','I got this when I tried to add a group award to the \"Test Group\"\r\n\r\n[img]http://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/Screenshot%20from%202012-07-31%2001%3A27%3A57.png[/img]',NULL,NULL),(45573,5868,84499,'2012-07-31 03:31:21','\r\nOkay I think I fixed this but it needs testing (by new uploads over 20gb) :smile1:',NULL,NULL),(45574,5775,84499,'2012-07-31 03:36:35','\r\n\r\nThe collage author can now set a permission level (Perv, GoodPerv etc.) or \'only creator\' for who can add/remove torrents from the collage. I changed the editing permissions so only the collage author can edit the description or delete the collage (plus staff). \r\nThe system has always been that deleted collages that are not personal collages can be recovered by staff (but not torrents that are removed, just the state when it was \'deleted\').\r\n\r\nI havent added logging yet but I will add some.',NULL,NULL),(45575,5671,84499,'2012-07-31 03:54:54','\r\n\r\nHopefully the layout and text issues are fixed now (it just writes a text link without a borky img if no image)\r\n\r\nThe columns should layout a bit nicer too. in theory.',NULL,NULL),(45576,5871,84499,'2012-07-31 03:59:09','\r\n\r\nwhoops... need to sort out a couple of groups permissions things.\r\n\r\nthanks :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(45577,5871,84499,'2012-07-31 04:13:51','\r\n\r\nshould be fixed now.',NULL,NULL),(45578,5868,86439,'2012-07-31 04:29:09','If I delete and re-up that same one, will that count? Or not count hopefully?\n\n\nReup, wouldnt allow as tracker knew the exact torrent existed :thumbsup:. Deleted old one, and now successfully reupped it again.\n\nReupped\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35214\n',86439,'2012-07-31 04:49:01'),(45579,5758,84499,'2012-07-31 04:30:46','\r\ndone :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(45580,5868,84499,'2012-07-31 04:36:41','[quote=knickers]If I delete and re-up that same one, will that count? Or not count hopefully?[/quote]\r\n\r\nyeah that should work :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(45581,5868,86439,'2012-07-31 04:48:18','See earlier edit\n\nReupped\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35214',86439,'2012-07-31 04:49:46'),(45582,5868,84499,'2012-07-31 04:52:13','\r\n\r\nthanks, grabbing now.\n\n\r\n\r\nseems to be working:cool: ',84499,'2012-07-31 05:02:03'),(45584,5872,84499,'2012-07-31 05:39:42','\r\n\r\nCollages now have a permissions setting which can be changed by the creator to change which classes can add/remove torrents. Only the creator can now edit the description etc. (and staff). Actions are logged.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45585,5867,84499,'2012-07-31 06:11:35','\r\n\r\nchanged the emp style font to \'Open Sans\'',NULL,NULL),(45586,5867,67255,'2012-07-31 06:55:54','nice',NULL,NULL),(45587,5873,171777,'2012-07-31 07:15:09','After testing the collage permissions I stumbled across the following bug:\r\nCreation of collages goes without a hitch but each time I try to edit one of my collages (1 public 1 personal and it happens on both) I get the following:\r\n\r\n[quote]Server error\r\nThe website encountered an error while retrieving http://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php. It may be down for maintenance or configured incorrectly.\r\nHere are some suggestions:\r\nReload this webpage later.\r\nHTTP Error 500 (Internal Server Error): An unexpected condition was encountered while the server was attempting to fulfill the request.[/quote]\r\n\r\nThis happens in google chrome latest version. Strangely enough if I place my cursor in the adress bar and just hit enter (to reload the page basically) it DOES load without an error.',NULL,NULL),(45588,5873,84499,'2012-07-31 07:31:34','\r\nfixed',NULL,NULL),(45589,5873,171777,'2012-07-31 07:53:50','confirmed',NULL,NULL),(45590,5867,49532,'2012-07-31 08:00:54','[quote=iamstoopid]crowded i can live with but overlapping is just crap.. i dont have any extensions on my browsers yet but i still get the bugs.\r\n\r\nme and yamchan tried troubleshooting this last week in this thread\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2746\r\n\r\nand came up with a couple of possible fixes. At the end of the day all we can do is inform the admins, i think they probably hate me now cos im always posting up bugs that they thought they fixed lol.[/quote] do you use text-only zoom or full page zoom. the only thing that Ive found to rpelicate your big is doing text-only zoom.  I don\'t think it\'s has anything to do with whether its a mac or what browser. I think it\'s all about settings.',NULL,NULL),(45591,5867,84499,'2012-07-31 08:02:53','\r\n\r\nctrl-0 to set your text to no zoom in most (all?) browsers.',NULL,NULL),(45592,5867,49532,'2012-07-31 08:05:56','[quote=mifune]changed the emp style font to \'Open Sans\'[/quote] very nice. Open Sans is an excellent font, technically and aesthetically.',49532,'2012-07-31 08:06:19'),(45593,5874,49532,'2012-07-31 08:34:52','sometimes you know that someone uploads a lot of videos that you are interestest in. on cheggeit we were able to see all the uploads from any user by viewing their profile.  Why don\'t we do one better and be able to filter search results by uploader.',NULL,NULL),(45594,5867,86439,'2012-07-31 08:37:16','While the new fonts are fine and all, on my smaller monitor (21\") they appear to be too small in places. I cant imagine how difficult that is to read on a 15.9 laptop.\r\n\r\nBasic Search text is fine, but the switch to advanced is almost unreadable.\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-E44F_50177D8B.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-E44F_50177D8B.jpg[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(45595,5874,86439,'2012-07-31 08:43:11','I can see you upped FTV Mary here via your profile. And i just looked on the old site, and I can see upped torrents in profiles too.',NULL,NULL),(45596,5869,1243,'2012-07-31 09:36:11','Well you have 10,000 slots and 4,000,000 credits. Fat chance that will happen on the live server.  :grin: ',NULL,NULL),(45597,5869,85111,'2012-07-31 09:48:53','haha true that i forgot about it tbh  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(45598,5875,37338,'2012-07-31 09:58:26','Okay I\'m really kind of out of words for this but I think it\'s a big problem\r\n\r\n[size=2][font=Arial Black]URL[/font][/size]: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35213\r\n\r\n[size=2][font=Arial Black]Problem:[/font][/size] Can\'t not download a torrent or seed\r\n\r\n[font=Arial Black][size=2]How I notice it:[/size][/font] I downloaded the torrent earlier today @11AM CST and watched it as it got to 11.1% and stopped. Now it\'s 2:35AM CST and yet it\'s still at 11.1%. I went to the torrent page and noticed that the download started up again. When I came back to the forums page the torrent started to throttle itself down to 0% download speed. \r\n\r\nThe problem is that it\'s not the only torrent I had this problem with. I am not able to download any other torrents expect one. I hope it\'s not just me but in any case I\'m going to try and sign out and back in to see if that affects anything.  ',NULL,NULL),(45599,5867,85111,'2012-07-31 10:03:26','[quote=mifune]ctrl-0 to set your text to no zoom in most (all?) browsers.[/quote]\r\n\r\nfont is pretty small here on my 15inch laptop. settings have not been altered, i use ctrl +/- and default 0 yesterday and default still had overlaps. But yeh the font changes seems to have fixed the problem as of right now since font is miniature. Also like Lanz said in another thread I doubt ill have 4.000,000 and 10,000 slots on the live server so any crowded problems should sort itself out. I\'ll let u know if any of your font tweaks messes things up.',NULL,NULL),(45600,5875,37338,'2012-07-31 10:05:10','Tired logging out and back in, did not fix the problem. I have to keep refreshing the page in order for the torrent to stray alive to download. I also tired downloading another torrent and it is still not downloading either.\r\n\r\n[font=Arial Black][size=2]URL for new torrent:[/size][/font] http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35215',NULL,NULL),(45601,5874,85111,'2012-07-31 10:13:34','yeh i have loads of torrents on the old site and you can see the uploaders torrents when you view their profile. New EMP puts these into columns however and i much prefer the old list/row layout as its easier to read.\r\n\r\n I also add my name in the tag also so i can use the sort by date function. e.g. click my banner at the bottom. \r\nby default i think the old profile page list\'s the torrents in alphabetical order.\n\nSo let me break it down, what i would like to see on a users profile page ->\r\n\r\n[*] List of the users uploads in row format (like the old emp) not the column format currently used\r\n[*] List can be sorted e.g. most seeded, most downloads, latest upload. This helps to highlight a particular uploaders most snatched torrent etc\r\n[*] Tags, tags and tags of each torrent.\r\n\r\n',85111,'2012-07-31 10:33:41'),(45602,5876,37338,'2012-07-31 10:33:29','As the title says. It\'s just an idea that came into my head at 3am.\r\n\r\nThe idea is this: Having the Mods and Lanz give the order to have one or two things checked in a weeks time.\r\n\r\nHave a bunch of users or a certain amount of users (depends on the item) to test a certain item for a week\r\n\r\n[size=1][font=Arial Black]Ex:[/font][/size] Upload. Have the testers check and test the upload feature. Being able to upload correct torrents and being able to edit and remove them. Once the certain guidelines have been meet then go on to the next issue. This does not include being able to download, comment, seed, or anything else. Just to see if the users can upload with ease. After that is done then move into the next phase to have them download torrents, check to see if it can seeded, or whatever the next action item is.\r\n\r\nIt\'s idea that I thought of, it seems like we have a bunch of ants running around trying to break crap. Having a schedule for action items will also help this site go live faster IMO. That way we all can focus on these certain things and get them fixed instead of having the problem re-appear cause I use Chrome while the next tester is using Firefox or a Mac. \r\n\r\nI could explain more in the morning but now I must sleep.\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45603,5876,85111,'2012-07-31 10:41:58','3am for you, its 9am for me.. my day is just beginning',85111,'2012-07-31 10:43:20'),(45604,5874,49532,'2012-07-31 11:04:32','[quote=knickers]I can see you upped FTV Mary here via your profile. And i just looked on the old site, and I can see upped torrents in profiles too.[/quote] in user profiles, it says \"recent uploads\", I didn\'t realize it showed uploads from 5 months ago.\r\n\r\nStill, it would be cool to be able to search, for the teen lesbian masturbation videos, uploaded by prakik',NULL,NULL),(45605,5875,171777,'2012-07-31 11:20:13','So small recap:\r\nYou have managed to download the .torrent file but the actual download in your torrentclient is not working?',NULL,NULL),(45606,5866,171777,'2012-07-31 11:26:07','[quote=MrRandom][quote=apparition]How about doing premium torrent buy-ins.[/quote]\r\n\r\nA site I\'m on for ebooks does something similar where the new releases are only available to donators for the first week or two, then they are opened up to the rest of the site. Something like that for premium or rare content might entice the wallets to open.[/quote]\r\n\r\nThis too sounds feasible (and even rather easy to do). The main thing I like about communities like this is that they are in essence free. So if certain types of contect get a waiting list for the non-donaters that is well withing that feature of free-ness.\r\n\r\nThis is also once again compatible with a prior suggestion that as soon as there are more donations then there are servers costs, the surplus could be used to obtain more content (which would then once again be on the waiting list for non-donaters)',NULL,NULL),(45607,5876,171777,'2012-07-31 11:29:02','This idea might be nice to use once the overall stream of bugs slows down enough. Right now the \"ants\" still find a lot of things.',NULL,NULL),(45608,5874,171777,'2012-07-31 11:32:03','There is also a link that shows all uploads you made so far. For iamstoopid this results in the following link:\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?type=uploaded&userid=85111\r\n\r\nYou can find this link on the right hand side in the community overview.',NULL,NULL),(45609,5874,86439,'2012-07-31 11:44:12','[quote=apparition][quote=knickers]I can see you upped FTV Mary here via your profile. And i just looked on the old site, and I can see upped torrents in profiles too.[/quote] in user profiles, it says \"recent uploads\", I didn\'t realize it showed uploads from 5 months ago.\r\n\r\nStill, it would be cool to be able to search, for the teen lesbian masturbation videos, uploaded by prakik[/quote]\r\nI have no idea how far back it lists, but I recall at least one member had a huge list under their profile on the main site.',NULL,NULL),(45610,5866,47234,'2012-07-31 12:27:37','Sorry im totally against coerced donations of any sort.\r\n\r\nThe idea of a torrent site being run on any sort of commercial basis would have me heading for another site.  What we do isnt exactly appreciated in certain circles.  If it becomes commercial then its on a whole higher level of harassment.  As staff that frightens me....\r\n\r\nI dont want to share a cell with Dotcom :lol: \r\n\r\nEmp runs on a shoestring budget at best.  Only Admin knows exactly what donations 