out at all, at least not in shorter time than a year according to the cookie.[/quote]\r\nI haven\'t measured the inactivity time needed for the site to logout the user automatically, but it\'s around 1 hour I guess.\r\n\r\nAbout the expiration date, odd. The browsers I use here:\r\n\r\n[b]Opera[/b] will not show any type of expire date on the cookie\r\n[b]Firefox[/b] lists the expire date as \"Session\"\r\n[b]Chrome[/b] also lists it as \"Session\" (close the browser and it\'s gone)',NULL,NULL),(45688,5875,37338,'2012-07-31 22:09:45','[font=Arial Black]ok step by step.[/font]\r\n\r\nWhen I go to the torrent page to select a torrent I can either download the torrent or select it to doubleseed it. \r\n\r\nEither way the torrent file downloads to my client and just sits there. Not downloading or nothing. One of them took up to 15 minutes to start downloading\r\n\r\nYet when it starts to download it starts off strong but throttles it itself down to 1.3kb or less\r\n\r\nI [font=Arial Black]have checked[/font] my settings on the utorrent client and yet it still does the same thing. I have even downloaded a torrent from the old site to see if it was me and it\'s not. Torrents starts up as soon as I download it.\r\n\r\nWhat I notice was that [font=Arial Black]if I\'m not on[/font] the browse torrent page the torrent will go to 1.5kb\\s when not on the browse torrent page, [font=Arial Black]but when I\'m on[/font] the page it goes to somewhere between 98.7kb\\s or higher when I\'m on the browse torrent page. \r\n\r\nIt\'s like I have to be on the browse torrent page in order to download a torrent. \r\n\r\nThe reason you guys are seeing me seed is because I left it on the browse torrent page in order to complete my download. \r\n\r\n[font=Arial Black]It\'s the weirdest shit ever[/font]',NULL,NULL),(45691,5783,86439,'2012-07-31 22:13:52','I leave my system running, FF open but minimised with an Emp tab still open, go to bed/out, hours later I come in hit refresh on the site and bobs your uncle. I dont have to log back in.\r\n\r\nI did in the beginning though, it occasionally asked for login details. Havent had that in a while.',NULL,NULL),(45692,5837,84499,'2012-07-31 22:38:04','\r\n\r\nplease everyone sacrifice a calculator to the gods of programming and pray this bug is finally squashed.  :pythfoot: ',NULL,NULL),(45693,5888,91522,'2012-07-31 22:38:39','Hi,\r\n\r\nwhat about uniting basic and advanced search? (already proposed this in another thread, but no reply)\r\n\r\nIt could work like this:\r\nJust allow boolean operators in basic search and add the filelist input box.\r\nUse the \'any\' \'all\' radiobuttons as default operators when no boolean operator is explicitly specified.\r\nThis way one gets the benefits of both search worlds ;)\r\n\r\nAlso, it would be more consistent to rename the search input boxes to \'description\', \'filelist\' and \'tags\' and use \'search terms\' as a heading. Another heading would be \'category\' for the categories and \'options\' for stuff like \'order by ...\'\r\n\r\nWhat do you think about that?\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45696,5774,84499,'2012-07-31 22:47:16','test',NULL,NULL),(45698,5837,129045,'2012-07-31 22:50:57',':laugh:\r\n\r\nWill do.',NULL,NULL),(45699,5837,86439,'2012-07-31 22:51:54','Ill smash an abacus. ',NULL,NULL),(45700,5702,70679,'2012-07-31 22:54:33','Thanks for implementing this suggestion but.... the italic is a bit hard to read for this old fart\'s eyes.... and overall maybe a tiny bit bigger font? Thanks.',NULL,NULL),(45701,5727,70679,'2012-07-31 22:57:36','bump :-)',NULL,NULL),(45702,5706,70679,'2012-07-31 22:58:44','bump',NULL,NULL),(45703,5890,70679,'2012-07-31 23:01:19','I think that the views counter is not working properly especially from the second page on unless is newly implemented so then is clear that is showing zero.',NULL,NULL),(45704,5890,84499,'2012-07-31 23:05:32','it is only counting from an hour ago :gjob:\n ',84499,'2012-08-01 00:06:40'),(45706,5706,84499,'20