t\'s going to be hard taking screen shots of it. ',37338,'2012-08-01 04:25:29'),(45739,5876,37338,'2012-08-01 04:29:20','Thanks guys, I\'m sure that what drkness said will come truw soon enough. Just trying to get a ball rolling',NULL,NULL),(45740,5875,86439,'2012-08-01 05:53:45','http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35216\r\n\r\nJust under 1.3gig. I am seeding it.',NULL,NULL),(45741,5875,84499,'2012-08-01 06:33:45','\r\nI just grabbed this at 9MB/s+ and will also leave it seeding :\r\n\r\n[url=/torrents.php?id=35174]Tiffany Hopkins 2.2GB[/url]\r\n\r\nits multifile so you could grab just a couple of files for testing.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45742,5783,1243,'2012-08-01 08:33:14','Yeah, session is the name of the cookie that deals with sessions. You don\'t have any extensions that can block cookies or something? You also don\'t have a few helper cookies for the GUI as far as I can tell.',NULL,NULL),(45743,5875,37338,'2012-08-01 08:39:25','The candy stripers is not downloading when I took the screen shot. \r\n\r\nI waited to take the screenshot and still it is not working. \r\n\r\nThe tiffany one started right away. \r\n\r\nhere are the pics\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=F5FA_5018CD4D][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=F5FA_5018CD4D&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1C9E_5018CD4D][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=1C9E_5018CD4D&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45744,5875,1243,'2012-08-01 08:57:06','First picture, on the info tab. The availability bar is red meaning that no one in the swarm has any parts of the torrent to share. You also see seeds 0 of 0 connected, meaning no one is seeding this torrent so you can not download it.\r\n\r\nThe second one has seeders so no problem.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45745,5875,37338,'2012-08-01 09:39:57','The candy stripers are showing that Knickers is seeding it and that he has it at 100%\n\nCan someone else try and download the candy stripers to see if it\'s not just me',37338,'2012-08-01 09:41:19'),(45746,5875,86439,'2012-08-01 09:42:13','EDIT: Im wondering if its uTorrent 3.1.3 related? Hasnt that version (3 onwards) been an endless source of problems?\n\n\n\nOdd, uTorrent shows me available to seed it, its progress bar is blue so no errors, tracker info says working, and full blue bar on availability. The site says Im a seed, and connectable etc.\n\nAdditionally, the site shows wallabe as a leech, and connectable. Albeit, no data transferred.\n\nMy screens\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-8BE0_5018E04C.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-8BE0_5018E04C.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-CABD_5018E04C.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-CABD_5018E04C.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-C58D_5018E04C.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-C58D_5018E04C.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-59F0_5018E04C.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-59F0_5018E04C.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-A455_5018E04C.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-A455_5018E04C.jpg[/img][/url]',86439,'2012-08-01 09:52:06'),(45747,5875,37338,'2012-08-01 10:11:21','Don\'t know what you did Knickers but it just started downloading anddddddd it just stopped.',NULL,NULL),(45748,5879,49532,'2012-08-01 10:54:40','[quote=knickers][quote=mifune]ah apprentices do not have tag adding / voting permissions, so that is working as intended. We do need to add it to the help articles on both tagging and user classes what you can/cant do as an apprentice/perv/etc though.\n\nI boosted your upload a bit and promoted you to good perv so you can help test the site better*\n\n\n\n(*just be aware the stats here will be wiped out and your stats from the main site imported when we go live).[/quote]\nI have started a tag tutorial article. It needs work.\nIm unsure of rules re: made up tags, I know they are at least discouraged ie: big.knockers in place of big.tits etc, but unsure on say names or the thousand other possible tags people will come up with.\n\nUntil two minutes ago I had no idea about user classes and tags, Im now aware that apprentices cant edit/vote tags.[/quote]\n\nPlease feel free to incorporate all or part of my [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=1611]\"introduction to effective tagging\"[/url]',49532,'2012-08-01 11:02:50'),(45749,5783,129045,'2012-08-01 13:11:51','Under Ubuntu it\'s all vanilla settings, I had only visited the front page there, but normally there\'ll be SearchPanelState, TorrentDetailsState and TorrentDetailsToolsState there along with the Session cookie.\r\n\r\nHere\'s Chrome (Win7), also vanilla:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1673_50190DAD][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=1673_50190DAD&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nI had made sure FF and Opera settings were as lax as possible under Win7, but that didn\'t change the cookies state, I\'ll try all clean profiles soon to see if there\'s any change :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b] No dice, clean profile and lax settings didn\'t change anything. The cookie still shows expire dates as session, went a little over 1 hour for me to get kicked out on Chrome and FF, Opera took a little less, around 40 minutes.\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT2:[/b] Now this sucks, setting an expiration date manually on Opera also does nothing, I just got kicked again after setting the expiration date to 2013. ',129045,'2012-08-01 15:29:08'),(45750,5875,86439,'2012-08-01 13:22:17','Well its seeding at 45kB now, to 4 leeches. \r\n\r\nJust as a tip, I had 3.1.3, it was a drama, reverted to 2.2.1 and no dramas since. Might be worth considering.',NULL,NULL),(45751,5879,86439,'2012-08-01 13:33:30','If senior staff want to look over it, Im fine with using it. It seems fairly complete. Its just will the tags you list (impressively long too) be the chosen ones for example.',NULL,NULL),(45752,5899,171777,'2012-08-01 13:52:48','Should there be a public overview of features that are known to work right now? This way a new tester will not keep testing the same things time and again when it has already been proven to work as intended. This way the focus of new tests can be somewhat directed in a general sense until the moment where staff switches to specific bug hunts in which they ask everybody to rape 1 specific functionality. \r\n\r\nRight now every new person that comes along tries the basic things: add a torrent, delete a torrent, report a torrent e.g. while probably no one even bothered to read the rules or check out all the settings they can access. ',NULL,NULL),(45753,5899,84499,'2012-08-01 19:57:53','\r\n\r\nTo be honest there isnt a list of stuff that is proven to work, some stuff is less likely to have bugs in it than others but things change and bugs can appear and bugs can get missed.\r\n\r\nPerhaps more useful would be a list of stuff on the website or something. I dunno I am tempted to just say work through the drop down and top menus thoroughly trying everything... and keep an eye on the test requests forum for specific things.  We could be more organised but its hard to find time to do it, and so far we are not exactly running out of stuff to do. I have 11 items on my immediate todo list and I have been neglecting some real life work the past couple of weeks as it is... and if I\'m honest I\'d prefer to spend what time I can coding just from a personal enjoyment pov.\r\n\r\nIf you want to make an effort at organising the testers better you are very welcome :D - if we put up a \'guide to testing\' of some sort that might be helpful :hmmm: I am gonna be really busy with RL work the next few days (I have a deadline monday) but I will try to make some time at the weekend to do something maybe.',NULL,NULL),(45754,5879,84499,'2012-08-01 20:03:22','[quote=2Xmatch]Yes i can see them now. They work properly. The problem is that before i received the status buff, i couldn\'t change tags on torrents i uploaded.\r\nI think all users should be able to edit tags on their own torrents.[/quote]\r\n\r\nyeah good point. I\'ll add that.\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45755,5879,84499,'2012-08-01 20:14:58','[quote=apparition][quote=knickers]\r\nI have started a tag tutorial article. It needs work.\r\nIm unsure of rules re: made up tags, I know they are at least discouraged ie: big.knockers in place of big.tits etc, but unsure on say names or the thousand other possible tags people will come up with.\r\n\r\nUntil two minutes ago I had no idea about user classes and tags, Im now aware that apprentices cant edit/vote tags.[/quote]\r\n\r\nPlease feel free to incorporate all or part of my [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=1611]\"introduction to effective tagging\"[/url][/quote]\r\n[quote=knickers]If senior staff want to look over it, Im fine with using it. It seems fairly complete. Its just will the tags you list (impressively long too) be the chosen ones for example.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nI\'m okay with it but I think we should seperate out the \'guide to tagging\' from the tag glossary. The tag glossary bit can be a seperate article or thread I think, and will probably need some modifying to make it fit with the official tags etc. But its a useful (and fairly comprehensive) list - especially for those not versed in tags. The stuff at the top can be incorporated as appropriate into the tagging tutorial - its good but the language is a little strident for empornium perhaps? (it needs to be toned down a tiny bit... we are not going to state in the tagging tutorial that you should be tagging \'english\' on 95% of torrents for example) ',NULL,NULL),(45756,5879,49532,'2012-08-01 21:17:48','[quote=mifune]we are not going to state in the tagging tutorial that you should be tagging \'english\' on 95% of torrents for example)[/quote]\n [b][size=6]TO ME THIS IS THE MOST IMPORTANT TAG.[/size][/b]\n\nWhy are you so against tagging torrents with english.   \n\nMy whole involvment in the beta testing is motivated by trying to get support, for making it easy to tell what videos are in in English and what videos aren\'t.  \n\nIt is so FUCKING frustrating, that people are more concerned with stupid meaningless SHIT, like what position people are fucking in, or where someone dumps their load, than they do about, CONTEXT.  And the only way to get the context is to be able to understand what the fuck people are saying.\n\n :banghead:  :argh:  :rant: \n\n',49532,'2012-08-01 21:22:57'),(45757,5879,84499,'2012-08-01 22:14:11','[quote=apparition][quote=mifune]we are not going to state in the tagging tutorial that you should be tagging \'english\' on 95% of torrents for example)[/quote]\r\n [b][size=6]TO ME THIS IS THE MOST IMPORTANT TAG.[/size][/b]\r\n\r\nWhy are you so against tagging torrents with english.   \r\n\r\nMy whole involvment in the beta testing is motivated by trying to get support, for making it easy to tell what videos are in in English and what videos aren\'t.  \r\n\r\nIt is so FUCKING frustrating, that people are more concerned with stupid meaningless SHIT, like what position people are fucking in, or where someone dumps their load, than they do about, CONTEXT.  And the only way to get the context is to be able to understand what the fuck people are saying.\r\n\r\n :banghead:  :argh:  :rant:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nMost pervs dont care. Whats important to you is not important to them and vice versa. And on the scale of important things to tag english language is pretty low down on the list for most users imo.\r\n\r\nAnd as nearly all the porn on emp [b]is[/b] in english its hard to understand why its such a big issue for you... ',NULL,NULL),(45758,5879,49532,'2012-08-02 01:15:21','[quote=mifune]\r\nAnd as nearly all the porn on emp [b]is[/b] in english its hard to understand why its such a big issue for you...[/quote]\r\nBecausee I\'m really into is very young looking teens, with no peircings or tatoos. More than half of that kind of videos are from eastern europe.  From what I\'ve been told (from someone who was forced into porn at 15, in russio), is that with eastern european porn, if they look like the could be underage, they probabaqbly are.\r\n\r\nCalifornia is a 3 strikes state, and each video can be charged as a separate count.  I\'m not about to spend life in prison for dowmloading 3 fucking videos.',NULL,NULL),(45759,5879,86439,'2012-08-02 03:05:41','I think the thing to remember is its Community Tagging. That doesnt simply mean that the community tag, but also the community will decide what tags to use, which are important. If the community agrees with you, then they will be tagged as English, or Russian etc naturally. Either right off the bat, or over time.\r\n\r\nKeep in mind, another option is for tags to disappear altogether. Be happy we have them.\r\n\r\nI dont plan to remove the section on language, or your reasons for it, I will just tone it down. I can see your point about its relevance and in reality there are potentially hundreds of things to tag some clips for and this would if done make a great search tool, but its not practical in reality. For example, Im sure theres at least one bloke/gal out there that is into Rollerskates or wooden spoons, but I wont be tagging it specifically unless it became more mainstream as a search. Youre missing the point about these things being voluntary. There are likely to be many torrents upped with no tags at all. Some people just dont like them and some arent affected by the same concerns in searches. But mostly there are some things that are that obscure that most wouldnt even think to list them, and I doubt anyone wants to revise a tags list with 1000+ tags (if language or origin is important, then why not rollerskates or wooden spoons) to check if it should be there every time they up a torrent. But you, and anyone else, can add them anyway. Imagine the potential for every last conceivable tag, fucked.on.concrete fucked.on.tiles fucked.on.timber and subsets, fucked.on.parquetry etc. \r\n\r\nIf certain tags were mandated, then people will either breach the rules, or not bother uploading, or leave the site. I mean even Cheggit with its tag system, there were always shitfights within torrents regarding tags.\r\n\r\nI believe given differences of opinion, past practices etc, the staff here have struck a good balance with the implementation and methodology. maybe youre not alone in your thoughts re: language. And if you\'re not, they will sooner or later be part of them anyway. Thats the power of community.\r\n\r\nIn other words, for the love of all things holy DONT ROCK THE BOAT. \r\n\r\nThankyou for your efforts in compiling it, for the explanations etc, Ive incorporated a lot of it as is, and some Ive mixed in with my own. Ive tried to write it for new to tags members, and old tag users from Cheggit. Ive tried to highlight that its benefit and extent of usefulness is determined by members and their inclusion.\r\n\r\nThe rest is up to the members to act or not.\r\n\r\n[quote=mifune]\r\n\r\nI\'m okay with it but I think we should seperate out the \'guide to tagging\' from the tag glossary. The tag glossary bit can be a seperate article or thread I think, and will probably need some modifying to make it fit with the official tags etc. But its a useful (and fairly comprehensive) list - especially for those not versed in tags. The stuff at the top can be incorporated as appropriate into the tagging tutorial - its good but the language is a little strident for empornium perhaps? (it needs to be toned down a tiny bit... we are not going to state in the tagging tutorial that you should be tagging \'english\' on 95% of torrents for example)[/quote]\r\nIm on it.',NULL,NULL),(45760,5619,79930,'2012-08-02 03:06:18','Maybe it\'s nothing but I read somewhere that this new site uses an old image of the old site. Maybe you have changed the passwords since then? I could log in and I have same password since start.',NULL,NULL),(45761,5879,67255,'2012-08-02 05:47:55','I concur with apparition, I believe that guide is a very helpful guide. It could make the work of staff and user such much easier.\r\nIs the administration help the user base follow a \"yellow brick road\" it should be easier to determine what is effective tagging. Those other obscure tags (it seems a Tag I use, is obscure \"big.dick) should be prune away by the very promising community tagging system implemented here.',NULL,NULL),(45762,5900,85111,'2012-08-02 05:51:52','This subject was originally brought up from this thread >> http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2874\r\n \r\nSo atm when you go on a user profile you pretty much see what the guys been up to e.g. recent downloads, recent torrents uploaded etc. Now thats all fine n dandy if you were some facebook stalker but what I would like to  see is:\r\n\r\n[*] List of the users uploads in row format (like the old emp) not the column format currently used so its easier to read.\r\n[*] List can be sorted e.g. most seeded, most downloads, latest upload. This helps to highlight a particular uploaders most snatched torrent etc\r\n[*] Tags of each torrent\r\n\r\nI feel that this info is much more relevant to what I look for when clicking on one of my favourite uploaders user names. Also with this layout they\'ll be more data on that single page so it\'ll much more efficient to find what your looking for. kinda like the old emp except you can organise list n more info.\r\n\r\nnow i know you can get to this info from the communities box on the right but you gotta open a new tab/navigate forward n backwards for each thing and it just seems like a step backwards if anything.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45763,5901,67255,'2012-08-02 06:03:21','    The page url http://empornium.mooo.com/bonus.php\r\n    What is wrong: \r\n\r\nWhen I go to the Bonus page, I click the personal 24 freeleech button but after the page refreshes nothing happens (I think a red banner was supposed to appear on the top of the page)\r\n\r\nIf I click the button of -10 GB for me (cost of 4,000 Credits) it pass to the next refresh where it say the credit was applied but my stats remain frozen on the top right corner\n\nhumm seem I was wrong on the 10 gig, now I can see the update after I navigate around the site',67255,'2012-08-02 06:06:42'),(45764,5902,73066,'2012-08-02 06:48:08','I like the bling idea. But byuing medals for bonus points seems wrong to me. (dont get me wrong i always max out on the seeding, so its good for me.) =)\n\nMy first though was having medals for other stuff. Like giving medals for torrents posted, 1 or 5 torrents gives the first medal and then it can expand with stars when more torrents are posted or some other simple feature. And likewise with forum post, maybe a request medal (for filling requests) and so on. Collage medal, tagging medal and so on. So you can have that one guy that always add tags to stuff who gets a super tagging master bling medal for his effort, or a super poster that get a medal for his and so on. Ofc you can have a seeding medal that is bound to the earned bonus points and it would represent a good seeder. And ofc a medal for those who takes the time to write thanks. =)\n\nThis is just an idea im trowing out there regarding the bling. Seems a lot more fun that way, atleast to me. And the members would get some bling for their effort in the community. And maybe it would be a reminder for the community to contribute in all aspekts of the community.\n\nAny other input on this?',73066,'2012-08-02 06:49:41'),(45765,5901,171777,'2012-08-02 07:12:01','both the freeleech and the -10GB work perfectly for me?\r\n\r\nThe freeleech starts a green countdown at the top.',NULL,NULL),(45766,5900,171777,'2012-08-02 07:16:10','All 3 options are already available:\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=EDB9_501A0D64][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=EDB9_501A0D64&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nPressing that button will give you a listed overview of all uploads that can be sorted like a normal torrent overview. All torrents also show their respective tags.',NULL,NULL),(45767,5901,67255,'2012-08-02 07:20:19','I don\'t have it',NULL,NULL),(45769,5902,49532,'2012-08-02 07:34:12','personaally, I don\'t see why anyone would buy bling on a live server.  I\'m all for rewarding people with bling though',NULL,NULL),(45770,5901,86439,'2012-08-02 07:42:40','I also just clicked -10gb. It has NOT yet removed 10gig from my stats, but that may take the tracker a few minutes to update.\n\nThe 24hr freeleech, immediately showed me the green bar at the top of the page and as DrkNess stated, is counting down.\n\n\nEdit: Stats still not deducting the 10 gig.\n\nEdit 2: Looking at my credits, I dont think it deducted the amount either, so maybe it didnt go through at all.\n\nEdit 3: I just tried it again. It immediately deducted the 10 gig. And 4.000 credits.\n\nI have no idea why it never went through the first time.',86439,'2012-08-02 07:58:32'),(45771,5901,48010,'2012-08-02 07:43:46','I got the green countdown on 24 freeleech too - you don\'t se it at the top of the below Home Torrents etc\n\ndid you see a confirmation after you bought it ? I did\n\nThe log on your account shows you bought 24FL twice today at 06:07 and 06:18 (site time)\n\ncan\'t test buy 10GBs as my download is 0\n\nEDIT: Also it should be cumulative. I just bought 2 more 24 hour FL and now have 2 days 23h 52 minutes of FL\n\nElkid should see 1 day 23 hours\n\nOff topic but - can someone else test if it is cumulative please',48010,'2012-08-02 08:00:59'),(45772,5879,49532,'2012-08-02 08:13:59','[quote=knickers]I think the thing to remember is its Community Tagging. That doesnt simply mean that the community tag, but also the community will decide what tags to use, which are important. If the community agrees with you, then they will be tagged as English, or Russian etc naturally. Either right off the bat, or over time.\r\n\r\nKeep in mind, another option is for tags to disappear altogether. Be happy we have them.\r\n\r\nI dont plan to remove the section on language, or your reasons for it, I will just tone it down. I can see your point about its relevance and in reality there are potentially hundreds of things to tag some clips for and this would if done make a great search tool, but its not practical in reality. For example, Im sure theres at least one bloke/gal out there that is into Rollerskates or wooden spoons, but I wont be tagging it specifically unless it became more mainstream as a search. Youre missing the point about these things being voluntary. There are likely to be many torrents upped with no tags at all. Some people just dont like them and some arent affected by the same concerns in searches. But mostly there are some things that are that obscure that most wouldnt even think to list them, and I doubt anyone wants to revise a tags list with 1000+ tags (if language or origin is important, then why not rollerskates or wooden spoons) to check if it should be there every time they up a torrent. But you, and anyone else, can add them anyway. Imagine the potential for every last conceivable tag, fucked.on.concrete fucked.on.tiles fucked.on.timber and subsets, fucked.on.parquetry etc. \r\n\r\nIf certain tags were mandated, then people will either breach the rules, or not bother uploading, or leave the site. I mean even Cheggit with its tag system, there were always shitfights within torrents regarding tags.\r\n\r\nI believe given differences of opinion, past practices etc, the staff here have struck a good balance with the implementation and methodology. maybe youre not alone in your thoughts re: language. And if you\'re not, they will sooner or later be part of them anyway. Thats the power of community.\r\n\r\nIn other words, for the love of all things holy DONT ROCK THE BOAT. \r\n\r\nThankyou for your efforts in compiling it, for the explanations etc, Ive incorporated a lot of it as is, and some Ive mixed in with my own. Ive tried to write it for new to tags members, and old tag users from Cheggit. Ive tried to highlight that its benefit and extent of usefulness is determined by members and their inclusion.\r\n\r\nThe rest is up to the members to act or not.\r\n.[/quote]\r\n\r\nActuallly I (Dan) wrote the tutorial, Cassie wrote the comment you are resonding to.  \r\n\r\nThe most common reason, someone would not tag language, is mostly because it doesn\'t even occur to them, that it\'s important to someone. From my perspective, requesting language tags, enlightens them to the fact that, yes this is importsant to someone. I does not obligate them to do anything, but it it fairly simple and effeortless for them to fulfill such a request.\r\n\r\nOne thing I\'ve seen in your comment, and several other peoples comments, is the interpreation of a request as a damand.  The goal is making a precident, not a mandate.  However, I sometimes fail to remember that, while I live in a culture of requests and choice, most people live in a culture of obligation and compliance. So the mere asking can be a burden, to someone who doesn\'t recogize that the are free to do or not do, that which is requested.\r\n\r\nJust to make things clear about where I\'m comeing from, yesterday someone I just met asked me to buy them a car, I considered that a perfctly reasonable thing for them to request, and it was equally as resonable for me to say no.   Likewise, it was reasonable for a hot teenage lesbian couple, that I met at a hotspring, to ask if they could move into my house.  That time, I said yes, and 3 years later, they are still here, sharing my bed as well as my house, and posting profanity filled comments on this forum. :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(45773,5901,86439,'2012-08-02 08:16:09','1 day, 23 hrs now.\n\n1 week 2 days now.\n\nAlthough Im not sure, but I think I noticed a quirk. I had 1 week 23 hrs, clicked it again and I then had 1 week 1 day, before I clicked again and shifted it to 1 week 2 days. Seems that maybe one of those gave me 1 hour only. Im not certain that i only got one hour though, but I am certain it altered state from ?? and 23 hrs to ?? and ?? full days.',86439,'2012-08-02 08:21:37'),(45774,5901,49532,'2012-08-02 08:24:23','I bought -10GB and my stats changed immediately. I bought 24 hours freeleech, and didn\'t get a counter.  Where is it supposed to appear?',NULL,NULL),(45775,5879,86439,'2012-08-02 08:33:39','[quote=apparition]\n\nActuallly I (Dan) wrote the tutorial, Cassie wrote the comment you are resonding to.  \n\nThe most common reason, someone would not tag language, is mostly because it doesn\'t even occur to them, that it\'s important to someone. From my perspective, requesting language tags, enlightens them to the fact that, yes this is importsant to someone. I does not obligate them to do anything, but it it fairly simple and effeortless for them to fulfill such a request.\n\nOne thing I\'ve seen in your comment, and several other peoples comments, is the interpreation of a request as a damand.  The goal is making a precident, not a mandate.  However, I sometimes fail to remember that, while I live in a culture of requests and choice, most people live in a culture of obligation and compliance. So the mere asking can be a burden, to someone who doesn\'t recogize that the are free to do or not do, that which is requested.\n\nJust to make things clear about where I\'m comeing from, yesterday someone I just met asked me to buy them a car, I considered that a perfctly reasonable thing for them to request, and it was equally as resonable for me to say no.   Likewise, it was reasonable for a hot teenage lesbian couple, that I met at a hotspring, to ask if they could move into my house.  That time, I said yes, and 3 years later, they are still here, sharing my bed as well as my house, and posting profanity filled comments on this forum. :laugh:[/quote]\nI cant decipher who is posting what. But anyway.\n\nWhile its true that where a person resides and the culture of that place or individuals may effect their interpretation that is not the only concern. Although a legitimate one anyway.\n\nFor those who are aware of where they are, despite living in a free society, the site is not. I too live in a free society but also recognise limits. Its a web site, owned and run. Not a democracy. Now the site staff seem quite happy to listen and try to accommodate as much as possible or reasonable given many variables. Such as, time, effort, popular opinion, etc. Thats pretty good of them, they dont have to.\n\nUnderstand this, tags nearly didnt exist at all. The staff have their reasons for that, and their reasons why they do exist anyway. Either answer was going to upset some people, damned if they do, damned if they dont. I dont know which staff supported them, and which dont but its not the point.\n\nBut the end result was not to mandate any tags, just offer them as an option and code the site to use them. While that in itself leaves some room for tags to be less effective, they make up for that with community tagging. Perfect to someone who likes tags?, probably not. But a good compromise it is.\n\nThats my take on it anyway. Im not privy to inner circle discussion, but Ive gleaned that much.\n\n\n\nPost pics of the ladies? Ladies, post your pics.',86439,'2012-08-02 08:36:19'),(45776,5901,86439,'2012-08-02 08:39:39','Same place messages alert appears. Right up top, immediately underneath\n\n    Home     Torrents     Requests    Forums    IRC    Top 10    Rules    Help    Staff\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-78A0_501A2190.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-78A0_501A2190.jpg[/img][/url]\n\nIts a long green bar with the counter in it.\n',86439,'2012-08-02 08:41:00'),(45777,5901,49532,'2012-08-02 09:12:10','I\'m stll not getting it. not in firefox (mac or linux), not in safari, not in madori. not in chrome',NULL,NULL),(45778,5901,1243,'2012-08-02 09:13:15','[quote=knickers]1 day, 23 hrs now.\n\n1 week 2 days now.\n\nAlthough Im not sure, but I think I noticed a quirk. I had 1 week 23 hrs, clicked it again and I then had 1 week 1 day, before I clicked again and shifted it to 1 week 2 days. Seems that maybe one of those gave me 1 hour only. Im not certain that i only got one hour though, but I am certain it altered state from ?? and 23 hrs to ?? and ?? full days.[/quote]\n\nThe time will become less detailed depending on how much time you have bought. If you have over a week of freeleech then it\'s really not that important to see hours and minutes.\n\n[quote=apparition]I\'m stll not getting it. not in firefox (mac or linux), not in safari, not in madori. not in chrome[/quote]\n\nThe database says this for you:\n[code]\n+---------------------+\n| personal_freeleech  |\n+---------------------+\n| 2012-08-05 08:16:44 |\n+---------------------+\n1 row in set (0.00 sec)\n[/code]\n\nStrange that you don\'t see the green freeleech alert in the header. I\'ll flush the cache, tell me if that helps.',1243,'2012-08-02 09:25:35'),(45779,5879,49532,'2012-08-02 09:33:53','[quote=knickers]\r\n\r\nPost pics of the ladies? Ladies, post your pics.[/quote]\r\nThank you for your interest, but we value our annonimity.',NULL,NULL),(45780,5879,86439,'2012-08-02 09:54:58','Sad panda :(',NULL,NULL),(45781,5901,48010,'2012-08-02 10:02:49','[quote=apparition]I\'m stll not getting it. not in firefox (mac or linux), not in safari, not in madori. not in chrome[/quote]\r\n\r\nI see it in firefox 13.0.1 running on xubuntu 12.04',NULL,NULL),(45782,5901,49532,'2012-08-02 11:21:46','[quote=Lanz]\nThe database says this for you:\n[code]\n+---------------------+\n| personal_freeleech  |\n+---------------------+\n| 2012-08-05 08:16:44 |\n+---------------------+\n1 row in set (0.00 sec)\n[/code]\n\nStrange that you don\'t see the green freeleech alert in the header. I\'ll flush the cache, tell me if that helps.[/quote]\nflushing the cace didn\'t seem to help.\n[quote=Dave][quote=apparition]I\'m stll not getting it. not in firefox (mac or linux), not in safari, not in madori. not in chrome[/quote]\n\nI see it in firefox 13.0.1 running on xubuntu 12.04[/quote]\nI\'m on firefox 14.0.1\n\nUpdate: I logged out, used a bad password to get a log in error, then logged in.  When I logged in, I had a red message bar saying \"You have 1 new message\", and over it I had the green bar saying \"Freeleech for 2 days, 19 hours\".  When I read my messages, both the red and green bar disapeared, instead of just the red one.',49532,'2012-08-02 12:32:19'),(45783,5899,171777,'2012-08-02 14:00:46','I am working on a guide to testing right now. I\'ll post it in the staff forum for review before it get\'s thrown into the insectarium for the bug hunters.',NULL,NULL),(45784,5901,1507,'2012-08-02 14:01:35',':dunno:\r\n\r\n[b]I\'ve added -100GB download to my account...  Bought -10GB, -5GB, -1GB, 3x 24hr Free Leech, and it all shows in the log and up at the top correctly...  I have a red bar that says \"Freeleech for 2 days, 23 hours\", so it appears to be working just fine for me...\r\n\r\nUsing Opera browser....\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:dunno:\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45785,5901,1507,'2012-08-02 14:06:45',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]To bad there is no way to override my 3 days of Free Leech now...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nSet it back to normal...  :dunno:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:hmmm:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45786,5902,1507,'2012-08-02 14:13:52','[quote=mepow]I like the bling idea. But byuing medals for bonus points seems wrong to me. (dont get me wrong i always max out on the seeding, so its good for me.) =)\r\n\r\nMy first though was having medals for other stuff. Like giving medals for torrents posted, 1 or 5 torrents gives the first medal and then it can expand with stars when more torrents are posted or some other simple feature. And likewise with forum post, maybe a request medal (for filling requests) and so on. Collage medal, tagging medal and so on. So you can have that one guy that always add tags to stuff who gets a super tagging master bling medal for his effort, or a super poster that get a medal for his and so on. Ofc you can have a seeding medal that is bound to the earned bonus points and it would represent a good seeder. And ofc a medal for those who takes the time to write thanks. =)\r\n\r\nThis is just an idea im trowing out there regarding the bling. Seems a lot more fun that way, atleast to me. And the members would get some bling for their effort in the community. And maybe it would be a reminder for the community to contribute in all aspekts of the community.\r\n\r\nAny other input on this?[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:smile1:\r\n\r\n[b]Yes, there are other medals/ribbons for different categories, awards, etc., that are automagically given out when one reaches the plateau and qualifies....  Others are awarded by staff...\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-08-02 14:19:38'),(45787,5902,1507,'2012-08-02 14:17:36','[quote=apparition]personaally, I don\'t see why anyone would buy bling on a live server.  I\'m all for rewarding people with bling though[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:smile1:\r\n\r\n[b]Well, this was suggested and so we went along with it as some members really liked the idea of being able to buy bling to show off with....  :laugh:\r\n\r\nThey\'re just jealous because no one but me can have the \'usb award\"  [img]http://empornium.mooo.com/static/common/badges/usb-award.png[/img] ...   :tease: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:laugh:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45788,5891,1507,'2012-08-02 14:25:00',':hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]If you close the search center, you can hide the categories...  you\'ll hide everything else as well, but at least it will look clean...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :giraffe: ',NULL,NULL),(45789,5879,1507,'2012-08-02 14:37:56','[b]tags....\r\n\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adsMfrvr.png[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :sigh: ',NULL,NULL),(45790,5902,94804,'2012-08-02 15:33:01','whadda ya mean? ;)\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=B466_501A8200][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=B466_501A8200&jpg[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(45791,5904,171777,'2012-08-02 15:59:20','Just something concerning Staff PMs. If we respond to a uploader respons stating that his upload was fixed and this is either accepted of not accepted, what do we do with the PM itself? Resolve it? \r\n\r\nI have done this with some of the test reports I made of my own crappy uploads just to test the feature but what to do when the site goes live (not that that will happen yet)?',NULL,NULL),(45792,5905,171777,'2012-08-02 16:02:33','[size=3][b]Guide to effective bug testing[/b][/size]\n\nThis guide is meant to be a good starting point for any tester. It contains some basic guidelines to testing and bug hunting aswell as some things that we already found. If you think that this guide is not complete or if it is incorrect please send me a PM or reply in this thread.\n\n[size=3][b]How to submit a bug report[/b][/size]\n\nLet\'s start with the most important information first. What do do when you find a bug. \n\nTo tell us about it we need specific information:\n\n\nNow for some simple guidelines when you want to share you bug with the coders.\n \n[*]Search the forum to see if the bug is already known.\n[*]If the bug is indeed new then start a new topic. As a topic name please use following: Location - Desription of bug. With location I mean things like [Forum] or [Torrent Details]. Example: [Torrent Upload] - My cover image is not accepted.\n[*]Fill the topic with as much information as you possibly can. Use images if it is hard to describe what is happening. Be sure to atleast give the information as noted in the following 3 bullets.\n[*][b]The page url[/b] For example the url for the browse torrents page is [code]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php[/code] which when written in a post becomes: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php\n[*][b]What is wrong[/b] Tell us what the problem is, and if applicable the way you expect it to work.\n[*][b]How to reproduce it[/b] Please include enough information so that we can reproduce the bug ourselves. Reproduce it yourself first if possible, and make a note of what actions produce the bug.\n[*]Keep track of your topic (potentially subscribe to it). Coders might require additional information or another tester might want to do additional tests working together with you.\n \n[size=3][b]How to hunt for bugs[/b][/size]\n \nThere is no set way in which one can hunt for a bug. The reason for this is that no one knows where the bugs are located. There are however a few simple pointers that you can follow while hunting:\n \n[*][b]Work systematically[/b] In other words don\'t go clicking haphazardly because that way it is almost impossible to reproduce what you did when things go wrong.\n[*][b]Test things multiple times[/b] A result could always be a fluke. This goes for both bugs and correct functionality. If you test something several times and the same thing always happens then you either have a bug that you can reproduce or you have correct behaviour that you can vouch for.\n[*][b]Test again at a later time[/b] Some bugs are easy to fix, others are a lot more complicated. To ensure that a bug is truly gone or that an old bug doesn\'t reappear it is always advisable to test features again a week later and yet again the next week. It would suck if 2 weeks after going live a bug reappears because it  is date triggered and happens every 2 weeks or something.\n[*][b]Don\'t assume anything[/b] As they say: \"Assumption is the mother of all fuck-ups\". If you think something works then please make sure that it does.\n \n \nPlease note that this list probably is not complete and is therefor subject to change. Take a look every once in a while to see if there were changes. Who knows the uploaders might have noticed that a certain step is not neccessary and you are still doing all that work for nothing! \n\n\n\n[size=3][b]End of guide so far.[/b][/size]\nOk this was just to get the ball rolling. Propose changes to the guide, expansions I don\'t care. Let\'s just make it in such a way that it will be helpful to the hunters and make those hunters more helpful to the coders\n\nNo one with any comments so far? Come on people...',171777,'2012-08-05 19:14:53'),(45793,5902,1507,'2012-08-02 16:06:02',':laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]usb banner huh....????  :hmmm:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(45794,5902,70679,'2012-08-02 16:06:58','The I pooped in my pants award\r\n\r\n :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(45795,5902,1507,'2012-08-02 16:09:06',' :sigh: \r\n\r\n[b]omg....  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:laugh:',NULL,NULL),(45796,5879,171777,'2012-08-02 16:10:02','Just out of curiosity but if an apprentice uploads a torrent is he THEN allowed to add more tags like any normal uploader or does his apprentice status mess that up (can\'t test this since I am above apprentice right now)?',NULL,NULL),(45797,5901,67255,'2012-08-02 17:09:41','I log out and log in again and nope no green bar tag on top. Using firefox 14.0.1\n\n\nNo problem when using internet explorer to log in the first time the green bar and the red bar appeared on top but after browsing the website it vanished again from the top (I did not click the two top bars)\n\nAfter using Internet Explorer, I logged in with chrome and the two top bars where not show',67255,'2012-08-02 19:03:51'),(45798,5904,84499,'2012-08-02 17:26:27','\r\n\r\nwhen you accept it it should auto-resolve, maybe i didnt add that bit though because that dosent happen atm :hmmm:\r\n\r\nit does auto-resolve it if its rejected and ends up deleted. I think logically it should only remain open if the status is warned or pending, if it is resolved as okay it should resolve it self the same as it does when its deleted. I\'ll change it at some point :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(45799,5904,171777,'2012-08-02 17:32:08','Logically speaking I would say that the next time the uploader fixes his torrent he would send another Staff PM thus resulting in 2 messages for the same torrent.',NULL,NULL),(45800,5902,70679,'2012-08-02 17:54:35','But seriously I am also of the opinion that trinkets and knick knacks should be awarded not bought...\r\n\r\nI prefer to use credits to help not too bad users who got themselves in trouble. The ones that come to IRC of course.',NULL,NULL),(45801,5901,94952,'2012-08-02 18:16:41','Freeleechbar does not show for me. Checked FF 14.0.1, Chrome and IE9. Both css.',NULL,NULL),(45802,5906,70679,'2012-08-02 18:20:58','not sure if it is a bug or a feature... the bottom link on my signature should be red.',70679,'2012-08-02 18:21:28'),(45803,5907,70679,'2012-08-02 18:37:07','title says all',NULL,NULL),(45804,5904,84499,'2012-08-02 18:59:30','\r\nit does send another message but its part of the same conversation. one conversation per torrent is enough i think.',NULL,NULL),(45805,5906,84499,'2012-08-02 19:04:07','[code]\n[url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2763][color=#FF0000]link[/color][/url]\n\n[/code]\n\n\n[url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2763][color=#FF0000]link[/color][/url]\n\n\nuse sparingly... ',84499,'2012-08-02 19:06:18'),(45806,5902,84499,'2012-08-02 19:22:05','\r\n\r\nThere are a whole bunch of medals and awards that are earned or awarded.\r\n\r\n\r\nIf you dont want to buy bling dont buy it, all the best medals are awarded anyway so...',NULL,NULL),(45807,5901,84499,'2012-08-02 19:35:05','\r\nfixed.',NULL,NULL),(45808,5901,67255,'2012-08-02 19:40:37','Thanks!',NULL,NULL),(45809,5906,70679,'2012-08-02 20:20:19','thx.... works  :smile1:  :gjob: ',NULL,NULL),(45810,5854,1243,'2012-08-02 20:25:12','Thanks everyone for testing.',NULL,NULL),(45811,5902,70679,'2012-08-02 20:25:42','so... just poop in your pants  :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(45812,5908,1243,'2012-08-02 20:31:48','Yep, finally got some time to sit down and rewrite the slot code a bit. A slot will now last for 14 days and then get removed. The old code had several problems, both with how the slots where updated on the tracker but also had limitations on the backend (ocelot). This should now be fixed, but frankly I haven\'t tested it much so things will probably show up. Please try it and report what you find. :)',NULL,NULL),(45813,5907,48010,'2012-08-02 20:38:28','[quote=barumba]title says all[/quote]\r\n\r\nI could add it to the \"welcome to the new site guide\" which I will write soon (waiting on some staff comments before I start on it)\r\n\r\nLater the guide will have a discussion thread for comments or input too',NULL,NULL),(45814,5904,48010,'2012-08-02 20:59:03','@drkNess put up a shit torrent with no screens or pres and I will happily test it - make it clear that it is a test for staff or some DH will try to DL it \r\n\r\n@mifune if they send a Staff PM or a second one does it add to the time before deletion or is it hard-coded and doesn\'t change?\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45815,5901,94952,'2012-08-02 21:16:32','[quote=mifune]fixed.[/quote]\r\nFixed, indeed! Thanks Mifune for all the hard work. :yaydance: ',NULL,NULL),(45816,5619,94952,'2012-08-02 21:18:05','[quote=l3af]Maybe it\'s nothing but I read somewhere that this new site uses an old image of the old site. Maybe you have changed the passwords since then? I could log in and I have same password since start.[/quote]\r\n\r\nNope. Same password for a loooong time :)',NULL,NULL),(45817,5908,48010,'2012-08-02 21:21:46','[quote=Lanz]Yep, finally got some time to sit down and rewrite the slot code a bit. A slot will now last for 14 days and then get removed. The old code had several problems, both with how the slots where updated on the tracker but also had limitations on the backend (ocelot). This should now be fixed, but frankly I haven\'t tested it much so things will probably show up. Please try it and report what you find. :)[/quote]\r\nI don\'t see my slot history in