wnload our property illegal\" then system ops people can just shrug and say \"we dont host no files.. but we love your work  :mad: \" since magnet links are mainly just code n hashtags. ',NULL,NULL),(45855,5902,47234,'2012-08-03 13:33:23','I think we still need to design and decide on all those awards before we create a list.  Im sure its on the to-do list somewhere :lol:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45856,5902,85111,'2012-08-03 13:57:43','yeh since this is the only a suggestion thread, bling i wanna see is: \n\n[*]Upload 100/250/500+ torrents Bling\n[*]Fast Seeder Bling\n[*]Notorious Leecher\n[*]Request Filler Bling (can only be gifted from one user to another)\n[*]Staff / Vip Bling\n[*]Idiot Bling (manually added by staff)\n[*]HQ 720p/1080p torrent Uploaders\n[*]Regular Uploader bling\n\n\n\n',85111,'2012-08-03 14:00:18'),(45857,5910,49532,'2012-08-03 14:24:30','[quote=Clownius]Holy shit you guys go all out on the tag stuff.................\n\nThankfully for everyone i dont code (or the server would be a smoking mess :lol:) but i can see massive amounts of time and effort going into a small suggestion like that and then even worse more effort going into maintaining it....\n\nRemember no one here is paid and we dont have infinite time to do this stuff.  Some days we even struggle to check all the torrents and catch up on the forums.  Never mind updating tag databases.[/quote]\n\nAre you referring to my suggestion or mepows\'s (which should be in it\'s own thread NOT this one).\nmepows\'s suggestion is certainly a coder\'s challenge, to say the least.\n\nOn the other hand, my suggestion is fairly simple to code (mostly it uses, what I expect is existing code, and runs it through a loop.).  \n\nIf given access to the current source code and database structures, I\'d code it myself (though it could take a while, because I don\'t have large blocks of spare time, to devote to it.) \n',49532,'2012-08-03 14:27:22'),(45858,5902,41468,'2012-08-03 14:27:27','I like the bling idea\r\nits