nd so on. Then a form could be started and a check box could be printed out and also a text input box. Then just check the boxes on the search result and add the tags at a text box. A few lines of code should do it. \r\n\r\nHere is my research on the subject just by checking the page.\r\nThe add tag formula, example ?id=1337 (select the most 1337 torrent) &did=3 (this on tells the server you did something, in this case added a tag) &addedtag=boobs (will give you a new tag boobs i the torrent with that specific id). So most of the functions already exist. The &did=3 however don\'t seem to work adding more then one tag in a go, so you would need another &did=x or call the function multiple times. Or maybe the &did=3 is not working as intended. Will see if there is any report on this.',NULL,NULL),(45869,5914,73066,'2012-08-03 15:21:38','Started checking around with the add new tags function (the text box under the voting tag system)\r\nI donÂ´t know if its working as intended or not, i tried adding two tags at the same time. It removed the space in between.\r\n\r\nLink (with action)\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35220&did=3&synonym=one%20two&addedtag=onetwo\r\nI entered \"one two\" in the box, but i gave me the combined answer and added it to the database. I was then unable to remove the wrong tag myself.\r\n\r\nIs this working as intended?',NULL,NULL),(45870,5910,171777,'2012-08-03 15:29:05','Why force feed the community loads and loads of tags? The torrent overview pages do not get anymore transparent if there are 30 tags for every torrent.\n\n[b]edit:[/b] And I do think that this is rather labor intensive to maintain. You have no idea how many people make spelling mistakes on a daily basis resulting in more shitty tags that are only used once but will still be checked by the automated system and thus have to be pruned...',171777,'2012-08-03 15:30:45'),(45871,5914,47234,'2012-08-03 15:30:04','It might need a note to add tags one at a time.  It looks to me like thats they way it should be done.\r\n\r\nI tested it and yeah....',NULL,NULL),(45872,5902,73066,'2012-08-03 15:38:42','Yeah, my basic tough was to use bling as a incentive, some fun bling just to keep the community active, to comment, to upload and try to contribute in a lot of different aspects. Buying bling for credits seems wrong, bling should be awarded for doing stuff not just keeping the computer on. Sure you could have a bling seeder medal for those who are kind enough to keep a seedbox, or keeping their computer on so others can download at great speeds. But uploading torrents and commenting and helping to categorize those torrents should be the main aspects of the site, and in my opinion should be rewarded with bling if there is to exist such a thing.',NULL,NULL),(45873,5910,73066,'2012-08-03 16:03:36','(Defending the tag system)\r\nWithout tags we would have only categories, lets say iÂ´m into teen movies with redhead i click teens and 2001 results, its going to take a while to find. Or could i with the help of tags get down the result, i do a tag search on redheads that would give me around 40 results. It can see how tags are useful and how a good taging system will be good for emp.\r\n\r\nIf the tagsystem is labor intensive then users are uploading stuff to the system, and that whatÂ´s emp is all about. The users uploading stuff that others can find. And helping people find the right stuff they are after should be a priority. Yes the overview gets messed up with to many tags, but the search function that help people finding specific stuff gets more accurate. IÂ´m starting a new tagging tread instead of hijacking this one. Seems we are away from the subject.',NULL,NULL),(45874,5915,73066,'2012-08-03 16:22:03','Taging seems to be an issue on the site, just raising it to debate or something. The taging right now is kind of chaotic as everyone knows. One problem with the tagging system and the first question i had when i saw it for the first time. Where is the list of approved tags? Should i write dp double.penetration, doublepenetration, oral, blowjob bj, cunnulingus, sexysite.com or sexysite? A lot of questions and no answers.\r\n\r\nIf we are going to categorize stuff so everyone can read and access it, a standard should be made. The problem is that everyone is contributing to the categorizing of the torrents but there is no standard of tags. So the users uses all kind of different tags that they can make up. pussy.piercing nipple.piercing i could probably categorize some torrents with 40-50 tags, describing actors settings and other stuff. these tags are noting wrong, if you ask me. The problem occurs when another user categories a similar torrent and used count.percing breast.piercing then the taging has failed.\r\n\r\nI did a narrow test, bondage bound tied are all in the main site, each one giving only a few results. (tried this with teen clicked in the category box) if all of these had only one tag, then the taging system would be stronger in my opinion.\r\n\r\nI\'m sure there are other concerns with the tagins system, but that the taging system is good for the site is hard to close your eyes too. So lifting these problems to the surface and try and solving them should be good for the community. \r\n\r\nAny other input on the dangers on taging? Does it lead to youth abortion? Or teenage smoking?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45875,5914,49532,'2012-08-03 16:24:47','Why do it one at a time?  The original upload adds multiple tags, it should be consistent.',NULL,NULL),(45876,5910,171777,'2012-08-03 16:32:14','the great part about the search mechanism of the site is that if you search for teen and redhead it will find these torrents. no matter if they were tagged that way or not. Now don\'t get me wrong. I use tags but I see no reason to tag stuff like whether or not there was a potted plant in the scene and what not. IMHO there is a rather select list of things that are worth tagging and using a list like that would result in torrents with 10 or less tags overall while still being correctly represented by those tags.\r\n\r\nPersonally I prefer the way a normal search engine works. If a torrent description contains the word redhead then it will appear when you search for redheads, tagged as such or not. This is also the way that the search engine of this site works and it technically makes tags overall a \"nice to have\" feature but definetly not a \"must have\" feature.',NULL,NULL),(45877,5915,171777,'2012-08-03 16:32:47','Quoting myself from other thread:\r\n\r\n[quote=DrkNess]\r\nthe great part about the search mechanism of the site is that if you search for teen and redhead it will find these torrents. no matter if they were tagged that way or not. Now don\'t get me wrong. I use tags but I see no reason to tag stuff like whether or not there was a potted plant in the scene and what not. IMHO there is a rather select list of things that are worth tagging and using a list like that would result in torrents with 10 or less tags overall while still being correctly represented by those tags.\r\n\r\nPersonally I prefer the way a normal search engine works. If a torrent description contains the word redhead then it will appear when you search for redheads, tagged as such or not. This is also the way that the search engine of this site works and it technically makes tags overall a \"nice to have\" feature but definetly not a \"must have\" feature.\r\n[/quote]',NULL,NULL),(45878,5915,73066,'2012-08-03 16:40:42','Yeah the normal search function of the site find those that have in the description text. But only if the uploader mentioned in text somewhere that it was a redhead in the movie. The users cant edit the text of the torrent but now they can edit tags. And if the uploader didn\'t mention there was a redhead some user might add the tag. And my luck if finding redhead teens would increase with the new taging system.',NULL,NULL),(45879,5915,86439,'2012-08-03 16:41:46','There will be an official list, there will be a synonym list too, there just isnt yet. Well there is to test with, but its very short.\n\nRelax!',86439,'2012-08-03 16:46:56'),(45880,5910,49532,'2012-08-03 16:47:34','[quote=DrkNess]Why force feed the community loads and loads of tags? The torrent overview pages do not get anymore transparent if there are 30 tags for every torrent.\n\n[b]edit:[/b] And I do think that this is rather labor intensive to maintain. You have no idea how many people make spelling mistakes on a daily basis resulting in more shitty tags that are only used once but will still be checked by the automated system and thus have to be pruned...[/quote]\n\nThat\'s precisely the beauty of this system.  If someone  (or several people) tags 100 torrents with brea.benet.  You can just search  for brea.benet, click the select all check box  put brea.benet in the remove field, and brea.bennett in the add field.  Hit the submit button and your done.\n\nEven better, also have bulk synonym replacement:  search  for brea.benet, click the select all check box  put brea.benet in the synonym field, and brea.bennett in the maintag field.  Hit the submit button and all instances of brea.benet are replaced with brea.bennett, and brea.benet is added to the synonyms, so it will be replaced on each additional attempt to add it.\n\nNow consider how it is now, mods have to select each torrent one at a time, delete brea.benet, add brea.bennett, the go to the next torrent, and do it again 100 times.  By far thats much more work for the mods.\n\n[quote=mepow]Yeah sorry about that apparition. I have been coding for the last 16-17 years and coded php and databases since 2001 so my i might have a different opinion on whats a big project and whats not.[/quote]\n I wrote m first piece of code in 1980. It may not be a big projject if that\'s your full time job. But as an unpaid spare time project, for someone elses website, its alot more hours than I\'d consider.\n\n[quote=mepow]Here is my research on the subject just by checking the page.\nThe add tag formula, example ?id=1337 (select the most 1337 torrent) &did=3 (this on tells the server you did something, in this case added a tag) &addedtag=boobs (will give you a new tag boobs i the torrent with that specific id).[/quote]\n\nOH NO! not the dreaded BOOBS tag.  I was hoping it would be :shoot2:  hunted to exinction by now  \n:lol:',49532,'2012-08-03 17:08:23'),(45881,5910,73066,'2012-08-03 17:15:34','[quote=apparition]I wrote m first piece of code in 1980. It may not be a big projject if that\'s your full time job. But as an unpaid spare time project, for someone elses website, its alot more hours than I\'d consider.[/quote]\nhaha, i wasn\'t even born in 1981 =)\n\n[quote=apparition]OH NO! not the dreaded BOOBS tag.  I was hoping it would be :shoot2:  hunted to exinction by now  \n:lol:[/quote]\nOfc, the first thing i was planning on doing was checking all torrents and adding the boob tag on all girls with boobs =)',73066,'2012-08-03 17:17:16'),(45882,5910,84499,'2012-08-03 17:19:08','\r\n\r\nthere are official tags and a synonym replacer already: [url=/torrents.php?action=tag_synonyms][/url]\r\n\r\nfor staff there are tools for doing mass conversions.\r\n\r\n\r\na mass add tool would need a lot of safegaurds/logging etc. and I dont think we need it.  We do not allow users to delete tags so we are not going to implement a mass delete system.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are bascially in feature lock now - unless somehting is vital for useability or very quick and simple to implement it is unlikely to fly.',NULL,NULL),(45883,5910,48010,'2012-08-03 17:56:02','[quote=mifune]We are bascially in feature lock now - unless somehting is vital for useability or very quick and simple to implement it is unlikely to fly.[/quote]\r\ncool, good to here that - not relevant in the thread but who cares - I don\'t',NULL,NULL),(45884,5910,84499,'2012-08-03 18:03:01','\r\n[quote=Dave][quote=mifune]We are bascially in feature lock now - unless somehting is vital for useability or very quick and simple to implement it is unlikely to fly.[/quote]\r\ncool, good to here that - not relevant in the thread but who cares - I don\'t[/quote]\r\n\r\nhaha in theory we were in feature lock before... but now we are serious!\r\n\r\n[quote=mepow]Here is my research on the subject just by checking the page.\r\nThe add tag formula, example ?id=1337 (select the most 1337 torrent) &did=3 (this on tells the server you did something, in this case added a tag) &addedtag=boobs (will give you a new tag boobs i the torrent with that specific id).[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nI dont know if you are joking around here but no, thats not what those things do :lol: \r\n\r\napart from the id=value which displays the correct page the other url stuff is just cosmetic stuff for reporting back to the user.\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(45885,5915,84499,'2012-08-03 18:03:58','\n\n[url=/torrents.php?action=tag_synonyms][/url]\n\n\n\nI have only added a handful of synonmyns so far (and will not add any more until we are live as they have to be added to an exisitng database to correctly work the process of turning tags into synonyms... and this local db will be trashed and replaced with a new import from the main site when we go live) but the synonym replacer will do most of what you want... I think.\n\n\n\nto test: try adding the tag \'big.boobs\' to some torrents.',84499,'2012-08-03 18:09:23'),(45886,5911,48010,'2012-08-03 18:32:08','[quote=knickers]Useless tag, read the tag rules. It has nothing to do with the content.\r\n\r\nIn before USB\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-4A8F_501BC5AB.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-4A8F_501BC5AB.jpg[/img][/url][/quote]\r\nLOL\r\n\r\nwait for usb to come by',NULL,NULL),(45888,5911,70679,'2012-08-03 18:48:14','personally really sick and tired of this cheggit mourning and nostalgia. Is over is gone get over it, move on.\r\n\r\n[IMG]http://i1261.photobucket.com/albums/ii581/barumba1/StopThisInsanity.gif[/IMG]\r\n\r\n[IMG]http://i1261.photobucket.com/albums/ii581/barumba1/fluch.gif[/IMG]',NULL,NULL),(45892,5911,48010,'2012-08-03 19:08:08','[quote=barumba]personally really sick and tired of this cheggit mourning and nostalgia. Is over is gone get over it, move on.\r\n\r\n[IMG]http://i1261.photobucket.com/albums/ii581/barumba1/StopThisInsanity.gif[/IMG]\r\n\r\n[IMG]http://i1261.photobucket.com/albums/ii581/barumba1/fluch.gif[/IMG][/quote]\r\n\r\nI agree 100% this is emp (from the old emp and ptna). We are not going to change or bend over backwards to make a cheg tag site. It has been posted in many other threads. This is the way we do things here so accept it or find somewhere else where you can tag bitch to your hearts content. I\'m getting really bored reading all there tag threads :wink: \r\n\r\nSite policy is set already and it\'s not going to change. ',NULL,NULL),(45893,5910,48010,'2012-08-03 19:10:02','[quote=mifune][quote=Dave][quote=mifune]We are bascially in feature lock now - unless somehting is vital for useability or very quick and simple to implement it is unlikely to fly.[/quote]\r\ncool, good to here that - not relevant in the thread but who cares - I don\'t[/quote]\r\n\r\nhaha in theory we were in feature lock before... but now we are serious![/quote]\r\n\r\nyou didn\'t tell us :grin:',NULL,NULL),(45894,5915,48010,'2012-08-03 19:10:45','we are getting bored with all the tag threads - site policy is set and won\'t change',NULL,NULL),(45895,5910,1243,'2012-08-03 19:13:11','[quote=mepow]Yeah sorry about that apparition. I have been coding for the last 16-17 years and coded php and databases since 2001 so my i might have a different opinion on whats a big project and whats not.[/quote]\r\n\r\nTime is limited, I struggle finding time doing this at all. RL is getting in the way.',NULL,NULL),(45899,5899,51063,'2012-08-03 19:40:04','If you guys want I can put together a torrent for testing and ask for everyone to grab it whether they want it or not.  I was thinking of the complete works of Shakespeare (or something similar that is in the public domain) that would result in a relatively large torrent to get a real load test going.',NULL,NULL),(45900,5863,51063,'2012-08-03 20:08:40','Yes there are ways of doing what you are suggesting DrkNess.  But the method which you are suggesting is not the best way to do things.  I am not going to get into the details here but there are far more efficient ways of doing what you suggest.\r\n\r\nWhen Lanz is ready to think about a cheat script he knows where to find me LOL.  It is really pretty simple to have a simple one.  The one we have at PB is very very sophisticated and judging from the explanations we get for people cheating it is far more sophisticated than other sites use (because users are surprised when we say . . . that explanation is totally bogus or we have even had users say \"but they bought that excuse on my 3 or 5 or whatever other sites\" and we say well our data says otherwise).\r\n\r\nHonestly the less people know about the details of a cheat detection script the better.  I will say that there are features built into the new PB that were only implemented to help detect cheaters.  I do not see the need to do that here but those are things that I can explain to Lanz and he can make the final decision.\r\n\r\nEven without the specific features of the site that makes things easier there are pretty easy simple ways to catch the buggers.  The bottom line is that the more data you have the better.\r\n\r\nThe biggest issue is that going over the cheat reports is a very very daunting task.  Even with all of the sophistication of the system we have at PB it generally takes about 5 minutes per new report to confirm or deny a cheat.  Again I am glad to help Lanz with the design of the script and once that is sorted I am glad to help teach all of the staff here how to interpret the data . . . but it is going to be a lot of extra work for staff.  On a closed site like PB where we get something like 5 or 10 new members a week at the most and we have ways of eliminating many of the false positives it still takes about an hour a day to go over the new cheats every day.  When there is a back log (like from me being on vacation) it can easily take 10 or 12 days of 2 hours a day to get caught back up.\r\n\r\nIf it sounds like I am trying to scare you all . . . that is because I am.  You need everyone pitching in to keep on top of cheaters.  It will make the site a much better place but it really is a huge amount of work.  The nice part about open signups is that there is always an influx of new users who are potential staffers so that helps.  The downside is that a lot of users are far more likely to cheat because they know that a new account is just a new IP address and e-mail address away.  When you start banning folks you will start getting folks from the cheating boards who will sign up for an account just to test the settings of the cheat script to find out the settings/boundaries and report back to their mates.  It really is a battle.  But let us face it the point on an open invite site is to eliminate the casual cheater.  The really sophisticated cheaters are very very hard to catch and quite frankly on an open invite site they are not worth going after . . . they all have VPN\'s and boatloads of e-mail addresses the only thing you can do to those folks is to keep squashing them like bugs until they get bored/frustrated signing up for a new account every few days/weeks/months.\r\n\r\nAgain when Lanz is ready I will give him a brain dump of the features required to make the job easier.  Those scripts that you linked are a good starting point but honestly they are lacking a lot of important features.  Using a canned script that is publicly available is ok for a small closed site but they will just not work for a site of this size without burning out staff at an astounding rate.',NULL,NULL),(45901,5744,51063,'2012-08-03 20:16:40','[quote=eimaimpala][quote=mifune]\r\n\r\nSay hi and ask any questions you have here.\r\n\r\nI can answer the first one... \r\n\r\nQ: what do FLS do?\r\nA: we dont know yet.\r\n\r\n\r\n:lol:[/quote]\r\n\r\nWell, this kinda sums up the whole thing doesn\'t it? :laugh:\r\nFrom my private tracker experience so far, \r\nFirst Line Support is volunteering to answer PM\'s about stuff, to ease the staff\'s load of work.\r\nFrom software stuff and coding, to simpler stuff like ripping, uploading, where to find covers etc. And other stuff, that people don\'t want to post in the forums, but isn\'t that important to bother a staff member.\r\n\r\nAs for access to staff messages and resolving reports, I don\'t know. I have a feeling these would be better off handled by actual staff members. \r\n\r\nSome suggestions/observations:\r\nThis is the FLS section of IPT\'s staff page:\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=8769_500A75CC][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=8769_500A75CC[/img][/url]\r\nPussytorrents, on the other hand, lists only names and the \"PM\" button.\r\nThere\'s a lot of text in IPT\'s section, but that\'s because of IPT being a general tracker, that offers help with OS and other stuff.\r\nSince Emp is xxx-only, only tracker/torrent related stuff could be listed. maybe there\'s no need to mention what every FLS member is familiar with (like in Pussytorrents\' FLS section), because xxx-only trackers don\'t have that many issues, as opposed to general trackers, but then again, I personally don\'t know much about connectability issues. \r\nSo, maybe the FLS people could make a post with a list of stuff they know their way around?\r\nOr a staff member can make a list of things, and FLS members say what they can answer questions for?\r\n\r\nAlso, [b][color=#FF0000]note a foreign language FLS members speak[/color][/b], so people can address someone in their native tongue.\r\nAnd maybe [b][color=#FF0000]a green/red thingy that shows if someone is online/offline[/color][/b]?[/quote]\r\n\r\nThere are some great suggestions here.  I have highlighted those I think will be extremely useful.  I know adding another table and code to fill it in etc is a big PITA but it will really make a huge difference to non or poor English speakers and it will endear the tracker to those users and it will gain the tracker users from that country as word gets out that hey they have staffers that speak our language and who are very willing to help out.\r\n\r\nIt will suck for say someone like Lanz if he is the only user who speaks Swedish but it will be a big plus for the site.',NULL,NULL),(45902,5635,51063,'2012-08-03 20:22:40','I am trying to catch up here (after vacation and everything) and there is no way I am reading 54 posts can someone who has been following this thread sum it up in 500 words or so?',NULL,NULL),(45903,5635,48010,'2012-08-03 20:32:46','[quote=GaryE]I am trying to catch up here (after vacation and everything) and there is no way I am reading 54 posts can someone who has been following this thread sum it up in 500 words or so?[/quote]\r\n\r\nWe have decided the system already and are now in fixed state as per mifune - is there any need to read them ?',NULL,NULL),(45904,5635,1243,'2012-08-03 20:52:16','The credits is not in a fixed state, it needs further tweaking.\n\nWhat we have been talking about is two different ways to give out credits:\nFlat rate: 1 torrent/h = 1 credit/h\npro: easy system to remember\ncon: needs a max torrent limit or some users will get flooded with credits (max 60 has been suggested)\n\nA diminishing return formula\nFew torrents give up to 2-3 credits per torrent, many torrents gives you just a fraction of a credit.\npro: makes every seeded torrent count but gives you less credits/torrent for every torrent you add.\ncon: Not as easy to explain, but still better than the current system on emp.me (might need to also have a limit but can be set higher)\n\nAfter this is decided, we need to adjust the prices to fit the new model.\n',1243,'2012-08-03 20:53:01'),(45905,5635,113711,'2012-08-03 20:57:26','[quote=Typhoon20]An option to donate credits to uploaders would be nice. Basically a thank you in credits.\r\nOr/And an extra 1000 or such for sharing a torrent with certain rules like the more seeders the more credits and encourage seeding and also add some rules to encourage people don\'t share awful ones just to collect credits.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI love the idea but I think it would be interesting if using the \"Thank You\" button by the downloaders was the method by which credits were given.  This way, the more epic the upload, the more credits you get.  Also, those \"awful\" uploads wouldn\'t get anything for their garbage.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45906,5863,171777,'2012-08-03 20:57:41','the linked scripts were just something I googled. Nothing I really gave any thought on a personal level. I don\'t know enough about what a tracker can see to really make a well argumented claim about what would and would not work. Still it is good that there is someone that can help set up a good anti cheat system.',NULL,NULL),(45907,5635,48010,'2012-08-03 20:58:37','[quote=Lanz]The credits is not in a fixed state, it needs further tweaking.\r\n\r\nWhat we have been talking about is two different ways to give out credits:\r\nFlat rate: 1 torrent/h = 1 credit/h\r\npro: easy system to remember\r\ncon: needs a max torrent limit or some users will get flooded with credits (max 60 has been suggested)\r\n\r\nA diminishing return formula\r\nFew torrents give up to 2-3 credits per torrent, many torrents gives you just a fraction of a credit.\r\npro: makes every seeded torrent count but gives you less credits/torrent for every torrent you add.\r\ncon: Not as easy to explain, but still better than the current system on emp.me (might need to also have a limit but can be set higher)\r\n\r\nAfter this is decided, we need to adjust the prices to fit the new model.[/quote]\r\n\r\napologies to Gary and Lanz\r\n\r\nsorry for my misunderstanding of the site status',NULL,NULL),(45908,5744,171777,'2012-08-03 21:01:01','Well for me you can note down that I speak English, Dutch and German.',NULL,NULL),(45909,5635,1243,'2012-08-03 21:02:44','[quote=Dave]\r\napologies to Gary and Lanz\r\n\r\nsorry for my misunderstanding of the site status[/quote]\r\n\r\nHey, no problem. We have just left this particular thing hanging lately. But overall you are right, we need to focus on tweek mode/bugs now so we can get this thing done. :D',NULL,NULL),(45910,5911,51063,'2012-08-03 21:04:33','As soon as the new site goes live (If I am still staff) I am deleting that fucking stupid tag and making it a synonym for I.am.a.nostalgic.luser same for the after.PTnA tag that has been popping up recently.\r\n\r\nNo one gives a fuck if you liked cheggit or Tna or whatever this is not cheggit or cheggit two or even cheggit three or TnA two or whatever else.  The staff and active members and leechers are what makes a site not a name . . . especially the name of a site who went under because it was not longer profitable enough for the site owner to be bothered anymore.  If you liked it so much then go pay that greedy sanctimonious hypocritical bastard for his precious site name and restart it . . . otherwise shut the fuck up.\r\n\r\nSorry but I am really sick of all of this pie in the sky rose colored glasses look at C!.  C! treated most new users like a cancer and if you spoke out against a site policy there you were flamed by about 6.022 * 10^23 different users who bowed down at the altar of the church of C!.  If you made it clear you would not bow down at the altar you were ostracized and ridiculed.   Yeah that is something worth emulating.  Let us try to emulate that here!!!!!  Seriously that is how I felt there and I am far from a torrenting noob.  Guess what all of you experienced C!\'s who used to treat all site noobs like the dirt on the bottom of your shoe were once new users also.  That is really not something worth remembering and venerating to my way of thinking.',NULL,NULL),(45911,5744,1243,'2012-08-03 21:05:25','[quote=GaryE]It will suck for say someone like Lanz if he is the only user who speaks Swedish but it will be a big plus for the site.[/quote]\r\n\r\nNah not really, don\'t know any swede under 60 that don\'t speek English so that wont happen much. :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(45912,5635,171777,'2012-08-03 21:06:05','Not entirely sure but isn\'t SQL rather slow in terms of math? That said can some part be simplified?\r\n\r\nAlso SQRT is almost always slower than number X number (sometimes in order of 3 or 4 times). Keep in mind though that I do not know how SQL usually does this but I know what the programming times of it were in standard C.',NULL,NULL),(45913,5915,171777,'2012-08-03 21:07:25','[quote=Dave]we are getting bored with all the tag threads - site policy is set and won\'t change[/quote]\r\n\r\nAmen to that',NULL,NULL),(45914,5913,51063,'2012-08-03 21:10:41','Magnet links and truely private torrents sites do not go together.  This thread is pointless\r\n\r\n:locked:',NULL,NULL),(45915,5911,1243,'2012-08-03 21:11:45','Agreed, and if you need that tag to remember the uploader, then that uploader can not have been worth remembering in the first place.',NULL,NULL),(45916,5911,171777,'2012-08-03 21:16:10','[quote=GaryE]As soon as the new site goes live (If I am still staff) I am deleting that fucking stupid tag and making it a synonym for I.am.a.nostalgic.luser same for the after.PTnA tag that has been popping up recently.\r\n\r\nNo one gives a fuck if you liked cheggit or Tna or whatever this is not cheggit or cheggit two or even cheggit three or TnA two or whatever else.  The staff and active members and leechers are what makes a site not a name . . . especially the name of a site who went under because it was not longer profitable enough for the site owner to be bothered anymore.  If you liked it so much then go pay that greedy sanctimonious hypocritical bastard for his precious site name and restart it . . . otherwise shut the fuck up.\r\n\r\nSorry but I am really sick of all of this pie in the sky rose colored glasses look at C!.  C! treated most new users like a cancer and if you spoke out against a site policy there you were flamed by about 6.022 * 10^23 different users who bowed down at the altar of the church of C!.  If you made it clear you would not bow down at the altar you were ostracized and ridiculed.   Yeah that is something worth emulating.  Let us try to emulate that here!!!!!  Seriously that is how I felt there and I am far from a torrenting noob.  Guess what all of you experienced C!\'s who used to treat all site noobs like the dirt on the bottom of your shoe were once new users also.  That is really not something worth remembering and venerating to my way of thinking.[/quote]\r\n\r\nWell I did not know C! but I have heard a lot about him in the last month or so. The things that I heard make me happy that I did not know him. That being said, the one statement that I really appreciate in the above rant (nothing personal GaryE) is this: \"[b]The staff and active members and leechers are what makes a site not a name...[/b]\". I think the past is something to learn from. Not to wallow in.',NULL,NULL),(45918,5635,51063,'2012-08-03 21:18:53','I do not have a philosophical problem with doing something like:\r\n\r\nseeding 1 - 5 torrents 3 credits per hour\r\nseeding 6 - 15 torrents 2 credits per hour\r\nseeding 15 + torrent 1 credit per hour\r\n\r\nmax credits are 60 * 24 * 7 per week.\r\n\r\nHowever that is needlessly complicated\r\n\r\nthe way it is currently done is well thought out and simple . . . one credit per hour max of 60 * 24 credits per day (or is it max of 60 * 24 * 7 per week).  Either way that is a lot of credits.\r\n\r\nAs far as the cost of items . . . I do agree that the 8000 or whatever for a single free leech slot is a bit much.  But it sounds like that has been resolved already.',NULL,NULL),(45919,5911,51063,'2012-08-03 21:21:41','Nothing wrong with calling a rant a rant mate LOL\n\n\n---- Edit oh and you made a double post some how . . . I have deleted one of them',51063,'2012-08-03 21:22:27'),(45920,5635,84499,'2012-08-03 21:29:38','[quote=Dave][quote=GaryE]I am trying to catch up here (after vacation and everything) and there is no way I am reading 54 posts can someone who has been following this thread sum it up in 500 words or so?[/quote]\r\n\r\nWe have decided the system already and are now in fixed state as per mifune - is there any need to read them ?[/quote]\r\n\r\nyeah I will justify this by saying this is not a new feature :lol: generally we are not changing stuff except to fix it, but a couple of things might need some tweaking yet.',NULL,NULL),(45921,5635,84499,'2012-08-03 21:30:14','[quote=Lanz]The credits is not in a fixed state, it needs further tweaking.\r\n\r\nWhat we have been talking about is two different ways to give out credits:\r\nFlat rate: 1 torrent/h = 1 credit/h\r\npro: easy system to remember\r\ncon: needs a max torrent limit or some users will get flooded with credits (max 60 has been suggested)\r\n\r\nA diminishing return formula\r\nFew torrents give up to 2-3 credits per torrent, many torrents gives you just a fraction of a credit.\r\npro: makes every seeded torrent count but gives you less credits/torrent for every torrent you add.\r\ncon: Not as easy to explain, but still better than the current system on emp.me (might need to also have a limit but can be set higher)\r\n\r\nAfter this is decided, we need to adjust the prices to fit the new model.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI favour the diminishing return formula, a little harder to explain (although a table of values works pretty well) but \"fairer\" while still being a fast calculation. (with a limit probably... although its not stricly nessecary).\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45922,5635,84499,'2012-08-03 21:32:26','\r\n[quote=DrkNess]Not entirely sure but isn\'t SQL rather slow in terms of math? That said can some part be simplified?[/quote]\r\n \r\nslower than what? slower than sequel selects - yes, slower than extracting the data and doing the math in php... no. \r\n\r\n[quote=DrkNess]Also SQRT is almost always slower than number X number (sometimes in order of 3 or 4 times). Keep in mind though that I do not know how SQL usually does this but I know what the programming times of it were in standard C.[/quote]\r\n\r\nDont worry we are aware of these issues. The sql lanz came up with for the diminishing returns method is lean mean and fast.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45923,5866,51063,'2012-08-03 21:39:26','The bottom line is that when the staff start to get paid that the staff become a target of the MPAA and DCMA nazi\'s.  Honestly I love the idea of getting paid to staff a site (God knows I have put a boatload of hours into staffing torrent sites) however, it opens up a very bad legal precedent.\r\n\r\nWhen staff can say \"I am not making any profit by doing this (running a site)\" it is very hard for staff to get sued by copyright holders.  When staff is getting paid and profits are very well known by the general membership that is when sites get into trouble.  It is my very informed opinion that is why the old Emp and TnA were targets as well as C! . . . simply because it was very obvious those sites were making lots of money.  As I have said elsewhere that is not a model you want to follow.\r\n\r\nI have no problem donating my time to run the sites I currently and formerly have staffed.  I for one do not want to risk getting sued by some DCMA nazi because I am making $50 a month or whatever to staff that site.  Yeah If I was getting paid a living wage that would be great . . . but let us face is that is not going to happen -- that being the case it is just not worth the risk to me.  There is no reason to make this site a target by paying staffers.  That is very obviously one of the things that C! in particular did very wrong and when C! went under it led to a lot of posturing and bad blood between the site owner and the very well compensated Admin who was actually running the site.\r\n\r\nI can not speak for anyone else but that is not why I do what I do on torrent sites.  I really do not want to get into arguments over pay and who contributes more hours and whose work is more valuable and all of that nonsense.  I personally got enough of that crap when I was a hiring manager in corporate America.  I do not need my hobby to generate that kind of aggravation especially for very little money -- if we were talking about staffers getting 20,000 a year or something that would be worth the risk but for 5,000 a year totally not worth the risk to me.',NULL,NULL),(45924,5706,51063,'2012-08-03 21:47:24','I have to admit that I love this feature that many other sites have.  I use it very often.  What I do now . . . is to simply make sure I visit the top two or three torrents in the list before I go away.  That way when I come back I just browse back to the point where I see a visited torrent and start looking from there.\r\n\r\nI think the main reason that most tagged based sites do not have this feature is that the whole point of tags it to keep everything searchable . . . you are not looking at each and every torrent you are just looking for the torrents that match your preferences.  At least that is the argument I have seen.  I admit that I prefer a new designator but with a tag based site it is much less critical than on a strictly category based site.  But if it is a boatload of work . . . I would vote no simply because of that amount of work.  There are plenty of more important things that need to be done from a staff perspective which are going to in the long run make this a much better site (which are invisible to the user).',NULL,NULL),(45925,5702,51063,'2012-08-03 21:59:02','If you want the font to be bigger (trust me I need it to be bigger) press control + (or command/apple + on the mac) and bingo all fonts one size larger.  I usually have it set about three sizes larger LOL  control 0 brings it back to normal and control - makes them all smaller\r\n\r\nWith my obscenely large display and very high resolution (and my need for new glasses/bifocals LOL) I use this feature on just about every site I visit.',NULL,NULL),(45926,5865,51063,'2012-08-03 22:00:56','I do not think this is something that will get used often . . . but I do hear you that sometimes that would be a useful feature.\r\n\r\nDo you have any sites in mind?',NULL,NULL),(45927,5702,70679,'2012-08-03 22:13:04','thanks for the tip but still want the italic to go away.... ',NULL,NULL),(45928,5818,51063,'2012-08-03 22:16:10','I agree . . . I was meaning to mention this but I got sidetracked with another request bug at the time and forgot.  This will add agro if it is not addressed.\n\nA simple are you sure pop up would do the trick . . .\n\nYou have offered a X GB bounty this means the person filling the request will get Y [X * .9] GB\n[color=#FF0000]X amount will immediately be removed from your upload total[/color] are you sure?\n\n[Yes] [No] [Back]\n\nOr a new page with that info or whatever ',51063,'2012-08-03 22:16:31'),(45929,5702,51063,'2012-08-03 22:18:06','Fair enough!',NULL,NULL),(45930,5702,1243,'2012-08-03 22:18:50','Yeah sorry about that barumba, posted during a time that I had very little time to check up on the forum. Perhaps that should be a clue to not post at all when you can not take the time to read the post properly. :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(45931,5830,51063,'2012-08-03 22:20:31','Did you ever correct this mifune?  (just a reminder no pressure mate)',NULL,NULL),(45932,5818,1243,'2012-08-03 22:26:34','Yeah I really don\'t like how that is implemented at all. But I\'m not gonna rewrite it now anyway. We should have an alert poping up at least. If no one can come up with a good reason for the tax I\'ll think I\'ll remove that too.',NULL,NULL),(45933,5902,84499,'2012-08-03 22:27:18','\r\n[quote=iamstoopid]yeh since this is the only a suggestion thread, bling i wanna see is: \r\n\r\n[*]Upload 100/250/500+ torrents Bling\r\n[*]Fast Seeder Bling\r\n[*]Notorious Leecher\r\n[*]Request Filler Bling (can only be gifted from one user to another)\r\n[*]Staff / Vip Bling\r\n[*]Idiot Bling (manually added by staff)\r\n[*]HQ 720p/1080p torrent Uploaders\r\n[*]Regular Uploader bling[/quote]\r\n\r\nI am adverse to adding negative awards because it could encourage idiot behaviour.\r\n\r\nThe actual content is not finished yet but the backend is done - there will be automatic awards for (subject to change):\r\nNumPosts\r\nNumComments\r\nNumUploaded\r\nRequestsFilled\r\nUploadedTB\r\nMaxSnatches (on a torrent of yours)\r\n\r\nplus maybe a couple of others.\r\n\r\nThen there are assorted staff made awards (totally subject to change);\r\n \r\nUSB Crap Award \r\nPotato Award \r\nSpecial Services to Users \r\nMost Secret Special Services to Users  \r\nCode Monkey  \r\nMost Valuable Perv \r\nOld Timers \r\nLife Saver (helping out)\r\nDescription \r\nGreat Uploader awards.\r\n \r\n\r\nI dont really want to give out the link to the awards page until its finalised as there are a bunch there right now which definitetly wont be there when we go live (we are going to condense some category awards and stuff). Exactly whats in the shop for purchase might change slightly but I dont have a problem with having both staff awarded/automatic awards and bought awards... who cares what ppl spend their credits on? The way to earn those credits is the same so as long as its encouraging seeding whats the harm?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45934,5899,84499,'2012-08-03 22:30:14','\r\nThe text version of the complete works of shakespeare is a couple of megs big :lol:',NULL,NULL),(45935,5744,84499,'2012-08-03 22:32:04','\r\na non extra work way of doing this is just to add that information to the FLS field under their profile page - currently it just says \'pervy little helper\' but it could/should say something actually useful.',NULL,NULL),(45936,5865,1243,'2012-08-03 22:33:16','I see no need to monitor this and while attachements are useful, it\'s not useful enough for us to spend time on it now. Perhaps for version 1.1 of the site.',NULL,NULL),(45937,5902,94804,'2012-08-03 22:37:04','[quote=knickers][size=10]POTATO!!!!!![/size][/quote] (I guess someone just pooped theirs;)',NULL,NULL),(45938,5863,84499,'2012-08-03 22:41:30','\r\n\r\nSomething else to balance is how much effort is worth putting into catching cheaters. I hate them but on a tracker economy level its only worth defeating x % of cheaters, after that you could get more benefit from your time doing other stuff on the site. Grinding staff down is not a good idea. Having said that I will be keen to put some brain and coding work into writing some good scripts and presenting the data in a useful way... but that will come after we go live.',NULL,NULL),(45939,5830,84499,'2012-08-03 22:51:48','\r\nyeah done a while ago :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(45940,5635,1243,'2012-08-03 22:56:06','[quote=DrkNess]Not entirely sure but isn\'t SQL rather slow in terms of math? That said can some part be simplified?\r\n\r\nAlso SQRT is almost always slower than number X number (sometimes in order of 3 or 4 times). Keep in mind though that I do not know how SQL usually does this but I know what the programming times of it were in standard C.[/quote]\r\n\r\nMost databases are really optimized for large number of calculations on several rows at once. The difference from a simple torrent count calculation and a much more complicated diminishing return formula for 15,000 users with 360,000 seeding peers is ~0.4 seconds with a total time of ~1.5 seconds. For a query that is executed once every 15 minutes, that\'s not bad imo.',NULL,NULL),(45941,5911,1243,'2012-08-03 23:07:40','Yeah not even the greatest coded tracker is worth anything without it\'s uploaders and it\'s community.  :bow: ',NULL,NULL),(45942,5888,1243,'2012-08-03 23:12:39','I prefer