t send and then every hour afterwards, to set a vhost either use the in channel method\n\nTo accept a vhost:\n[quote]!vhost a [b]Nickname[/b][/quote]\nTo reject a vhost:\n[quote]!vhost r [b]Nickname[/b][/quote]\n\nIf you don\'t want to use the in channel method,\nTo accept:\n[quote]/hs a [b]nickname[/b][/quote]\nTo reject:\n[quote]/hs r [b]nickname[/b][/quote]',70679,'2012-09-11 20:00:55'),(45948,5911,171777,'2012-08-04 00:54:01','[quote=GaryE]Nothing wrong with calling a rant a rant mate LOL\r\n\r\n\r\n---- Edit oh and you made a double post some how . . . I have deleted one of them[/quote]\r\n\r\nye I noticed the double post but couldn\'t delete it myself. That is why I left it for someone else that actually could remove it.',NULL,NULL),(45950,5635,171777,'2012-08-04 00:55:38','SQRT means square root. And sorry about that post earlier. I didn\'t see there were more pages.... stupid me :S',NULL,NULL),(45951,5679,16616,'2012-08-04 00:58:04','I\'m not a greek, but credits are allways appreciated [img]http://empornium.mooo.com/static/common/smileys/chase.gif[/img]\n\nBTW I love that gif!',16616,'2012-08-04 01:00:07'),(45952,5911,86439,'2012-08-04 01:26:36','i think if that tag were to be [s]synonymed[/s] [s]synonymised[/s] symonyimed it should be called, \r\n\r\n1.2.potato   or\r\n\r\nharblrgg   or\r\n\r\nbant',NULL,NULL),(45953,5911,171777,'2012-08-04 01:50:21','if stuff is going to be replaced by synonyms then most likely every tag will change into usb',NULL,NULL),(45954,5705,70679,'2012-08-04 01:51:39','I think this is not done.... I cannot see any way for editing my own thread titles...',NULL,NULL),(45955,5875,37338,'2012-08-04 02:00:53','[quote=apparition]I don\'t know what the fuck is causing this shit, but i bet my ass it\'s not a site bug.  \r\n\r\nI\'d guess problem is with the peers.[/quote]\r\n\r\nThat makes me wonder now how many users may of had this problem and was thinking the same thing I was. But ever since I switched I haven\'t had a problem. Looks ugly as crap though',NULL,NULL),(45956,5911,86439,'2012-08-04 02:03:47','Wait wait ...interdasting',NULL,NULL),(45957,5865,49532,'2012-08-04 02:35:59','[quote=Lanz]I see no need to monitor this and while attachements are useful, it\'s not useful enough for us to spend time on it now. Perhaps for version 1.1 of the site.[/quote]\r\nSo then people could just use megaupload, rapidshare, pastebin, etc. with no need for approval?',NULL,NULL),(45958,5910,49532,'2012-08-04 02:53:13','[quote=mifune]\r\n\r\nWe are bascially in feature lock now - unless somehting is vital for useability or very quick and simple to implement it is unlikely to fly.[/quote]\r\n\r\nWell maybe it can be inplemented in the future, Dan already volunteered to do the work.\n\n[quote=mifune]a mass add tool would need a lot of safegaurds/logging etc. and I dont think we need it.  We do not allow users to delete tags so we are not going to implement a mass delete system.[/quote]\r\n\r\nthe mass delete was suggested only for staff. and the mass add could be restricted to any user class the staff decided was trustworthy enough, even making it also just the staff.',49532,'2012-08-04 03:01:36'),(45959,5917,37338,'2012-08-04 02:55:32','Problem: When sending PM\'s to other user\'s the messages do not show up in the Sent Box.\r\n\r\nWhat I did: I sent 3 PM\'s to different user\'s this morning and neither message has shown up in my Sent Box. I know the notification system works cause I marked the previous messages in my inbox unread and it shows a red bar under the Home Torrent Request ......\r\n\r\nI need two other people to help me test and confirm this.',NULL,NULL),(45960,5917,49532,'2012-08-04 03:16:58','I sent to Wallebe99 and also didn\'t get confirmation, not in sentbox.  ',NULL,NULL),(45961,5911,85111,'2012-08-04 03:18:24','lol everyone has a point, cheggit died ages ago.. think im gonna retire the after.cheggit tag from now on.  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(45962,5865,86439,'2012-08-04 03:31:45','They\'ll have real trouble with that first one.',NULL,NULL),(45963,5917,86439,'2012-08-04 03:37:13','Was working, I have plenty in the sentbox, but seems not to work now.',NULL,NULL),(45964,5679,94952,'2012-08-04 03:40:27','I have 10k slots and 2.2 mil creds so I think Im good',NULL,NULL),(45965,5706,94952,'2012-08-04 03:50:34','[quote=GaryE]I have to admit that I love this feature that many other sites have.  I use it very often.  What I do now . . . is to simply make sure I visit the top two or three torrents in the list before I go away.  That way when I come back I just browse back to the point where I see a visited torrent and start looking from there.\r\n\r\nSnip...[/quote]\r\n\r\nI do the same and it kinda works. And I see the point of tags vs categories only (but then a category is just a tag in my eyes.\r\nIf the people actually coding feel its too much I\'m not going to push for it. And by the looks of it I am pretty alone in wanting this feature. \r\n\r\nI\'m an out of work web/db programmer so I have a pretty good idea of the complexity involved.  ',NULL,NULL),(45966,5918,49532,'2012-08-04 03:53:26','A lot of people are sometimes looking for specific things which turn them on, that searching for, is like searching for a fucking needle in a haystack.  I\'d like to see a forum where people can describe, in detail, what they are looking for, and others can recomend videos they\'ve seen, that they think the OP will like.\r\n\r\nI\'d also like to see:\r\n\r\na forum where people can post a picture or describe a scene in a video,  to identify pornstars. \r\n\r\na forum for talking about porn pornstars and the porn industry.\r\n\r\na forum for talking about fucking, masturbation, fetishes, turn ons, and all things sexual.   \r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45967,5702,94952,'2012-08-04 03:55:11','Slightly off-topic: Can we please keep italics (the bane of readability) to a minimum. On site text I mean, if people want to use italics in bb-code let them.\r\n\r\nHmm, random thought, Can I use a custom css to override ALL italics?  :tongue: ',NULL,NULL),(45968,5705,84499,'2012-08-04 05:01:12','There should be a field for editing the title on the edit description page.',NULL,NULL),(45969,5918,37338,'2012-08-04 06:25:56','I was with you until I read that last sentence, wtf did I just read. LOL\r\n\r\nStill you have my vote',NULL,NULL),(45970,5910,73066,'2012-08-04 07:49:20','[quote=mifune]\n[quote=mepow]Here is my research on the subject just by checking the page.\nThe add tag formula, example ?id=1337 (select the most 1337 torrent) &did=3 (this on tells the server you did something, in this case added a tag) &addedtag=boobs (will give you a new tag boobs i the torrent with that specific id).[/quote]\n\n\nI dont know if you are joking around here but no, thats not what those things do :lol: \n\napart from the id=value which displays the correct page the other url stuff is just cosmetic stuff for reporting back to the user.[/quote]\n\nAh, i donÂ´t follow why you have a post and a get at the same time with the same information but anyway... (debug maybe?)\nI can take the time and check the code, instead of just checking the page. And itÂ´s just a simple post form. \n\nSo in short the same formula but with post groupid=1337 (select the most 1337 torrent) action=add_tag (this on tells the server you did something, in this case added a tag) tagname=boobs (will give you a new tag boobs i the torrent with that specific id). Then you have the authentication key that follows named auth=xxxx (the users authkey). As you all can see below in the code. \n\n[code]\n<form action=\"torrents.php\" method=\"post\">\n	<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"action\" value=\"add_tag\" />\n	<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"auth\" value=\"xxxxxxxxx\" />\n	<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"groupid\" value=\"1337\" />\n	<input type=\"text\" name=\"tagname\" size=\"15\" value\"boobs\" />\n	<input type=\"submit\" value=\"+\" />\n</form>\n[/code]\n\nThen on the serverside you have the function add_tag that does the work with the information you provided. Hence if you provide the information the serverside will do the work. So you could do a own script that grabs your auth from emp and then post the information in to emp. Tested this briefly and posted a tag from my computer to cheggit, and it works. Coding a script that grabs a search and then post tags to all should not be that difficult. And if you want mass add tags in a userlevel account, it\'s probably a time saver to code it.',73066,'2012-08-04 07:50:19'),(45971,5910,1243,'2012-08-04 08:08:42','Do you really think we need help figuring out how to code stuff? I appreciate the thought but I\'ve been coding for 28 years and mifune is not a freshman either. :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(45972,5910,73066,'2012-08-04 08:20:36','No, i never said you needed help. I said it was easy to code a script that does the desired action.',NULL,NULL),(45973,5917,171777,'2012-08-04 10:20:47','Can confirm. Nothing in sentbox. Have checked if there are settings in profile for this but can\'t find anything. Messaging system does however nicely block messages without header/body',NULL,NULL),(45974,5875,171777,'2012-08-04 10:21:38','[quote=Wallabe99][quote=apparition]I don\'t know what the fuck is causing this shit, but i bet my ass it\'s not a site bug.  \r\n\r\nI\'d guess problem is with the peers.[/quote]\r\n\r\nThat makes me wonder now how many users may of had this problem and was thinking the same thing I was. But ever since I switched I haven\'t had a problem. Looks ugly as crap though[/quote]\r\n\r\nWell ugly or not. Atleast now you can once again download beautifull porn  :gjob: ',NULL,NULL),(45975,5919,49532,'2012-08-04 10:33:49','I\'m not sure when this happened, but U\'m no longer getting boardrs on table views, with the empornium stylesheet\r\n  [url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=CF52_501CDE51][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=CF52_501CDE51[/img][/url]\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45976,5919,86439,'2012-08-04 11:45:19','Yeah, but they are shaded. I think it looks sexy sleek. Not that i noticed borders there before.',NULL,NULL),(45977,5920,47234,'2012-08-04 13:05:46','May as well keep updates on whos done what somewhere.\r\n\r\nIm finding time to do this again :)\r\n\r\nJust copy pasta\'d the User Agreement from emp.me to a rules article here and fixed the link in the FAQ.\r\n\r\nLooking through some help stuff next',NULL,NULL),(45978,5875,1243,'2012-08-04 15:00:13','Most people seem to be able to use uTorrent 3.0 or use deluge instead.',NULL,NULL),(45979,5705,70679,'2012-08-04 15:01:55','http://i.imgur.com/dP7np.png\r\n\r\nI am maybe blind but do not see any title edit field when I go to edit...',NULL,NULL),(45980,5875,67255,'2012-08-04 15:55:44','Deluge  :gjob: ',NULL,NULL),(45981,5920,86439,'2012-08-04 16:03:37','Started an article on tags, and a glossary for tags (in articles too) from a thread here. Mifune suggested the glossary should be separate from the guide so I did that. Ive grouped the tags in semi logical groups so poor bastards dont have to hunt through a couple hundred possible tags to find one.\r\n\r\nIt all needs work though, its still rough.',NULL,NULL),(45982,5919,129045,'2012-08-04 16:08:27','I think it was removed around the same time the new fonts were implemented.\r\n\r\nWell, it looks cleaner now, can\'t say I miss the borders :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(45985,5705,94952,'2012-08-04 16:51:37','I don\'t see it either.',NULL,NULL),(45986,5705,70679,'2012-08-04 16:57:27','[quote=Mobbo]I don\'t see it either.[/quote]\r\n\r\nonly the author of the thread is supposed to see it',NULL,NULL),(45990,5917,48010,'2012-08-04 17:46:22','confirm too \r\n\r\nI sent PMs to DrkNess and knickers but they don\'t show in sentbox',NULL,NULL),(45991,5635,94804,'2012-08-04 17:51:08','Yeah, figured as much! :)\r\nbut why not reward those with their own created torrents a little more than you\'re just seeding after leeching? It makes creating a torrent more worthwhile',NULL,NULL),(45992,5635,1243,'2012-08-04 18:19:20','[quote=schlager][i]SQRT[/i] same as squirt? :)\r\n\r\n[quote=Lanz]\r\nA diminishing return formula\r\nFew torrents give up to 2-3 credits per torrent, many torrents gives you just a fraction of a credit.\r\npro: makes every seeded torrent count but gives you less credits/torrent for every torrent you add.\r\ncon: Not as easy to explain, but still better than the current system on emp.me (might need to also have a limit but can be set higher)[/quote]\r\nI don\'t get it. So, basically, the more torrents you\'re seeding the less credits you get? Is it possible to make separte rewards for torrents CREATED and just seeding after leeching?[/quote]\r\n\r\nYou will always get more credits for more torrents seeded, it\'s just that the paybacks diminish for each additional torrent. This is actually simulating the real world quite good too. After a certain point, it\'s questionable if adding more torrents are worth it.\r\n\r\nI see no difference between keeping something you personally have uploaded alive contra something you\'ve just leeched, keeping the torrent alive is what matters. I don\'t really want to start giving out credits for uploading either. It will easily lead to questions like \"what about X, shouldn\'t that give you Y credits too?\" It\'s hard balancing the bonus shop alone, setting values on doing regular task will not end well IMO.',NULL,NULL),(45993,5902,48010,'2012-08-04 18:25:12','[quote=mifune][quote=iamstoopid]yeh since this is the only a suggestion thread, bling i wanna see is: \n\n[*]Upload 100/250/500+ torrents Bling\n[*]Fast Seeder Bling\n[*]Notorious Leecher\n[*]Request Filler Bling (can only be gifted from one user to another)\n[*]Staff / Vip Bling\n[*]Idiot Bling (manually added by staff)\n[*]HQ 720p/1080p torrent Uploaders\n[*]Regular Uploader bling[/quote]\n\nI am adverse to adding negative awards because it could encourage idiot behaviour.\n\nThe actual content is not finished yet but the backend is done - there will be automatic awards for (subject to change):\nNumPosts\nNumComments\nNumUploaded\nRequestsFilled\nUploadedTB\nMaxSnatches (on a torrent of yours)\n\nplus maybe a couple of others.\n\nThen there are assorted staff made awards (totally subject to change);\n \nUSB Crap Award \nPotato Award \nSpecial Services to Users \nMost Secret Special Services to Users  \nCode Monkey  \nMost Valuable Perv \nOld Timers \nLife Saver (helping out)\nDescription \nGreat Uploader awards.\n \n\nI dont really want to give out the link to the awards page until its finalised as there are a bunch there right now which definitetly wont be there when we go live (we are going to condense some category awards and stuff). Exactly whats in the shop for purchase might change slightly but I dont have a problem with having both staff awarded/automatic awards and bought awards... who cares what ppl spend their credits on? [b]The way to earn those credits is the same so as long as its encouraging seeding whats the harm?[/b][/quote]\n\nexactly',48010,'2012-08-04 18:27:59'),(45994,5911,48010,'2012-08-04 18:59:39','[quote=iamstoopid]lol everyone has a point, cheggit died ages ago.. think im gonna retire the after.cheggit tag from now on.  :laugh:[/quote]\r\n\r\ncool\r\n\r\nI could add stupid tags like  former.emporium.member or former.ptna.member or i.am.seeding.on.blah.blah.blah.site\r\n\r\nWTF is that worth ?\r\n\r\nThe joys of tags and community tagging will bear fruit in the garden of the new emp.me :wink: and I and others will be there waiting :grin:',NULL,NULL),(45995,5705,84499,'2012-08-04 19:01:02','\r\n\r\nlol, excuse me I am stupid  :blush:   everytime I read something about titles I think its talking about torrent titles... those the user can edit now! \r\n\r\nTitle for forum threads... I dont know. Can you edit them on emp.me? I am inclined to say we dont do it... its not a 5 min job to implement and we would probably want to time limit it, seems like more effort than its worth. A user can always report their own thread asking for the title to be renamed.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(45996,5918,48010,'2012-08-04 19:11:43','[quote=apparition]A lot of people are sometimes looking for specific things which turn them on, that searching for, is like searching for a fucking needle in a haystack.  I\'d like to see a forum where people can describe, in detail, what they are looking for, and others can recomend videos they\'ve seen, that they think the OP will like.\r\n\r\nI\'d also like to see:\r\n\r\n[b]a forum where people can post a picture or describe a scene in a video,  to identify pornstars. [/b] [color=blue]on emp.me already[/color]\r\n[b]a forum for talking about porn pornstars and the porn industry.[/b] [color=blue]on emp.me in general already ?[/color]\r\n\r\na forum for talking about fucking, masturbation, fetishes, turn ons, and all things sexual  [color=blue]and your point is .. ? [/color].[/quote]',NULL,NULL),(45997,5705,70679,'2012-08-04 19:18:47','he he no problem... and nope cannot edit on the actual site and always wished when I screwed up and realized after the fact thus the suggestion for the new site.... but if too complicated OK maybe later once the site is operational...\r\n\r\nwhile at it can you correct MrRandom IRC Tutorialss <- double \"s\"\r\n\r\nThanks.',NULL,NULL),(45998,5744,48010,'2012-08-04 19:22:59','[quote=knickers]I speak gooderer England.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI spik beddr anglis than you :grin:',NULL,NULL),(45999,5635,49532,'2012-08-04 19:25:16','With the current system, someone gets more credit, for seeding ten low resolution, 2 mintute clips, that they do for seeing 1  high resolutions 100GB siterip.  instead of just calculating bonus on the number of torrents, it should be calculted on both number and size.\n\nTorrentVault, which also uses gazelle/ocelot has a formula like:\n[quote]\nThe gold [what they call bonus points] system gives out gold according to the file size of the torrent. This way people who seed bigger files and therefore use more space on their harddrive, are rewarded with more gold. Gold is handed out once every hour.\nSize	Gold\nLarger than 10 MB	1\nLarger than 100 MB	2\nLarger than 250 MB	3\nLarger than 400 MB	5\nLarger than 1.0 GB	7\nLarger than 2.5 GB	10\nLarger than 4.0 GB	20\nLarger than 10.0 GB	50\n\n[/quote]\nThe size to reward ratio needs changing, but I like the method.',49532,'2012-08-04 19:26:15'),(46000,5914,51063,'2012-08-04 19:29:03','so you tried to add:\n\ndp double.penetration\n\nand it got added as\n\ndpdouble.penetration\n\nis that correct?\n\n\n\n\n\nIt seems that is correct\n\non that same torrent I just added:\n\nusb.loves.tags usb.pink.dildo\n\nand they got added as a single tag\n\nusb.loves.tagsusb.pink.dildo\n\nI do not know if this is a bug or a feature.  But we need either a note which states \"only add one tag at a time\" or it needs to work the same way as it does on the initial upload form.\n\nMy vote is for it to work the same way as it does on the initial upload form.  But let us face it adding the note is probably a much quicker fix LOL\n\nSo whatever Lanz and or mifune decide!\n\n\n---- Edit\nOh yeah only staff can remove tags.  That works as intended.  There was much debate about this (among staff/advisers) and I really do not want to rehash it all but that is the way we decided to do it . . . and no it is not worth trying to convince us otherwise.',51063,'2012-08-04 19:32:33'),(46001,5635,1243,'2012-08-04 19:32:11','So they don\'t have a limit for the number of golds one can earn per hour then?',NULL,NULL),(46004,5901,51063,'2012-08-04 19:38:42','[quote=knickers]I also just clicked -10gb. It has NOT yet removed 10gig from my stats, but that may take the tracker a few minutes to update.\r\n\r\nThe 24hr freeleech, immediately showed me the green bar at the top of the page and as DrkNess stated, is counting down.\r\n\r\n\r\nEdit: Stats still not deducting the 10 gig.\r\n\r\nEdit 2: Looking at my credits, I dont think it deducted the amount either, so maybe it didnt go through at all.\r\n\r\nEdit 3: I just tried it again. It immediately deducted the 10 gig. And 4.000 credits.\r\n\r\nI have no idea why it never went through the first time.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI am trying to catch up and I just read this . . . all I can tell you is what the log for your account shows:\r\n\r\n 2012-08-02 07:57:28 - User bought -10 gb. Cost: 4000 credits\r\n\r\nunfortunately because the log shows real time and the forums only show relative time I am unsure about the timing of all this but it seems either the first request did not go through or you did not really click on that button or there was a weird error that prevented the request from reaching the server or God knows what else.  The bottom line is that the log only shows you purchasing -10 GB once.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46005,5920,48010,'2012-08-04 19:39:47','I already said I would write a welcome guide to the new site detailing the changes and new features - I\'ll start on it tomorrow and post a draft ',48010,'2012-08-04 19:40:58'),(46006,5918,49532,'2012-08-04 19:43:07','[quote=Dave]\n[b]a forum where people can post a picture or describe a scene in a video,  to identify pornstars. [/b] [color=blue]on emp.me already[/color][/quote]Where?  \n\n[quote=Dave]\n[b]a forum for talking about porn pornstars and the porn industry.[/b] [color=blue]on emp.me in general already ?[/color]\n\na forum for talking about fucking, masturbation, fetishes, turn ons, and all things sexual  [color=blue]and your point is .. ? [/color].[/quote]My point is that the [b]General[/b] forum is for talking about [i]anything[/i].  I don\'t like that everything fucking gets lumped together in one general forum. I think portalk and sextalk deserve their own forums.',49532,'2012-08-04 19:48:23'),(46007,5863,48010,'2012-08-04 19:43:57','[s]are cheats a big problem on emp.me ?\n\nI think we have that covered already ?\n\nanyway a script would probably help but seems low priority right now ?[/s]\n\nEDITED by Dave -