miting once.... ',171777,'2012-08-04 20:24:59'),(46027,5918,51063,'2012-08-04 20:24:35','That is something we can consider apparition . . . however we are not going to add forums right now.  When the site goes live I see no harm in adding additional forums ( I very well might get over ruled though . . . you see I am not really a staffer here I was made staff here on the beta site to help test staff only features which I might be a little more familiar with than other staffers from the main site . . . it might carry over it might not we have not talked about it in a while)\r\n\r\nThe point here is that once we go live Lanz (or maybe mifune?) will copy over the current forums from the main site and all of this will be wiped out (at least that is what happened the two or three times that has been tested).  So there is no point to add it now.\r\n\r\nYes there is a forum on the main site for identifying porn stars . . . I do not have the link handy but I have posted in it several times so I am beyond certain that it is there.\r\n\r\nBack to the main point . . . I see no harm in adding additional forums . . . if they then die a natural death we can get rid of them at that time.  I do see your point in wanting those forums but I honestly do not think they be very busy.  But again I see no harm in trying them.  We all want more folks in the forums and if adding a few new sections or sub-sections might do that I for one say it is worth a shot . . . but only after we go live with this site.',NULL,NULL),(46028,5902,1507,'2012-08-04 20:31:16',':laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]There is a Potato Award, and I have it showing somewhere.....\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:laugh:',NULL,NULL),(46029,5902,85636,'2012-08-04 20:32:03','[quote=usillyboy]:laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]There is a Potato Award, and I have it showing somewhere.....\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:laugh:[/quote]\r\n\r\nSecond from the left, top row.',NULL,NULL),(46030,5902,1507,'2012-08-04 20:33:04','[quote=MrRandom][quote=usillyboy]:laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]There is a Potato Award, and I have it showing somewhere.....\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:laugh:[/quote]\r\n\r\nSecond from the left, top row.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n:gjob:\r\n\r\n[b]usb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(46031,5854,51063,'2012-08-04 20:35:50','[quote=mifune]isnt a week of FL a bit much? :sigh: :lol:[/quote]\r\n\r\nNO it is way way way way to fucking much . . . it is way beyond a bit LOL\r\n\r\nIf you are rich enough to to buy 1 week of free leech . . . you do not need a week of free leech LOL\r\n\r\nAs for it being used for contests . . . the fact that they are cumulative is more than enough is it not?\r\n\r\nI would say that 2 or 3 days of free leech is plenty even for contests though.  I bought a 24 hour free leech on the main site shortly after I got back from vacation and yeah ok I had 25 Mbit/sec download at the time (I now have 75 Mbit/sec down) . . . but that was enough to get everything my heart desired.\r\n\r\nI really think anything more than 2 or 3 days is just insane.  I mean how many people are there out there who are serious about torrenting who does not have at least 8 Mbit/sec download speed?  Three days of 8 mbit/sec is the rough equivalent of my 25 Mbit/sec over 1 day.  And really I had bandwidth to spare.',NULL,NULL),(46034,5635,49532,'2012-08-04 20:37:44','[quote=Lanz]So they don\'t have a limit for the number of golds one can earn per hour then?[/quote]\nI don\'t think they have a limit, but I could be wrong. Once, I had 300 torrents earning me a total of more than 800 points every hour.  They require 75,000  points to buy 10 GB',49532,'2012-08-04 20:38:20'),(46035,5705,70679,'2012-08-04 20:46:10','thx I see is done  :smile1: ',NULL,NULL),(46037,5635,1243,'2012-08-04 20:55:19','Damn that\'s expensive. No wonder they don\'t need a limiter.\n\nLets say a regular user has 50 torrents and the average point/per credit is 2.6 based on your 800 points for 300 torrents. Thats 130 points per hour. To be able to buy off 10GB you would need to seed those torrents for 576 hours or 24 days.\n\nThat can of course be tweaked but, running multiple queries to calculate the points kind of locks you not limit the points. That drives up the prices to compensate for the 300+ torrents users, but punish the small guys with 15 torrents running.',1243,'2012-08-04 20:56:19'),(46038,5854,1243,'2012-08-04 21:01:26','Yeah the mod tool goes up to 1 week, lets see how long it takes usb to give one out once we go live :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(46039,5635,49532,'2012-08-04 21:01:41','[quote=Lanz]Damn that\'s expensive. No wonder they don\'t need a limiter.\n\nLets say a regular user has 50 torrents and the average point/per credit is 2.6 based on your 800 points for 300 torrents. Thats 130 points per hour. To be able to buy off 10GB you would need to seed those torrents for 576 hours or 24 days.\n\nThat can of course be tweaked but, running multiple queries to calculate the points kind of locks you not limit the points. That drives up the prices to compensate for the 300+ torrents users, but punish the small guys with 15 torrents running.[/quote]\n\nI sent you an invite, did you get it?   \n\n[Everyone else, please don\'t ask me for invites, its against the rules to publicly offer them]',49532,'2012-08-04 21:05:08');
INSERT INTO `forums_posts` VALUES (46040,5754,51063,'2012-08-04 21:05:06','I am all for anonymous uploads.  I know I would be more likely to upload with anonymous uploads.  This is going to sound arrogant and that is far from my intent but it is what it is.\r\n\r\nI am a fairly highly visible torrent user.  In general I use the same user name everywhere I am an Admin on one site and I was a very visible staffer on another huge site (the old emp) I was a member of the \"board of directors\" of another very popular torrent/file sharing discussion site.  I am not trying to brag here I just love torrenting and I do not make much of an effort to hide it.  However, uploading is different.  The vast majority of legal action has come against uploaders and site Admins and owners.  Maybe my paranoia and delusions of grandeur are out of place but it is my opinion that I am exactly the type of person who the MPAA and DCMA would love to bust and then put me on a plinth and say see this is what we do to file sharers.\r\n\r\nAs a result I prefer my uploads to completely anonymous.  There are other options of course . . . like allowing paranoid users to have two accounts or what I am currently doing when I upload to .me . . . clearly stating that I am just passing on what I have found from other sites and that I am not the person who ripped the content.\r\n\r\nYes I could suck it up and pay the $10 a month and get a good VPN but as we all know if someone really wants to find out who you are all of those VPN\'s require a copy of your drivers license or a copy of a utility bill or more so they are not as anonymous as some think.  Yes there are steps you can take to make it harder to get identified but nothing is fool proof.\r\n\r\nYes an anonymous upload does not protect me completely but it does keep the baddies from seeing that the one upload they are picking on is only one of 100 or whatever the number is.  That is a degree of protection I know that I enjoy.  I just do not want the baddies to be able to say . . . hey we are going after this guy and he has over 100 uploads.  Let us try to get all of the producers of that content in on this [legal action].\r\n\r\nI know it is a lot of work and it requires a lot of testing but to me personally it is worth it.  Of course I travel in circles where folks love anonymous uploads; but, like attracts like so that is not exactly surprising.  So I do know lots and lots of folks who will only upload when they can do so anonymously -- but that very well might be because I know almost all of the folks who think that way.\r\n\r\nAs far as who can see them . . . if I mark an upload as anonymous I for one think only full staff (meaning all staff except FLS) should be able to see the uploaders user name.  I do not want some Pimp or Sextreme or whatever to be able to see it just because they have uploaded a lot.  There is not inherent security in someone being a Sextreme or whatever not being a baddie . . . especially when that title is automatically conferred based on number of torrents uploaded.\r\n\r\nAlso if you are going to implement anonymous uploads please make sure that when the uploader comments on their own anonymous upload that the comment is anonymous as well ;-)  Just because I want to upload anonymously does not mean that I do not want to interact with the people who comment on my uploads.',NULL,NULL),(46041,5635,1243,'2012-08-04 21:06:05','nope\n\nhmm, pm is obviously broken for some reason...\n\npm\'s should work again.',1243,'2012-08-04 21:34:41'),(46042,5854,51063,'2012-08-04 21:06:31','LOL that is a good question.  I would not want to take that bet.',NULL,NULL),(46044,5899,51063,'2012-08-04 21:18:27','The point is to get about 200 + people on the same torrent and see what happens.  The size of the torrent is not the big issue.  I misspoke when I said relatively large torrent . . . I mean a relatively large swarm.\n\nThe size of the torrent does not change the load on the server.  ;-)\n\nMe being paranoid I do not want to say \"everyone download this copyrighted material\" and then have the site Admins and owners end up in hot water because they \"required\" users to download copyrighted material so something that is in the public domain is safe LOL.\n\nHell if we wanted to . . . we could even upload the .torrent (with the passkey of a test account) to the main site and ask the pervs to download the small torrent to help load test this server.\n\nIf we keep it small we are not infringing on peoples limited HD space and hopefully people can keep it up and running for 3 days or so.',51063,'2012-08-04 21:18:45'),(46045,5744,51063,'2012-08-04 21:22:39','[quote=Lanz][quote=GaryE]It will suck for say someone like Lanz if he is the only user who speaks Swedish but it will be a big plus for the site.[/quote]\r\n\r\nNah not really, don\'t know any swede under 60 that don\'t speek English so that wont happen much. :laugh:[/quote]\r\n\r\nI hear you I was just using you as an example because you are very busy and I know you speak Swedish.  The point is that if someone is the only person who speaks a certain language they might get overwhelmed with requests.\r\n\r\nAnd for the record I am English only . . . in person I can get by in French but not written and certainly not in technical lingo.  I can only rely on google translate (or altavista babele fish ;-) )',NULL,NULL),(46046,5917,1243,'2012-08-04 21:35:44','Fixed.',NULL,NULL),(46047,5744,1243,'2012-08-04 21:43:42','Yeah I know bud, just thought it was funny.  :clownhat: ',NULL,NULL),(46049,5914,84499,'2012-08-04 22:34:05','\r\nactually it should add multiple tags its just there is a small bug...\r\n\r\nI have been meaning to rewrite the add tag code slightly anyway, its going straight to the top of the list!',NULL,NULL),(46050,5818,1243,'2012-08-04 22:50:30','This has now been changed to make it more obvious that the sum is deducted at once, plus the tax is now gone to.',NULL,NULL),(46051,5854,171777,'2012-08-04 23:25:45','[quote=GaryE]LOL that is a good question.  I would not want to take that bet.[/quote]\r\n\r\nwhoever bids the shortest wins on that one?',NULL,NULL),(46052,5744,171777,'2012-08-04 23:29:27','[quote=GaryE]And for the record I am English only . . . in person I can get by in French but not written and certainly not in technical lingo.  I can only rely on google translate (or altavista babele fish ;-) )[/quote]\n\nI have seen you write german on the .me website.',171777,'2012-08-04 23:29:46'),(46053,5910,84499,'2012-08-05 00:32:13',' \r\nThe reason adding tags to multiple torrents isnt in is not because we cant figure out how to do it. To do it properly would take more effort than we think it is worth. I dont really want to get into a debate about it... but there is considerably more to consider than just immediate implementation of an add routine (and looping the existing function would not be the optimal way to do it).',NULL,NULL),(46054,5863,51063,'2012-08-05 00:33:22','I guarantee you it is a huge fucking problem mate.  I catch users on PB all the time . . . some of whom have been on the site for over 4 years . . . and that is on a closed invite-only site where invites are given out to most users at a rate of 1 per month . . . and only then when the user requests an invite (so 99.9% of users only get one invite at a time per month) and if you already have one from the previous month you do not get another LOL.  The point being that when you cheat on a site that gives out invites very sparingly you know that if you get caught once you are pretty much gone forever.  Where as on an open invite site a new account is just a new IP address and new e-mail address a day.\r\n\r\nWhen PB was open invite . . . oye fucking vey . . . I was banning about 3 to 5 users a day.  And that was using a very unsophisticated cheat script.  If we had the script we have on the new site when we were open invites that number probably would be double -- if not triple.\r\n\r\nI just caught a guy last night on .me who Clownius told me had never legitimate uploaded anything!  He had been on the site for like 4 months.  I only caught him because he was stupid enough to cheat on a torrent I had uploaded and I happened to hit the refresh button at the right instance.\r\n\r\nTrust me you have boatloads of cheaters.\r\n\r\nAs far as mifune\'s statement . . . it is very valid especially on an open invite site.  However, with the IP history features of gazelle it really is easier to keep the cheaters out.  That IP history is a huge bonus in trying to eliminate cheaters.  You can do a simple search and find multiple accounts much easier than on TBDev.  Also everyone who is examining cheat reports needs to be able to ban IP addresses.  But it is still like trying to bail out your canoe with a thimble.  But if you keep on top of it . . . eventually the cheaters will go somewhere else where they do not have to create a new account every few days.  It takes a lot of work but it does eventually pay off.  Word gets out that site XXX bans cheaters without mercy and that you are better off cheating elsewhere and then the cheats do start to die off.  But that takes about 6 to 10 months LOL\r\n\r\nThe point is that cheaters are by definition bad users that are doing nothing at all for your torrent site except boosting upload totals for the legitimate users.  They never participate in the forums, they never say thanks for the upload, they do not comment . . . they just grab whatever they want and then they bugger off.\r\n\r\nI can not tell you how many users I have banned for cheating with more than 3 forum posts or torrent comments combined but the number is very very close to zero LOL.\r\n\r\nThey are like ticks (or leeches or pick the blood sucking insect of your choice).  So yeah getting rid of as many as possible is worth while.  But as mifune implied detecting say 90% of them is a reasonable goal.  To get rid of that last 10% will take more time and effort than getting rid of the first 90% -- these numbers are just examples do not take these as gospel.  There is a point of diminishing returns.  This is very common in the programming world . . . getting say a 90% solution is fairly easy but getting that last 10% often takes more than double the effort in design and programming and then effort to analyze the data.\r\n\r\nWhen Lanz or mifune are ready I expect we can get a cheat script and data presentation system cobbled together in about a regular working day or more likely a few hours  (if you want to look at a worst case scenario we can even call it 3 8 hour days but I can not imagine it will take that long).  It will then probably take about a week or so to teach everyone how to interpret the common issues with analyzing the cheat reports.  At which point on a site this size I would guesstimate there will probably be about 2 hours of work a day dealing with the reports.  After about 6 weeks that time will probably fall to about 1 hour a day at which time interpreting the data will be more innate and everyone will no longer be thinking . . . what do I do next?\r\n\r\nSo is all that worth the effort . . . I honestly do not know the answer to that and let us face it . . . we will not know for sure until we start the process if my numbers are even close to accurate.  LOL\r\n\r\nBut that is my best estimate so that is probably what we should base the discussion on.',NULL,NULL),(46055,5854,1507,'2012-08-05 00:51:59','[quote=Lanz]Yeah the mod tool goes up to 1 week, lets see how long it takes usb to give one out once we go live :laugh:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n:laugh: :laugh: :laugh:\r\n\r\n :yes2: ',NULL,NULL),(46056,5744,51063,'2012-08-05 00:56:21','LOL google translate wrote in German LOL I wrote in English LOL\n\nAnd it was a quote from that episode of Fawlty Towers.',51063,'2012-08-05 00:56:56'),(46059,5635,1507,'2012-08-05 01:05:22','[quote=apparition][quote=Lanz]So they don\'t have a limit for the number of golds one can earn per hour then?[/quote]\r\nI don\'t think they have a limit, but I could be wrong. Once, I had 300 torrents earning me a total of more than 800 points every hour.  [color=magenta]They require 75,000  points to buy 10 GB[/color][/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n :ohmy:  :ohmy:  :ohmy:  :blink:  :blink:  :blink: \r\n\r\n[b]holy crap that\'s expensive...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nand they complain about us being expensive...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46060,5705,51063,'2012-08-05 01:17:43','It was not done by me LOL but it is all good!',NULL,NULL),(46061,5705,84499,'2012-08-05 02:00:19',':ninja:',NULL,NULL),(46062,5918,84499,'2012-08-05 02:06:13','[quote=usillyboy]:gjob:\r\n\r\n[b]Yeah, now that staff have the tools to create forums, this can be done, whereas on the present site only SysOp/Admin can do that....\r\n\r\nIt gets too cluttered too quickly, whereas we can separate some of the stuff and make it a little cleaner...\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nI wouldnt get too attached to all the admin tools that are currently available  :devil:  definitely some of them wont be available to staff on the site... but its useful to have more testers for the admin tools than just the coders  :D ',NULL,NULL),(46064,5907,84499,'2012-08-05 02:19:55','\r\n\r\nI assume the IRC stuff is going to end up in the help section as an IRC article(s).',NULL,NULL),(46065,5899,86439,'2012-08-05 02:29:01','What if I just make a 300 meg amateur torrent? Admin/mod can make it freeleech so even limited HDD can just delete it afterwards if they like. I cant seed quickly (about 100kB/s), so the load will last for some time.',86439,'2012-08-05 02:29:56'),(46066,5754,48010,'2012-08-05 06:52:21','I personally agree with everything Gary posted above but I don\'t think he is arrogant - far from it :grin:',NULL,NULL),(46067,5854,48010,'2012-08-05 07:03:31','[quote=Lanz]Yeah the mod tool goes up to 1 week, lets see how long it takes usb to give one out once we go live :laugh:[/quote]\r\nLOL',NULL,NULL),(46068,5863,48010,'2012-08-05 07:16:03','Gary as usual great advice and recommendations\r\n\r\n[quote=GaryE]I guarantee you it is a huge fucking problem mate. \r\n\r\nTrust me you have boatloads of cheaters.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI really didn\'t know the scale of it. I have edited my previous post to reflect this too.',NULL,NULL),(46069,5917,48010,'2012-08-05 08:12:26','TEST\n\nPMs sent again to knickers and DrkNess\n\nI see the PM sent to system and waited for a couple of minutes but no change - see the screenshot here\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=E678_501E0F3A][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=E678_501E0F3A[/img][/url]\n\nThe screen says \"just now\" but honestly it has been 5 minutes - I can do another screenshot if needed',48010,'2012-08-05 08:14:54'),(46070,5917,49532,'2012-08-05 08:39:29','I just sent a PM, and it appeared imediatly om sent box ',NULL,NULL),(46071,5917,48010,'2012-08-05 09:02:13','ummmm\r\n\r\nI just sent a PM to appariton\r\n\r\nsame again shows as sent to system - a staff bug ?\r\n\r\nI don\'t use any friends or blocked list - not sure if that makes a differnece but will state it here for the record and duplication if needed',NULL,NULL),(46072,5917,1243,'2012-08-05 09:03:04','PM\'s where still broken, but it should be working now.',NULL,NULL),(46076,5917,48010,'2012-08-05 09:12:51','PM sucessfully sent to Lanz (just ignore it)\n\ncheck sending PM to aparition DrkNess and knickers - all show up as sent too\n\n',48010,'2012-08-05 09:13:22'),(46086,5925,171777,'2012-08-05 09:56:42','Just found out what sometimes causes the double posts. You can click the post button multiple times. If you are the previous poster then it will add the info as several different edits in the original post. If however you are NOT the last poster then it will add several seperate posts as replies.\r\n\r\nProof @:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2924\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2917&postid=26083#post26083',NULL,NULL),(46087,5926,171777,'2012-08-05 09:56:42','Just found out what sometimes causes the double posts. You can click the post button multiple times. If you are the previous poster then it will add the info as several different edits in the original post. If however you are NOT the last poster then it will add several seperate posts as replies.\r\n\r\nProof @:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2924\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2917&postid=26083#post26083',NULL,NULL),(46088,5926,1243,'2012-08-05 10:05:41','test',NULL,NULL),(46089,5926,1243,'2012-08-05 10:05:42','test',NULL,NULL),(46090,5926,1243,'2012-08-05 10:05:43','test\n\n :rant: ',1243,'2012-08-05 10:06:18'),(46091,5926,49532,'2012-08-05 10:09:09','',49532,'2012-08-05 10:14:56'),(46094,5917,86439,'2012-08-05 10:41:44','I got the message when I clicked inbox in knickers dropdown, but the red alert bar is no longer appearing at all.\n\nJust sent one to lanz to see if the message bar is borked.',86439,'2012-08-05 10:43:50'),(46096,5926,171777,'2012-08-05 12:09:10','just noticed that this probably also works when creating threads...\n\n[b]edit:[/b] Can confirm that it also works on thread creations. See:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewforum&forumid=23',171777,'2012-08-05 12:31:14'),(46097,5917,171777,'2012-08-05 12:10:20','indeed I did have a message after all. just no notification from both the red bar at the top and the (1) normally showing near the message box.',NULL,NULL),(46098,5899,171777,'2012-08-05 12:16:40','Well the problem a 300 meg torrent is that it is done before a lot of leechers start showing up. That way you will always just test 1 or 2 leechers at the same time.',NULL,NULL),(46099,5754,171777,'2012-08-05 12:20:07','Anon uploading has major benefits but there is also the abuse point that has to be taken into account so there will always have to be a link of user+torrent. If however as USB already said this can only be seen by staff (and I don\'t agree that normal users no matter their rank should be able to circumvent Anon settings) this would still make it so that people can be made responsible for uploading utter crap.\r\n\r\nSo I vote yes for Anon uploads as long as it does not make people Anon to staffers.',NULL,NULL),(46100,5863,171777,'2012-08-05 12:26:39','I have been wondering about people that instantly start seeding a torrent I just made completely from scratch. Probably should start paying more attention to that again on .me to report a user or 2...',NULL,NULL),(46106,5917,86439,'2012-08-05 12:41:57','Yeah, Im getting the red bar now. Either lanz fixed it when he replied to my PM, or there was a temp glitch.\n\nFailed to mention it earlier, but I never got the (1) near the inbox either. I didnt check this time, I just clicked the red bar.\n\nEdit: Lucky I leave tabs open, the (1) next to inbox is there too.',86439,'2012-08-05 12:45:14'),(46107,5932,171777,'2012-08-05 12:42:33','The new system makes a double post into an edit. I like this but it also removes the ability to bump a thread. This way no-one ever remembers older threads even if the last poster makes an edit....',NULL,NULL),(46108,5932,86439,'2012-08-05 12:46:04','Oh, the merge checkbox is gone?',NULL,NULL),(46109,5932,86439,'2012-08-05 12:47:33','No, there it is. It only appears when youre the last poster.\r\n\r\nThe merge button will stop posts being merged. Sensibly its set to merge by default so you have to remember to uncheck it.',NULL,NULL),(46110,5907,85636,'2012-08-05 12:52:41','[quote=mifune]I assume the IRC stuff is going to end up in the help section as an IRC article(s).[/quote]\r\n\r\nSome of the detailed stuff isn\'t suitable for a help page (the ones with every possible command for that service, for example), but the posts showing how to setup an IRC Client could be moved.',NULL,NULL),(46111,5917,1243,'2012-08-05 13:20:26','Yeah I noticed that bug when I fixed the pm system earlier so I made some changes, good that it works now.',NULL,NULL),(46112,5932,171777,'2012-08-05 14:03:06','You know I never even noticed that little check mark?',NULL,NULL),(46113,5754,1243,'2012-08-05 15:01:22','[quote=DrkNess]So I vote yes for Anon uploads as long as it does not make people Anon to staffers.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYeah that almost goes without saying. I\'m a bit hesitant to include it at this time though. Regular bug fixes has priority and perhaps not until later anyway.',NULL,NULL),(46114,5863,47234,'2012-08-05 15:18:17','We are catching cheats left and right but its amazing how often when one comes to my attention and i look back over their stats its obvious they have been cheating for some time and have escaped notice.....\r\n\r\nMy main fear is knocking off legitimate users.  Especially those who seedbox.  We do want those around.  What we dont need are people who straight cheat....',NULL,NULL),(46115,5754,47234,'2012-08-05 15:21:58','If it is possible i like the idea.  Im as paranoid as the next clown too.  Notice i have done just one upload.  I was planning to site rip at one point but being staff i have decided i dont need the added attention of being an uploader :lol:\r\n\r\nThat and i dont have time being another factor',NULL,NULL),(46116,5875,47234,'2012-08-05 15:30:03','[quote=elkid]Deluge  :gjob:[/quote]\r\n\r\n+1\r\n\r\nLoving Deluge',NULL,NULL),(46117,5905,171777,'2012-08-05 15:57:44','Bump: Please read this people. Might be nice to post this in the general domain so people will have a more organised search method',NULL,NULL),(46118,5933,85636,'2012-08-05 16:03:16','When I set my forum signature I noticed that when I used this\n\n[code][url=http://empornium.mooo.com/chat.php][b][size=3]If you are not busy [you], get your ass on to the IRC.[/size][/b][/url][/code]\n\nThe characters after the \"you\" tag were different sizes (at least on the preview).\n\nExample:\n[url=http://empornium.mooo.com/chat.php][b][size=10]If you are not busy [you], get your ass on to the IRC.[/size][/b][/url]',85636,'2012-08-05 16:03:42'),(46119,5905,47234,'2012-08-05 16:39:45','Hmm could we add this to Home?',NULL,NULL),(46120,5933,1243,'2012-08-05 16:58:14','That\'s because the you tag is a link, you can\'t nest links. It\'s a limitation of html, not the bbcode so the result might differ from browser to browser. You need to do something like this instead:\r\n\r\n[code][b][size=3][url=http://empornium.mooo.com/chat.php]If you are not busy[/url] [you][url=http://empornium.mooo.com/chat.php], get your ass on to the IRC.[/url][/size][/b][/code]\r\n\r\n\r\n[b][size=3][url=http://empornium.mooo.com/chat.php]If you are not busy[/url] [you][url=http://empornium.mooo.com/chat.php], get your ass on to the IRC.[/url][/size][/b]',NULL,NULL),(46121,5905,171777,'2012-08-05 17:01:13','Sure once it is approved and potentially expanded upon.',NULL,NULL),(46122,5905,84499,'2012-08-05 18:34:33','\r\n\r\nLooks good to me  :thumbsup:  the only thing I might alter slightly is :\r\n\r\n[*]Test things multiple times A result could always be a fluke. Statistically it is safest to test anything atleast 3 times because then you will always have 2 results that match (and if you have 3 different ones that that too is a bug and needs documentation)\r\n\r\n- this is correct but I would frame it in terms of reproductability. If a bug is not reproducible it kind of dosent exist... of course some bugs are hard to pin down, there are a couple of examples in the forums of bugs that only showed for non-staff or only show with a certain combination of settings etc but thats why you need to reproduce them and carefully note the environment that produced the bug. \r\n\r\nTrying to rewrite that though and I just end up with something similar to the last point in my quoted post... in fact bearing that in mind maybe its better to merge the info from my earlier post into this guide (instead of quoting it) - make it just one list of non overlapping information.',NULL,NULL),(46123,5917,84499,'2012-08-05 18:44:14','\r\n\r\nwhoops... I think I introduced at least one of those bugs  :evilbunny: \r\n\r\n\r\nthanks lanz :D\r\n\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(46124,5932,84499,'2012-08-05 18:53:56','\r\n\r\n[quote=knickers]No, there it is. It only appears when youre the last poster.\r\n\r\nThe merge button will stop posts being merged. Sensibly its set to merge by default so you have to remember to uncheck it.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nI honestly dont know how sensible it is... or who should and shouldnt have the right to double post? It could be unchecked by default, And should apprentices and pervs not be able to double post? what about good pervs? I guess the purpose of the merge is to prevent spamming up the forums, but how much of a problem is that compared to the inconvinience of having your posts auto-merge? \r\n\r\nPerhaps we should have the default state of the checkbox be different for different classes? maybe everyone can potentially double post but for only say good pervs up / pimps+ / only staff it should be unchecked by default?\r\n\r\n\r\n:hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(46125,5932,1243,'2012-08-05 18:56:40','I hate double posts, and that obviously goes for the gazelle guys too.',NULL,NULL),(46130,5932,84499,'2012-08-05 19:04:58','\r\n\r\nlol, okay :D\r\n\r\n\r\nI am pretty ambivalent. You think its okay as it is now? IIRC apprentices/pervs cannot double post and everyone else can but the default action is to merge.',NULL,NULL),(46131,5932,1243,'2012-08-05 19:12:03','yeah that\'s fine. Looking at it objectively there\'s no need to take it too far. But the only reason I can see for double posting is in for example a funny image thread or similar where you post content for others to watch in some way.',NULL,NULL),(46132,5905,171777,'2012-08-05 19:15:23','changed original post based on what mifune said. please reread.',NULL,NULL),(46133,5926,84499,'2012-08-05 19:21:27','teeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeest',NULL,NULL),(46134,5926,84499,'2012-08-05 19:21:49','tesssssssssssst',NULL,NULL),(46135,5932,171777,'2012-08-05 19:23:25','As I said. Sometimes you might wish to bump a thread to get it in the spotlights again. Like the guide concept I wrote in the staff section. Only after bumping it did people start to respond even though it was there for days already.',NULL,NULL),(46136,5926,84499,'2012-08-05 19:30:23',' :worm: ',NULL,NULL),(46137,5926,84499,'2012-08-05 19:30:32',' :nasher: ',NULL,NULL),(46138,5926,84499,'2012-08-05 19:30:33',' :nasher: ',NULL,NULL),(46139,5926,84499,'2012-08-05 19:30:34',' :nasher: ',NULL,NULL),(46140,5926,84499,'2012-08-05 19:31:37','okay finally... I found that pretty tricky to double post, dunno if its a difference between browsers or the server being a bit quicker :hmmm:\n\nhow big a problem is this?',84499,'2012-08-05 19:32:05'),(46141,5933,84499,'2012-08-05 19:34:37','\r\n\r\ngood point though... we should make a note in the bbcode article that the [code][you][/code] tag is a link itself so cannot be inside [code][url][/code] tags',NULL,NULL),(46142,5875,84499,'2012-08-05 19:36:00','\r\n\r\nI use deluge on linux but I hate it compared to utorrent (2.1.2) :D\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(46143,5926,171777,'2012-08-05 19:52:34','So far I have only found this to be present on the forums. Normally it would not really be a problem were it not for the fact that I have also been doing this without actively clicking the reply button more then once, hence the fact that I started searching for a cause.',NULL,NULL),(46144,5875,171777,'2012-08-05 19:55:06','utorrent 3. something on normal PC but I hardly use it. libtorrent with rutorrent gui on the seedbox.',NULL,NULL),(46145,5933,94952,'2012-08-05 19:55:43','The [code][you][/code]tag creeps me out.  :grin: \nParanoia level: Over 9000',94952,'2012-08-05 19:55:57'),(46146,5875,94952,'2012-08-05 19:59:21','I\'m running Transmission version 1.92. Residing on my NAS connected to my secondary internet 100/10 MBit works like a homemade seedbox',NULL,NULL),(46147,5818,94952,'2012-08-05 20:08:34','Tested out the request/bounty system. Looks good, a lot clearer. \r\n\r\nHowever it took a few seconds for one of my requests to show up. Nothing major but maybe worth testing some more.',NULL,NULL),(46148,5905,84499,'2012-08-05 20:16:26','\r\ncool post it I reckin, if we want to make later changes we can do :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(46149,5926,129045,'2012-08-05 20:27:25','So mashing the button isn\'t the cause? It isn\'t just a server hiccup or something along those lines?\r\n\r\n[quote]So far I have only found this to be present on the forums.[/quote]\r\n\r\nNo idea what could cause accidental double posts, but mashing buttons will have the same behavior everywhere (forum posts and threads as you tested and comments too - Collages, Requests, torrent\'s comments, etc).',NULL,NULL),(46150,5926,171777,'2012-08-05 20:30:02','Just did a little test and yes it also works on torrent comments thus it stands to reason that it works on comments in general.',NULL,NULL),(46151,5926,129045,'2012-08-05 20:33:08','Ok, so can\'t the buttons be disabled after the first click?\r\n\r\nAs for accidental double posts, I have no idea, never experienced one here on EMP.mooo :\\',NULL,NULL),(46152,5905,171777,'2012-08-05 20:33:09','I can only post this as a new topic on the forums since it feels kinda stupid to make this into an article since it will most likely not be needed once the site goes live. So if it is desired to have this on the home page then i\'d like to ask someone else to do that since I don\'t have permissions.',NULL,NULL),(46153,5905,1243,'2012-08-05 21:05:17','Yeah that looks good.',NULL,NULL),(46154,5818,1243,'2012-08-05 21:08:00','That\'s because of how the system works, that wont change unfortunately. The same goes for uploading torrent, it can take up to a minute before it shows up.',NULL,NULL),(46155,5818,94952,'2012-08-05 22:44:44','I see. Well then bug/change req closed. Good job!',NULL,NULL),(46156,5879,84499,'2012-08-05 23:55:07','\r\n\r\nas of right now yes they can add tags to their own uploads.',NULL,NULL),(46157,5934,84499,'2012-08-05 23:59:48','\r\nI have revamped the add/delete tag code slightly, please test!  :smile1: ',NULL,NULL),(46158,5935,94952,'2012-08-06 00:08:38','I can add tags, but the inputbox doesn\'t clear after I add a tag. Intentional? I can not however add the same tag again so that seems to work.\n\nI can not remove or edit tags in my upload [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35209]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35209[/url] Maybe I didn\'t see it in the interface. I\'m gonna go back and hunt for it. I could be that my torrent now is part of a collage that blocks my editability of tags.\n\nWill test some more and update soon.\n\nEdit: Nope. Can\'t find a way to edit my tags.',94952,'2012-08-06 00:16:47'),(46159,5933,85636,'2012-08-06 00:11:35','why would it creep [you] out?',NULL,NULL),(46160,5933,94952,'2012-08-06 00:20:00','I was reading the torrent tutorial last night and it just appeared in the body of the text, in my sleep-deprived mind I wondered if I was used as an example. It never occurred to me that it was tag bound to my username. Well I figured it out after a few minutes. But it gave me a jolt.  :smile2:   ',NULL,NULL),(46161,5935,84499,'2012-08-06 00:27:36',' \r\n\r\nThe uploader not being able to delete tags is deliberate... after some consideration I reckon its a bad idea. While your tag is there it stops anyone else from adding that tag, and in the meantime that tag has probably been voted up or at least not voted down enough to be removed so it should stay I think. There is an argument for being able to delete your own tag before a certain time or if no-one (else) has voted on it, but I\'m not sure its worth the effort to implement that. But I go back to the idea that tags belong to the community as a means to search not to the uploaders presentation.',NULL,NULL),(46162,5935,94952,'2012-08-06 00:36:09','Okay. So then it is working as intended. Basicly the community can remove a tag by down-voting it enough. Makes sense, but a bit annoying if I make a typo or have a total brainfart.\r\n\r\nAnd I agree on your basic idea that a feature freeze are in effect. \r\nSo working as intended. \r\nBut clear the add tag box would be nice, I can\'t really see any reason not to clear it.',NULL,NULL),(46163,5935,84499,'2012-08-06 01:52:38','\r\ntag box now clears (and you can use the enter key to submit again).\r\n\r\nAt least for the moment I enabled adding multiple tags for good perv+.',NULL,NULL),(46164,5935,94952,'2012-08-06 01:54:59','Tested. Works like a charm!',NULL,NULL),(46166,5933,86439,'2012-08-06 02:28:46','[quote=MrRandom]why would it creep [you] out?[/quote]\nit doesnt creep me out. :laugh:',86439,'2012-08-06 02:29:10'),(46167,5936,84499,'2012-08-06 02:38:08','\r\nI added a setting for users to change the style of the time display so you can toggle between time since and date time formats.\r\n\r\nThere are one or two places where it should probably [i]not[/i] change - like in the last forum topics box. Please test and also if anyone spots somewhere else it would make sense to force it to one format or the other let us know.\r\n\r\n :evilbunny: \r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46168,5933,49532,'2012-08-06 02:52:41','[quote=MrRandom]why would it creep [you] out?[/quote]\n\nwhy whould it creep [me] out?     :lol:',49532,'2012-08-06 02:53:28'),(46169,5932,86439,'2012-08-06 02:52:53','[quote=mifune][quote=knickers]No, there it is. It only appears when youre the last poster.\r\n\r\nThe merge button will stop posts being merged. Sensibly its set to merge by default so you have to remember to uncheck it.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nI honestly dont know how sensible it is... or who should and shouldnt have the right to double post? It could be unchecked by default, And should apprentices and pervs not be able to double post? what about good pervs? I guess the purpose of the merge is to prevent spamming up the forums, but how much of a problem is that compared to the inconvinience of having your posts auto-merge? \r\n\r\nPerhaps we should have the default state of the checkbox be different for different classes? maybe everyone can potentially double post but for only say good pervs up / pimps+ / only staff it should be unchecked by default?\r\n\r\n\r\n:hmmm:[/quote]\r\nI think its sensible to have it default to auto-merge, that way it does its job without the poster having to interact with that feature. If for example you want to bump a thread, you deselct it and deliberately double post. Well, its not really double post if days later but you know what I mean. To me it wouldnt make sense to default the opposite way, given its purpose.\r\n\r\nAs for who should, and who shouldnt? I dont know. How big an issue has deliberate double posting been on the main site? Ive seen a few, and Ive made a few due to internal server errors, so I back page, hit post again and boom, both are there. But I havent noticed anyone abusing the ability to double post over there.',NULL,NULL),(46170,5934,86439,'2012-08-06 03:03:33','I can add tags, just added tits.on.a.bull to this torrent http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35220\r\n\r\nBut I have no option to delete tags. Although its not my torrent either.\r\n\r\nAnd just checked one of my own torrents, and I can not remove tags from it either.\n\nOK, I also added -anal, it appeared with 3 votes. I voted it down (-), it went to 2. Green bar appeared telling me it removed my vote for it. I then clicked (-) again, it removed one more point, its now at 1 and a bar appeared saying removed up vote. I clicked (-) again and it stated already voted on it.\r\n\r\nBut it did let me remove 2 votes.',86439,'2012-08-06 03:07:00'),(46171,5936,94952,'2012-08-06 03:10:05','Looks good from what I can see. Feels a litte strange for free leech say \"Freeleech for aug 06 2012, 18:03\". But I can live with that. \r\n\r\nCan we please have a ISO/euro option of the date as in: YYYY-mm-DD HH:MM unless it\'s too mush trouble and/or invites too many dateformat requests,',NULL,NULL),(46172,5934,94952,'2012-08-06 03:12:02','[quote=knickers]\n\nOK, I also added -anal, it appeared with 3 votes. I voted it down (-), it went to 2. Green bar appeared telling me it removed my vote for it. I then clicked (-) again, it removed one more point, its now at 1 and a bar appeared saying removed up vote. I clicked (-) again and it stated already voted on it.\n\nBut it did let me remove 2 votes.[/quote]\n\nSo its not just me happened on one tag I tried but just on so I let it go.\n\nEdit check my post here [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2935]http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2935[/url] Knickers',94952,'2012-08-06 03:13:15'),(46173,5936,86439,'2012-08-06 03:13:16','Edit nevermind, apparently I cant read.',86439,'2012-08-06 03:14:04'),(46174,5932,94952,'2012-08-06 03:14:51','I\'m with Knickers on this one. Scary thought  :wink: ',NULL,NULL),(46175,5933,86439,'2012-08-06 03:15:51','Hey, you are not me.\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-A078_501F1B93.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-A078_501F1B93.jpg[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(46176,5933,94952,'2012-08-06 03:17:10','[user]Mobbo[/user]=[you]  :worm: ',NULL,NULL),(46177,5934,84499,'2012-08-06 03:41:36','[quote=knickers]I can add tags, just added tits.on.a.bull to this torrent http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35220\r\n\r\nBut I have no option to delete tags. Although its not my torrent either.\r\n\r\nAnd just checked one of my own torrents, and I can not remove tags from it either.\r\n\r\nOK, I also added -anal, it appeared with 3 votes. I voted it down (-), it went to 2. Green bar appeared telling me it removed my vote for it. I then clicked (-) again, it removed one more point, its now at 1 and a bar appeared saying removed up vote. I clicked (-) again and it stated already voted on it.\r\n\r\nBut it did let me remove 2 votes.[/quote]\r\n\r\nyou cannot delete tags... they belong to the community! (ie. vote them down)\r\n\r\nit didnt exactly let you remove two votes... it let you remove your implicit up vote from when you added it, then let you down vote it. It could add them with one less vote and with you not having voted on it, which might make more sense in theory but once you understand this do you really want to have to remember to up vote every tag you add?',NULL,NULL),(46178,5936,84499,'2012-08-06 03:45:04','[quote=Mobbo]Looks good from what I can see. Feels a litte strange for free leech say \"Freeleech for aug 06 2012, 18:03\". But I can live with that. \n\nCan we please have a ISO/euro option of the date as in: YYYY-mm-DD HH:MM unless it\'s too mush trouble and/or invites too many dateformat requests,[/quote]\n\nThe freeleech thing should always be in time since/to style - good catch :gjob:\n\nThe date-time format... er I think one date-time format to rule them all is enough, but I dont really care too much what it is (possibly a lie but I dont mind iso format), what do others prefer?',84499,'2012-08-06 03:46:42'),(46179,5936,86439,'2012-08-06 03:50:35','Its all readable.\r\n\r\nI would suggest though, that any posts in the last 24hrs should be how long ago, while older stuff gets time and date. Again though, I have no idea how difficult that is, or worthwhile. i guess its just what Im used to on other forums.\r\n\r\nOr\r\nToday, blah blah\r\nYesterday, blah blah\r\nDate\r\n\r\nOr some such similar.',NULL,NULL),(46180,5934,94952,'2012-08-06 03:51:32','So a new tag is created with 7 votes and then upvoted automaticly to 8. Makes sense. Tested again and I can down vote twice. In essence move the votes between 6 and 8. As expected.\nWhat\'s slightly confusing is that old tags before some code change moves between 7 and 9.\n\nBut the new code works and is logical.  :gjob: \n\nEdit: The old code works the same, just starts with a diffrent value.  :smile2: ',94952,'2012-08-06 03:52:44'),(46181,5934,86439,'2012-08-06 03:59:04','[quote=mifune]\r\n\r\nyou cannot delete tags... they belong to the community! (ie. vote them down)\r\n\r\n[/quote]\r\nIIRC used to have an (x). :sad panda: I just noticed it was gone.\r\n\r\n[quote=mifune]\r\n\r\nit didnt exactly let you remove two votes... it let you remove your implicit up vote from when you added it, then let you down vote it. It could add them with one less vote and with you not having voted on it, which might make more sense in theory but once you understand this do you really want to have to remember to up vote every tag you add?[/quote]\r\nAh all good, that makes sense.\r\n\r\nI seem to recall some time ago (days/weeks) that tags added had a score of 2, so the 3rd is my implicit vote.',NULL,NULL),(46182,5936,94952,'2012-08-06 04:04:35','Freeleech [b]until[/b] yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm\n\nAs for date format I don\'t really care either, but others will (I\'m pretty sure). \n\nMost sites have field in the profile where the user can input his own date format string (raw php date-format).\nOh, timezone offset in the profile since all dates are servertime. I\'m not sure how time is handled so this could be pretty major. Search-replace coding is fast but scary. \n\n\nKnickers idea of hours on less than 24 hours and yesterday is nice, but really necessary I think. Lots of \"if datediffs then\"\n :smile1:   \nAnd you get the hours in the latest forum topics box and mouse-overs.\n\n  ',94952,'2012-08-06 05:50:10'),(46183,5935,51063,'2012-08-06 05:05:27','Marked as fixed!',NULL,NULL),(46184,5925,51063,'2012-08-06 05:08:12','interesting!',NULL,NULL),(46185,5925,51063,'2012-08-06 05:08:58','Hmmm I just did that and fuck all happened let me try again',NULL,NULL),(46186,5925,51063,'2012-08-06 05:10:04','Ok it did not work . . . either it is fixed or it does not do that on Firefox 14.0.1 running on Mac OS X 10.6.8',NULL,NULL),(46187,5935,86439,'2012-08-06 05:14:55','^^^ Burn the witch.',NULL,NULL),(46188,5879,51063,'2012-08-06 05:24:14','This is solved now right?  I know it got very very off topic but the original question and follow up questions have been answered right?\r\n\r\nI am marking this as done.  If some other staffer disagrees change the title back!',NULL,NULL),(46189,5937,86439,'2012-08-06 05:24:27','Time format seems to display wrong time. Or is it using site time? Gary Es posts were not done at 5:05 or 5:10 my time.\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-6914_501F3DEF.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-6914_501F3DEF.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-6624_501F3DEF.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-6624_501F3DEF.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n\nOriginal text, seems unlikely its a bug, just a quirk. But the above is still true.\n\n[s]Not sure if this is a bug, or some other quirk. But since the time format was changed, the icons indicating new posts etc are not changing colour.\n\nGary E\'s posts (bugs) had not been viewed by me, but the forums in which they appear were still dulled, as was the individual thread icons. Until someone else posts I cant replicate it.[/s]\n\nEdit: I now see Gary Es subsequent posts and the icon is darker blue.\n\n\n\n\n',86439,'2012-08-06 05:43:04'),(46190,5935,49532,'2012-08-06 05:28:05','I added 2 tags at once: both added and both up voted\r\nAdded 2 tags, one of swhich already existed: the new tag added and up voted, the existing tag upvoted.\r\n\r\nIt\'s working as intened, but I don\'t like the automatic up vote.',NULL,NULL),(46191,5937,94952,'2012-08-06 05:28:47','Strange, it works for me.',NULL,NULL),(46192,5938,49532,'2012-08-06 05:33:54','Sometimes, when I submit a new posting, the [b]latest forum posts[/b] list it as [b]2 minutes ago[/b] or [b]5 minuts ago[/b] instead of [b]Just now[/b]',NULL,NULL),(46193,5754,51063,'2012-08-06 05:40:47','Yeah it is a bit of work there are a lot of places where the uploaders name is shown and you need to make sure on each of those that it shows anonymous unless your user class is Mod or higher . . . it is not difficult but it is pretty tedious.  On the other place where I staff it is shown as\r\n\r\nanonymous (real name here) for staff (and the uploader) and just anonymous for everyone else  . . . except for the torrent list/browse list whatever you want to call it . . . where it shows real name for staff (and uploader) and anonymous for everyone else.\r\n\r\nJust to be clear if/when you do this the uploaders name appears:\r\n1) on the browse list\r\n2) on the mouse over on the browse list\r\n3) on the torrent page where the uploaders name appears\r\n4) on the torrent page under seeders (or leechers for the dumb asses)\r\n5) in comments on the torrent page\r\n\r\nAt least that is all I can come up with . . . so as Lanz implied it is not a trivial thing to implement.\r\n\r\nThe reason I mention this is because on one site I (and mifune) am a member of during testing no one was bright enough to notice that when you upload anonymously the uploaders name appears anonymously everywhere . . . except for the \"upload by\" field :facepalm: and in the comments.',NULL,NULL),(46194,5776,49532,'2012-08-06 05:41:57','s\r\n[quote=Lanz]:hmm: need to think about that.[/quote]\r\nnow that you\'ve ad time to think about it have you made any decisions?\r\n\r\nIs it dead in the water, still underconsideration, or planned for a later update?',NULL,NULL),(46195,5937,51063,'2012-08-06 05:44:09','Title changed to timestamp is not specific to users timezone per knickers request',51063,'2012-08-06 05:44:47'),(46196,5937,86439,'2012-08-06 05:44:46','[quote=Mobbo]Strange, it works for me.[/quote]\r\nYeah, its not doing it now. No idea why it did it before, but its now acting correctly re: icon changing colour.\r\n\r\nIve changed the thread context anyway. Times are not correct in relation to me.\n\n[quote=GaryE]Title changed to timestamp is not specific to users timezone per knickers request[/quote]\r\nThanks Gary.',86439,'2012-08-06 05:45:36'),(46197,5937,94952,'2012-08-06 05:51:59','That\'s why I called for a timezone offset on the profile page. To avoid confusion.\r\n[url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2936#post26182]http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2936#post26182[/url]',NULL,NULL),(46198,5933,37338,'2012-08-06 06:02:38','My mind is getting fucked while I\'m looking for stuff that involves fucking....Inception ',NULL,NULL),(46199,5899,51063,'2012-08-06 06:03:41','It does not matter how many people are leeching at the same time leeching does not generate more load than seeding.  We need to test the tracker and how it handles hundreds of updates at the same time . . . we do not need to test how the torrent client handles receiving data from 200 other peers.',NULL,NULL),(46200,5863,51063,'2012-08-06 06:06:28','Not axing seedbox users is very simple mate . . . you do a whois on the IP address to determine the host.  On PB we do that by making the IP address in the cheat report clickable which redirects to a site that automagically does a whois on the address.\r\n\r\nSometimes the free web-based whois does not give the data you want and you need to run it manually on your own computer . . . but that is pretty rare.',NULL,NULL),(46201,5939,51063,'2012-08-06 06:09:54','I just checked all of the torrents on the first page and sent out about 6 or 8 auto pm\'s and marked them for auto deletion.\r\n\r\nI am pretty sure I remember seeing a post somewhere which stated that we are starting to treat this like the main site . . . so I took that ball and ran with it.\r\n\r\nIf I am incorrect . . . oh well someone please fix those 8 I marked for deletion and you have my apologies (for making more work for you).',NULL,NULL),(46202,5940,51063,'2012-08-06 06:16:10','When I go to a forum . . . say this one http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewforum&forumid=3  and I click on the catch up link at the bottom of the page it does not mark all of the unread threads in that forum section as read.\r\n\r\nI am desperately trying to catch up in all of the forums here so this might have already been posted and I have just not gotten to it yet . . . if this has already been reported this can be deleted and sorry for the confusion!\n\n---- Edit\r\n\r\nI have tested it with several other sections and it does not work anywhere for me ;-(',51063,'2012-08-06 06:20:24'),(46203,5863,47234,'2012-08-06 06:19:32','I love that idea Gary :)',NULL,NULL),(46204,5938,51063,'2012-08-06 06:22:25','I am not certain but I would guess that is because of all of the caching that occurs with this code base . . . Lanz or mifune will have to confirm or deny that.',NULL,NULL),(46205,5938,49532,'2012-08-06 06:23:33','that would have the opposite effect',NULL,NULL),(46206,5940,94952,'2012-08-06 06:25:18','I can confirm only the newest (top) thread is marked as read. And all stickies.\n\nEdit: If sticky thread(s) exists the get marked as read, all of them and nothing else. If not just the newest thread gets marked as read.',94952,'2012-08-06 06:31:00'),(46207,5940,51063,'2012-08-06 06:25:21','---- Edit 2\n\nClarification . . . the forums has unread messages tag on the main forum list (the unread indicator on this page http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php) does get cleared . . . however the individual threads/posts do not get marked as read . . . interesting feature!',51063,'2012-08-06 06:26:42'),(46208,5940,94952,'2012-08-06 06:27:43','Yeah, in the forum list the subforum get marked as all read.',NULL,NULL),(46209,5933,67255,'2012-08-06 06:33:24','I was thinking...[img]http://i.imgbox.com/acbOhr4s.png[/img] this is fucked up :banghead: ',67255,'2012-08-06 06:33:54'),(46210,5933,47234,'2012-08-06 06:42:05','That [code][you][/code] Is rather frightening.   I can see a lot of worried Pervs the first time they see some of those sigs :lol:',NULL,NULL),(46211,5941,94952,'2012-08-06 06:52:01','[b]URL:[/b] [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php]http://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php[/url]\r\n[b]What:[/b] Checkbox label is now \"Pesonal\" should be \"Personal\" \r\n[b]Reproduce:[/b] Go to URL  :smile1: ',NULL,NULL),(46212,5936,171777,'2012-08-06 07:11:47','In all honesty I don\'t like ISO. It is very confusing since in my country we write time as DD-MM instead of the other way around.',NULL,NULL),(46213,5754,171777,'2012-08-06 07:15:07','1-4 very logical but why number 5? In the comments there is no way to differentiate between who uploaded, downloaded or just came to take a look. Well unless the uploader is stupid enough to say: I UPLOADED THIS!',NULL,NULL),(46214,5776,171777,'2012-08-06 07:17:49','Personally I vote against this. It makes it a lot easier to link the xxx.image.us website to the tracker and technically even uploading images taken from videos is a crime (still copyrighted material though a lot harder to proof anything by). Not to mention that those sites are publicly accessible thus making it very easy to look around.',NULL,NULL),(46215,5941,171777,'2012-08-06 07:22:35','Confirmed:\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=07BE_501F556D][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=07BE_501F556D&jpg[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(46216,5936,49532,'2012-08-06 07:26:16','I like ISO format it is the most universal\r\n\r\ndd-mm-yyyy and mm-dd-yyyy are both too confusing, to those who use the other, but yyyy-mm-dd is understandable, because noone uses yyyy-dd-mm',NULL,NULL),(46217,5776,49532,'2012-08-06 07:29:52','[quote=DrkNess]Personally I vote against this. It makes it a lot easier to link the xxx.image.us website to the tracker and technically even uploading images taken from videos is a crime (still copyrighted material though a lot harder to proof anything by). Not to mention that those sites are publicly accessible thus making it very easy to look around.[/quote]\n\nThe link between empornium.me and xxx.freeimage.us is already very obvious. I don\'t think that\'s really a consideration.',49532,'2012-08-06 07:30:58'),(46218,5933,86439,'2012-08-06 07:42:16','First time I saw it, I was wondering why the fuck does MrRandom want me in IRC, not only in IRC but so badly he made it his sig and not a PM? I noticed knickers was a link, but you know these things dont necessarily mean anything. Then I noticed DrkNess had the same impression and I clicked, its some code thing.\r\n\r\nSo I noticed a few sigs with it and decided on what I assumed would invoke the most paranoia I could muster.',NULL,NULL),(46219,5933,171777,'2012-08-06 08:00:38','Yep it really had me going the first time I saw it.... IMHO it is friggin annoying but that might just be me.',NULL,NULL),(46220,5942,49532,'2012-08-06 08:40:49','I predict a large problem, of people voting tags up and down, based on preference instead of applicability.  I know it\'s in the tagging rules, but I expect that many people won\'t bother to read the rules before voting.\n\n\nI sugest that above the tags you put: [quote][b]Please vote for tags [i][color=#FF0000]only[/color][/i] based on thir apropriatness for this upload[/b].[/quote]',49532,'2012-08-06 09:33:03'),(46221,5942,94952,'2012-08-06 08:52:02','I agree.',NULL,NULL),(46222,5943,49532,'2012-08-06 09:02:15','[s]In my external [url=http://lorem.us/empornium.css]stylesheet[/url], I reference local Empornium images, but the images don\'t show up.  e.g.:\n\n[code]\n.unread_locked_sticky{background: url(\'http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/locked_sticky_unread.png\') no-repeat center center;}\n.read_locked_sticky{background: url(\'http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/locked_sticky_read.png\') no-repeat center center;}\n.read_sticky{background: url(\'http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/sticky_read.png\') no-repeat center center;}\n.unread_sticky{background: url(\'http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/sticky_unread.png\') no-repeat center center;}\n.unread_locked{background: url(\'http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/locked_unread.png\') no-repeat center center;}\n.read_locked{background: url(\'http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/locked_read.png\') no-repeat center center;}\n.unread{background: url(\'http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/unread.png\') no-repeat center center;}\n.read{background: url(\'http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/read.png\') no-repeat center center;}\n[/code]\'\n\nI suspect this is because of something with the file permissions.\n\n[/s]\nEdit: not a bug',49532,'2012-08-07 00:59:31'),(46223,5942,47234,'2012-08-06 12:03:53','Sadly people wont even read that bit either :sigh:\r\n\r\nBut not a bad idea',NULL,NULL),(46224,5944,5825,'2012-08-06 12:42:15','How about this: the ability too edit ones feed to only include specific categories and or tags.',NULL,NULL),(46225,5933,70679,'2012-08-06 15:06:41','[you] I am watching you be careful....\n\nyeah is unsettling  :w00t: \n\nBut of course could not resist to the temptation... :laugh: ',70679,'2012-08-06 15:23:40'),(46226,5944,70679,'2012-08-06 15:29:17','AFAIK is already there under your nick -> notifications.\r\n\r\nBut also had a hard time finding it as I was also looking for RSS so maybe some change to make it clearer?\r\n\r\nChange Notification to RSS or to Notifications (RSS)?',NULL,NULL),(46227,5942,94804,'2012-08-06 16:37:50','advocate of devil here: why even the possibility of rating?',NULL,NULL),(46228,5942,86439,'2012-08-06 16:44:16','[quote=schlager]advocate of devil here: why even the possibility of rating?[/quote]\nCant call it Community Tagging without that aspect.\n\nTags tend to be, lets say kooky. As someone pointed out, pot.plant could be a tag. Moreover, hot has been a tag. People tag things with aspects not actually in the clip, it simply generates hits on their torrent. When that happens the usefulness of tags is lost and they may as well be banned, they are more like spam at that point. The alternative is to make staff take care of them... all of them.\n\nLook at it like minimum standards for clips uploaded. Without it, theres just no quality control. This is something that hopefully the members are mature enough to handle. Who knows, you can only give it a go.',86439,'2012-08-06 16:45:43'),(46229,5936,84499,'2012-08-06 16:57:15','\r\n\r\nISO time is universal - and I use it all the time mainly for when you want dates to order correctly.. but can anyone really not understand Aug 06 2012 ? For me thats the most human readable format by a long way.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46230,5935,84499,'2012-08-06 16:59:40','\r\n\r\nyou mean you want added tags to not have an automatic up vote from the adder?',NULL,NULL),(46231,5942,94804,'2012-08-06 17:15:26','yeah,agreed \"overtagging\" is a problem\nand it indeed Ã­s called Community Tagging \ncan\'t we award some sort of stimulus for (the approriate voting of) tagging?\nbest idea EVER Mifune ;)',94804,'2012-08-06 17:15:49'),(46232,5936,94952,'2012-08-06 17:27:20','[quote=mifune]ISO time is universal - and I use it all the time mainly for when you want dates to order correctly.. but can anyone really not understand Aug 06 2012 ? For me thats the most human readable format by a long way.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI agree. Kinda stupid to open that can of worms.   :sorry: ',NULL,NULL),(46233,5936,94804,'2012-08-06 17:35:17','Mobbo is scared of schlager\r\nwhy? I\'m kindness itself!',NULL,NULL),(46234,5936,1243,'2012-08-06 20:03:30','[quote=mifune]ISO time is universal - and I use it all the time mainly for when you want dates to order correctly.. but can anyone really not understand Aug 06 2012 ? For me thats the most human readable format by a long way.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYes that is perfectly good enough.',NULL,NULL),(46235,5942,1243,'2012-08-06 20:06:11','[quote=schlager]can\'t we award some sort of stimulus for (the approriate voting of) tagging?[/quote]\r\nNope, we are not gonna go down that rode.\r\n\r\n[quote=schlager]best idea EVER Mifune ;)[/quote]\r\nNot to sound crankier than I am, but that function was built in to Gazelle already.',NULL,NULL),(46236,5942,94804,'2012-08-06 20:31:19','sorry, but I don\'t know Gazelle. Yeah after typing it, I realised the stupidity of that idea',NULL,NULL),(46237,5936,94804,'2012-08-06 20:32:13','[quote=Lanz][quote=mifune]ISO time is universal - and I use it all the time mainly for when you want dates to order correctly.. but can anyone really not understand Aug 06 2012 ? For me thats the most human readable format by a long way.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYes that is perfectly good enough.[/quote] agreed',NULL,NULL),(46238,5945,94804,'2012-08-06 20:34:38','even gifs works with cover-image! Great!',NULL,NULL),(46239,5945,84499,'2012-08-06 20:41:06','\r\n\r\nhmmmm... which reminds me, we should probably limit the size of certain images a bit more :lol: I dont think we want 2mb cover images, they get loaded on the mouseover in torrents as well as the collages page etc. ',NULL,NULL),(46240,5945,94804,'2012-08-06 20:42:08',':) yeah',NULL,NULL),(46241,5946,94804,'2012-08-06 20:49:37','I wanted to delete my own torrent because the description was too short, but got this: You can no longer delete this torrent as it has been uploaded for over a week with no problems. If you now think there is a problem, please report it instead. Why is that? I don\'t see the benefits of it. Enlighten me, please',NULL,NULL),(46242,5645,70679,'2012-08-06 20:50:44','bump to relaunch this also as a suggestion to implement the mouse over load pics view feature.',NULL,NULL),(46243,5935,49532,'2012-08-06 20:55:47','[quote=mifune]you mean you want added tags to not have an automatic up vote from the adder?[/quote]\r\nyes, thats what I mean',NULL,NULL),(46244,5935,84499,'2012-08-06 20:58:44','\r\nI think most users who add a tag will want to vote that tag up, making them click again once for each tag seems like a needless task. :dunno:',NULL,NULL),(46245,5946,49532,'2012-08-06 20:58:53','[quote=schlager]I wanted to delete my own torrent because the description was too short, but got this: You can no longer delete this torrent as it has been uploaded for over a week with no problems. If you now think there is a problem, please report it instead. Why is that? I don\'t see the benefits of it. Enlighten me, please[/quote]\r\n\r\nThis isn\'t a bug, it\'s a feature.',NULL,NULL),(46246,5935,49532,'2012-08-06 21:02:50','Yes they most likely want to do it, but they also want to know that they are doing it, and choose to do it. Manually voting it up feels better to me.',NULL,NULL),(46247,5935,84499,'2012-08-06 21:07:29','\r\nWell as you dont mind clicking you are welcome to remove your (automatic) up votes from all your tags and then vote them up again :D\r\n\r\n\r\nIf there is enough demand we could add a user setting for whether your tags are added with an upvote or not, I\'m not at all sure there is a need though.',NULL,NULL),(46248,5946,94804,'2012-08-06 21:11:59','yeah, thought so. But what\'s the use, for torrents with only 1 seed I understand, but multiple seeds?',NULL,NULL),(46249,5947,94804,'2012-08-06 21:17:49','Just noticed that on this (test)server I got a higher rank than on the regular server. Why?',NULL,NULL),(46250,5947,1243,'2012-08-06 21:37:13','I guess you got promoted because of a problem you might have had based on class permissions. So to get that confirmed (mifune?) promoted you.',NULL,NULL),(46251,5947,84499,'2012-08-06 22:29:21','[quote]2012-08-04 01:00:18 - Class changed to Sextreme Perv by System[/quote]\r\n[quote][b][color=orange]Sextreme Perv[/color] [/b]\r\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 26 weeks\r\n[*]have uploaded at least 1TB \r\n[*]have uploaded 50 torrents \r\n[*]have a ratio at or above 1.05\r\n[*]The promotion is automatic when these conditions are met.\r\n[*]Note that you will be automatically demoted if your ratio drops below 0.95 at any time.[/quote]\r\n\r\n :smile1: ',NULL,NULL),(46252,5935,86439,'2012-08-06 22:47:52','Seems pointless to alter the status quo to me.\n\nEdit: Clarification as that statement could be ambiguous. A date format is a date format. Whichever one is selected will cause the ire in those used to the alternative. 9/11, 11/9 for example. The current one does the job and is easy to read.\n',86439,'2012-08-07 00:28:26'),(46253,5645,171777,'2012-08-06 22:50:07','just noticed this topic because it was bumped... I\'ll take a look when it is not the middle of the night.',NULL,NULL),(46254,5947,94804,'2012-08-06 22:52:09','ok, thanks!',NULL,NULL),(46255,5947,1243,'2012-08-06 23:27:15','yeah even more obvious :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(46256,5943,129045,'2012-08-07 00:03:02','I can\'t replicate it. Grabbing the default CSS and making changes to it will still display the images just fine :hmmm:\r\n\r\nIs that stylesheet displaying correct for you? Here apart from the lack of those icons, it\'ll also cause some inconsistencies with the user avatar\\medals\\plaques area:\r\n\r\nhttp://lorem.us/empornium.css\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=285D_50203F0D][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=285D_50203F0D[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nShould be more like this:\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=6110_50203F0D][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=6110_50203F0D[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nWhatever you changed, it isn\'t playing nicely with other elements.',NULL,NULL),(46257,5943,49532,'2012-08-07 00:17:40','Last week I grabbed the default stylesheet, and made font changes, to test google fonts.\nYesterday I added absolute paths to the urls, to test image laoding. The images I mentioned, were the only ones that didnt load, that I found so far. All the other problems, that you showed, were not part of my test.\n\nEdit:  I regrabbed the current default stylesheet. and added absolute paths to the urls.  Now the Icons are showing.  ',49532,'2012-08-07 00:33:31'),(46258,5943,129045,'2012-08-07 00:54:13','[s]Can you reproduce the problem with the latest CSS file? I just tried what you said, simple font change + absolute paths: http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/EMP-.css\r\n\r\nImages loading fine here, only other change is that I re-added borders to the forum\'s thread list, trying to match your stylesheet.\r\n\r\nMaybe it\'s caused by the CSS file not playing together with whatever recent changes the site got?[/s]\r\n\r\nD\'oh. I\'m slow. Should have reloaded the page before posting -_-',129045,'2012-08-07 00:55:26'),(46259,5946,129045,'2012-08-07 01:43:16','Deleting for trivial reasons would only cause problems. [b]When you delete a torrent, the Tracker drops it. That kills the torrent for everybody.[/b] Doesn\'t matter the quantity of Seeders or Leechers, no one will be able to seed or complete their uploads after you delete it.\r\n\r\nIf the description wasn\'t quite like you wanted, you could simply edit it.',NULL,NULL),(46260,5939,84499,'2012-08-07 02:43:54','\nno thats fine.\n\nI have just slightly modified the torrents review interface so the accept/reject buttons are only shown once the user has responded. \n\nI have been meaning to do this for a while so here is a beginning to a staff/fls guide to the torrents review system: \n(And we will need to do a user guide to the torrents review system as well I reckon).\n\n[b][size=3]1) Status: None (An unreviewed torrent)[/size][/b]\nstaff have the option to mark as okay or select a reason to mark for deletion\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adgdNocE.png[/img]\n\n\n[b][size=3]2a) Status: Warned.[/size][/b]\n[b]Staff with torrents review permission will see this: [/b]\nthere are no actions that can be carried out until the uploader responds.\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/acorRvJa.png[/img]\n\n[b]Staff with override torrents review permission will see this: [/b]\nyou can override or reset the warning - be aware that if you set another warning it generates a fresh pm and resets the auto-delete timer. \n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adsiH6XW.png[/img]\n\n\n[b][size=3]2b) Status: Warned.[/size][/b]\n[b]What the uploader sees: [/b]\nThe uploader gets a PM telling them what they need to do:\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adm8VkKy.png[/img]\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adlLBqNQ.png[/img]\n\nOn the torrent detail page there is the green button for them to tell the staff they have fixed it:\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/acuQUEr3.png[/img]\nOnce they click the button the status is \'pending\' - although to users it still appears as \'warned\'.\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adq9K7uw.png[/img]\n\n\n[b][size=3]3) Status: Pending.[/size][/b]\n[b]Staff with torrents review permission will see this: [/b]\nYou can accept or reject the fix. If accepted the status is set to okay, if rejected the uploader gets another message telling them it still needs fixing and the status is set back to warned.\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/abf5LJ34.png[/img]\n[b]Staff with override torrents review permission will see this: [/b]\nYou can accept or reject the fix, or you can set a new warning - be aware that if you set another warning it sets the status to warned and generates a new message and resets the auto-delete timer. \n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/ace0Spuh.png[/img]\n\n\n[b][size=3]4) Status: Okay.[/size][/b]\nIf a torrent has been marked okay it will allow all staff/fls to set the status to warned but it will give a warning message in red:\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/ace3anKU.png[/img]\n\n\nThe system should always close any message conversation once the status is set to okay or the torrent is deleted. There was an edge case bug where you could end up with two conversations which should be fixed so there should only ever be one conversation attached to one torrents reviews, and it should always automatically be closed properly.\n\n \n',84499,'2012-08-07 02:50:22'),(46261,5939,86439,'2012-08-07 02:50:34','Just a thought, not sure if overlooked, or just not mentioned how it will be handled, but I note that the options for dealing with said torrents is dulled until responded to, what happens if the uploader does not respond, or they take a week to log back in etc? Should there be a time up thingamejigame where it automatically assumes a response, or a reaction to non-response?\r\n\r\nIf its not an issue, ignore me. Its just something that occurred to me as I read that Mifune.',NULL,NULL),(46262,5939,84499,'2012-08-07 02:56:26','\r\n \r\nis it really not obvious that it will be automatically deleted? :hmmm:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46263,5939,86439,'2012-08-07 03:00:09','As I said, ignore me. :lol:\r\n\r\nIt is now. :smart:',NULL,NULL),(46264,5939,84499,'2012-08-07 03:01:20','[quote]Your upload Kuras does not meet our standards for uploading and has been marked for deletion.\n\n[b][size=2]It will be automatically deleted if you do not fix your upload in the next 24 hours  (Aug 08 2012, 00:53).[/size]\n\nOnce you have fixed your upload be sure to click the green button at the top of the torrent page to send the staff a message telling them you have done so. [/b]\n\nReason:  [color=#FF0000][b]Not enough screenshots.[/b][/color]\n\nPlease make sure you read the Upload Rules\nYou will find useful guides in the Tutorials section\nIf you need further help please post in the Help & Support Forum [/quote]\n\n:lol:\n ',84499,'2012-08-07 03:01:35'),(46265,5939,86439,'2012-08-07 03:13:44','[quote=mifune][quote]Your upload Kuras does not meet our standards for uploading and has been marked for deletion.\r\n\r\n[b][size=2]It will be automatically deleted if you do not fix your upload in the next 24 hours  (Aug 08 2012, 00:53).[/size]\r\n\r\nOnce you have fixed your upload be sure to click the green button at the top of the torrent page to send the staff a message telling them you have done so. [/b]\r\n\r\nReason:  [color=#FF0000][b]Not enough screenshots.[/b][/color]\r\n\r\nPlease make sure you read the Upload Rules\r\nYou will find useful guides in the Tutorials section\r\nIf you need further help please post in the Help & Support Forum [/quote]\r\n\r\n:lol:[/quote]\r\nSo technically that would be the time out ... no I wont go there. I cant defend my idiocy as it is. \r\n\r\nNothing to see here, move along.',NULL,NULL),(46266,5939,84499,'2012-08-07 03:18:33','\r\n\r\nIf something isnt obvious I genuinely want to know... I like designing systems that are easy to use and that requires feedback from testers. Useability is something that you can strive to acheive but the coder always has a blindspot as they understand the system from the other side too well to see it from a users pov.',NULL,NULL),(46267,5946,51063,'2012-08-07 03:34:52','The benefits are that some wanker who gets pissed off at staff for some perceived slight can not delete all of his torrents and bugger off in a huff often leaving hundreds (if not thousands) of users in the lurch.  I can not tell you how often this happened on the old site and it has happened on the present site more than a few times.\r\n\r\nIt is a royal pain in the ass the forums fill up with first time posters saying why I am getting the \"Error: torrent does not exist\" (or whatever the exact text is) message.  Not to mention that the act is cowardly, petty, and childish LOL\r\n\r\nHaving said that this is the first I have heard of this feature . . . but I love it and I will defend it!\r\n\r\n\r\nI mean in one case this id-10-t deleted all of his torrents because a staffer had the gall to fix a few of his uploads that were sub-standard.  Yeah you did not delete my torrent and instead you fixed it for me and did not even bitch at me . . . I will show you bastards I will delete all of my torrents!\r\n\r\nSeriously that happened about what 6 weeks ago on the main site.',NULL,NULL),(46268,5935,51063,'2012-08-07 03:37:51','Which is why I am a fan of 11SEP instead . . . no confusion for people who are used to reading the date one way or another. :D',NULL,NULL),(46269,5946,84499,'2012-08-07 03:38:00','\r\n\r\nhe had quite a few torrents as well, iirc it took him over an hour to delete all 60 or so :lol:',NULL,NULL),(462