NULL),(46277,5754,51063,'2012-08-07 03:59:09','Good question . . . let us say someone asks the upload a specific question . . . for example \"Does this have subtitles?\".  Then let us suppose that the torrent is still only being seeded by the uploader and someone answers . . . yes it does . . . then bingo everyone knows who the uploader was.\r\n\r\nThat is just one example . . . there are lots of others.  When we first implemented anonymous uploads on that other site where I staff we did not anonymize (is that a word) the uploaders torrent comments and most of the uploaders immediately asked for the features.\r\n\r\nSo call it experience but that feature will get requested (if nothing else by me LOL).',NULL,NULL),(46278,5934,84499,'2012-08-07 04:04:48','\r\n\r\nif you can also test voting tags up and down, when they go below 0 they should be removed (and the taglist for that updated properly etc.).\r\n\r\nI set it so all the FLS as well as staff can delete tags directly too. Although I dont think users should be able to delete tags directly I think FLS/staff should just delete misspellings or stupidity in tags.\r\n\r\nThere might still be a mismatch in votes applied when adding through uploading or from the page (for the uploader), although maybe its just with imported data.',NULL,NULL),(46279,5946,49532,'2012-08-07 04:05:11','[quote=GaryE]Good man!  I love that show!!!!  I am anxiously awaiting the new season to be shown here in the US . . . but to be honest I do not know if it has been shown in the UK yet.[/quote]\r\nNew season?????????     I wasn\'t even born when that went on the air. Is this a reboot like with Dr Who?\r\nA new season with the original cast would be fucking awsome!!!!!',NULL,NULL),(46280,5936,51063,'2012-08-07 04:08:53','FWIW I prefer ddMMMyy or ddMMMyyyy but that is more or less the same as what mifune suggested so never mind.',NULL,NULL),(46281,5754,84499,'2012-08-07 04:10:22','\r\nplus...\r\n\r\nlogs\r\ncollages\r\nsnatches list\r\nrequest list\r\ntorrent page: downloaded list, snatched list\r\n\r\nI will bet there is more too.\r\n\r\nI want to wrap this project up pretty soon lol.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46282,5934,86439,'2012-08-07 04:10:42','This torrent has one tag at 0, so one more (-) vote should kill it. Ive already done mine, so cant again.\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35220#tags\n\nEdit: This one above seems to be gone now. As there are none with 0. Still some close to 0 though.\n\n\n\n\nThis next one has two ready to kill.\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35177#tags\nhuge.cock\n[-] 0 [+] \n\nstrapon\n[-] 0 [+] \n\n\n\n\n\nVoting tags up seems to work as it should, will only let me add the one vote.\n\nJust voted down, then voted up, message stated removed down vote, then voted up again, and it added my vote. End result was +1 from when i first played with it. Perfect.',86439,'2012-08-07 04:24:24'),(46283,5934,51063,'2012-08-07 04:11:23','I think usb\'s votes and my votes on tags should count as 10 regular votes that way we can quickly remove all but one or two tags from every upload!\n\n\nOk not really just kidding (I am pretty punchy tonight because I find this hilarious)',51063,'2012-08-07 04:11:36'),(46284,5946,51063,'2012-08-07 04:26:19','Shooting wrapped about 4 or 5 months ago IIRC . . . I follow Kryten (what is his real name I just drew a blank . . . David/Doug Llewelin??? (sp?) I think) on twitter and he tweeted about a new series about IDK 6 or 7 months ago.  That is the only reason I know about it.  The producers were worried that the show would no longer be popular.  When the tickets were announced as available . . . I think it took less than 36 hours (maybe even less but I can not really remember) for them to get snatched up.  LOL no longer popular my ass LOL.\r\n\r\nIf you did not know about the new series did you ever the three episode series \"Red Dwarf: Back to Earth\" To the best of my knowledge it never got shown in the US (I got it on the pirate bay LOL).\r\n\r\nThe newest series is with all of the original cast.  When I asked the question I was told it would be broadcast in the US at more or less the same time as in the UK.  In the UK it will be shown on the Dave network (I only know the name of the network I do not think I had ever heard of it before) I have not heard what network will show it in the US but I think PBS is the safe bet because Red Dwarf has never been shown on any other network in the US (at least that I am aware of).  I know my DVR is set to record and save every instance of Red Dwarf regardless of network.  I am not going to miss it!\r\n\r\nThe show was first on the air in 1987 IIRC I think the last series \"back to earth\" was made in about 2006 or 8 which you certainly were alive for ;-)  (it was 2009 according to wiki)',NULL,NULL),(46285,5935,84499,'2012-08-07 04:26:54','\r\n[quote=knickers]Seems pointless to alter the status quo to me.\r\n\r\nEdit: Clarification as that statement could be ambiguous. A date format is a date format. Whichever one is selected will cause the ire in those used to the alternative. 9/11, 11/9 for example. The current one does the job and is easy to read.[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=GaryE]Which is why I am a fan of 11SEP instead . . . no confusion for people who are used to reading the date one way or another. :D[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nand time formats are relevant to tagging because...\r\n\r\n:lol:',NULL,NULL),(46286,5948,49532,'2012-08-07 04:27:14','when I moused over [b]Seduced By A Cougar Eva Notty - 2012-08-06 *EARLY SCENE* [1080p HD][MP4] [/b] it took about 4 seconds for the civer to load (it loaded imediatly once cached). Has anyone else had slow cover loads?\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46287,5935,49532,'2012-08-07 04:29:56','[quote=mifune]Well as you dont mind clicking you are welcome to remove your (automatic) up votes from all your tags and then vote them up again :D\r\n\r\n\r\nIf there is enough demand we could add a user setting for whether your tags are added with an upvote or not, I\'m not at all sure there is a need though.[/quote] It\'s not about clicks it\'s about clarity.  The current way will confuse a lot of people.',NULL,NULL),(46288,5948,51063,'2012-08-07 04:32:24','I asked apparition to start this thread he/she/she/they reported the torrent and I did not notice a problem.  apparition (rightly) questioned whether it was in my cache.  I tried another browser and it only took about 1/2 a second.  But since I have pretty stupid speed (75/35) I realize that I am not the best judge.  So I asked apparition to start this thread.\r\n\r\nPlease try it in other browsers than your main browser in case you already have it in your cache as well.\r\n\r\nThanks for starting the thread and for the report!\r\n\r\nPlease everyone report your results!',NULL,NULL),(46289,5935,51063,'2012-08-07 04:34:19','[quote=mifune][quote=knickers]Seems pointless to alter the status quo to me.\r\n\r\nEdit: Clarification as that statement could be ambiguous. A date format is a date format. Whichever one is selected will cause the ire in those used to the alternative. 9/11, 11/9 for example. The current one does the job and is easy to read.[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=GaryE]Which is why I am a fan of 11SEP instead . . . no confusion for people who are used to reading the date one way or another. :D[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nand time formats are relevant to tagging because...\r\n\r\n:lol:[/quote]\r\n\r\nDo not ask me . . . I view hundreds of threads a day . . . you have got to give me one or two slip-ups a day LOL',NULL,NULL),(46290,5754,51063,'2012-08-07 04:35:17','Yeah it is not a trivial change LOL',NULL,NULL),(46291,5935,86439,'2012-08-07 04:38:41','[quote=mifune][quote=knickers]Seems pointless to alter the status quo to me.\n\nEdit: Clarification as that statement could be ambiguous. A date format is a date format. Whichever one is selected will cause the ire in those used to the alternative. 9/11, 11/9 for example. The current one does the job and is easy to read.[/quote]\n\n[quote=GaryE]Which is why I am a fan of 11SEP instead . . . no confusion for people who are used to reading the date one way or another. :D[/quote]\n\n\nand time formats are relevant to tagging because...\n\n:lol:[/quote]\noh poop.\n\nToo many tabs open. The first part belongs in this thread, the clarification does not.',86439,'2012-08-07 04:39:49'),(46292,5948,129045,'2012-08-07 04:39:46','...\r\n\r\nWhat exactly are you trying to find out?\r\n\r\nThe images aren\'t hosted on EMP, the site is only responsible to bring up the popup (happens instantly as soon as you hover the torrent name), after that, it\'ll be up to the imagehost and your connection to do the job. Another thing to keep in mind, the cover image is actually the fullres image, it\'s size is only constrained to that small area in the tooltip.\r\n\r\nDifferent connections speeds, different results.\r\n\r\nAll browsers here:\r\n\r\n2-5 seconds for JPG (not stupid large images)\r\n\r\nAnd my connection chokes on GIF\'s, so that may take up to a minute to load.',129045,'2012-08-07 04:41:07'),(46293,5949,51063,'2012-08-07 04:40:09','http://empornium.mooo.com/reportsv2.php\n\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1095_50208094][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=1095_50208094&jpg[/img][/url]\n\nI think that should read tested or at the very least something other than tasted or am I missing something?',51063,'2012-08-07 04:40:43'),(46294,5948,86439,'2012-08-07 04:43:42','On the browse page, about 2 seconds, if that.\r\n\r\nFF14.0.1 (24,000/1024 connection), I dont have another browser, Opera is spitting the lolly and wont reinstall for some reason. I refuse to recognise the existence of IE.',NULL,NULL),(46295,5935,49532,'2012-08-07 04:44:05','[quote=knickers]\r\noh poop.[/quote]\r\n\r\nis that anything like [b]oh [color=#FF0000]shit[/color][/b] ? :lol:  :laugh:  :lol: \r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46296,5948,49532,'2012-08-07 04:46:45','[quote=yamchan07bb]...\n\nWhat exactly are you trying to find out?\n\nThe images aren\'t hosted on EMP, the site is only responsible to bring up the popup (happens instantly as soon as you hover the torrent name), after that, it\'ll be up to the imagehost and your connection to do the job. Another thing to keep in mind, the cover image is actually the fullres image, it\'s size is only constrained to that small area in the tooltip.\n\nDifferent connections speeds, different results.\n\nAll browsers here:\n\n2-5 seconds for JPG (not stupid large images)\n\nAnd my connection chokes on GIF\'s, so that may take up to a minute to load.[/quote]\n\nTrying to find out, if there needs to be a size limit on covers, that is smaller than that.  Ideally covers should load nearly instantaneously.',49532,'2012-08-07 04:48:45'),(46297,5949,86439,'2012-08-07 04:47:23','Im inclined to agree. I just tried, and it tasted like I expect a slightly dusty screen would. Delightful.',NULL,NULL),(46298,5948,86439,'2012-08-07 04:54:04','The gif (animated pic anyway) on \'Lots of grool XXVI\' took longer. But that is to be expected I suppose.',NULL,NULL),(46299,5948,129045,'2012-08-07 05:18:46','A size limit sure is needed. As of now, cover images are a waste. It\'s cool to see it in the torrent detail page, click on it and then see it expanded.\r\n\r\nBut this test, the covers that appear on the on the user\'s profile and the covers that appear on collages proves that they are a total waste of bandwidth. You are loading a fullres picture and their only purpose is to sit constrained on a small area of about 150x150px. (160x280px for collages)\r\n\r\nIf the concern is to load them quickly, it would be better to make more strict rules and only allow actual covers (high-res pictures - OK) or in case of performers pictures\\site logo\\etc, something more reasonably sized.',129045,'2012-08-07 05:23:50'),(46300,5949,51063,'2012-08-07 05:37:22','LMFAO you are so much fun mate!',NULL,NULL),(46301,5934,171777,'2012-08-07 07:11:39','[quote=knickers]\r\nThis next one has two ready to kill.\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35177#tags\r\nhuge.cock\r\n[-] 0 [+] \r\n\r\nstrapon\r\n[-] 0 [+] \r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nVoted them down. They stood at -1 for a short moment and then were gone. However isn\'t 0 supposed to be gone already? afterall a rating of 0 means that the tag is not representative of the torrent already.\r\n\r\n\r\nGaryE, you basicllay have that power since you can just click the [X] at the end and remove a tag :P',NULL,NULL),(46302,5948,171777,'2012-08-07 07:14:34','might be easiest to just make a local thumbnail that is shown and when someone want so see the entire image it loads the original from external location. The only annoying thing is resizing a .gif since I am not sure if that can be done using the same type of script.',NULL,NULL),(46303,5934,86439,'2012-08-07 08:05:17','[quote=DrkNess]Voted them down. They stood at -1 for a short moment and then were gone. However isn\'t 0 supposed to be gone already? afterall a rating of 0 means that the tag is not representative of the torrent already.\r\n\r\n[/quote]\r\nIts a split hair IMO. Same as the extra vote for tags the uploader adds when first uploading. They get 8, plus one vote.\r\nI imagine over time when live those numbers might get revised depending how effective they are. But for now, well its got to start somewhere.\r\n\r\nWhether it should be zero or one I assume people could argue either way. For clarity maybe 0 should be the cut off point, instead. But other than that, its just a number.\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=DrkNess]\r\n\r\nGaryE, you basicllay have that power since you can just click the [X] at the end and remove a tag :P[/quote]\r\nOh Jebus, dont tell him that.\r\n\r\nSomeone keep USB out of this thread. Clownius already knows so that cats already out of the bag. :laugh:',NULL,NULL),(46305,5946,94952,'2012-08-07 08:28:35','It is Robert Llewellyn. I didn\'t know there was a series 10 in the works. But to be honest I\'m not that stoked series 9 felt like a huge let down.',94952,'2012-08-07 08:29:49'),(46306,5946,94804,'2012-08-07 08:56:48','[quote=GaryE]\r\nIt is a royal pain in the ass the forums fill up with first time posters saying why I am getting the \"Error: torrent does not exist\" (or whatever the exact text is) message.  Not to mention that the act is cowardly, petty, and childish LOL\r\n[/quote]\r\nchildish indeed, cant\'t staff get pm\'ed if delete torrent is clicked?',NULL,NULL),(46307,5934,171777,'2012-08-07 10:01:01','[quote=knickers]\r\nOh Jebus, dont tell him that.\r\n\r\nSomeone keep USB out of this thread. Clownius already knows so that cats already out of the bag. :laugh:[/quote]\r\n\r\nErm I take that back. If you click the [x] at the end you ad 100 random useless tags with a score of over 9000 that you can not downvote anymore  :panic: ',NULL,NULL),(46308,5946,49532,'2012-08-07 11:27:35','[quote=GaryE]Shooting wrapped about 4 or 5 months ago IIRC . . . I follow Kryten (what is his real name I just drew a blank . . . David/Doug Llewelin??? (sp?) I think) on twitter and he tweeted about a new series about IDK 6 or 7 months ago.  That is the only reason I know about it.  The producers were worried that the show would no longer be popular.  When the tickets were announced as available . . . I think it took less than 36 hours (maybe even less but I can not really remember) for them to get snatched up.  LOL no longer popular my ass LOL.\r\n\r\nIf you did not know about the new series did you ever the three episode series \"Red Dwarf: Back to Earth\" To the best of my knowledge it never got shown in the US (I got it on the pirate bay LOL).\r\n\r\nThe newest series is with all of the original cast.  When I asked the question I was told it would be broadcast in the US at more or less the same time as in the UK.  In the UK it will be shown on the Dave network (I only know the name of the network I do not think I had ever heard of it before) I have not heard what network will show it in the US but I think PBS is the safe bet because Red Dwarf has never been shown on any other network in the US (at least that I am aware of).  I know my DVR is set to record and save every instance of Red Dwarf regardless of network.  I am not going to miss it!\r\n\r\nThe show was first on the air in 1987 IIRC I think the last series \"back to earth\" was made in about 2006 or 8 which you certainly were alive for ;-)  (it was 2009 according to wiki)[/quote]\r\n\r\nI did\'t know about back to earth, it wasn\'t in the torrent I downloaded.  I don\'t know what is and what isn\'t broadcast in the US, because I don\'t have regular TV. Everything I watch is dowloaded from torrent sites, or online video.  ',NULL,NULL),(46309,5946,94804,'2012-08-07 12:57:22','haha get a room/thread!\r\n(pref. called Red Dwarf, the sequel;)',NULL,NULL),(46311,5948,41468,'2012-08-07 13:41:41','most (that are working)\r\nonly take a sec or so\r\nthe img pop-up is instant \r\nff 14.0.1',NULL,NULL),(46312,5948,171777,'2012-08-07 16:21:52','[quote=cofree]most (that are working)\r\nonly take a sec or so\r\nthe img pop-up is instant \r\nff 14.0.1[/quote]\r\n\r\nthat might be because they are in the browser cache. Hence the suggestion of using an alternate browser.',NULL,NULL),(46313,5899,48010,'2012-08-07 16:32:58','who\'s going to put up the test torrent ?',NULL,NULL),(46314,5934,48010,'2012-08-07 16:54:43','I\'m sure usb noticed the [X] already\r\n\r\nIf not he didn\'t play with it (unlikely) or he found no bug with it so he is happy :wink:',NULL,NULL),(46317,5948,94804,'2012-08-07 17:05:16','@ me it took 4.2 sec. (timed it),so quite slow indeed, (latest)Chrome, 64-bit, max bandwith 2 mb/s, not in IE(64bit)(in IE it\'s fast)',NULL,NULL),(46319,5899,51063,'2012-08-07 17:10:42','I am happy to do it if we are decided that we want to do this.  Also do we want to involve the main site?  We could say make 10 test accounts and upload a torrent on the main site with all 10 .torrent files in it.  The instructions would be to look at the total number of downloads just before you grab it (after hitting refresh) and look at the last digit . . . and the main site memeber would use the loadtest1 .torrent if the total downloads eneded with 1 and loadtest5 .torrent when the totaldownloads ended with 5 etc etc etc.\r\n\r\nWe could generate a boatload of load in no time flat.  The downside is that with everyone seeding/leeching with the same 10 accounts we would not get a good barometer if stats were getting recorded correctly.\r\n\r\nTo be honest I am waiting to hear from Lanz or mifune to see which approach they want.\r\n\r\nI guess the first load test should probably be official beta testers only, that way the load will increase gradually and if is gets borked (which I serious doubt will happen) we will have a very good idea of how many users cause that to happen.\r\n\r\nAlso it would probably be nice to have some debug code in some log somewhere that could be review in case something goes tits up.\r\n\r\nI am thinking I could get a torrent ready and wait for word from Lanz or mifune that the debug code is in place and ready to go.  Then I upload the torrent and Lanz (or Mifune?) hard code the torrent ID into the debug/log code and we are off and running.\r\n\r\nIn the mean time I will put together a few public domain books into a torrent and await further instructions.\n\n---- Edit\r\nOk I have a torrent ready to go it is about 60 MB  Just awaiting further instructions.',51063,'2012-08-07 17:31:16'),(46320,5946,51063,'2012-08-07 17:34:00','[quote=apparition][quote=GaryE]Shooting wrapped about 4 or 5 months ago IIRC . . . I follow Kryten (what is his real name I just drew a blank . . . David/Doug Llewelin??? (sp?) I think) on twitter and he tweeted about a new series about IDK 6 or 7 months ago.  That is the only reason I know about it.  The producers were worried that the show would no longer be popular.  When the tickets were announced as available . . . I think it took less than 36 hours (maybe even less but I can not really remember) for them to get snatched up.  LOL no longer popular my ass LOL.\r\n\r\nIf you did not know about the new series did you ever the three episode series \"Red Dwarf: Back to Earth\" To the best of my knowledge it never got shown in the US (I got it on the pirate bay LOL).\r\n\r\nThe newest series is with all of the original cast.  When I asked the question I was told it would be broadcast in the US at more or less the same time as in the UK.  In the UK it will be shown on the Dave network (I only know the name of the network I do not think I had ever heard of it before) I have not heard what network will show it in the US but I think PBS is the safe bet because Red Dwarf has never been shown on any other network in the US (at least that I am aware of).  I know my DVR is set to record and save every instance of Red Dwarf regardless of network.  I am not going to miss it!\r\n\r\nThe show was first on the air in 1987 IIRC I think the last series \"back to earth\" was made in about 2006 or 8 which you certainly were alive for ;-)  (it was 2009 according to wiki)[/quote]\r\n\r\nI did\'t know about back to earth, it wasn\'t in the torrent I downloaded.  I don\'t know what is and what isn\'t broadcast in the US, because I don\'t have regular TV. Everything I watch is dowloaded from torrent sites, or online video.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYou can definitely get it on the pirate bay  It is called \"Red Dwarf season 9\" . . . I am not seeding it anymore but I do still have it in my torrent client it is showing 6 seeders atm.',NULL,NULL),(46321,5946,51063,'2012-08-07 17:36:13','[quote=schlager]haha get a room/thread!\r\n(pref. called Red Dwarf, the sequel;)[/quote]\r\n\r\nI was going to split this off into its own thread . . . but I do not see a split option in my staff tools LOL',NULL,NULL),(46322,5934,51063,'2012-08-07 17:39:20','I have noticed that every torrent no longer gets tagged with the usb.loves.tags tag LOL  Which in all honesty is probably a good thing . . . but I do miss it LOL',NULL,NULL),(46325,5933,48010,'2012-08-07 17:48:44','[quote=MrRandom]why would it creep [you] out?[/quote]\r\nno not at all - I\'ve been busy \r\n\r\nJust for MrR and barumba I am going to IRC now',NULL,NULL),(46326,5933,48010,'2012-08-07 18:09:45','I\'m on irc now as you know already',NULL,NULL),(46327,5899,47234,'2012-08-07 18:23:40','I checked server load btw its still under 5%.  I cant see the tracker crashing as gazelle should have a decent one.  The server certainly has the capacity...',NULL,NULL),(46328,5951,47234,'2012-08-07 18:40:42','Seriously its a great fun tag but a fair few people are falling for it.....\r\n\r\nIts bad enough with the staff and beta testers.  But the general Emp population is going to have fits about this one....\r\n\r\nNot to mention abuse the crap out of it.',NULL,NULL),(46329,5951,85636,'2012-08-07 18:55:04',':(',NULL,NULL),(46330,5951,94952,'2012-08-07 19:31:31','While it is fun and can be used in fun ways. Knickers sig proved how disruptive it can be. \r\n\r\nSo I think it has to go. ',NULL,NULL),(46331,5951,41468,'2012-08-07 19:42:13','\r\nguys dont rush into this because my dumb ass fell for it.\r\n\r\n\r\nthat being said, i do think a shit ton of member will not understand what is going on.\r\nit will just lead to questions if we are lucky or if the worst happens they just want \r\nstop in anymore.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46332,5899,48010,'2012-08-07 19:45:43','sure Gary knows already but suggest if Gary gets the green light make clear in the title it is not pron and a load test',NULL,NULL),(46333,5951,47234,'2012-08-07 19:46:49','If it was just one cofree i would laugh about it an move on but there has been a few cases i know of due to that sig....\r\n\r\nHow many took off wondering what they did wrong and didnt say anything?\r\n\r\nI never underestimate our userbase when it comes to abusing things....\r\n\r\nI sadly think this tag could end in tears',NULL,NULL),(46334,5951,49532,'2012-08-07 19:50:25','[quote=Clownius]Seriously its a great fun tag but a fair few people are falling for it.....\r\n\r\nIts bad enough with the staff and beta testers.  But the general Emp population is going to have fits about this one....\r\n\r\nNot to mention abuse the crap out of it.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI agree, it\'s been fun for here, but it can cause a shit storm on the live site.',NULL,NULL),(46336,5934,49532,'2012-08-07 20:10:12','[quote=DrkNess][quote=knickers]\r\nThis next one has two ready to kill.\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35177#tags\r\nhuge.cock\r\n[-] 0 [+] \r\n\r\nstrapon\r\n[-] 0 [+] \r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nVoted them down. They stood at -1 for a short moment and then were gone. However isn\'t 0 supposed to be gone already? afterall a rating of 0 means that the tag is not representative of the torrent already.\r\n\r\n\r\nGaryE, you basicllay have that power since you can just click the [X] at the end and remove a tag :P[/quote]\r\n\r\nI was able to up vote a -1 back to 0,  it still appeared in the tag box, but it disapeared from the tags on the torrent browse page.',NULL,NULL),(46338,5645,70679,'2012-08-07 20:24:21','means you think you can fix it to work here? That would be cool.  :yaydance: ',NULL,NULL),(46339,5951,48010,'2012-08-07 20:26:31','I didn\'t understand this before so I reported appariton LOL who told me to **** myself\r\n\r\nNow I understand how it works I say remove it immediately\r\n\r\nIt is just going to open a shitload of reorts or questions if we keep it. We will have enough problems when this new version of the site goes live - no need to complicate things with the [you] tag\r\n\r\n@apparition the report is closed :wink:',NULL,NULL),(46340,5948,129045,'2012-08-07 20:31:24','[quote=DrkNess][color=#FF0000]might be easiest to just make a local thumbnail[/color] that is shown and when someone want so see the entire image it loads the original from external location. The only annoying thing is resizing a .gif since I am not sure if that can be done using the same type of script.[/quote]\r\n\r\nBut where would it be hosted? On the EMP server? Still seems like waste of bandwidth.\r\n\r\nThe same cover is used on different locations, but apart from the torrent\'s detail pages, it\'s basically used for identification on the others, which may or may not work \'correctly\', since on different browsers, the resized images locked to small areas may just look like shit (aliased\\jagged mess, Chrome circumvents it by re-sampling the image, but the majority of other browsers do not). Different aspect ratios also doesn\'t help, tall images may look better, while wide images will suffer because of size constraints.\r\n\r\nWould be better to set a standard size for all cover thumbnails and ask the user two cover images instead, one small (e.g. 250x250px max) to be used as thumbnail on all necessary areas and one fullres for when users click on it to expand. The user doesn\'t need to have a graphics editor, there\'s a bunch of online image resizers they can use for this task. [b]And ban GIFs from being used >:[[/b]\r\n\r\nAlso, the purpose of covers needs to be clearer. Is it supposed to make the torrent identifiable? Is it to serve as a preview of the content? Should only actual covers be allowed (VHS\\DVD\\BR\\Magazines...)? etc. Looking at the uploads here you can see the mess it could cause if it\'s not addressed before the site goes live.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46341,5953,48010,'2012-08-07 20:32:44','why does every page now run this - they didn\'t seem to before - i only noticed it today\r\n\r\nit is slowing down my page load big time\r\n\r\ndo i need to use script block - i prefer not as that interfers with other sites i use',NULL,NULL),(46342,5948,94952,'2012-08-07 20:39:53','I tested with Chrome, FireFox and IE 9. All cover images took less than one second to load except on IE 9. I have 800 kb/s downstream so I think it is mostly bandwidth related. Except for the craptacular IE. Chrome felt a bit fast than FF but not much.\r\n.',NULL,NULL),(46343,5953,129045,'2012-08-07 20:40:36','What the... that\'s not a Google domain. And themes.googleusercontent.com (no [color=#FF0000]s[/color]) doesn\'t exist (Google Robot 404 error)\r\n\r\nOdd :\\',NULL,NULL),(46344,5953,94952,'2012-08-07 20:42:41','It was requested that emp had a diffrent font (open sans, iirc) thats why themes.googleusercontent.com is called. It\'s part of the css.',94952,'2012-08-07 20:43:33'),(46345,5953,48010,'2012-08-07 20:44:04','[quote=yamchan07bb]What the... that\'s not a Google domain. And themes.googleusercontent.com (no [color=#FF0000]s[/color]) doesn\'t exist (Google Robot 404 error)\n\nOdd :\\[/quote]\ndo you see it too ?\n\nEDIT - I only see it on here not on any other site\n\nsee bottom left of the screenshot here\n\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=763E_50216363][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=763E_50216363[/img][/url]',48010,'2012-08-07 20:47:00'),(46346,5953,129045,'2012-08-07 20:47:30','No man, I don\'t see it, was just pointing that out\r\n\r\n[quote=Mobbo]It was requested that emp had a diffrent font (open sans, iirc) thats why themes.googleusercontent.com is called. It\'s part of the css.[/quote]\r\n[s]The custom fonts request leads to this: http://fonts.googleapis.com , that url is something else.[/s] Yeah, it just goes too fast here :(\r\n\r\nLooking at all the elements being loaded, yeah, it\'s the fonts being loaded.',129045,'2012-08-07 20:49:44'),(46347,5953,48010,'2012-08-07 20:52:20','ok I saw fonts.googleapis.com before\r\n\r\nprobably just my shit connection as usual - never mind\r\n\r\nforget this\r\n\r\nmark as solved ?',NULL,NULL),(46349,5951,129045,'2012-08-07 21:01:29','First time I encountered the [code][you][/code] tag was on a [b]mifune[/b] test torrent, inviting users to upload something.\r\n\r\nSo, can it be limited to Staff only? Good for a site wide warning or invites, etc (or special cases like barumba\\MrRandom IRC invites). Not so good for smartasses and pranksters >:[',NULL,NULL),(46350,5951,51063,'2012-08-07 21:12:50','Honestly I have been on a few sites that use the you tag.  It is never as big of a problem as you think it will be.  Yes it needs to be used appropriately.  For example on the live site the you tag in the F* you thread that apparition started/postedin/whatever it was would not be acceptable -- but on here with only testers I thought it was just fine.  But a simple rule of . . . do not use the you tag abusively . . . usually is enough.  I mean my sig and Mobbo\'s sig are just going to creep people out at first and nothing more.\n\nEventually after a short while everyone gets used to it and when some one comes in and says something like \"how the fuck did Gary know I would read this next?  I have never set foot in the forums before\" there will be regular members explaining things.  Hell usually after the first few weeks it is available it does not get used much.\n\nIt is just harmless fun . . . and when someone abuses it they will get spanked.  It really is not a big deal.  Ok yeah if we get 10 pervs a day abusing it . . . it will be a problem . . . but I have never seen that happen.\n\nI mean if someone uses that bit of HTML in their sig to say \n\nYou are on a Mac using firefox and your IP address is XXX.YYY.ZZZ.WWW are we going to disallow that too?  That got me the first time I saw it too.\n\nI really do not think we need to do anything other than say \"do not make inflammatory/abusive comments with the you tag\" and enforce that fairly and we will be just fine.',51063,'2012-08-07 21:13:21'),(46351,5934,51063,'2012-08-07 21:15:37','It is a cache thing I am certain.  I seem to recall reading somewhere that 0 tags stay around for at most 15 minutes.',NULL,NULL),(46352,5948,51063,'2012-08-07 21:17:56','[quote=yamchan07bb][quote=DrkNess][color=#FF0000]might be easiest to just make a local thumbnail[/color] that is shown and when someone want so see the entire image it loads the original from external location. The only annoying thing is resizing a .gif since I am not sure if that can be done using the same type of script.[/quote]\r\n\r\nBut where would it be hosted? On the EMP server? Still seems like waste of bandwidth.\r\n\r\n[snip][/quote]\r\n\r\nAlso you do not want to \"knowingly\" host possibly copyrighted images on the torrent tracker/server.  That could open up a legal loophole for prosecution.',NULL,NULL),(46353,5899,51063,'2012-08-07 21:25:21','Great point I [b]hopefully[/b] would have remembered to do that without the reminder LOL  but the reminder is appreciated!\r\n\r\nThe reason I want a proper load test Clownius is to make sure that the coders did not inadvertently do something that buggers the load somehow.  I hold Lanz and Mifune in the highest regard . . . but it is beyond silly to assume that the server will be fine under load when we do not have a single torrent with more than 8 or 10 peers.  It is just something that is too important not to formally test.  But in theory I agree I think it will go swimmingly.\r\n\r\nWe might even want to hold off until we are closer to going live when the to do list is nice and small in case something get buggered while fixing the last few bugs.\r\n\r\nWe did not do this when we went live with the new PB site . . . and it took several days before the site was working optimally . . . of course the new PB site was written from scratch but still it is something we want to avoid if possible.',NULL,NULL),(46355,5849,51063,'2012-08-07 21:47:24','This seems resolved is it not?  Well I have marked it as such!  If I was wrong you know what to do!',NULL,NULL),(46356,5852,51063,'2012-08-07 21:55:51','That is a good one . . . any more info on this?  I have not experience the bug for what it is worth.',NULL,NULL),(46357,5798,51063,'2012-08-07 22:00:31','[quote=apparition][quote=Clownius]Oh i beg of you please ban IE .....  I swear you spend half your bug squashing time on bugs that only affect IE...[/quote]\r\n+1 for banning IE.\r\n\r\nBut in the other hand, IE is only on MS Windows. People with real operating systems don\'t need to worry. :smartass:[/quote]\r\n\r\nOk so I am grave digging a bit but +1 real operating systems do not have IE as an option (thank God!)',NULL,NULL),(46358,5841,51063,'2012-08-07 22:03:02','Lanz is this complete?',NULL,NULL),(46359,5843,51063,'2012-08-07 22:03:53','bump',NULL,NULL),(46360,5948,171777,'2012-08-07 22:06:18','[quote=GaryE][quote=yamchan07bb][quote=DrkNess][color=#FF0000]might be easiest to just make a local thumbnail[/color] that is shown and when someone want so see the entire image it loads the original from external location. The only annoying thing is resizing a .gif since I am not sure if that can be done using the same type of script.[/quote]\r\n\r\nBut where would it be hosted? On the EMP server? Still seems like waste of bandwidth.\r\n\r\n[snip][/quote]\r\n\r\nAlso you do not want to \"knowingly\" host possibly copyrighted images on the torrent tracker/server.  That could open up a legal loophole for prosecution.[/quote]\r\n\r\nisn\'t the xxx.image.us stuff also already hosted on the same servers?',NULL,NULL),(46361,5852,49532,'2012-08-07 22:13:11','[quote=GaryE]That is a good one . . . any more info on this?  I have not experience the bug for what it is worth.[/quote]\r\n\r\nHappened once. never again. \r\n\r\nI\'m not sure which was the default stylesheet at the time it happened, or now, but the first time I logged in, light was the default stylesheet.',NULL,NULL),(46362,5852,51063,'2012-08-07 22:21:36','I have changed back and forth so many times I do know . . . I know at one point the Emp stylesheet was the default but that was when there was only staff here IIRC so what about 3 months ago maybe????  LOL\r\n\r\nIt really sounds just like a random glitch but with limited information . . . you have to tag everything with limited information as a a random glitch LOL so that does not really answer anything.  I guess we leave this open/unrecolved for now?',NULL,NULL),(46363,5934,84499,'2012-08-07 22:21:52','they used to but now they get removed when they are -1. Voting dosent reload the list though, which is deliberate because 1) its annoying to have the list reordered when they are score ranked (the default sort) and 2) because reloading the taglist involves a query/cache call and its better to make tag voting as light as possible in terms of server load. However it should probably just remove the -1 tags when they are voted down instead of waiting for the page to be reloaded... \r\n\r\nincidentally if you vote a tag to -1 and then vote it up back to 0 and reload the page is the tag still there?',NULL,NULL),(46364,5934,51063,'2012-08-07 22:23:15','LOL that is what I get for being certain!',NULL,NULL),(46365,5948,51063,'2012-08-07 22:24:28','different domain name . . . that is all that really matters.  But yes you are right I should have said on the torrent domain instead of server\n\nAlso that is not every cover image.  What was suggested was to store every cover image locally . . . that is not the best idea IMO.',51063,'2012-08-07 22:26:06'),(46367,5934,49532,'2012-08-07 22:30:57','[quote=mifune]\r\nincidentally if you vote a tag to -1 and then vote it up back to 0 and reload the page is the tag still there?[/quote]\r\n\r\nI don\'t know if it used to be, it\'s not anymore.',NULL,NULL),(46368,5852,49532,'2012-08-07 22:35:01','Even if there is a real bug, it\'s one that doesn\'t do much harm, and isn\'t worth hunting down, if it wasn\'t easily found.',NULL,NULL),(46369,5954,70679,'2012-08-07 22:38:43','I think is a good indicator how good we are doing  :wink: ',NULL,NULL),(46370,5951,70679,'2012-08-07 23:10:10','My vote is not to get rid of it as it has its good use. That said some ideas other than put in the rules that abuse of it will be punished and let it use from some level up (Good Perv? Sextreme?) AND signal it like add for example ** around it like \n\n*[you]* is required not to abuse of the you tag.\n\nI THINK is a different color but forgive my old eyes the very dark blue is almost the same as black.',70679,'2012-08-07 23:12:06'),(46371,5951,94952,'2012-08-07 23:16:38','[you][color=#000099] is way cool.[/color]\nThe color tag makes it way easy to make it blend in. Just look at MrR\'s sig, perfect example. :)\n\nI just think it will be abused and annoy/scare a lot of pervs.',94952,'2012-08-07 23:17:55'),(46372,5948,84499,'2012-08-07 23:18:03','\r\nI highly doubt we are going to implement having two cover images one big one small, what if we just restricted it to be a more sensible max size and stop the click on image to expand thing for cover images? Really they should just be the smaller size.',NULL,NULL),(46373,5852,84499,'2012-08-07 23:22:43','\r\n\r\nif you cant reproduce it its not a bug  :borg: \r\n\r\n :D',NULL,NULL),(46374,5951,75827,'2012-08-07 23:22:45','[quote=Clownius]If it was just one cofree i would laugh about it an move on but there has been a few cases i know of due to that sig....\r\n\r\nHow many took off wondering what they did wrong and didnt say anything?\r\n\r\nI never underestimate our userbase when it comes to abusing things....\r\n\r\nI sadly think this tag could end in tears[/quote]\r\n\r\nWow i just fell for it.. well almost, I became skeptical as to why someone would not just PM to go on IRC then to write it in there signature.\r\n\r\nIt`s funny but yes i could see allot of members thinking they did something wrong...',NULL,NULL),(46375,5955,75827,'2012-08-07 23:34:11','I think a hide button would be a nice specialization feature Not sure how easy or hard it would be to implement. \r\n\r\n\r\nThis would be for all torrent listings. Think of it as, instead of picking all the content you want to see as just the opposite.\r\n\r\nBut then again i can see how we can do that already by just checking off the content we want to see all the time and hitting default button right?\r\n\r\nFeel free to shoot this ideal down, just figured i would  share this thought. ',NULL,NULL),(46376,5956,84499,'2012-08-07 23:37:11','\r\nSo [you] what do you think of the [code][you][/code] tag?\r\n\r\nSome options...\r\n\r\n**[b]note[/b]: poll results may count for nothing... lol :D',NULL,NULL),(46377,5948,129045,'2012-08-07 23:40:39',':hmmm:\r\n\r\nLimiting the image size may not work as intended... the only place that really benefits from the cover image is the torrent\'s detail page, which doesn\'t make much sense to be limited to a small area (\'thumbnail\' sized, but 300x500px could work OK), but the other areas would still struggle with whatever size is chosen, because the site will try to cram it in a smaller space and the results may vary based on the browser and the images aspect ratio.\r\n\r\nSee my profile http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=129045, Digambar http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=16616 and NovaGent\'s http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?id=71038\r\n\r\nThat plus the cover display on collages and the popup on http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php would still suffer, now, if you had set the cover to be small (e.g. 150x150px or 250x250px), it would show up Ok on these places, but cripple the torrent\'s detail page.\r\n\r\nSeriously, it seems like a hard task to make EMP work with the cover feature -_-',129045,'2012-08-07 23:57:12'),(46378,5956,129045,'2012-08-07 23:47:32','Well then, I guess we keep it. Strap some strict rules to it + the permissions thingy based on class :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(46379,5948,84499,'2012-08-07 23:57:20','\r\nIts only displayed 250 wide on the torrent details page. honestly I dont see the problem with having it say max 250x400 (or whatever the preferable ratio is), its just a \'nice\' thing you can use that shows up in the browseover on the torrents page or in collages etc but its not required or essential.',NULL,NULL),(46380,5956,84499,'2012-08-08 00:03:33','[s]I may have been a bit misleading with the \'time consuming\' comment... its really not that big a task in itself its just the other options are 0-5min changes but it wont take that long, if thats the preferred option or if thats what the bosses want I could do it.[/s]\n\nit would be time consuming to put a 2nd permission in.',84499,'2012-08-14 12:00:00'),(46381,5956,70679,'2012-08-08 00:17:35','I expressed my view in the other thread  :tiphat: ',NULL,NULL),(46382,5957,94952,'2012-08-08 00:31:01','[b]URL:[/b] http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2956\r\n[b]Bug:[/b] The link that hide and shows the poll always read \"View\". Should read Hide and View.\r\n[b]Reproduce:[/b] Visit poll and use View link',NULL,NULL),(46383,5948,129045,'2012-08-08 00:34:01','Looking at the dimensions here, the other places are more or less close to:\r\n\r\nCollages: 160x280\r\nProfiles: 120x[color=#FF0000]170[/color]?\r\nPopup: 150x[color=#FF0000]225[/color]?\r\n\r\nImages constrained to these dimensions can look just plain bad on some cases :\\ [i](I guess this is my biggest beef, after resized, tall images are mostly ok, but wide images can suffer a lot)[/i]\r\n\r\nSo IMO, the middle ground would be along with a limit to the cover filesize\\dimensions, it could be set a standard size for all the other areas (e.g. Profile page and the popup to use the same cover display dimensions as the Collages page).\r\n\r\n:hmmm:',129045,'2012-08-08 01:20:03'),(46384,5956,85636,'2012-08-08 00:44:28','I do not think it should be nuked, since I can see uses for it in things like mass PM\'s, announcement, etc. But I think it should be limited in use to either trusted users (sextreme perv) or FLS and Staff.',NULL,NULL),(46385,5956,41468,'2012-08-08 01:55:15','[b]well i think its fun for this site at this time.[/b]\r\nonce its open to all there is no way i would want to be on staff  :banghead: \r\nyour pm\'s are going to go nuts  :cry: \r\nyou guys have what 100,000 users\r\ni would not put this on my site with only 22,500 members \r\nso i can only imagine what it would be like with 100,000  :gunshot: \r\nshit i get to many pm\'s as it is  :cry: \r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46386,5948,49532,'2012-08-08 01:55:29','I think filesize limits, make more sense, than imagesize limits.  I cam make the same image 1 mb or 10mb, depending on how I save the file.',NULL,NULL),(46387,5948,129045,'2012-08-08 02:17:39','Both are important, since the resize function isn\'t handled the same by all browsers. A limit on dimensions would ensure consistency, the image would always appear on its optimal state, no ugly jaggies\\aliasing since there wouldn\'t be any scaling done by the site\\browser (this on the torrent details page, the other sections would still need to fit a bigger image in small area, there\'s no easy way around that)\r\n\r\nFile types accepted could be limited to PNG (lossless, filesize limit keep this under control) and JPG (lossy, dimensions limit would keep this one under control). This would give flexibility to users while avoiding animated GIFs from being used as covers.',NULL,NULL),(46388,5958,129045,'2012-08-08 02:47:38','[*][b]What I\'m talking about[/b]\r\nAs of now, if you look at any of the page titles, they look somewhat like this:\r\n\r\n[color=#FF0000][b][i]______ :: Empornium Test Tracker[/i][/b][/color]\r\n\r\ne.g.\r\n\r\n[color=#660099][b][i]Forums :: Empornium Test Tracker\r\nNews :: Empornium Test Tracker[/i][/b][/color]\r\n\r\n[*][b]Problem[/b]\r\nYou open some threads (plus whatever other pages you have open) and it gets really hard to know which tab is the correct one, since the page titles will contain the full path to each thread:\r\n\r\n(favicon) [color=#0000FF]Forum > Sub-section > Thread title[/color]\r\ne.g. (favicon) [color=#FF0000][b][i]Forums > request tests > Please test mousever cover loading times :: Empornium Test Tracker[/i][/b][/color]\r\n\r\nOpen 10 threads, that\'s 10 tabs that may end looking all like: \"[color=#FF0000][b][i]Forums > request tests...[/i][/b]\"\r\n[/color]\r\nOpen more threads + whatever other pages you have opened and your tab bar will be full of \"[color=#FF0000][b][i]Forums...[/i][/b][/color]\"\r\n\r\n[b]So[/b], why not limit it to thread titles  only?\r\n\r\nAfter all, \"[color=#FF0000][i][b]Please test mouse...[/b][/i][/color]\" would be a lot better than \"[color=#FF0000][b][i]Forums > request tests...[/i][/b][/color]\" :hmmm:\r\n\r\nSpeaking of titles, the [b]Rules[/b] and [b]Help[/b] pages could use some specific titles, as of now, every page under there appears as \"Empornium Test Tracker\".\r\n\r\n[b][i][color=#FF0000][size=2]EDIT:[/size][/color][/i][/b]\r\n\r\n... I think I should have worded that better, updated the OP :hmmm:\r\n\r\nAs far as I can tell, you\'re in the same boat as everybody, regardless of monitor size.\r\n\r\nAll tabs have a limited width, they do not show the full title, while the titlebar will only show the current page title (Chrome doesn\'t even have a titlebar, for example):\r\n\r\n[b]IE[/b]\r\nFew tabs, titles are truncated anyway\r\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/adhUKxHk][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/adhUKxHk.jpg[/IMG][/URL]\r\nMany tabs, titles are truncated even more\r\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/acf2BuaI][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/acf2BuaI.jpg[/IMG][/URL]\r\n\r\n[b]Chrome[/b]\r\nThis behavior is the same across all browsers, unless you have custom settings to allow wider tabs or multi-tab-rows\r\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/acdTYp0e][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/acdTYp0e.jpg[/IMG][/URL]\r\n\r\nGetting rid of the [color=#FF0000][i][b]Forums > Sub-section[/b][/i][/color] part would result into this:\r\n\r\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/aczyTYsK][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/aczyTYsK.jpg[/IMG][/URL] ',129045,'2012-08-08 15:40:46'),(46390,5956,48010,'2012-08-08 03:25:36','[quote=mifune]So [you] what do you think of the [code][you][/code] tag?\r\n\r\nSome options...\r\n\r\n**[b]note[/b]: poll results may count for nothing... lol :D[/quote]\r\nI\'ve read the other thread as well so I\'m now up on this - I reported before out of ignorance and my worry is others will too\r\n\r\nAt first I took it as abusive but I know the poster wouldn\'t do that on a live site\r\n\r\nI feel it could be useful as stated above but agree it needs some restriction  or at least rules to control\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46391,5951,86439,'2012-08-08 03:27:52','[quote=yamchan07bb]First time I encountered the [code][you][/code] tag was on a [b]mifune[/b] test torrent, inviting users to upload something.\n\nSo, can it be limited to Staff only? Good for a site wide warning or invites, etc (or special cases like barumba\\MrRandom IRC invites). Not so good for smartasses and pranksters >:[[/quote]\nI think this is the answer. Any member can request it if they have a genuine use for it.\n\nMaybe its just my experience with shock sites/forums and users who have no end of malevolence, but I see problems with open use. I used the sig I used because it seems to me that anyone reading it would likely be aware they cant have done anything wrong. Not that wrong anyway. Cofree PM\'ed me so he was aware he couldnt have, but just had to know.\n\nImagine this though as a sig.\n\n[you] peddles cp, beware of his uploads. \n\nI didnt even put any effort into that. Given the time and motivation Im pretty sure I could start a shitstorm of problems with it on a site with 100k+ active members. Sure it can be sorted afterwards, but at what cost? How many members might just change preference to another site?',86439,'2012-08-08 03:28:56'),(46392,5934,84499,'2012-08-08 04:34:32','okay now neg voted tags are removed instantly (in the interface as well as the backend). I quite like 0 rated tags... shows they are on the verge of being removed.\n\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI added a user setting to allow you to add tags with no up vote. I also made the value of added tags consistent in upload/torrent details - this will only affect newly uploaded torrents, it now records an up vote for tags added at upload (or adds with one less vote if the user has it set that way for them). ',84499,'2012-08-08 05:33:15'),(46393,5852,51063,'2012-08-08 05:10:45','Ok I am marking this as discounted as is not reproducible and discounted due to non repeatability ',51063,'2012-08-08 05:11:51'),(46394,5957,51063,'2012-08-08 05:14:21','Confirmed',NULL,NULL),(46395,5958,51063,'2012-08-08 05:21:39','I should probably just keep out of this due to my very large screen (27\" 2560 X 1440)  But it is fine for me LOL\r\n\r\nHonestly I do see your point; but, I really like it the way it is.  Just my opinion of course I really do not have strong feelings but I do prefer it the way it is.',NULL,NULL),(46396,5951,51063,'2012-08-08 05:24:31','That is a good point but in all honesty if someone is going to leave a site because of something they see in a sig I say good riddance.  Also if they leave because of something they see in a sig they are probably just looking for any excuse to leave.',NULL,NULL),(46398,5814,51063,'2012-08-08 05:45:53','I would second the nomination for a page with just the new posts listed . . . that is something that is just huge for me on sites I staff.  It is the only reliable way I have ever used to make sure I read all of the new posts since I last visited.  The current method (especially when the catch up button does not work as expected) makes it easy for me to miss new posts.',NULL,NULL),(46399,6042,51063,'2012-08-08 05:58:34','LOL usb needs to change his sig to one that has a bug catching him!\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]split from thread[/i][br]\'deadline?\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(46400,5836,51063,'2012-08-08 06:00:07','marked as resolved',NULL,NULL),(46401,5835,51063,'2012-08-08 06:02:42','This seems resolved!',NULL,NULL),(46402,5951,86439,'2012-08-08 06:14:47','Some people are sensitive to such things. Others dont seem to notice the sarcasm or humour dripping from posts etc. That doesnt mean they dont contribute to the community, even if its only seeding torrents they dl.\r\n\r\nThe kind of person Im thinking about is someone from a competitor tracker that doesnt share Emps \'the more the merrier\' approach. Or the more likely, uploader/member that spits the dummy. Like the member mentioned in another thread that deleted 60 torrents. Some people might like the opportunity to disrupt more than that.\r\n\r\nhow effective that attempt might be I have no idea. But its the potential that would concern me. The loss of any member that doesnt deserve to be gone is something I would not want to see.',NULL,NULL),(46404,5814,171777,'2012-08-08 09:39:42','I too think that it is a bit short right now but same as GaryE I\'d prefer a overview page with new posts like on the old forum over expanding the listing. No way all info would ever fit on there anyway.',NULL,NULL),(46405,5951,171777,'2012-08-08 09:49:25','To problem is that you ALWAYS read stuff where your internet nickname is posted. Usage of the [code][you][/code] tag thus can be very annoying when skimming over pages. Still I\'d say wait for he poll results in the other topic. So far it looks like people want it to go.',NULL,NULL),(46406,5814,86439,'2012-08-08 10:25:25','I dont know if gazelle is capable of it, but Ive been on forums where the new posts page was live. i.e: Leave the page open, and any new post is automatically added to the top. You can just scroll down and click the threads your interested in as activity is added.\r\n\r\nYou know, for a simple idea I cant think of a better way of explaining it. But I hope someone can get the gist of it from that butchery.',NULL,NULL),(46407,5814,171777,'2012-08-08 10:50:04','[quote=knickers]I dont know if gazelle is capable of it, but Ive been on forums where the new posts page was live. i.e: Leave the page open, and any new post is automatically added to the top. You can just scroll down and click the threads your interested in as activity is added.\r\n\r\nYou know, for a simple idea I cant think of a better way of explaining it. But I hope someone can get the gist of it from that butchery.[/quote]\r\nsort of like an rss feed for forum posts.',NULL,NULL),(46408,5814,86439,'2012-08-08 12:38:42','r...s...s...? Thats up there with IRC to me, I dont use them, at least Im unaware I do if I do. But from what I can gather RSS is a feed of regular updates etc, so yep, seems right.\n\nIt would look something like\n\nthread a   post   poster   time    forum\nthread d   post   poster   time    forum\nthread e   post   poster   time    forum\nthread b   post   poster   time    forum\nthread a   post   poster   time    forum\nthread b   post   poster   time    forum\n\nWith new posts being added to the top a second or two after they are posted. Each of those threads or posts being a clickable link to take to the post, or last unread etc. Poster too for that matter if desired or simpler.\n\nI would think its a great tool for a mod to be able to leave said window open and look through posts without necessarily going into the threads etc. Either sitting there live, or checking it every however often. No need to refresh as its live updated.\n\nBut I have no idea how much work is involved in it, or server loads etc.\n',86439,'2012-08-08 12:43:01'),(46414,5958,129045,'2012-08-08 15:39:18','... I think I should have worded that better, updated the OP :hmmm:\r\n\r\nAs far as I can tell, you\'re in the same boat as everybody, regardless of monitor size.\r\n\r\nAll tabs have a limited width, they do not show the full title, while the titlebar will only show the current page title (Chrome doesn\'t even have a titlebar, for example):\r\n\r\n[b]IE[/b]\r\nFew tabs, titles are truncated anyway\r\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/adhUKxHk][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/adhUKxHk.jpg[/IMG][/URL]\r\nMany tabs, titles are truncated even more\r\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/acf2BuaI][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/acf2BuaI.jpg[/IMG][/URL]\r\n\r\n[b]Chrome[/b]\r\nThis behavior is the same across all browsers, unless you have custom settings to allow wider tabs or multi-tab-rows\r\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/acdTYp0e][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/acdTYp0e.jpg[/IMG][/URL]\r\n\r\nGetting rid of the [color=#FF0000][i][b]Forums > Sub-section[/b][/i][/color] part would result into this:\r\n\r\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/aczyTYsK][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/aczyTYsK.jpg[/IMG][/URL] ',129045,'2012-08-08 15:40:37'),(46415,5958,171777,'2012-08-08 15:47:35','In all honesty? I don\'t really read the text on those things ever... Still I can see the benefit in the last screenshot.',NULL,NULL),(46416,5958,129045,'2012-08-08 16:04:14','Makes me question how the hell you guys use this site with many tabs open :P\r\n\r\nI just fail to see the benefit of keeping things the way it is :\\\r\n\r\nTorrent titles and Collage titles will be displayed alone as the page title, that make them easily identifiable. Requests will always be preceded by \"[b]View request:[/b]\", while some specific user pages will always be preceded by [i][b]Username\'s[/b] whatever[/i], that takes some space, but they are still identifiable.\r\n\r\nThread titles on the other hand, easily get lost in there.',NULL,NULL),(46418,5956,94804,'2012-08-08 17:39:49','ouch, THE WEIGHT!\r\nit should be restricted to few users indeed\r\nthere you have it',NULL,NULL),(46420,5956,48010,'2012-08-08 17:46:25','[quote=schlager]ouch, THE WEIGHT!\r\n[b]it should be restricted to few users indeed[/b]\r\nthere you have it[/quote]\r\n\r\nSo if not nuked it should be staff only IMHO',NULL,NULL),(46421,5958,171777,'2012-08-08 18:12:32','I open tabs for stuff that I want to look. look at the tab and close it until i am back at the page from where i opened the tabs.',NULL,NULL),(46422,5956,171777,'2012-08-08 18:13:48','I voted nuke because of the \"(time consuming - might be more work than its worth from a coding pov)\" part. If this is not really the case I say staff and FLS only.',NULL,NULL),(46423,5958,129045,'2012-08-08 18:30:04','I see, most browsers, upon closing a tab will always return focus to the page that spawned it, that\'s nice and all, but it d