at forum',NULL,NULL),(46526,5937,84499,'2012-08-10 01:04:20','\r\n\r\nThere is now a setting under user profile for your timezone.\r\n\r\nThere was a little funkiness going on with the server time... but server time is now UTC, it was UTC+2 (but only on the server config not the project config :argh: lanz!) which means times of old posts etc are now 2 hrs out but everything going forward will be correct. ',NULL,NULL),(46528,5949,84499,'2012-08-10 01:31:30','\r\n\r\nremoved the tasted reference.',NULL,NULL),(46529,5937,86439,'2012-08-10 01:41:40','Excellent. BUT\n\nAustralia is GMT+ not GMT-. We lives in the future. Brisbane, the setting I would use is GMT+10, and never has DLS. Clownius is Sydney (I think) which is GMT+10, and does have DLS.\n\nThe options show Aus as GMT-10. I think many are borked actually, I dont think too many US would be GMT+ either, except maybe some territories off the mainland. US is all GMT -, as I said, maybe some territories are different but I dont actually know.\n\n\n\n\nEdit: OK thats odd too, this post was made at 11:40am 10 Aug. The time stamp says 1:41am 10 Aug. So it minuses 10 hours from my systems time. Not GMT. Or is it just displaying GMT 0 time regardless.',86439,'2012-08-10 01:48:14'),(46530,5937,84499,'2012-08-10 01:47:27','\r\nif you look at the tooltip where it says x mins ago on your post is the actual time correct?',NULL,NULL),(46531,5937,86439,'2012-08-10 01:50:45','It says 6 mins ago, but Id just changed it to a +1 timeslot to test my GMT theory.\n\nIve reverted back to Brisbane GMT-10. and Ill edit this post with my answer in context with that timeslot.\n\nEdit: Right now on this post, I get a message saying \'just now\'.\n\n',86439,'2012-08-10 01:54:49'),(46532,5937,86439,'2012-08-10 01:55:00','I just changed my setting to a US timeslot with +7, the above post times have not altered at all. Maybe lag, or some other reason.\n\nIll edit this post too with results in a second.\n\n\n\nEdit: The time with +7 selected as setting, still shows 1:55am. So it hasnt altered the time stamp no matter what timezone I select. They all give the same result.\n\nIt was 1am with GMT-10, 1am with +4 or something, and 1am with +7. Unless theres lag in updating those settings and their effect on timestamps displayed to me.\n\nand they all show the tooltip with an accurate \'how many minutes ago\'. 13, to just now.',86439,'2012-08-10 01:59:10'),(46533,5937,84499,'2012-08-10 02:06:22','\r\n\r\nokay it should update properly without having to logout now (you will need to change the setting though).\r\n\r\nI fixed the reversed +/- in the select box too.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe timestamp will not be altered. The timezone setting is just applied in the interface. I *think* the interface time should be correct for DST settings... \r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46534,5937,86439,'2012-08-10 02:08:56','Ah OK, so not logging out explains not changing at all. Makes sense.\n\n\nEdit: Had to log out, but time is correct now. Cant tell about DST, DST is not current anywhere in Aus at this time of year.\n\nAnd by timestamp, I actually meant what I as a user see. I should have realised theres a coding timestamp and used a different phrase. Sorry bout that.',86439,'2012-08-10 02:12:04'),(46535,5937,94952,'2012-08-10 02:08:57','Fixed by logging out. DST seems right. ',94952,'2012-08-10 02:09:40'),(46537,5937,84499,'2012-08-10 02:21:47','\r\nokay... honestly [i]now[/i] it should update the interface time properly after you change your timezone without having to logout  :noexpression: ',NULL,NULL),(46538,5940,51063,'2012-08-10 02:27:56','Yes it works as expected now . . . yes the threads in question were all over 30 days old\n\nThank mifune!',51063,'2012-08-10 02:28:11'),(46539,5914,84499,'2012-08-10 02:33:13','\r\n\r\nthis should all be fixed now. not everyone can add multiple tags but you should get meaningful feedback either way.',NULL,NULL),(46540,5743,51063,'2012-08-10 02:38:33','Yeah it just happened to occur at the same time they 