t specific thing.\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(46559,5814,84499,'2012-08-10 17:37:25','\r\nI added an unread posts page.\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=knickers]I dont know if gazelle is capable of it, but Ive been on forums where the new posts page was live. i.e: Leave the page open, and any new post is automatically added to the top. You can just scroll down and click the threads your interested in as activity is added.\r\n\r\nYou know, for a simple idea I cant think of a better way of explaining it. But I hope someone can get the gist of it from that butchery.[/quote]\r\nGazelle dosent have it but its simple enough to code... however I am not sure I can think of a way of doing it that dosent potentially hammer the server :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(46560,5975,129045,'2012-08-10 17:39:36','Here, it actually returns an error the first time you use the php link, the second time though, it will accept anything',NULL,NULL),(46561,5804,84499,'2012-08-10 17:49:05','\r\nAdded.\r\n\r\nPlease test!\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46562,5975,84499,'2012-08-10 17:56:41','\r\n\r\nIf it dosent work on one load but does on another then it sounds like its taking too long for freeimage to initially serve up the php link, but thats not a site error thats an imagehost issue.\r\n\r\nWhat I mean is short of us only accepting actual image links and not php served images there isnt much we can do about it. I am strongly resistant to coding hacks to convert specific imagehost php urls into hotlinks... in fact its not going to happen lol, it breaks a lot of good design principles and is designed to fail going forwards.\r\n\r\nIf you want to use proper image urls go ahead, but the site cannot work out they should be from the php url in a reliable or good way.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46564,5975,70679,'2012-08-10 18:02:39','ah well my problem is that it did not accept the original format like on the old site... like for the Avatar you have to reformat it to the second format but is strange then if it takes the second time but I also just put the tags manually and is just for our image server that I use all the time.\r\n\r\nAnd YamChan then it works? Meaning shows the image?\n\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=4200_50254CDE[/img]\r\n\r\nyeah the first time it complains is not a .jpg, .gif, etc... the second time you try it accepts it and shows it as you can see above.... so do not know what to say... if you know it you just do it twice but if you do not know...',70679,'2012-08-10 18:06:14'),(46566,5975,84499,'2012-08-10 18:28:35','okay....\n\nlets get basic here.\n\nPlease carefully explain what steps to take to replicate the behaviour.',84499,'2012-08-10 18:33:07'),(46568,5975,129045,'2012-08-10 18:42:14','Really mifune, you don\'t get the first warning?\r\n\r\nTry to paste the php link:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=F56E_50255667][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=F56E_50255667&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nYou should get this warning:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=A508_50255667][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=A508_50255667&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nClick Ok, it goes back to the first popup:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=96A1_50255667][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=96A1_50255667&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nPaste the link again and it should go without giving the same warning again:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1A79_50255667][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=1A79_50255667&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n\r\nActually, it\'ll throw a warning the first time and then accept [color=#FF0000][b]anything[/b][/color] on the second try (you could paste\\type anything in there, it would get wrapped in [code][img][/code] tags without any problems)',129045,'2012-08-10 18:43:17'),(46569,5975,84499,'2012-08-10 18:45:07','\r\nlol, okay. It would have helped if you had said you were talking about the img prompt...',NULL,NULL),(46570,5975,129045,'2012-08-10 18:50:04','lol, oh confusion.\r\n\r\nSpeaking of which, would it 