e allow it with a [code][you][/code] tag? Just police it like that, if its not acceptable if a users name is there then its not acceptable to put a you tag there either. simples.',84499,'2012-08-11 03:28:24'),(46597,5977,49532,'2012-08-11 05:48:22','What jenny was trying to say was that if you use https://raw.github.com/gist/3318471/c56a71b2add37b50806d233c8b905a296d46e795/emp.css, as your external stylesheet, the site renders as plain text, on a white background, with no formatting.\n\nthe link however does work, and even shows up in the page source:\n\n[code]<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" xml:lang=\"en\" lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n	...\n	<link href=\"static/styles/global.css?v=1343698061\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" />\n		<link href=\"https://gist.github.com/raw/3318471/c56a71b2add37b50806d233c8b905a296d46e795/emp.css\" title=\"External CSS\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" media=\"screen\" />\n	       \n	...\n</head>\n<body id=\"user\" > \n...[/code]\n\nThis stylesheet is identical to http://lorem.us/empornium.css, which renders correctly, as a minor variant of the default empornium stylesheet.\n\nIf there isn\'t a known reason for this, I\'ll post a test request, to see if there is a problem with other hosts using https.',49532,'2012-08-11 05:52:38'),(46598,5977,84499,'2012-08-11 05:55:59','\r\n\r\nAs you show in your quote it correctly places the address in the attribute... I thought it would work but it dosent :dunno:\r\n\r\nCan anyone host a css file on a different https:// address? be nice to know if thats the thing :hmmm:\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(46600,5978,84499,'2012-08-11 06:02:49','\r\nIt is pretty cool.\r\n\r\n\r\nI am not sure if it should be in a help article or a forum thread but its mesmerizing.',NULL,NULL),(46601,5977,49532,'2012-08-11 06:11:51','[quote=mifune]As you show in your quote it correctly places the address in the attribute... I thought it would work but it dosent :dunno:\n\nCan anyone host a css file on a different https:// address? be nice to know if thats the thing :hmmm:[/quote]\none issue that just occured to me,  external css files, will put empornium into the access logs of the host server.  cheggit banned any kind of direct (non-anonymized) linking for that reason.\n\n\n\n',49532,'2012-08-13 06:55:37'),(46603,5951,47234,'2012-08-11 09:48:01','Sounds like that will work Mifune :)\r\n\r\nIF it becomes a problem we can asses things again.  Maybe we can trust our users.  Especially with all the ban hammers floating around now',NULL,NULL),(46604,5743,47234,'2012-08-11 09:49:19','May need to look at the last line of that page.  It says your wont receive additional upload credit.  Its kinda redundant :)',NULL,NULL),(46605,5979,85111,'2012-08-11 11:57:13','so far thanking a torrent doesnt do anything.. so why not add in the Top 10 section something like the top Thanked torrents to make use of it. Or even give the uploader 1 credit for each thank his torrent gets. Probably wont do much but least it\'ll make some use out of the function.\n\njust thought people might just trade unlimited likes so might be wise to limit each user to 10 likes a day. probably more work than its worth but thought i\'d just throw it out there.',85111,'2012-08-11 11:59:41'),(46606,5951,85111,'2012-08-11 12:04:01','sextreme and above makes sense. my vote goes for keeping it.',NULL,NULL),(46607,5970,171777,'2012-08-11 12:57:52','edited to done',NULL,NULL),(46608,5951,171777,'2012-08-11 13:00:02','choice was made. Tag is staying with elevated usage rights. Edited to done.',NULL,NULL),(46609,5979,171777,'2012-08-11 13:02:45','there already was a discussion about giving credits upon pressing thank you but that was dismissed. The overview is still a valid suggestion though.',NULL,NULL),(46611,5975,171777,'2012-08-11 13:05:55','Tested and it is working. thread set to [done]',171777,'2012-08-11 13:06:14'),(46615,5981,70679,'2012-08-11 13:39:36','[b]0. Register[/b]\n\n[color=#FF0000]Now [b]very important[/b] type these commands in the status window as well as all involving your password. So if you mess up you do not show your password in the channel for all to see!![/color]\n\nSo first make sure you are using the nickname you want. if not you can change it with:\n\n[b]/nick <nickname>[/b]\n\nexample : /nick barumba_is_the_man\n\nThen register your nickname:\n\n[b]/ns register <password> <email>[/b]\n\nexample: /ns register empircisfun barumba@gmail.com\n\nmake sure you use a password you remember!\nyou will not get an email notifications. This will only be used to recover your password. \nOnce given that command you are done. And you need to do it only once.\nIf you mess up contact the staff and they can help you fix it.\n\n\n[b]1. Using the Webchat[/b] -> [color=#FF0000]not to state the obvious but.... you will make your life a LOT LOT LOT easier using a client instead.[/color]\n\nWith this option all you have to do is identify yourself in the [b]status window[/b]:\n\n[b]/ns identify <password>[/b]\n\nexample: /ns identify empircisfun\n\nthen use the [b]/join[/b] command in the [b]status window[/b]:\n\n/join #empornium-staff\n\nyou can do this manually but with the new webchat interface you can have it done for you.\n\nFirst you select the channel(s) you want to join:\n\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=CC57_504BE3AA[/img]\n\nThen you select the Auth pull-down menu and input your password:\n\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=4293_504BE3AA[/img]\n\n\n\n[b]2. Using mIRC[/b]\n\nIf you are not familiar with mIRC after getting it and installing it read the guide (no point in duplicating it, is good) : [url=http://www.mirc.com/install.html]Link to first use guide[/url]\n\nThe to connect to the staff channel you need to enable SSL in mIRC.\n\nGet and install OpenSSL 1.0.1c from here: [url=http://www.mirc.com/downloads/openssl/openssl-1.0.1c-setup.exe]openssl-1.0.1c-setup.exe[/url]\n\nLet it install in your System32 folder. Is OK this way SSL is available to all of your applications if needed. Including mIRC. You will see that mIRC is SSL enabled now going to [b]Tools [/b]then [b]Options [/b]and choosing [b]Options [/b]under [b]Connect[/b] and you will see the [b]SSL [/b]button is active (not grey anymore.\n\nClick it and in the windows from the pull down menu select [b]accept invalid certificates automatically[/b].\n\nThe add the empornium server like in the image below:\n\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=8DA7_50267CD4[/img]\n\nnotice the port is +6697. This is very important for all to work\n\nThen after you connect to the server and identify yourself you can access the staff forum with the /join command and then you can add it to your favorites, make it auto join, etc... as you like.\n\nThen in mIRC you can automate the identify. So you do not have to worry about it anymore.\n\nsimply go to [b]Tools [/b]then [b]Script Editor...[/b] and select the [b]Remote [/b]tab is is not.\n\nThen copy/paste this text in the window:\n\n[color=#0000FF]on 1:NOTICE:*This nickname is registered and protected*:?: {\n  if ($nick == NickServ) {\n    ns identify PASSWORD\n  }\n}\n\non 1:NOTICE:*This nick is owned by someone else*:?: {\n  if ($nick == NickServ) {\n    ns identify PASSWORD\n  }\n}[/color]\n\nand change the two instances of PASSWORD to yours. Click OK and you are done!\n\n[b]3. Using Chatzilla[/b] \n\nChatzilla is a Firefox plug-in so it works on any OS where Firefox can be installed. You install it like any other plug-in and access it from the tools window. Then to access the Empornium IRC server type:\n\n/sslserver irc.emprn.tk 6697\n\nWhen you connect you will be warned that the server has an invalid certificate, click \"add exeption\" and remember to change your nickname to the one you use on the site and identify yourself. Then use the /join command.\n\nYou can automate the identification in Chatzilla preferences see below:\n\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=F16A_50269083[/img]\n\nand you can add channels for an auto-join when you start Chatzilla right click the channel tab and do as below:\n\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=8B09_5026A1EF[/img]\n\n[b]4. XChat (thanks MrRandom for this)[/b]\n\nHow to connect with xchat (this tutorial also works for clients based off of xchat such as HexChat)\n\nFirstly we need to get xchat installed. For linux users it should be in your repository e.g. ubuntu is \"sudo apt-get install xchat\". If you are on windows you can grab it from [url=http://www.silverex.org/download/]here[/url].\n\nWhen you first run xchat you will be presented with a server connect list.\n\n[img]http://xchat.org/docs/start/xchat-1-servlist.png[/img]\n\nChange your nickname and real name settings. Then click add to add a new IRC network and change the name to \"Empornium IRC\" and hit enter.\n\n[img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/xchat_server_edit.PNG[/img]\n\nClick edit double click on \"newserver/6667\" and change it to \"irc.digitalwizardry.org/6697\", [color=#FF0000]once edited click somewhere else or it will not be saved![/color] Click the check boxes on Use SSL and Accept invalid SSL Certificate, and if you registered your nickname enter the password you used.\n\n[img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/xchat_server_edit2.PNG[/img]\n\nClick the close button, then click connect and that\'s you you should be connected to Empornium IRC over secure SSL.\n\n\n\n\n[u][url=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comparison_of_Internet_Relay_Chat_clients]Here[/url][/u] you can find a very nice comparative list of the IRC clients available with lots of information.\n\nIf you decide to use one different than the ones mentioned make sure that it does support SSL otherwise you cannot enter the staff channel.',70679,'2012-09-09 00:34:17'),(46616,5967,1507,'2012-08-11 14:07:01',' :panic:  :panic:  :panic: \r\n\r\n[b]no forums, means no Contest thread, means no more freebies to give away....   :panic:  :panic:  :panic: \r\n\r\nwhat will I ever do....???\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:laugh:\r\n\r\n:usb:',NULL,NULL),(46617,5982,75827,'2012-08-11 15:02:02','Hi, i have tried the notifications system, Last night i made a filter list with these tags,\n\nHardcore teen fisting fetish\n\nNone of these Tags: fake.tits\n\nand pick a few categories to match: Teen Natural Tits Fetish Megapack\n\nBut when i check it today there was still nothing added to my Notification list, even if there was a torrent posted with the Hardcore tag in it. { [color=#CC6600]Just notice all the torrents are few days old so this might be why they din`t get added All still post some small torrents with corresponding tags to see if it works[/color]}\n\nToday i will post some torrent with the same tags as i used in my filter to see if the system will pick up. Anybody know how often the system will check for new torrents and add it to our list?',75827,'2012-08-11 15:21:34'),(46619,5979,84499,'2012-08-11 15:44:35','\r\n\r\nIt does exactly what the thanks button on emp does.\r\n\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(46620,5982,84499,'2012-08-11 15:46:52','\r\n\r\nthank-you this definitely does need testing.',NULL,NULL),(46621,5981,85636,'2012-08-11 17:56:59','you can grab the xchat one from the irc tutorials thread',NULL,NULL),(46623,5982,48010,'2012-08-11 18:59:57','test 1 uploaded\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46624,5982,75827,'2012-08-11 19:21:01','Nope still nothing',NULL,NULL),(46625,5982,48010,'2012-08-11 19:24:33','wait for mifune :grin:',NULL,NULL),(46627,5982,75827,'2012-08-11 19:33:40','Alright lol,',NULL,NULL),(46629,5982,129045,'2012-08-11 21:11:25','Odd, this feature was working before :\\\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\r\nEh, looking now, it seems to have been broken since my first test as my filter didn\'t catch anything new since it, this was more than 3 weeks ago IIRC.',129045,'2012-08-11 21:51:24'),(46630,5982,75827,'2012-08-11 22:34:14','Okay so it`s not just me \nYay