messages that all staff can use. Just copy paste or something. It will still feel semi personal to the recipient.',NULL,NULL),(46659,5956,75827,'2012-08-12 16:07:08','[b][font=Palatino Linotype][size=4][color=#CC6600]I Say Nuke it! [/color][/size][/font][/b]',75827,'2012-08-12 16:08:12'),(46660,5956,94804,'2012-08-12 17:34:28','[url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=suaveqvlWP8]dickhead?[/url]',NULL,NULL),(46661,5984,94804,'2012-08-12 17:45:31','When I go to collages>Chelsie Rea>manage torrents it shows the torrents with her in it with behind \'m \"edit\" and \"remove\" but when I click on either nothing happens (except for a page refresh) shouldn\'t there be some message saying \"you can\'t edit/remove torrents that you didn\'t upload\"?',NULL,NULL),(46662,5814,51063,'2012-08-12 19:09:32','I think we can list this as No/other suggestion done.  If that is incorrect (or if someone disagrees) there are enough folks around who can change it back LOL',NULL,NULL),(46663,5984,184595,'2012-08-12 19:12:36','\nworks for me. (that collage is set to allow sextremes+ to edit it).\n\nTry changing the sort order and clicking \'edit\' - it saves the new sort order.\n\nIf I click remove it removes the torrent... and this account is a sextreme with no other permissions.\n\n\nCan anyone else replicate the problem schlager is having?',84499,'2012-08-12 19:18:11'),(46664,5814,84499,'2012-08-12 19:17:08','\r\n\r\nwell I might add a user option for the number of forum entries... who knows.\r\n\r\nBtw - No need to bump threads you are just changing the title of, I mean bump them if you want to discuss something or get a query answered but no need otherwise.',NULL,NULL),(46665,5951,51063,'2012-08-12 19:18:02','[quote=barumba]My vote is not to get rid of it as it has its good use. That said some ideas other than put in the rules that abuse of it will be punished and let it use from some level up (Good Perv? Sextreme?) AND signal it like add for example ** around it like \r\n\r\n*[you]* is required not to abuse of the you tag.\r\n\r\nI THINK is a different color but forgive my old eyes the very dark blue is almost the same as black.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI missed this the last time I read this forum . . . there is a site which I just found out that I am still a member of that does something similar to the you tag because of the reasons stated here.  Does it help . . . yes . . . but not much.  In fact [b]I[/b] would say that it helps so little that it is not worth it (which is why I do not suggest it before) -- and it also takes a little of the fun out of it LOL.  The bottom line is that people still fell for it all the time so it did not help all that much.',NULL,NULL),(46667,5978,51063,'2012-08-12 19:26:58','That is very cool . . . I totally understand what is going on there . . . however I like mifune am not sure that it should be in a help thread or whatever . . . I think without a lot more words explaining things its message (that it shows how the torrent protocol is used to disseminate information so quickly) will not get understood by the vast majority of users (yeah the users who are actually here and helping testing will all get it).',NULL,NULL),(46668,5984,94804,'2012-08-12 19:38:18','huh? Now I CAN remove torrents(silly me, I deleted them all, so now I can\'t see if that also goes for \"edit\")',NULL,NULL),(46671,5814,51063,'2012-08-12 19:47:35','Yeah I hear you . . . I only do it where there is doubt in my mind weather it really should be marked as such.  I do not want to be seen as throwing my opinion around (especially if it is wrong or not the consensus).',NULL,NULL),(46673,5984,129045,'2012-08-12 20:16:56','[quote=schlager]huh? Now I CAN remove torrents(silly me, I deleted them all, so now I can\'t see if that also goes for \"edit\")[/quote]\r\nWell, just add more torrents and test again :\\\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b] Here, testing on my collages (Test Run) it\'s is working as intended.',129045,'2012-08-12 20:19:04'),(46678,5985,171777,'2012-08-12 21:39:46','Helped someone on the old site that was stuck on the password reset page. The mail did not arrive for some reason. Took him ages to find out the IRC information without being able to login to the website. We could either post this info on the same page or make the chat link also available for people that are not logged in.',NULL,NULL),(46681,5978,70679,'2012-08-12 23:26:49','actually I was thinking of doing a piece for dummies (my latest specialty seems...) about how swarms work and use it in there... to give some answers to the FAQ why I my torrents are not uploading etc...',NULL,NULL),(46682,5985,70679,'2012-08-12 23:28:43','I think on the old site there is a bug for this feature. Clownius mentioned something at some point...\r\n\r\nBut I concur that it may be a good idea to allow people to get help through IRC even in case they cannot log on.',NULL,NULL),(46683,5978,84499,'2012-08-13 00:03:03','\r\nyeah go for it I reckon. If we dont like it we can change it :P',NULL,NULL),(46685,5985,85636,'2012-08-13 00:04:40','If you use this iframe instead of the default one it will make them connect with a random nickname and join #empornium-help\r\n\r\n[code]<iframe src=\"http://webchat.digitalwizardry.org/?nick=EMPUser......&channels=empornium-help&uio=OD1mYWxzZSYxMD10cnVlJjExPTIwNQa1\" width=\"647\" height=\"400\"></iframe>[/code]',NULL,NULL),(46699,5956,78084,'2012-08-13 05:05:30','Nice polling feature linked to the forums.  Well done.  Personally I like the you tag, but maybe limit it.  Encourage others to maintain a good account? It\'s interesting.  It could become annoying though...',NULL,NULL),(46702,5977,49532,'2012-08-13 06:55:50','',49532,'2012-08-13 20:09:50'),(46703,5987,94804,'2012-08-13 10:06:43','I got four awards for popular uploader and good seeder, but as you can the image doesn\'t work, and it would be nice to know what torrent it concerns, posted in \"Bugs\" because of the image\nusing latest Chrome, win7 64bit\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=985C_5028D1D0][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=985C_5028D1D0&jpg[/img][/url]',94804,'2012-08-13 10:12:08'),(46706,5987,86439,'2012-08-13 10:37:08','Weird, my new potato showed up in the message just fine.',NULL,NULL),(46709,5987,129045,'2012-08-13 11:35:39','Broken URL, same thing here and I\'m pretty sure it doesn\'t matter which browser is used.',NULL,NULL),(46710,5987,84499,'2012-08-13 12:09:52','\r\n[quote=schlager]I got four awards for popular uploader and good seeder, but as you can the image doesn\'t work, and it would be nice to know what torrent it concerns, posted in \"Bugs\" because of the image\r\nusing latest Chrome, win7 64bit\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=985C_5028D1D0][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=985C_5028D1D0&jpg[/img][/url][/quote]\r\n\r\nwhats strange is the first batch had missing urls but the next batch didnt. Dunno seems like a \'server hiccup\' - the site url is defined in a config constant and I have no explanation of how one constant can be not defined and yet the constant for the static/ part of the url worked. Weirdness.\r\n\r\nSorry but no way am I going to have it tell you the torrent name, dosent sound like much difference I know but it would take substantial rewriting and redesigning of the awards scheduler code to be able to do that. In fact if as I suspect the \'server hiccup\' is a direct result of processing several thousand awards at once I may turn off PM\'s for some of the lesser awards anyway.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46711,5987,129045,'2012-08-13 12:45:34','By batch, you mean the awards being given twice? Here both notifications have broken URLs\r\n\r\nOdd :\\',NULL,NULL),(46712,5987,86439,'2012-08-13 13:31:55','Not sure if Im missing something here, I often am, but my award had the image of the award displayed, not a broken URL.\n\nMy message looked like this\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-3BC5_50290305.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-3BC5_50290305.jpg[/img][/url]\n\n\n\nIf you guys are talking specifically about the awards in question I apologise.\n\nEdit: On second thoughts, the message attached to mine probably indicates it was manual, not auto.',86439,'2012-08-13 13:33:07'),(46713,5987,84499,'2012-08-13 13:38:01','\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=yamchan07bb]By batch, you mean the awards being given twice? Here both notifications have broken URLs\r\n\r\nOdd :\\[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nActually no, the 2nd batch was some ribbons. The 1st batch got done twice, both times with the hostname part of the url missing... but with the pathname correct - the weirdness is that hostname and pathname are both supplied by constants which are both defined in the same place, but for some inexplicable reason only the hostname part was missing... I dont understand it.\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=knickers]Not sure if Im missing something here, I often am, but my award had the image of the award displayed, not a broken URL.\r\n\r\nMy message looked like this\r\n[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-3BC5_50290305.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-3BC5_50290305.jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIf you guys are talking specifically about the awards in question I apologise.\r\n\r\nEdit: On second thoughts, the message attached to mine probably indicates it was manual, not auto.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYes this was a manual award, the later batch of just ribbons also sent out PM\'s with correct images, I think its a load issue, hopefully it wont be an issue on the proper server.',NULL,NULL),(46716,5989,171777,'2012-08-13 15:50:49','Just encountered this on the main site. Twerp is disrespectfull of a mod. I edit the torrent comment and warn him about it. Today he has edited my edit and posted a second comment that gave him a 4 week warning with UL rights revoked.\r\n\r\nSuggestion is as follows: A way to make a user unable to change an edited comment if the mod in question does not want that to happen.',NULL,NULL),(46717,5978,171777,'2012-08-13 15:51:38','Damn you barumba! You just cost me 30 minutes of my life because of some creepy form of hypnotism!',NULL,NULL),(46718,5989,70679,'2012-08-13 17:50:11','yes I think a lock feature could be useful',NULL,NULL),(46719,5978,70679,'2012-08-13 17:51:27','check your bank accounts....  :wink:  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(46720,5989,48010,'2012-08-13 18:04:32','[quote=DrkNess]Just encountered this on the main site. Twerp is disrespectfull of a mod. I edit the torrent comment and warn him about it. Today he has edited my edit and posted a second comment that gave him a 4 week warning with UL rights revoked.\r\n\r\nSuggestion is as follows: [b]A way to make a user unable to change an edited comment if the mod in question does not want that to happen.[b][/quote]\r\n\r\nhas this been tested on the here ? probably not - may need to announce and try to find a voulnteer to test this or let testy do it',NULL,NULL),(46721,5989,171777,'2012-08-13 18:23:45','gimme a moment to test.\n\nEdit: Ok tested it and the original poster can once again change a comment. Also there is no way to see what the original message as like the old site provides.\n\nI have a test account for this btw :P\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35232 is where the test took place.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n \n-',84499,'2012-08-14 01:32:00'),(46722,5987,1507,'2012-08-13 18:35:09',' :yaydance:  :yaydance:  :yaydance: \r\n\r\n[b]I logged in and found that I had 13 messages from the system, and saying that I was awarded a badge/award/ribbon, and it showed the image of the award and what it stood for...\r\n\r\nThe Good Member Medal (100 cumment award), The Good Seeder Medal, The Uploaders Award, The Very Popular Upload Award, Popular Upload Award, Frequent Poster, Good Member, Good Seeder, Uploader Award, etc., all had broken urls as well...  \r\n\r\nhttp:///static/common/badges/uploaded-tb_1.png\r\n\r\n:dunno:\r\n\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46723,5989,48010,'2012-08-13 18:47:18','thanks for test Drk - so i guess it goes over to the coders\