essage itself\n\nI noticed that in threads created by me I can edit the message, but on threads created by others I cannot.',94804,'2012-08-14 12:03:36'),(46795,5995,49532,'2012-08-14 12:10:20','I can, maybe it\'s a browser issue?',49532,'2012-08-14 12:11:07'),(46796,5995,94804,'2012-08-14 12:19:50','nope, in IE neither (nor in latest Chrome)\n\n[quote=schlager]no, I meant the possibility to edit the message itself\r\n\r\nI noticed that in threads created by me I can edit the message, but on threads created by others I cannot.[/quote] That\'s a lie, sorry\r\nin here I can\'t edit either\n\nhuh? HUH? now I can, I think I\'m finally going insane',94804,'2012-08-14 12:24:44'),(46797,5995,84499,'2012-08-14 12:32:15','\r\n\r\n:lol:\r\n\r\n\r\nI feel like I could have more fun if I dont tell you but I will relent... you get 5 minutes to edit your posts.',NULL,NULL),(46798,5994,84499,'2012-08-14 12:36:52','[quote=schlager]..And if it doesn\'t apply to collages why is \"cover image\" displayed in a collage?[/quote]\r\nIt isnt.\r\n\r\nCover Art is  displayed, and that is made up of the cover images of the torrents in that collage.\r\n\r\nIf you want to include an image you can do so in the collage description.',NULL,NULL),(46799,5987,84499,'2012-08-14 12:38:19','\r\n\r\nI have no idea what you mean sorry.',NULL,NULL),(46800,5995,94804,'2012-08-14 12:45:28','oow thank God not insane (ok, then, a little) when someone else posts something, I can\'t edit anymore, so untill someone replies to this I can edit it, but after someone replied I can\'t\nsee?',94804,'2012-08-14 12:46:35'),(46801,5995,84499,'2012-08-14 12:47:49','no, you get 5 minutes lol.',NULL,NULL),(46802,5995,184595,'2012-08-14 12:48:16','\ntest\n\n---  EDITING less than 5 mins after.... but after someone else has posted after me. ----',184595,'2012-08-14 12:50:33'),(46803,5995,84499,'2012-08-14 12:48:37','post',NULL,NULL),(46804,5995,94804,'2012-08-14 12:51:50','now \"edit\"=gone',94804,'2012-08-14 12:52:04'),(46805,5995,84499,'2012-08-14 12:57:14','\r\n\r\nwhat part of you get 5 minutes to edit your post dont you understand?',NULL,NULL),(46806,5995,94804,'2012-08-14 13:03:39','hahaha oow just now i got it\nfinally',94804,'2012-08-14 13:04:19'),(46807,5995,67255,'2012-08-14 13:33:41','poor Mifune he is going to declare insanity after this tracker goes live and take a few days off. :laugh: \r\n\r\nDon\'t worry Mifune this tracker is the best there is! :hooray:  :hooray:  :hooray: ',NULL,NULL),(46808,5995,84499,'2012-08-14 14:01:56','[quote=schlager]hahaha oow just now i got it\r\nfinally[/quote]\r\n\r\nno problem :wink:\n\n[quote=elkid]\r\nDon\'t worry Mifune this tracker is the best there is! :hooray:  :hooray:  :hooray:[/quote]\r\n\r\n  :buttlicker: \r\n\r\n\r\n:lol:\r\n\r\nhaha actually I agree with you, I just like breaking out the asslicker smiley.',84499,'2012-08-14 14:06:00'),(46811,5993,129045,'2012-08-14 15:38:09','Spacing problems on IE? Which version? Using IE9 here it renders the page normally as far as I can tell, not much differences between it, Chrome and Firefox, Opera on the other hand:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=2985_502A62F2][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=2985_502A62F2&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nApplying a [code]line-height: 1;[/code] will tighten things up, but it still is too spaced out when compared to the other browsers.\r\n\r\nLooking around and setting a margin of 0 here:\r\n\r\n[code]#header_bottom ul li {\r\n    margin: 0px;\r\n}[/code]\r\n\r\nWill tighten everything across all browsers, but it kills the spacing between Tool\\Upload\\Donate Username\\Settings\\Logout ...\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\r\nNevermind, now just by setting the margin to 0 seems to make everything behave the same across different browsers, odd :hmmm: \r\n\r\n[s]Setting the spaces individually seems to have uniform results here:[/s]\r\n\r\n[code]#nav_tools {margin: 0px 7px 0px 7px !important;}\r\n#nav_upload {margin: 0px 7px 0px 7px !important;}\r\n#nav_donate {margin: 0px 7px 0px 7px !important;}\r\n#nav_userinfo {margin: 0px 7px 0px 7px !important;}\r\n#nav_useredit {margin: 0px 7px 0px 7px !important;}\r\n#nav_logout {margin: 0px 7px 0px 7px !important;}[/code]\r\n\r\n\r\n:bombie:\r\n\r\nAbout the IE thingy with the Tools dropdown, remove [code]top: 17px;[/code] from [code]#userinfo_username li ul, #userinfo_tools li ul[/code] and set it individually:\r\n\r\n[code]#userinfo_username li ul {\r\n    top: 17px;\r\n}\r\n[/code]\r\n\r\nSetting any [code]Top[/code] value under [code]#userinfo_tools li ul[/code], will \'fix\' it to IE, but break the dropdown everywhere else :hmmm:\r\n\r\nSo, act like it doesn\'t exist and don\'t mention it in the CSS :laugh:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=8B3F_502A6D70][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=8B3F_502A6D70&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n:bombie:\r\n\r\nIf people want to test it on other OSs, here\'s the custom CSS: http://dl.dropbox.com/u/90195908/DefaultEMP.css\r\n\r\n\r\nSo, is that it or am I missing the point here?',129045,'2012-08-14 20:57:56'),(46812,5684,84499,'2012-08-14 16:01:03','\r\n\r\nI fixed the quick links and the cache issue, both should be working as expected now.',NULL,NULL),(46814,5993,84499,'2012-08-14 16:28:38','\r\n\r\nno thats what I wanted :gjob:\r\n\r\nI have incorporated the fixes... untested though (I\'ll test ie later, let us know if its worked in other browsers and OS\'s etc.)',NULL,NULL),(46815,5674,84499,'2012-08-14 16:30:01','\r\nokay I incorporated yamchans fixes: let us know if its worked.\r\n\r\n(and if not please include browser version and OS when bug reporting)\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46816,5674,129045,'2012-08-14 17:08:49','I used IE9 dev tools (F12 key) to test it under Win7, so far no problems affecting negatively any other browser I tested here (Chrome 21.0.1180.75 m, Opera 12 and Firefox 13).\n\nbrb, going to check under Ubuntu.\n\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\nShowing up normally too, tested Firefox 11 and Opera 12, can\'t find a way to install Chromium correctly so, I can\'t test that :\\\n\n[b]EDIT2:[/b]\nlol, [color=red]WTF IE you piece of shit![/color]\n\n[color=#FF0000]IE7 mode will not work with the fix[/color], the dropdown will appear over Tools not under. But IE8 and IE9 will display it correctly like the other browsers :hmmm:',129045,'2012-08-14 18:16:07'),(46817,5989,51063,'2012-08-14 17:50:42','It will not apply to staff at all :D',NULL,NULL),(46819,5798,84499,'2012-08-14 18:40:02','\r\n\r\nfixed the selection issues.\r\n\r\n\r\nthe prompt is an IE behaviour that cannot be changed... there are workarounds but they are not trivial to implement. How big an issue is it? How do those buttons in the sandbox behave on emp.me?',NULL,NULL),(46820,5996,70679,'2012-08-14 18:41:34','OK seen some stuff and having done some experience myself in supporting people in their own native language to help them with especially solving upload problems I thought of this.\r\n\r\nWe can ask on the regular site as the pool is bigger, for volunteers to cover different languages with good English and technical knowledge. The we we can draft a list and use it to direct people with problems and poor English to PM them.\r\n\r\nSo.... opinions?\r\n\r\nand offer rewards also.... as yamchan put just now in IRC.',NULL,NULL),(46821,5996,48010,'2012-08-14 18:53:42','I added this to the emp.me staff forum',NULL,NULL),(46823,5989,184595,'2012-08-14 18:59:53','testy\n\nmerge\n\nskank!',84499,'2012-08-14 19:42:00'),(46824,5798,129045,'2012-08-14 19:22:21','Using IE9 here, behavior is the same still. IE will not respect the selection, instead of wrapping correctly it will simply insert the tags after it: selection[code][i][/i][b][/b][/code]\r\n\r\nBehavior is the same thing on EMP.me, tags are inserted after the selection. And the prompts also spawn at the top left corner of the window.\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\r\nOdd, the Align and Uppercase\\lowercase buttons wrap the selections correctly :hmmm:\r\n\r\n:bombie:',129045,'2012-08-14 19:30:08'),(46825,5987,94952,'2012-08-14 19:22:32','Sorry uploaded image to be clearer.\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=2EF1_502AA66C][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=2EF1_502AA66C[/img][/url]\n\nIs the \"Shop\" text there for a purpose?\nI was thinking it was meant as a link to the bonus shop. ',94952,'2012-08-14 19:23:32'),(46826,5674,94952,'2012-08-14 19:27:48','IE\'s Trident needs to die in a fire, along with it\'s QA team. \nEverything thats wrong with code is the QA peoples fault!! :ras: \n\nCoders are awesome!! Trust me I am one!!',94952,'2012-08-14 19:28:21'),(46827,5998,70679,'2012-08-14 19:48:34','Well the CDC could take a stab at this pernicious virus but... maybe...\r\n\r\na. I think that the list of seeds and peers is more useful to n00bs so why don\'t make it generally available? So they can MAYBE see why their torrents are slow etc...\r\n\r\nb. have the system (if possible) generate a warning PM and ask the user to correct the situation with short explanation and link to the appropriate tutorial?',NULL,NULL),(46828,5999,164805,'2012-08-14 19:55:30','Can the number of torrents viewed per page be changed to anything other than 50? \r\nThe old site has a section under my profile to manually type in any number.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46829,5995,70679,'2012-08-14 19:59:01','erm actually .... this is BAD I need my edit button back... thanks.',NULL,NULL),(46830,6000,70679,'2012-08-14 20:03:26','thanks really need it....',NULL,NULL),(46831,5998,129045,'2012-08-14 20:08:59','An automatic check\\warning? Is that feasible?\r\n\r\nManual checking can be made here: http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?action=connchecker\r\n\r\nI can\'t test now, but is the peerlist still locked to some user classes?',NULL,NULL),(46832,5995,129045,'2012-08-14 20:27:18','You know, seeing the post\\comment edit history working as intended, I gotta side with [b]barumba[/b] here.\r\n\r\nAs he pointed it out on IRC, it punishes other users for the actions of just a few. Plus, having the such a limited window to edit posts\\comments wouldn\'t stop the user from posting new inflammatory comments\\posts anyway.\r\n\r\n:hmmm:',129045,'2012-08-14 20:29:30'),(46833,6001,94952,'2012-08-14 20:31:08','[b]URL:[/b] http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php\n[b]What\'s Wrong:[/b]\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=912A_502AB58F][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=912A_502AB58F[/img][/url]\nSubforum view shows that \"Suggestions\" subforum ha no unread threads.\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=6A70_502AB58F][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=6A70_502AB58F[/img][/url]\nSubforum \"Suggesstions\" has one (or more) unread threads.\n\n[b]Reproduce:[/b] Wait until two or more posts are unread. Read one. Hit the \"Forums\"-link at the top and subforum is marked as read.\n\n[b]My thoughts[/b]\nMaybe this is the way it should be, I just wanted to point it out.\n\nEdit: If timing is off it is because of a copy-pasta error. The problem is there. ',94952,'2012-08-14 20:32:55'),(46834,5989,84499,'2012-08-14 20:36:23','test\n\nmmm',84499,'2012-08-14 20:36:29'),(46835,6001,84499,'2012-08-14 20:39:45','\r\n\r\nThat is just showing you the latest thread in each forum.\r\n\r\n\r\nFor unread posts click on the unread posts button.',NULL,NULL),(46836,6001,94952,'2012-08-14 20:41:43','Okay. My mistake.',NULL,NULL),(46837,5674,84499,'2012-08-14 20:42:48','\r\n\r\nfuck IE7.\r\n\r\nif it works in IE9 I am satisfied. The tools menu is only for staff and I expect them to at least use a modern version of their browser.',NULL,NULL),(46838,5987,84499,'2012-08-14 20:44:19','\r\noh I\'ll remove that its a remnant from a previous version of that list.',NULL,NULL),(46839,5995,70679,'2012-08-14 20:45:51','indeed I think much better solution could be used to wrestle an unruly user.... let\'s switch back and have a discussion where solutions can be presented and we can find a better one that also does not involve too complicated programming... I can think a few...\r\n\r\nalso generally in my long experience as admin in other places and times users openly defying mods/admins got ONE warning and then it was ban city.',NULL,NULL),(46840,5993,129045,'2012-08-14 20:58:11','Now about the spacing on Opera... lol\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\r\nYes it is! Run the usual tests here and seems 100% fine.\r\n\r\nWin7: Chrome, Firefox, IE, Opera\r\nUbuntu: Firefox and Opera\r\n\r\nAll menus are accessible, no gaps or weird spacing and it\'s all aligning correctly. If [b]iamstoopid[/b] didn\'t report any problems after the new fonts were applied, then I guess now it will show up ok everywhere :hmmm:',129045,'2012-08-19 21:02:47'),(46841,5995,84499,'2012-08-14 21:01:00','\r\n\r\nalthough it came about as a reaction to that problem (users editing a staff edit) that isnt the primary purpose of it imo.\r\n\r\nFor the most part when you make a forum post /comment I think there is a definite logic to not being able to go back and change the record of your conversation at some arbitary point in the future. Most forums I am a member of time limit it and with good reason... because otherwise you can go back and \'change history\' - and most users cannot use the edit back button to see what was said before. \r\n\r\nThere are some obvious exceptions to this, like people wanting to edit tutorial posts etc. and I can easily add a permission that can be set for specific users (and/or classes) to allow them to edit their own posts, already the moderate forums permission does this but it makes sense to add a specific one as well. Or we can go back to allowing edits at any point in time, if we do keep the time restriction it will be longer than 5 mins - in fact its actually whatever time is set in the frontend - currently 5 mins - plus 15 mins to allow a little grace period for editing a post. 5 mins was just a good setting for testing.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46842,5747,84499,'2012-08-14 21:06:03',' :sorry: ',NULL,NULL),(46843,5674,129045,'2012-08-14 21:16:58','There\'s an slightly inconsistency yet, under [code]#userinfo_username li ul, #userinfo_tools li ul[/code] you may need to set [code]Left: 7px;[/code], because the dropdown isn\'t aligning correctly with the dropdown arrow, sorry.\r\n\r\nAnd fucking hell. Forgot to test the Light stylesheet -_-\r\n\r\nUnder Opera, due to the weird spacing issue, if the user tries to access the Tools menu \'slowly\' (approach [b]Tools[/b] from below with the mouse cursor) there will be a small gap between it and the dropdown, in which case will result in the same problem we were having before with IE, the dropdown disappears if the user doesn\'t move the cursor fast enough.\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\r\nThe later, seems to only happens on Windows, Ubuntu\'s Opera is fine accessing the menu.',129045,'2012-08-17 18:39:28'),(46844,5996,1246,'2012-08-14 21:42:05','I support a multilingual help and support staff, and I\'d be happy to help whomever pick people suited for this task.',NULL,NULL),(46845,5998,1246,'2012-08-14 21:44:23','I suggested in IRC that the best way I know of to inform people that they are not connectable is a large, undismissable RED BAR at the top of every page that says \"YOU ARE NOT CONNECTABLE. CLICK HERE TO FIX THIS.\"\r\n\r\nThough I am unsure of the amount of time required to code something like this into the site, I believe it may be less of a hassle to do it now rather then delay it.',NULL,NULL),(46846,5998,84499,'2012-08-14 21:49:59','\r\n\r\nokay just looking at the code... maybe I can put in a banner like bork says (certainly this is the only possiblity I am really considering, its relatively easy and i think will be effective) - bear this in mind - unconnectability is not a certain calculation, connectable peers can briefly appear unconnectable when they first connect etc and i do not want to be doing anything more complex than putting the current connectable status up top. If we can live with the false positives this is probably the best way.',NULL,NULL),(46847,5996,70679,'2012-08-14 21:57:58','OK then any proposals for rewards to motivate? Let\'s have all set and agreed before we do a call for action...',NULL,NULL),(46848,5998,70679,'2012-08-14 22:06:42','we can warn that it could be a false positive... or if not too complicated only warn if not connectable over a period of time...',NULL,NULL),(46851,5693,51063,'2012-08-14 22:58:40','Sorry but if some wanker comes in and offers a bounty for a torrent that is already present . . . it is his own damn fault.\r\n\r\nYeah if it was the uploaders intent to collect the bounty and someone beats him to it that is an issue.  But that will become known in an hour or so.  Also if you are uploading to fill a request you should post the link as soon as it starts hash checking in your client (that is what I do).   If the uploader forgets or whatever I guess that is possible but all he has to do is let staff know somehow and as long as it is done in a reasonable time frame we can work it out.  I really do not think this will be a big issue.\r\n\r\nAs to the rest of your complaints/issues . . . I agree 100%',NULL,NULL),(46853,5998,84499,'2012-08-14 23:32:14','\nimplemented. needs testing...\n\n\nit looks for any connections you currently have where you are unconnectable - but if you have any valid connections it wont show it, updates every 10 minutes.\n\n-',84499,'2012-08-15 13:40:42'),(46854,5998,70679,'2012-08-14 23:46:41','and now ladies and gents we need guinea pigs... I can see if I can try this afternoon.',NULL,NULL),(46855,5996,1246,'2012-08-15 00:00:52','[mcom]I\'d suggest giving any active members of the H&S teams freeleech. Also, what does this tag do....[/mcom]',NULL,NULL),(46856,6000,47234,'2012-08-15 00:34:30','For those who write any sort of guide in the forums this is a really useful feature.  Hmmmm',NULL,NULL),(46857,6000,84499,'2012-08-15 00:37:53','\r\n\r\nI have already added a specific permission to allow users to edit their own posts at any time so those who write guides etc can have the ability to do so.',NULL,NULL),(46858,5998,47234,'2012-08-15 00:38:33','Hmm i wouldnt even know how to go about becoming unconnectable :lol:',NULL,NULL),(46859,6000,47234,'2012-08-15 00:39:39','Ahh so we need to add that permission for those who ask then?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46860,5996,51063,'2012-08-15 00:40:46','It is so staff can edit a luser\'s post and the luser knows a staffer has responded or spanked him or whatever',NULL,NULL),(46861,6000,51063,'2012-08-15 00:42:24','I think that is the plan yes\n\n--- Edit but I have no fucking idea how to do it LOL',51063,'2012-08-15 00:44:56'),(46862,6000,84499,'2012-08-15 00:46:25','\r\nits an admin thing',NULL,NULL),(46863,6000,47234,'2012-08-15 00:47:54','[quote=mifune]its an admin thing[/quote]\r\n\r\nThat means bug Clownius if someone needs it :lol:',NULL,NULL),(46864,5998,94952,'2012-08-15 01:09:47','I tested my connectivity with Conn-Checker, it was green and working.\r\nI killed my torrent client.\r\nRetested my connectivity with Conn-Checker, it was red and not working.\r\n11 minutes later still no red annoying warning. \r\nRedid my test to be sure. I will report in a while again, 30 minutes or so.',NULL,NULL),(46866,6004,94952,'2012-08-15 01:15:51','[b]URL:[/b] forum.php\r\n[b]Whats wrong:[/b] I got the following error message after trying to post my edit. I was within a minute of my original post.\r\n\"Sorry - you only have 1970-01-01 00:15:00 to edit your post before it is automatically locked.\" Looks like cast or datediff mistake\r\n[b]Reproduce:[/b] I reproduced it in the same post. For others make a post and try to edit it. \n\nDoubleposting since I can\'t edit. Tried it in another thread, same error.',94952,'2012-08-15 01:22:27'),(46868,6004,84499,'2012-08-15 01:32:16','\r\n\r\nfixed... I think.',NULL,NULL),(46869,6004,94952,'2012-08-15 01:33:38','It works. Inserted before so it is an edit not a merged post.\nTesting now :smile1: \n\nFixed.  :gjob: ',94952,'2012-08-15 01:34:54'),(46871,6005,84499,'2012-08-15 01:52:31','\r\n\r\nIt seems the connectable status in the peerlist never shows anyone as unconnectable, even when they are unconnectable on emp.me they still show as connectable on torrents here...\r\n\r\n\r\nThis isnt that easy to test so could all testers who are able to set their ports incorrectly or whatever and who do show up as unconnectable on any torrents at emp.me report your experiences here.\r\n\r\nAnd even more so if anyone can get themselves to show up as unconnectable in a peerlist here please take a screenshot, note the torrent and tell us asap. Thanks!\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46872,6005,94952,'2012-08-15 02:00:06','[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=CA8C_502B0307][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=CA8C_502B0307[/img][/url]\nPeerlist from Candy Stripers. I downloaded and seeded, but now I killed my BitTorrent client. And you can see for yourselves.\nBombshells 4 it is the same deal. \n\nI will keep my BT client off for a few hours.',94952,'2012-08-15 02:00:33'),(46873,6005,84499,'2012-08-15 02:02:46','\r\n\r\nbut should you have been unconnectable? \r\n\r\nwhere you showing as unconnectable on emp.me on any/all torrents you were seeding there?\r\n\r\nhow long are you showing in that peerlist after you closed your client?\r\n\r\ndid you force a manual update from your client?\r\n\r\nhow long were you connected on that torrent for?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46874,6005,94952,'2012-08-15 02:11:42','[quote=mifune]but should you have been unconnectable? \n\nwhere you showing as unconnectable on emp.me on any/all torrents you were seeding there?\n\nhow long are you showing in that peerlist after you closed your client?\n\ndid you force a manual update from your client?\n\nhow long were you connected on that torrent for?[/quote]\n\n1. Yes. I sigtermed(kill -15) my client. Conn-Checker goes red and reports correctly that I\'m unreachable.\n2. Empornium.me shows as 0 seeding, was 400+ (gotta clean some of that mess up)\n3. 30+ minutes. I will leave it off for a few hours at least, and update with results.\n4. Nope, I dont know if I can do that. Client lacks certain features. But I killed it nicely so it should have performed clean up operations.\n5. Days. I downloaded pretty fast after it went up.',94952,'2012-08-15 02:16:10'),(46875,6000,70679,'2012-08-15 02:14:04','[quote=Clownius][quote=mifune]its an admin thing[/quote]\r\n\r\nThat means bug Clownius if someone needs it :lol:[/quote]\r\n\r\nactually I do not know how to says this.... but you did not give me the proper permissions.... but not to worry his excellency the great Mifune did fix it for me so I have few more stuff to confuse me.',NULL,NULL),(46877,6005,84499,'2012-08-15 02:18:36','\r\nyes you are unreachable. but that is not the same as being unconnectable.\r\n\r\nIf you are saying it is taking too long to update the status in the peerlist yes you might be right, it may even be a related issue but I am specifically looking for users who show as unconnectable on torrents at emp and show as connectable on torrents here. preferably after they have been on the torrents for several hours.',NULL,NULL),(46878,6005,94952,'2012-08-15 02:28:48','Ahhh! I see. I blame it on my lack off sleep. But it could be a related issue as you say.\n\nAdditional info: I\'m not connected at all on emp.me. Emp.me correctly sensed that I killed my client. As in not active nor connectable.',94952,'2012-08-15 02:37:20'),(46880,6000,51063,'2012-08-15 03:05:36','[quote=mifune]its an admin thing[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nThat would explain why I could not find the option on barumba\'s profile LOL',NULL,NULL),(46883,6005,51063,'2012-08-15 03:19:46','If you sig term (15) your client it will probably not send a proper shutdown message to the tracker(s) in question.  This as mifune pointed out is not the same thing at all.  Most torrent sites have an inactive timeout of 45 minutes . . . if your client has not reported back after 45 minutes the tracker will remove you from the peer list.  If you Sig kill (9) this will definitely happen.  In theory a sig term should not do that . . . but if your client has no way to manually update the tracker I suspect it does not handle a sig term correctly.\r\n\r\nI suspect that your emp.me torrents were closer to that 45 minute inactive timeout than your torrents here . . . but without detailed logs of both sites and your torrent client it is impossible for me to be certain.  For example if your .me torrents were at say 29 minutes since last update . . . it would only take 16 more minutes for the tracker to delete you from that/those torrents.',NULL,NULL),(46886,6005,94952,'2012-08-15 03:50:58','Actually GaryE you got it reversed. Kill <pid> (sigterm) should clean up after it self and Kill -9 <pid> (sigkill) can not.\r\n\r\n\"When sent to a program, SIGKILL causes it to terminate immediately. In contrast to SIGTERM and SIGINT, this signal cannot be caught or ignored, and the receiving process cannot perform any clean-up upon receiving this signal.\"\r\nQuote from Wikipedia\r\n\r\nAnd sigterm takes about four seconds longer to perform than sigkill, I\'m hoping clean up takes place during that time.\r\nBut that is not relevant to this bug anyway. \r\n\r\nWhat is relevant is that I use a unusual torrent client (Transmission 1.92) and therefore will stop testing any connection related bugs unless I am asked by Mifune or Lanz to do so. \r\n\r\nI\'m not mad or upset in anyway I just don\'t want to pollute the data needed to debug this.',NULL,NULL),(46887,6005,153855,'2012-08-15 04:17:16','I just made myself unconnectable. It shows on empornium.me but on this site it says I am still connectable.\r\nI am using utorrent 2.2',NULL,NULL),(46888,6007,153855,'2012-08-15 04:48:23','Just checked the amount of uploaded torrents on the test tracker and on empornium.me and they are not the same. I got 54 uploads on empornium.me and 52 overhere. I dont know if it matters but I thought I\'d tell you anyways.\r\n\r\n:wave:',NULL,NULL),(46889,6007,86439,'2012-08-15 04:52:55','Stats are from the past, not current. Relax, all stats will be transferred from the main site. Stats here are just test stats.',NULL,NULL),(46891,6005,84499,'2012-08-15 05:03:26','\r\n\r\nThanks.\r\n\r\nIf you (and/or anyone else) could confirm that result over an hour or two - staying unconnectable on emp.me but apparently connectable in the peerlists here - that would be a big help to us. ',NULL,NULL),(46892,6005,86439,'2012-08-15 05:08:11','I just unticked the permission in my router for utorrent (2.2.1). The conn checker fails (red bar) when I enter my correct IP, and the port I was using.\n\nMain site says not connectable (definitely was connectable prior) However my uploads here show me as connectable as you predict.\n\nDone maybe 5 minutes ago. I will leave it like that for a few hours if needed.\n\nEdit: I see its needed.',86439,'2012-08-15 05:09:09'),(46893,6008,84499,'2012-08-15 05:35:49','\r\n\r\nWe are nearing the end... next week(....ish) I hope to be able to say we have 100% nailed all the features down and killed all the outstanding bugs and we will be just hunting for the last bugs and preparing to go live,\r\n\r\n\r\nTo help us make one last big push I will probably put up some announcement or thread next week. This is just some preperation for that, feel free to post additions in the \"stuff you should be testing\" list:\r\n\r\n\r\nOh, DrkNess - that reminds me we (you, haha) should put your testers guide up somewhere and that can lead into this (or at least be referenced by whatever this becomes).\r\n\r\n\r\nFUNCTIONALITY\r\n\r\nUSEABILITY\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTorrents\r\n- uploading\r\n- uploading badly (wrong files, exact dupes (matching files), bad input)\r\n- comments\r\n- Reports\r\n- Marked for deletion system\r\n- Community tagging\r\n- Search\r\n\r\nForums\r\n- bbcode, sandbox, bad bbcode\r\n- all things post, edit, poll, new, history\r\n\r\nRequests\r\n\r\nCollages\r\n- authoring/permissions\r\n- diff categories (personal is a \'special\' category)\r\n- logging, abuse.\r\n\r\nNotifications\r\n\r\nRules/Help section\r\n- links, spelling, formatting?, missing topics?, organisation?\r\n\r\nPrivate Messaging.\r\n- conversations, blocks, inbox/sentbox functionality.\r\n\r\nStaff Messaging.\r\n- open conversations (all staff + user), assigning to levels, initiated by user normally but also by report system.\r\n\r\nUser profiles/Settings\r\n\r\n\r\n============================\r\n\r\n\r\nfor Staff:\r\n\r\nall the staff tools\r\nuser groups\r\nforum tools (delete/merge/etc - remember to test merging polls/threads)\r\nmoderation tools\r\nreports (non-torrent) system\r\nREPORTSv2 SYSTEM (torrent report system)\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46900,6008,86439,'2012-08-15 06:36:31','I just merged two threads, it merges them in chronological order by time posted. Connected posts likely will be all over the shot.\n\nNot sure how else you would do it though.\n\npoll moved across fine.\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3002&postid=26898#post26898\n\n\nEdit: And it wont merge two threads if each has a poll.\n\n',86439,'2012-08-15 08:10:09'),(46912,6005,153855,'2012-08-15 09:08:18','After 2 and a half hour of being unconnectable the trackers still show the same results: connectable here and unconnectable at .me',NULL,NULL),(46913,6012,171777,'2012-08-15 10:00:09','[size=3][b]Guide to effective bug testing[/b][/size]\n\nThis guide is meant to be a good starting point for any tester. It contains some basic guidelines to testing and bug hunting aswell as some things that we already found. If you think that this guide is not complete or if it is incorrect please send me a PM or reply in this thread.\n\n[size=3][b]How to submit a bug report[/b][/size]\n\nLet\'s start with the most important information first. What do do when you find a bug. \n\nTo tell us about it we need specific information:\n\n\nNow for some simple guidelines when you want to share you bug with the coders.\n \n[*]Search the forum to see if the bug is already known.\n[*]If the bug is indeed new then start a new topic. As a topic name please use following: Location - Desription of bug. With location I mean things like [Forum] or [Torrent Details]. Example: [Torrent Upload] - My cover image is not accepted.\n[*]Fill the topic with as much information as you possibly can. Use images if it is hard to describe what is happening. Be sure to atleast give the information as noted in the following 3 bullets.\n[*][b]The page url[/b] For example the url for the browse torrents page is [code]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php[/code] which when written in a post becomes: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php\n[*][b]What is wrong[/b] Tell us what the problem is, and if applicable the way you expect it to work.\n[*][b]How to reproduce it[/b] Please include enough information so that we can reproduce the bug ourselves. Reproduce it yourself first if possible, and make a note of what actions produce the bug.\n[*]Keep track of your topic (potentially subscribe to it). Coders might require additional information or another tester might want to do additional tests working together with you.\n \n[size=3][b]How to hunt for bugs[/b][/size]\n \nThere is no set way in which one can hunt for a bug. The reason for this is that no one knows where the bugs are located. There are however a few simple pointers that you can follow while hunting:\n \n[*][b]Work systematically[/b] In other words don\'t go clicking haphazardly because that way it is almost impossible to reproduce what you did when things go wrong.\n[*][b]Test things multiple times[/b] A result could always be a fluke. This goes for both bugs and correct functionality. If you test something several times and the same thing always happens then you either have a bug that you can reproduce or you have correct behaviour that you can vouch for.\n[*][b]Test again at a later time[/b] Some bugs are easy to fix, others are a lot more complicated. To ensure that a bug is truly gone or that an old bug doesn\'t reappear it is always advisable to test features again a week later and yet again the next week. It would suck if 2 weeks after going live a bug reappears because it  is date triggered and happens every 2 weeks or something.\n[*][b]Don\'t assume anything[/b] As they say: \"Assumption is the mother of all fuck-ups\". If you think something works then please make sure that it does.\n \n \nPlease note that this list probably is not complete and is therefor subject to change. Take a look every once in a while to see if there were changes. Who knows the coders might have noticed that a certain step is not neccessary and you are still doing all that work for nothing! ',171777,'2012-08-15 10:02:42'),(46914,6008,171777,'2012-08-15 10:04:21','Ok the bug hunt guide is available to the public. Made it an announcement to give it some initial views but it is also in the bugs section of the forum.',NULL,NULL),(46915,5989,70679,'2012-08-15 11:04:21','ok.... I was wondering how difficult it would be to program a \"mute\" or \"silence\" user flag that can be set by admis/mods to wrestle unruly users, to give them a time out. Once set the user cannot post or modify entries in the forum or torrents or use PMs.\r\n\r\nThen once the muzzle is on you could warn to user that it will stay on say 24h and then expire. If he behaves fine otherwise is ban city.\r\n\r\nThis way everybody can have edit back...',NULL,NULL),(46916,5989,47234,'2012-08-15 11:06:51','My understanding is we could just disable certain things on the user account to achieve this now.  We would just need to remember to give them back later',NULL,NULL),(46917,5989,70679,'2012-08-15 12:29:34','could be an one button automated thing.... that takes away, warns and give back after say 24h. So you do not have to track it',NULL,NULL),(46918,6013,78455,'2012-08-15 12:55:03','(Example) URL: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=10929\r\n\r\nThe final tag listed is an empty tag created by voting in a tag consisting only of three or more non-alphanumeric characters, e.g. \"???\".',NULL,NULL),(46919,6013,84499,'2012-08-15 12:59:22','\r\n\r\nnice catch. thanks. :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(46920,6008,84499,'2012-08-15 13:01:28','[quote=knickers]I just merged two threads, it merges them in chronological order by time posted. Connected posts likely will be all over the shot.\r\n\r\nNot sure how else you would do it though.\r\n\r\npoll moved across fine.\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3002&postid=26898#post26898\r\n\r\n\r\nEdit: And it wont merge two threads if each has a poll.[/quote]\r\n\r\nCool. I dont think there is any other way to merge threads.  \n\n\r\n[quote=DrkNess]Ok the bug hunt guide is available to the public. Made it an announcement to give it some initial views but it is also in the bugs section of the forum.[/quote]\r\n\r\nThanks Drkness, looks good.',84499,'2012-08-15 13:03:04'),(46921,5989,84499,'2012-08-15 13:07:15','User Privileges\r\nDisable: 	Posting\r\n\r\n\r\nalready exists. You would have to remember to re-enable it... but this is a rare issue. I have plenty of ideas for tools that would be used a lot more often that I dont have time to implement already...',NULL,NULL),(46922,5989,70679,'2012-08-15 13:10:24','ok then means edit back to normal for all? :wink:  :tongue: ',NULL,NULL),(46923,5989,86439,'2012-08-15 13:19:18','While we\'re on the subject of editing etc, will we get, or is it specific to certain people, the ability to check the edit history of a post?\n\nIts just I noticed Yamchan has it on the old site (\"View edit\" edit history or some such named thing), while I have quote and he doesnt. I notice its not here either, view edit that is.\n\n\n\nlook for the little arrow symbol Â« to the bottom left of the \"Last edited by mifune just now\" text below this',84499,'2012-08-15 13:41:57'),(46925,5989,84499,'2012-08-15 13:43:18','\nI edited your post ^^ with a hint\n\n\nOh... and everyone has the quote button :hmmm:',84499,'2012-08-15 13:45:42'),(46926,5989,86439,'2012-08-15 13:46:47','Awesomeness.\n\nNot on the old site. Not every mod has the post edit history button either. Myself and Eimaimpala noticed Yamchans loked different to ours. He has edit history, but no quote.\n\nAnd I mentioned that wasnt a mod feature I always had quote.\n\nNot that it matters, its short lived now.',86439,'2012-08-15 13:49:06'),(46927,5989,84499,'2012-08-15 13:51:52','\r\n\r\nThe edit time out is 15 minutes. (in the front end, ie if you reload after 15 mins there will be no edit button.)\r\n\r\nIn the backend it is whatever it is in the front end plus 15 minutes to allow a little grace period for those who are editing.\r\n\r\nStaff and anyone who has general forum mod permissions (ie. FLS) can edit all posts anyway.I have added a specific permission to allow specific users to override this - so if a user is writing some guides or something they can be given the permission to edit their own posts at any point.\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(46928,5989,84499,'2012-08-15 13:55:33','[quote=knickers]Awesomeness.\r\n\r\nNot on the old site. Not every mod has the post edit history button either. Myself and Eimaimpala noticed Yamchans loked different to ours. He has edit history, but no quote.\r\n [/quote]\r\n\r\nAre you talking about here or emp.me????\r\n\r\neither way I am dubious... on emp there are no permissions there are just ranks... all mods have the same interface (unless they are fucking with it through greasemonkey scripts or somesuch).\r\n\r\nHere I am pretty sure all the mods have the same permissions set. And everyone has the quote button.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46929,5989,86439,'2012-08-15 14:02:36','Yeah Ive got that, its all good here. It was the main site I was referring to when i mentioned the lack of a quote button. I have it there, yamchan doesnt.\n\nYesterday Yamchan posted some screens of a conversation (main site), his posts showed he had a view history button (or similar named) but no quote.\n\nWhile eimaimpala and myself have the same 3 buttons, edit quote delete. IIRC, yamchan had 4 button, but not one was quote, cant remember what they all were, edit delete view history but he specifically mentioned he had no quote button.\n\nBut its all main site related and not really important, I was just curious about it as we discussed it over there.\n\n\nEdit: Ah yeah thats the other one, report post. Neither eimaimpala or myself have that either. Yamchan did.\n\nCame up in a thread with this image\nhttp://hcd-1.imgbox.com/adqmiHTZ.png?st=UPaKxgjKCtp8hvtUe1Mj0Q&e=1345041954',86439,'2012-08-15 14:07:53'),(46930,5989,84499,'2012-08-15 14:11:50','\r\n\r\nlol\r\n\r\non emp.me everyone can see quote buttons in the forums (but not the comments), and all mods can see edit history buttons in the torrent comments (but not the forums).\r\n\r\nI agree its stupid that they work differently to eachother but its page based not user based differences ;)',NULL,NULL),(46931,5989,86439,'2012-08-15 14:16:34','DOH!!!\r\n\r\n:laugh:',NULL,NULL),(46932,6005,86439,'2012-08-15 14:43:05','Still showing as connectable here, while not connectable on main site. I tried logging out too a few times earlier, it made no difference.\n\ngoing by my last post, that was 9 hrs.',86439,'2012-08-15 14:44:31'),(46933,6005,129045,'2012-08-15 14:52:15','Same results as reported yesterday on IRC:\r\n\r\n- UPnP disabled on utorrent 3.1.3 and router (no special permissions\\ports forwarded)\r\n- Port 6881 used: Fails utorrent network check and the site conn-check. Yet, utorrent display the connection as OK (Green icon)\r\n- EMP.me lists me as [color=red]not connectable[/color] immediately\r\n- EMP.mooo still lists me as connectable\r\n- Queue Seed on utorrent, EMP.mooo will still list me as Connectable, but will update my [b]Active[/b] status immediately to \'No\'.\r\n\r\nAnd I\'m out of ideas of what to do to test it further :\\',NULL,NULL),(46934,6005,70679,'2012-08-15 15:32:55','Well I reported the same yesterday and at this point we wait that the tracker code is looked at....',NULL,NULL),(46936,6015,48010,'2012-08-15 15:41:26','[align=center]\n[size=2][b]***************************[/b][/size]\n[spoiler=instructions] \nThis is the staff draft version - feel free to comment in this thread\n\nI\'ll leave this open to staff for a few days then add it as an Article with a forum thread for members to comment (***remind self add forum link later ****)\n\nI probably missed some things and others are maybe not  clear !! Some things may be stating the obvious but I am trying to cover all options especially for those who are not so good at English. I have tried to keep my language simple where possible - not to patronise but to be clear.\n\nComments on layout, colour, font etc welcome - I\'m not that creative but we don\'t need this to look like a Christmans tree, or be pink either :wink:\n\nEdit it if you need to - but please post in the thread a brief description of what you edited (sort of changelog but I\'m not going to impose one). Senior staff can just remove the clarifications or correct if necessary - no need for us to go back and forward with that. If I see they are gone then it\'s confirmed - simple as that :wink:\n\nEspecially look for typos :wink:\n\nPlease note where it says [b]clarication needed[/b] leave it to senior staff (Lanz or Clownius) to remove that unless you are absolutely sure.\n\n[/spoiler]\n[size=2][b]***************************[/b][/size]\n[/align]\n\n\n\n[size=4][align=center][#=top]Welcome to the new empornium.me[/#][/align][/size]\n\nThere have been a lot of changes so this guide is a summary to help you.\n\nSome things are new, many things have changed, please take the time to read this guide and make sure you understand how the new site works - what new features and functions are available to you (we now have a bounty based requests system, collages, bookmarks etc.) and how some of the new systems will affect you (uploaders need to understand how the marked for deletion system works for example).\n\nThis guide serves as a brief introduction, for more details please see the new [url=/articles.php?topic=tutorials]Help tutorials[/url] and [url=/articles.php?topic=rules]Rules articles[/url] - they are linked in the main header too. Or if you have further questions please post in the [url=/forums.php?action=viewforum&forumid=6]Help & Support forum[/url].\n\n[spoiler=notes] \n[b]Staff note:[/b]  We should no longer be using forum threads for stuff like reference rules/help information. ALL of that stuff should be in an article somewhere, preferably written as concisely as possible while still being thorough. The point of articles is partly so we can have \"proper\" webpages instead of forum threads for this kind of information - but staff/whoever can still have access to change them through the site software (instead of being static content you need a coder to change).[/size]  - obviously drafting stuff in threads is fine - this only applies to finished content [b] - mifune[/b][/spoiler]\n\n\n\n\n[bg=grey,310px,left][color=white][font=Tahoma][size=4][align=center][b]Contents[/b][/align][/size][/font][/color][bg=white,300px][bg=270px] \n[url=#top]Welcome[/url]\n[url=#clients]Client whitelist[/url]\n[url=#upload]Uploading[/url]\n[url=#search]The search function[/url]\n[url=#credits]Credits and bonus shop[/url]\n[url=#requests]Requests[/url]\n[url=#freeleech]Automatic Freeleech[/url]\n[url=#collages]Collages[/url]\n[url=#tagging]Community Tagging[/url]\n[url=#mfd]Marked for Deletion[/url]\n[url=#badges]Badges and Medals[/url]\n[url=#classes]User Classes[/url]\n[url=#fls]Front Line Support[/url]\n[url=#bounty]Reward for dupe reports[/url] \n[url=#irc]IRC[/url] \n[url=#restrict]Restrictions on Editing Torrents/Editing Posts[/url] \n[url=#notifications]Notifications[/url] \n[url=#inactive]Inactive Users[/url]\n[url=#reaper]Torrent Reaper[/url]\n[url=#profile]Profile page[/url]\n[url=#settings]User Settings[/url]\n[/bg][/bg]\n[/bg]\n\n\n\n\n[#=clients]Client Whitelist[/#]\n\nWe now have a strict whitelist for torrent clients that are allowed/blacklist for clients that are banned.\n\n[whitelist]**NOTE: in the articles section this will appear as a table of the allowed clients.\n\n\n[#=upload]Uploading[/#] \n\nThere is no fixed announce url anymore - when you create a torrent you can leave it blank. The site uses your passkey to announce the torrent and add stats to you. \n\nRead the uploading rules and see[URL=http://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=286] Uploading guide - a quick checklist[/url] [size=3]<-- change thread to article[/size]\n\n[b]Note[/b] the uploading form will not continue if the torrent does not contain enough basic information. \nAll presentations must follow the [url=/articles.php?topic=upload]uploading rules[/url]\n \nThere are various [url=/articles.php?topic=tutorials#uploading]help tutorials for uploading[/url]:\n[url=/articles.php?topic=presentation]Guide to Presentations [/url] - A useful guide to making a presentation \n[url=/articles.php?topic=tag_glossary]Tags - Glossary[/url] - A list of potential tags for use and their meanings.\n[url=/articles.php?topic=uploadchecklist]Uploading Checklist[/url] - A helpful guide to uploading\n[url=/articles.php?topic=utorrentupload]Uploading with uTorrent for Dummies[/url] - A small guide on how to upload with uTorrent\n[url=/articles.php?topic=vuzeupload]Uploading with Vuze for Dummies[/url] - A guide on how to download with Vuze \n 	\n\n[#=search]The search function[/#]\n\nOne of the biggest changes under the hood of the new site is the tagging system which allows for a much better search function. The search interface on the [url=/torrents.php]Browse torrents[/url] page is very similar to the one on the old site but will give you much better results.\n\nFor a more details on search and the differences between basic and advanced search please see the [url=/articles.php?topic=search]Search[/url] article in the help section.\n\n\n[#=credits]Credits and bonus shop[/#]\n\nThe bonus system has changed. Click on [url=/bonus.php]Credits[/url] (in the top right corner of the page) or Bonus in the drop-down list under your site nickname. \n\nThere are no longer any next credits the tracker awards credits at short regular intervals instead.\n\nUnder your user profile you will see a bonus log section, this is a record of how you have spent your credits (only visible to you).\n\n\n[*]New credit formula: There is no longer a weekly cap, but the more you seed the less extra bonus you get per extra torrent (more seeded is always worth more though) - see spoiler for details:\n\n[spoiler=amounts][font=Courier New]\n+----------+---------+\n| torrents | credits |\n+----------+---------+\n| 1        | 2       |\n| 2        | 3       |\n| 3        | 5       |\n| 4        | 6       |\n| 5        | 7       |\n| 6        | 8       |\n| 7        | 9       |\n| 8        | 10      |\n| 9        | 11      |\n| 10       | 12      |\n| 11       | 13      |\n| 12       | 14      |\n| 13       | 15      |\n| 14       | 16      |\n| 15       | 16      |\n| 16       | 17      |\n| 17       | 18      |\n| 18       | 19      |\n| 19       | 19      |\n| 20       | 20      |\n| 21       | 21      |\n| 22       | 21      |\n| 23       | 22      |\n| 24       | 23      |\n| 25       | 23      |\n| 26       | 24      |\n| 27       | 24      |\n| 28       | 25      |\n| 29       | 25      |\n| 30       | 26      |\n| 31       | 27      |\n| 32       | 27      |\n| 33       | 28      |\n| 34       | 28      |\n| 35       | 29      |\n| 36       | 29      |\n| 37       | 30      |\n| 38       | 30      |\n| 39       | 31      |\n| 40       | 31      |\n| 41       | 32      |\n| 42       | 32      |\n| 43       | 33      |\n| 44       | 33      |\n| 45       | 34      |\n| 46       | 34      |\n| 47       | 34      |\n| 48       | 35      |\n| 49       | 35      |\n| 50       | 36      |\n| 51       | 36      |\n| 52       | 37      |\n| 53       | 37      |\n| 54       | 38      |\n| 55       | 38      |\n| 56       | 38      |\n| 57       | 39      |\n| 58       | 39      |\n| 59       | 40      |\n| 60       | 40      |\n| 61       | 40      |\n| 62       | 41      |\n| 63       | 41      |\n| 64       | 42      |\n| 65       | 42      |\n| 66       | 42      |\n| 67       | 43      |\n| 68       | 43      |\n| 69       | 43      |\n| 70       | 44      |\n| 71       | 44      |\n| 72       | 45      |\n| 73       | 45      |\n| 74       | 45      |\n| 75       | 46      |\n| 76       | 46      |\n| 77       | 46      |\n| 78       | 47      |\n| 79       | 47      |\n| 80       | 47      |\n| 81       | 48      |\n| 82       | 48      |\n| 83       | 48      |\n| 84       | 49      |\n| 85       | 49      |\n| 86       | 49      |\n| 87       | 50      |\n| 88       | 50      |\n| 89       | 50      |\n| 90       | 51      |\n| 91       | 51      |\n| 92       | 51      |\n| 93       | 52      |\n| 94       | 52      |\n| 95       | 52      |\n| 96       | 53      |\n| 97       | 53      |\n| 98       | 53      |\n| 99       | 54      |\n| 100      | 54      |\n| 100      | 54      |\n| 110      | 57      |\n| 120      | 60      |\n| 130      | 63      |\n| 140      | 65      |\n| 150      | 68      |\n| 160      | 71      |\n| 170      | 73      |\n| 180      | 75      |\n| 190      | 78      |\n| 200      | 80      |\n| 210      | 82      |\n| 220      | 84      |\n| 230      | 86      |\n| 240      | 88      |\n| 250      | 90      |\n| 260      | 92      |\n| 270      | 94      |\n| 280      | 96      |\n| 290      | 98      |\n| 300      | 100     |\n| 310      | 102     |\n| 320      | 104     |\n| 330      | 105     |\n| 340      | 107     |\n| 350      | 109     |\n| 360      | 110     |\n| 370      | 112     |\n| 380      | 114     |\n| 390      | 115     |\n| 400      | 117     |\n| 410      | 118     |\n| 420      | 120     |\n| 430      | 122     |\n| 440      | 123     |\n| 450      | 125     |\n| 460      | 126     |\n| 470      | 127     |\n| 480      | 129     |\n| 490      | 130     |\n| 500      | 132     |\n| 550      | 139     |\n| 600      | 145     |\n| 650      | 152     |\n| 700      | 158     |\n| 750      | 163     |\n| 800      | 169     |\n| 850      | 175     |\n| 900      | 180     |\n| 950      | 185     |\n| 1000     | 190     |\n| 1050     | 195     |\n| 1100     | 200     |\n| 1150     | 205     |\n| 1200     | 209     |\n| 1250     | 214     |\n| 1300     | 218     |\n| 1350     | 223     |\n| 1400     | 227     |\n| 1450     | 231     |\n| 1500     | 235     |\n| 1550     | 239     |\n| 1600     | 243     |\n| 1650     | 247     |\n| 1700     | 251     |\n| 1750     | 255     |\n| 1800     | 259     |\n| 1850     | 262     |\n| 1900     | 266     |\n| 1950     | 269     |\n| 2000     | 273     |\n| 2050     | 277     |\n| 2100     | 280     |\n| 2150     | 283     |\n| 2200     | 287     |\n| 2250     | 290     |\n| 2300     | 293     |\n| 2350     | 297     |\n| 2400     | 300     |\n| 2450     | 303     |\n| 2500     | 306     |\n| 2550     | 310     |\n| 2600     | 313     |\n| 2650     | 316     |\n| 2700     | 319     |\n| 2750     | 322     |\n| 2800     | 325     |\n| 2850     | 328     |\n| 2900     | 331     |\n| 2950     | 334     |\n| 3000     | 337     |\n| 5000     | 437     |\n| 10000    | 623     |\n| 15000    | 765     |\n| 20000    | 884     |\n+----------+---------+\n[/font][/spoiler]\n\n[spoiler=the maths]\nROUND( ( SQRT( 8.0 * ( COUNT( * ) /20 ) + 1.0 ) - 1.0 ) / 2.0 *20 )  per hour\nwhere COUNT( * ) = the total number of torrents you are seeding.[/spoiler]\n\n\n[#=requests]Requests[/#]\n\nThere is a completely new requests system linked from the top of the page. Instead of making forum posts you use the new system to enter a request and offer a bounty in GB from your upload credit. The bounty is deducted immediately once you make the offer, and others may also offer bounties to sweeten the request. \n\nPlease see the [url=/articles.php?topic=requests]Requests article[/url] in the help section for more info.\n\nnote: You must be a Good Perv with a ratio of at least 1.05 to be able to make a Request.\n\n[spoiler=notes]\nThere is now a link on the top of the page rather than using the forums like before.\nNote the requests Forum will now close.  [color=green]Im thinking i will personally throw a 1GB request on any request from the forums thats not yet filled.  Thoughts on that?[/color][color=#6699FF]Drk: I suggest making a transfer account for stuff like that.[/color] *** decision needed - Dave********\nIf you are a Good Perv or above you will see the following options\n[New request] [My requests] [Requests I\'ve voted on] \n\nAll requests now need a bounty but in MB/GB\'s not credits any more.\n\nlink to article needed too[/spoiler]\n\n\n[#=freeleech]Automatic Freeleech[/#]\n\nFreeleech will be automatically set for all torrents 20GB+. \n\nThere will be no more freeleech requests in the forum.\n\n\n[#=collages]Collages[/#]\n\n\n[size=4][b][color=#FF0000]<<insert content>>[/color][/b][/size]\n\n\n\n[#=tagging]Community tagging[/#]\n\nCommunity tagging is a system where members can add tags to a torrent, and also vote tags up or down (so yes it is possible a tag will disappear if enough members vote it down).\n\n[b]Note:[/b]This feature is [b]ONLY[/b] available to Good Pervs and above so Apprentices cannot use it.\n\nFor full details on how it works see [url=/articles.php?topic=tags]Tagging and tags guide[/url]\nFor a list of common tags see [url=/articles.php?topic=tag_glossary]Tag Glossary[/url]  \n\n\n[#=mfd]Torrent marked for deletion[/#]\n\nIf a Torrent is marked for deletion it will be deleted in 24 hours after it was marked.  The reason for it being marked will be clear on the torrent page.  If any user chooses to download a marked torrent any lost ratio etc. is on that users head.  It is a gamble if the users chooses to take that gamble and it fails so be it . . . do not come whining to staff about ratio issues arising from downloading torrents marked for deletion.\n\nIf you are the uploader and you want to fix the torrent visit the torrent page and edit the torrent when you are done click on the \"If you have fixed this upload make sure you have told the staff: By clicking here\" link (and then the yes you are sure prompt). This will notify staff you have fixed your torrent. Once staff have reviewed your changes we will either re-mark the torrent for deletion (if the changes were not adequate) or we will mark the torrent as ok. \n\nNote: Torrents will not be deleted if they are waiting for a staff member to review your changes (as long as you clicked the button on the page) but you get 24 hours total to fix your torrent [b]including rejects[/b] - IOW if your fix is rejected you get no time extension... for this reason alone you should make sure you fix your torrent asap just in case the fix is rejected and you need to fix it again! (but also it will get more peers if it is fixed more quickly).\n\n \n[#=badges]Badges/medals[/#]\n\nThese show how much a member has contributed to the site. Some are awarded automatically others can be bought using credits and some are awarded at the staffs discretion, anyone begging for a medal or badge will automatically be disqualified from getting it.\n\nFor a full list of available awards see the [url=/bonus.php?action=awards]Awards and Badges[/url] page.\n\n[b]Note:[/b] If you turn off avatars in your profile you will not see users badges/medals (except on their user profile page).\n\n\n[#=classes]User classses[/#]\n  \n[b][color=#92a5c2]Apprentice[/color][/b]\n[*]The default class of new members.  \n[b][color=#4Ec89B]Perv[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 1 week, uploaded 10GB+, ratio 0.7+\n[b][color=#3c3]Good Perv[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 4 weeks, uploaded 25GB+, ratio 1.05+\n[b][color=orange]Sextreme Perv[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 13 weeks, uploaded 1TB+, uploaded 50+ torrents, ratio 1.05+\n[b][color=#00f]Smut Peddler[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 26 weeks, uploaded 10TB+, uploaded 250+ torrents, ratio 1.05+\n\nThere are a few restrictions on community tagging and making requests for apprentice and perv ranks.\nAt Good Perv you get access to all the site functions and pages.\n \n[b]Promotions are now automatic[/b] - Please see the [url=/articles.php?topic=ranks]User Classes[/url] article for more details. \n\n[spoiler=notes]\n[color=green]Staff can override settings to promote if required.  I think[/color]\n[b] Clarication needed[/b] - Staff can manually promote users but its not a route to promotion users should be aiming at - its a footnote in the user article and I dont think it should be mentioned here - mifune.[/spoiler]\n\n\n[#=fls]Front Line Support[/#]\n\n[*]Not a rank as such, any user may be invited to be a FLS - amongst other things they help out with solving users problems and answering user enquiries.\n[*]IMPORTANT NOTE - FLS are users who volunteer to help us run the site well, please treat them with some respect.\n\n[spoiler=notes]\nSenior staff comment needed [color=green] New rank who are volunteers who will do their best to help users.  To be respected as much as Mods... i dont know whats needed.  Thoughts?  Im not sure we have sorted what FLS will do, have power wise yet.  We should![/color][color=#6699FF]Drk: Change this into something like: FLS (or first line support) is a new user rank that is invite only.[/color] For specifics as to what the role partains please look in the roles overview located here (****insert link****).\nON HOLD UNTIL THE FLS ROLE IS FINALISED - Dave[/spoiler]\n\n\n[#=bounty]Credits for reporting Dupes/Banned content[/#] \n\nIf you make an [u]accurate[/u] dupe report (including the link to the torrent that is a dupe of) you will receive a bounty of 400 credits. \n\nAnyone mass spamming the report funtion with inaccurate reports will be warned and repeat offenders banned. Making an honest mistake will not be punished. You are welcome to make as many accurate dupe reports as you like, please make sure you have read and understood the [url=/articles.php?topic=dupes]Dupe Rules[/url] to avoid making bad reports.\n\nThis bounty will also be paid for reporting banned content (on the do not upload list).\n\n\n[#=irc]IRC[/#]\n\nIRC can be accessed by using the link at the top of the page or by an IRC client.\nUse IRC to chat with fellow members, or if you need it there is a Help and Support channel.\nStill waiting on guides - will be added later\n\n\n[#=restrict]Editing Restrictions/Posting Restrictions[/#] \n\nTorrent descriptions may be edited at any time but torrents cannot be deleted once they have a couple of peers. If you want to delete your torrent for some reason report the torrent (using reason \'other\' if there is no better type) and explain why you want to delete it.\n\nPosts and comments may be edited for up to 15 minutes after they have been made. After this if you need a post edited for some reason report the post and explain your reason.\n\nThere is a 10 second flood control on posting in the forums and comments, this is mainly to prevent spam/double click double posts but is hopefully a short enough span that it will not be too much inconvenience.\n\n\n[#=notifications]Notifications[/#]\n\n[size=4][b][color=#FF0000]<<insert content>>[/color][/b][/size]\n\n\n[#=inactive]Inactive Users[/#]\n\n[b]User Reaper[/b] - after 4 months of no activity (no login) your account will be diabled. If you find yourself in this position you can contact us on IRC and (nicely) ask the staff if you can be reinstated. If the only reason you were disabled is inactivity we will be happy to re-enable old accounts.\n\n\n[#=reaper]Torrent Reaper[/#]\n\n[b]Torrent Reaper[/b] - after ....... ..... inactive torrents will be deleted. Once a torrent is deleted it is gone for good, we no longer have the data to reinstate deleted torrents, you are welcome to reupload in this case.\n\n\n[#=profile]Profile page[/#]\n\nClicking on your [b]username[/b] takes you to your user profile which has your info field and statistics. \n\nYou can view your current credits and your credit log here. The boxes on the right contain your personal statistics and links to your history pages etc. What information is shown to other users here depends on your privacy settings.\n\nIf you have your uploaded torrents as visible to other users (list) then they will be listed here at that bottom (if the user viewing has the setting to view other users torrents on that page set).\n\n[#=settings]User settings[/#]\n\nUnder your [b]username[/b] there is a drop down list with links to various sections of the site:\n\n[table=nball]\n[tr][td=25%]Inbox[/td][td]PM inbox.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Staff Inbox [/td][td] [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Message Staff [/td][td] [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Uploads[/td][td] Your uploaded torrents.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Bookmarks [/td][td] Your bookmarked collages/requests/torrents.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Notifications [/td][td] View the results of any notifications you receive, add new notifications.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Subscriptions [/td][td] Threads you are subscribed too.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Post history [/td][td] shows your forum posts.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Comments [/td][td]shows any torrnet comments you made[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Collages[/td][td] Collages are collections of torrents on a theme - see below for information about Collages (a new feature)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Logs [/td][td] site logs. If you want to know what happened to your torrent or who edited your collage look here.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Sandbox[/td][td] a place to experiment or test bbCode. The same bbcode parser is used across the site for presentaions, forum posts,  torrent comments etc.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Conn-Checker [/td][td] An independent method of checking if you are connectable through your torrent client.[/td][/tr]\n [/table]\n\n[size=2]Clicking on [b]Settings[/b] takes you to your user settings page. [/size]\n\n[table=nball]\n[tr][td=25%]Stylesheet [/td][td]Select which stylesheet you want to use[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]External CSS:[/td][td]You can use an external css if you want <<link to thread?>> [i]note:[/i] we do not officially support external stylesheets although you may be able to get help in the forums[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Time Zone [/td][td]Set your timezone[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Time style [/td][td]	Display times as time since (date and time is displayed as tooltip)/ Display times as date and time (time since is displayed as tooltip)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Default Search Type [/td][td] Basic or Advanced - please see the [url=/articles.php?topic=search]How to use search[/url] article[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Torrents per page [/td][td] 25/50/100 [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Posts per page (Forum) 	[/td][td] 25/50/100 [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Collage torrent covers to show per page [/td][td]25/50/100[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Category list in torrent search [/td][td] Whether to show the list of categories in the search center by default [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Tag list in torrent search [/td][td] Whether to show the list of tags in the search center by default [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Tags in lists 	[/td][td]Hide tags in lists[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Add tag behaviour [/td][td]	Automatically vote up my added tags[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Accept PM\'s [/td][td]	All (except blocks) / Friends only / Staff only[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Comments PM [/td][td]	Notify me by PM when I receive a comment on one of my torrents[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Subscription [/td][td]	Subscribe to topics when posting[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Page Titles [/td][td]	Use short page titles (ie. instead of Forums > Forum-name > Thread-title use just Thread-Title)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Forum topics [/td][td]	Disable latest forum topics[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]User Torrents [/td][td]	Show users uploaded torrents on user page (if allowed by that users paranoia settings)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Smileys [/td][td]Disable smileys[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Avatars [/td][td]Disable avatars (disabling avatars also hides user badges)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Signatures [/td][td]Disable Signatures[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Download torrents as text files [/td][td]For users whose ISP block the downloading of torrent files[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Unseeded torrent alerts[/td][td]Whether you want to recieve a PM alert before your unseeded torrents are deleted[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Your Info field[/td][td][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Signature[/td][td][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Paranoia Settings[/td][td] << insert >>[/td][/tr]\n[/table]\n \n\n[spoiler=old]\nClicking on your nickname now only shows what you entered in the Info field and site related stats. The Info field and all other profile changes are now done by clicking on Settings (next to your nickname).\n\nNow under your nickname is a drop-down list and most options are mostly self-explanatory\nPost history - shows your forum posts\nComments - shows any torrnet comments you made\nCollages - see below for information about Collages (a new feature)\nLogs - shows what has happened on the site such as uploads, edits and other information *** are we going to let all members see this ? [b]clarification needed[/b]\nSandbox - a place to test bbCode (before you add it). It can be used for presentaions, forum posts or torrent comments.\nConn-Checker - check to see if you shown as connectable (you can also if you are connectable in any torrent your active on). If not see \n[URL=http://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=1445]An In-Depth Guide to become Connectable[/URL]\n\nSettings is similar to the old way. The only differences are:\n1. Stylesheet - which changes the look (or appearance) of the site. Try both and use the one you like. An external CSS can be used if you want to.\n\n2. Paranoia settings - allow you to control what other members see. They are self-explanatory.\n\n3. Required ratio - Required ratio is now dependent on how much you have downloaded.  As you download more it will raise up until you reach the top ratio of 0.6. **** Maybe link to the ratio article? was suggested but I dont see one - Dave****\n[/spoiler]\n\n\n',84499,'2012-09-07 02:46:06'),(46937,6015,48010,'2012-08-15 15:42:39','I\'m having a lot of shit adding the articles and reported as such - please help to complete this as it is about 90% done already\r\nThanks Dave',NULL,NULL),(46938,6015,47234,'2012-08-15 16:01:42','Ok let me edit some things here as i think i know about then.  All my edits will be green',47234,'2012-08-15 16:09:52'),(46939,6015,48010,'2012-08-15 16:18:56','[quote=Clownius]Ok let me edit some things here as i think i know about then.  All my edits will be green[/quote]thanks Clownius\n\nEDIT seen the green posts - good additions but I\'ll leave them there until tomorrow for other staff to view them - then I\'ll edit the post or you can',48010,'2012-08-15 16:59:46'),(46940,6015,86439,'2012-08-15 17:44:24','On the promotions one, do you want to add that demotion is automatic too? At least for sextreme it is.',NULL,NULL),(46942,6015,51063,'2012-08-15 18:22:17','[color=#FF0000]My edits will be red![/color]\n\n--- Edit ok it was just one thing . . . but hey every little bit helps right?  LOL',51063,'2012-08-15 18:39:45'),(46944,5989,51063,'2012-08-15 18:48:07','I think they are talking about the post history button.  Full Mods and above can quote an old version of the posts and others can not.  At least that is what I think they are saying?\n\nI get a quote button on all of the past edits for what it is worth.\n\n\n\n--- Edit . . . fuck me never mind . . . I did not see the next page of posts . . . just ignore the man behind the curtain!',51063,'2012-08-15 18:49:10'),(46945,6005,51063,'2012-08-15 19:17:46','Has anyone tried the connectibility checker ?  In theory it should say the same thing as the site . . . but it would be interesting to see if it agrees or disagrees!\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?action=connchecker',NULL,NULL),(46946,6005,129045,'2012-08-15 19:40:26','Read my report above.\r\nBoth the utorrent network test and the site conn-check fails (aka they work as intended), but the site still lists me as [color=#009900]connectable[/color] anyway (at the same time, EMP.me will list me as [color=red]not connectable[/color]).',NULL,NULL),(46947,6005,84499,'2012-08-15 20:06:28','[quote=GaryE]Has anyone tried the connectibility checker ?  In theory it should say the same thing as the site . . . but it would be interesting to see if it agrees or disagrees!\r\n\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?action=connchecker[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nNot really - the connchecker attempts to connect to you and reports the results, so its an independent test.\r\n\r\nThe peerlist status comes from the tracker recording the current torrent-peer connections in the database.\r\n\r\nThe problem is all the torrent-peer records always say connectable, regardless of connectability. I suspect its an ocelot thing but I havent investigated it at all beyond trying to diagnose it.',NULL,NULL),(46949,6005,51063,'2012-08-15 20:34:18','Yeah that is where I was going mate.  LOL  But still it would be a way of verifying the connectibility checker is working correctly.  If they are both failing . . . there just might be a common cause.\r\n\r\nIf the site is incorrectly reporting the connectibility status . . . there are a few places to look.  First off at the raw data stream coming in from the tracker . . . is the tracker setting everyone to connectible regardless of what their torrent client is reporting?  Or is the tracker just ignoring the connectibility field or what?  Or is the site ignoring the field from the tracker and reporting the status incorrectly?  And there are probably some other things that I can not think of right now.  LOL',NULL,NULL),(46952,6005,94804,'2012-08-15 21:03:21','sorry,  but I can\'t reproduce the prob Bittorrent says \"connectable\" so says the site.',NULL,NULL),(46953,6005,86439,'2012-08-15 21:05:19','Just as clarity the conn checker is perfectly fine. \n\nFailed when I made myself unconnectable. Red bar.\nShowed me as connectable just now after reinstating router settings. Green bar.\n\n\n[quote=schlager]sorry,  but I can\'t reproduce the prob Bittorrent says \"connectable\" so says the site.[/quote]\nYeah, its when you are genuinely NOT connectable that the site still says you are that is the issue. Peerlists is what are being referred to here.',86439,'2012-08-15 21:07:25'),(46954,5679,85636,'2012-08-15 22:02:07','Can I have some credits I managed to spend 4.9 million somehow.....',NULL,NULL),(46955,5679,86439,'2012-08-15 22:23:15','try to spend that',NULL,NULL),(46956,5679,85636,'2012-08-15 23:16:29','[quote=knickers]try to spend that[/quote]\r\n\r\nas long as mifune doesn\'t keep resetting the medals I should be almost alright',NULL,NULL),(46957,5743,150658,'2012-08-16 00:20:29','[quote=Clownius]May need to look at the last line of that page.  It says your wont receive additional upload credit.  Its kinda redundant :)[/quote]\r\nYes and no.  It looks like you guys put two donation options in place.  If anything, the \"What you will not receive\" part should be in the same table as \"Donation for love\" because it is applicable there.',NULL,NULL),(46958,5743,84499,'2012-08-16 00:22:38','\r\n\r\nupload credit is different to download credit, you will never get upload credit.',NULL,NULL),(46959,5900,184595,'2012-08-16 05:45:38','\r\nI added uploaded torrents on the user profile page (dependent on the users paranoia settings though). If anyone dosent want to see uploads on that page you can turn it off in your own user settings.',NULL,NULL),(46960,5900,84499,'2012-08-16 05:46:25','\r\n[quote=testy]I added uploaded torrents on the user profile page (dependent on the users paranoia settings though). If anyone dosent want to see uploads on that page you can turn it off in your own user settings.[/quote]\r\n\r\nwhoops wrong account... \r\n',NULL,NULL),(46961,5900,86439,'2012-08-16 06:40:26','Yeah sure, Im betting testy did all the work. :lol:',NULL,NULL),(46962,6016,94804,'2012-08-16 07:21:27','I think it\'s a glitch, but when I insert http://www.takkietakkie.com/domo.jpg (my own site) it says that that\'s not on an approved pichost but it shows in my profile anyway. How\'s that possible?',94804,'2012-08-16 07:21:46'),(46963,6016,84499,'2012-08-16 07:32:47','\r\nYou must have had it set from before the error check was put in place. The error check only stops you from changing it to a disallowed host, if the url is already set to a disallowed host it dosent rectify it.\r\n\r\nSorry I changed your avatar while I was testing this theory... and now it cant be changed back to the banned host :lol:',NULL,NULL),(46964,5679,39588,'2012-08-16 07:47:30','Spent a bundle and everything\'s working fine!',NULL,NULL),(46965,6016,94804,'2012-08-16 08:34:11',' :bash: ',NULL,NULL),(46966,6017,171777,'2012-08-16 10:08:41','Just a question (and I do not see this being abused a lot if at all) but is it known that I as a mod can promote others to mod aswell? I tested for higher ranks and those don\'t work (thnk god else drkness_testy would now be a sysop) but normally I would expect that a MOD can not promote to same rank. This only being reserved for admins and sysop.',NULL,NULL),(46969,6015,171777,'2012-08-16 10:19:28','[color=#6699FF]For my edits then.[/color]\n\nI suggest we take a look at all older articles, guides and what not and try to make a bit of a uniform style out of it. I have already done this a little a couple of weeks back but this has to be addressed before the site goes live.',171777,'2012-08-16 10:29:22'),(46970,6017,47234,'2012-08-16 10:37:37','Yeah its a simple tick box in class permissions if you can promote up to your own rank or just one below.  Tested and confirmed it works.\r\n\r\nWill put it back to being able to promote up to your own class again so Mods can Promote test accounts to test with\r\n',NULL,NULL),(46972,6015,48010,'2012-08-16 11:59:47','Thanks for all the additions - I will leave them there for another day then do the edits to update (I\'m not being lazy just waiting for the other staff who haven\'t seen it yet)\r\n\r\nOn that note if you have no additions please just post to say you read it\r\n\r\nAfter that we can review it again\r\n\r\nDave',NULL,NULL),(46973,6015,171777,'2012-08-16 12:09:13','1 other small addition or change: If you mention that a person will see something like XXXXX I think it is best to make a screenshot instead of copy pasting text',NULL,NULL),(46974,6015,48010,'2012-08-16 12:25:03','I thought about this before - for torrent deletion I suggest adding the screenshot\n\nbut unless something is a new feature and absolutely important to make it clear I would say not add a screenshot as I want the guide to load quickly and not become image laden and slow \n\nThis was my intention from the start - it is a summary and quick guide to help members when we move and cut down on help/supoort questions - hence the links for further details. It was never intended to be the site Bible otherwise I would have to add all the Articles and the page would be too big and too long so nobody (even me) would read it :grin:\n\njust my 2 cents',48010,'2012-08-16 12:26:40'),(46975,6018,70679,'2012-08-16 14:16:01','1. When you create a new article the Sub-Category is not saved. You then need to edit it to set it.\r\n\r\n2. When you go from edit to preview the edit button does not work to let you go back to edit.',NULL,NULL),(46983,6018,84499,'2012-08-16 15:53:58','\r\n1) sounds like a bug.\r\n\r\n2) sounds like you are mixing up the buttons. They are labelled a little funny. but the left hand button toggles the preview (the label changes from \'Preview\' to \'Make Changes\') and the right button to save the edit says \'Edit Article\'. The save button should probably be called \'Save Article\' instead.',NULL,NULL),(46986,6013,84499,'2012-08-16 18:50:58','\r\nfixed.',NULL,NULL),(46987,5954,70679,'2012-08-16 19:47:35','bump\r\n\r\nThis will show how many new torrents were uploaded in the last 24 hours. Updated every 24 hours at the same time... say 00:00 GMT.',NULL,NULL),(46988,6020,94804,'2012-08-16 20:00:03','I never paid any attention to requests on the mainsite, but I got curious after seeing the one in here. I must say, what a HUGE improvement compared to the current/mainsite one! Kudos!',NULL,NULL),(46990,6021,94804,'2012-08-16 20:15:45','dunno but when entering a non-approved imagehost for cover-image it does appear in \"preview\" but not when it\'s actualy uploaded (then I get thisdoesn\'t seem right, does it?[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=CD7E_502D5493][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=CD7E_502D5493&jpg[/img][/url])',NULL,NULL),(46992,5954,94804,'2012-08-16 20:23:13','done!',NULL,NULL),(46993,6021,84499,'2012-08-16 21:11:36','\r\n\r\nnot a bad idea - I added validation to the upload preview.',NULL,NULL),(46994,5954,70679,'2012-08-16 21:16:02','huh?',NULL,NULL),(46995,6022,49532,'2012-08-16 21:16:31','rather than disallowing commas for entering tags, replace the commas with spaces.\r\n\r\nthe reason for this is so that people can copy and paste lists of tags without having to edit out the commas',NULL,NULL),(46997,5954,94804,'2012-08-16 21:26:08','added a new torrent',94804,'2012-08-16 21:26:26'),(46999,6021,94804,'2012-08-16 21:33:46','Just out of curiousity, why does one have to use an approved pichost for the cover image? It would be far more easy to copy/paste the image-URL from any site in there(then you only have to right-click and select \"copy URL\", instead of saving it, uploading it to an approved pichost, and thÃ©n copying it\'s URL)',NULL,NULL),(47000,6022,94804,'2012-08-16 21:35:41','yeah, but sometimes spaces need to be points..........',NULL,NULL),(47001,6022,49532,'2012-08-16 21:46:29','[quote=schlager]yeah, but sometimes spaces need to be points..........[/quote]\n\nWhat do you mean?  Spaces are delimiters between tags, points are not. ',49532,'2012-08-16 21:47:08'),(47002,6021,84499,'2012-08-16 21:56:22','\r\n\r\nare you talking about hotlinking from paysites?',NULL,NULL),(47003,6022,84499,'2012-08-16 22:12:00','\r\nyou can actually copy and paste the tags anyway, the commas will just be stripped out (although it wont split multiple tags on commas the taglists have a comma and a space between them so it works out).\r\n\r\naesthetically you may be right anyway though... dunno I might try it and see what others think.',NULL,NULL),(47005,5926,84499,'2012-08-16 23:49:51','test',NULL,NULL),(47006,5926,84499,'2012-08-16 23:50:12','test222',NULL,NULL),(47007,5926,84499,'2012-08-16 23:50:55','\r\nI added a 10 second flood control between posts.',NULL,NULL),(47008,5668,84499,'2012-08-17 00:25:25','\r\n\r\nprobably related to the other peerlist issues (connectable status not correct).',NULL,NULL),(47009,5999,84499,'2012-08-17 01:36:01','\r\nadded a user option (25/50/100)',NULL,NULL),(47010,6022,84499,'2012-08-17 01:39:01','\r\n\r\ndone but I am not exactly 100% sold on it... lets see if I get used to it.',NULL,NULL),(47011,6022,49532,'2012-08-17 01:52:57','Not completely done :\nI tried adding [b]brcc,blonde,324p[/b] to\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35234  but added it as [b]brccblonde324p[/b]\n',49532,'2012-08-17 01:54:06'),(47012,5985,84499,'2012-08-17 02:30:42','\r\n\r\nI stuck a way to join the webchat on the recover password page. It will add \'nologin_\' to the start of their username, although if they use their own client that wont nessecarily be true.. Let me know if anything needs changing with the text or whatever.',NULL,NULL),(47013,6022,84499,'2012-08-17 02:31:44','\r\nI already said it wont split on commas... where are you copying a list with no spaces inbetween the tags from?',NULL,NULL),(47014,6022,84499,'2012-08-17 02:40:30','\r\n\r\noh I guess you originally meant \'replace commas with spaces when the tags are input\'... I understood it as replace the commas in the taglists on the site with spaces (like in the browse list etc).  \r\n \r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47016,6022,49532,'2012-08-17 04:26:30','[quote=mifune]oh I guess you originally meant \'replace commas with spaces when the tags are input\'... I understood it as replace the commas in the taglists on the site with spaces (like in the browse list etc).[/quote] Yes that\'s what I meant, sorry I was unclear',NULL,NULL),(47017,6024,78455,'2012-08-17 05:10:00','From what I can tell, the empty tag bug was fixed by moving the valid-tag check to follow the filtering of special characters, but this still potentially creates problems. Foreign or unconventional titles and names are quietly converted into unsearchable versions of themselves: \"zoÃ«.cerny\" becomes \"zo.cerny\"; \"melissa.faurÃ©\" becomes \"melissa.faur\"; \"die.mÃ¤dchen\" becomes \"die.mdchen\". The current filtering also still allows some nonsense tags like \"---\", but that is probably a non-issue. Tags containing unacceptable characters should be rejected rather than modified, so that the user has the opportunity to correct them.',NULL,NULL),(47018,6025,78455,'2012-08-17 05:44:15','The site allows tags of up to one hundred characters, but for me (Firefox 10) tags longer than 47 characters are wider than the tag box.\n\nExample: http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=10382',78455,'2012-08-17 05:48:47'),(47019,6021,94804,'2012-08-17 07:37:07','no, I tried this: http://bangbrosasses.com/ass1/Haley/01.jpg but it wouldn\'t let me',NULL,NULL),(47020,6026,100132,'2012-08-17 10:56:51','Problem:\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgur.com/A9dEx.png[/img]\r\n\r\nSuggested solution: Make one row out of Torrent Info/Collages , Tags , Cover.\r\nExample: \r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgur.com/XwWzu.png[/img]\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47021,6026,94804,'2012-08-17 11:13:55','I (wholeheartly) agree',NULL,NULL),(47022,6025,86439,'2012-08-17 11:41:57','How many characters does a tag need to be before in reality its better off two or more tags?\n\nlong.curly.red.hair probably should be curly.hair red.hair long.hair, I dont know, Im joining USB, damn tags.\n\nMaybe the issue raised in this thread might offer an answer.\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3026',86439,'2012-08-17 11:43:03'),(47023,6026,86439,'2012-08-17 11:42:12','A solution to this issue, might also be a solution to the issue raised in this thread\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3025',86439,'2012-08-17 11:44:04'),(47025,5926,171777,'2012-08-17 12:40:43','so I am going to get a lot of warning over this one...\n\nwell ok no warnings but thre was only 1 post so I think this is indeed perfectly fixed. Well done mifune',171777,'2012-08-17 12:41:17'),(47026,5926,86439,'2012-08-17 13:05:41','It works perfectly. I was playing with two threads, hit post reply on one, then hit the same on the other one within 4 seconds, and i indeed got a message re: flood control and had to wait 6 more seconds.\r\n\r\n:thumbsup:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47027,6025,94804,'2012-08-17 14:01:18','Knickers, you caught me in a loop, \'cause on the thread mentioned no solution is given only a link to this thread (hence the loop)',NULL,NULL),(47028,6025,84499,'2012-08-17 14:29:20','\r\n\r\n\r\ndont put stupidly long tags in.\r\n\r\n\r\nYou can only idiot proof stuff so much.\r\n\r\n\r\nThis is not a bug.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47029,6026,84499,'2012-08-17 14:38:03','\r\n\r\nThis \"solution\" will break the page - we know this because once upon a time the layout was similar to what you are proposing and with the torrent info box so narrow it gets fucked up with large filelists etc.\r\n\r\n\r\nThere is a lot of stuff that can end up in that torrent info box, reports, filelists, peerlists, etc. and they need the width. \r\n\r\n\r\nWe have redesigned that page several times and I think we are done.\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47030,6021,84499,'2012-08-17 14:45:52','\r\n\r\nWe do not want pervs hotlinking us to commercial pron sites, or anywhere that does not explicity allow it. I am not sure exactly what that site is but I bet its a bad idea for us to hotlink to them... they will see that we are stealing their bandwidth and ta-da! now emp has made an enemy of an other site.',NULL,NULL),(47031,6026,171777,'2012-08-17 14:47:36','You could reshape the tags box to be as wide as the rest but that is about it I think.',NULL,NULL),(47032,6025,86439,'2012-08-17 15:08:06','[quote=schlager]Knickers, you caught me in a loop, \'cause on the thread mentioned no solution is given only a link to this thread (hence the loop)[/quote]\r\nMy post wasnt to offer a solution. Just to point the two thread together without merging them. If one was going to be addressed, then the other might be relevant to the coders.',NULL,NULL),(47033,6027,70679,'2012-08-17 15:18:20','Cannot delete my own thread in Staff testing forum at least on my level.',NULL,NULL),(47034,6027,47234,'2012-08-17 15:31:30','FLS with all the Forum admin rights cant delete threads but Mod plus can.',NULL,NULL),(47035,6028,94804,'2012-08-17 15:50:01','ok, but what about the threads \"On torrents detail page, put tags somewhere else so it doesn\'t push down the description\" and \"DONE: unapproved imagehost for cover\"?',NULL,NULL),(47036,6025,94804,'2012-08-17 15:57:01','[quote=mifune]dont put stupidly long tags in.[/quote] yeah,agreed, but most users will use them anyway, so to avoid the big open (gaping) space, wouldn\'t a\'s suggestion be a solution?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47037,6029,84499,'2012-08-17 15:59:44','\r\n\r\nWe are now in feature lock.\r\n\r\nThis means no new features are likely to be implemented.\r\n\r\nWe wont say dont make any suggestions... but dont be surprised if we ignore/shoot down any new ideas/postpone them till