t never need to be deleted.  Much less staff only threads.  I can never remember wanting to delete a thread anywhere under any circumstances.  I think it is fine as it is.',NULL,NULL),(47057,6024,51063,'2012-08-17 21:41:20','I would have to agree with you on this one . . . but this might not be that easy to implement.',NULL,NULL),(47058,6027,84499,'2012-08-17 21:55:52','\r\n\r\nThere are two permissions for the forums;\r\n\r\n [b]site_moderate_forums[/b] == Can moderate the forums (lock/sticky/rename/move threads). \r\n [b]site_admin_forums[/b] == Can administrate the forums (above + see edit history + delete posts + merge/delete threads). \r\n\r\narguably the edit history thing should be in the mod permissions instead of the admin ones. But the admin permissions should probably be restricted to mods or admins... (sysop only is a bad idea imo)... I leave that decision to the bosses anyway.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47059,6030,1507,'2012-08-17 22:04:06','[quote=GaryE]not a bug because of potato[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: \r\n\r\n\r\n[b]unless it is a potato bug...  :slap:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[img]http://i.imgbox.com/adrv5MDV.jpg[/img]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-08-17 22:06:14'),(47060,6030,94804,'2012-08-17 22:15:08','LOL @ usilly\'s avatar!',NULL,NULL),(47061,5743,94804,'2012-08-17 22:17:37','I\'m in a generous mood, what\'s the cost for upkeep for a week?',NULL,NULL),(47062,5743,85636,'2012-08-17 22:52:17','[quote=schlager]I\'m in a generous mood, what\'s the cost for upkeep for a week?[/quote]\r\n\r\n[img]http://stampingsimulation.com/ximages/blog/100-billion-dollars-276x300(1).jpg[/img]',NULL,NULL),(47063,6033,94952,'2012-08-17 23:51:42','[b]URL:[/b] forums.php?action=unread\n[b]What\'s wrong:[/b] When there are 10 or more unread threads the \"Unread posts get paginated. Pagination reads \"1-25|26-27|Next> Last>>\" \nSee attached screen. \nGoing to the next page yields a blank page.\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=FA83_502EDA3D][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=FA83_502EDA3D[/img][/url]\n[b]Reproduce:[/b] Wait until there are 10+ unread threads and click \"Unread posts\"',94952,'2012-08-17 23:52:29'),(47064,6033,129045,'2012-08-18 00:35:46','Odd, I don\'t get that here... I can\'t replicate it:\r\n\r\nOn my test account, default settings, I\'ll get a list of 20 posts per page, with a total of 111 pages (newly created account, that\'s why the high number)\r\n\r\nOn this account, I\'ll have 19 posts listed, single page.\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\r\nHum, now the test account is borked here too.\r\n\r\n- I went to various sections and used \"[b]Catch Up[/b]\"\r\n- Went back to the [b]Unread Posts[/b] http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=unread to check\r\n\r\nNow the results are inconsistent, it will list 68 pages of results, but only the first 3 pages have any posts (an uneven number: 1, 5 and 2 posts), the rest is empty.\r\n\r\nReally odd :hmmm:\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT2:[/b]\r\nUsed \"[b]Catch up all[/b]\", now it\'s all empty. Will need to wait for new posts to see if the behavior will be the same as yours. But yeah, there\'s something wonky in there.\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT3:[/b]\r\nNo dice. 28 news posts here. They will be listed correctly. :hmmm:\r\nWill try the other way around, see if the problem appears on the test account.',129045,'2012-08-18 14:12:14'),(47065,6027,51063,'2012-08-18 00:41:22','Yeah for all of that I would agree . . . I was just talking about deleting threads . . . and I was not suggesting it . . . just saying that it has to be done so rarely that it could probably be relegated to sysop only.  LOL',NULL,NULL),(47066,6027,70679,'2012-08-18 02:28:02','Well in my case I work on the guides in the staff forum as it is not for everybody\'s eyes until they are ready then move them to help or wherever and at that point I want remove them as it becomes redundant. I could do it in articles but then it would not be so exposed to view and feedback.\r\n\r\nSo please before passing judgment try to understand the reasons behind it. Thanks.\r\n\r\nIn any event I will be happy to delegate the work of removing them.',NULL,NULL),(47068,6027,84499,'2012-08-18 03:20:08','\r\n\r\n\r\nWell there are two seperate issues here...\r\n\r\n[b]1) How should forum permissions work.[/b] At the moment if you have access to a forum through the permitted forums setting and you also have site_admin_forums permission you can view edit history as though you had read permission or delete posts as though you had the class based write permission, but you cannot delete threads - its inconsistent. So I think if you have a forum in your permitted forums field that should act as though you have class permissions for that forum - that is the logical thing - thats the basic purpose of that field and it should behave in an expected way for all actions. \r\n\r\n[b]2) Who should have admin_permissions for the forums.[/b] Probably just admins and maybe mods... but individuals can be given custom permissions as is needed and appropriate - my gut just says it should be a rare thing that we need to delete a thread or post. In this specific case they may not even be needed - once the guides are finished you (barumba) should be able to move them with just mod permissions anyway.\r\n\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(47069,6024,78455,'2012-08-18 03:32:41','At the moment the site returns \"xyz is not a valid tag\" if the tag in question is shorter than three characters after filtering. Cutting the filtering out and just doing a check for any special characters at the same point as the length-check should work, although I\'m not sure if the upper case to lower case conversion is part of the same operation as the filtering, and it would probably be sadistic to remove that. Either way, the change shouldn\'t complicate things much. If a blanket \"is not a valid tag\" is too ambiguous, maybe a little reminder that you\'re restricted to a-z + 0-9 + . could be tucked in somewhere?',NULL,NULL),(47070,6024,84499,'2012-08-18 04:05:46','\r\n\r\nwell I pretty much agree...\r\n\r\nits a more complex thing than you imagine because of all the feedback information but I will take a look at the weekend.',NULL,NULL),(47072,6027,51063,'2012-08-18 05:12:23','Passing judgement?  Really?  Sorry but that was not my intent.  I am sorry if you thought it was.',NULL,NULL),(47073,6025,47234,'2012-08-18 07:38:46','Just cant stop people putting all the tags into one tag can we?\r\n\r\nIm just wondering how many tags like that will actually survive community tagging.  Im thinking none.',NULL,NULL),(47074,6027,47234,'2012-08-18 08:07:23','It is rare to need to delete a thread in the staff forum thats for sure but sadly not so uncommon on the general forums.  Especially in BT and OffTopic.\r\n\r\nIm not so sure it should be too heavily restricted.  Mods should be able to IMO.  Admin or SysOp only means thing may not be dealt with in a timely fashion.',NULL,NULL),(47075,5743,94804,'2012-08-18 08:59:04',' :grin: ',NULL,NULL),(47076,5743,47234,'2012-08-18 09:03:02','Only admin could answer that.  I think his server costs more than this one.  But this wouldnt be a long term hosting solution either (the hosts wouldnt like a tracker i dont think lol).  This one sets me back around 50Euro a month.',NULL,NULL),(47077,6025,86439,'2012-08-18 09:24:11','Im hoping none.\r\n\r\n\r\nIve seen titles typed as tags.',NULL,NULL),(47078,6027,86439,'2012-08-18 09:26:41','Staff only in here yeah!?!\r\n\r\nMore POWAHHHH!',NULL,NULL),(47079,6025,94804,'2012-08-18 10:48:01','I guess comm.tagging will take care of that(@ least I hope)',NULL,NULL),(47093,6027,70679,'2012-08-18 14:00:56','I agree with Mifune. It should be predictable. If I see a delete thread button and click it, it should work. Otherwise I should not see it or it should be disabled. As simple as that. Vulcan logic.  :wink: ',NULL,NULL),(47113,6027,47234,'2012-08-18 14:27:52','Doesnt look like FLS will be moderating the forums when we go live in any case so i would close this bug',NULL,NULL),(47140,6033,129045,'2012-08-18 14:39:56','The test account has an odd result, but for the most part it\'s listing \'normally\'. Default settings (25 posts per page), will accuse 29 unread posts, but only list 28.\r\n\r\n24 posts in the first page and 4 other in the second. :hmmm:\r\n\r\nAnyway, can\'t really replicate your exact problem. Less than 25 unread posts and it will show up normally here in a single page.',129045,'2012-08-18 14:50:05'),(47144,6025,171777,'2012-08-18 15:00:55','this will most likely always need some moderation... but indeed community taggin would often times kill these things rather quickly.',NULL,NULL),(47150,6027,70679,'2012-08-18 15:31:50','well it kinda still needs fixing... if FLS cannot remove threads that option should not be visible... or do I have special permissions? (confused). Generally speaking an option should either work or not be visible...\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47174,6033,94952,'2012-08-18 15:52:45','Now thanks to Knickers I see 25 posts on the first unread-page. But second page is still weird. \n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=3333_502FBB8F][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=3333_502FBB8F[/img][/url]',94952,'2012-08-18 15:53:13'),(47175,6033,86439,'2012-08-18 16:08:35','Oh I get it now, its the 26-45 that bothers you?',NULL,NULL),(47176,6033,129045,'2012-08-18 16:18:14','Test account has inconsistencies, it says 32 unread posts. But it\'s missing 1, the first page lists 24 posts only and the second lists the remaining 7 correctly:\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=D454_502FC138][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=D454_502FC138[/img][/url]\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=929F_502FC138][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=929F_502FC138[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nThis account shows everything correctly, first page has 25 posts listed and the second page lists the remaining 1:\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=72B3_502FC138][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=72B3_502FC138[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(47177,6035,51063,'2012-08-18 17:00:18','Hey mifune and Lanz:\r\n\r\nHave you guys (hell or anyone else) taken note of what happens to a warned user when they have an active warning on the old site and we then migrate over here?\r\n\r\nIs the warning still going to auto time out . . . is it going to get permanently assigned (and never time out) . . . will it get dropped or what?\r\n\r\nI know it is a minor issue.  But it is probably one that needs to be at lest intellectually investigated (like looks at the import code and think about what will happen).  You do not want to have 20 or 30 users (or 200 or whatever) who have unending warnings.\r\n\r\nIf the import code does not handle it properly . . . all that would need to be done is to run a quick report just before we switch over and then have any staffer manually re-add the warnings or manually disable them or whatever.',NULL,NULL),(47182,6035,47234,'2012-08-18 17:59:48','Hmm good question GaryE.  Very good question',NULL,NULL),(47183,6033,84499,'2012-08-18 18:26:55','\r\n\r\nI think the bug is becaues it hides posts in forums you shouldnt see after it collects the unread posts from the database... I\'ll sort it out later.',NULL,NULL),(47184,6035,84499,'2012-08-18 18:55:03','\r\n\r\nright now they are dropped (ie. we dont set any warning data on transfer). So if we dont do anything else we lose current warnings but there will be no problems or errors in the data.\r\n\r\nI cant actually imagine there are that many users on warnings... but then it should also be relatively painless to transfer the data (I am assuming any date conversions can be done in pure sql but its a good bet).',NULL,NULL),(47185,6027,84499,'2012-08-18 19:02:08','\r\n[quote=barumba]well it kinda still needs fixing... if FLS cannot remove threads that option should not be visible... or do I have special permissions? (confused). Generally speaking an option should either work or not be visible...[/quote]\r\n\r\ncorrect, and yeah you currently still have admin_permissions for forums. What permissions Mods/FLS and/or individuals will have when go live is yet to be decided.\r\n\r\nI will fix it so the permitted forums setting does act as a class permission for that forum for all actions.',NULL,NULL),(47186,6027,70679,'2012-08-18 20:01:34','thanks   :yaydance: ',NULL,NULL),(47187,6042,84499,'2012-08-18 20:34:29','\nI dont think anyone has noticed but I have added some better code for dealing with bad tags and the like a while ago.\n\nIf you have unclosed tags you will see them in big red text flashing in the preview - and if you make a post with unclosed tags it will silently close them (immediately so they are empty of content) - this should mean its impossible to screw up the page with badly formed bbcode.\n\nIt [i]could[/i] work so that it errors out if you try and submit a post with unclosed tags... I am very tempted to make it like this...\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]split from thread[/i][br]\'deadline?\'[/size][/align]',84499,'2012-08-18 20:34:43'),(47188,6035,171777,'2012-08-18 21:15:51','oke same line of reasoning but different part. THe old site has some 25k accounts that are disabled (aka the user was banned). What happens to those?',NULL,NULL),(47189,6042,129045,'2012-08-18 21:16:50','That\'s really nice :D\r\n\r\n[quote]It could work so that it errors out if you try and submit a post with unclosed tags... I am very tempted to make it like this...[/quote]\r\nYes please.\r\n\r\nAlso, I don\'t know if this can be a big issue or not, what could be done against mixed tags? EMP.moo will show as this:\r\n\r\n[code][b][i][u]Test2[/u][/i][/b][/code] = OK = [b][i][u]Test2[/u][/i][/b]\r\n\r\n[i]But it must respect this order:[/i]\r\n- tag1 wraps the word\\text block\r\n- tag2 wraps tag 1\r\n- tag3 wraps tag2 ... and so forth and so on\r\n\r\nBut if the order gets messed somehow (tag 1 wraps the word and part of tag2 or tag3), EMP.moo will not accept it:\r\n\r\n[code][b][i][u]Test1[/b][/i][/u][/code] = Not OK = [b][i][u]Test1[/b][/i][/u]\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b]\r\nHeh, the preview shows like this:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=2BD6_5030088B][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=2BD6_5030088B&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nThe actual post shows up differently :hmmm:\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]split from thread[/i][br]\'deadline?\'[/size][/align]',129045,'2012-08-18 21:20:41'),(47190,6042,84499,'2012-08-18 21:51:25','\r\n[quote=yamchan07bb,f2813,27189]\r\nThe actual post shows up differently :hmmm:[/quote]\r\n\r\nWell I already said in the preview it shows you an error message - but on the actual page it silently closes the tags, I dont think we want those error messages showing up in all the errors present in old presentations and posts.\r\n\r\n[quote=yamchan07bb,f2813,27189]That\'s really nice :D\r\n \r\nAlso, I don\'t know if this can be a big issue or not, what could be done against mixed tags? EMP.moo will show as this:\r\n\r\n[code][b][i][u]Test2[/u][/i][/b][/code] = OK = [b][i][u]Test2[/u][/i][/b]\r\n\r\n[i]But it must respect this order:[/i]\r\n- tag1 wraps the word\\text block\r\n- tag2 wraps tag 1\r\n- tag3 wraps tag2 ... and so forth and so on\r\n\r\nBut if the order gets messed somehow (tag 1 wraps the word and part of tag2 or tag3), EMP.moo will not accept it:\r\n\r\n[code][b][i][u]Test1[/b][/i][/u][/code] = Not OK = [b][i][u]Test1[/b][/i][/u]\r\n\r\n[b][i]EDIT:[/i][/b]\r\nHeh, the preview shows like this:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=2BD6_5030088B][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=2BD6_5030088B&jpg[/img][/url]\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nyes if you mix your tags they are in effect unclosed tags. This is deliberate, its the correct way to parse bbcode. Mixing tags only leads to bad things...\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]split from thread[/i][br]\'deadline?\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(47191,6035,84499,'2012-08-18 21:52:59','\r\nthat information is copied over.\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(47192,6042,129045,'2012-08-18 22:00:51','doh. I read it like 3 times and didn\'t actually... read it lol\r\n\r\nSorry man, need some sleep -_-\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]split from thread[/i][br]\'deadline?\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(47193,6033,84499,'2012-08-18 22:27:33','\r\n\r\nfixed.',NULL,NULL),(47195,5993,84499,'2012-08-18 23:02:16','\r\n\r\nis it any better now?',NULL,NULL),(47196,5693,84499,'2012-08-18 23:10:52','\r\n\r\nIf the uploader dosent fill the request why shouldnt someone else be able to do it? otherwise it just goes unfulfilled... uploaders have a one hour grace period to fill it (enforced in the backend).\r\n\r\nre: editing... I dunno. Its not difficult to add (mods can already edit them), but should it be time limited? logged? I havent thought about it at all... :dunno:\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47197,5693,51063,'2012-08-19 00:46:10','Ideally I would say time limited and logged.  However, as far as editing goes . . . why not just say . . . \"if you need to make an edit report the request and document what you want changed.  A staffer will modify the request for you.\".  If this generates too much workload for the staff we can then consider spending coder time to time limit and or log the changes.\n\nWhat I do not want to see happen is what borky was complaining about in the fuck you forum on the active site . . . where he filled a request on another site and by the time he had the torrent up the request had changed.  That is just not cool.  At least if that happened with the system I just proposed the report would still be around and we could check to see if the first request really was filled and then hold the requester to his original request.\n\nThis just seems like the simplest solution to me. :dunno:',51063,'2012-08-19 00:46:44'),(47198,6036,84499,'2012-08-19 02:49:53','\r\n\r\nI have made it so if you try and submit badly formed bbcode you get an error message. Please test if this works in all the numerous places you can enter bbcode.',NULL,NULL),(47199,6025,51063,'2012-08-19 03:19:38','I have visited this thread 6.022 * 10^23 times and it still shows as unread . . . maybe this will solve the issue.',NULL,NULL),(47200,6036,51063,'2012-08-19 03:20:41','works here!',NULL,NULL),(47201,6024,84499,'2012-08-19 03:39:45','\r\n\r\ndone.',NULL,NULL),(47202,6025,84499,'2012-08-19 03:42:24','[quote=GaryE,f3025,27199]I have visited this thread 6.022 * 10^23 times and it still shows as unread . . . maybe this will solve the issue.[/quote]\nhaha, I deleted a post last night I put in the wrong place :P Deleted posts that are also unread posts is a known issue that is hard to fix... but its rare and fairly inconsequential - assuming it is now fixed for you... (if not i will have to do something about it...)\n\n\nI made it so you cannot enter a tag more than 32 chars in length.\n\n',84499,'2012-08-19 03:45:54'),(47203,6025,51063,'2012-08-19 03:47:10','ahh ok that would explain the problem.  And yes posting in the thread solved the problem.  So no there is nothing which needs to be fixed.',51063,'2012-08-19 03:47:41'),(47204,6036,94952,'2012-08-19 04:12:55','I can\'t seem to slip anything past the check :gjob:\n\nChecked forum, torrent comment, pm and sandbox.\n\nSandbox and all previews looks a little funky since there are no Error text. Just the red blinking. No explanation given.\n\nAlso maybe the first time I have seen the blinktag used well. :)',94952,'2012-08-19 04:18:19'),(47205,6025,78455,'2012-08-19 04:21:40','Whoops. Posted without refreshing, post is now irrelevant in light of the fix. :)\n\n',78455,'2012-08-19 04:24:18'),(47206,6036,49532,'2012-08-19 04:34:44','Most of the tests I did were caught, but it allows a tag close[/b] without a [b]tag open[/b]',NULL,NULL),(47207,6025,49532,'2012-08-19 04:38:49','[quote=mifune]Maybe I was a little cranky earlier... dosent look like there are any valid tags longer than 32 characters anyway. Let me think about it a bit...[/quote]\r\n[b]interracial.blowjobs.bukkake.gang[/b] isn\'t a valid tag?  [i]:laugh: [/i]',NULL,NULL),(47208,6036,84499,'2012-08-19 05:12:37','\r\n[quote=Mobbo,f3036,27204]I can\'t seem to slip anything past the check :gjob:\r\n\r\nChecked forum, torrent comment, pm and sandbox.\r\n\r\nSandbox and all previews looks a little funky since there are no Error text. Just the red blinking. No explanation given.\r\n\r\nAlso maybe the first time I have seen the blinktag used well. :)[/quote]\r\n\r\nactually there is an explanation on the tooltip... it could add the tooltip text to the page but I think it is kind of self explanatory anyway. \r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=apparition,f3036,27206]Most of the tests I did were caught, but it allows a tag close[/b] without a [b]tag open[/b][/quote]\r\n\r\nYeah but a closing tag does not cause any kind of error... as the tag is never opened its just a bit of bad text. I am mostly concerned with preventing page errors, the error messages are a help but users are responsible for their own proofreading.',NULL,NULL),(47209,6025,84499,'2012-08-19 05:22:12','[quote=apparition,f3025,27207][quote=mifune]Maybe I was a little cranky earlier... dosent look like there are any valid tags longer than 32 characters anyway. Let me think about it a bit...[/quote]\n[b]interracial.blowjobs.bukkake.gang[/b] isn\'t a valid tag?  [i]:laugh: [/i][/quote]\n\nLaugh it up... its a terrible tag  :slap: \n\nIt\'s only of any use at all if you happen to already know it is being used. You would never intuitively put those tags together in that order, well only by trial and error maybe. Much much more useful would be if those torrents were tagged \"[b]interracial bukkake gangbang[/b]\", then they would show up with the other very specifically tagged 12 out of 30,000 torrents that have similar content. \n\n',84499,'2012-08-19 05:22:52'),(47210,6015,48010,'2012-08-19 08:24:26','Update - most suggestions have been added but still a few holes !!\r\n\r\nPlease check again and comment.\r\n\r\nThanks to all for their input\r\nDave',NULL,NULL),(47211,6015,86439,'2012-08-19 09:18:04','That tagging guide link to the main site thread, Ive already made that into an article here, \'Tags Glossary\'. This I have tweaked some, removed some tags, stated Lolita is banned etc. Ive also tried to group them into categories rather than one long list of tags. Ive added a contents by category too. Hopefully it might make it easier for people to look for a tag suggestion.\r\n\r\nTheres also a more detailed explanation of community tagging and how it works. \'Tagging and Tags guide\' with a link to the glossary, tag rules, offical tags list etc. \r\n\r\nIt still needs work though, both do IMO, at least input on them.',NULL,NULL),(47212,6015,48010,'2012-08-19 09:39:38','[quote=knickers,f3015,27211]That tagging guide link to the main site thread, Ive already made that into an article here, \'Tags Glossary\'. This I have tweaked some, removed some tags, stated Lolita is banned etc. Ive also tried to group them into categories rather than one long list of tags. Ive added a contents by category too. Hopefully it might make it easier for people to look for a tag suggestion.\r\n\r\nTheres also a more detailed explanation of community tagging and how it works. [b]\'Tagging and Tags guide\' with a link to the glossary, tag rules, offical tags list etc. [/b]\r\n\r\nIt still needs work though, both do IMO, at least input on them.[/quote]\r\n\r\nwheres the link to tags glossary? and I\'ll add it as I dont see it - manage articles is still a no go for me the page still wont load quickly or properly',NULL,NULL),(47213,6015,86439,'2012-08-19 09:49:51','OK, I cant seem to see a URL directly to the article itself. But I do have a url on the edit page\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/tools.php?action=editarticle&id=59  -  Tags explained etc\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/tools.php?action=editarticle&id=64  -  Glossary\n\nAnd note, it opens in an edit page, not the entire articles page so probably wont cause you grief. But to see it as presented to users, you will need to view it in articles. I cant find any way to view it as its will display on its own.\n\nIm assuming Im missing something though.',86439,'2012-08-19 09:57:35'),(47214,6015,171777,'2012-08-19 12:42:10','about the site style: There is no official site style but it looks better if all articles have roughly the same look. Right now there are 5 or 6 different looks depending on when the article was made and if it originally came from the forums and what not... This would need some generalisation to make it all look better as a whole.',NULL,NULL),(47215,6015,48010,'2012-08-19 14:09:23','[quote=DrkNess,f3015,27214]about the site style: There is no official site style but it looks better if all articles have roughly the same look. Right now there are 5 or 6 different looks depending on when the article was made and if it originally came from the forums and what not... This would need some generalisation to make it all look better as a whole.[/quote]\n\nNo disrespect but I removed your coment from the guide\n\nSorry I took you out of context - I thought there was a style I missed - np\nI think it is a good idea to have a uniform look on the site so I suggest a new thread for this - if others agree let\'s start a thread and thrash out a standard layout (including colours font sizes ... etc)\nWhen that is done we can all pitch in together to change the articles to the site standard',48010,'2012-08-19 14:14:24'),(47216,6015,84499,'2012-08-19 15:04:30','[quote=knickers,f3015,27213]OK, I cant seem to see a URL directly to the article itself. But I do have a url on the edit page\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/tools.php?action=editarticle&id=59  -  Tags explained etc\n\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/tools.php?action=editarticle&id=64  -  Glossary\n\nAnd note, it opens in an edit page, not the entire articles page so probably wont cause you grief. But to see it as presented to users, you will need to view it in articles. I cant find any way to view it as its will display on its own.\n\nIm assuming Im missing something though.[/quote]\n\n\nJust use the links from the rules and help user sections?\n \n[code][url=/articles.php?topic=tags]Tagging and Tags[/url][/code]\n[url=/articles.php?topic=tags]Tagging and Tags[/url]\n\n[code][url=/articles.php?topic=tag_glossary]Tags -  Glossary[/url][/code]\n[url=/articles.php?topic=tag_glossary]Tags -  Glossary[/url]\n\n\n\n\n\nAlso I noticed while I was editing then a lot of the url links were to http://empornium.moo/whatever.php?id=something .... [size=3]PLEASE use the form [code][url=/whatever.php?id=something]your link[/url][/code] instead.[/size] This will mean the links will continue to work when the url changes to the main site url.',84499,'2012-08-19 17:48:45'),(47217,6015,84499,'2012-08-19 17:35:24','\nThis is the style I have been using for headers already in other articles:\n\n[size=2][code][color=#0261a3][font=Arial Black]A heading[/font][/color][/code]\nlooks like:\n[color=#0261a3][font=Arial Black]A heading[/font][/color][/size]\n\n\nPlease do not color the links using bbcode... they should be properly colored anyway. There is a problem with the light css style where visited links appear as normal text... I dont know why but Lanz specifically set it that way so I have been reluctant to change it... but I dont think I can live with it lol. But links should \"work\" without having to use special bbcode or markup to highlight them. \n\n',84499,'2012-08-19 17:49:20'),(47218,6037,150658,'2012-08-19 19:15:57','I made a poll, and it\'s showing not only the percentage of each answer, but also the percentage of people who chose to not vote, and just see the results.  This could have been done on purpose, but I\'m not sure, and I\'ve never seen it done anywhere else.',NULL,NULL),(47221,6038,42521,'2012-08-19 20:33:07','I dont know if this is a bug but my stats arent matching from the other site maybe a bug or stats were put in wrong could you please check thanks. My current stats are 53.86GB u/l 18.50 d/l ',NULL,NULL),(47222,6038,84499,'2012-08-19 20:44:06','\r\nthe stats here are about a month old or so, and are not synched with the main site.',NULL,NULL),(47224,6036,171777,'2012-08-19 21:06:13','tried several things (focussing on those strange exceptions where you don\'t NEED to close the tags) but can\'t seem to get a bad tag in or keep a good tag out. Looks like it is all working as intended.',NULL,NULL),(47225,6040,70679,'2012-08-19 21:17:08','The move is set to bugs and cannot select staff forum or blank...\n\n[img]http://desmond.imageshack.us/Himg441/scaled.php?server=441&filename=snap82.jpg&res=landing[/img]',70679,'2012-08-19 21:18:49'),(47228,6036,84499,'2012-08-19 21:34:36','\r\n\r\nthanks, I think it is pretty bulletproof but that is a very good thing to test :gjob:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47229,6040,84499,'2012-08-19 21:34:57','\r\nfixed.',NULL,NULL),(47230,6041,154271,'2012-08-19 21:58:53','It seems a lot of people are needing to reset their passwords to log into the test tracker. It might just be because caps aren\'t being transferred with the passwords. If you have any caps in your password, try logging in using all lowercase. This solution worked for me. Hope this helps.  ',NULL,NULL),(47231,6037,51063,'2012-08-19 22:07:35','To the best of my knowledge it was done on purpose.',NULL,NULL),(47232,6041,51063,'2012-08-19 22:12:54','wow that is a good catch . . . thanks!  This is something the coders will have to look at in the transfer script/code.',NULL,NULL),(47233,6041,84499,'2012-08-19 22:28:07','\r\nnah. we dont store passwords, just hashes. And we dont do any case conversion on pw input either. Unless emp.me does something weird like convert to lowercase before using/storing passwords (which seems most unlikely to me) this is unrelated.',NULL,NULL),(47234,6041,51063,'2012-08-20 02:08:23','Same distro/build/os on both sites?',NULL,NULL),(47235,6041,84499,'2012-08-20 02:21:20','\r\nI dont know but I know if you hash your password on the new site it returns the same hash that is in (both) databases.',NULL,NULL),(47236,6030,1507,'2012-08-20 02:51:45','[quote=schlager,f3030,27060]LOL @ usilly\'s avatar![/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n:laugh:\r\n\r\n[b]I got it from b0rky....  :thumbsup:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:laugh:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47237,6042,84499,'2012-07-25 20:08:16','[quote=the system]45 posts moved to this thread from [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2813]\"deadline?\"[/url][/quote]',NULL,NULL),(47238,5813,84499,'2012-08-20 03:01:41','[quote=the system]45 posts moved to thread [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3042]\"FIXED: bad bbcode tags make page go fubar (split from deadline?)\"[/url][/quote]',NULL,NULL),(47243,6042,84499,'2012-08-20 03:04:35','testing testing',84499,'2012-08-20 03:06:50'),(47244,6041,51063,'2012-08-20 03:11:27','Well then it does not matter LOL',NULL,NULL),(47245,6043,84499,'2012-08-20 03:12:11','\r\n\r\nThose with forum_admin permissions can now access a split posts tool. Please test, hopefully its straightforward enough to use, you click on the link in the thread tools panel to open the tool and then select which posts you want to split (a checkbox appears on the header bar for each post).',NULL,NULL),(47246,6043,84499,'2012-08-20 03:13:37','\r\nJust a note: the tool is not available for threads with only one post!',NULL,NULL),(47247,5934,84499,'2012-08-20 03:26:13','\r\n\r\nAnd.... once again the tag code is slightly changed (actually a couple of days ago). It should now reject tags with invalid characters in them instead of just removing the characters. Please test!  :smile1: ',NULL,NULL),(47249,5934,84499,'2012-08-20 03:35:28','test',NULL,NULL),(47250,5934,49532,'2012-08-20 06:18:02','[quote=mifune,f2934,27247]And.... once again the tag code is slightly changed (actually a couple of days ago). It should now reject tags with invalid characters in them instead of just removing the characters. Please test!  :smile1:[/quote] so far, all the tags with invalid characters, have been blocked for me',NULL,NULL),(47251,6043,171777,'2012-08-20 08:06:34','hmmm found another bug... sry for the weird posts in this topic.... ',NULL,NULL),(47255,6045,171777,'2012-08-20 08:15:56','Been playing around with one of the forum mod functions, specifically the reordering one. \r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=65D9_5031F2A6][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=65D9_5031F2A6&jpg[/img][/url]\r\nFor some reason it keeps cloning posts that I am relocating. See test topic:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3044',NULL,NULL),(47267,6043,129045,'2012-08-20 15:15:34','[size=3][b]EDIT3:[/b] [color=red]Don\'t mix the split tool with sticky posts![/color][/size]\n\nI think I broke something... This is totally on me, because I probably shouldn\'t have tried to split the posts with the system messages, sorry -_-\n\nSee http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2922\n\n- From that thread, I split 1 post into 1 new thread.\n- Operation went OK\n- Deleted the newly created thread\n- Tried again, now merging with an existing thread.\n- Operation went OK\n- Edited the thread title (removing  \"[i](merged with posts from ... )[/i]\") and deleted my posts with the system message (\"[i]...post moved to...[/i]\").\n\n- Back to the original thread, I used the split tool to move my post with the system message to another thread (http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3033).\n- Operation apparently went OK.\n- Deleted the posts and system messaged on the target thread.\n- Again back at the original thread, I deleted my post with the system message.\n\nNow that thread is showing 2 \"System Never\" blank posts, delete 1 and both disappears, but a simple refresh will spawn them again.\n\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\nQuoting the empty post, these are the contents:\n[code][quote=,f2922,]\n\n\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n	null\n\n	null\n		null\n	       \n	null\n	null\n	null\n	\n      null\n	null\n\n\nnull\nnull\nnull\nnull\n\n Extra divs, for stylesheet developers to add imagery \nnull\nnull\nnull\nnull\nnull\nnull\n\n\n[/quote][/code]\n\n[b]EDIT2:[/b]\nSorry, forgot the Sitcky feature, stickying the post before splitting seems to be the key to trigger the issue. I guess I messed up because I was also looking into DrkNess thread about the clone posts, sorry -_-',129045,'2012-08-20 17:18:49'),(47280,6015,48010,'2012-08-20 16:20:00','Thanks for the comments, edits and general makeover mifune',NULL,NULL),(47281,6043,84499,'2012-08-20 16:22:38','\nOkay, cool. Well at least we have somehat nailed it now... What is happening is the stickypostID is stored with the thread, when it splits a thread it dosent check if the post being moved is the stickypostID, if it is then you now have a id number in that value that it is not in that thread... that causes the error. Good catch :gjob:\n\n:bugchases:\n\nwill fix later.',84499,'2012-08-20 17:58:03'),(47295,6045,84499,'2012-08-20 19:05:47','\r\nfixed (I hope).',NULL,NULL),(47309,6038,47234,'2012-08-21 06:09:29','I could swear this was point 4 of the last batch of Invites i sent out :sigh:',NULL,NULL),(47310,6038,171777,'2012-08-21 06:53:59','still makes you wonder why one would be afraid of losing less then 30 GB of upload credit.... soo many torrents are bigger then that.',NULL,NULL),(47315,6052,84499,'2012-08-21 12:40:59','\nI have added a status indicator for staff to show who is currently checking torrents at the top of the browse page.\n\nYou can click on it to manually set it on or off, and it will also be set on if you use the torrent review tools (okay/fixed/rejected/warned etc.) It times out after [s]10[/s] 8 - 12 minutes if you do not turn it off manually. Only staff (actually: anyone with the torrents_review permission) can see and use it.\n\nI\'m hoping its an end to the presentation check thread for avoiding collisions :D\n \n\n',84499,'2012-08-21 18:29:29'),(47316,6053,84499,'2012-08-21 12:46:29','\r\n\r\nWe have added a third stylesheet.\r\n\r\nIt was touch and go whether it would be included but I gave it a bit of a touch up and I think its not too buggy anyway. Let me know if there is any \'invisible\' text anywhere etc.',NULL,NULL),(47317,6053,85111,'2012-08-21 13:01:19','looks alright, more stylesheets the better imo.. something for everyone. The \"last activity\" section in the footer could use a font colour change since its a similar colour to the background and hardly readable. Also is that EMP logo final cos it looks pretty rough... just sayin\'  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(47318,6052,1507,'2012-08-21 15:01:54',':thumbsup:\r\n\r\n[b]that sounds cool mifune...  thanks...  :smile1:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:  I\'ve just tried it and so far it is working...  I\'ll leave it \"on\" to see if it does shut off after the timed allotment passes....  :smile1: [/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-08-21 15:04:22'),(47319,6053,129045,'2012-08-21 15:06:31','Just can\'t get used to the header, it has a hazy look that is really throwing me off.\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\r\nOn http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php , the [b]File[/b] and [b]Size[/b] (used to sort torrents) will be hardly readable, as it\'s light grey text over a light blue background.',129045,'2012-08-21 16:43:17'),(47320,6052,129045,'2012-08-21 15:07:00','I can see you usb! :D',NULL,NULL),(47321,6052,51063,'2012-08-21 15:09:43','I can see usb as well . . . how long has it been?\n\n\n--- Edit only 8 minutes ok!',51063,'2012-08-21 15:10:04'),(47322,6052,129045,'2012-08-21 15:11:59','Now I see knickers too and usb is blinking\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\r\nNow everybody is gone D:\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT2:[/b]\r\nNow knickers is there too, 9min20s for me to timeout',129045,'2012-08-21 15:14:23'),(47323,6052,86439,'2012-08-21 15:12:42','Now we are both there, and USB is flashing.\n\nMaybe this is just coincidence and USB timed out at the same time, but when I clicked my name again to cancel my checking, USB cancelled too.\n\nEdit: Must be coincidence, I did it again with Yamchan there, cancelled mine and Yamchan stayed. Although, Yamchan never blinked/flashed. OK, so I take it the flashing is an indication that Mod is about to time out?\n\nEdit: And the time left, is in the same format as post times. ie: Some see time left, I see time since starting? Or is yamchan just doing the maths and posting that instead? Hmm, he wouldnt see seconds if it was maths as Im not, so I assume he is seeing a time left instead.\n\n\nVery cool.\n',86439,'2012-08-21 15:20:35'),(47326,6052,129045,'2012-08-21 15:18:33','So, what\'s the blinking\\flashing about? Soon to timeout?',NULL,NULL),(47327,6052,51063,'2012-08-21 15:19:56','Sounds that way to me yamchan . . . this is a brilliant feature mifune!',NULL,NULL),(47328,6052,129045,'2012-08-21 15:23:36','@GaryE, indeed! It\'s very nice :D\r\n\r\n@knickers, just calculating the difference here :). The tooltip shows the same here: [i]checking torrents (xx min ago)[/i]\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\r\nDidn\'t see it blinking this time :\\ It went up to \"(11 min ago)\" and then turned off.',129045,'2012-08-21 15:28:02'),(47329,6052,86439,'2012-08-21 15:28:43','Yeah, that was weird. I never saw it blink/flash either like it did with USB. So what happened there. Yamchan you stayed for at least 12 minutes. While I timed out at 10? But cancelled or set time for both?\n\nI was thinking it wssnt timing out because it wasnt idle? Did you click any torrents?\n',86439,'2012-08-21 15:30:45'),(47330,6052,129045,'2012-08-21 15:31:38','I didn\'t click on anything, just refreshed the page a few times :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(47331,6052,86439,'2012-08-21 15:33:25','Same as me. I wonder why it allowed you 12 minutes according to my last tooltip, while i was maybe 9 minutes or so. I refreshed the page, and both were gone, well you were gone I was back to the left and pink.\n\nI notice youre in there alone now so well leave it and see what happens. Then maybe one of us goes in, and the other 5 minutes later to see if the newest mod resets the timer for all or some such thing?',86439,'2012-08-21 15:34:43'),(47332,6052,129045,'2012-08-21 15:35:49','I only saw it go to 11min, then I refreshed again the page.\r\n\r\nAbout your name in the left, that\'s normal, just means it\'s not active :hmmm:\r\n\r\nTesting again, 3 minute to go (unless it lets me go over the 10min again)\r\n\r\n[b]EDIT:[/b]\r\n10 min and bam, it disabled itself :)',129045,'2012-08-21 15:38:53'),(47333,6052,84499,'2012-08-21 15:37:12','\r\n\r\nhi sorry I got a bit caught up with a clients (annoying) phonecall.\r\n\r\nI left a bug in so it dosent update the time properly unless someone changes their status (click your name or carry out a review action on a torrent).\r\n\r\nJust gonna make a few changes... will update soon.\n\n\r\n\r\nBTW - in theory it gives you 8 minutes of inactivity, right now the tooltip shows you total time since you first logged on (for the current \'session\') but its probably more useful if it gives you time since last review activity.',84499,'2012-08-21 15:38:50'),(47335,6052,84499,'2012-08-21 15:39:33','\r\n\r\n--- ps -\r\n\r\nyour name in red on the left is so you can manually \'activate\' yourself before you start checking.',NULL,NULL),(47336,6052,86439,'2012-08-21 15:39:42','Nope, last tooltip I saw was 9 minutes a few second before you vanished. No refresh it updated live. And no flashing.\n\n\nDidnt see mifunes posts, this post is related to yamchans last.',86439,'2012-08-21 15:41:18'),(47337,6052,84499,'2012-08-21 15:40:33','oh and you shouldnt have to refresh the page... it updates itself every 15 seconds. (and it is way more efficient on the server to allow it to update itself)\n\n\nthe lack of a blink is because of the aforementioned bug.\n\n\nI will now stop posting and go fix it :P',84499,'2012-08-21 15:41:58'),(47339,6052,47234,'2012-08-21 15:45:21','Thanks Mifune this sounds great',NULL,NULL),(47340,6052,86439,'2012-08-21 16:25:17','When I just clicked on one of my own torrents via my profile, it shows me as checking without me selecting to check. So it will show me as checking if I click any torrent even to download as a member.\r\n\r\ni just clicked off checking. Then clicked a torrent just to browse it, again, it listed me as checking.',NULL,NULL),(47341,6052,48010,'2012-08-21 16:33:27','I just browsed torrents to see this new feature\r\n\r\nshowed me as browsing so I clicked my name and went red (not checking) in and out pf browse page and not checking sticks\r\n\r\nthis feature seems great - nice one mifune',NULL,NULL),(47342,6052,86439,'2012-08-21 16:40:46','Did you try to view a torrent Dave? When i just view a torrent it shows me as checking. Ive tried new tabs, and just clicking them within the same tab, same. Each time I click a torrent it automatically adds me as checking. I click me off, try again, Im back as checking each time I enter a torrent.',86439,'2012-08-21 16:41:37'),(47343,6052,48010,'2012-08-21 16:42:08','no -let me check now\n\nEDIT -I was green in a torrent but still red on browse page - had to click my name again and went red\n\nNow to logout and see if i come back red or green - will report soon\n\nEDIT2 after logout when i came back i was green again - so reset it to red',48010,'2012-08-21 16:46:12'),(47344,6053,85111,'2012-08-21 16:48:23','yeh i remember bringing this up and starting a thread about the logo >> http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2756 .. My offer to help you guys with graphics still stands if you need it.  :gjob: ',NULL,NULL),(47345,6052,84499,'2012-08-21 17:08:35','\r\nI fixed something, hopefully now it only turns you \'on\' (to green status) if you set it yourself or carry out a review action.  You get 8 minutes before it times out, although you might get more because it only checks every 4 mins to delete timed out records.',NULL,NULL),(47346,6052,48010,'2012-08-21 17:13:23','no i logged out and came back as green on browse and in a torrent',48010,'2012-08-21 17:13:43'),(47347,6052,84499,'2012-08-21 17:14:18','\r\ntry again :D',NULL,NULL),(47348,6052,84499,'2012-08-21 17:16:01','\r\nlogging out the site wont in itself set you to off, but if you just set your status to off, reload/visit a torrent page and it should not set you to on unless you manually set it or carry out a review action.',NULL,NULL),(47349,6052,48010,'2012-08-21 17:30:06','[quote=mifune,f3052,27348]logging out the site wont in itself set you to off, but if you just set your status to off, reload/visit a torrent page and it should not set you to on unless you manually set it or carry out a review action.[/quote]\r\n\r\nthat works - tested 5 torrents i never looked at before - red on all of them\r\n\r\ngood work mifune - i like this new tool',NULL,NULL),(47350,6052,86439,'2012-08-21 17:44:01','Nice, thats got it.',NULL,NULL),(47351,6052,103720,'2012-08-21 22:03:18','awesome.......\r\n :grin:  :gjob: ',NULL,NULL),(47353,6054,85636,'2012-08-22 00:40:29','Noticed that the modern theme\'s bonus page displays unavailable options the same as if they were available\r\n\r\ne.g.\r\n[img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/3012235/static/glitch.PNG[/img]',NULL,NULL),(47354,6054,84499,'2012-08-22 00:47:05','its not actually anything to do with the stylesheet, I originally thought you were asking me about why it was a certain color... this bug is independent of css. (I know what the problem is... lets just call it bad logic).\n\nwill take a look tomorrow.',84499,'2012-08-22 00:47:27'),(47356,6053,47234,'2012-08-22 02:29:41','Just tried to change my stylesheet and instead it threw an error due the the fact of i have a speedtest.net image in my profile lol.  Seems Speedtest is not an approved Image host.',NULL,NULL),(47357,6053,1507,'2012-08-22 06:09:04',':dunno:\r\n\r