till shows seeds and or leechers on most torrents.  Something is seriously borked.\n\nAt least we now know that it is not just one person.  With the data we had I really thought it was just me or the one torrent.  In hindsight I guess I should have tried other torrents . . . but I thought that if everyone was getting errors that they would certainly report it.  So now I guess we need Lanz (or mifune) to sort it out.  It really looks to me (now anyhow) like the tracker is down.  That is one issue.\n\nThe other issue is why are most torrents reporting active seeders and or leechers if indeed the tracker is down?  That seems like a bug to me.',51063,'2012-08-25 18:48:34'),(47417,6058,94804,'2012-08-25 19:46:59','after reading Gary\'s post, I maximized bittorrent and noticed NONE of the torrents work, neither the ones from the \"old\" site, nor from this one. \n\n\"old\" site and xxx.freeimage.us appear to be down, too\n\nnow those are working again but empornium.mooo\'s tracker isn\'t',94804,'2012-08-25 20:46:58'),(47418,6062,94952,'2012-08-25 22:52:07','I found 2 bugs at torrents.php related to modern.css\r\nBanner ad is not centred and download icon is missing, The link is there just not the disk-icon.\r\nSee attached screen for further info.\r\nTested with IE9, FF14.0.1 and Chrome, same error in all. \r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=0269_5039562D][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=0269_5039562D[/img][/url]\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]split from thread[/i][br]\'modern css stylesheet\'[/size][/align]',NULL,NULL),(47420,6058,86439,'2012-08-26 00:46:27','Mifune is well aware that .moo has spat the dummy.\n\n[quote=schlager,f3058,27417]after reading Gary\'s post, I maximized bittorrent and noticed NONE of the torrents work, neither the ones from the \"old\" site, nor from this one. \n\n\"old\" site and xxx.freeimage.us appear to be down, too\n\nnow those are working again but empornium.mooo\'s tracker isn\'t[/quote]\n\n.me and freeimage are on one server.\n\n.moo is on another.\n\nSo it seems highly likely that both servers being down at the same time is a coincidence nothing more.',86439,'2012-08-26 00:48:38'),(47421,6053,84499,'2012-08-26 02:10:22','\r\n\r\nthanks mobbo, well spotted :gjob:',NULL,NULL),(47423,6053,1507,'2012-08-26 03:48:37','[quote=mifune,f3053,27403]:gunshot:[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: ',NULL,NULL),(47425,6058,94804,'2012-08-26 11:43:22','[quote=knickers,f3058,27420]Mifune is well aware that .moo has spat the dummy.\r\n[/quote]\r\nhaha didn\'t know that saying, nice one though!',NULL,NULL),(47426,6061,84499,'2012-08-26 17:28:11','Stuff for [s]Lanz[/s] Mobbo and I to do:\n\nbefore we go live...\n[*][s]Tracker Bug(s) - not updating peerlist/connectable status[/s]\n[*][s]Add a couple of functions to groups section for adding credits/something else[/s]\n[*][s]articles manager needs an overhaul[/s]\n[*][s]investigate if we can record seeding hours easily [*credit query in scheduler] - done[/s]\n[*][s]alex noted downloaded amount was missing in peerlist - added download/ratio/timespent[/s]\n[*][s]number of comments in browse torrents list[/s]\n[*][s]remove cat check from requests[/s]\n[*][s]update database import sql (friends/blocks list / warned status)[/s]\n[*][s]make a multiline entry form for the clientlist so we can enter 100\'s of clients at once[/s]\n[*][s]fix the forward PM insanity[/s]\n\nwhen we actually go live...\n[*]remember to reenable sending warning emails to users in schedule etc\n\n\nStuff other staff/fls can help with:\n\nthere are a few articles left to write:\n[*]search article is incomplete\n[*]stylesheets article (with shiney pics)\n[*]finish transferring threads like \"uploading guide\" to articles\n[*]check the faq article to see if anything can go in its own help article instead -- see this thread: http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3080\n[*]finish all content related stuff\n\n[*][s]Work out what we are doing with the client Whitelist situation[/s]\n\n[*]plus others we havent thought of yet',84499,'2012-10-23 15:26:42'),(47427,6058,47234,'2012-08-26 17:47:30','We think the tracker is working properly again if its not yell :)',NULL,NULL),(47428,6015,84499,'2012-08-26 17:53:13','\r\n\r\nI did some more, there are still a couple of bits that need finishing.',NULL,NULL),(47429,6058,129045,'2012-08-26 17:59:36','Working fine here :D',NULL,NULL),(47430,6058,86439,'2012-08-26 18:04:28','[quote=yamchan07bb,f3058,27429]Working fine here :D[/quote]',NULL,NULL),(47431,6061,70679,'2012-08-26 20:19:46','not to forget the connectable/not connectable tracker bug\r\n\r\nI did a new uploading guide with uTorrent and is already in Help.',NULL,NULL),(47432,6058,49532,'2012-08-26 21:16:27','working fine here too  :gjob: \r\nwe\'re runing out of bugs to hunt down   :guns: ',NULL,NULL),(47434,6058,51063,'2012-08-26 21:38:51','Yeah!!!!  Someone put the dummy back in the trackers mouth!  ',NULL,NULL),(47435,6053,51063,'2012-08-26 21:40:54','someone deleted a post . . . I am posting so this thread appears as read\n\n\n--- Edit fuck me it was the second page.  Well now if I delete this the problem really will be there . . . so I fix a non-existent problem . . . then created one . . . and can not fix it.  LMFAO\n\n\n\n---- Edit maybe that is a bug.  After I read the first page . . . and I refreshed the unread list and clicked on the arrow it should have brought me to the second page . . . it did not . . . it brought me to the end of the first page again.  Yeah I think this is a bug.',51063,'2012-08-26 21:44:40'),(47437,5934,84499,'2012-08-26 22:19:15','testing1',NULL,NULL),(47438,6053,84499,'2012-08-26 22:28:35','The problem is when you read a page it stores the last read post which is the post at the bottom of the page, thats the best it can do at that point because that may very well be the last post in that thread.  When you load the unread posts page it checks if your last read post in that thread is not the last post in that thread, and if so it presents it as an unread post with a link to the last read post. Getting the next post after the last read post in that thread for the link is not so straightforward... and I dont think can be done without doing another query for every entry on the page - and none of these queries can be usefully cached... I am not sure the solution is worth it.',84499,'2012-08-26 22:32:55'),(47439,6053,51063,'2012-08-27 02:22:57','I would say that neither solution is worth it.  Thanks for the explanation.',NULL,NULL),(47440,6062,84499,'2012-08-25 22:51:57','[quote=the system]1 posts moved to this thread from [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3053]\"modern css stylesheet\"[/url][/quote]',NULL,NULL),(47441,6053,84499,'2012-08-27 02:36:37','[quote=the system]1 posts moved to thread [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3062]\"BUG: modern css stylesheet (adbanner + disk icons) (split from modern css stylesheet)\"[/url][/quote]',NULL,NULL),(47442,6063,86439,'2012-08-27 02:38:14','Are we aware that no credits are being awarded for being available to seed? I have never received any anyway according to the logs.\r\n\r\nor did I miss something?',NULL,NULL),(47443,6063,51063,'2012-08-27 03:15:18','I am glad you asked this . . . I meant to ask the same question . . . but I forgot.  LOL',NULL,NULL),(47444,6062,47234,'2012-08-27 08:50:09','Bug confirmed FF 14 Kubuntu 12.04',NULL,NULL),(47445,6061,171777,'2012-08-27 09:30:44','reenable that setting that send mails to users that are inactive for a few months?',NULL,NULL),(47447,6063,49532,'2012-08-27 11:59:09','My credits have increased since a few days ago. but I hve not seen what\'s happened in the past 24 hours',49532,'2012-08-27 11:59:23'),(47448,6063,86439,'2012-08-27 12:16:19','Credits themselves may or may not be being awarded, that is one issue, however the logs show no record of what you get. Well not that Ive seen anyway.',NULL,NULL),(47450,6064,6203,'2012-08-27 15:56:10','hello all,\r\n\r\non every torrent page you can do these actions:\r\n\r\n[Edit Torrent] [Bookmark] [View log] [Report] [Remove]\r\n\r\nwhy not replacing the text with images?\r\n\r\nhere are some examples:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=EA32_503B984A][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=EA32_503B984A[/img][/url][url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=25CE_503B9812][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=25CE_503B9812[/img][/url][url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=5012_503B9812][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=5012_503B9812[/img][/url][url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=2D77_503B9812][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=2D77_503B9812[/img][/url][url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=48C3_503B9812][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=48C3_503B9812[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(47451,6058,113902,'2012-08-27 18:20:38','working! but without seeders for my downloads torrents!',NULL,NULL),(47452,6064,94804,'2012-08-27 19:36:39','Yeah, good idea, but uhm, with icons you always have the risk of misinterpretation, but not so with text links.',NULL,NULL),(47453,6064,6203,'2012-08-27 19:40:17','for that we have a tool tip',NULL,NULL),(47454,6064,94804,'2012-08-27 19:59:44','yea, I know but my guess is that most users have the patience of a kid with ADD on speed (hence they won\'t take the time to hover over icons)',NULL,NULL),(47455,6063,84499,'2012-08-27 20:38:43','\r\n\r\nYou get your credits every 15 minutes. There is no good way to log that imo. (without adding a tracking counter of what you have been credited every 15 minutes and logging it daily/weekly... which kind of defeats the purpose of having a nice simple elegant self contained query doling out the credits).',NULL,NULL),(47456,6061,171777,'2012-08-27 21:08:32','Ok made a start on the articles. So far already encountered 2 articles that need edits that have to be decided upon by senior staff... This would be the Avatar guidelines and the Clients articles. Please take a look and fill in the blanks.',NULL,NULL),(47457,6063,129045,'2012-08-27 22:23:07','Kept a closer eye on the credits here and it\'s updating normally.\r\n\r\n[b]Mifune[/b], got a related question... On the old system, it calculated the total seed time in a week period, but how do we check seed time now? Or it\'s not important anymore? Or maybe it\'s listed somewhere and I missed it...\r\n\r\nLooking at the current Seeding torrents http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?type=seeding&userid=129045 , I can see their start time (1 hour ago), but that\'s per session. [i](Stopped then restarted, now they should be listing \'just now\' or some minutes ago)[/i]',NULL,NULL),(47458,6063,51063,'2012-08-27 22:44:37','[quote=mifune,f3063,27455]You get your credits every 15 minutes. There is no good way to log that imo. (without adding a tracking counter of what you have been credited every 15 minutes and logging it daily/weekly... which kind of defeats the purpose of having a nice simple elegant self contained query doling out the credits).[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nAhh Ok I get it that makes perfect sense!  In fact it is probably a better system in most ways.  The only downside I see (and it is very very minor) is that we can not quickly tell how long a user has been seeding this day/this week and their seeding history.\r\n\r\nI am sure a scheme could be devised to do so . . . but I am really not sure if it is worth it.  The only thing I use that information for is helping lusers with bad ratios to sort out why they have such bad ratios and for determining if a user asking for a bail out deserves one.\r\n\r\nI mean that is useful . . . but is it worth the extra effort on mifunes part (or Lanz\'s) to implement such a scheme?  I would say no.  And even if it was worth mifune\'s time . . is it then worth the extra load that such a scheme would put on the tracker.  From what mifune is saying I would again say no.  What say the other staffers?  Let us face it my experience with using that data is very limited.  LOL\r\n\r\n\r\n--- Of course as I am re-reading this I just read Yamchan\'s comment and I see I am not the only one to have thought of this LOL',NULL,NULL),(47459,6064,51063,'2012-08-27 22:47:30','Honestly I prefer text . . . but I am very old fashioned and I realize that I am almost certainly in the minority.  But really the time to bring this up was before we went into feature lock.',NULL,NULL),(47461,6065,85636,'2012-08-27 23:44:39','[color=#33FF33][b]ONLINE[/b][/color]\nAs requested, logs from the staff irc channel are now available online.\n\n[url=http://logs.emprn.tk]http://logs.emprn.tk/[/url]\nUsername: staffofempornium\npassword: yoursinormine\n\n[color=#FF0000]Password changed 15 Oct 2012 for GaryE leaving[/color]\n\nlogs are updated every 5 mins.',85636,'2012-10-15 18:55:00'),(47462,6066,49532,'2012-08-28 00:22:37','Ive made a new stylesheet, based on the modern style sheet. Please test it and give me feedback on bugs and anything that you think could be improved:\r\n\r\n[url=http://lorem.us/new.css]http://lorem.us/new.css[/url]',NULL,NULL),(47463,6063,84499,'2012-08-28 01:12:20','\r\n\r\nthe workload isnt the issue as such, its a few lines of code. Its all about the scheduler, seeding is counted every x minutes so its a regular operation and the user and peer tables have a few hundred thousand records in them so its a non trivial query just to select the records. Lanz came up with a nice elegant compound query to add credits that executes fairly quick, but it dosent immediately lend itself to recording who is seeding without adding another subquery to it.\r\n\r\nlet me mull it over a few days... there is probably a clever way to do this but I have a couple of other things I want to get done first then I\'ll see if I can come up with some inspiration. If I can find a way of doing it that does not add load I think it would be useful to have the seeder hours that week available for staff.',NULL,NULL),(47464,6066,94952,'2012-08-28 01:47:34','1. Font is defaulting to Times New Roman.\r\n2. Icons are missing. DL-icon, read/unread posts, go to first unread post and so on.\r\n\r\nI didn\'t check very much but those two stood out.',NULL,NULL),(47466,6064,6203,'2012-08-28 03:17:20','yes i saw that after i wrote the original post, so forget the idea. ;)',NULL,NULL),(47467,6061,84499,'2012-08-28 03:29:36','[quote=DrkNess,f3061,27445]reenable that setting that send mails to users that are inactive for a few months?[/quote]\r\n\r\nyep those are the warning pm\'s in the scheduler. well remembered though :D',NULL,NULL),(47468,6064,84499,'2012-08-28 03:41:25','\r\n\r\nI am not adverse to using icons... the principle problem is not coding it - its finding complete sets of nice icons and deciding what stays as a text link and what becomes an icon. I am also not sure about just the torrents page having them, there are a lot of pages all over the site that have a row of text links at the top of the page and I like things to have a unified look (different stylesheets could have different sets of icons though). So at this stage whats stopping it is just the amount of time needed to properly think about what becomes iconised and then finding all the appropriate matching icons. If someone comes up with an already totally thought through set of icons for the whole site and a plan on where they should be used I will give it serious attention.  ',NULL,NULL),(47469,6066,84499,'2012-08-28 03:44:36','\r\nwell the missing disk icons is because I hadnt fixed that in the base stylesheet (modern) yet.\r\n\r\nThis is the missing css:\r\n\r\n[code]\r\n.icon_disk_none {\r\n    background: url(\'images/disk.png\') no-repeat center center;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.icon_disk_leech {\r\n    background: url(\'images/diskdown.png\') no-repeat center center;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.icon_disk_seed {\r\n    background: url(\'images/diskup.png\') no-repeat center center;\r\n}\r\n[/code]',NULL,NULL),(47470,6062,84499,'2012-08-28 03:54:55','\r\nfixed.',NULL,NULL),(47471,6054,84499,'2012-08-28 03:59:59',' :badboy: :whip:\r\n\r\nsorry forgot about this...',NULL,NULL),(47472,6061,171777,'2012-08-28 06:09:45','[quote=mifune,f3061,27467][quote=DrkNess,f3061,27445]reenable that setting that send mails to users that are inactive for a few months?[/quote]\r\n\r\nyep those are the warning pm\'s in the scheduler. well remembered though :D[/quote]\r\n\r\nAh ok. My bad. PM/Email. No worries then :P',NULL,NULL),(47473,6058,47234,'2012-08-28 07:11:08','Yeah being a test site with less than 500users thats likely to be an issue.  You should have plenty of credits to buy down any ratio issues though',NULL,NULL),(47474,6061,84499,'2012-08-28 11:14:47','[quote=DrkNess,f3061,27472][quote=mifune,f3061,27467][quote=DrkNess,f3061,27445]reenable that setting that send mails to users that are inactive for a few months?[/quote]\r\n\r\nyep those are the warning pm\'s in the scheduler. well remembered though :D[/quote]\r\n\r\nAh ok. My bad. PM/Email. No worries then :P[/quote]\r\n\r\nlol oh yeah. well I knew what I meant  :lol: ',NULL,NULL),(47475,6018,84499,'2012-08-28 11:15:39','\r\n\r\nfixed',NULL,NULL),(47478,6018,70679,'2012-08-28 13:02:45','thx',NULL,NULL),(47479,6064,6203,'2012-08-28 15:30:59','I think the best is to use icons the majority is familiar with. That means the integrated symbols of windows operating systems. okay, the style is a matter of taste, nonetheless this collection is the most popular/used in the world (the old windows curse). So, if the rest is comfortable, i can gather a set of images.',NULL,NULL),(47480,6066,49532,'2012-08-28 16:16:23','[quote=Mobbo,f3066,27464]1. Font is defaulting to Times New Roman.\r\n2. Icons are missing. DL-icon, read/unread posts, go to first unread post and so on.\r\n\r\nI didn\'t check very much but those two stood out.[/quote]\r\n\r\nWhat browser are you using, and which part is defaulting to Times New Roman? \r\nI made a fix in the monospaced font, but didn\'t see a problrm with the main font.\r\n\r\nI added the code for the missing icons.',NULL,NULL),(47481,6064,94804,'2012-08-28 18:03:19','can\'t icons replace text by means of a stylesheet?',NULL,NULL),(47482,6066,94952,'2012-08-28 19:52:07','[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1D72_503D1D58][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=1D72_503D1D58[/img][/url]\nAll text is Times New Roman (see screenshot)\nAlso icons are still missing. All of them even the DL-icon. See screenshot again. \nHowever the banner-ad is centered now.\n\nTested on windows with FF 14.0.1, IE9 and Chrome(21.0.1180.83)\n\nOkay looking through your css-source\nIs:[quote][code]\n.icon_disk_none {\n   background: url(\'ihttp://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/mages/disk.png\') no-repeat center center;[/code][/quote]\n\nShould be. I think even one center is redundant. I don\'t know how big the container for the disk-icon is.[quote][code]\n.icon_disk_none {\n   background: url(\'http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/disk.png\') no-repeat center;[/code][/quote]\n\nIs:\n[quote][code]/* Bonus SHop */\n\ntr.itembuy {\n     background: #6e6 url(\"images/bggreenfade.png\") repeat scroll 0% 0%;  \n}\ntr.itemnotbuy {\n     background: #d33 url(\"images/bgredfade.png\") repeat scroll 0% 0%;  \n}\ntr.itemduplicate {\n     background: #ccc url(\"images/bgfade.png\") repeat scroll 0% 0%; [/code][/quote]\n\nShould be:\n[quote][code]/* Bonus Shop */\n\ntr.itembuy {\n     background: #6e6 url(\"http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/bggreenfade.png\") repeat scroll 0% 0%;  \n}\ntr.itemnotbuy {\n     background: #d33 url(\"http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/bgredfade.png\") repeat scroll 0% 0%;  \n}\ntr.itemduplicate {\n     background: #ccc url(\"http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/bgfade.png\") repeat scroll 0% 0%;[/code] [/quote]\n\nMore missing imagepaths\n\nIs:\n[quote][code].last_post {width: 15px; height: 15px; background: url(images/go_last_read.png) no-repeat center center; margin-left: 5px;}\n.last_read {width: 15px; height: 15px; background: url(images/go_last_read.png) no-repeat center center; margin-left: 5px;}\n.last_read a { border: none; width: 100%; height: 100%; display: block; }\n.last_read a:hover { border: none; }\n.colhead_dark .last_read { background-image:url(images/go_last_read.png); }\n\n.unread_locked_sticky{background: url(images/locked_sticky_unread.png) no-repeat center center;}\n.read_locked_sticky{background: url(images/locked_sticky_read.png) no-repeat center center;}\n.read_sticky{background: url(images/sticky_read.png) no-repeat center center;}\n.unread_sticky{background: url(images/sticky_unread.png) no-repeat center center;}\n.unread_locked{background: url(images/locked_unread.png) no-repeat center center;}\n.read_locked{background: url(images/locked_read.png) no-repeat center center;}\n.unread{background: url(images/unread.png) no-repeat center center;}\n.read{background: url(images/read.png) no-repeat center center;[/code]}[/quote]\n\nThere are a few more image-paths that are incorrect. Search for images/ in your CSS. \n\nAlso there are some irregularities in coding, some URLs are double quoted and some are not. Probably a leftover artefact from the original modern css.\n\nHope I\'m not too annoying or picky.  :clown:  ',94952,'2012-08-28 19:56:21'),(47483,6065,51063,'2012-08-28 21:37:57','Ok it is great to have this and it will prove useful.  I read over it quickly but kind of carefully.  What would be really helpful (to me at least) would be for someone to post here saying.\n\nWe/I/whoever had an important conversation with whoever from timestamp to timestamp that everyone should be aware of . . . please read that.\n\nI really do not want to have to spend the time reading over a bunch of mundane stuff . . . for example how are you doing at pronoloab or whatever.  On the other hand when say I do not know . . . clownius and mifune have a conversation which we all need to know about . . . highlighting that would be most useful for everyone.\n\nI honestly prefer forums simply because they are easier to read and it is easier to see when there is a new post that I need to read.  But this is a very good middle ground because it allows for a staffer who was not present at the time to become privy to possibly important conversations.\n\nThanks for implementing this . . . but again please post here when important decisions are made in the staff IRC.\n\nOf course the downside to the current implementation is that let us say I have to be fired from staff for some reason . . . I would still be able to access this log . . . at least until which time the password was changed or whatever.  But that is a surmountable hurdle.',51063,'2012-08-28 21:40:02'),(47484,6063,51063,'2012-08-28 21:42:38','Sure absolutely . . . if there is a quick way which does not add too much load then my objections are moot!  Take as much time as you need . . . I see no rush for this feature . . . yeah if we were going live tomorrow or something we might need to move it up the priority list but as it is now . . . no rush at all LOL.',NULL,NULL),(47486,6065,84499,'2012-08-28 22:00:05','\r\n\r\nI think as a general rule all decisions should be made in the staff forums anyway, thats the only way to make sure everyone has had an opportunity to participate. The irc staff channel is just a secure place for staff to chat which has its own uses.\r\n\r\nI totally agree with giving a heads up if there is important stuff in the irc logs though... if stuff is particularly important it can always be reposted in the staff forum or something too. \r\n ',NULL,NULL),(47487,6066,49532,'2012-08-28 22:57:13','[quote=Mobbo,f3066,27482][url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=1D72_503D1D58][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=1D72_503D1D58[/img][/url]\r\nAll text is Times New Roman (see screenshot)\r\nAlso icons are still missing. All of them even the DL-icon. See screenshot again. \r\nHowever the banner-ad is centered now.\r\n\r\nTested on windows with FF 14.0.1, IE9 and Chrome(21.0.1180.83)\r\n\r\n....\r\n\r\nThere are a few more image-paths that are incorrect. Search for images/ in your CSS. \r\n\r\nAlso there are some irregularities in coding, some URLs are double quoted and some are not. Probably a leftover artefact from the original modern css.\r\n\r\nHope I\'m not too annoying or picky.  :clown:[/quote]\r\n\r\nThank you Mobbo,  \r\nYour pickyness is very helpful and not at all annoying.   Dan isn\'t around to clean up my work, so I appreciate all the help I can get. I think I have eveytthing fixed, and did major for on the fonts.\r\n\r\n\r\nI would like to get feedback on the aesthetic changes:\r\n I added background images to the torrent and forum lists,  with different images for the hover. I also made several changes to font sizes, and made change to the font color for links.\r\n\r\nI\'m trying to make this style look more advanced and more professional than the old site in every way, in my opinion the other styles looked like a step backwards without the hover, and and gradients. Plus I didn\'t like so much blue tex, and I think black looks more professional..',NULL,NULL),(47488,6065,85636,'2012-08-28 23:10:10','I was going to give senior staff access to the account that the logger runs under since thats all it does. They would be able to access and do what they wanted with the log\'s.',NULL,NULL),(47489,6064,85636,'2012-08-28 23:16:27','[quote=schlager,f3064,27481]can\'t icons replace text by means of a stylesheet?[/quote]\r\n\r\nAs far as I know. It is not possible',NULL,NULL),(47490,6064,49532,'2012-08-28 23:27:36','[quote=Hexensabbat,f3064,27479]I think the best is to use icons the majority is familiar with. That means the integrated symbols of windows operating systems. okay, the style is a matter of taste, nonetheless this collection is the most popular/used in the world (the old windows curse). So, if the rest is comfortable, i can gather a set of images.[/quote]\r\nif you used the integrated symbols of windows operating systems, I would be totally lost, as I\'m unfamiliar with windows. Symbols common to windows, osx, and linux would be needed.',NULL,NULL),(47491,6066,94952,'2012-08-29 00:28:42','Looks like you got all the bugs. Fonts look good and all icons are where they should be.  :smile2: \n\nOn a aesthetic note, the search boxes feels a little small. Maybe bump font size up a bit. \n\nSee below for my suggestion\nIncreased the height and font-size to values that looked good to me. \n\n[code]#searchbars {\n    padding: 6px 0px 0px 0px;\n    background: url(http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/hbg1.png) repeat-x;\n    background-position: bottom;\n    text-align: center;\n    height: 37px;   /*  33px; Was 30px - Mobbo */\n}\n\n#searchbars form {\n    display: inline;\n}\n\n#searchbars input {\n   /*  background-color: #e4ebef;      #F4F6FB; */\n    background: #e4ebef url(http://empornium.mooo.com/static/styles/empornium/images/mglass.png) no-repeat scroll 96% 0%;\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    font-size: 1em;  /* Was 0.75em - Mobbo */\n    color: #222;\n    position: relative;\n    width:10%;\n    border-radius: 6px 6px 2px 2px;       /* FF9+ IE9+ */\n    -moz-border-radius: 6px 6px 2px 2px;\n    -webkit-border-top-left-radius: 6px;\n    -webkit-border-top-right-radius: 6px;\n    -webkit-border-bottom-left-radius: 2px;\n    -webkit-border-bottom-right-radius: 2px;\n}[/code]',94952,'2012-08-29 00:29:39'),(47492,6063,1507,'2012-08-29 05:11:46',' :laugh:  :laugh:  :laugh: \r\n\r\n[b]I actually asked that they shut off the projected credit earned function as we kept getting so many messages/complaints that the members weren\'t getting their earned credits as it showed the amount projected to be earned and that is what the members were counting on and not taking into account nor understanding that this amount being displayed was just a projected amount and changed when they changed a variable, but they kept hounding staff with complaints that I said it would be best if the guys just left that off or had it hidden so that people would shut the hell up about it and stop saying that we were cheating them out of credits...   :slap: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n :sigh: \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',1507,'2012-08-29 05:12:13'),(47493,6036,1507,'2012-08-29 05:26:23','[b]test[/b][/size]',NULL,NULL),(47494,6036,1507,'2012-08-29 05:32:24','[b]test[/b][/size]\r\n\r\n[size=3][b]test2...\r\n\r\nusb[/b][/size]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47495,6065,70679,'2012-08-29 13:39:59','[quote=GaryE,f3065,27483]Ok it is great to have this and it will prove useful.  I read over it quickly but kind of carefully.  What would be really helpful (to me at least) would be for someone to post here saying.\r\n\r\nWe/I/whoever had an important conversation with whoever from timestamp to timestamp that everyone should be aware of . . . please read that.\r\n\r\nI really do not want to have to spend the time reading over a bunch of mundane stuff . . . for example how are you doing at pronoloab or whatever.  On the other hand when say I do not know . . . clownius and mifune have a conversation which we all need to know about . . . highlighting that would be most useful for everyone.\r\n\r\nI honestly prefer forums simply because they are easier to read and it is easier to see when there is a new post that I need to read.  But this is a very good middle ground because it allows for a staffer who was not present at the time to become privy to possibly important conversations.\r\n\r\nThanks for implementing this . . . but again please post here when important decisions are made in the staff IRC.\r\n\r\nOf course the downside to the current implementation is that let us say I have to be fired from staff for some reason . . . I would still be able to access this log . . . at least until which time the password was changed or whatever.  But that is a surmountable hurdle.[/quote]\r\n\r\nHow about this: On top of sysops, admins, mods, fls, we also hire secretaries? They can do this and serve us coffee and give us back rubs  :icecream: we can have topless secretary days.... etc.',NULL,NULL),(47496,6066,49532,'2012-08-29 14:31:02','I\'ve enlarged the search bar, and made a lot of small changes.  \r\n\r\nI\'m still not satidfied with the gradients, and I\'m having a hard time finding what to change, to make links in forum posts and comments, a different color than main link color.',NULL,NULL),(47497,6066,84499,'2012-08-29 15:40:17','\nWhen you say you are not satisfied with the gradients I am really not sure what you mean. There are a few gradients defined in the css directly and there might still be an image or two with a gradient color change in them... but if you dont like them change them!\n\n\nThere is no entry in the stylesheets specifically for links in posts or comments but you can add one yourself.\n\nTo work out how to insert them requires some knowledge of how css selectors work - then you look at the html output (rather than looking at the raw page source I would use some kind of web developer extension that allows you to select elements and examine the css selectors directly but you can do it either way) and see if its possible to select the elements you want by some common pattern.\n\noff the top of my head all posts and comments are contained in a div.post_content (a div with css class post_content). \nSo in theory css definitions like:\n[code].postcontent a {\n    what: ever;\n}\n.postcontent a:visited {\n    what: ever;\n}\n.postcontent a:hover {\n    what: ever;\n}[/code]\n\nwill change the style of links only in posts and comments. I am not at all sure its a good idea to do that... links that are \"normal text\" (ie. not in headers or buttons etc) anywhere on the site should have the same style according to most principles of web design but ymmv.',84499,'2012-08-29 15:45:28'),(47498,6066,84499,'2012-08-29 15:44:43','\r\n\r\nperhaps I should also point out that there might still be changes made to the base stylesheets... espeically the modern one as it has had the least bugfixing done. So I would carefully track what changes I was making for any external stylesheet so they can be more easily reapplied to the base stylesheets once they are truly finalised (hopefully when we go live).',NULL,NULL),(47499,6065,51063,'2012-08-29 15:56:02','I am not even sure what the point of that comment is.  Are you just trying to be funny or you have a serious point to make?',NULL,NULL),(47500,6063,51063,'2012-08-29 15:59:35','That is a good point usb and I agree.\r\n\r\nI think what you are saying here is the following (please correct me if I got your sentiment incorrect).\r\n\r\nAll we want to see is seed time this week not projected credits.\r\n\r\nis that right usb?\r\n\r\nIf it is I completely agree but it is kind of a moot point since credits are awarded every 15 minutes . . . there is no reason to post predicted credits since there are no such thing anymore.',NULL,NULL),(47501,6064,51063,'2012-08-29 16:04:24','Exactly apparition . . . which is why I prefer text as well.  LOL  I only use windows under protest so whenever I see symbols I have to wait for the tooltip before I click on anything because most are either too small or are simply not familiar.  Again I recognize that we Mac users are the minority so if you are going to insist on using the icons that using the windows icons is the way to go; however, if the only reason the icons are used is for some aesthetic reason I would rather just see text.',NULL,NULL),(47502,6064,1783,'2012-08-29 17:24:53','Well, I like the idea of icons replacing text links, but I wouldn\'t use Windows icons... \n\nEither make your own or search the web for icons that better fit what we need. Nothing from Windows really does in my opinion.\n\nText links are outdated, but they still work...\n\nI would do something like this:\n\n[img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=19A5_503E5144[/img]\n\nThese of course are just examples for just editing a torrent and deleting a torrent. But the rest would be the same only with a different icon and the right function written next to it.\n\n[quote=GaryE]I predict iigreatoneii will be the next person to read this[/quote]\n\nHow did you know? :laugh:',1783,'2012-08-29 17:37:01'),(47503,6064,94952,'2012-08-29 17:25:03','Replacing text with images seems trivial. [url=http://css-tricks.com/css-image-replacement/]http://css-tricks.com/css-image-replacement/[/url]\r\n\r\nSo this would be a good exercise for custom css-builders. \r\n\r\nAs for icons good icons should be self-evident and not tied to a specific operating system. However using familiar icons would lessen any learning curve. But for instance which operating system has a standard icon for download? To my knowledge not one. \r\n\r\nAs for the five icons presented by Hexensabbat they are quite recognisable for any windows user, but that don\'t make them good.\r\n\r\nThis isn\'t a value judgement towards Hexen nor windows just a deconstruction of how icons can be missunderstood or outright bad. \r\nFirst icon - Edit icon? I see a representation for a (written) document.\r\nSecond icon - Bookmark? This is one of the worst icons in Windows history, the favourite\'s-icon. It is a folder with a star. Come on there are real bookmarks you know.\r\nThird icon - View log? Nope that one has been used as an Error-icon since Windows 3.1 at least and is probably even recognisable as such by our Mac friends. \r\nFourth icon - Report? Yes, this I can see mainly due to the fact that the Warning-icon from Windows 3.1 era has be subsumed by various forums as a reportbutton. However to me it represents Warning (non-critical error). This is also one that I think most users would agree upon. Then again I might be wrong.\r\nFifth Icon - Remove? It is used in Windows to denote system-files (dll). \r\n\r\nSo even with Windows icons viewed by a Windows-centric observer the waters get muddy. \r\nIt was a good cross section of icons that could be used but would make the site less user-friendly. \r\n\r\nAgain nothing against you Hexen, just the use of Windows icons. And as a end note I\'m not a mac user, just to forestall any PC vs Mac flaming. ',NULL,NULL),(47504,6064,94952,'2012-08-29 17:28:27','[quote=iigreatoneii,f3064,27502]\r\n\r\n[quote=GaryE]I predict iigreatoneii will be the next person to read this[/quote]\r\n\r\nHow did you know? :laugh:[/quote]\r\n\r\n[you] tag strikes again  :sigh:',NULL,NULL),(47505,6064,84499,'2012-08-29 18:19:53','[quote=Mobbo,f3064,27503]Replacing text with images seems trivial. [url=http://css-tricks.com/css-image-replacement/]http://css-tricks.com/css-image-replacement/[/url]\n\nSo this would be a good exercise for custom css-builders. \n[/quote]\n\nreplacing text with images is trivial in css IF the text is enclosed in a unique css selector... I take it you havent looked at the html for the links here...',84499,'2012-08-29 18:20:54'),(47506,6069,85636,'2012-08-29 18:28:59','[code]<html>\n<head>\n       <title>title</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n<?php\nforeach (glob(\"*.log\") as $filename) {\n    echo \"<a href=/~emp-logging/$filename>$filename size \" . filesize($filename) . \"\\n <br /></a>\";\n}\n?>\n</body>\n</html>[/code]\n\n[b]Log Lister[/b]\n\n[code]<?php\nforeach (glob(\"../logs/*.log\") as $log) {   \n    $file = $log;\n    $contents = file($file); \n    $string = implode(\"<br>\", $contents);\n    echo $string;\n//    echo \"<br></br>\";\n}\n?>[/code]\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]split from thread[/i][br]\'IRC Staff Logs\'[/size][/align]',85636,'2012-08-29 19:06:33'),(47507,6064,94952,'2012-08-29 18:59:15','[quote=mifune,f3064,27505][quote=Mobbo,f3064,27503]Replacing text with images seems trivial. [url=http://css-tricks.com/css-image-replacement/]http://css-tricks.com/css-image-replacement/[/url]\r\n\r\nSo this would be a good exercise for custom css-builders. \r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nreplacing text with images is trivial in css IF the text is enclosed in a unique css selector... I take it you havent looked at the html for the links here...[/quote]\r\n\r\nNope. Quite so. After a quick glance at the html I see that you are right of course. Sorry about that. \r\nPersonally I prefer text links. ',NULL,NULL),(47508,6069,84499,'2012-08-29 19:14:40','I would have 2 pages.\n \n[b]Logs.php[/b]\n[code]<?php\nfunction ListFiles($dir) {\n\n    $dh = opendir($dir);\n    if($dh !== FALSE) {\n\n        $files = Array();\n        $inner_files = Array();\n\n        while($file = readdir($dh)) {\n            if($file != \".\" && $file != \"..\" && $file[0] != \'.\'  && $file != \"test-index.php\") {\n                if(is_dir($dir . \"/\" . $file)) {\n                    $inner_files = ListFiles($dir . \"/\" . $file);\n                    if(is_array($inner_files)) $files = array_merge($files, $inner_files); \n                } else {\n                    $files[] = array( $file, $dir . \"/\" . $file );\n                    //array_push($files, $dir . \"/\" . $file);\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        closedir($dh);\n        return $files;\n    }\n    return false;\n}\n\n \n$logfiles = ListFiles(\'/home/emp-logging/logs\');\nif($logfiles==FALSE){\n    die(\"Error getting logs directory\") ; \n}\n  \n?>\n\n<html>\n<head>\n        <title>Emp Logfiles</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Emp Logfiles</h1> \n    <div>\n<? \n    foreach ($logfiles as $file){\n        list($name, $path) = $file;\n        $path = urlencode($path);\n        echo \"<a href=\\\"Logfile.php?lfile=$path\\\" title=\\\"open logfile\\\">$name</a><br />\";\n    }  \n?>\n\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n\n[/code]\n[b]Logfile.php[/b]\n[code]\n<?\nif (!isset($_GET[\'lfile\']) || $_GET[\'lfile\'] == \'\' ) die(\"No logfile specified\");\n\n$filename = $_GET[\'lfile\'];\n$file = file($filename);\nif($file==FALSE){\n    die(\"Error getting file: $filename\") ;\n}\n\n?>\n<html>\n<head>\n        <title>Logfile <?=$filename?></title>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Logfile <?=$filename?></h1> \n    <div>\n<? \n    foreach ($file as $line){\n        $css = \"log\";\n        if ( strpos($line, \"@@\")!=0 ) $css .= \" highlight\";\n?>     \n        <span class=\"<?=$css?>\"><?=htmlentities($line)?></span><br />\n<? \n    }  \n?> \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n\n[/code]\n\n\n[align=right][size=0][i]split from thread[/i][br]\'IRC Staff Logs\'[/size][/align]',84499,'2012-08-29 19:27:59'),(47509,6063,1507,'2012-08-29 21:21:03',':smile1:\r\n\r\n[b]yes, just show the seed time this week....  and if it\'s a moo point, then that\'s okay too, as I love moo, and we are on the mooo tracker anyways....  :slap:\r\n\r\nsorry, I couldn\'t resist...  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:usb:\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47510,6068,84499,'2012-08-29 21:33:19','\r\na/b/c?\n\n\r\n\r\nokay it displays names on polls in specififed forums... useful for staff voting.',84499,'2012-08-29 21:45:24'),(47511,6065,51063,'2012-08-29 22:05:55','[quote=mifune,f3065,27486]I think as a general rule all decisions should be made in the staff forums anyway, thats the only way to make sure everyone has had an opportunity to participate. The irc staff channel is just a secure place for staff to chat which has its own uses.\r\n\r\nI totally agree with giving a heads up if there is important stuff in the irc logs though... if stuff is particularly important it can always be reposted in the staff forum or something too.[/quote]\r\n\r\nI think it is pretty obvious that I agree . . . but I forgot to say so LOL . . . so here I am saying so LOL.\r\n\r\nI have been staff at a site where important discussions were made more or less exclusively in IRC and even though that was in the days I was in IRC pretty much 24 X 7 but I still missed a lot of important conversations and no one told me :facepalm: then I would go about staffing the site in a way contrary to what was discussed because I did not know any better.  It was beyond stupid.  This system obviates a lot of that . . . but as I said elsewhere I am not going to read through the log every day if I do not need to LOL.\r\n\r\nAs far as the code here . . . I have no idea what the context even is . . . so I am not even going to try to decipher it LOL',NULL,NULL),(47512,6063,51063,'2012-08-29 22:06:59','LOL and holy shit . . . does this mean I speak usb-eese?',51063,'2012-08-29 22:07:51'),(47513,6068,129045,'2012-08-29 22:07:01','There\'s no c! D:',NULL,NULL),(47514,6065,84499,'2012-08-29 22:14:28','sorry i was just discussing some code thing with MrR regarding the log pages on his server... and somehow it ended up in this thread.\n\nYou can see the results on the log pages... it now displays then in your browser instead of just being a downloadable file.\n\n ',84499,'2012-08-29 22:18:14'),(47515,6069,84499,'2012-08-29 18:28:49','[quote=the system]2 posts moved to this thread from [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3065]\"IRC Staff Logs\"[/url][/quote]',NULL,NULL),(47516,6065,84499,'2012-08-29 22:15:31','[quote=the system]2 posts moved to thread [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3069]\"Code for IRC Staff Logs (split from IRC Staff Logs)\"[/url][/quote]\n\n(merge test)\r\n\r\n- I split those posts anyway... MrR you can nuke that thread unless you want it for reference\r\n\r\n',84499,'2012-08-29 22:18:01'),(47517,6069,84499,'2012-08-29 22:24:08','\r\nIt occurs to me you might still want for staff to be able to download the files as well:\r\n \r\n[b]In Logs.php[/b]\r\n[code] \r\n \r\n    foreach ($logfiles as $file){\r\n        list($name, $path) = $file;\r\n        $path = urlencode($path);\r\n        echo \"<a href=\\\"Logfile.php?lfile=$path\\\" title=\\\"open logfile\\\">$name</a> &nbsp; <a href=\\\"$path\\\" title=\\\"download logfile\\\">download .log file</a><br />\";\r\n    }  \r\n \r\n[/code]\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47518,6068,84499,'2012-08-29 22:26:41','\ncan someone who hasnt voted tell me if they can see the results? (in polls in normal forums staff can see results before voting but users cannot).',84499,'2012-08-29 22:27:17'),(47519,6066,49532,'2012-08-29 22:51:07','[quote=mifune,f3066,27497]When you say you are not satisfied with the gradients I am really not sure what you mean. There are a few gradients defined in the css directly and there might still be an image or two with a gradient color change in them... but if you dont like them change them!\r\n\r\n\r\nThere is no entry in the stylesheets specifically for links in posts or comments but you can add one yourself.\r\n\r\nTo work out how to insert them requires some knowledge of how css selectors work - then you look at the html output (rather than looking at the raw page source I would use some kind of web developer extension that allows you to select elements and examine the css selectors directly but you can do it either way) and see if its possible to select the elements you want by some common pattern.\r\n\r\noff the top of my head all posts and comments are contained in a div.post_content (a div with css class post_content). \r\nSo in theory css definitions like:\r\n[code].postcontent a {\r\n    what: ever;\r\n}\r\n.postcontent a:visited {\r\n    what: ever;\r\n}\r\n.postcontent a:hover {\r\n    what: ever;\r\n}[/code]\r\n\r\nwill change the style of links only in posts and comments. I am not at all sure its a good idea to do that... links that are \"normal text\" (ie. not in headers or buttons etc) anywhere on the site should have the same style according to most principles of web design but ymmv.[/quote]\r\n\r\nThank you Mifune, I\'ll try that code tonight for for links.  I\'m not much of an expert on css, and unfortunatly Dan wont be around, for the next couple weeks, to help me.\r\n\r\nWhen I said I\'m not satisfied with the gradienrs I mean the images using for tr.rowa and r.rowb. I\'m still looking foe ones that look better, and give the same general feel as the old site, but fit better with the modern color scheme.\r\n\r\n[quote=mifune,f3066,27498]perhaps I should also point out that there might still be changes made to the base stylesheets... espeically the modern one as it has had the least bugfixing done. So I would carefully track what changes I was making for any external stylesheet so they can be more easily reapplied to the base stylesheets once they are truly finalised (hopefully when we go live).[/quote]\r\n\r\nI\'ve been merging in your changes once a night, so any change you make will find it\'s way into my stylesheet, if it fits.\r\n\r\nAlso I\'ve made a few cleanups, that you may want to merge back, e.g. removed inconsistant quote marks in url(...).',NULL,NULL),(47520,6066,84499,'2012-08-29 23:26:11','\r\n\r\nI think the .rowa and .rowb classes are just background colors, no gradients and no images. If you are going to use an image remember it has to look good in rows of various shapes and sizes, something like a thin vertical image which can be repeated horizontally and probably stretched vertically is what you want... good luck! It might actually be better to define a gradient in the css - that way it scales properly and usually looks better than an image (it only works in modern browsers but screw old browsers) with an element that can have a variable shape and size. Look at the [code].head, tr.colhead, tr.colhead_dark {[/code] class (lines 1207-1209) in modern.css for an example.\r\n\r\n\r\nyou can use single or double quotes for any given string in css (as long as you use the same type at the start and end of the string). That is the CSS specification, so inconsistent quote marks are not even technically bad (obviously either works fine in all browsers anyway).',NULL,NULL),(47521,6054,84499,'2012-08-30 01:53:19','\r\n\r\nfixed.',NULL,NULL),(47522,6065,51063,'2012-08-30 02:02:46','Got you . . . it would be nice if it were sorted properly by day . . . instead of 29th 30th 28th but that is a minor issue. ',NULL,NULL),(47523,5747,84499,'2012-08-30 02:07:27','\r\nfixed.',NULL,NULL),(47524,6069,84499,'2012-08-30 02:27:47','\r\nIf you want the files to be sorted (just added the line \"sort($files);\" before the $files var is returned).\r\n\r\n[code]\r\n    function ListFiles($dir) {\r\n\r\n   $dh = opendir($dir);\r\n   if($dh !== FALSE) {\r\n\r\n       $files = Array();\r\n       $inner_files = Array();\r\n\r\n       while($file = readdir($dh)) {\r\n           if($file != \".\" && $file != \"..\" && $file[0] != \'.\'  && $file != \"test-index.php\") {\r\n               if(is_dir($dir . \"/\" . $file)) {\r\n                   $inner_files = ListFiles($dir . \"/\" . $file);\r\n                   if(is_array($inner_files)) $files = array_merge($files, $inner_files);\r\n               } else {\r\n                   $files[] = array( $file, $dir . \"/\" . $file );\r\n                   //array_push($files, $dir . \"/\" . $file);\r\n               }\r\n           }\r\n       }\r\n\r\n       closedir($dh);\r\n       sort($files);\r\n       return $files;\r\n   }\r\n   return false;\r\n}\r\n[/code]',NULL,NULL),(47526,6068,86439,'2012-08-30 03:04:32','I see 3 people voted b, ...and I know who you are.\r\n\r\n\r\nDamn \'a\' fascists.',NULL,NULL),(47529,6068,51063,'2012-08-30 16:06:29','LMFAO knickers\n\n\n---- Edit and oh you have your potato back . . . you look naked without it.',51063,'2012-08-30 16:07:46'),(47530,6015,84499,'2012-08-30 21:15:57','\nstuff:\n\n[*]User Reaper - after 4 months of no activity (no login) your account will be diabled. If you find yourself in this position you can contact us on IRC and (nicely) ask the staff if you can be reinstated. If the only reason you were disabled is inactivity we will be happy to reneable old accounts.\n\n[*]Torrent Reapaer - after ....... ..... inactive torrents will be deleted. Once a torrent is deleted it is gone for good, we no longer have the data to reinstate deleted torrents, you are welcome to reupload in this case.\n\n\n\n\r\n[*]New credit formula: No cap, but the more you seed the less extra bonus you get (more seeded is always worth more though) - see spoiler for details:\r\n\r\n[spoiler=the maths]\r\nROUND( ( SQRT( 8.0 * ( COUNT( * ) /20 ) + 1.0 ) - 1.0 ) / 2.0 *20 )  per hour\r\nwhere COUNT( * ) = the total number of torrents you are seeding.[/spoiler]\r\n\r\n[spoiler=amounts][font=Courier New]\r\n+----------+---------+\r\n| torrents | credits |\r\n+----------+---------+\r\n| 1        | 2       |\r\n| 2        | 3       |\r\n| 3        | 5       |\r\n| 4        | 6       |\r\n| 5        | 7       |\r\n| 6        | 8       |\r\n| 7        | 9       |\r\n| 8        | 10      |\r\n| 9        | 11      |\r\n| 10       | 12      |\r\n| 11       | 13      |\r\n| 12       | 14      |\r\n| 13       | 15      |\r\n| 14       | 16      |\r\n| 15       | 16      |\r\n| 16       | 17      |\r\n| 17       | 18      |\r\n| 18       | 19      |\r\n| 19       | 19      |\r\n| 20       | 20      |\r\n| 21       | 21      |\r\n| 22       | 21      |\r\n| 23       | 22      |\r\n| 24       | 23      |\r\n| 25       | 23      |\r\n| 26       | 24      |\r\n| 27       | 24      |\r\n| 28       | 25      |\r\n| 29       | 25      |\r\n| 30       | 26      |\r\n| 31       | 27      |\r\n| 32       | 27      |\r\n| 33       | 28      |\r\n| 34       | 28      |\r\n| 35       | 29      |\r\n| 36       | 29      |\r\n| 37       | 30      |\r\n| 38       | 30      |\r\n| 39       | 31      |\r\n| 40       | 31      |\r\n| 41       | 32      |\r\n| 42       | 32      |\r\n| 43       | 33      |\r\n| 44       | 33      |\r\n| 45       | 34      |\r\n| 46       | 34      |\r\n| 47       | 34      |\r\n| 48       | 35      |\r\n| 49       | 35      |\r\n| 50       | 36      |\r\n| 51       | 36      |\r\n| 52       | 37      |\r\n| 53       | 37      |\r\n| 54       | 38      |\r\n| 55       | 38      |\r\n| 56       | 38      |\r\n| 57       | 39      |\r\n| 58       | 39      |\r\n| 59       | 40      |\r\n| 60       | 40      |\r\n| 61       | 40