example.\r\n[/quote]\r\nOk I did a major rewrite, and replaced all the background images with css gradients, it\'s really looking good now.  I think it would great, if it was added to the main styles.\r\n\r\n[quote=mifune,f3066,27520]you can use single or double quotes for any given string in css (as long as you use the same type at the start and end of the string). That is the CSS specification, so inconsistent quote marks are not even technically bad (obviously either works fine in all browsers anyway).[/quote]\r\nIt may work perfectly, but it sure makes search and replace moe complicated.\n\nI made a bunch more changes, but I\'m stumped on a couple of things and could use some help:\r\n[*]removing the border from the requests table\r\n[*] making the [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/requests.php]request[/url] title bold; without bolding the requester name bold\r\n[*] making the [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/collages.php]collage[/url] title bold\r\n\r\n\r\nBesides those, I\'m pretty much finished, except for adding changes, that mifune makes to the base theme.',49532,'2012-09-01 22:44:00'),(47536,5635,49532,'2012-08-31 05:40:44',' :yaydance: ',NULL,NULL),(47537,6015,171777,'2012-08-31 09:22:45','I suspect that the hole between 15k and 20k means that you keep getting the same as with 15k \r\n\r\n(I doubt anyone will ever have more then 100 or so torrents seeding at the same time though)\r\n\r\nHow ofen are credits awarded like this? ever minute? every hour? every day?',NULL,NULL),(47538,6015,51063,'2012-08-31 12:02:00','every 15 minutes\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47539,5635,94804,'2012-08-31 14:21:38','I.m.o. the price for 1 slot = wÃ¡y too high, now I\'m seeding 111 torrents, but buying a slot would take me a little more than 4 days of seeding, my pc is almost always on, but 4 days of continuus seeding, seems a bit too much for me',NULL,NULL),(47540,6070,47234,'2012-08-31 14:26:38','I have asked him and hes agreed to help out as FLS.  So say Welcome to him.\r\n\r\nNext any other good candidates people can think of?',NULL,NULL),(47541,6070,88669,'2012-08-31 14:34:16','Harro :) thank you, will be my pleasure',NULL,NULL),(47542,6015,84499,'2012-08-31 14:53:13','\r\n[quote=DrkNess,f3015,27537]I suspect that the hole between 15k and 20k means that you keep getting the same as with 15k [/quote]\r\n \r\neh? There is no \'hole\'... I just picked some representative values. put numbers inbetween 15k and 20k into ROUND( ( SQRT( 8.0 * ( COUNT( * ) /20 ) + 1.0 ) - 1.0 ) / 2.0 *20 )  per hour and you will get the inbetween values. Those values are only there for curiosity... I do not expect people to seed 1000\'s of torrents at once.\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=DrkNess,f3015,27537]How ofen are credits awarded like this? ever minute? every hour? every day?[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nwell yes every 15 minutes you get 0.25 the amounts shown in that list. Thats the hourly rate. ',NULL,NULL),(47543,6070,70679,'2012-08-31 15:13:31','and of course the hugged pussy  :w00t:  :laugh: \r\n\r\nWelcome Cyber  :yaydance: ',NULL,NULL),(47545,5635,51063,'2012-08-31 18:36:05','in the current system it is what . . . 1.3 slots a week or something?  So 1.8 slots a week is too much?  Sorry I do not get your argument?',NULL,NULL),(47546,6070,51063,'2012-08-31 18:36:52','Welcome!  Thanks for agreeing to help out.',NULL,NULL),(47547,5635,94804,'2012-08-31 20:51:59','(on bonus-page it says) You get 0.25 credits for every 15 minutes of every torrent you seed. Every torrent is counted, so 2 torrents seeded for 1 hour will give you 2 credits etc.\r\nthat\'s 2264 credits per day, 11000/2264= approx. 4 days of seeding ',NULL,NULL),(47548,5635,84499,'2012-08-31 21:11:41','max 3360 a week',NULL,NULL),(47549,6070,1507,'2012-08-31 21:23:23',':wave:\r\n\r\n[b]welcum cyber and thanks for helping out....   :yes2: \r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:hooray:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47550,6063,1507,'2012-08-31 21:30:33','[quote=GaryE,f3063,27512]LOL and holy shit . . . does this mean I speak usb-eese?[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\n :sigh:  :sigh:  :sigh: \r\n\r\n[b]you poor bastard....  :laugh:\r\n\r\nusb[/b]\r\n\r\n:slap:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47551,6063,51063,'2012-08-31 21:53:54','LOL ',NULL,NULL),(47552,5635,94804,'2012-08-31 22:14:21','so, then it\'s even longer 11000/3360=over 3 weeks!. Which I think is a bit much!',NULL,NULL),(47553,5635,84499,'2012-08-31 23:12:37','lol..\r\n\r\nokay we are talking at cross purposes.\r\n\r\nits 3360 max a week at emp.me. So the max number of slots you can buy a week is 3360/2500 = 1.34.\r\n\r\nThe new system here has just been changed - now there is no max, but you would earn less per hour for seeding 110 torrents, about 57 credits per hour. I have updated the bonus shop page with the new details.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe prices here are not really balanced yet. I will note your pov that slots are too expensive... but bear in mind that the point of the bonus system is not to give away as much as possible, its to find the right balance to encourage seeding. But slots probably will come down in price a bit when I get round to it.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47555,6072,76180,'2012-09-01 10:26:24','So, I just filled a request, and it seems to have worked properly (I got the proper credits, it was noted as filled in the Requests section).  But I ran into a snag just before I did:  When I initially posted the torrent, it was listed as Gangbang (makes sense, given the main video is a threesome vid).  When I initially tried to fill the request, I was denied because the request was in a different category (BDSM), even though the request itself was clear that the video needed only to be something by Amber Rayne, not necessarily BDSM.  I switched categories (which I could do because the other vid, a brief Kink.com clip, could plausibly fit the category), and it worked.\r\n\r\nBut the issue at heart, to me at least, is the fact that there are categories for requests to begin with, and that the torrent\'s category has to match the request\'s category.  Is that really necessary?  I mean, for starters, unlike the torrents page, there are no category icons next to the request, and you only would be able to find out the category by going into the request itself, which is a little tedious.  I understand the category system has uses as a filter, but is it really necessary to force your torrents to match the category?  It\'s a bit much, especially if you have general requests like the one I filled, and the categories are rather vague anyways.',NULL,NULL),(47556,6072,129045,'2012-09-01 13:52:18','There was an ongoing discussion here: http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2716\r\n\r\nBut I guess attention was diverted to other problems. Anyway, people agreed that removing the lock would be better, since a lot of content really span across to many categories.',129045,'2012-09-01 13:53:24'),(47557,6061,84499,'2012-09-01 14:39:02','\nOkay!\n\nEverytime I cross another task of this list someone else reminds me of some missing feature.\n\nThats okay... kind of. But if anyone (staff/fls) can think of anything else that we have forgotten or that is missing and which they really think should be here - now is the time to remember it!',84499,'2012-09-01 14:53:03'),(47558,6070,86439,'2012-09-01 15:03:37','Thanks for stepping up. You have a nice arse. \r\n\r\nYes, I assume everyone is their avatar, GaryE is apparently a paper bag.',NULL,NULL),(47559,6073,88669,'2012-09-01 15:06:42','Show number of comments or views of the torrents on the userprofile (user.php).\r\nIt\'s nice to see if anyone post a new comment or question on any of your torrents without needing to open one by one every week or so.',NULL,NULL),(47560,6070,85636,'2012-09-01 15:17:31','[quote=knickers,f3070,27558]Yes, I assume everyone is their avatar, GaryE is apparently a paper bag.[/quote]\r\n\r\nWhat about me then?',NULL,NULL),(47561,6072,94952,'2012-09-01 15:46:03','Thanks onigami for filling the request.\r\nI got the system message \r\n\r\n[