e freeleech all the time?',NULL,NULL),(47571,5635,94804,'2012-09-01 22:40:19','nah, but it\'s hardly everything now, is it?',NULL,NULL),(47572,5635,84499,'2012-09-01 22:42:54','No, but that means you agree that there is a limit where having more freeleech stuff becomes counter-productive. We may disagree about where that point is... you will just have to trust (or live with) our judgement  :wink: ',NULL,NULL),(47574,6066,49532,'2012-09-01 22:45:10','Double post, I didn\'t see thatm my post got added to my last post (forgot to uncheck merge)',49532,'2012-09-01 22:47:07'),(47575,6066,84499,'2012-09-01 22:59:50','\r\nthe > symbol means first child of:\r\n\r\n#requests .thin>div.head {\r\n}\r\n\r\nselects the first header style bar inside the div.thin element (the central inside column element) inside the #requests element (the document name is given as an id to every containing body element).\r\n\r\nI\'m not sure exactly what you are trying to select on the collages page but you can similarly use something like #collages .thin>h2 / div.head depending on what you mean.\r\n\r\n\n\n\r\n\r\noh what table do you mean?',84499,'2012-09-01 23:01:01'),(47576,5635,94804,'2012-09-01 23:00:02','hÃ¨hÃ¨hÃ¨, true, I think 0.75 per week = fine',NULL,NULL),(47578,6066,49532,'2012-09-02 02:06:48','[quote=mifune,f3066,27575]the > symbol means first child of:\n\noh what table do you mean?[/quote]\n\nI\'m trying to make just the title of the collage/requset bold inside the td of the collage/request listing table. see the screenshots:\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=700C_5042BD77][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=700C_5042BD77[/img][/url]',49532,'2012-09-02 02:13:42'),(47579,6075,49532,'2012-09-02 02:46:23','The top ten, collage and staff pages, have a header, at the top if the content table, that makes the page look really awsome with the modern theme (other pages like the torrents page and the forum don\'t have it). How about making a similar header on every page?\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=EAF0_5042C742][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=EAF0_5042C742[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(47581,6072,94952,'2012-09-02 06:50:31','You made it even better!! I didn\'t think to link it to the request itself, which is superior in every way!\r\n :bow: ',NULL,NULL),(47582,6070,86439,'2012-09-02 08:19:29','[quote=MrRandom,f3070,27560][quote=knickers,f3070,27558]Yes, I assume everyone is their avatar, GaryE is apparently a paper bag.[/quote]\r\n\r\nWhat about me then?[/quote]\r\n           .........it isn\'t fair\r\nI\'ve had enough now I want my share\r\nCan\'t you see? I wanna live!\r\nBut you just take more than you give...\r\n\r\nWell there\'s a pretty girl servin\' at the counter of a corner shop\r\nShe\'s been waitin\' back there, waitin\' for her dream\r\nAnd dreams walk in and out, they never stop\r\nWell she\'s not too proud to cry out loud\r\nShe runs to the street and she screams;\r\n\r\n\r\nI have no idea, but you sure are handsome.',NULL,NULL),(47583,6075,84499,'2012-09-02 16:22:33','\r\n\r\nWell I have been meaning to make some parts a bit more consistent, which includes adding page headers to some pages. Probably not all though as there are a couple of places where it might not fit so well... we\'ll see.',NULL,NULL),(47584,6076,49532,'2012-09-02 19:53:21','I\'m getting an extra site header on the torrents page, inside the contena table. This happens with all styles. \r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=A9BE_5043B85C][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=A9BE_5043B85C[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(47585,6076,84499,'2012-09-02 21:24:05','\r\nfixed',NULL,NULL),(47586,6075,49532,'2012-09-03 05:15:07','[quote=mifune,f3075,27583]Well I have been meaning to make some parts a bit more consistent, which includes adding page headers to some pages. Probably not all though as there are a couple of places where it might not fit so well... we\'ll see.[/quote]\r\nSo far it looks really good.   What about the forum and IRC, and inbox pages?   I think thty would fit really well there, if it\'s not too difficult.',NULL,NULL),(47588,6078,75827,'2012-09-03 06:50:31',' i do think you should add Libtorrent in General but specifically i see this two version often  0.13.2  0.12.9  any how i`m not sure if the client list is only for windows (home and wont affect seedbox)',NULL,NULL),(47589,6078,16616,'2012-09-03 09:04:05','In many Linux Debian related repositorys : lenny (a.f.a.i.k) /[b]Ubuntu 11.11[/b] / Mint (12) ist Transmission 2.33 (12565) included. I suggest to add this client\r\nTHX',NULL,NULL),(47590,6070,171777,'2012-09-03 10:37:52','Guess I honor my name then... \r\n\r\nAnyway. Welcum Cyber',NULL,NULL),(47591,6070,86439,'2012-09-03 10:49:50','Who?\r\n\r\n\r\nI wonder if he wants his nick here changed too?',NULL,NULL),(47592,6070,171777,'2012-09-03 13:33:41','[quote=knickers,f3070,27591]\r\nI wonder if he wants his nick here changed too?[/quote]\r\n\r\nWill happen automatically upon migration.',NULL,NULL),(47593,6079,94804,'2012-09-03 14:29:19','don\'t know know if it\'s just my machine acting up, or it\'s larger but where the stats normally are is a white square visible.[url=http://www.freeimage.us/share-A733_5044BE68.html][img]http://www.freeimage.us/image-A733_5044BE68.jpg[/img][/url]',94804,'2012-09-03 14:30:10'),(47594,6078,47234,'2012-09-03 15:03:47','I suggest those people switch to deluged lol.  But yeah the list is far from complete.\r\n\r\nI noticed that KTorrent is missing.  The 3.x.x and 4.x.x ones are good as far as im aware.  Some of the 2.x.x series did report bad stats to the tracker so id leave that whole lot out by default.',NULL,NULL),(47595,6079,84499,'2012-09-03 16:22:58','\nthats what happens when you use an external css and dont update it when the base css is updated.\n\n\nyou are missing some new css classes - can\'t remember exactly what they are, something like table.userstats and related entries...',84499,'2012-09-03 16:25:17'),(47596,6079,94804,'2012-09-03 16:28:43','oow, thanks, I\'ll look into it',NULL,NULL),(47597,6078,152838,'2012-09-03 17:06:35','I don\'t think it makes sense to allow Transmission 1.93 / 2.13 / 2.51 / 2.61 but no other versions. I for instance am using 2.50 and therefore the tracker rejects me. At the moment I also have no option to upgrade without a huge hassle for me.\n\nIsn\'t it possible to whitelist all versions of the \"good\" clients released in the last, lets say three years? (Except the known bad versions)',152838,'2012-09-03 17:13:15'),(47598,6078,84499,'2012-09-03 17:12:49','\nunless there is some issue I am unaware of all the libtorrent and transmission versions will be on the whitelist.\n\n[quote=porntgr,f3078,27597]I don\'t think it makes sense to allow Transmission 1.93 / 2.13 / 2.51 / 2.61 but no other versions. I for instance am using 2.50 and therefore the tracker rejects me. At the moment I also have no option to upgrade without a huge hassle for me.\n\nIsn\'t it possible to whitelist all versions of the \"good\" clients released in the last, lets say three years? (Except the known bad versions)[/quote]\n\nI have added transmission 2.50 now.\n\nThere are a couple of hundred specific client versions yet to be added (we have just started weeding out the bad clients from the list of all used clients on emp.me) and it will probably be a week until we get that sorted - if anyone else wants a specific client adding right now to the tracker so you can download/upload here then tell us what client and version you are using and we will add it (dont ask for bitcomet or bitlord though... they are banned).  \n\n\n',84499,'2012-09-03 17:15:34'),(47599,6061,84499,'2012-09-03 18:11:36','\nmoved to thread: [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3080]Articles, help wanted[/url]\n\n\n\n \n',84499,'2012-09-03 18:12:48'),(47600,6080,84499,'2012-09-03 18:12:12',' \n\nDrkness has been doing a great job with the articles but there is a lot of work and we could definitely do with some more help.\n\n[*][url=/articles.php?topic=faq]FAQ[/url] [b][color=#FF0000]***needs a decision making***[/color][/b] - Personally I think everything useful in the faq should be in a different article somewhere, either a new one or an existing one, then we can nuke the faq. I just think its hard to find information if its in the faq so would like to see the end of it.\n[*][url=/articles.php?topic=approvedimg]Approved Imagehosts[/url] - needs a little more text i think?\n[*][url=/articles.php?topic=avatar]Avatar Rules[/url] [b][color=#FF0000]***needs a decision making***[/color][/b] - atm avatar xy size is restricted by userclass, are we keeping this? (iirc lanz was not too enthusiastic about the restrictions) - whatever decision is made the restrictions need to be clearly described in the rules.\n[*][url=/articles.php?topic=collages]Collages rules[/url] - text is a little rough... could do with someone who has got to grips with collages writing some nice text about what they are?\n[*][url=/articles.php?topic=forum_guidelines]Forum Guidelines[/url]  [b][color=#FF0000]***needs a decision making***[/color][/b] - says no double posting no exceptions... we have never enforced that rule so perhaps we should not state it so unequivocally? or start enforcing it? either way I was surprised to read that. Also mentions no ratio cheats... I dont understand why that is in the forum rules?\n[*][s][url=/articles.php?topic=irc_rules]IRC rules[/url] - \"Probably more to follow.\" ?[/s]\n \n[*][url=/articles.php?topic=uploadchecklist]Upload Checklist[/url] - has some links to forum threads. Content(s) should be transferred to the article (or new articles as appropriate). In fact I think some of the thread contents are already transferred (probably drkness\' handiwork, thanks dude!) so some of it is just links needing updating. This article could probably be something more useful than just a short list of links anyway.\n[*][url=/articles.php?topic=presentation]Guide to presentations[/url] - Needs an overhaul. [b]edit:[/b] hmm... since I started drafting this post yesterday I think drkness has done a bunch of work on this already.\n[*][url=/articles.php?topic=shop]Bonus Shop[/url] - I just added a stub for this, I think we should have a help article briefly explaining what the shop is for.\n[*][url=/articles.php?topic=collagehelp]Collages help[/url] - needs adding. How to use etc.\n[*][url=/articles.php?topic=stylesheets]Stylesheets[/url] - needs adding. Shiney pics of the 3 official stylesheets, instructions how to change. How to use external stylesheets with a disclaimer they are not officially supported. Just a thought but... IF someone (not nessacarily staff... this could be farmed out to some random user who has knowledge in this case) wants to write some kind of help guide to css for external stylesheets I would be happy for us to host it with a big disclaimer its not supported... or maybe link to a post in the forums... has to be an unoffical guide though because we are not supporting external css as a rule.\n[*][url=/articles.php?topic=search]Torrents Search[/url] - Needs basic guide adding.\n\n\nAnd also there are still a couple of sections in the introduction article that need finishing.\n\n\n \n',84499,'2012-09-07 02:10:31'),(47601,6078,16616,'2012-09-03 18:37:30','Aktually I have one seed running with the Transmission 2.33 (12565) version I wrote above. Plz do me favor and liberate me :D\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47602,6078,84499,'2012-09-03 18:45:35','Added Transmission 2.33',NULL,NULL),(47603,6061,84499,'2012-09-03 19:03:58','\r\n\r\nJust to restate...\r\n\r\nThis a last call for anything you still want added/think is missing.\r\n\r\nThings that are already shelved for v2.5 (ie. will not be done before we go live)\r\n[*]A \'new\' status for torrents\r\n[*]rearranging the db structure for greater optimisation.\r\n[*]proper cheater tools\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47604,6078,70679,'2012-09-03 19:04:29','shocking  :w00t: I would like to suggest not an addition but that uTorrent 3.21b be removed. I do not thinki is a good idea to allow alpha and beta versions.',NULL,NULL),(47605,6078,152838,'2012-09-03 19:48:45','Well, at least I can report that the blocking works, I got an error status which clearly said what the problem was and adding to the whitelist also works.  :D',NULL,NULL),(47606,6080,85636,'2012-09-03 21:29:05','IRC rules is done, just needs senior staff to sign off on it.',NULL,NULL),(47607,6081,88669,'2012-09-03 23:07:14','Well I notice that we can\'t see more then 250 on the list. So how about having a Top 500 or even \"top X\" where user could select how many wish to see.\r\nOf course listing 500 entries on the same page can be bad, so would need to have a \"next page\"link or so.\r\nI know this is not essential but it has some effect on user competition and feeling like she/she can make to top, etc.\r\nWhat you g uys think? :)',NULL,NULL),(47608,6078,49532,'2012-09-04 03:58:56','Just as a test, I tried xtorrent, and it successfully blocked it.  Xtorrent is a client I would keep off the whitelist.',49532,'2012-09-04 03:59:31'),(47609,6082,86439,'2012-09-04 09:18:00','Arrow at end of thread title does what it says, but the one on the far right in the \'latest\' column does nothing. It shows a tooltip saying \'jump to last post\', but is not clickable.\r\n\r\nModern css, FF14.0.1 XP pro sp3.',NULL,NULL),(47610,6082,171777,'2012-09-04 10:27:37','Works fine for me on the empornium stylesheet using google chrome.',NULL,NULL),(47611,6082,86439,'2012-09-04 12:09:04','The two other stylesheets I see work too, but modern does not.',NULL,NULL),(47612,6083,70679,'2012-09-04 12:22:31','The new sites allows for signatures and many of us have taken advantage of this feature, some more than others.\r\n\r\nSo I wonder if it should be regulated like I am not sure I want to see a girl pooping or puking or worst or advertisement banners or PPC or page long ones or.... you know how people can get creative.',NULL,NULL),(47613,6078,93967,'2012-09-04 13:57:18','My trusty uTorrent 2.0.4 isn\'t working, what bout this one?',NULL,NULL),(47615,6082,84499,'2012-09-04 17:08:15','\r\n\r\n\r\n?\r\n\r\nperhaps if you tell me what page etc. I might know what you are talking about.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47616,6082,129045,'2012-09-04 17:46:09','[quote=mifune,f3082,27615]?\r\n\r\nperhaps if you tell me what page etc. I might know what you are talking about.[/quote]\r\n\r\nHe\'s talking about this other arrow:\r\nhttp://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewforum&forumid=17\r\n\r\n\"started by x714x - 3 - 25 - by mifune 2 weeks ago [color=red]=>[/color]\"\r\n\r\nOn the Modern stylesheet, that arrow doesn\'t link to anywhere.',NULL,NULL),(47617,6078,84499,'2012-09-04 17:52:11','added',NULL,NULL),(47618,6082,84499,'2012-09-04 17:52:36','fixed',NULL,NULL),(47621,5635,88669,'2012-09-04 21:12:01','OK and what about the Double Seed slots?\r\nWhat usually happens to me is that after one or two peers snatch, my upload speed drops and they become the major uploader.\r\nSo I \"buy\" a double seed for like 13 days but benefit from it only during first hours.\r\n\r\nI would suggest a DS that limited to 24 hrs for example. I know the idea is to keep the user seeding for long time and keep torrents alive.\r\nHowever this way makes it not worth uploading new content, since it would  \"steal\" bandwidth from the old doubleseeded (even if no one is downloading it might not be worth). In the end I just keep seeding the DS torrent or simply upload new content and waste that DS.',NULL,NULL),(47622,5635,84499,'2012-09-04 21:52:57','Well its doable, but it means tracking 2 types of slots as all slots atm are 14 day slots. You are suggesting having a 24hr slot too... its a smallish change to the engine but quite a lot of interface changes, and thats before we get to balancing it.\r\n\r\nAbout which... I\'m not so sure its even a good idea to promote 24hr seeding, like you say we want to promote long term seeding. If you haven\'t got enough up bandwidth to seed more than one thing at once fast then I\'m not sure the site should encourage you to seed stuff for 24hrs and run... I just dunno.\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(47623,5635,88669,'2012-09-04 23:11:43','The idea would be during the first 24 hrs, when I the only seed I get double. After that I keep seeding anyway, but I\'ll give priority to my new uploads. It\'s not that I stop seeding after everyone snatch, but the final effect is the same.\r\nMaybe a 48 hrs would be more suitable, or a 7 days. These would have to be cheaper or sold in groups, like two 7 days slots costing +100 credits then a 14 days one.\r\nOf course I can\'t guarantee the behavior of other users, but I don\'t think short DL would be an incentive for short seeding.',NULL,NULL),(47624,5635,49532,'2012-09-05 03:49:34','Why not just make all uploads double seed for the original uploader? That way there would be an incentive to add new stuff, and you don\'t need to track 2 separate types slots.',NULL,NULL),(47625,5635,171777,'2012-09-05 08:04:12','[quote=apparition,f2635,27624]Why not just make all uploads double seed for the original uploader? That way there would be an incentive to add new stuff, and you don\'t need to track 2 separate types slots.[/quote]\r\n\r\nPotential for major abuse. We already have that people with DD and LW start uploading a lot of small random torrents, often with terrible descriptions. Like this we would reward them for that because we never get to those torrents within moments of them bein uploaded so the user already get\'s some seed ratio which would in your idea be doubled even.',NULL,NULL),(47627,5635,94804,'2012-09-05 15:58:24','True Drkness, is it much work to just ADD a 24hour-slot to the bonus-page? \'Cause in i.mo it\'s quite a good idea, just not for me, my max. upl. = 350 kb/s',NULL,NULL),(47631,6084,94804,'2012-09-05 21:10:14','Hi, don\'t think this\'s the place for this, so please move it to the appropriate section (this is linked with the mainsite, right? So when I post in \"help\" others will see it as well)\r\nI\'ve been messinng with the css but now I\'m wondering how I edit what\'s displayed in the stats, or if I want to remove a searchbox how do I do that?',NULL,NULL),(47633,6084,84499,'2012-09-05 22:01:21','\r\n\r\nthis site is not linked with the main site no.\r\n\r\nyour css question is a little vague... I dont know what you mean by \'edit whats displayed in the stats\' - possibly you can\'t, depends what you mean.\r\n\r\nIf you want to hide an element you have to select it and then do something like display:none or left:-10000px depending on what exactly you are trying to do. I warn you... hiding elements that are not designed to be hidden might render the site inoperable for you, it could screw up the page layout in a serious way... iow you can do what you want but you are on your own if it goes wrong.\r\n\r\ncss tutorials: http://www.w3schools.com/css/css_id_class.asp\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47634,6083,51063,'2012-09-05 22:09:31','I [b]know[/b] we have talked about this before . . . and I have no recollection of what we decided.  LOL Not the most helpful comment I realize however someone will hopefully remember.  It might have been one of the threads that got deleted in one of the tests.  I just remember that we did talk about it.\r\n\r\nThere was talk about the size of the sig should be class specific which is why I remember the thread but again that is all I remember LOL',NULL,NULL),(47635,6081,51063,'2012-09-05 22:16:13','I will go out on a very large limb and say probably not.  Even with caching those lists take up a lot of cpu cycles.  By proposing a random entry amount you are basically saying that we can no longer cache those lists.  Running that many queries can really bog down a site so I am pretty sure that is a no go.\r\n\r\nAs to your suggestion that we maybe have another list of the top 500 that might be doable.\r\n\r\nOf course all of this is assuming my assumption is correct that even with caching there is no easy way to have a user selectable amount which is cached.  For example if someone selected 400 and the next guy selects 500 if the 400 is cached and we just run a live query for the 401 - 500 entries it might be possible . . . but I doubt it works that way.',NULL,NULL),(47636,6081,84499,'2012-09-05 22:32:31','well in theory you could make it work like that, problem is with your scenario that the top 400 might have changed in the meantime - so what was 399 might now be 401... you might have dupes or all sorts... so it has to be a single snapshot to make sense. So like you say having a variable number top X is not great because its not usefully cacheable (although in actuality I doubt it would be used that much, so real load might not be a problem because of that). Also I cant really be bothered to code a variable top X.\n\nAnyway I looked into it and although adding a top 500 or top 1000 is easy to do if its a single page (once its generated its cached for 12/24 hrs so load isn\'t an issue) - and also paginating a set of results is relatively straightforward with the gazelle engine - for reasons that are too boring to explain its a huge PITA to add paginated results to the top10 page. So.... probably not going to happen.',84499,'2012-09-05 22:35:43'),(47637,6084,94804,'2012-09-05 22:55:21','oow, good to know. I wanna let \"required\" disappear, or the \"search user\"box, but pref. that \"required\" . And weird, when I set headercolor to a shade of pink, it\'s add a gradient, while (since I gave only 1 colorcode in the header) it should be solid.[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=F980_5047D6F3][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=F980_5047D6F3&jpg[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(47640,6084,84499,'2012-09-05 23:29:34','\r\n\r\nthis is (one reason) why we do not officially support external stylesheets...\r\n\r\nThe site css doesn\'t do that. I could have a pretty informed guess as to what is going on (you have changed one part of a gradient definition) but unfortunately I am busy enough coding the site... I am not going to debug someone elses css too. Maybe someone else can help you, probably you need to learn some more css...',NULL,NULL),(47641,6080,51063,'2012-09-06 01:44:21','I really would love to help . . . but it would be a bad idea LOL.  I get the rules confused with too many places and I am sure I would make mistakes LOL  Do you want separate threads for the things which need decisions or just talk about all of them here (probably better to have individual threads IMHO).  If so I can at least start them.',NULL,NULL),(47642,6061,51063,'2012-09-06 01:48:24','[quote=mifune,f3061,27557]Okay!\r\n\r\nEverytime I cross another task of this list someone else reminds me of some missing feature.\r\n\r\nThats okay... kind of. But if anyone (staff/fls) can think of anything else that we have forgotten or that is missing and which they really think should be here - now is the time to remember it![/quote]\r\n\r\nDid anyone ever fix the first bug I ever reported?  The issue where when you sign up for a new account it says you must be over 13 years old (rather than 18).',NULL,NULL),(47643,6081,51063,'2012-09-06 01:59:42','Yeah of course you are right I was just kind of thinking out loud.  I just know that the top 10/100/250 lists were a huge load problem on older versions of TBDev.  But if they are getting checked often enough . . . that is a lot of queries.  Especially if they are not easily cached.  But even if they did not I am not sure it would be worth the effort.\r\n\r\nI do get the OP\'s point though.  I am patiently waiting to show up on the top 250 list for upload amount . . . and yeah it would be nice to see exactly were I am.  But it is not hard to say . . . I am 500 GB away or whatever.  That is enough for me in all honesty.  But I do see why the OP asked.',NULL,NULL),(47645,6081,84499,'2012-09-06 02:28:58','\r\nwell its easy to cache a fixed result, which is what all the topX lists do, so its one query every 24 hrs for each distinct list. You could get clever and cache a long list and then retrieve the whole list and only display part of it... but honestly caching 3 * 4 * 3 (or however many lists there are total) even though some of them are big lists is not a problem at all and makes it nice and quick to retrieve and display them.\r\n\r\nmaybe I\'ll add an unpaginated top 500 (easy and not a load problem)... just no complaining that the page takes a long time to load!',NULL,NULL),(47646,6084,49532,'2012-09-06 07:16:29','[quote=schlager,f3084,27637]oow, good to know. I wanna let \"required\" disappear, or the \"search user\"box, but pref. that \"required\" . And weird, when I set headercolor to a shade of pink, it\'s add a gradient, while (since I gave only 1 colorcode in the header) it should be solid.[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=F980_5047D6F3][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/image.php?id=F980_5047D6F3&jpg[/img][/url][/quote]\r\n\r\nCan you paste the link to your css? I\'ll give it a look and see if I can find the problem.',NULL,NULL),(47647,6081,171777,'2012-09-06 08:07:49','In all honesty I don\'t see why you would need more then a top 250. Overal I don\'t even expect people to really look further then the top 100. \r\n\r\nThe only thing that might be interesting is to see (in the profile) a position in the rankings because that is all you do with this top X stuff anyway: check at what position you are yourself. This is offcourse something that might require some tweaking to lessen server load (generate static lists once a day and base numbers on that and such)',NULL,NULL),(47649,6083,86439,'2012-09-06 08:22:29','Can I use a gif where a dude shoves something glass up his arse, it breaks, and blood starts pouring out?',NULL,NULL),(47650,6084,94804,'2012-09-06 09:57:07','www.takkietakkie.com/alto.css\r\n\n\n[quote=mifune,f3084,27640] I am not going to debug someone elses css too. Maybe someone else can help you, probably you need to learn some more css...[/quote]\r\nI totally understand, it\'s just a minor request. But a new CssHelpThread (nice one for Wordfeud;) on the new site will be nice',94804,'2012-09-06 10:01:33'),(47651,6084,171777,'2012-09-06 11:50:18','[quote=schlager,f3084,27650]But a new CssHelpThread (nice one for Wordfeud;) on the new site will be nice[/quote]\r\n\r\nFeel free to make one once we go live.',NULL,NULL),(47653,6085,171777,'2012-09-06 15:04:14','Basically this is Dave\'s article in staff forum. This has the most compelte layout of anything atm on the site so if anyone has time please try to make the articles look like this:\n\n\n\n[align=center][#=top]Welcome to the new empornium.me[/#][/align]\n\nThere have been a lot of changes so this guide is a summary to help you.\n\nSome things are new, many things have changed, please take the time to read this guide and make sure you understand how the new site works - what new features and functions are available to you (we now have a bounty based requests system, collages, bookmarks etc.) and how some of the new systems will affect you (uploaders need to understand how the marked for deletion system works for example).\n\nThis guide serves as a brief introduction, for more details please see the new [url=/articles.php?topic=tutorials]Help tutorials[/url] and [url=/articles.php?topic=rules]Rules articles[/url] - they are linked in the main header too. Or if you have further questions please post in the [url=/forums.php?action=viewforum&forumid=6]Help & Support forum[/url].\n\n[spoiler=notes] \n[b]Staff note:[/b]  We should no longer be using forum threads for stuff like reference rules/help information. ALL of that stuff should be in an article somewhere, preferably written as concisely as possible while still being thorough. The point of articles is partly so we can have \"proper\" webpages instead of forum threads for this kind of information - but staff/whoever can still have access to change them through the site software (instead of being static content you need a coder to change).[/size]  - obviously drafting stuff in threads is fine - this only applies to finished content [b] - mifune[/b][/spoiler]\n\n\n\n\n[bg=grey,310px,left][color=white][font=Tahoma][size=4][align=center][b]Contents[/b][/align][/size][/font][/color][bg=white,300px][bg=270px] \n[url=#top]Welcome[/url]\n[url=#clients]Client whitelist[/url]\n[url=#upload]Uploading[/url]\n[url=#search]The search function[/url]\n[url=#credits]Credits and bonus shop[/url]\n[url=#requests]Requests[/url]\n[url=#freeleech]Automatic Freeleech[/url]\n[url=#collages]Collages[/url]\n[url=#tagging]Community Tagging[/url]\n[url=#mfd]Marked for Deletion[/url]\n[url=#badges]Badges and Medals[/url]\n[url=#classes]User Classes[/url]\n[url=#fls]Front Line Support[/url]\n[url=#bounty]Reward for dupe reports[/url] \n[url=#irc]IRC[/url] \n[url=#restrict]Restrictions on Editing Torrents/Editing Posts[/url] \n[url=#notifications]Notifications[/url] \n[url=#profile]Profile page[/url]\n[url=#settings]User Settings[/url]\n[/bg][/bg]\n[/bg]\n\n\n\n\n[#=clients]Client Whitelist[/#]\n\nWe now have a strict whitelist for torrent clients that are allowed/blacklist for clients that are banned.\n\n[whitelist]**NOTE: in the articles section this will appear as a table of the allowed clients.\n\n\n[#=upload]Uploading[/#] \n\nThere is no fixed announce url anymore - when you create a torrent you can leave it blank. The site uses your passkey to announce the torrent and add stats to you. \n\nRead the uploading rules and see[URL=http://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=286] Uploading guide - a quick checklist[/url] [size=3]<-- change thread to article[/size]\n\n[b]Note[/b] the uploading form will not continue if the torrent does not contain enough basic information. \nAll presentations must follow the [url=/articles.php?topic=upload]uploading rules[/url]\n \nThere are various [url=/articles.php?topic=tutorials#uploading]help tutorials for uploading[/url]:\n[url=/articles.php?topic=presentation]Guide to Presentations [/url] - A useful guide to making a presentation \n[url=/articles.php?topic=tag_glossary]Tags - Glossary[/url] - A list of potential tags for use and their meanings.\n[url=/articles.php?topic=uploadchecklist]Uploading Checklist[/url] - A helpful guide to uploading\n[url=/articles.php?topic=utorrentupload]Uploading with uTorrent for Dummies[/url] - A small guide on how to upload with uTorrent\n[url=/articles.php?topic=vuzeupload]Uploading with Vuze for Dummies[/url] - A guide on how to download with Vuze \n 	\n\n[#=search]The search function[/#]\n\nOne of the biggest changes under the hood of the new site is the tagging system which allows for a much better search function. The search interface on the [url=/torrents.php]Browse torrents[/url] page is very similar to the one on the old site but will give you much better results.\n\nFor a more details on search and the differences between basic and advanced search please see the [url=/articles.php?topic=search]Search[/url] article in the help section.\n\n\n[#=credits]Credits and bonus shop[/#]\n\nThe bonus system has changed. Click on Credits (in the top right corner of the page) or Bonus in the drop-down list under your site nickname. \n\nThere are no longer any next credits the tracker awards credits at short regular intervals instead.\n\nUnder your user profile you will see a bonus log section, this is a record of how you have spent your credits (only visible to you).\n\n\n[#=requests]Requests[/#]\n\nThere is a completely new requests system linked from the top of the page. Instead of making forum posts you use the new system to enter a request and offer a bounty in GB from your upload credit. The bounty is deducted immediately once you make the offer, and others may also offer bounties to sweeten the request. \n\nPlease see the [url=/articles.php?topic=requests]Requests article[/url] in the help section for more info.\n\nnote: You must be a Good Perv with a ratio of at least 1.05 to be able to make a Request.\n\n[spoiler=notes]\nThere is now a link on the top of the page rather than using the forums like before.\nNote the requests Forum will now close.  [color=green]Im thinking i will personally throw a 1GB request on any request from the forums thats not yet filled.  Thoughts on that?[/color][color=#6699FF]Drk: I suggest making a transfer account for stuff like that.[/color] *** decision needed - Dave********\nIf you are a Good Perv or above you will see the following options\n[New request] [My requests] [Requests I\'ve voted on] \n\nAll requests now need a bounty but in MB/GB\'s not credits any more.\n\nlink to article needed too[/spoiler]\n\n\n[#=freeleech]Automatic Freeleech[/#]\n\nFreeleech will be automatically set for all torrents 20GB+. \n\nThere will be no more freeleech requests in the forum.\n\n\n[#=collages]Collages[/#]\n\nNot my thing - I haven\'t tested this at all - can someone else add a summary please !!\n\n*************************************\n\nI added the following - suggestions on the order are welcome as now they are just as I thought of them ***to be removed later***\n\n\n[#=tagging]Community tagging[/#]\n\nCommunity tagging is a system where members can add tags to a torrent, and also vote tags up or down (so yes it is possible a tag will disappear if enough members vote it down).\n\n[b]Note:[/b]This feature is [b]ONLY[/b] available to Good Pervs and above so Apprentices cannot use it.\n\nFor full details on how it works see [url=/articles.php?topic=tags]Tagging and tags guide[/url]\nFor a list of common tags see [url=/articles.php?topic=tag_glossary]Tag Glossary[/url]  \n\n\n[#=mfd]Torrent marked for deletion[/#]\n\nIf a Torrent is marked for deletion it will be deleted in 24 hours after it was marked.  The reason for it being marked will be clear on the torrent page.  If any user chooses to download a marked torrent any lost ratio etc. is on that users head.  It is a gamble if the users chooses to take that gamble and it fails so be it . . . do not come whining to staff about ratio issues arising from downloading torrents marked for deletion.\n\nIf you are the uploader and you want to fix the torrent visit the torrent page and edit the torrent when you are done click on the \"If you have fixed this upload make sure you have told the staff: By clicking here\" link (and then the yes you are sure prompt).   This will notify staff and it will stop the deletion timer[color=red] right? [/color]  Once staff have reviewed your changes we will either re-mark the torrent for deletion (if the changes were not adequate) or we will mark the torrent as ok.  **add screen*****\n\n\n[#=badges]Badges/medals[/#]\n\nThese show how much a member has contributed to the site. Some are awarded automatically others can be bought using credits and some are awarded at the staffs discretion, anyone begging for a medal or badge will automatically be disqualified from getting it.\n\nFor a full list of available awards see the [url=/bonus.php?action=awards]Awards and Badges[/url] page.\n\n[b]Note:[/b] If you turn off avatars in your profile you will not see users badges/medals (except on their user profile page).\n\n\n[#=classes]User classses[/#]\n  \n[b][color=#92a5c2]Apprentice[/color][/b]\n[*]The default class of new members.  \n[b][color=#4Ec89B]Perv[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 1 week, uploaded 10GB+, ratio 0.7+\n[b][color=#3c3]Good Perv[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 4 weeks, uploaded 25GB+, ratio 1.05+\n[b][color=orange]Sextreme Perv[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 26 weeks, uploaded 1TB+, uploaded 50+ torrents, ratio 1.05+\n[b][color=#00f]Smut Peddler[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 52 weeks, uploaded 10TB+, uploaded 500+ torrents, ratio 1.05+\n\nThere are a few restrictions on community tagging and making requests for apprentice and perv ranks.\nAt Good Perv you get access to all the site functions and pages.\n \n[b]Promotions are now automatic[/b] - Please see the [url=/articles.php?topic=ranks]User Classes[/url] article for more details. \n\n\n[#=fls]Front Line Support[/#]\n\n[*]Not a rank as such, any user may be invited to be a FLS - amongst other things they help out with solving users problems and answering user enquiries.\n[*]IMPORTANT NOTE - FLS are users who volunteer to help us run the site well, please treat them with some respect.\n\n\n[#=bounty]Credits for reporting Dupes/Banned content[/#] \n\nIf you make an [u]accurate[/u] dupe report (including the link to the torrent that is a dupe of) you will receive a bounty of 400 credits. \n\nAnyone mass spamming the report funtion with inaccurate reports will be warned and repeat offenders banned. Making an honest mistake will not be punished. You are welcome to make as many accurate dupe reports as you like, please make sure you have read and understood the [url=/articles.php?topic=dupes]Dupe Rules[/url] to avoid making bad reports.\n\nThis bounty will also be paid for reporting banned content (on the do not upload list).\n\n\n[#=irc]IRC[/#]\n\nIRC can be accessed by using the link at the top of the page or by an IRC client.\nUse IRC to chat with fellow members, or if you need it there is a Help and Support channel.\nStill waiting on guides - will be added later\n\n\n[#=restrict]Editing Restrictions/Posting Restrictions[/#] \n\nTorrent descriptions may be edited at any time but torrents cannot be deleted once they have a couple of peers. If you want to delete your torrent for some reason report the torrent (using reason \'other\' if there is no better type) and explain why you want to delete it.\n\nPosts and comments may be edited for up to 15 minutes after they have been made. After this if you need a post edited for some reason report the post and explain your reason.\n\nThere is a 10 second flood control on posting in the forums and comments, this is mainly to prevent spam/double click double posts but is hopefully a short enough span that it will not be too much inconvenience.\n\n\n[#=notifications]Notifications[/#]\n\n<<insert content>>\n\n\n[#=profile]Profile page[/#]\n\nClicking on your [b]username[/b] takes you to your user profile which has your info field and statistics. \n\nYou can view your current credits and your credit log here. The boxes on the right contain your personal statistics and links to your history pages etc. What information is shown to other users here depends on your privacy settings.\n\nIf you have your uploaded torrents as visible to other users (list) then they will be listed here at that bottom (if the user viewing has the setting to view other users torrents on that page set).\n\n[#=settings]User settings[/#]\n\nUnder your [b]username[/b] there is a drop down list with links to various sections of the site:\n\n[table=nball]\n[tr][td=25%]Inbox[/td][td]PM inbox.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Staff Inbox [/td][td] [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Message Staff [/td][td] [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Uploads[/td][td] Your uploaded torrents.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Bookmarks [/td][td] Your bookmarked collages/requests/torrents.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Notifications [/td][td] View the results of any notifications you receive, add new notifications.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Subscriptions [/td][td] Threads you are subscribed too.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Post history [/td][td] shows your forum posts.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Comments [/td][td]shows any torrnet comments you made[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Collages[/td][td] Collages are collections of torrents on a theme - see below for information about Collages (a new feature)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Logs [/td][td] site logs. If you want to know what happened to your torrent or who edited your collage look here.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Sandbox[/td][td] a place to experiment or test bbCode. The same bbcode parser is used across the site for presentaions, forum posts,  torrent comments etc.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Conn-Checker [/td][td] An independent method of checking if you are connectable through your torrent client.[/td][/tr]\n [/table]\n\n[size=2]Clicking on [b]Settings[/b] takes you to your user settings page. [/size]\n\n[table=nball]\n[tr][td=25%]Stylesheet [/td][td]Select which stylesheet you want to use[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]External CSS:[/td][td]You can use an external css if you want <<link to thread?>> [i]note:[/i] we do not officially support external stylesheets although you may be able to get help in the forums[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Time Zone [/td][td]Set your timezone[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Time style [/td][td]	Display times as time since (date and time is displayed as tooltip)/ Display times as date and time (time since is displayed as tooltip)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Default Search Type [/td][td] Basic or Advanced - please see the [url=/articles.php?topic=search]How to use search[/url] article[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Torrents per page [/td][td] 25/50/100 [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Posts per page (Forum) 	[/td][td] 25/50/100 [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Collage torrent covers to show per page [/td][td]25/50/100[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Category list in torrent search [/td][td] Whether to show the list of categories in the search center by default [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Tag list in torrent search [/td][td] Whether to show the list of tags in the search center by default [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Tags in lists 	[/td][td]Hide tags in lists[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Add tag behaviour [/td][td]	Automatically vote up my added tags[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Accept PM\'s [/td][td]	All (except blocks) / Friends only / Staff only[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Comments PM [/td][td]	Notify me by PM when I receive a comment on one of my torrents[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Subscription [/td][td]	Subscribe to topics when posting[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Page Titles [/td][td]	Use short page titles (ie. instead of Forums > Forum-name > Thread-title use just Thread-Title)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Forum topics [/td][td]	Disable latest forum topics[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]User Torrents [/td][td]	Show users uploaded torrents on user page (if allowed by that users paranoia settings)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Smileys [/td][td]Disable smileys[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Avatars [/td][td]Disable avatars (disabling avatars also hides user badges)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Signatures [/td][td]Disable Signatures[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Download torrents as text files [/td][td]For users whose ISP block the downloading of torrent files[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Unseeded torrent alerts[/td][td]Whether you want to recieve a PM alert before your unseeded torrents are deleted[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Your Info field[/td][td][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Signature[/td][td][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Paranoia Settings[/td][td] << insert >>[/td][/tr]\n[/table]\n\n\n\n[codeblock]\n[align=center][#=top]Welcome to the new empornium.me[/#][/align]\n\nThere have been a lot of changes so this guide is a summary to help you.\n\nSome things are new, many things have changed, please take the time to read this guide and make sure you understand how the new site works - what new features and functions are available to you (we now have a bounty based requests system, collages, bookmarks etc.) and how some of the new systems will affect you (uploaders need to understand how the marked for deletion system works for example).\n\nThis guide serves as a brief introduction, for more details please see the new [url=/articles.php?topic=tutorials]Help tutorials[/url] and [url=/articles.php?topic=rules]Rules articles[/url] - they are linked in the main header too. Or if you have further questions please post in the [url=/forums.php?action=viewforum&forumid=6]Help & Support forum[/url].\n\n[spoiler=notes] \n[b]Staff note:[/b]  We should no longer be using forum threads for stuff like reference rules/help information. ALL of that stuff should be in an article somewhere, preferably written as concisely as possible while still being thorough. The point of articles is partly so we can have \"proper\" webpages instead of forum threads for this kind of information - but staff/whoever can still have access to change them through the site software (instead of being static content you need a coder to change).[/size]  - obviously drafting stuff in threads is fine - this only applies to finished content [b] - mifune[/b][/spoiler]\n\n\n\n\n[bg=grey,310px,left][color=white][font=Tahoma][size=4][align=center][b]Contents[/b][/align][/size][/font][/color][bg=white,300px][bg=270px] \n[url=#top]Welcome[/url]\n[url=#clients]Client whitelist[/url]\n[url=#upload]Uploading[/url]\n[url=#search]The search function[/url]\n[url=#credits]Credits and bonus shop[/url]\n[url=#requests]Requests[/url]\n[url=#freeleech]Automatic Freeleech[/url]\n[url=#collages]Collages[/url]\n[url=#tagging]Community Tagging[/url]\n[url=#mfd]Marked for Deletion[/url]\n[url=#badges]Badges and Medals[/url]\n[url=#classes]User Classes[/url]\n[url=#fls]Front Line Support[/url]\n[url=#bounty]Reward for dupe reports[/url] \n[url=#irc]IRC[/url] \n[url=#restrict]Restrictions on Editing Torrents/Editing Posts[/url] \n[url=#notifications]Notifications[/url] \n[url=#profile]Profile page[/url]\n[url=#settings]User Settings[/url]\n[/bg][/bg]\n[/bg]\n\n\n\n\n[#=clients]Client Whitelist[/#]\n\nWe now have a strict whitelist for torrent clients that are allowed/blacklist for clients that are banned.\n\n[whitelist]**NOTE: in the articles section this will appear as a table of the allowed clients.\n\n\n[#=upload]Uploading[/#] \n\nThere is no fixed announce url anymore - when you create a torrent you can leave it blank. The site uses your passkey to announce the torrent and add stats to you. \n\nRead the uploading rules and see[URL=http://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=286] Uploading guide - a quick checklist[/url] [size=3]<-- change thread to article[/size]\n\n[b]Note[/b] the uploading form will not continue if the torrent does not contain enough basic information. \nAll presentations must follow the [url=/articles.php?topic=upload]uploading rules[/url]\n \nThere are various [url=/articles.php?topic=tutorials#uploading]help tutorials for uploading[/url]:\n[url=/articles.php?topic=presentation]Guide to Presentations [/url] - A useful guide to making a presentation \n[url=/articles.php?topic=tag_glossary]Tags - Glossary[/url] - A list of potential tags for use and their meanings.\n[url=/articles.php?topic=uploadchecklist]Uploading Checklist[/url] - A helpful guide to uploading\n[url=/articles.php?topic=utorrentupload]Uploading with uTorrent for Dummies[/url] - A small guide on how to upload with uTorrent\n[url=/articles.php?topic=vuzeupload]Uploading with Vuze for Dummies[/url] - A guide on how to download with Vuze \n 	\n\n[#=search]The search function[/#]\n\nOne of the biggest changes under the hood of the new site is the tagging system which allows for a much better search function. The search interface on the [url=/torrents.php]Browse torrents[/url] page is very similar to the one on the old site but will give you much better results.\n\nFor a more details on search and the differences between basic and advanced search please see the [url=/articles.php?topic=search]Search[/url] article in the help section.\n\n\n[#=credits]Credits and bonus shop[/#]\n\nThe bonus system has changed. Click on Credits (in the top right corner of the page) or Bonus in the drop-down list under your site nickname. \n\nThere are no longer any next credits the tracker awards credits at short regular intervals instead.\n\nUnder your user profile you will see a bonus log section, this is a record of how you have spent your credits (only visible to you).\n\n\n[#=requests]Requests[/#]\n\nThere is a completely new requests system linked from the top of the page. Instead of making forum posts you use the new system to enter a request and offer a bounty in GB from your upload credit. The bounty is deducted immediately once you make the offer, and others may also offer bounties to sweeten the request. \n\nPlease see the [url=/articles.php?topic=requests]Requests article[/url] in the help section for more info.\n\nnote: You must be a Good Perv with a ratio of at least 1.05 to be able to make a Request.\n\n[spoiler=notes]\nThere is now a link on the top of the page rather than using the forums like before.\nNote the requests Forum will now close.  [color=green]Im thinking i will personally throw a 1GB request on any request from the forums thats not yet filled.  Thoughts on that?[/color][color=#6699FF]Drk: I suggest making a transfer account for stuff like that.[/color] *** decision needed - Dave********\nIf you are a Good Perv or above you will see the following options\n[New request] [My requests] [Requests I\'ve voted on] \n\nAll requests now need a bounty but in MB/GB\'s not credits any more.\n\nlink to article needed too[/spoiler]\n\n\n[#=freeleech]Automatic Freeleech[/#]\n\nFreeleech will be automatically set for all torrents 20GB+. \n\nThere will be no more freeleech requests in the forum.\n\n\n[#=collages]Collages[/#]\n\nNot my thing - I haven\'t tested this at all - can someone else add a summary please !!\n\n*************************************\n\nI added the following - suggestions on the order are welcome as now they are just as I thought of them ***to be removed later***\n\n\n[#=tagging]Community tagging[/#]\n\nCommunity tagging is a system where members can add tags to a torrent, and also vote tags up or down (so yes it is possible a tag will disappear if enough members vote it down).\n\n[b]Note:[/b]This feature is [b]ONLY[/b] available to Good Pervs and above so Apprentices cannot use it.\n\nFor full details on how it works see [url=/articles.php?topic=tags]Tagging and tags guide[/url]\nFor a list of common tags see [url=/articles.php?topic=tag_glossary]Tag Glossary[/url]  \n\n\n[#=mfd]Torrent marked for deletion[/#]\n\nIf a Torrent is marked for deletion it will be deleted in 24 hours after it was marked.  The reason for it being marked will be clear on the torrent page.  If any user chooses to download a marked torrent any lost ratio etc. is on that users head.  It is a gamble if the users chooses to take that gamble and it fails so be it . . . do not come whining to staff about ratio issues arising from downloading torrents marked for deletion.\n\nIf you are the uploader and you want to fix the torrent visit the torrent page and edit the torrent when you are done click on the \"If you have fixed this upload make sure you have told the staff: By clicking here\" link (and then the yes you are sure prompt).   This will notify staff and it will stop the deletion timer[color=red] right? [/color]  Once staff have reviewed your changes we will either re-mark the torrent for deletion (if the changes were not adequate) or we will mark the torrent as ok.  **add screen*****\n\n\n[#=badges]Badges/medals[/#]\n\nThese show how much a member has contributed to the site. Some are awarded automatically others can be bought using credits and some are awarded at the staffs discretion, anyone begging for a medal or badge will automatically be disqualified from getting it.\n\nFor a full list of available awards see the [url=/bonus.php?action=awards]Awards and Badges[/url] page.\n\n[b]Note:[/b] If you turn off avatars in your profile you will not see users badges/medals (except on their user profile page).\n\n\n[#=classes]User classses[/#]\n  \n[b][color=#92a5c2]Apprentice[/color][/b]\n[*]The default class of new members.  \n[b][color=#4Ec89B]Perv[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 1 week, uploaded 10GB+, ratio 0.7+\n[b][color=#3c3]Good Perv[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 4 weeks, uploaded 25GB+, ratio 1.05+\n[b][color=orange]Sextreme Perv[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 26 weeks, uploaded 1TB+, uploaded 50+ torrents, ratio 1.05+\n[b][color=#00f]Smut Peddler[/color] [/b]\n[*]Must have been be a member for at least 52 weeks, uploaded 10TB+, uploaded 500+ torrents, ratio 1.05+\n\nThere are a few restrictions on community tagging and making requests for apprentice and perv ranks.\nAt Good Perv you get access to all the site functions and pages.\n \n[b]Promotions are now automatic[/b] - Please see the [url=/articles.php?topic=ranks]User Classes[/url] article for more details. \n\n\n[#=fls]Front Line Support[/#]\n\n[*]Not a rank as such, any user may be invited to be a FLS - amongst other things they help out with solving users problems and answering user enquiries.\n[*]IMPORTANT NOTE - FLS are users who volunteer to help us run the site well, please treat them with some respect.\n\n\n[#=bounty]Credits for reporting Dupes/Banned content[/#] \n\nIf you make an [u]accurate[/u] dupe report (including the link to the torrent that is a dupe of) you will receive a bounty of 400 credits. \n\nAnyone mass spamming the report funtion with inaccurate reports will be warned and repeat offenders banned. Making an honest mistake will not be punished. You are welcome to make as many accurate dupe reports as you like, please make sure you have read and understood the [url=/articles.php?topic=dupes]Dupe Rules[/url] to avoid making bad reports.\n\nThis bounty will also be paid for reporting banned content (on the do not upload list).\n\n\n[#=irc]IRC[/#]\n\nIRC can be accessed by using the link at the top of the page or by an IRC client.\nUse IRC to chat with fellow members, or if you need it there is a Help and Support channel.\nStill waiting on guides - will be added later\n\n\n[#=restrict]Editing Restrictions/Posting Restrictions[/#] \n\nTorrent descriptions may be edited at any time but torrents cannot be deleted once they have a couple of peers. If you want to delete your torrent for some reason report the torrent (using reason \'other\' if there is no better type) and explain why you want to delete it.\n\nPosts and comments may be edited for up to 15 minutes after they have been made. After this if you need a post edited for some reason report the post and explain your reason.\n\nThere is a 10 second flood control on posting in the forums and comments, this is mainly to prevent spam/double click double posts but is hopefully a short enough span that it will not be too much inconvenience.\n\n\n[#=notifications]Notifications[/#]\n\n<<insert content>>\n\n\n[#=profile]Profile page[/#]\n\nClicking on your [b]username[/b] takes you to your user profile which has your info field and statistics. \n\nYou can view your current credits and your credit log here. The boxes on the right contain your personal statistics and links to your history pages etc. What information is shown to other users here depends on your privacy settings.\n\nIf you have your uploaded torrents as visible to other users (list) then they will be listed here at that bottom (if the user viewing has the setting to view other users torrents on that page set).\n\n[#=settings]User settings[/#]\n\nUnder your [b]username[/b] there is a drop down list with links to various sections of the site:\n\n[table=nball]\n[tr][td=25%]Inbox[/td][td]PM inbox.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Staff Inbox [/td][td] [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Message Staff [/td][td] [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Uploads[/td][td] Your uploaded torrents.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Bookmarks [/td][td] Your bookmarked collages/requests/torrents.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Notifications [/td][td] View the results of any notifications you receive, add new notifications.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Subscriptions [/td][td] Threads you are subscribed too.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Post history [/td][td] shows your forum posts.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Comments [/td][td]shows any torrnet comments you made[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Collages[/td][td] Collages are collections of torrents on a theme - see below for information about Collages (a new feature)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Logs [/td][td] site logs. If you want to know what happened to your torrent or who edited your collage look here.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Sandbox[/td][td] a place to experiment or test bbCode. The same bbcode parser is used across the site for presentaions, forum posts,  torrent comments etc.[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Conn-Checker [/td][td] An independent method of checking if you are connectable through your torrent client.[/td][/tr]\n [/table]\n\n[size=2]Clicking on [b]Settings[/b] takes you to your user settings page. [/size]\n\n[table=nball]\n[tr][td=25%]Stylesheet [/td][td]Select which stylesheet you want to use[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]External CSS:[/td][td]You can use an external css if you want <<link to thread?>> [i]note:[/i] we do not officially support external stylesheets although you may be able to get help in the forums[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Time Zone [/td][td]Set your timezone[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Time style [/td][td]	Display times as time since (date and time is displayed as tooltip)/ Display times as date and time (time since is displayed as tooltip)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Default Search Type [/td][td] Basic or Advanced - please see the [url=/articles.php?topic=search]How to use search[/url] article[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Torrents per page [/td][td] 25/50/100 [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Posts per page (Forum) 	[/td][td] 25/50/100 [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Collage torrent covers to show per page [/td][td]25/50/100[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Category list in torrent search [/td][td] Whether to show the list of categories in the search center by default [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Tag list in torrent search [/td][td] Whether to show the list of tags in the search center by default [/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Tags in lists 	[/td][td]Hide tags in lists[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Add tag behaviour [/td][td]	Automatically vote up my added tags[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Accept PM\'s [/td][td]	All (except blocks) / Friends only / Staff only[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Comments PM [/td][td]	Notify me by PM when I receive a comment on one of my torrents[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Subscription [/td][td]	Subscribe to topics when posting[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Page Titles [/td][td]	Use short page titles (ie. instead of Forums > Forum-name > Thread-title use just Thread-Title)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Forum topics [/td][td]	Disable latest forum topics[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]User Torrents [/td][td]	Show users uploaded torrents on user page (if allowed by that users paranoia settings)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Smileys [/td][td]Disable smileys[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Avatars [/td][td]Disable avatars (disabling avatars also hides user badges)[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Signatures [/td][td]Disable Signatures[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Download torrents as text files [/td][td]For users whose ISP block the downloading of torrent files[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Unseeded torrent alerts[/td][td]Whether you want to recieve a PM alert before your unseeded torrents are deleted[/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Your Info field[/td][td][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Signature[/td][td][/td][/tr]\n[tr][td]Paranoia Settings[/td][td] << insert >>[/td][/tr]\n[/table]\n\n\n[/codeblock]',171777,'2012-09-06 15:25:46'),(47654,6084,49532,'2012-09-06 15:20:19','in your css:\r\n[code]#header {\r\n    width: 100%;\r\n    min-width:1000px; \r\n    padding: 0;\r\n    background-color: #ab0ca6;\r\n    background: -moz-linear-gradient(top, #0074b7 0%, #2c5687 100%); /* firefox */\r\n    background: -webkit-gradient(linear, left top, left bottom, color-stop(0%,#ab0ca6), color-stop(100%,#2c5687)); /* webkit */\r\n    background-image: -o-linear-gradient(top, rgb(0,116,183) 0%, rgb(44,86,135) 100%); /* opera */\r\n    filter: progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.gradient( startColorstr=\'#ab0ca6\', endColorstr=\'#2c5687\' ); /* ie */\r\n    \r\n    font-weight: normal;\r\n}[/code]\r\n\r\n\r\nThis part is a gradient:\r\n[code] background: -moz-linear-gradient(top, #0074b7 0%, #2c5687 100%); /* firefox */\r\n    background: -webkit-gradient(linear, left top, left bottom, color-stop(0%,#ab0ca6), color-stop(100%,#2c5687)); /* webkit */\r\n    background-image: -o-linear-gradient(top, rgb(0,116,183) 0%, rgb(44,86,135) 100%); /* opera */\r\n    filter: progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.gradient( startColorstr=\'#ab0ca6\', endColorstr=\'#2c5687\' ); /* ie */\r\n  [/code]\r\n\r\nFor solid it should be:\r\n[code]\r\n#header {\r\n    width: 100%;\r\n    min-width:1000px; \r\n    padding: 0;\r\n    background-color: #ab0ca6;\r\n     \r\n    font-weight: normal;\r\n}[/code]\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47655,6085,48010,'2012-09-06 17:59:04','Actually the credit goes to mifune.\r\n\r\nI just knocked up the basic draft and mifune transformed it to make it look nice.\r\n\r\nBut it seems like a good template',NULL,NULL),(47656,6084,94804,'2012-09-06 23:31:30','Guess I could\'ve figured that 1 out myself, thanks anyway!',NULL,NULL),(47657,6061,84499,'2012-09-07 01:41:47','\r\nthat was fixed so long ago I had forgotten it was ever a bug :)',NULL,NULL),(47658,6080,84499,'2012-09-07 02:23:09','\r\n\r\n[quote=GaryE,f3080,27641]... Do you want separate threads for the things which need decisions or just talk about all of them here (probably better to have individual threads IMHO).  If so I can at least start them.[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nwell.... kind of. \r\n\r\n1) The FAQ; I\'ve sort of already made the decision that the faq is going (its partially stripped already)... I just want other people to agree and then do the work lol.\r\n2) Avatar Rules; Make a thread, I dont think its that big a thing so hopefully we can decide pretty quick. In any event its changeable in the interface so its not really that urgent in any event.\r\n3) Double posting; Double posting with a reason seems to have always been tolerated on emp.me so the permission to double post here has been enabled for quite a while, and there plainly are legitimate reasons to double post... So I think it\'ll be enough if we just confirm we are staying with the de-facto rule and rewrite the rules a little to match the practice. Unless anyone feels strongly otherwise?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47659,6080,84499,'2012-09-07 02:23:31','\r\nhey [you]\r\n\r\n :flirty: \r\n\r\n\r\nplease help finish the site content!\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\nplease?  :cry: ',NULL,NULL),(47660,6015,84499,'2012-09-07 02:30:06','\r\nI did a few more bits.... and there are still a few bits need doing.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47661,6080,171777,'2012-09-07 15:07:01','[quote=mifune,f3080,27659]hey [you]\r\n\r\n :flirty: \r\n\r\n\r\nplease help finish the site content!\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\nplease?  :cry:[/quote]\r\n\r\nNo worries I have been sick for a while this week. Will work on articles as much as possible again from now on.',NULL,NULL),(47662,6061,51063,'2012-09-07 18:54:48','With everything that got deleted and all the time that passed I had no idea LOL',NULL,NULL),(47663,6086,51063,'2012-09-07 19:02:21','Per mifune we need to make a decision about Avatar sizes.  I offered to start a thread to discuss this . . . so here I am.\n\n[quote=mifune]atm avatar xy size is restricted by userclass, are we keeping this? (iirc lanz was not too enthusiastic about the restrictions) - whatever decision is made the restrictions need to be clearly described in the rules.[/quote]\n\nOk here is my $0.02 I have no preference.  LOL  So I vote for whatever means the least amount of work for mifune LOL\n\nOnce a decision is made someone will need to edit the rules.',51063,'2012-09-07 19:03:05'),(47664,6080,51063,'2012-09-07 19:07:14','Regarding double posting . . . I agree with mifune 100%  I see no real reason to disallow it.  There are legitimate reasons for it.\r\n\r\nI made an avatar size thread where that can be discussed.\r\n\r\nAs far as the FAQ going away . . . I honestly like having a FAQ . . . but not so much that I am going to argue for keeping it.  LOL',NULL,NULL),(47665,6080,84499,'2012-09-07 19:25:07','\r\n\r\nwell to be honest I don\'t object to having a FAQ, I just have a dislike of the way on tracker sites the FAQ has become a bloated hybrid of rules, history and site/help information. This makes it hard to find the information you want (historically I suspect tbdev is to blame lol). So we can have a FAQ, but lets have one that actually is a section containing anwsers to frequently asked questions not covered by the help or rules... or something. If we look at the \"whats new article\" that is becoming a kind of faq in itself lol... I dont know what the best solution is I just want a better solution than what you face when you join some random tracker site of missing or hard to find information. I am open to ideas...',NULL,NULL),(47666,6086,84499,'2012-09-07 19:29:21','for reference:\n[font=Courier New]\n                   Sig length  Avatar size\nApprentice        0           [b]75 x 75[/b] 	       \nPerv              128         [b]100 x 100[/b] 	 	 \nGood Perv         256         [b]125 x 125[/b] 	   \nSextreme Perv     512         [b]150 x 200[/b] 	  \nSmut Peddler      1024        [b]150 x 250[/b]  	 \nMod Perv +        4096        [b]150 x 250[/b]  	 \n  [/font] \n\n\r\nthe way I see it is sig length & avatar size are a cheap way of giving some perks to the upper user ranks.\r\n\r\nOf course there are some other distinctions (not many though)... and if we do want some difference it doesn\'t have to be so pronounced... I am open to suggestions.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',84499,'2012-09-07 20:14:24'),(47667,6083,171777,'2012-09-07 19:48:50','1 guy 1 cup? Seen it. IMHO 2 girls 1 cup is worse. 1 guy 1 cup is just hilarious\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47668,6083,84499,'2012-09-07 20:20:32','\r\n\r\nI dont remember having discussed this before - perhaps we only talked about size restrictions previously?\r\n\r\n\r\nAnyway... personally I dont want to see goat.se or other shock shit in the images, so my vote is some kind of restriction... even though its arguably stupid on a pron site. But I am a prude, and I can just keep hiding signatures as I have to on this site lol.',NULL,NULL),(47669,6083,85636,'2012-09-07 22:58:43','I\'m with mifune on there being some kind of restriction.',NULL,NULL),(47670,6083,86439,'2012-09-07 23:51:36','I hate animated sigs. Its all fine until you load a thread with 50 posts or whatever each one with more and more elaborate sigs that take forever to load, especially with various hosts etc some of which invariably go down so take time to time out.\n\nnot to mention the sick shit mifune mentioned. Some people just have no decorum.',86439,'2012-09-07 23:52:34'),(47671,6083,85636,'2012-09-08 00:38:26','[quote=knickers,f3083,27670]I hate animated sigs. Its all fine until you load a thread with 50 posts or whatever each one with more and more elaborate sigs that take forever to load, especially with various hosts etc some of which invariably go down so take time to time out.\r\n\r\nnot to mention the sick shit mifune mentioned. Some people just have no decorum.[/quote]\r\n\r\nOr signatures that have a wallpaper sized images. I\'ve seen people who have 10 of them in there signature takes an age to load and if the server doesn\'t resize them properly......\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47672,5763,85636,'2012-09-08 00:44:51','TODO:\n\nUpdate webchat tut with screens of the new nickserv auth.\nRemove NickServ & Chanserv Sections and instead link to the IRC Network website.\nUpdate vhost stuff.\nRemove stuff about registering channels, and running them (as a founder).\nWrite a command list for the bot that makes sense. (also the announce channel bot?)\n\nprobably more.',85636,'2012-09-08 00:46:57'),(47673,6083,84499,'2012-09-08 00:46:26','well the xy resizing is down to the html... if any too large images are not constrained here its a bug!\r\n\r\nactual file size of the image... hmm.... actually I never did revisit the filesize restriction on images, maybe I will take a look at that.',NULL,NULL),(47674,6087,70679,'2012-09-08 01:14:03','Work in progress\n\nThis will be a simplified manual. There will also be a reference guide for more in depth documents. We are still trying to decide and moving things around.\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n[size=2][b]Bot commands.[/b][/size]\n\nFantasy commands allows you to use simple shortcuts in place of many of the NickServ, ChanServ, and BotServ commands. \n\n[b]Moderator Commands[/b]\n\n!INVITE\n Syntax: !INVITE\n \n  Invites \'nick\' to the channel if the user is present on the network.\n  N.B. This is the only way to invite someone to an official empornium channel.\n \n!UP\n Syntax: !UP [nick]\n \n Gives the user the modes he has rights to. This will unset modes if he has any\n the user has no access to.\n \n Note: A nick can only be specified by the founder of the channel or \n a Services Root Administrator.\n \n!DOWN\n Syntax: !DOWN [nick]\n\n Does the opposite of the !up command\n \n!KICK\n Syntax: !KICK [nick [reason]]\n \n Kick a user from the channel.\n \n!KB\n Syntax: {!KICKBAN | !KB} [nick!]ident@host] [reason]\n \n This will kick and ban the specified user or all users matching the given \n mask from the channel. If a mask is given and someone who should not be \n kicked according to the channels\' settings matches it, the command is \n aborted before anyone is kicked or banned.\n \n!TKB\n Syntax: !tkb or !tkban [nick | [nick!]ident@host] [time] [reason]\n \n This will kick and temporarily ban the specified user\n\n Also be aware that this command may not work with IPs for privacy reasons.\n\n If the time is not given or is invalid, it will default to 1 hour.\n The time should be given in the format <(s)/m/h/d>.\n \n Example: !tkb SillyTroll 10m Bye \n This command will kickban the user SillyTroll for 10 minutes.\n\n!BAN\n Syntax: !BAN [nick | mask]\n \n Bans user from the channel without kicking.\n \n!TBAN\n Syntax: {!TB | !TBAN} [nick | [nick!]ident@host] [time]\n \n This will ban the given nick or hostmask from the channel for the specified\n amount of time. If the time is not given, it will default to 1 hour.\n The time should be given in the format <(s)/m/h/d>.\n \n Example: !tb SillyTroll 10m \n This command will kickban the user SillyTroll for 10 minutes.\n \n Note: if services are restarted before the ban expires, the ban will\n not be automatically removed\n\n!UNBAN\n Syntax: !UNBAN [nick | [nick!]ident@host]\n \n  Removes the ban on a user.\n \n!MUTE\n Syntax: !MUTE  [nick | mask]\n \n Bans or mutes the given nickname or usermask from the channel.  \n See the Silencing Users with Extended Bans for more details.\n \n!UNMUTE\n Syntax: !UNMUTE  [nick | mask]\n \n Unbans or unmutes the given nickname or usermask from the channel.  \n See the Silencing Users with Extended Bans for more details.\n \n[b]Admin Commands[/b]\n\n!ACCESS\nÂ Syntax: !ACCESS add nick level\nÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â !ACCESS del {nick | entry-num | list}\nÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â !ACCESS list [mask | list]\nÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â !ACCESS clear\nÂ \nÂ Maintains the access list for a channel. Â The access\nÂ list specifies which users are allowed chanop status or\nÂ access to commands on the channel.\nÂ \nTo add a mod: !access add nickname 5\nTo add a FLS: !access add nickname 4\nTo add a user to to autovoice: !access add nickname 3\n\nN.B. only users who have registered can be added to the access lists.\n\n!AKICK\nÂ Syntax: !AKICK add {mask | user} [reason]\nÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â !AKICK {list | view} [mask]\nÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â !AKICK {enforce | clear}\nÂ \nÂ Maintains the channel auto-kick list (people who match this list will not be able to join the channel at all).\n\nExamples:\n!akick add GaryE bye\n!akick del Barumba\nÂ \n!TOPIC\nÂ Syntax: !TOPIC [topic]\n\nÂ Sets the channel topic. If no topic is given, the currentÂ \nÂ topic is displayed in the channel.\nÂ \nÂ The CTOPIC command clears the topic.\nÂ \n!TAPPEND\nÂ Syntax: {!TAPPEND Â | !APPENDTOPIC} Â text to be appended to topic\nÂ \nÂ Appends the given text to the channel\'s current topic. (only use if you need to add emergency information to the topic e.g. site going offline for a few days)\n\n[b]Announce Commands (only work in #empornium-announce)[/b]\n\n!EMPORNIUM\n Syntax: !EMPORNIUM\n \n Displays the last 5 torrents uploaded to torrents.empornium.me\n\n[b]Staff Commands (only work in #empornium-staff)[/b]\n\n@@\n Syntax: @@ [optional comment]\n \n Adds a hilight line to the staff IRC logs. To access the [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3065]logs check out this thread.[/url]\n\n!sitestatus\n Syntax: !sitestatus\n \n Uses isup.me to check the status of torrent.empornium.me\n\n[size=2][b]How to deal with annoying users.[/b][/size]\n\n[b]Simple Guide[/b]\n\nIf a user is being aggressive toward others, being a nuisance, disruptive, trolling, breaking rules, spamming in the channel and/or advertising excessively, give them a warning first. \n\nIf they persist use: \n\n!kick nickname <reason for kick>\n\nThis will kick t he user out of the channel once. He can come back right away. If they still continue use: \n\n!tkb nickname 1d \n\nThis will kick the user out of the channel and ban him for one day.\n\nif they evade the ban report it to either barumba, clownius, or MrRandom who will add a network wide ban.\n\nIf a user PM\'s you continually, direct them to an appropriate channel (e.g. #empornium-help, #empornium, etc). If they continue and you use a client use the /ignore feature which is included in all major clients. If you use the webchat message barumba, clownius or MrRandom who will disconnect the user from the network.\n\n[b]Silencing Users[/b]\n\nWhen you silence a user, you allow the person to stay in the channel, but block the personâ€™s ability to participate in the discussion or change nicks. Itâ€™s an online equivalent of a short timeout, where the person has to sit quietly for several minutes before rejoining discussion.\n\nTo silence a user, youâ€™d type:\n\n[quote]!mute nickname[/quote]\nThat command sets a bans, ~q:nick!ident@user.host which prevents the user from participating in the discussion (unless the user is +v or higher, this will be autoremoved when you use the command). The ~q stands for quiet.\n\nSilence Ban:\n\n[quote]!unmute nickname[/quote]\n\nEverything is the same. Youâ€™re just removing the ban.\n \n[b]Different banning options Senior staff ONLY (e.g IRC Operators)[/b]\n\nProceed with caution. If you are not sure consult the usual suspects.\n\n[b][u]KLine[/u][/b]\n\n[quote]Syntax: /KLINE [+|-]user@host | nick [time] <reason>\n \n  Example: /KLINE *@127.0.0.1 2d Abuse\n \n Bans the hostmask from the server it is issued on. A\n kline is not a global ban.   time to ban is\n either: a) a value in seconds, b) a time value, like\n \'1d\' is 1 day or c) \'0\' for permanent.  Time and reason\n are optional, if unspecified a ban time of 7 days and \'no reason\' are used.  \n To remove a kline use /kline -user@host[/quote]\n\n[b][u]GLine[/u][/b]\n\n[quote]Syntax: /GLINE [+|-]user@host | nick [time] <reason>\n\n  Example: /GLINE *@127.0.0.1 2d Abuse \n\n Adds a global ban to anyone that matches. See kline for\n more syntax info.      \n Use /gline -user@host to remove.[/quote]\n\n[b][u]ZLine[/u][/b]\n\n[quote]Syntax: /ZLINE [+|-]*@ip [time] <reason>\n\n Example: /ZLINE *@127.0.0.1 2d Abuse\n \n Bans an IP Address from the local server it is issued\n on (not global). See kline for more syntax info.  \n Use /zline -*@ip to remove.[/quote]\n\n[b][u]GZLine[/u][/b]\n\n[quote]Syntax: /GZLINE [+|-]*@ip [time] <reason>\n\n Example: /GZLINE *@127.0.0.1 2d Abuse\n \n Bans an IP Address from connecting to any server on the network.\n See kline for more syntax info.   \n Use /zline -*@ip to remove.[/quote]',85636,'2012-09-10 22:16:03'),(47675,6080,51063,'2012-09-08 19:07:17','Ahh ok I\'ve got you.  Yeah I can agree with that 100%  But really I am not going to argue for it.  But your points are very valid.',NULL,NULL),(47676,5763,51063,'2012-09-08 19:10:45','Post to make unread.',NULL,NULL),(47677,6087,85636,'2012-09-08 19:29:24','TODO:\n\n[s]Bot commands.[/s] Mostly done.\n[s]How to register, identify & use ssl. (copy from help page?)[/s]\n[s]How admin\'s can add people to auto-op & auto-halfop.[/s]\nHow to deal with annoying users. (needs senior approval)\n\n\n\n[hr]\nDelete this post when this thread is done',85636,'2012-09-10 21:57:41'),(47678,6061,85636,'2012-09-08 19:46:40','Shouldn\'t you also remove the IRC Key from the settings page, unless you\'re going to use it.',NULL,NULL),(47682,6087,70679,'2012-09-08 21:22:41','the first item is already covered in the staff guide...',NULL,NULL),(47683,6088,70679,'2012-09-08 21:26:16','I was wondering if there is one, will be one, should be one?\r\n\r\nSo that we can move for example all irc guides for staff only once done there and avoid they get either lost in the thread or have to sticky them. \r\n\r\nThe can be joined with other staff only guides etc...',NULL,NULL),(47684,6087,85636,'2012-09-08 21:36:07','Including !k, etc?',NULL,NULL),(47686,6087,70679,'2012-09-08 22:26:35','How to register, identify & use ssl. (copy from help page?) -> http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=2981',NULL,NULL),(47687,6087,85636,'2012-09-08 23:03:05','So the second item then.',NULL,NULL),(47689,6087,70679,'2012-09-09 00:13:44','second and third and probably more...',NULL,NULL),(47691,6089,85636,'2012-09-09 01:21:40','When I try to add an image via the quick select buttons ([img]http://www.digitalirc.org/rsz_screenshot.png[/img]) from the image host I added yesterday (www.digitalirc.org) to the whitelist. It comes up saying \"this is not an approved image host\", even though it is when I try to add it to my forum signature. I was able to manually add it by putting [code][img][/img][/code] around it.',85636,'2012-09-09 16:48:31'),(47692,6089,84499,'2012-09-09 16:25:01','\r\n\r\nwhat does \'via the quick buttons at the top\' mean?\r\n\r\n\r\nwhat was the image url from that host?\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47693,6089,84499,'2012-09-09 16:49:36','\n[img]http://www.digitalirc.org/rsz_screenshot.png[/img]\n\n:dunno: works for me\n',84499,'2012-09-09 16:59:37'),(47695,6089,84499,'2012-09-09 19:42:38','\r\n\r\nThis is a good example of why detailed bug reports are needed.\r\n\r\nThe error you mean is \"Not a valid image url\" - more different thank you think to \"not an approved host\".\r\n\r\nWithout the actual url and a step by step guide to reproduce the error message its very difficult to know what the problem is.\r\n\r\nOnce you gave me the url that was giving you the error message : http://www.digitalirc.org/tools/recycledcounter/?chan=empornium it was a quick diagnosis...\r\n\r\nThis error has nothing to do with the imagehost, its a problem with the regex in the javascript used to check if the format of an image url is valid.\r\n\r\nto reproduce - try using an image url from a valid imagehost without any file extension specificed : ie. without .jpeg/.jpg/,png etc but also without a page extension either, so no .php/,html/.cgi in the address either. That is what causes the error.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47696,6089,84499,'2012-09-09 20:58:22',' \r\nfixed.',NULL,NULL),(47705,6091,70679,'2012-09-10 21:47:10','Work in progress\n\nThis will be a reference manual for more in depth documents. There will also be a simplified guide. We are still trying to decide and moving things around.\n\n[hr]\n\n[bg=grey,50%,left][color=white][size=4][align=center][b]Contents[/b][/align][/size][/color]\n\n[bg=white,97%]\n\n[bg=100%]\n[b][size=3][u]Sections[/u][/size][/b]\n\n[bg=grey,98%,center]\n[url=#bot][size=3][align=left][u]Bot Commands[/u][/align][/size][/url]\n[bg=white,96%]\n[align=left][url=#bot-general]Genreal Bot Commands[/url]\n[url=#bot-access]Access Bot Commands[/url]\n[url=#bot-channel]Channel Action Commands[/url]\n[url=#bot-mode]Channel Modes Commands[/url]\n[url=#bot-emp]Empornium Specific Commands[/url][/align]\n\n[/bg]\n\n[/bg]\n\n[url=#link1]example link for this document[/url]\n\n[/bg]\n\n[/bg]\n\n[/bg]\n\n[#=bot][/#][u][b]Full list of bot commands[/b][/u]\n\n[#=bot-general][/#][b]General Commands[/b]\n\n!HELP\n Syntax: !HELP\n\n Help for BotServ fantasy commands\n\n!CMDLIST\n Syntax: !CMDLIST\n\n  A list of all available fantasy commands\n\n!IRCOPS\n Syntax: !IRCOPS\n\n  Shows a list of all available global IRCops in the Status Window (It will not show empornium staff)\n\n!STAFF\n Syntax: !STAFF\n\n  Shows a list of all available global IRCops in the Status Window (It will not show empornium staff)\n\n!INFO\n Syntax: !INFO [ALL]\n\n  Shows information about the channel. \n The \'all\' option is limited to founders and Services Admins.\n\n[#=bot-access][/#][b]Access Control Commands[/b]\n\n!ACCESS\n Syntax: !ACCESS add nick level\n         !ACCESS del {nick | entry-num | list}\n         !ACCESS list [mask | list]\n         !ACCESS clear\n\n Maintains the access list for a channel.  The access\n list specifies which users are allowed chanop status or\n access to commands on the channel.\n\n Different user levels allow for access to different subsets of\n privileges; cf. /msg ChanServ HELP ACCESS LEVELS for more specific \n information. Any nick not on the access list has a user level of 0.\n\n!LEVELS\n Syntax: !LEVELS set type level\n         !LEVELS {dis | disable} type\n         !LEVELS list\n         !LEVELS reset\n\n The LEVELS command allows fine control over the meaning of\n the numeric access levels used for the channel.  With this command,\n you can define the access level required for most administrative functions.\n (The SET FOUNDER and SET PASSWORD commands, as well as this command, \n are always restricted to the channel founder.) \n\n LEVELS SET allows the access level for a function or group of \n functions to be changed.\n\n LEVELS DISABLE (or DIS for short) disables an automatic\n feature or disallows access to a function by anyone other \n than the channel founder.\n\n LEVELS LIST shows the current levels for each function or group\n  of functions.\n\n LEVELS RESET resets the levels to the default levels of a \n newly-created channel.\n\n (See /msg ChanServ HELP ACCESS LEVELS for more info.)\n\n For a list of the features and functions whose levels can be\n set, see HELP LEVELS DESC.\n\n[b]Channel Setting Commands[/b]\n\n!AKICK\n Syntax: !AKICK add {mask | user} [reason]\n         !AKICK {stick | unstick | del} mask\n         !AKICK {list | view} [mask]\n         !AKICK {enforce | clear}\n\n Maintains the channel AKICK list. See the ChanServ AKICK command for more details.\n\n!SET\n Syntax: !SET option parameters\n\n Changes channel\'s settings. \n\n Available options:\n See the ChanServ SET command for more details on the following:\n   founder       -  Set the founder of a channel\n   successor     -  Set the successor for a channel\n   desc          -  Set the channel description\n   url           -  Associate a URL with the channel\n   email         -  Associate an E-mail address with the channel\n   entrymsg      -  Set a message to be sent to users when they enter the \n                    channel\n   bantype       -  Set how Services make bans on the channel\n   mlock         -  Lock channel modes on or off\n   keeptopic     -  Retain topic when channel is not in use\n   topiclock     -  Topic can only be changed with TOPIC\n   opnotice      -  Send a notice when OP/DEOP commands are used\n   peace         -  Regulate the use of critical commands\n   private       -  Hide channel from LIST command\n   restricted    -  restrict access to the channel\n   secure        -  activate services\' security features\n   secureops     -  stricter control of chanop status\n   securefounder -  stricter control of channel founder status\n   signkick      -  Sign kicks that are done with KICK command\n   xop           -  Toggle the user privilege system\n\n See the BotServ SET command for more details on the following:\n   noexpire      -  Sets whether the given channel will expire. \n                    (limited to SA)\n   dontkickops   -  Protect channel ops against kicks by the services bot.\n   dontkickvoices - Protect voices against kicks by the services bot.\n   greet         -  Enable greet messages on join.\n   fantasy       -  Enable fantasy commands on the channel.\n   symbiosis     -  Allow the bot to act as a real bot.\n   nobot         -  Prevents a bot from being assigned to this channel. \n                    (limited to SA)\n\n!BKICK\n Syntax: !BKICK option {on | off} [ttb [params]]\n\n See the BotServ SET command for more details on the following options:\n\n   bolds       -  Sets whether the bot kicks bolds.\n   badwords    -  Sets whether the bots kicks for words in  \n                  the badwords list.\n   caps        -  Sets whether the bot kicks for CAPS.\n   colors      -  Sets whether the bot kicks for colors.\n   flood       -  Sets whether the bot kicks for floods.\n   repeat      -  Sets whether the bot kicks for repeats.\n   reverses    -  Sets whether the bot kicks for reverses.\n   underlines  -  Sets whether the bot kicks for underlines.\n\n ttb is the number of times a user can be kicked before he gets banned.\n Don\'t give ttb to disable the ban system once activated.\n\n[#=bot-channel][/#][b]Channel Action Commands[/b]\n\n!CLEAR\n Syntax: !CLEAR {modes | bans | excepts | invites | ops | hops | voices | users}\n\n Clears the specified option on the channel. \n See the ChanServ CLEAR command for more details.\n\n!TOPIC\n Syntax: !TOPIC [topic]\n         !CTOPIC\n Sets the channel topic. If no topic is given, the current \n topic is displayed in the channel.\n\n The CTOPIC command clears the topic.\n\n This command is most useful in conjunction with SET TOPICLOCK \n\n See the ChanServ TOPIC command for more details.\n\n!TAPPEND\n Syntax: {!TAPPEND  | !APPENDTOPIC}  text to be appended to topic\n\n Appends the given text to the channel\'s current topic.\n This command is most useful in conjunction with SET TOPICLOCK\n\n!INVITE\n Syntax: !INVITE\n\n  Invites \'nick\' to the channel if the user is present on the network.\n\n!UP\n Syntax: !UP\n\n Gives the user the modes he has rights to. This will unset modes if he has any\n the user has no access to.\n\n Note: A nick can only be specified by the founder of the channel or \n a Services Root Administrator.\n\n!DOWN\n Syntax: !DOWN [nick] [level]\n\n Unsets all modes. If the channel is moderated, it will reset voice,\n unless issued on another user by a founder. It is also possible\n to specify a target level. \n\n The target level can be any one of the following:\n\n    - q - Channel founder (modes +qo) (IRCd Dependant)\n    - a - Protected Operator / Administrator (modes +ao) (IRCd Dependant)\n    - o - Channel Operator (mode +o)\n    - h - Channel Halfop (mode +h) (IRCd Dependant)\n    - v - \\\"Voice\\\" (mode +v)\n\n If a target level is specified, the users\' current privileges will be  \n replaced by the target one.\n\n!KICK\n Syntax: !KICK [nick [reason]]\n\n Kick a user from the channel.\n See the ChanServ KICK command for more details.\n\n!KB\n Syntax: {!KICKBAN | !KB} [nick!]ident@host] [reason]\n\n This will kick and ban the specified user or all users matching the given \n mask from the channel. If a mask is given and someone who should not be \n kicked according to the channels\' settings matches it, the command is \n aborted before anyone is kicked or banned.\n\n!TKB\n Syntax: !tkb or !tkban [nick | [nick!]ident@host] [time] [reason]\n\n This will kick and temporarily ban the specified user or all users matching\n the given mask from the channel for the specified amount of time. \n\n If a mask is given and someone who should not be banned according to the\n channels\' settings matches it, the command is aborted before anyone is \n kicked.\n\n Also be aware that this command may not work with IPs for privacy reasons.\n\n If the time is not given or is invalid, it will default to 1 hour.\n The time should be given in the format <(s)/m/h/d>.\n\n Example: !tkb SillyTroll 10m Bye \n This command will kickban the user SillyTroll for 10 minutes.\n\n Note: if Services are restarted before the ban expires, the ban will\n not be automatically removed.\n\n[#=bot-mode][/#][b]Channel Modes Commands[/b]\n\n!BAN\n Syntax: !BAN [nick | mask]\n\n Bans (a) user(s)/mask from the channel without kicking.\n\n!TBAN\n Syntax: {!TB | !TBAN} [nick | [nick!]ident@host] [time]\n\n This will ban the given nick or hostmask from the channel for the specified\n amount of time. If the time is not given, it will default to 1 hour.\n The time should be given in the format <(s)/m/h/d>.\n\n Example: !tb SillyTroll 10m \n This command will kickban the user SillyTroll for 10 minutes.\n\n Note: if services are restarted before the ban expires, the ban will\n not be automatically removed\n\n!UNBAN\n Syntax: !UNBAN [nick | [nick!]ident@host]\n\n  Removes the ban on a user.\n\n!MUTE\n Syntax: !MUTE  [nick | mask]\n\n Bans or mutes the given nickname or usermask from the channel.  \n See the Silencing Users with Extended Bans for more details.\n\n!UNMUTE\n Syntax: !UNMUTE  [nick | mask]\n\n Unbans or unmutes the given nickname or usermask from the channel.  \n See the Silencing Users with Extended Bans for more details.\n\n!OP\n Syntax: !OP  [nick]\n\n Op yourself or another user.  See the ChanServ OP command \n for more details.\n\n!DEOP\n Syntax: !DEOP  [nick]\n\n Deop yourself or another user.  See the ChanServ OP command \n for more details.\n\n!VOICE\n Syntax: !VOICE [nick]\n\n Voice yourself or another user. See the ChanServ VOICE command \n for more details.\n\n!DEVOICE\n Syntax: !DEVOICE [nick]\n\n Devoice yourself or another user. See the ChanServ DEVOICE command \n for more details.\n\n!PROTECT\n Syntax: !PROTECT [nick]\n\n Protect yourself or another user (so you cannot be kicked). See \n the ChanServ PROTECT command for more details.\n\n!DEPROTECT\n Syntax: !DEPROTECT [nick]\n\n Remove protection from  yourself or another user. See the \n ChanServ DEPROTECT command for more details.\n\n!OWNER\n Syntax: !OWNER\n\n Give yourself the owner mode. See the ChanServ OWNER command \n for more details.\n\n!DEOWNER\n Syntax: !DEOWNER\n\n Remove the owner mode. See the ChanServ DEOWNER command for \n more details.\n\n!HALFOP\n Syntax: !HALFOP [nick]\n\n Halfop yourself or another user. See the ChanServ HALFOP command \n for more details.\n\n!DEHALFOP\n Syntax: !DEHALFOP [nick]\n\n Dehalfop yourself or another user. See the ChanServ DEHALFOP command \n for more details.\n\n[#=bot-emp][/#][b][u]Empornium Specific Commandsu[/u][/b]\n\n[b]Announce Commands[/b] (only work in #empornium-announce)\n\n!EMPORNIUM\nSyntax: !EMPORNIUM\n\nDisplays the last 5 torrents uploaded to torrents.empornium.me\n\n[b]Staff Commands[/b] (only work in #empornium-staff)\n\n@@\nSyntax: @@ [optional comment]\n\nAdds a hilight line to the staff IRC logs. To access the logs check out this thread.\n\n!sitestatus\nSyntax: !sitestatus\n\nUses isup.me to check the status of torrent.empornium.me',85636,'2012-09-10 22:48:52'),(47706,6088,84499,'2012-09-11 01:59:08','\r\nI have added a permission level for articles, you need the level specified to view or edit the article.\r\n\r\nI added a new sub category \'staff\' which I suggest is only used for non-user articles, they will still need a category but I think it will probably work best like this with a staff subcategory under help (or rules if appropriate). Non user articles can still be in other sub categories and they will work the same - only users with the appropriate class level will be able to see them.\r\n\r\nThere is no way atm for FLS to be able to view staff rated articles... I could add a permission setting that allows for this if needed.',NULL,NULL),(47707,6088,70679,'2012-09-11 02:20:21','Thanks a bunch Mifune that is great! OK created the first one.',NULL,NULL),(47723,6093,70679,'2012-09-11 20:27:01','using the code bbcode to show u below adds one space.\r\n\r\n[o]\r\n[a]\r\n[q]\r\n[code][u][/code]',NULL,NULL),(47724,6093,84499,'2012-09-11 20:40:08','[quote=barumba,f3093,27723]using the code bbcode to show u below adds one space.\r\n\r\n[o]\r\n[a]\r\n[q]\r\n[code][u][/code][/quote]\r\n\r\nthats not a space, its just that the code element has a little padding - otherwise the off white bg is flush with the edge of the text which dosent look all that great in most uses.\r\n\r\nin practical terms I would format the above text as \r\n[code][o]\r\n[a]\r\n[q]\r\n[u][/code]\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(47739,6094,73595,'2012-09-12 09:21:16','deluge appears to be banned, why?',NULL,NULL),(47740,6094,152838,'2012-09-12 09:29:03','http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3078',NULL,NULL),(47741,6094,94804,'2012-09-12 10:34:40','hahaha stupid me, I thougt that was a user, I was just about to post why a link to banned/allowed clients when I realised.',NULL,NULL),(47744,6095,184601,'2012-09-12 14:17:19','When I tried to test disabling IRC for my account (like you would when you leech warn or upload disable), which somehow caused the account to be lost.',184601,'2012-09-12 15:29:41'),(47746,6095,51063,'2012-09-12 15:51:51','Yes your MrRandom account has been completely deleted.  Interesting feature!  So we can delete accounts!  But you can only do it by disabling IRC access for that account . . . do I have that right?  I would test it . . . but it does not seem prudent.\r\n\r\nHmm maybe the deletion shows up in the site log . . . need to check there.\r\n\r\nNope I do not see the deletion in any of the logs I looked at.  There must be a log which mifune can look at which I can not see where the deletion might at least show up.  That would give us something to go on.',NULL,NULL),(47747,6095,184601,'2012-09-12 15:53:49','[quote=GaryE,f3095,27746]Yes your MrRandom account has been completely deleted.  Interesting feature!  So we can delete accounts!  But you can only do it by disabling IRC access for that account . . . do I have that right?  I would test it . . . but it does not seem prudent.\n\nHmm maybe the deletion shows up in the site log . . . need to check there.\n\nNope I do not see the deletion in any of the logs I looked at.  There must be a log which mifune can look at which I can not see where the deletion might at least show up.  That would give us something to go on.[/quote]\n\nWell it apparently can\'t be replicated.....\n\n ',84499,'2012-09-12 16:13:44'),(47748,6095,84499,'2012-09-12 16:13:07','\r\n :panic: \r\n\r\nno you cannot delete accounts by disabling the IRC .',NULL,NULL),(47749,6095,184601,'2012-09-12 16:15:18','[quote=mifune,f3095,27748]:panic: \r\n\r\nno you cannot delete accounts by disabling the IRC .[/quote]\r\n\r\nTheres just a random bug that fucks up the account.',NULL,NULL),(47750,6095,84499,'2012-09-12 16:15:57','\r\n\r\nAnd his account was not deleted... lol.\r\n\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(47752,6095,85636,'2012-09-12 16:18:34','[quote=mifune,f3095,27750]And his account was not deleted... lol.[/quote]\r\nJust rather hard to find.',NULL,NULL),(47753,6095,84499,'2012-09-12 16:20:16','\r\n\r\nwell its not \'random\' in the sense it could happen at any time....\r\n\r\nthere appears to be a bug in the takemoderate page somewhere but its not easy to replicate. Not easy at all...\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47755,6094,84499,'2012-09-12 16:24:02','\r\ntell us what version of deluge you want to use and we will add it. (in this thread: http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3078)',NULL,NULL),(47761,6095,51063,'2012-09-12 19:35:47','Hmm interesting.  I did search for his account and it did not show up . . . odd.   But ok it sounds like you have a handle on it.  ',NULL,NULL),(47763,6095,85636,'2012-09-12 19:45:29','[quote=GaryE,f3095,27761]Hmm interesting.  I did search for his account and it did not show up . . . odd.   But ok it sounds like you have a handle on it.[/quote]\r\n\r\nWell considering it did this:\r\nClass changed to , username changed from MrRandom to , title changed to , Freeleech Tokens changed from 10019 to 0, Personal Freeleech changed from 6 days, 23 hours to none, Bonus Credits changed from 7834136.50 to 0, number of invites changed to 0, first-line support status changed to , IRC status changed, account Enabled->Unconfirmed\r\n\r\nIn other words 0\'d everything.',NULL,NULL),(47764,6095,51063,'2012-09-12 20:11:10','Wow!  That would explain why I could not find it LOL',NULL,NULL),(47767,6094,73595,'2012-09-12 21:36:34','apparently i was using an old version (1.3.1) and that was the last stable one until the new builds in 2012.  i updated and it works, so thank you for adding it or i am sorry i was not updated and missed the other thread.',73595,'2012-09-12 21:37:03'),(47769,6095,84499,'2012-09-12 22:45:40','Somehow the code that processes any changes on the user page got sent the page but without any data filled in, so all the variables are there just empty... that then gets processed as a valid staff action (so it must be whilst a staff is looking at the page and presses the submit button).\n\nIt may be as simple as a double-click with immaculate timing + a server burp or something... or maybe even just a server burp, where it somehow loses all the post data and you get an array with empty values (but not an empty array... hmmm).\n\nI have no idea what is causing it - I dont think it is user error either, theres no way to deliberately cause it even. I have been unable to replicate it in any way.\n\nI have however added an error trap in the code that processes the user page actions - if a blank username or class is passed it will error out and send the admins a data dump and not make any changes - hopefully this will prevent it happening again and although I cannot test it I think it will work.',84499,'2012-09-12 22:48:38'),(47771,6095,51063,'2012-09-13 03:51:34','Sounds like a good plan mifune . . . I hope you are right and it does work . . . It really sounds like it should.   Nice job!',NULL,NULL),(47780,6095,47234,'2012-09-13 14:40:08','Gotta love those random oopsies that happen :lol:',NULL,NULL),(47782,6094,47234,'2012-09-13 15:05:36','Well it shows the whitelist is working at least :lol:',NULL,NULL),(47788,6096,94804,'2012-09-14 12:28:55','hi, I wanted to post a video but in \"preview\" it only showed the url as text , and after posting it just remained blank. So I tried url but then it shows the url instead of the word linking to it. See what I mean at \"last person to post wins\".using latest Chrome, win7 64bit',NULL,NULL),(47790,6096,51063,'2012-09-14 15:51:10','try the video tag [video=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ#t=0m9s] [code][video=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ#t=0m9s][/code]\n\n',51063,'2012-09-14 15:55:12'),(47791,6096,94952,'2012-09-14 16:18:01','Looks like anonym.to are tripping upp the bb-code.\n[video=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ#t=0m9s]\n[video=http://anonym.to/?http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ#t=0m9s]\n[url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ#t=0m9s]winning[/url] \n[url=http://anonym.to/?http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ#t=0m9s]winning[/url]\nCode used:\n[code][video=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ#t=0m9s]\n[video=http://anonym.to/?http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ#t=0m9s]\n[url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ#t=0m9s]winning[/url] \n[url=http://anonym.to/?http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ#t=0m9s]winning[/url][/code]',94952,'2012-09-14 16:18:31'),(47793,6096,94804,'2012-09-14 17:07:52','yeah, it works if not anonymized, though deeplinking doesn\'t work with video. I wanted to start the movie at 9 sec. in hence the #t0m9s attached to the link, can that be fixed?',NULL,NULL),(47795,6096,51063,'2012-09-14 23:40:30','That is a question for someone other than me LOL',NULL,NULL),(47796,6096,94952,'2012-09-15 00:04:44','Looks like all links posted on the board gets the anonym.to link added automaticly. Probably why doing it manually won\'t work. Mifune probably knows for certain, I\'m just guessing.\r\n\r\nLooks like anonym.to are stripping start time info from the link. I tried pasting the http://anonym.to/?http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ#t=0m9s in a new tab and it stripped off #t=0m9s',NULL,NULL),(47797,6096,84499,'2012-09-15 02:14:21','\r\nyeah anon.to is automatically added to external links.\r\n\r\nanon.to links dont like stuff after the hash - but thats not the issue with the youtube links. I am not even sure you can embed a yt link with a time to start on it :hmmm: I\'ll have a look and see if its possible.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47798,6096,94804,'2012-09-15 08:44:14','[quote=mifune,f3096,27797]yeah anon.to is automatically added to external links.[/quote]\r\nOow, didn\'t know that.',NULL,NULL),(47811,6096,84499,'2012-09-18 10:05:24','\r\nokay after an extremely minimal amount of research (ie. the first hit on google for \'embedding youtube videos start time\'... im just saying  :smartass:)\r\n\r\nyou just need to use the correct format for embedded video rather than the format for the direct url. \r\n\r\nSo:\r\n\r\n[code][video=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ&start=9][/code]\r\n\r\nnote the important bit is you add \"&start=x\" where x= the number of seconds you want it to start at.\r\n\r\n[video=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pipTwjwrQYQ&start=9]',NULL,NULL),(47812,6097,84499,'2012-09-18 10:15:13','You can no longer use an image for your avatar that is more than 300x500 in size. \n\nAvatars are resized to a max of 150x250 (for pimps, less for others) so I think thats a reasonable limit?\n\nplease test, and I guess if you have objections to the restriction you can let us know but I am unlikely to be swayed :lol:\n\n\nOh and theoretically we will be restricting filesize of avatar images to max 512kb but right now that code only works on my local mirror  :sorry: \n\n\nOh and I guess I should point out that this check is only done when you submit your user settings to be saved - in other words it doesn\'t check existing avatars automatically only when something on that page is changed - which will no doubt need to be explained if we are going to copy over all the avatars when we do the transfer (I assume we will keep this... its not practical to check avatar images when we do the db transfer so if we wanted to check everyone\'s existing avatar I will need to write a script that loops thru all the users and does it but its probably not practical, so we could nuke all the avatars on transfer and therefore make users explicitly set it and force a check that way.. anyway i digress... just something to think about for transfer)\n',84499,'2012-09-18 10:53:53'),(47813,6097,67255,'2012-09-18 10:30:58','Will test',NULL,NULL),(47814,6097,84499,'2012-09-18 10:54:11','\r\nupdated OP with real dimensions instead of guessed ones lol',NULL,NULL),(47815,6097,94952,'2012-09-18 11:20:29','Works as intended. I could not link to a big picture (1600x1200) but a smaller one worked great.\r\n\r\nOne tiny thing to fix is the dimensions on the settings page says: \r\nMaximum Size: 125x125 pixels (will be resized if necessary)\r\n\r\nNeeds to be updated to the new values. \r\n',NULL,NULL),(47816,6097,84499,'2012-09-18 11:23:54','\r\n\r\nno what it says is true. that is the size it will be displayed at, its different for the different user classes.\r\n\r\nthe max dimensions check is for the source image, but its then resized on the page. ',NULL,NULL),(47817,6097,94952,'2012-09-18 11:27:42','Ahh.. I checked a few avatars but I found no 125x125 ones. But I didn\'t check my own avatar. D\'oh!\r\n\r\nWell then Works as intended. Good job!!',NULL,NULL),(47818,6097,51063,'2012-09-18 14:02:00','It successfully blocked my avatar . . . it seems to be working well.',NULL,NULL),(47819,6098,84499,'2012-09-18 15:50:22','\r\n\r\nYou can buy universal freeleech (freeleech for everyone forever) for one of your own torrents in the bonus shop.\r\n\r\n\r\nplease test.',NULL,NULL),(47820,6098,48010,'2012-09-18 17:23:31','doesnt work for me\r\n\r\nget error message [quote]TorrentID was not set[/quote]',NULL,NULL),(47821,6098,94952,'2012-09-18 19:02:32','Worked for me on [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35209&torrentid=30075]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35209&torrentid=30075[/url]\n\nI also tried breaking the system and it blocked me nicely with good error messages. \nAlso confirmed FL. The filelist has recorded me DLing 130 Mb but my stats stay the same.\n',94952,'2012-09-18 19:05:35'),(47822,6098,84499,'2012-09-18 19:36:46','[quote=Dave,f3098,27820]doesnt work for me\n\nget error message [quote]TorrentID was not set[/quote][/quote]\n\nIn theory you should only get that message if you entered a blank value, entered 0, or pressed cancel.\n\n\nEDIT: I changed it a bit so if you cancel or enter a blank value it wont process it. If you enter text that isn\'t a number you should still get a TorrentID was not set message.',84499,'2012-09-18 20:04:34'),(47824,6098,49532,'2012-09-19 00:56:53','\n\nI tested it on http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35200&torrentid=30066\n\nWhen I tried it, entering the 30066. I got the error:\n[quote]You are not the owner of torrent ID=30066 - only the uploader can buy Universal Freeleech for their torrent[/quote]\n\n\nEdit:\n\nWhen I entered 35200 it worked.  There needs to be better clarification on which number needs entering.',49532,'2012-09-19 01:05:54'),(47826,6098,48010,'2012-09-19 15:55:53','[quote=apparition,f3098,27824]I tested it on http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?id=35200&torrentid=30066\r\n\r\nWhen I tried it, entering the 30066. I got the error:\r\n[quote]You are not the owner of torrent ID=30066 - only the uploader can buy Universal Freeleech for their torrent[/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nEdit:\r\n\r\nWhen I entered 35200 it worked.  There needs to be better clarification on which number needs entering.[/quote]\r\n\r\nsame here - used the last number = fail\r\nused the first number = success\r\n\r\nfor mifunes info last night i was tired and entered the whole url hence the error LOL',NULL,NULL),(47828,6098,84499,'2012-09-19 18:04:58','\r\n\r\nI added an example in the prompt dialog - hopefully should be a little clearer now.',NULL,NULL),(47829,6099,84499,'2012-09-19 18:12:08','\r\n\r\nIdeally I would have added an \'unlimited\' PFL option - but it would require making a change to the tracker side of the PFL thing.\r\n\r\nSo instead I have added a 10yr PFL option... \r\n\r\nI also rejigged the PFL bar so it takes up less room in the header.',NULL,NULL),(47831,6099,51063,'2012-09-19 18:56:35','seems like it works !  Yeah pfl for 10 years!',NULL,NULL),(47832,6099,94952,'2012-09-19 20:01:25','Im guessing this is a Staff option/tool. I couldn\'t find it and it makes more sense as a stafftool',NULL,NULL),(47833,6099,84499,'2012-09-19 20:42:53','\r\n\r\nOh yes thats true. Although if you buy a 24hr PFL (personal freeleech) slot in the bonus shop you will see the same PFL bar.',NULL,NULL),(47834,6099,94952,'2012-09-19 22:08:47','Loving the new bar!',NULL,NULL),(47836,6099,49532,'2012-09-20 01:18:43','[quote=The average Empornium dipshit]What the [color=#FF3300][b]fuck[/b][/color] does PFL mean???[/quote]\n\nI think the bar should say Freeleech not PFL',49532,'2012-09-20 01:20:19'),(47837,6099,84499,'2012-09-20 02:09:37','On the other hand its called PFL on emp.me, and I like it shorter in the header bar. I changed the bonus shop item to say PFL and then Personal FreeLeech to make it clearer (users will only see the bar if they buy it in the shop). ',84499,'2012-09-20 02:10:35'),(47838,6100,150658,'2012-09-20 07:09:44','I was looking at the forums or the homepage (I don\'t remember which) and when I clicked on my username to look at my profile, a popup came up with \"!!\" in it.  I haven\'t been able to replicate this again, but if I do, I\'ll post how to get it.\r\n\r\nHas anyone else had this happen to them?',NULL,NULL),(47839,6100,84499,'2012-09-20 09:28:48','\r\nwhoops.\r\n\r\nleft that in (i was debugging something) the code when you first set a cookie on the user page... fixed now.',NULL,NULL),(47840,6100,86439,'2012-09-20 09:37:48','I just got it by clicking my user name next to settings.\n\nIt doesnt repeat though when i click it subsequently.',86439,'2012-09-20 09:38:53'),(47841,6098,86439,'2012-09-20 09:43:27','Works fine for me too.',NULL,NULL),(47842,6100,84499,'2012-09-20 09:59:57','\r\nyeah well I hadnt actually uploaded the change 20 mins ago ;)\r\n\r\n\r\nwe are having some server issues... its updated now though. \r\n\r\nIf you want to properly test if its fixed delete the cookie for emp.mooo called \'userPageState\' and then go to your user profile (or any user profile) and if its fixed it wont give you the silly alert.',NULL,NULL),(47844,6099,51063,'2012-09-20 15:47:03','[quote=Mobbo,f3099,27834]Loving the new bar![/quote]\r\n\r\nAt least you can see it for a few days ;-)',NULL,NULL),(47845,6098,48010,'2012-09-20 17:20:38','[quote=mifune,f3098,27828]I added an example in the prompt dialog - hopefully should be a little clearer now.[/quote]\r\nthat\'s clear - thanks',NULL,NULL),(47847,6101,171777,'2012-09-21 13:01:00','Tested this by pm-ing between my own account and drkness_testy but also noticed this while sending PM to Mifune.\r\n\r\nProblem: If someone send a PM you can reply with no problem. However as soon as the original sender recieves the reply he is no longer able to reply to that himself. Ergo the problem is when replying to a reply. This 2nd reply also does not appear in the PM sent box.\r\n\r\nTested: Sent messages from both DrkNess and DrkNess_Testy to each other. Neither one had a problem with replying the others message but both were unable to perform the above described 2nd PM.\r\nWhen sending messages to Mifune I encountered the exact same problem but the difference in this case is that there was a longer period between receiving a message and sending the 2nd reply',NULL,NULL),(47848,6101,84499,'2012-09-21 14:54:21','\r\naha... now I see it.\r\n\r\nyeah the replyto id is getting messed up (you end up sending to yourself which doesnt work out so good).\r\n\r\n\r\nthanks for the bug report  :D\r\n\r\n\r\n(oh and send us whatever you were trying to send me as a new pm)',NULL,NULL),(47849,6101,84499,'2012-09-21 16:01:28','\r\n\r\n\r\nI think I fixed it... definitely needs testing lol.',NULL,NULL),(47852,6078,51063,'2012-09-21 21:55:30','please add the latest version of Vuze 4.7.2.0',NULL,NULL),(47853,6100,86439,'2012-09-21 23:53:41','logged out, deleted cookie, logged in, checked profile no popup.',NULL,NULL),(47854,6078,84499,'2012-09-22 14:56:42','added',NULL,NULL),(47856,6078,51063,'2012-09-22 19:01:50','It works fine . . . thanks mate!',NULL,NULL),(47858,6078,94804,'2012-09-23 19:52:12','',94804,'2012-09-23 19:52:39'),(47859,6102,94804,'2012-09-23 19:59:46','occurs here as well as on emp.me\r\nI tried deleting multiple posts [url=http://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=3713]here[/url], but over there it says something like \"cannot post: your post is empty\" over here it just posts an empty message. Can\'t a \"delete\"-button be added \'cause how else can I delete dupes?',NULL,NULL),(47860,6102,84499,'2012-09-23 20:32:16','\r\n\r\nthere is a delete button but only staff can delete posts. this is deliberate!\r\n\r\n\r\nif you want a post nuked report your post and ask for it to be deleted.\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47865,6102,94804,'2012-09-24 13:36:29','oow, but why is that?',NULL,NULL),(47866,6102,47234,'2012-09-24 13:41:14','Because it makes us staff feel important.  \r\n\r\nMost forums only allow staff to delete posts.  Nothing like a user starting a war and then deleting the post that started it just to confuse the situation and get someone else in trouble/banned.  Otherwise you start talking logs and multiple edits being saved and yeah more trouble than its worth IMO to let users delete posts.',NULL,NULL),(47868,6102,94804,'2012-09-24 20:21:42','yeah, true\n\nThat\'s good reason, but last night I thought of big loophole, I can still edit it deleting the content and replacing it with a single symbol, or is that why the 5-min-to-edit is in effect on the new site?\n\ntest',94804,'2012-10-06 12:18:05'),(47874,6103,49532,'2012-09-25 22:17:03','When changing the class of a torrent table row to redbar, the disk Icon in wrong place.\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=17E2_50622CA7][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=17E2_50622CA7[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(47877,6104,94804,'2012-09-26 18:12:00','I just thought of something, can someone demote me, and make sure my ratio is 0, to test how stuff works for potential \"0\'s\"',NULL,NULL),(47878,6103,49532,'2012-09-26 20:14:37','[quote=apparition,f3103,27874]When changing the class of a torrent table row to redbar, the disk Icon in wrong place.\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=17E2_50622CA7][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=17E2_50622CA7[/img][/url][/quote]\r\n\r\n\r\nNot a bug; Cassie put [b]class=\"redbar\"[/b], instead of [b]class=\"torrent redbar\"[/b]in Firebug',NULL,NULL),(47879,6104,51063,'2012-09-26 22:13:53','Done!\n\n---- Edit \nI also removed your badges  so you pretty much have a virgin account (other than your bonus credits and your slots)',51063,'2012-09-26 22:15:12'),(47888,6078,49532,'2012-09-27 19:13:55','Transmission 2.7.1 \r\n\r\nWhy do individual versions need to be whitelisted? Can\'t you whitelist an app, and blacklist only the bad versions?',NULL,NULL),(47890,6078,51063,'2012-09-27 21:12:07','Almost every version of Transmission is a bad version . . . or will eventually be proved to be LOL\r\n\r\nNo there is no blacklist function . . it is only a white list.',NULL,NULL),(47894,6078,84499,'2012-09-28 07:37:55','I added transmission 2.71',NULL,NULL),(47896,6103,84499,'2012-09-28 07:52:57','\r\n\r\nsweet, self fixing bugs!\r\n\r\n:)\r\n\r\n ',NULL,NULL),(47897,6104,84499,'2012-09-28 07:53:28','\r\n\r\nthanks guys.',NULL,NULL),(47898,6105,84499,'2012-09-28 12:22:30','Things inbetween us and getting the new site online:\n\n[b]1) The ocelot code.[/b] The tracker code has a couple of issues, one minor, one very annoying. \nMinor issue: the tracker does not update the peerlist data very often.\nMajor issue: the tracker always reports a peers status as connectable regardless of real status.\nDrkNess has the ocelot code and I am hopeful he will be able to sort this.\n\n[b]2) Various content bits.[/b] [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3061]See this *TODO* thread for details[/url]\nMaybe I will end up doing this stuff, but I would be happier if I didn\'t. Probably we need to light a fire under the rest of the staff, I kind of ran out of steam trying to engage others to produce the content.\n\n[b]3) An open beta week.[/b] We cannot do this until we have a plan we are comfortable with. Also I will want to do a resynch with the site data before we do this, so I will need an import of the emp database so I can recreate it on the test server to run the importer. Its important I (or whoever is going to do the data import when we go live) uses this to test the latest importer code. At the end of the open beta week/when we have squashed any new bugs we will go live. Therefore I imagine we will be running announcements and a thread on emp making it clear we will be changing site at the end of the week.\n\n[b]4) The changeover.[/b] This was really Lanz\'s thing but I guess we have to assume he isn\'t returning anytime soon. As far as I can work out here is what needs to be done:\n[b]The Plan:[/b]\n[*]Close the site (I suggest we put up a temp page saying check back at 12 hours later or something, could even have an irc webchat on it so random pervs can at least know we are not dissappeared).\n[*]We keep the current emp db on the server.\n[*]Install lamp (will already be on server), git, ocelot, sphinx, then pull the site code with git pull. (this will install the basic site code + media)\n[*]do a few db things like build the raw gazelle db and import the articles/categories/bonus shop/awards data.\n[*]run the special importer code on the new site. This builds the torrent and user data from the current emp database. It will take a few hours to run this process.\n[*]point the domain at the right place and cross our fingers. (open the new site)\n[size=2][b]NOTE:[/b][/size] I can do most of this stuff at the changeover, but I cannot do the ocelot and sphinx install... or at least I do not feel that comfortable doing it and if it goes wrong I will be fubar. I imagine Alex will want to do the domain stuff and that will be helpful anyway. Hopefully alex (or j4n/lanz if they ever return) can do the installations on the server.\n',84499,'2012-10-01 20:21:33'),(47899,6106,84499,'2012-09-28 12:38:57','\r\nWe have ground to a halt because of Lanz\'s absence, I have tried emailing him but got no reply. As far as I am aware J4n has also not responded to email. For the moment I think we have to assume they are not going to be assisting us in the near future.\r\n\r\nI would like us to move on with the new site though, so we need to find other solutions.\r\n\r\nI have made another thread - [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3105]Changeover plan[/url] - which is an attempt to list the practical things we need to do to get there. I cannot do it all myself, I am hopeful DrkNess can sort the tracker code and maybe Alex will be able to cover the server stuff I cannot do? If not we will have to come up with something else...\r\n\r\nI have restricted this forum to admins only for the moment, possibly DrkNess should be given access as well. We can invite whoever we want but this is not intended to be a debate about anything just a place where those its relevant to can plan the changeover.\r\n\r\nClownius - if you have been in contact with alex recently maybe you would invite him to here as we will need his input one way or another.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47902,6107,94952,'2012-09-29 06:15:38','Are there any plans for a load test before the new site goes live? And what can we the testers do to help out with load/stress test?',NULL,NULL),(47903,6107,48010,'2012-09-29 17:04:28','yes we plan to do a load test later - thanks for mentioning it though',NULL,NULL),(47904,6106,48010,'2012-09-29 17:30:00','As this is only a forum I see no problem giving DrkNess access to it. If you are hopeful about him then you know a lot more than me (and Clownius too ?).\n',48010,'2012-09-29 17:55:23'),(47905,6108,85636,'2012-09-29 18:18:52','When testing the RSS feed for the IRC channel, instead of displaying the category correctly (e.g. BDSM, etc) it uses the tags of that torrent.\n\nYou may also want to add the option for users to use freeleech & doubleseed slot option\'s on the rss feed',85636,'2012-09-30 00:57:40'),(47913,6109,49532,'2012-09-30 04:21:58','When on a screen with resolution of 1024x768, the stats overlap the searchbars:\r\n\r\n[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=AAD3_5067C535][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=AAD3_5067C535[/img][/url]\r\n\r\nThis happens with all 3 of the main styles.\r\n\r\nI fixed this in [url=http://lorem.us/new.css]http://lorem.us/new.css[/url], by using [b]Open Sans Condensed[/b] for the stats and searchbars, and making the width of the searchbars 9.5% instead of 10%.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47914,6106,47234,'2012-09-30 07:27:47','Sorry for the late reply.  Yes i think DrkNess should have access to this and next time emp is working i will ask Alex to pop over and have a look.\r\n\r\nAs for DrkNess well the proof is in if he manages to get things fixed.  I know him a little (from emp) but mainly you never know just how much someone knows until they demonstrate it.  Its not like we can ask for references from previous employers etc :lol:\r\n\r\nI have given him a user account on this server and he was looking into the tracker code.  Im sure he knows more than i do.',NULL,NULL),(47915,6106,84499,'2012-09-30 11:50:37','\r\n\r\nI have already given DrkNess access to this forum.',NULL,NULL),(47916,6109,84499,'2012-09-30 11:52:50','\r\n\r\nwhen you have less than a million credits it wont be such a problem.',NULL,NULL),(47920,6105,1,'2012-10-01 14:40:27','Already put a backup i had on hdd here: http://torrents.empornium.me/emp(3).sql\r\nLast time i used sphinx got a error so i better try it first. memcached and git-core are already there so i only need to install ocelot. (done this with no problems on a windows box when first gazelle was released) but this when will be ready.\r\nAlso i will need a git command to get current test tracker (with or without a sql dump, i think better try the converter code) on emp server to see if will encounter any problem/error.\r\n\r\nnot sure if this will help, but ocelot check connectability by ip+port, DrkNess can you check the lines with the port code maybe something its wrong there.',NULL,NULL),(47922,6105,84499,'2012-10-01 20:13:47','Thanks Alex  :gjob: \n\n\nTo get the latest code:\n\nfrom the www/ directory (? assuming this is the same but I will let you worry about that)\n\n[b]tracker code[/b]\n[code]$ git clone git@github.com:mifune/ocelot.git\n$ cd ocelot\n$ git remote add origin git@github.com:mifune/ocelot.git\n$ git checkout work[/code]\n\n\n[b]site code[/b]\n[code]$ git clone git@github.com:mifune/gazelle.git\n$ cd gazelle\n$ git remote add origin git@github.com:mifune/gazelle.git\n$ git checkout work[/code]\n\nonce that is done you can update any new changes with [code]$ git pull[/code] (from the appropiate directory).\n\nI *think* anyone can do this without having a github user account set up (the projects are public read only). \n\nYou might need to set up an identity in your git settings:\n[code]$ git config --global user.email johndoe@example.com[/code]\n\nI am far from a git expert but I will answer any questions you have as best I can.\n\nreference: http://git-scm.com/docs\nmanual: http://git-scm.com/book/en/Getting-Started-First-Time-Git-Setup\n\n\n- oh and you will need to change various settings in the config file. Easiest thing is to look at/copy the gazelle/classes/config.php on the test server for the values actually being used  (there is a config.template file but obviously various pw\'s etc are left blank in that version).\n\n',84499,'2012-10-17 22:10:28'),(47924,6106,171777,'2012-10-02 08:22:18','Am looking at code whenever I have some free time. Currently running from job interview to job interview (including preparing for them) so my life is rather hectic.',NULL,NULL),(47925,6106,47234,'2012-10-03 13:12:36','Fair enough having a job is kinda helpful :lol:\n\nI dont want to sound pushy DrkNess but the current site is hitting the wall.  Any idea when your likely to have time to look at this?  How is the future looking at the moment?\r\n\r\nIm just wondering when we get desperate enough to send a general call out to the Emp community basically asking for any experienced C++ coders :lol:',47234,'2012-10-06 17:26:19'),(47926,6110,94804,'2012-10-06 12:25:47','I just noticed something strange again. When in a thread I make a remark on my own post (that is I reply to myself)it gets added to the existing post instead of a new post being created, and on top of that it can\'t be edited, because \"the system thinks\" it was posted when that previous post was posted...........',NULL,NULL),(47927,6110,86439,'2012-10-06 12:34:25','Auto merge and editing time limits. Not sure if you are aware but both things are implemented here and it appears they are conspiring against you.',NULL,NULL),(47928,6110,84499,'2012-10-06 15:59:22',':hmmm:\n\nmaybe the edit timer for users (iirc its about 10 mins) should be reset when a post is merged?  \n\n',84499,'2012-10-06 15:59:36'),(47929,6110,47234,'2012-10-06 17:21:30','[quote=mifune,f3110,27928]:hmmm:\r\n\r\nmaybe the edit timer for users (iirc its about 10 mins) should be reset when a post is merged?[/quote]\r\n\r\nSounds reasonable',NULL,NULL),(47930,6110,94804,'2012-10-06 22:22:35','What is the auto-merge for then? And resetting sounds reasonakbe yes',NULL,NULL),(47931,6110,86439,'2012-10-08 12:46:45','[quote=schlager,f3110,27930]What is the auto-merge for then? And resetting sounds reasonakbe yes[/quote]\nTo prevent double posts.\n\nThere are a few occasions where DP is useful, but generally its just the result of user error. Ergo, the feature to fuck them off.',86439,'2012-10-08 12:47:18'),(47932,6110,86439,'2012-10-08 12:46:58','[quote=schlager,f3110,27930]What is the auto-merge for then? And resetting sounds reasonakbe yes[/quote]\nTo prevent double posts.\n\nThere are a few occasions where DP is useful, but generally its just the result of user error. Ergo, the feature to fuck them off.',86439,'2012-10-08 12:47:32'),(47933,6110,48010,'2012-10-08 17:16:41','to prevent double posts?\r\n\r\nknickers just did that',NULL,NULL),(47934,6110,94804,'2012-10-08 20:17:58','[quote=knickers,f3110,27932]There are a few occasions where DP is useful[/quote]\nFunny, given the \"explicit nature of this site\" :D',94804,'2012-10-08 20:18:38'),(47938,6111,48010,'2012-10-09 19:00:48','From a PM I sent to Clownius and mifune:\r\n\r\nMy suggestion to find a C++ coder for the new tracker is to make an announcement. You may agree or not. All POV will be considered. This is getting quite urgent but is something we need to deal with and I feel between us we can sort it out. The website side of things is pretty much sorted ?\r\n\r\nThe only problem is how to vet applicants. mifune could you deal with this? but I don\'t want to overload you with PMs - we could add a forum thread instead and then ask any potential candidate by PM for more info and make it clear not to PM staff?\r\n\r\nWould it be an idea to set up a forum on the test site for only the 3 of us as we don\'t always meet on irc, and irc (if we discuss directly) and PMs will keep one of us of the loop. Or do we post a Staff thread on emp.me ?\r\n\r\nA draft announcement would be :\r\n\r\n****************************\r\n\r\nThe site is running slowly at times as all members havce noticed. It is no secret we have been working on a new site. However, we have run into some difficulties. We need an experienced C++ coder with tracker experience to help us finish this work. If you feel you have the skills required please post here (add thread). All irrelevant posts will be deleted. Staff will contact you later.\r\n\r\nEmpornium.me is a free site to all members. The Staff give their time for free to manage this site. There is no way in the world you will get paid for this, so the salary for this job is the square root of zero !\r\n\r\nThere is an offer of upload credits in the forums (later link to Myran\'s post)\r\n\r\n******end of announcement*********\r\n\r\nComments appreciated as always.\r\n\r\n--------------------------------------\r\n\r\nThat was the PM - would like input from Alex and DrkNess too\r\n\r\nThanks Dave',NULL,NULL),(47939,6111,47234,'2012-10-09 19:40:59','Im beginning to think this might be a viable option which isnt a good thing :lol:',NULL,NULL),(47940,6078,96400,'2012-10-09 21:45:04','Can you please add uTorrent Mac version 1.5.* and higher? 1.6.* is also out already.',NULL,NULL),(47941,6078,47234,'2012-10-09 22:21:38','[quote=sasquatch,f3078,27940]Can you please add uTorrent Mac version 1.5.* and higher? 1.6.* is also out already.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYou need to give us version numbers so we can enter them.  We can then find out the client ID which we need to add them to the whitelist\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47942,6078,84499,'2012-10-09 23:34:49','[quote=apparition,f3078,27888]Transmission 2.7.1 \r\n\r\nWhy do individual versions need to be whitelisted? Can\'t you whitelist an app, and blacklist only the bad versions?[/quote]\r\n[quote=sasquatch,f3078,27940]Can you please add uTorrent Mac version 1.5.* and higher? 1.6.* is also out already.[/quote]\r\n\r\nBecause of the way clients are identified in the torrent protocol each version has to be individuallly added. Theoretically we could have a blacklist but we have already decided to keep it as a whitelist.',NULL,NULL),(47943,6111,1,'2012-10-10 00:16:01','it could be an option, but the user that will get access to source code should be chosen carefully.\r\nalso i was thinking to ask for help on their project gazelle forum but seems nobody was there for few months.',NULL,NULL),(47944,6111,47234,'2012-10-10 00:22:21','Yeah i checked out the project Gazelle forums myself trying to see if there was any info on this.  That place has been dead fro over 6 months now. The code is Open Source and as we found freely available on github in any case so its no state secret at the end of the day.\r\n\r\nWhat we would need to protect would be the database unless we trust someone.  Any ideas?  Maybe set up another test server somewhere with no imported EMP database on it?\r\n\r\nWould give someone practice doing the install too :lol:',NULL,NULL),(47945,6111,84499,'2012-10-10 00:40:31','DrkNess has PM\'d me indicating he probably wont be able to help us. (I forwarded it to clownius... and fuck knows why but you can only forward a convo once... may take a look at that ... maybe). Mobbo perhaps maybe might be able to help... he is not as experienced as I had hoped however he does appear to actually be working on it! \n\nI am pretty busy for the next couple of weeks but I can still check in at least once a day, and can make time to write pm\'s as needed. (perhaps I can get a hand dealing with pm\'s etc if theres a lot but I\'ll let you know if thats the case). It might make sense to wait until friday before making any announcement, lets see if Mobbo makes any progess, and then I will have a bit more time at the weekend to deal with stuff. I can also then see if I can set up a forked project on github which will hopefully mean we can give any potential helper contributer access etc (good idea clownius!).\n\n\nIf we do go that way I think the announcement may as well tell them to message the staff or maybe PM me directly, some folks (me for instance) would not feel that comfortable giving a resume in public. Hopefully only folks who have some chance of fitting the requirements will get in touch.\n\n[quote=possible announcemnt] \nThe site is running slowly at times as all members have noticed. It is no secret we have been working on a new site, the site itself is essentially finished, and its great. There is one thing left to be implemented with the tracker software, unfortunatley at the last hurdle we have lost our c++ coder. Therefore we need an [u]experienced C++ coder[/u] to help us finish up the tracker software (a partially modififed version of ocelot). There really isnt a huge amount to do but we do need someone with a certain amount of skill.\n \nsome basics:\nubuntu server (running lamp)\nsite software: heavily modified version of gazelle\ntracker software: modified version of ocelot\n\nWe need someone who can work independently and who can read and understand complex enough c++ code. You will need to be able to get git (source control) up and running (probably on an ubuntu installation) and you will probably need to do some research/already have some experience of how trackers work.\n\nIf you feel you have the skills required please use the contact staff button to get in touch. (note: it may take us a day or two to respond, please be patient!)\n\n\nEmpornium.me is a free site to all members. The Staff give their time for free to manage this site. There is no way in the world you will get paid for this, so the salary for this job is the square root of zero. Anyone who does end up helping us will get our undying thanks and a year of freeleech or something. \n[/quote]\n\nI can vet the applications and get them going. How about a year of FL as a reward? And if they are actually good (rather than just good enough) they can probably end up as staff if they are suitable enough? (we wouldnt mention that in advance though)\n\n',84499,'2012-10-10 00:51:09'),(47946,6111,84499,'2012-10-10 00:44:06','\r\n\r\noh does anyone mind if we give mobbo access to this forum? At the moment I am having a PM convo with him which I have tried to forward to both dave and clownius and now I am not sure who can see what of that convo lol. Might just be easier if that was a thread in this forum?',NULL,NULL),(47947,6111,47234,'2012-10-10 01:29:00','Agreed Mifune.  Anyone whos helping out should have access to where we are discussing things.  \r\n\r\nSave those 3 and 4 way PM\'s that are beginning to get confusing.\r\n\r\nAs for the reward yes i think we can afford to hand out a years FL and if they manage to fix things its almost certain they would be a valuable addition to the staff.  We need a couple of people around who know code thats for sure :)  Its fine having guys who can handle reports etc but we also need a couple of people who can squash the bugs that crop up from time to time.\r\n\r\nOff Topic a bit its always amazed me a piece of software can run fault free for months untouched and suddenly develop bugs.',NULL,NULL),(47948,6112,84499,'2012-10-10 01:50:08','\r\nSorry its bad manners to post a private conversation but then this is a very private forum :smile1:\r\n\r\nTo all who can read this: lets use this thread to carry on this converstaion here.\r\n\r\n\r\n[quote=Mobbo]Clownius reached out to me asking for help with fixing the last bugs. This is what I found/figured out about the connectable bug (I know this is overly simplstictly written, but I wanted to be as clear as possible)\r\n\r\nOkay so I couldn\'t help myself so I took a peek at the git for emp and I found some stuff.\r\nFirst it seems like there are a mashup between Gazelle/xbtt/ocelot. Or rather a gazelle/xbtt install that recived a ocelot transplant.\r\n\r\nI will try to make this as clear as possible. There are a bit of jumping between back-end and frontend to make this clearer\r\nL4nz/Gazelle branch\r\n1. In gazelle.sql we get the table structure and creation for xbt_files_users\r\n	on line 2924 we have \"`connectable` tinyint(4) NOT NULL DEFAULT \'1\'\"\r\n	So any new peers in this table gets set to TRUE\r\n2. xbt_files_users is queryed in /sections/torrents/peerlist.php \r\n\r\nL4nz/ocelot branch\r\n1. The only place xbt_files_users is used is on line 236-242\r\n		sql = \"INSERT INTO xbt_files_users (uid,fid,active,uploaded,downloaded,upspeed,downspeed,remaining,\" +\r\n		std::string(\"timespent,announced,ip,peer_id,useragent,mtime) VALUES \") + update_peer_buffer + \r\n				\" ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE active=VALUES(active), uploaded=VALUES(uploaded), \" +\r\n				\"downloaded=VALUES(downloaded), upspeed=VALUES(upspeed), \" +\r\n				\"downspeed=VALUES(downspeed), remaining=VALUES(remaining), \" +\r\n				\"timespent=VALUES(timespent), announced=VALUES(announced), \" + \r\n				\"mtime=VALUES(mtime)\";\r\n2. As you can see Connectable is never set or updated using the default value of true.\r\n\r\nIm not really sure how to fix this. I gotta do some thinking. I will look into how xbtt does this, but it looks lite the code is a bit spread out.[/quote]\r\n[quote=Mobbo]Just went over the ocelot code again, there are no code to check for connectability in the current code. Also client port isn\'t saved to the database as far as I can tell.\r\n\r\nI have a few ideas on how to fix this, But way too tired to be coherent atm(insomnia isn\'t fun). I will try write it down if you want it.\r\n\r\n//Oscar[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=mifune]Hi, thanks for taking a look at it.\r\n\r\nYeah it looked that way to me - no check for connectability in ocelot. I can just about read c++ (I mean I studied it about 20 years ago) but dont feel comfortable writing it or compiling it etc. I also dont know off the top of my head how you would check for connectability. (well I know how to do it by opening a socket on the target machine but is that really what a tracker is doing for tens of thousands of peers??)\r\n\r\nOh, are you looking at the L4nz/ocelot work branch btw? The master branches are just the original raw gazelle/ocelot projects, the work branches are the emp projects. \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/L4nz/ocelot/tree/work\r\nhttps://github.com/L4nz/gazelle/tree/work\r\n\r\nThere are a couple of queries for xbt_files_users in the emp version that arent in the original. Not that that will matter of course, but there are also some changes to the ocelot code which afaics have no bearing on the connectable stuff... but just so you are looking at the latest correct version.\r\n\r\nAny help you can give would be much appreciated. I\'m kind of hoping you can grab the source from github, fix it, then mail me the fix and give me precise instructions on how to compile/install it on the test server... (then rinse repeat for any bugs/testing etc) unfortunatley lanz is the only one who can set up new contributer accounts on github else I would give you direct access so you could upload the fix yourself.\r\n\r\nLet me know how you get on.\r\n\r\nregards - mifune.[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=Mobbo]Well we are in the same boat then as far as c++ knowledge then. I\'m basicly channelling my 20 year old C knowledge, mixed in with a bit of java. \r\n\r\nConnectability is actually pretty simple, I think. You just try to open a socket and look at the resultcode. Using the socket() command [url=http://www.linuxhowtos.org/data/6/socket.txt]http://www.linuxhowtos.org/data/6/socket.txt[/url]\r\nI am looking at [url=http://www.linuxhowtos.org/C_C++/socket.htm]http://www.linuxhowtos.org/C_C++/socket.htm[/url]\r\nfor quick and dirty socketcode, only thing is that ocelot is the client in this scenario.\r\n\r\nIm gonna include a example on human readable diff file just so I can feed you updates in an intelligible fashion.\r\n\r\nLine 490 in worker.cpp\r\ndb->record_peer(record_str, ip, peer_id, headers[\"user-agent\"]);\r\nto\r\ndb->record_peer(record_str, ip, port, peer_id, headers[\"user-agent\"]);\r\n\r\nLine 65 in db.h\r\nvoid record_peer(std::string &record, std::string &ip, std::string &peer_id, std::string &useragent); // (uid,fid,active,peerid,useragent,ip,uploaded,downloaded,upspeed,downspeed,left,timespent,announces)\r\nto\r\nvoid record_peer(std::string &record, std::string &ip, std::string &port, std::string &peer_id, std::string &useragent); // (uid,fid,active,peerid,useragent,ip,port,uploaded,downloaded,upspeed,downspeed,left,timespent,announces)\r\n\r\nLine 127 in db.cpp\r\nvoid mysql::record_peer(std::string &record, std::string &ip, std::string &peer_id, std::string &useragent) {\r\nto\r\nvoid mysql::record_peer(std::string &record, std::string &ip, std::string &port, std::string &peer_id, std::string &useragent) {\r\n\r\nLine 133 in db.cpp\r\nq << record << mysqlpp::quote << ip << \',\' << mysqlpp::quote << peer_id << \',\' << mysqlpp::quote << useragent << \",\" << time(NULL) << \')\';\r\nto\r\nq << record << mysqlpp::quote << ip << \',\' << mysqlpp::quote << port << \',\' << mysqlpp::quote << peer_id << \',\' << mysqlpp::quote << useragent << \",\" << time(NULL) << \')\';\r\n\r\nThese changes would record the port into the peer list used in the flush_peers() function responsible for updating the xtb_files_users table. \r\n\r\nIs this good for you? I will get back to you about how to compile the files.[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=Mobbo]Do you use linux and/or windows to do your coding?[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=mifune]For this project I have been working in ubuntu (in my day job I work in c# on windows more often than not).\r\n\r\nYou still appear to be working from the original (unaltered) project instead of the current one - you need to make sure you are looking at the work branch not the master branch. See https://github.com/L4nz/ocelot/blob/work/worker.cpp - the db->record_peer(record_str, ip, peer_id, headers[\"user-agent\"]); line is at 499 not 490.\r\n\r\nWhat is the purpose of recording the port? To do a socket test somewhere? Is that really how trackers test for connectability :hmmm: I had assumed as ocelot is the client, plus just the large number of peers/connections would mean there was some other method.\r\n\r\nIf possible I\'d prefer it if you sent me the actual files. You can email me at mifune@virginmedia.com[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=Mobbo]Yeah the purpose of these mods are to do a connection test called in flush_peers.\r\nflush_peers() iterate through all the connected peers. \r\nWell there will be a hell of a lot in terms of Connections here. Maybe its better to move the connect test to worker.cpp then only one connect test will be made per announce from the bittorrent-client. \r\n\r\nGetting the data from the infohash and making a socket call is the only way I see how to make sure the client is connectable from the back end. I will check how xbtt does it. but xbtt\'s code is much more convoluted. \r\n\r\nI will make sure I\'m working from the correct files. I think I am. I was using VS to grab the line numbers, you never know with MS :)\r\n\r\nOkay I\'m gonna setup eclipse on my ubuntu machine and try to get the code to compile, so I can give you some help with compiling. \r\n\r\nCan you check the ip-field in xbt_files_users if it contains just an ipadress or an ip/port combo. Also a row count from xbt_files_users would be great, just to get an idea of the size.\r\n\r\nBTW Im in located Sweden. So you can get an idea of when I online.[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=Mobbo]I think you are right. Doing 1000000+ connections would be bad. I\'m going to give it some thought.\r\n\r\n//Oscar[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=Clownius]Coming from a total noob here (i dont code).  \r\n\r\nBut would it be worth grabbing the xbtt code and seeing how it was checking connectability?  It may give you an idea? \r\n\r\nAnother question for Mifune is can you fork the current Emp code so you can add collaborators to your fork and we starting using your fork rather than the Lanz setup?  Just froma  quick look over github it appears collaborators can fork the current code that way but not those who are not.  Thinking longer term here too so we can have more than one person able to work on things in future.[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=mifune]I am not sure who this reply is going to now... lol. both of you? (fuck it I am going to have to think about how forwarding convos should really work...)\r\n\r\nClownius: Mobbo has already said he is going to take a look at xbtt\'s code. good plan though.\r\n\r\nAnd yeah I will try and fork the project at the weekend. (I am pretty busy atm with a RL project I have to get done but I will be around)\r\n\r\nMobbo: There are around 400,000 -> 500,000 peers on emp atm => that number of records in xbt_files_users, although that number is growing every day! I dont have the code on this machine (and I am too tired to boot up the other one right now, sorry) but I am fairly sure the xbt_files_users ip field is just the ip address :hmmm: You can probably work it out from the db structure? I\'ll take a closer look tomorrow...[/quote]\r\n\r\n[quote=Clownius]Agreed Mifune.  To be honest its confusing the hell out of me.\r\n\r\nNo huge rush Mifune.  Emps held together this long another few weeks cant hurt much can it?[/quote]\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47949,6111,84499,'2012-10-10 02:05:48','[quote=Clownius,f3111,27947] \r\nOff Topic a bit its always amazed me a piece of software can run fault free for months untouched and suddenly develop bugs.[/quote]\r\n\r\nBugs dont really appear.... they just go ignored/unnoticed lol.',NULL,NULL),(47950,6112,94952,'2012-10-10 11:06:44','Regarding the IP-field. You are right, it is a char(15) field. Only big enough to store an ip-adress.\r\n\r\n500 000 records means that putting the connectability-test in the flush_peers()-function would generate way to many connections. ',NULL,NULL),(47951,6113,94952,'2012-10-10 12:02:02','I\'m here. And I agree with Clownius and Mifune the PMs were getting confusing as hell.\n\nJust a short intro. I\'m an old C programmer same as Mifune but I can read and understand the code just fine because it is pretty simple(unlike xbtt). I\'m also familiar with Java and a pretty good C# programmer.\n\nI\'m unemployed and on sickleave so that gives a lot of free time. This also leaves me with really odd sleeping patterns. \n\nI have a good handle on the ocelotcode and gazelle-database and a working understanding of the gazelle-website(helps with debugging)\n\nSo far I have:\n1. Updated my ubuntu workstation with eclipe and the work branch of ocelot \n2. Tried compiling and found out that work is missing \"mysql++.h\" and probably \"mysql++.cpp\"\n\nMifune, to compile ocelot:\n[code]make -f Makefile[/code] \nin the ocelotsource dir. Simple as that. I\'m unable to do it myself for now as I\'m missing two files at least.\n\nThat\'s is for now.\n\n//Oscar aka Mobbo',94952,'2012-10-10 12:02:30'),(47952,6112,84499,'2012-10-10 12:36:02','\r\nI wont get a chance until the weekend but perhaps we should take a look at the tbdev php tracker - not to use but to see how it is checking for connectability.',NULL,NULL),(47953,6114,94952,'2012-10-10 14:36:36','I know I am starting a bunch of new threads, but I think it will help keep things organised.\r\n\r\nMifune: can you try to compile Ocelot on your machine and if that fails on on the tracker server.\r\n\r\nI\'m having problems getting the compiling to work. So far I have installed mysql++ (mysql-c wrapper), libev (eventhandler of some sort) and libboost (I think this is used for threading)\r\nBut I\'m still stuck, I think it is compiling but the linking is throws up on me with:\r\n[code]ocelot.cpp:(.text.startup+0x2d): undefined reference to `config::config()\'[/code]\r\n\r\nI think I have resolved most of the issues getting Ocelot into eclipse correctly.\n\nOkay we or rather I am in business, thanks to Clownius I was able to figure out the final part of the compile-issues.\r\n\r\nI needed the correct config.cpp (duh). But now I\'m able to compile ocelot both at home and on the emp-server. Clownius gave me an unprivileged account so I can\'t break anything. And I have uploaded a separate version of ocelot to test with in my homedir \"mobbo\"\r\n\r\nIndecently the config-file contains the announce interval currently set at 1800 sec. So now I\'m gonna start tinkering with the code here at home. I will update when I get anything good to report.',94952,'2012-10-12 06:40:53'),(47954,6111,48010,'2012-10-10 15:52:04','[quote=mifune,f3111,27946]oh does anyone mind if we give mobbo access to this forum? At the moment I am having a PM convo with him which I have tried to forward to both dave and clownius and now I am not sure who can see what of that convo lol. Might just be easier if that was a thread in this forum?[/quote]I didn\'t get any PMs here or on emp.me',NULL,NULL),(47955,6111,94952,'2012-10-10 15:56:04','I think it was just me, Mifune and Clownius that conferred via pm. And Mifune posted the whole mess in a another [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3112]thread[/url] on this subforum.',94952,'2012-10-10 15:57:12'),(47957,6112,1,'2012-10-10 19:21:55','tbdev it checking by sockets, by ip and port if i remember well.\r\nthe code should be in announce.php',NULL,NULL),(47959,6112,94952,'2012-10-10 20:50:35','You are very much correct admin (Alex?)\n@fsockopen command is on line 481 in announce.php\n\nI was thinking this is a better place to put then conn-check. Since announce gets called once per 30 minutes per active torrent.\n\nBut it still would amount to 500k connections per 1800 seconds. That\'s about 280 connections per second. \nWe could be smarter. We only really need to check if a peer is connectable. Not do it for every active torrent one every peer. For example if Clownius has 300 torrents we really only need to check his connectablity once every announce-cycle since it is an all or nothing deal. So we could save a lot of connections by being a little smarter.\nPseudo-code:\n[code]\n\nPeerList=SELECT distinct peer_id, ip, port FROM xbt_files_users\n\nfor each peer in PeerList\n{\n    \n    If socket(ip, port) then\n    {\n        SQL.execute=\"UPDATE xbt_files_users SET connectable = true WHERE peer_id =\'{0}\'\", peer\n    }\n    else\n    {\n        SQL.execute=\"UPDATE xbt_files_users SET connectable = false WHERE peer_id =\'{0}\'\", peer\n    }\n}\n[/code] \n\nSomething like that. I know the code is ugly as hell but as a starting point. What do you think?\nOnly problem is where do we hook it into the code so it don\'t get called all the time?\nEdit: I think mysql::flush()-function in db.cpp is a good option to place the call, after the peer:flush() that way we have a newly updated xbt_files_users-table to work with. Opinions?\n\nSure it eats some CPU and one extra select, but it saves us 400k socket tries (assuming we have 100k users and 500k active torrens) and instead of making a separate update for every torrent we only make one per peer. The same ratio 1/5.  \n',94952,'2012-10-10 21:00:10'),(47960,6112,94952,'2012-10-10 21:01:01','Oh. Is the psuedo code good for you Mifune? Can you read it okay?\n\nDamn it for my slick little plan to work we need the port for the peer, which isn\'t stored in the current ocelot-code. Which means changes need to be made to do this. \r\nPort IS extracted from the infohash in worker.cpp \r\n[code]unsigned int port = strtolong(params[\"port\"]);[/code]\r\nWe need to add a field to xbt_files_users\r\n[code]\'port\' int(6) NOT NULL[/code]\r\n\r\nBasicly I\'m just generating some ideas, please give me some feedback. :smile2:',94952,'2012-10-10 21:22:39'),(47961,6112,1,'2012-10-10 21:42:35','thats what i previously wanted to say, the port variable needs to be in xbt schema :laugh: \r\n\r\nyes Oscar, i\'m Alex, nice to met you',NULL,NULL),(47962,6112,84499,'2012-10-11 12:27:47','\n[quote=admin,f3112,27957]tbdev it checking by sockets, by ip and port if i remember well.\nthe code should be in announce.php[/quote]\n\nThanks for the input Alex :smile1:\n\nOkay well if tbdev does it by opening a socket then I suspect that is way it is done in all trackers (we could be wrong here but sockets and connections work the same in php as they do in c++! lets assume tbdev is doing it right...).\n\n[quote=Mobbo,f3112,27959]You are very much correct admin (Alex?)\n@fsockopen command is on line 481 in announce.php\n\nI was thinking this is a better place to put then conn-check. Since announce gets called once per 30 minutes per active torrent.\n\nBut it still would amount to 500k connections per 1800 seconds. That\'s about 280 connections per second. \nWe could be smarter. We only really need to check if a peer is connectable. Not do it for every active torrent one every peer. For example if Clownius has 300 torrents we really only need to check his connectablity once every announce-cycle since it is an all or nothing deal. So we could save a lot of connections by being a little smarter.\nPseudo-code:\n[code]\n\nPeerList=SELECT distinct peer_id, ip, port FROM xbt_files_users\n\nfor each peer in PeerList\n{\n    \n    If socket(ip, port) then\n    {\n        SQL.execute=\"UPDATE xbt_files_users SET connectable = true WHERE peer_id =\'{0}\'\", peer\n    }\n    else\n    {\n        SQL.execute=\"UPDATE xbt_files_users SET connectable = false WHERE peer_id =\'{0}\'\", peer\n    }\n}\n[/code] \n\nSomething like that. I know the code is ugly as hell but as a starting point. What do you think?\nOnly problem is where do we hook it into the code so it don\'t get called all the time?\nEdit: I think mysql::flush()-function in db.cpp is a good option to place the call, after the peer:flush() that way we have a newly updated xbt_files_users-table to work with. Opinions?\n\nSure it eats some CPU and one extra select, but it saves us 400k socket tries (assuming we have 100k users and 500k active torrens) and instead of making a separate update for every torrent we only make one per peer. The same ratio 1/5.[/quote]\n\n[quote=Mobbo,f3112,27960]Oh. Is the psuedo code good for you Mifune? Can you read it okay?\n\nDamn it for my slick little plan to work we need the port for the peer, which isn\'t stored in the current ocelot-code. Which means changes need to be made to do this. \nPort IS extracted from the infohash in worker.cpp \n[code]unsigned int port = strtolong(params[\"port\"]);[/code]\nWe need to add a field to xbt_files_users\n[code]\'port\' int(6) NOT NULL[/code]\n\nBasicly I\'m just generating some ideas, please give me some feedback. :smile2:[/quote]\n\nThe pseudocode is readable lol. If you would prefer to write it in c++ rather than pseudocode thats fine too.\n\nWe can add a port field in xbt_files_users no problem. (I\'ll add it to the gazelle project at the weekend).\n\nI think you are probably right that we should test once per user rather than once per connection, although we have to think about this a little as connectability is reported on a per connection basis in the interface. (ie. connectivity is displayed in the peerlists, which reflect the xbt_files_user records). hmm, I cannot see a problem with setting all of a users connection records to the same value although I do have a little niggle wondering if this is the right way... just because it seems a little weird that the value is stored per connection if its one value per peer? Anyway despite my niggles I think you probably have the right approach. (Assuming that mysql::flush() is called once per announce etc but you seem to know what you are doing).\n\nOh, where do you get an announce every 30 mins from? for some reason I thought the announce was every 15 mins although I may be wrong - the scheduler in gazelle is called every 15 mins from a cronjob anyway.\n \nI am really busy the next couple of days (and next week) with some RL work, but I\'ll be around daily. At the weekend I will have some more time to catch up with stuff properly (I also have a couple of other minor things to implement in gazelle waiting). I will (try to) fork the projects on github at the weekend which will give us proper control over the source. Once I have forked the projects I should be able to set you up with a contributer account for the projects on github - meaning you will be able to update the ocelot project directly. We can also give you ssh access to the test server - so you can pull the latest source to the live test server and get ocelot installed etc. (once I have worked out how to point git to the new project etc.)\n\n',84499,'2012-10-11 12:38:28'),(47963,6111,84499,'2012-10-11 12:35:27','\r\nDave - hmm... yeah I definitely need to look at how forwarding PM\'s work... grumble grumble. See the thread Mobbo linked to I reposted that convo in there.\r\n\r\nMobbo - I feel a lot more confident today than I did 2 days ago that we (ie. you) might be able to crack this thing... :smile1:\r\n\r\nDave/Clownius/Alex - Unless Mobbo feels differently I suggest we hold the announcement and plea for another coder and lets see how we get on.',NULL,NULL),(47964,6111,48010,'2012-10-11 16:00:30','[quote=Mobbo,f3111,27955]I think it was just me, Mifune and Clownius that conferred via pm. And Mifune posted the whole mess in a another [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3112]thread[/url] on this subforum.[/quote]No problem Mobbo - mifune said above he tried to PM me and Clownius so it was really directed at him\r\n[quote=mifune,f3111,27963]Dave - hmm... yeah I definitely need to look at how forwarding PM\'s work... grumble grumble. See the thread Mobbo linked to I reposted that convo in there.\r\n\r\nMobbo - I feel a lot more confident today than I did 2 days ago that we (ie. you) might be able to crack this thing... :smile1:\r\n\r\nDave/Clownius/Alex - Unless Mobbo feels differently I suggest we hold the announcement and plea for another coder and lets see how we get on.[/quote]\r\nyes unless Mobbo has something to say as far as I\'m concerned let\'s leave it on hold. I understand the other thread except the code. Seems like we may be able to move forward.',NULL,NULL),(47965,6111,94952,'2012-10-11 20:52:07','Sooo... No pressure then :smile2:\r\nI will get the changes made I think is necessary and get them to Mifune or make my own branch if Mifune beats me with the git-fork. \r\nThe current obstacles are, I can\'t compile the unaltered source at home. I\'m missing some library when compiling from the command line (config specificly) and when building in eclipse I get several errors related to std::unordered_map which is weird since it is a standard library. That is why I asked Mifune if he can compile it on the server, it should have all the right libs and dependencies. \r\n\r\nI\'m not a C++ wizard but I am a decent coder so the logic and flow I can see, and the C++ I just have to reverse-engineer. But I agree for now lets wait a little bit longer with recruiting more coders or we will have a mess on our hands. \r\n\r\nA git fork is a good first step, makes it easier to involve more coders without risking the entire project.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47966,6111,47234,'2012-10-12 00:35:17','Mobbo if you need Server access im the man to talk to on that one.  Let me know if you need sudo and i will set the account up for you.  Hit me up on the irc or send me a PM.',NULL,NULL),(47967,6114,94952,'2012-10-12 06:41:59','Bah. Merge got me. Excuse doublepost\r\nOkay we or rather I am in business, thanks to Clownius I was able to figure out the final part of the compile-issues.\r\n\r\nI needed the correct config.cpp (duh). But now I\'m able to compile ocelot both at home and on the emp-server. Clownius gave me an unprivileged account so I can\'t break anything. And I have uploaded a separate version of ocelot to test with in my homedir \"mobbo\"\r\n\r\nIndecently the config-file contains the announce interval currently set at 1800 sec. So now I\'m gonna start tinkering with the code here at home. I will update when I get anything good to report. ',NULL,NULL),(47968,6112,48010,'2012-10-12 16:45:41','As you know I\'m not a coder. \n\nA site I use for UK TV thebox.bz used to show if you were connectable up until a few months ago, then it stopped. AFAIR iptorrents never showed this.\n\nUsing logic here the conn_check is a serious overload on the tracker? It is useful but do we need it? (I\'m not suggesting it goes)\n\nsuggestion - many members use a seedbox or are 24/7 - do we need to keep checking them? probably not\n\nWould it be possible to code it so if you connected in the last hour (or something) you are conn_checked and if you\'ve been connected for over an hour no need? \n\nIs it possible to use a time stamp in the code such as \n[code]if connected for more than one hour then ignore the account (no check)\nif not then check it[/code]\n\n\n',48010,'2012-10-12 16:58:30'),(47969,6112,84499,'2012-10-12 17:27:41','\r\n[codeblock]\r\n[17:47] <~mifune> hmmm... hopefully the new tracker will run a bit leaner... conincidentally the outstanding issue on the tracker that Mobbo is looking at at the moment is getting the connectable status for peers - and adding that funtionality may well add a huge load to the tracker\r\n[17:48] <~mifune> i think i am going to have to investigate a bit further how we might do that a bit better\r\n[17:50] <~mifune> As it stands it looks like the way trackers get the connectable status of a peer is they open another connection to the peer - thats the definition of connectable - but doing that for a few tens of thousands of peers every 30 mins seems like it is always going to a strain *strokes beard thoughtfully*\r\n[17:50] <~mifune> **be a strain\r\n[17:51] <@yamchan> kick it up to hourly checks only?\r\n[17:52] <@barumba> or store it somewhere if yes and only check it then for that user once a week or so?\r\n[17:52] <@yamchan> or much less often\r\n[17:53] <~mifune> maybe... i am wondering if there is some sensible way we can only grab it when we actually want it. Or perhaps we can do something clever like store a positive result for a longer time and only requery the unconnectables ??\r\n[17:54] <@barumba> that is what I suggested ;)\r\n[17:54] <~mifune> oh barumba you already said that lol. yes, something like that maybe\r\n[17:55] <@barumba> yeah if somebody is connectable is unlikely will not be\r\n[17:55] <~mifune> we already have the manual connchecker too\r\n[17:56] <@barumba> the issue is find the non connectable and beat them with a hammer until they fix it\r\n[17:56] <~mifune> well there is already some code (that only I have ever seen working) that displays a big red banner of you are not connectable\r\n[17:57] <@barumba> does it send a PM too?\r\n[17:57] <~mifune> you have to manually set the connectable flag to false in the peer records to see it atm\r\n[17:59] <~mifune> no it dosent send a PM - and the slight difficulty is when should it send a PM? the red banner is just displayed when that user loads a page on the site, the connectable status isnt set atm, and the \'normal\' way for it to be implemented is for the tracker to check the status every announce cycle\r\n[17:59] <~mifune> but we wouldnt want it sending PM\'s every 30 minutes\r\n[18:01] <@barumba> oh no ofc not\r\n[18:01] <~mifune> also the tracker cannot send PM;s as such, so it would have to be in the site scheduler anyway... technically its not difficult its just not that obvious how it should be done, connectable status as it is is just a field in the peer-torrent records, the scheduler could check that say once a day but if you werent seeding at that time it wouldnt catch you\r\n[18:01] <@barumba> only once first time is detected\r\n[18:03] <~mifune> yeah, but that implies that the scheduler checks say every 15 mins and does that - but that means keeping a seperate record of who has been PM\'d that day to prevent sending every 15 mins\r\n[18:03] <~mifune> and perhaps thats the solution, but I need to think about it a bit, perhaps we need to actually record the connectable status seperately from the peer records\r\n[/codeblock]',NULL,NULL),(47970,6112,48010,'2012-10-12 17:30:46','k',NULL,NULL),(47971,6112,84499,'2012-10-12 17:35:00','\r\n\r\nSo yeah... \r\n\r\nPerhaps we should do something cleverer than just checking all the peers every announce?\r\n\r\nWhat we need to think about is when do we need someones connectable status checking? We can probably take a positive result and rely on it for a certain length of time, and then just frequently query the unconnectables. We will need to load test this stuff but presumably it will be much much quicker to query a value in the db (the users \"current connectable\" status - could be logically stored in the user records or even as a seperate table, whatever makes the most sense from the trackers pov) than to make a new connection. Also to consider is possibly shifting some of this from the announce to when the peer first connects? \r\n\r\nI\'ll be back tomorrow to think about this properly... :smile1:\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47972,6112,48010,'2012-10-12 17:37:32','rename this thread ?',NULL,NULL),(47973,6112,94952,'2012-10-12 17:41:31','Conn-checking takes time. Especially when failing, when connecting it takes a ping roundtrip. 200 ms on average I\'d say. When failing it waits until it times out how long that is I don\'t know. \r\n\r\nThe code I have in mind will be smarter than most trackers since it will  be looking at connectability per active peer instead of per active torrent.\r\n\r\nI think threading is necessary to get this done right but I\'m not familiar with threading in c++. \r\n\r\nAlmost anything is possible, I am still thinking of where to make the call to the conn-check but at most it should happen once every 30 minutes or so (the current announce time). \r\n\r\nEasiest but not desirable is to ignore the conn-check altogether, that is dead simple :smile2:\r\n\r\nPlease contiune to post your ideas and theories it will make the tracker better. ',NULL,NULL),(47974,6112,94952,'2012-10-12 17:49:36','I like your thinking Mifune. But if we move from the xbt_files_user table we are gonna need new code on the website as well. Or do something clever to update the table too.',NULL,NULL),(47975,6112,47234,'2012-10-12 18:51:37','Im thinking if someone is connectable could the check be backed off to 12-24hrs or when the conn checker is used. \r\n\r\nIf someone shows as not connectable have it check something like every 2 hours or when the conn checker is used.\r\n\r\nIf this thing causes real load then back it right off.  But giving the user the ability to check on demand as well could be useful.\r\n\r\nThen the question becomes do we have this as part of site or tracker code?  The tracker code would obviously still need adjusting to save the port used.  As far as i understand it doesnt yet do that.  The site code if you wanted to add on demand conn checking would also need to be modified to allow for the conn checker to import the IP and port stats.\r\n\r\nJust throwing ideas out there.  But im thinking this would allow for the bulk of the code to be written in a language more familiar to our current coders which hopefully would make life easier.',NULL,NULL),(47976,6112,84499,'2012-10-12 18:53:56','New code on the site is not a problem. Also we can make whatever changes we want to the database structure.\n\nlogically the users connectable status could be in the users_main or users_info table. Or it could even be in a seperate table with just a userID and connectable status  - which would probably execute queries on it marginally faster than if its in one of the user tables, and the speed increase would be very marginal but might still add up to something meaningful with 30k users online at once and ~200k+ records in the table.\n\n[codeblock]\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS `users_connectable_status` (\n  `UserID` int(10) unsigned NOT NULL,\n  `Status` enum(\'0\',\'1\') NOT NULL DEFAULT \'1\',\n  `Time` int(10) NOT NULL DEFAULT \'0\',\n  UNIQUE KEY `UserID` (`UserID`),\n  KEY `Status` (`Status`) ,\n  KEY `Time` (`Time`) \n) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8;\n[/codeblock]\n\nI will have to revisit the connectable status being reported in the header code anyway as when I wrote it I incorrectly assumed that connectable status could be different in seperate connection records - so it can be rewritten to be slightly quicker anyway. \n\n\n\nSo... some more musings...\n\nI dont have the ocelot code in front of me but is there some function that gets called when a peer connects? If so then it might make sense to do this individually when peers connect - anyway here is the group version:\n\n[code]\n// get peers who do not have status = \'1\' OR where status has not been set for over a week.\npeers = SELECT distinct xbt.peer_id, xbt.ip, xbt.port, ucs.Status \n          FROM users_connectable_status AS ucs \n          JOIN xbt_files_users AS xbt ON xbt.peer_id=ucs.UserID\n         WHERE ucs.Status = \'0\' \n            OR ucs.Time < \'Now()- ( 7*24*3600 )\'; // ( - 1 week )\n\n// do check for unconnectable/timed out peers:\n\nfor each peer in peers \n{\n   // do the connectable test\n   result = socket(ip, port) ? \'1\' : \'0\';\n\n   // store result\n   SQL = UPDATE users_connectable_status SET Status = \'result\', Time = \'Now()\' WHERE UserID =\'peer.peer_id\'\";\n \n}\n[/code]\n\n\n\n\n\n\n',84499,'2012-10-12 19:05:22'),(47977,6112,84499,'2012-10-12 18:57:18','[quote=Clownius,f3112,27975]Im thinking if someone is connectable could the check be backed off to 12-24hrs or when the conn checker is used. \n\nIf someone shows as not connectable have it check something like every 2 hours or when the conn checker is used.\n\nIf this thing causes real load then back it right off.  But giving the user the ability to check on demand as well could be useful.\n\nThen the question becomes do we have this as part of site or tracker code?  The tracker code would obviously still need adjusting to save the port used.  As far as i understand it doesnt yet do that.  The site code if you wanted to add on demand conn checking would also need to be modified to allow for the conn checker to import the IP and port stats.\n\nJust throwing ideas out there.  But im thinking this would allow for the bulk of the code to be written in a language more familiar to our current coders which hopefully would make life easier.[/quote]\n\n\nyeah but the whole point of having a tracker written in c++ is because its faster than php. The actual code wont be that complex imo, so hopefully we (mobbo :D) can implement whatever solution we come to in ocelot.\n\nOne thing we can consider is the manual connchecker test that is on the new site: http://empornium.mooo.com/user.php?action=connchecker\n\nAlso thinking about it the connchecker could query the users ip records and pre-fill the boxes for the user. Staff might not get a useable ip address. Hmm.... depends exactly what we query (there are ip\'s stored in at least 3 different places as it happens...)\n\n- perhaps the results of a manual connchecker test should be stored wherever we store the connectable status, so if a user uses that the tracker dosent have to repeat it later.\n',84499,'2012-10-12 19:01:03'),(47978,6112,84499,'2012-10-12 19:33:03','\r\nOh Mobbo - if you get on irc we will get you into the staff channel so we can chat sometime. You will need to register your irc nick with nickserver.',NULL,NULL),(47979,6112,84499,'2012-10-12 19:35:50','\r\n\r\nI changed the thread title... no pressure Mobbo :lol:',NULL,NULL),(47980,6112,84499,'2012-10-12 23:37:41','maybe we can make the looping update more efficient too:\n\n[code]\n\n// get peers who do not have status = \'1\' OR where status has not been set for over a week.\npeers = SELECT distinct xbt.peer_id, xbt.ip, xbt.port, ucs.Status\n         FROM users_connectable_status AS ucs\n         JOIN xbt_files_users AS xbt ON xbt.peer_id=ucs.UserID\n        WHERE ucs.Status = \'0\'\n           OR ucs.Time < \'Now()- ( 7*24*3600 )\'; // ( - 1 week )\n\n// do check for unconnectable/timed out peers:\n\nSQL_0 = \"\";\nSQL_1 = \"\";\ndiv0 = \"\";\ndiv1 = \"\";\ncurrent = Now(); // current utc time in seconds\n\nfor each peer in peers\n{\n   // do the connectable test\n   if ( socket(ip, port) )\n   {\n      // build query string \n      SQL_1 += div1 + \"(\'peer.peer_id\',\'1\',\'current\')\" ;\n      div1 = \",\";\n\n   } else {\n      // build query string \n      SQL_0 += div0 + \"(\'peer.peer_id\',\'0\',\'current\')\" ;\n      div0 = \",\";\n   }\n\n}\n\n// update db with connectable status\nSQL = \"INSERT INTO users_connectable_status (UserID, Status, Time) VALUES \" + SQL_0 + \n ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE Status=\'0\', Time=\'current\'\";\n\nSQL = \"INSERT INTO users_connectable_status (UserID, Status, Time) VALUES \" + SQL_1 + \n ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE Status=\'1\', Time=\'current\'\";\n\n[/code]',84499,'2012-10-12 23:42:35'),(47981,6112,84499,'2012-10-12 23:48:40','\r\nI think in mysql that is functionally equivalent to doing\r\n[code]UPDATE table SET val2=x, val3=y WHERE val1 IN ( p1, p2, p3, ... , pN )[/code]\r\n\r\nwhich is another way to construct those queries :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(47982,6115,84499,'2012-10-13 00:07:50','Clownius got this on emp:\n\n[quote=salvia5x]\n\nHi,\n\nI saw your post in the Current site status thread in the forum about C++ help. I\'ve got quite of a bit of experience with C++ system-level programming (10+ years at a major \"three letter\" multinational that you would definitely recognize). Also, was a cheggit member since nearly the beginning. I can\'t donate an immense amount of time, but if you\'re in a jam I can probably carve off an evening here and there to help out. Sounds like things may already be moving forward, but do let me know if you need another hand.\n\nRegards,\n\ns.\n[/quote]\n\nMobbo - do you want some assistance? I am inclined to say lets see how we do for at least a week or so, perhaps I should reply to him saying we are just trying something out but if we get stuck we might give him a call? Thoughts?',84499,'2012-10-13 00:08:12'),(47983,6115,94952,'2012-10-13 00:15:07','Sounds good we should hammer out how we want to deal with it first.\n\nBut if he can help that\'s great.',94952,'2012-10-13 00:16:16'),(47984,6112,94952,'2012-10-13 00:30:56','[quote=mifune,f3112,27981]I think in mysql that is functionally equivalent to doing\r\n[code]UPDATE table SET val2=x, val3=y WHERE val1 IN ( p1, p2, p3, ... , pN )[/code]\r\n\r\nwhich is another way to construct those queries :hmmm:[/quote]\r\n\r\nThat is correct and a much nicer looking code.',NULL,NULL),(47985,6115,47234,'2012-10-13 01:36:41','Well if you guys decide you can use the assistance  i gave him the details of that test tracker.  At this point if you want his help give him access to this forum and i can set up another user account on the server in minutes.  Obviously then PM the details.',NULL,NULL),(47986,6115,1,'2012-10-13 13:44:09','he got access here.',NULL,NULL),(47987,6116,70679,'2012-10-13 14:45:25','So it does not get forgotten I post it here too\r\n-------------------------------------------------\r\nOK I think I saw one too many of these...\r\n\r\nCan anyone help me with sending some credits my way? D; I was really excited finding this site but I never really knew that there was a ratio I had to stick by. I used my credits before but im still stuck in a low ratio. Not only that but I\'ve been trying to seed the only 4 videos I still have as the rest of them have been deleted but they seem to not be popular.\r\nPlease help.\r\n\r\nSo I did give a fresh look at the registration page and supposing it is not too difficult to make canges there, small one....\r\n\r\nPut on top of the check boxes in bold and red\r\n\r\nI understand that this is a private tracker and if I do not keep a ratio of at least XX I will lose my download privileges or worst. Before I go ga-ga and get myself in trouble I will find out how to best do this here.\r\n\r\nhere a link to the obvious we state umpteen times about FL torrents, torrents with high seed/peer ratio etc. But just simple. Oh yeah and SEEDING not hitting and running thinking this is TPB.\r\n\r\nSo just a suggestion that MIGHT eliminate some work...',NULL,NULL),(47988,6117,70679,'2012-10-13 17:30:37','To avoid looking around here is a simplified step by step.\n(You can also check out the IRC Network\'s website for hints and tips. [url=http://www.digitalirc.org/]www.digitalirc.org[/url])\n\n[b]1. Join (open) the channel with:[/b] \n\n[quote]/join #channel[/quote]\n\nFor example:\n\n[quote]/join #empornium-secrets[/quote]\n\nNote: the channel should not be already in use. If you find out it is then chose another name. If it worked you will be the only one in the channel with a \"@\" before your nick. Means you are the operator.\n\n[b]2. Register your channel with:[/b]\n\n[quote]/cs register #channel password description[/quote]\n\nFor example:\n\n[quote]/cs register #empornium-secrets sexygirls empornium secrets[/quote]\n\nOnce you have done that, you should see your name in the nick list prefixed with the \"~\" symbol. This means you are the owner of the channel.\n\nOn Empornium IRC a Services Bot (either \"God\" or \"Drone\") will automatically be assigned to your channel. You can change or remove it later.\n\n[b]3. Hide your channel with:[/b]\n\n[quote]!set mlock +nts[/quote]\n\nIf you want to make it invite only:\n\n[quote]!set mlock +ntis[/quote]\n\nNote: You should also add this channel to your autojoin list with /ns ajoin add #channel . This will auto invite you to the channel.\n\n[b]4. Switch bot with:[/b]\n\nCheck the list of available not names with:\n\n[quote]/bs botlist[/quote]\n\nAssign your chosen bot with\n\n[quote]/bs assign #channel botname[/quote]\n\nFor example for empornium bot:\n\n[quote]/bs assign #empornium-secrets ^empornium^[/quote]\n\nNote: ^empornium^ is only assignable by IRCOp\'s (a.k.a. Clownius, barumba, Lanz, mifune or MrRandom)\n\n[b]5. Add nicks to the access list with:[/b]\n\nTo use the Access system (prefered) do:\n\n[quote]!set xop off[/quote]\n\nTo add a person to the access list:\n\n[quote]!acc add nick level[/quote]\n\nFor example:\n\n[quote]!acc add barumba 5[/quote]\n\nmost used are 3 for voice and 5 for operator. (Level 10 is channel admin, and 9999 is if you wish to add a second channel owner. Level 9 is only used on #empornium since it has been given special access priv\'s on that channel -MrR)\n\n[b]6. Invite people so they can access your channel with:[/b]\n\n[quote]!invite nick[/quote]\n\nFor example:\n\n[quote]!invite barumba[/quote]\n\n----------------------------------------------\nShould be all if I forgot anything will edit.\n',70679,'2012-10-14 18:34:19'),(47989,6118,84499,'2012-10-13 17:43:58','git@github.com:mifune/gazelle.git\ngit@github.com:mifune/ocelot.git\n\n\nMobbo:  You will need a github account and a ssh key, PM me your details (or get on IRC!) and I will get you setup as a contributer.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n',84499,'2012-10-13 18:49:04'),(47990,6118,84499,'2012-10-13 17:49:08','Shamelessly ripped from a post lanz made at empforums:\n\n[b]How to setup git/ get a local dev server going.[/b]\n\nI made a folder in my home directory called www and git cloned gazelle there.\n\nin terminal:\n[code]\nmkdir ~/www\ncd www/\ngit clone git@github.com:mifune/gazelle.git\nit will create a folder called gazelle\ncd gazelle/\ngit remote add origin git@github.com:mifune/gazelle.git\ngit checkout work\n[/code]\n\nNow you should have gazelle in /home/<your username>/www/gazelle\n\nnow to get ocelot:\ngo back to the www folder\n[code]\ncd ..\ngit clone git@github.com:mifune/ocelot.git\ncd ocelot\ngit remote add origin git@github.com:mifune/ocelot.git\ngit checkout work\n[/code]\n\nThen in my hosts file I would add a fake domain in the list, like empornium.dev\n\n[code]\nsudo nano /etc/hosts\n127.0.0.1       empornium.dev\n[/code]\n(ctrl-o to save, ctrl-x to exit from nano)\n\nthen I would add a new virtual host to apache:\n\n[code]\nsudo nano /etc/apache2/sites-available/empornium-dev\nwith the following content:\n\n<VirtualHost 127.0.0.1:80>\nServerName empornium.dev\nServerAlias www.empornium.dev\nDocumentRoot /home/<your username>/www/gazelle\n</VirtualHost>\n[/code]\n\nTo enable the new virtual host:\n[code]\nsudo a2ensite empornium-dev\nsudo /etc/init.d/apache2 reload\n[/code]\n\n\n\nAlso: one thing that can catch you out - you need to copy the file gazelle/classes/config.template -> gazelle/classes/config.php and change certain values - like the mysql username & password.\n\nGet on irc, or maybe PM (but IRC would be better) and I will give you the missing values.',84499,'2012-10-13 23:17:49'),(47991,6118,84499,'2012-10-13 18:39:47','\r\n\r\nokay i updated the test server with the new fork, the site is still here so I think it worked.',NULL,NULL),(47992,6112,84499,'2012-10-14 00:20:55','I have been looking at the peerlist code on the site and it occurs to me that maybe we ought to store connectable status not per user but per user/ip ?\n\nwhat I am thinking of is when someone has a seedbox and a home connection - it would be nice for it to say specifically if each is connectable.\n\nThe complication is users with dynamic ip\'s...\n\nMaybe we have an ip field in the users_connectable_status table, make the primary key a compound key; UserID / IP. Then daily have the scheduler delete records that are older than one week from users_connectable_status.\n\n[code]\n\ncurrent = Now(); // current utc time in seconds\n\n// get peers who do not have status = \'1\' OR where status has not been set for over a week.\n \npeers = SELECT xbt.peer_id, xbt.ip, xbt.port\n          FROM xbt_files_users AS xbt \n     LEFT JOIN users_connectable_status AS ucs ON xbt.peer_id=ucs.UserID AND xbt.ip=ucs.IP\n      GROUP BY xbt.peer_id, xbt.ip\n         WHERE ucs.Status IS NULL \n            OR ucs.Status = \'0\'\n            OR ucs.Time < \'current - ( 7*24*3600 )\'; // ( - 1 week )\n\n\n// do check for unconnectable/timed out peers:\n\nSQL_0 = \"\";\nSQL_1 = \"\";\ndiv0 = \"\";\ndiv1 = \"\";\n\nfor each peer in peers\n{\n   // do the connectable test\n   if ( socket(ip, port) )\n   {\n      // build query string \n      SQL_1 += div1 + \"(\'peer.peer_id\', \'peer.ip\', \'1\', \'current\')\" ;\n      div1 = \",\";\n\n   } else {\n      // build query string \n      SQL_0 += div0 + \"(\'peer.peer_id\', \'peer.ip\', \'0\', \'current\')\" ;\n      div0 = \",\";\n   }\n\n}\n\n// update db with connectable status \nSQL = \"INSERT INTO users_connectable_status (UserID, IP, Status, Time) VALUES \" + SQL_0 + \n ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE Status=\'0\', Time=\'current\'\";\n\nSQL = \"INSERT INTO users_connectable_status (UserID, IP, Status, Time) VALUES \" + SQL_1 + \n ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE Status=\'1\', Time=\'current\'\";\n\n[/code]',84499,'2012-10-14 02:36:27'),(47993,6112,84499,'2012-10-14 00:59:15','\r\n\r\nokay the structure for users_connectable_status is now:\r\n[code]+--------+------------------+------+-----+---------+-------+\r\n| Field  | Type             | Null | Key | Default | Extra |\r\n+--------+------------------+------+-----+---------+-------+\r\n| UserID | int(10) unsigned | NO   | PRI | NULL    |       |\r\n| IP     | varchar(15)      | NO   | PRI |         |       |\r\n| Status | enum(\'0\',\'1\')    | NO   | MUL | 1       |       |\r\n| Time   | int(10)          | NO   | MUL | 0       |       |\r\n+--------+------------------+------+-----+---------+-------+\r\n[/code]',NULL,NULL),(47994,6112,47234,'2012-10-14 04:12:49','I think by IP is a very good idea yes Mifune.  I know i personally have the seedbox and the Home link.  I know other people have even more than that :)',NULL,NULL),(47995,6110,84499,'2012-10-14 19:20:37','[quote=Clownius,f3110,27929][quote=mifune,f3110,27928]:hmmm:\n\nmaybe the edit timer for users (iirc its about 10 mins) should be reset when a post is merged?[/quote]\n\nSounds reasonable[/quote]\n\n\nThe problem is this: there is no way to distinguish a merge from a normal edit. So if resetting on a merge it will also be resetting on an edit - unless merging instead of just changing the edit time changed the actual post time - but thats a very non-intuitive way of having it in the interface. Ie. you would expect the post time at the top of the post to reflect the original post time not the time the post was merged into.\n\nIf it resets on an edit (this would actually be done by instead of just testing if the orig post time is < 15 mins ago testing that OR the edit post time < 15 mins ago) it would potentially mean you could edit an old post (if no-one else has posted after it) after any amount of time by merging a new post into it, then you can edit the whole of the old post. There is no way to only allow the user to edit the merged portion of the post because when you merge by definition it just appends the new post to the current post contents. (I mean it could be done but it would mean a fairly major rewrite of the way edits and merges are handled etc and its not going to happen...)\n\nStill this is probably the best solution; you can edit up to 15 mins after the last edit/merge was done. We will just have to be aware that means in some cases users can edit their posts a lot later than we might think. ',84499,'2012-10-14 23:29:17'),(47996,6110,84499,'2012-10-14 22:18:18','\r\n\r\nOkay you can now edit posts and comments 15 mins after they are last posted/edited/merged. Please test!',NULL,NULL),(47997,6119,84499,'2012-10-15 19:02:44','\r\n\r\nWe have set up a dev channel at #empornium-dev\r\n\r\ncurrently those on the access list are:\r\nmifune\r\nadmin\r\nDave\r\nclownius\r\nMobbo\r\n(and MrRandom for irc support!)\r\n \r\nif you have problems getting in ask someone already in to invite you again (shouldnt need doing though).\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47998,6115,84499,'2012-10-15 20:08:32','\r\n\r\nI am a bit confused as to what the status is here?\r\n\r\nWhat has he been told exactly?\r\n\r\nRight now he has access to this forum and afaik thats it so far...\r\n\r\nMobbo - do you want the guy as a co-coder? Or just contributing in this forum (to start with maybe)? I am happy to have him in here and to give him contributor access to the source on github if thats what we want, or he could just be in this forum and giving advice?  but whatever we want lets explicitly invite him to do so!\r\n',NULL,NULL),(47999,6112,84499,'2012-10-15 22:57:02','[quote=Mobbo,f3112,27984][quote=mifune,f3112,27981]I think in mysql that is functionally equivalent to doing\r\n[code]UPDATE table SET val2=x, val3=y WHERE val1 IN ( p1, p2, p3, ... , pN )[/code]\r\n\r\nwhich is another way to construct those queries :hmmm:[/quote]\r\n\r\nThat is correct and a much nicer looking code.[/quote]\r\n\r\nUsing INSERT INTO means it will create new entries as well though, the UPDATE syntax is functionally equivalent to what happens with duplicate entries only.\r\n\r\n\r\nOn how long should we treat a positive connectable status as good: perhaps 1 week is too long, maybe 1 day ? \r\n\r\nI added a line in the scheduler to clean up the users_connectable_status - atm the scheduler does this every 15 mins: \r\n[code]$DB->query(\"DELETE FROM users_connectable_status WHERE Time<\'\".time() - (3600*24*7).\"\'\");[/code]\r\n\r\nalthough thinking about it perhaps the cleanup should be done in the tracker as well?\r\n\r\nand logically we could drop the time clause from the select statement in the tracker code as we know that table only contains records younger than whatever time limit we use:\r\n[code]\r\nDELETE FROM users_connectable_status WHERE Time < now() - (3600 * 24)\r\n\r\npeers = SELECT xbt.peer_id, xbt.ip, xbt.port\r\n         FROM xbt_files_users AS xbt\r\n    LEFT JOIN users_connectable_status AS ucs ON xbt.peer_id=ucs.UserID AND xbt.ip=ucs.IP\r\n     GROUP BY xbt.peer_id, xbt.ip\r\n        WHERE ucs.Status IS NULL\r\n           OR ucs.Status = \'0\'[/code]\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(48000,6112,94952,'2012-10-16 01:26:59','I think that using the tracker to handle the clean up is better and faster but since we don\'t really have a C-coder on hand I think that handling it in php is good enough. \r\n\r\nI have been bashing away at the tracker-code with very little progress.',NULL,NULL),(48001,6115,94952,'2012-10-16 01:29:45','I have been trying to get the c++ code do my bidding but this is obviously beyond my capabilities. \r\nI get hung up on type declarations. So getting salvia5x in on this is a good thing. \r\nI can continue to try to get the code to work but it is better if someone with a better understanding does it. The code we are going for isn\'t complicated and shouldn\'t take long for an experienced coder to hammer out.',NULL,NULL),(48002,6115,47234,'2012-10-16 01:43:51','Well i pm\'d him back but checking my messages he hasnt read it of yet.  So.....\r\n\r\nIm not sure if hes going to find the time either.',NULL,NULL),(48003,6115,84499,'2012-10-16 02:13:46','\r\nThanks for the effort anyway Mobbo, I hope you wont disappear right away - we may still want to pick your brains.\r\n\r\nHopefully salvia5x will check in in the next few days :smile1:',NULL,NULL),(48004,6115,94952,'2012-10-16 02:42:20','I\'m not going away. I will be around. I will try to get the code working too. I just don\'t want you to get the wrong idea. \r\nI rather this is handled by someone more qualified. But I will help anyway I can.',NULL,NULL),(48005,6115,47234,'2012-10-16 03:30:25','We seem to have a shortage of more qualified people around here :lol:\n\nIn any case we are a lot further ahead than we were before :)  So my thanks and im sure the thankls of every Perv on Emp when its finished :)\n\nWorst case we send out a general cry for help on Emp.  Maybe someone will come out of the woodwork.',47234,'2012-10-16 03:31:23'),(48006,6115,84499,'2012-10-16 03:41:59','\r\nIts not a question of being more qualified - its a question of having some specific skills (ie. working knowledge of c++ syntax and compiling c++ apps).\r\n\r\nThe code needed is not actually that complicated.',NULL,NULL),(48007,6115,94952,'2012-10-16 04:49:03','[quote=mifune,f3115,28006]Its not a question of being more qualified - its a question of having some specific skills (ie. working knowledge of c++ syntax and compiling c++ apps).\r\n\r\nThe code needed is not actually that complicated.[/quote]\r\nI agree. I meant I\'m not qualified to muck about with the tracker-code. And the code is pretty simple which is a huge bonus. ',NULL,NULL),(48008,6115,47234,'2012-10-16 05:23:46','If you want to see a disaster i can have a crack at it after asking google for help :lol:',NULL,NULL),(48009,6112,84499,'2012-10-16 16:59:38','\r\nI have been looking at the ocelot code again and trying to understand the logic flow a bit better.\r\n\r\nIt seems to me that the correct place to get the port is in the announce function in worker.cpp - I think this function processes each peer as they join the tracker and updates current peers as the tracker gets the info from the clients.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/mifune/ocelot/blob/work/worker.cpp\r\nthe port is already read into a var in worker.cpp line 364: \r\n[code]364 |       unsigned int port = strtolong(params[\"port\"]);[/code]\r\n\r\nthe current peers details are stored (for later insertion when db->flush() is called from the scheduler) at line 500:	\r\n[code]\r\n497 |       std::stringstream record;\r\n498 |       record << \'(\' << u.id << \',\' << tor.id << \',\' << active << \',\' << uploaded << \',\' << downloaded << \',\' << upspeed << \',\' << downspeed << \',\' << left << \',\' << (cur_time - p->first_announced) << \',\' << p->announces << \',\';\r\n499 |       std::string record_str = record.str();\r\n500 |       db->record_peer(record_str, ip, peer_id, headers[\"user-agent\"]);[/code]\r\n\r\nSo I think we can just add the port at the end of the record var: (I think this because port is an int and all the other vars appended to record are also numbers, whereas the vars passed as parameters to db_>record_peer() are strings/binary and are quoted properly after they are passed on).\r\n[code]\r\n498 |       record << \'(\' << u.id << \',\' << tor.id << \',\' << active << \',\' << uploaded << \',\' << downloaded << \',\' << upspeed << \',\' << downspeed << \',\' << left << \',\' << (cur_time - p->first_announced) << \',\' << p->announces << \',\' << port << \',\';\r\n499 |       std::string record_str = record.str();\r\n500 |       db->record_peer(record_str, ip, peer_id, headers[\"user-agent\"]);[/code]\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/mifune/ocelot/blob/work/db.cpp\r\nThen we need to update the sql insert string in db.cpp mysql::flush_peers() method at line 250 adding in the port field at the right place:\r\n[code]\r\n250 |       sql = \"INSERT INTO xbt_files_users (uid,fid,active,uploaded,downloaded,upspeed,downspeed,remaining,\" +\r\n                 std::string(\"timespent,announced,port,ip,peer_id,useragent,mtime) VALUES \") + update_peer_buffer +\r\n                 \" ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE active=VALUES(active), uploaded=VALUES(uploaded), \" +\r\n                 \"downloaded=VALUES(downloaded), upspeed=VALUES(upspeed), \" +\r\n                 \"downspeed=VALUES(downspeed), remaining=VALUES(remaining), \" +\r\n                 \"timespent=VALUES(timespent), announced=VALUES(announced), port=VALUES(port), \" +\r\n                 \"mtime=VALUES(mtime)\";\r\n[/code]\r\n\r\n\r\nIf we can store the port then we could at least get a users connection status on demand on the site :hmmm:',NULL,NULL),(48010,6112,94952,'2012-10-16 18:03:31','I finally figured out what I as doing wrong. I\'m about to push my edits to github.\n\nPushed my updates. The code compiles but I havn\'t tested it yet. Has I have no sql server setup.\nThe update is exactly as you described it Mifune.',94952,'2012-10-16 18:15:15'),(48011,6120,84499,'2012-10-16 19:27:07','\r\n\r\nInterestingly the lack of getting a connectable status in ocelot appears to be a deliberate design choice... that is what I infer from some old posts I have found where other devs scorn inquiries about how to implement such things by saying ocelot is a lightweight daemon.\r\n\r\nWhich makes me wonder... we have approx 30k peers at any one time. lets assume for simplicity the num of unique peers a day is around 30-40k - do we really want to do 30-40k connection tests a day/week? There is an overhead just in terms of the connections, then the tests themselves are fairly fast when they are connectable but deadly slow when they aren\'t. The worker->announce() function does most of the work in the tracker, its where each peer is processed and as far as I can work out gets called every time a client sends data to the tracker (excepting scrapes). Having it hanging around waiting for unconnectable sockets to time out may just be a bad design choice. \r\n\r\nThe goal here is for all users to be connectable, so we record the status and display a red warning banner to them if they arent. But unless a user visits the site the information will go unused.\r\n\r\nOne approach could be that the default state for users is \'unset\' and they have to themselves go and run the connchecker on the site to get rid of the banner. This would mean we leave the tracker pretty much as is but with a small change to store the port with each connection. Then the scheduler (which already does some stuff with the connections table to get bonus credits) could store ip\'s for users in the users_connectable_status table with status = -1 (a flag for unset). When a user visits the site it checks for the most recent ip for that user and what its status is. The default connectable state for each record would be \'unset\' - which could display a red banner saying \'Are you connectable?\'. When they click on that it takes them to the connchecker page with the values filled in - whatever result they get is stored for that ip address. If they get a no result then the banner changes to \'You are not connectable!\' and if they get a yes result it removes the banner. Yes results would be stored until they are overwritten by a new check by the user, No results until they are overwritten or after a week. Ip addresses for a user that have not been checked would be displayed as \'unset/unknown\' in the peerlists. There would also be a button for staff to initiate a connection test for a users ip (although it would only be clickable/present when the user has an active connection).\r\n\r\nAlthough it would be faster if there were the same amount of connection tests in c++ this approach has the advantage of doing the least possible number of tests. Some users will not bother to test, and the delay from when the site first records a users ip and port to when they next login and do the test will mean the tests get delayed... and for users with dynamic ip\'s who kind of spam up any connection test regime if they dont login and their ip changes in the meantime it will skip doing a test unnecessarily. I think there will be less overall load even though the test is being done in php.\r\n\r\nA possible issue with this approach is dynamic ip\'s : users that get a new ip regularly could pretty annoyed with having to record a new result each time. One possibility could be a flag in each users settings for \'suppress no connect banner\', if a user has a frequently changing ip they could prove to us they are always connectable (by recording yes results for a while - staff/fls can see all the connectable records for each ip on each user page under the \'Personal\' stats box) and then staff could set the flag for that user so they arent bothered by them anymore. I was thinking we could have some system that did something clever with the subnet part of the address but on examining actual ip records of users, dynamic ip\'s are surprisingly often not that closely related.\r\n\r\n\r\nAnyway its a kind of different philosophy to the current system, we would be putting the burden on the users to prove they are connectable (or live with the red banner). \r\n\r\n\r\nIf we think is a possible way forward do we want to run it by the other staff as well? I cant really get to actually coding before the weekend realistically anyway. And I\'m presuming we will be able to make the relatively simple change to the ocelot code needed (and when I say \'we\' I mean Mobbo, or maybe the new guy).\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(48012,6112,84499,'2012-10-16 19:30:24','\ncool looks good :gjob:\n\n\none thing: You didnt add a [code]port=VALUES(port)[/code] to the ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE clause. We\'ll need that as a lot of torrent clients change ports automatically.',84499,'2012-10-16 19:34:26'),(48013,6112,94952,'2012-10-16 19:58:23','Fixed the on duplicate key thing.\nThis code should be safe to test on the tracker. And after a few minutes there should be port numbers in the database',94952,'2012-10-16 19:59:33'),(48014,6112,90006,'2012-10-16 23:07:36','Hi,\r\n\r\nI\'ve exchanged a couple of messages with mifune about giving a hand with the C++ struggles you\'re are having and am just sort of catching up on the thread. I\'ve got quite a bit of experience with C++ on UNIX/Linux, including several years of client-server and am happy to help out as much as I can. I haven\'t had a chance to dig into Ocelot yet or the latest commit and am not totally sure where you guys are with it, though.\r\n\r\nIt sounds like you\'ve found a decent spot for grabbing the port. Is the connection check the next problem?',NULL,NULL),(48015,6112,84499,'2012-10-17 00:27:19','\r\nHi salvia5x :wave:\r\n\r\nThanks for joining us  :demon: - I think we got the port being saved - or we will have when we compile it and run it lol. I will see if we can get clownius to set you up with an account on the test server because to be frank I would prefer it if someone who knew what they was doing does that.\r\n\r\nConnection check: Yes but I am having second thoughts about doing the connection check at all in the tracker. See this thread: http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3120&page=1#post28011. Would be good to get your thoughts in there.\r\n\r\n\r\nI will wait till you have had a look at the source maybe but theres a couple of other things that I would at least like to pick your brains over. (one is very simple actually - lanz remmed out the code that stores some kind of peer history as the table didnt exist and there is nothing in the frontend to do with it, but I have recreated the table and wouldnt mind capturing that info as I\'m pretty sure thats at least part of the missing anti-cheating tools). \r\n  \r\nI will add you as a contributer to the project. We are working from the work branch of the source.',NULL,NULL),(48016,6120,47234,'2012-10-17 01:20:09','Im getting my head around this and this is how i understand it.\r\n\r\nTracker stores peer IP and port number but does not check it. (Great)\r\nIt assumes the user is not connectable.\r\nRed Banner displays\r\nUser and/or staff member can use the stored data to do a conn check using the site code.  But only if users is currently a peer on a torrent.\r\nIf passed Red banner goes away.\r\nData is stored.\r\nIf User IP changes goes back to not connectable and Red Banner displays.\r\nCon Checker is used again.\r\nElse if IP stays the same (or is listed against the user as connectable) Banner stays gone.\r\n\r\nFor those users with dynamic IP\'s i would prefer that after x passed checks on IP\'s banner stays gone even if IP changes unless they fail a manual conn check.  Another option seems to be a tick box to say consider connectable.  I prefer automatic as it requires less intervention.\r\n\r\nHow long would we keep this record?  Permanent?\r\n\r\nI can see this idea saving a lot of tracker load and manual checks wont be anywhere near as regular as currently so great idea i think Mifune.  Now let me know what i missed.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(48017,6120,84499,'2012-10-17 01:27:52','couple of changes for clarity:\n\n[quote]\nTracker stores peer IP and port number (in the site db) but does not check it. (Great)\n[s]It[/s] The site assumes the user is not connectable.\n[*]If no IP/port is stored then the site does nothing (the user is not actually using the tracker so we can ignore this)\n[*]If a record(s) for an IP/port exists for that user - the site gets the latest record only.\n[*]If the record has no connectable status (never tested) then you get a red banner saying \'Are you connectable?\' (could be a different shade/color?)\n[*]If the record has a negative result stored then you get a red banner saying \'You are not connectable!\'\n[*]If the user has a positive result stored for the latest ip/port they get no banner.\n[ note: older records for that user\'s ip\'s are viewable by the user and the staff on the user page ]\nUser and/or staff member can use the stored data to do a conn check using the site code.  But only if users is currently a peer on a torrent.\nIf passed Red banner goes away.\n[s]Data[/s] Result is stored.\nIf User IP changes goes back to not connectable and Red Banner displays.\nCon Checker is used again.\nElse if IP stays the same ([s]or is[/s] which means it is listed against the user as connectable) Banner stays gone.\n[/quote]\n\n\nthe red banner \'Are you connectable?\' links to the connchecker page\nprobably the red banner \'You are not connectable!\' links to the \'getting connectable\' help topic.\n\nrecords are stored for... a while. Perhaps they are stored until they are a month old then reaped - and when the tracker updates a record it resets the time. So it would only delete your ip/port status if you dont connect to the tracker for a month. Could be 2 months... or whatever we feel is the right amount of time to not overly annoy users. At some point we have to reap old records or else the table will grow forever.',84499,'2012-10-17 01:33:32'),(48018,6120,47234,'2012-10-17 01:36:21','2-3 months sounds good :)',NULL,NULL),(48019,6120,94952,'2012-10-17 02:45:38','I have been doing a fair bit of thinking on this as well.\r\n[*] There are no code or hooks in the original code to handle connectability, this is a design choice to keep it sleek. We are trying to add a feature ocelot never had. Much like FL and slots\r\n[*] Adding this will increase load on the server.\r\n[*] To handle the actual connection check in the announce cycle could be a could.problem even with the smart things we have come up with. I will come back to this.\r\n[*] The connection check [b]MUST[/b] threaded. We can\'t have the tracker stalling for 1-2 seconds on every failed connection. I totally unfamiliar with threading in c++ and this can go horrible wrong if not handled carefully, so I can\'t build this.\r\n\r\nWorker.cpp does the bulk of the work for the tracker it handles the announce from the torrentclients. \r\nNow I\'m gonna make a lot of assumptions; Users=100000, torrents per user=5 and announce interval = 30 minutes (best case).\r\nMath time (yay!). This means if the code runs completely serially (can\'t tell if it uses threading, I haven\'t looked that hard). 500 k announces every 1800 seconds = 278 announces per second or a one announce must be handled in 3.6 ms. And that is with our current load. So a connection check should really be handled as a separate process. As for recording the port into the database that is a very small change no extra calls. It just passes one extra string of 5 numbers.\r\n\r\nBut not sell ourself short we have an idea how to reduce the code used in the announce cycle to 2 or 3 sql-calls if we wanted but I think the way forward is a separate scheduler for connect-test or Mifunes manual approach outlined above. \r\n\r\nI would like to hear from Salvia5x on this: How long would you estimate it would take to check a socket() 100 000 times? With a failure rate of say 5%. I did some quick reading on this. Apparently there is a lot more to this than I thought especially on Linux. Socket would probably be the stupid way to go, rawsockets looks more flexible. To put it another way what we are doing is basicly port-scanning :) just multiple host instead of multiple ports. A port scan involving 100k+ ports to test. Yeah, this needs to be multi-threaded and completed outside the 30 minute announce window.\r\n\r\nSorry about the rambling post, I was thinking as I was writing.',NULL,NULL),(48020,6112,94952,'2012-10-17 04:53:42','Well after some self doubt, general dicking around and a very nice session on IRC we now have a new version of ocelot up and running that records port numbers. While not perfect yet it is a big hurdle cleared. :beer2: \n\nI checked a few ip/port pairs and they are connectable so the correct data is recorded.\n\nThanks Mifune and Clownius',94952,'2012-10-17 04:58:14'),(48021,6112,84499,'2012-10-17 13:23:47',' :happydancing: \r\n\r\n :choir: \r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(48022,6120,48010,'2012-10-17 15:59:14','I\'m begining to think the best way is to get rid of this.\n\nI was suggested before by Mobbo as the easiest way forward. I posted on emp.me to disable it and see what happens. As I said in another thread other big sites dont use it or removed it.\n\nI like the idea of just referring the member to the conn_checker if they contact us (similar to how we do it on emp.me right now) and if it fails links them to port-forwarding and after that the forums if they need further help. \nmifunes idea is good as it helps all members but is the server load and coding time to do it worth it ?? We really need to get off the current emp.me tbdev asap\n\nthe conn_checker could be part on V.2 ?? but not essential right now (I know you coding guys see it a challenge to fix it :grin:) but at the end of the day is it really necessary?\n\nJust my thoughts. Dave',48010,'2012-10-17 16:07:27'),(48023,6121,48010,'2012-10-17 17:42:09','[url=http://xxx.freeimage.us/share.php?id=DED0_507EEDCA][img]http://xxx.freeimage.us/thumb.php?id=DED0_507EEDCA[/img][/url]',NULL,NULL),(48024,6121,48010,'2012-10-17 17:56:24','it dosen\'t work\n\nPort 60641 on 113.169.168.185 failed to connect\n\non this torrent on emp.me http://torrents.empornium.me/peerlist.php?id=47371#seeders\n\nDave 	Yes 	0.00 kB 	0.00 kB/s 	0.00 kB 	0.00 kB/s 	--- 	4.30% 	4:39:54 	23:57 	Deluge 1.3.5',48010,'2012-10-17 18:02:59'),(48025,6121,48010,'2012-10-17 18:19:05','also failed on my test account davedave\r\n\r\n113.169.176.112 same port 60641',NULL,NULL),(48026,6122,94804,'2012-10-17 18:40:31','conn. check says failed but I\'m seeding just fine at the \"old\" empornium, and I checked my settings in uTorrent and they all match',NULL,NULL),(48027,6121,48010,'2012-10-17 18:49:42','schlager opened another thread posting the same - it doesnt work !!',NULL,NULL),(48028,6122,84499,'2012-10-17 19:25:26','\r\n\r\nIts possible you managed to try it before I fixed an error with it - I just tried it for you now and it said you are connectable. (could also just be a random failure to connect, the internet is funny sometimes).',NULL,NULL),(48029,6121,84499,'2012-10-17 19:44:54','\r\ntry again :smile1:',NULL,NULL),(48030,6123,84499,'2012-10-17 20:24:40','\r\n\r\nI have implemented a manual conn-checking system. If a user has recent activity on the tracker the site will prompt them to check if they are connectable, once they record a result it is stored for a month after their last activity on the tracker. Results are stored per user/ip. If a user has no status recorded or a no result they will keep getting prompted.',NULL,NULL),(48031,6123,94952,'2012-10-17 21:42:42','Worked great for me.',NULL,NULL),(48032,6120,1,'2012-10-17 23:22:45','I think will be a good idea to just leave as a tool, to don\'t prompt user.\r\nif they want to know if are or are not connectable just use the tool.\r\n',NULL,NULL),(48033,6120,84499,'2012-10-17 23:27:30','\r\nI have already implemented a manual system with an auto-prompt. The user will only get an annoying red banner if they are actually on the tracker though, and then they are just 2 clicks away from getting a connectable test... I dont think thats too much. Users being unconnectable has to be the number one reason why users are lusers (ie. cannot seed and end up getting limited), I think we should keep the auto prompter!',NULL,NULL),(48034,6105,84499,'2012-10-17 23:32:46','\r\n\r\nWell I think we have the connectable issue wrapped up...\r\n\r\nWhy dont we do a resynch this weekend - maybe alex wants to test the db import and installing sphinx - and then go public beta next week with an aim to changeover the following weekend maybe?\r\n\r\nnote: There is still content needed - [url=/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3061]See this *TODO* thread for details[/url] - its not the end of the world if its not done but if we have an end in sight maybe we can light a fire under the staff to contribute.',NULL,NULL),(48035,6061,84499,'2012-10-17 23:36:17','\n\n :bounce: ',84499,'2012-10-17 23:38:13'),(48036,6015,84499,'2012-10-17 23:39:21',' :bounce: ',NULL,NULL),(48037,6123,49532,'2012-10-17 23:59:46','I don\'t see what\'s new? I\'ve been using the conn-checker for weeks.',NULL,NULL),(48038,6123,84499,'2012-10-18 00:12:41','\nthe actual connchecker is part of the original gazelle source, for a long time it wasnt linked to from anywhere - and just in the last 2 days we have got the tracker recording the port info and made it so the site prompts users to check their status.\n\nits possible you never saw a prompt to record your connectable status as iirc I implemented the connchecker saving the result before I added the code that displays the prompt!\n\nIf you go to your user page and look under the \'Personal\' stats box on the right hand side you should see a connectable record for any ip\'s you have recently used on the tracker. You can remove the record of your current ip if you want - and then if you wait ~15 minutes the tracker will update and then the site will prompt you (in the header).',84499,'2012-10-18 00:15:44'),(48039,6123,84499,'2012-10-18 00:19:24','\r\n\r\nThe end result of all this is that the connectable status in the peerlists actually means something, and the system is a more \'pro-active\' approach to getting users to be connectable. Whilst avoiding doing tens of thousands of connection tests a day (this is a significant load in tb.dev for example).',NULL,NULL),(48040,6123,86439,'2012-10-18 03:12:02','Log in\nRed bar at top, asking me to check\nDid so\nDetails already there for me, click check.\nGreen bar saying Im connected or similar such message.\n\nSeems to work as it should to me. Excellent especially if its saves resources.',86439,'2012-10-18 03:12:45'),(48041,6120,47234,'2012-10-18 04:21:15','Agreed Mifune i generally check that almost first when someone is limited.  At least 90% of the time they are not connectable.  Obviously this is slipping past many a perv.  Trying to convince them early its important can only save us a lot of staff messages and forum threads askign for bail outs.',NULL,NULL),(48042,6121,48010,'2012-10-18 16:05:26','ok it works now - good job',NULL,NULL),(48043,6124,84499,'2012-10-18 19:30:01','\r\nI think we should use a client blacklist instead of a whitelist.\r\n\r\nI have asked this question at the emp.me staff forum:\r\nhttp://torrents.empornium.me/forums.php?action=viewtopic&topicid=3477&page=p40889#40889\r\nand that is where any discussion about whether we should do it or not should probably go.\r\n\r\n\r\nIf we do decide to do it :\r\n\r\nI have had a look at the code for this and it should be a simple thing, in [b]worker.cpp[/b]:\r\n[code]\r\n227 |       if(whitelist.size() > 0) {\r\n228 |           bool found = false; // Found client in whitelist?\r\n229 |           for(unsigned int i = 0; i < whitelist.size(); i++) {\r\n230 |               if(peer_id.find(whitelist[i]) == 0) {\r\n231 |                   found = true;\r\n232 |                   break;\r\n233 |               }\r\n234 |           }\r\n235 |           \r\n236 |           if(!found) {\r\n237 |               return error(\"Your client is not on the whitelist\");\r\n238 |           }\r\n239 |       }\r\n[/code]\r\n\r\nso change line 236 to if(found) and for sanity I think change all instances of \'whitelist\' to \'blacklist\' - which I think will just mean updating [b]worker.cpp[/b] at lines  741 - 769  (adding and removing items when the tracker is running) and the declaration in [b]worker.h[/b] as well.\r\n\r\nWhat do you reckon? Have I missed anything stupid? \r\n',NULL,NULL),(48044,6124,94952,'2012-10-18 19:31:35','Looks right to me. I will get on that.\n\nEdit: I also needed to update db and ocelot files. Just to keep it consistent.',94952,'2012-10-18 20:09:12'),(48045,6124,84499,'2012-10-18 19:32:48','oh and obviously the message changes to \'Your client is blacklisted\' :)',NULL,NULL),(48046,6124,94952,'2012-10-18 20:10:04','Actually it is: Your client is blacklisted!\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(48047,6123,94804,'2012-10-18 21:13:14','[quote=knickers,f3123,28040]Seems to work as it should to me. Excellent especially if its saves resources.[/quote]\r\nHere as well now, thanks!',NULL,NULL),(48048,6122,94804,'2012-10-18 21:15:55','seems like this needs a -FIXED- in front of it, right?',NULL,NULL),(48049,6120,90006,'2012-10-18 21:21:11','[quote]I would like to hear from Salvia5x on this: How long would you estimate it would take to check a socket() 100 000 times? With a failure rate of say 5%. I did some quick reading on this. Apparently there is a lot more to this than I thought especially on Linux. Socket would probably be the stupid way to go, rawsockets looks more flexible. To put it another way what we are doing is basicly port-scanning :) just multiple host instead of multiple ports. A port scan involving 100k+ ports to test. Yeah, this needs to be multi-threaded and completed outside the 30 minute announce window.[/quote]\r\n\r\nMulti-threading is an absolute must for this to have any sort of scalability. There is no other way to do this that can work. It\'s very hard to even guess at an upper bound on how long this might take. I\'d have to do a little digging on the best way to tell if the socket is truly connectable, but at the most basic level you\'d let the TCP handshake complete and then close the socket cleanly, to be nice. That involves the exchange of at least 6 packets, each with an associated round trip time. You\'re going to have to pick a timeout that is reasonable so that you don\'t end up with lots of false negatives. A certain number of checks can be done in parallel, but that amounts to a hell of a lot of connections, and a lot of waiting on network I/O.\r\n\r\nAs a back of the envelope calculation, if you allow a 10s maximum for the connectivity test (which might even be too aggressive), and figure 5% are not connectable with the average for those that are connectable at 5s (a wild guess given this is a world-wide site), that puts you at 525,000s or around 145 hours of total checking time. Some of that can be parallelized or broken up into batches, but there\'s obviously a limit to the number of threads you want to have running, or the number of outbound ports you want this to suck up.\r\n\r\nOn the whole, I think automated connection testing is a pretty tall order. Making this an \"on-demand\" feature that users initiate really seems like the best approach to me.',NULL,NULL),(48050,6124,90006,'2012-10-18 21:38:44','Looks like you guys have this one knocked out.  :smile1: ',NULL,NULL),(48051,6120,84499,'2012-10-18 22:08:24','\r\n\r\nwhats weird is that tbdev just loops through the connections opening a socket for all of them every announce cycle... and with no multi-threading...\r\n\r\nanyway I am agreed we go with the manual approach - its implemented here now and appears to be working okay. \r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(48052,6120,90006,'2012-10-18 23:11:52','Wow, very interesting. I\'m kinda shocked that that isn\'t causing problems.  :laugh: \r\n\r\nSounds good, though. Is there anything else I can give you guys a hand with?',NULL,NULL),(48053,6120,94952,'2012-10-18 23:26:28','I\'m quite certain it causes some of the issues with emp.me at the moment are caused by the enormous load created by testing connections.',NULL,NULL),(48054,6120,84499,'2012-10-18 23:58:55','[quote=salvia5x,f3120,28052]Wow, very interesting. I\'m kinda shocked that that isn\'t causing problems.  :laugh: \r\n\r\nSounds good, though. Is there anything else I can give you guys a hand with?[/quote]\r\n\r\nNow we aren\'t adding a socket test to the tracker the changes are pretty simple - simple enough that Mobbo has completed all of them already. In many ways I would like to engage you in some tracker work just so we can involve you and keep you around and interested (I want more technical folks on hand), but inventing changes for the sake of it is probably not a good idea ;)\r\n\r\nWe might still be able to use your expertise if we run into any issues with setting up stuff on the emp server or something, or if there are uncaught bugs in the tracker maybe. Have a look at the changeover planning thread in this forum - I am hoping now that we will be going open beta next week maybe, certainly in the very near future - with the plan being to changeover the site a week after that if all goes well. Whether we actually [i]need[/i] you or not it would be good just to get another persons opinion on some of the technical stuff. I am going to boost you to staff on the test tracker anyway, hopefully you will stick around and see what happens :smile1:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(48055,6120,90006,'2012-10-19 00:31:58','Cool. I actually did have a chance to go out on github and check out Mobbo\'s changes earlier today (looked good to me).\r\n\r\nSounds good on the changeover planning. I\'ll keep an eye on that thread and of course feel free to PM me if you need anything specific.  :smile1: \r\n\r\nCheers and great work on the new site!',NULL,NULL),(48056,6125,6203,'2012-10-19 01:05:35','i am not sure if this is a bug but when i move my mouse over my user name in the top right menu, i see no counter behind the bookmarks but behind the suscription a counter appears.\n\nokay got it now. the counter shows up for new messages in a topic. sry.',6203,'2012-10-19 01:15:48'),(48057,6120,47234,'2012-10-19 04:36:21','I swear we had 2 or 3 tracker issues not just one.  Wasnt there something about it not updating quick enough.  Sorry too many conversations :lol:\n\nPeer lists updating maybe?\n\n\nEdit;  Found it in Changeover planning\n\n1) The ocelot code. The tracker code has a couple of issues, one minor, one very annoying.\nMinor issue: the tracker does not update the peerlist data very often.  <-- thats the one\n[s]Major issue: the tracker always reports a peers status as connectable regardless of real status.[/s]  this ones fixed :)',47234,'2012-10-19 04:41:47'),(48058,6105,94952,'2012-10-19 04:59:13','There are a few special packages needed to compile ocelot on Ubuntu atleast. I found out this the hard way. \r\n[*]MySQL++\r\n[*]Boost (system & thread)\r\n[*]libEvent',NULL,NULL),(48059,6126,84499,'2012-10-19 14:16:50','\n[quote=Mobbo]Query error: BIGINT UNSIGNED value is out of range in \'(`gazelle`.`users_main`.`Uploaded` + values(`gazelle`.`users_main`.`Uploaded`))\' in flush users with a qlength: 181 queue size: 34\nComing once per second. I will try to figure out what is generating the error[/quote]\n\n[quote=Mobbo]The error comes from line 344-347 in worker.cpp and 184-197 in db.cpp. record_user and flush_user.\n[code]\nlong long uploaded_change = 0;\nlong long downloaded_change = 0;\n[/code] are used in the tracker. I think they are too big for the db-table[/quote]\n\n:hmmm:\n\n\nbigint is a 64 bit integer and afaics long long is also a 64 bit integer.\n\nlong long is signed I think, the bigint is unsigned, but surely that could only be the cause of the error if uploaded_change/downloaded_change is negative? - which afaics cannot happen.\n \nI dont know... \n\nthings possibly worth trying:\nusing an unsigned int64 in the tracker\ntesting if uploaded_change/downloaded_change goes negative (shouldnt be happening but...)\ncan we get the error message to include the sql string? or some other logging so we can examine the values that are causing the problem.\n\n',84499,'2012-10-19 14:17:45'),(48060,6126,84499,'2012-10-19 14:28:56','\nOR it could just be an addition overflow lol\n\n[code]+--------+-----------+----------------------+---------------+\n| ID     | Username  | Uploaded             | Downloaded    |\n+--------+-----------+----------------------+---------------+\n| 100033 | mc2k6     | 18446744073709551615 |             0 |\n|  85636 | MrRandom  | 18446744073709551615 | 1100585369600 |\n|  59364 | Sibbe     | 17255242132922826752 |             0 |\n+--------+-----------+----------------------+---------------+[/code]\n\nbigint max size=18446744073709551615 ...\n\n\n :banghead: \n\nlet me try and work out why mc2k6 and MrR have maxed out their uploaded... if thats the result of an error its our fault, if its the result of staff jiggery fuckery ...  :nasher: \n',84499,'2012-10-19 14:44:45'),(48061,6126,84499,'2012-10-19 14:40:21','\r\nokay the mc2k6 guy is some cheater who was banned by usb in feb.\r\n\r\nthe cause I am fairly sure is MrR having a maxed out upload and then uploading...\r\n\r\nI have removed his silly upload amount - hopefully that will stop the errors being thrown in the tracker.\r\n\r\n\r\nIf thats the case then problem solved. Except perhaps we should have some guard against this - although its an \'impossible\' amount to upload (its 18 million TB+) the one edge case where it can happen is with cheaters. Hopefully we would catch them fairly quick (these are very bad cheaters... and you cannot stay at the top of the top10 with 18,000,000+ TB for long without being noticed...) but perhaps we should have some trap somewhere to stop a maxed out field from causing this error in the meantime? ',NULL,NULL),(48062,6120,84499,'2012-10-19 15:05:52','\r\n\r\nI\'ve thought about it but having got to know ocelot a bit better I think about the only practical thing we can do about that is make the announce happen quicker than every 30 minutes.\r\n\r\nThat may be a possibility, but we should probably load test the tracker with a 30 min announce first and see how it goes. Personally I would like it to do an announce every 15 mins from the pov of useability (quicker updates to peerlists) but we\'ll have to see.\r\n\r\nI had thought it would just be a case of updating the db when a peer connects or disconnects - but ocelot by design queues up all the db updates and then flushes them every announce cycle in a separate thread. In theory we could force an immediate db update for new peers but its a bad idea imo, better to have a shorter announce cycle I think and keep the (good) design to the db flushing.\r\n\r\n',NULL,NULL),(48063,6078,84038,'2012-10-20 03:12:48','My headless torrenting Linux box uses rTorrent 0.8.9/0.12.9\r\n\r\nThat\'s rTorrent version 0.8.9 and version 0.12.9 of the lib.',NULL,NULL),(48064,6078,84499,'2012-10-20 04:06:36','\r\nactually we should have said but we have just implemented it as a blacklist after all :lol:\r\n\r\nmuch better idea at the end of the day.',NULL,NULL),(48065,6120,47234,'2012-10-20 08:26:15','Ok i will believe you :lol:  Most of that was beyond my understanding but thats ok i dont need to understand.  If your happy with the way things are i say leave them.  One thing about a shorter announce is its going to increase server load.  15 minutes would be nice but can the server cope?',NULL,NULL),(48066,6078,47234,'2012-10-20 08:28:06','Yeah we now have a blacklist :)',NULL,NULL),(48067,6124,47234,'2012-10-20 08:30:16','One quick question for mifune.  When a staffer stumbles across a user using a (fairly unknown) client thats reporting bad stats to the tracker is there any way to retrieve the information we need to add it to the blacklist?  Or would someone need to manually check the DB or similar?',NULL,NULL),(48068,6120,94952,'2012-10-20 09:09:54','I would leave it at 30 minutes for now and look at the load some time after launch. And then maybe decrease it to 15 minutes. Right now we are using a overpowered server with barely 50 active clients.',NULL,NULL),(48069,6127,47234,'2012-10-20 12:15:05','Ok so some time (hopefully very soon) this will be what Empornium looks like and i get my Seedbox back.\r\n\r\nBut would it be helpful to the developers to still have a test server?\r\n\r\nI need to discuss it with USB yet but im thinking of three options.  \r\n\r\nFirst my current seedbox a Kimsufi2G could be used as i doubt we would need to much server when not running a huge test like this.\r\n\r\nSecond is empforums which is on my old seedbox underutilises the server a lot (its just a forums and the chat).  That server could double up as the Emp test server and maybe IRC as well (must speak to MrR as IRC exists on my current seedbox)\r\n\r\nThird option is i order up another 16G. Move empforums and IRC on to it and being that it has plenty of capacity left it gets used for an emp test server too.\r\n\r\nWhats not optional though is my Seedbox changing from a 2G to a 16G\r\n\r\nCurrently im running 2G (empforums), 2G (seedbox and IRC server) and 16G (test tracker)\r\n\r\nUnder option one that wouldnt change much just the uses on the same 3 servers.  \r\nUnder option two i reduce my costs by one 2G.  Never a bad thing.\r\nUnder option three my costs increase slightly as you can get two 2G\'s for less than a 16G but the server is likely to be much more useful.  The extra about $10 a month wont kill me.\r\n\r\nSo thoughts.  Would a test server being available help?  If so what option would suit best?',NULL,NULL),(48070,6127,84499,'2012-10-20 14:36:53','\nIf we want to make changes to the code then it will be useful to still have a test tracker - for example if we want to add some proper cheating tools say its nearly impossible to meaningfully test tracker-site interaction on my local dev server (at home). I say just stick it on the empforums server though, we wont need (or want) a big bunch of testers. So... option 2.',84499,'2012-10-20 14:37:16'),(48071,6123,67255,'2012-10-20 17:13:32','Works great',NULL,NULL),(48072,6128,70679,'2012-10-20 22:59:32','I am starting this thread because you may or may not have noticed there were changes in the backend of our IRC system. So some commands changed.\n\nWe are also thinking of changing the reference guides structure. Instead of having them all here we are thinking of just linking to a web site that then will be kept up to date. Should be easier this way. We then just put a link in the local guides and also implement a bot command like for example !emphelp that will take you there at any moment from IRC.\n\nThat said this thread can be used to report commands that no longer work so that the web guide can be updated or another fix like an alias can be implemented.',70679,'2012-10-20 22:59:54'),(48073,6129,84499,'2012-10-21 00:06:21','\r\nI have changed the way the PM system deals with forwarding.\r\n\r\nPlease test forwarding PM\'s, and other PM functions.\r\n\r\n\r\nnote: old PM\'s that were forwarded using the old system may possibly throw up some weird stuff... I\'ll be mildly interested to know but as long as newly forwarded PM\'s work as expected I will be happy.',NULL,NULL),(48074,6128,84499,'2012-10-21 00:10:12','\r\n\r\nI would prefer it if instructions at least for users remain here, otherwise they wont be seen nearly as much.\r\n\r\n\r\nAlso, I am all for doing stuff the right way, but there is value in having stability - what I am saying is lets not change all the commands every few months, my brain cannot learn new stuff quickly anymore.',NULL,NULL),(48075,6128,85636,'2012-10-21 00:25:28','This should be the only time the commands should change since we moved to the IRC Services I would have originally used, and the new system is more flexible so we shouldn\'t need to change again',NULL,NULL),(48076,6015,48010,'2012-10-21 03:59:55','Client whitelist needs to be changed to blacklist when it\'s ready\n\nCollages -can we copy a guide from what.cd ? I couldnt find a guide on google - just basic crap like these !!\n\nA collage starts with a collection of torrents with similar properties - for example, \"classic jazz albums of the 60s\". The covers of these albums are then juxtaposed together to form a masterful work worthy of Henre Matisse, or some other famous artist you\'ve never heard of. Any power user can create their own collage, and any member can add to an existent project.\n\nIf you\'re a fan of minimalism (or have a slow connection), there is an option in your profile to only list the torrents, instead of having both the torrent list and the album art list.\n\nAND\n\n[url]http://filesharefreak.com/2008/09/24/5-reasons-why-you-need-to-be-a-whatcd-power-user[/url] - see number 4 with a picture example.\n\nI could put a rough description together using this - then maybe during beta test see if a member can add a guide in the forums which we could turn into an article ?\n\n[s]EDIT I did suggest before that collages were a waste of time. Thoughts on this quickly please[/s]\n\nFLS - do we need that? we have a lot of mods now\n\n[s]Notifications - are they any differnet to what we use on emp.me ?\nwe already have the torrent marked for deletion done - any others in the code that may need explaining? if no remove this from the guide[/s]\n\nEDIT strike throughs dealt with on IRC',48010,'2012-10-22 17:25:51'),(48077,6128,70679,'2012-10-21 05:29:41','I said the [b]reference [/b]manuals. The User Guides will stay here. And those commands did not change as far as I know but will recheck and correct if needed.',NULL,NULL),(48078,6130,79784,'2012-10-21 10:43:47','I know that the time to leave suggestions to be implemented in this testing phase is up. So this suggestion is for the longer future after this new emp is already up and running, basically a future improvement. Basically I had this idea today when using YouTube. On YouTube you can subscribe to channels, would it not be great if there was a function here at emp that enabled downloaders to subscribe to their favourite uploaders?\r\n\r\nThen I would be able to find subscribed content on my profile page and the uploaders would be able to see how many subscribers they have. That would be an even better form of appraisal and keep uploaders motivated and happy rather than just rely on comments, thanks and nr of downloads. Perhaps it could also be possible for uploaders to compose newsletters to send to subscribers email addresses so that their subscribers would be notified of new content by their fave uploaders ( of course subscribers should have the option to choose if they want to subscribe to such newsletters).\r\n\r\nWhat do you guys think of this idea?\r\n\r\nI think it would be great! :gjob: ',NULL,NULL),(48079,6015,84499,'2012-10-21 15:37:48','\r\n\r\na few of the testers really liked collages, and we spent some time fixing and adjusting them. They are not being removed now.\r\n\r\nWhat notifications on emp? :hmmm:\r\n\r\nI dont understand what you are saying about MFD? any other what in the code?',NULL,NULL),(48081,6130,84499,'2012-10-21 15:49:03','\r\n\r\nmoved thread to suggestions forum.',NULL,NULL),(48082,6129,86439,'2012-10-21 19:46:10','Ok weird quirk, I just selected Clownnius from the staff list to forward a message to (I expected the radio button to auto select), but it never highlighted the check button so i have no idea where it sent it. I needed to manually click the staff radio button, then select Clownius on my second attempt.\n\nThere also is no way to tell who it forwarded to after its sent, so no idea if clownius even received it.\n\nThis is an older message so maybe its one of the weird responses you expected, I have no new ones to play with.',86439,'2012-10-21 19:48:25'),(48083,6129,84499,'2012-10-21 23:06:54','\r\n\r\nif it was sent it should be in your sentbox, the new forwarding system just lets you compose a new message and automatically quotes the fwded post or conversation in the new message.',NULL,NULL),(48084,6127,1,'2012-10-21 23:28:31','After the move won\'t be needed many users to test future addons,\r\nso as mifune said, option 2',NULL,NULL),(48085,6061,1,'2012-10-21 23:48:35','Click on [Mass PM Snatchers] and you will get an sql error regarding to torrent description, is this exist on db ? or is this really needed when we pm users ?\nsomeone else getting this:\n[...]WHERE t.ID=\'30114\' SQL error: 1054 (Unknown column \'t.Description\' in \'field list\')',1,'2012-10-21 23:56:51'),(48086,6127,94952,'2012-10-21 23:54:09','I gotta add my voice to option 2. Sounds like a good deal to me.',NULL,NULL),(48087,6061,84499,'2012-10-22 00:35:27','\r\n\r\ndam, that is a pretty bad bug to still be around at this stage!\r\n\r\n(its been a long time since that field name was changed...)\r\n\r\nfixed :smile1:',NULL,NULL),(48088,6129,86439,'2012-10-22 02:33:30','I just received a couple from you (One re: forwarded one, and one fresh from you, and a couple of mass ones re: torrents DLed).\n\nI just tried to FWD the new one from you to schlager, sentbox says it went to mifune.\n\nI did initially try to click another staff member (USB), then reselected admin, however the radio button for staff was still blank. I entered \'schlager\' into the member box, radio botton was highlihgted for members, sentbox still says it went to mifune. It never lists schlager as the recipient of a forwarded message.\n\ni also resent the last one, without touching anything unnecessarily, sent to schlager and still lists as sent to mifune in sentbox.',86439,'2012-10-22 02:37:13'),(48089,6129,84499,'2012-10-22 02:36:22','\r\n\r\nwhat button are you pressing to forward it?',NULL,NULL),(48090,6129,86439,'2012-10-22 03:19:48','It would seem I was pressing the wrong one. But it appeared to forward anyway, but not to the intended recipient. It seems to bounce to the original, or nowhere\n\nImage of message you sent to me, I forwarded, or so I thought. Note, it records it as part of a convo, but has no recipient in that reply by me.\n\n[URL=http://imgbox.com/abuWzde6][IMG]http://t.imgbox.com/abuWzde6.jpg[/IMG][/URL] \n\nunless thats just a reply, as I probably clicked send message, despite having clicked the radio button below it and selected schlager.\n\n',86439,'2012-10-22 03:21:17'),(48091,6127,47234,'2012-10-22 05:47:32','Ok i will talk to USB and see about moving it to my John Smith 2G once i have moved the seedbox side to my tracker and then i can keep it up and running as the Emp test server.\r\n\r\nWill need to wait a little while but option 2 it shall be :)',NULL,NULL),(48092,6015,48010,'2012-10-22 14:14:32','[quote=mifune,f3015,28079]a few of the testers really liked collages, and we spent some time fixing and adjusting them. They are not being removed now.\n\nWhat notifications on emp? :hmmm:\n\nI dont understand what you are saying about MFD? any other what in the code?[/quote]\n\nSorry I wasnt clear - let\'s try again now i\'m not so tired !\n[s]\nThe new site guide already has Marked for deletion in it. As tp notifications I meant can you give a list off them from the relevant code? and are they any different to the notifications we currently use on emp.me? In other other words do we need the Notifications section?\n\nIs it clear now?[/s]\n\nAs to collages ok - so what do we do about a guide?\n\nEDIT I edited my post above',48010,'2012-10-22 17:28:59'),(48093,6128,85636,'2012-10-22 16:43:59','Guides that need checked:\r\n01. IRC for Dummies\r\n02. IRC Clients for Dummies\r\n[s]03. How to register your nickname on IRC[/s]\r\n[s]04. Grouping Nicknames together on IRC.[/s]\r\n05. Add IRC Channels to automatically join (Broken? Seems to work with #empornium but not staff channels)\r\n06. What is a vhost and how to get one. (There\'s a new offer system that needs documented)\r\n07. What staff can and cannot do on IRC.\r\n[s]08. IRC User commands[/s]\r\n09. ChanServ Commands\r\n10. NickServ Commands',NULL,NULL),(48094,6015,48010,'2012-10-22 17:33:10','TO DO\r\n\r\n1. for nofications we need a short guide to this [url=http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=notify]http://empornium.mooo.com/torrents.php?action=notify[/url]\r\n\r\n2. a quick collage item or better a proper article\r\n\r\n3. FLS text needs finalising/tidying up',NULL,NULL),(48095,6128,103720,'2012-10-22 18:53:40','I type [b]/join #empornium-staff[/b]\nbut i get this message:\n[quote]INFO: This channel requires that you have registered and identified yourself with the network\'s nickname registration services (e.g. NickServ). Please see the documentation of this network\'s nickname registration services that should be found in the MOTD (/motd to display it).[/quote]\n\n(Help and empornium channels are working ok).\n\nIt it under maintenance or something?\nIs the nick database being revised?\nI haven\'t changed anything since barumba helped me register etc.\n\nEDIT: ok, MrRandom is on it, as posted in irc.\nSo I\'ll wait. :)',103720,'2012-10-22 18:55:02'),(48096,6128,85636,'2012-10-22 19:36:30','The datacenter where one irc server which also hosted services is currently having problems and the virtual machine crashed and it isn\'t currently possible to restart it (their words not mine)',NULL,NULL),(48097,6128,70679,'2012-10-22 23:03:58','Thinks are back to normal.',NULL,NULL),(48098,6131,84499,'2012-10-22 23:27:54','\r\nMobbo connected up some code in the tracker for recording connection speeds and I have made a first stab at some cheater tools.\r\n\r\nUnder Staff Tools you will find: [url=/tools.php?action=cheats]Speed Records[/url]\r\n\r\nThe tracker records all peer speeds (for every connection) every announce cycle in the db. Obviously this can generate a huge volume of data very quickly. On the Speed Records page there is a setting for how long after they are first recorded records are deleted in the scheduler, and then a setting to keep records after this time if the upload speed is over the amount set.\r\n\r\nYou can also put users and torrents on a watch list, which will also stop their records from being deleted (staff right now can add and remove torrents/users from the torrent detail page and the user page, I will probably add some links to do this on the speed records page as well for each user/torrent listed). The idea being that if you see some suspicious activity from a user but are not sure - which is often the case in my experience - you can add them to the user watchlist, and/or add a torrent they are on and then check the detailed records later.\r\n\r\nI will make (some of) the columns on the Speed Records page sortable at some point. And there are some other things left to add like a direct link to ban a user for cheating maybe. And listing only records for a specific user or torrent, and probably a link from a users info in a peerlist to put them/the torrent on the watchlists. Anyway the record keeping part of it should work already lol\r\n',NULL,NULL),(48099,6128,86439,'2012-10-23 01:15:29','Normal? Normal?\r\n\r\nI have to enter my password each time i log in now. No idea why, but its changed from before where i just opened mIRC and \'voila\'.',NULL,NULL),(48100,6131,47234,'2012-10-23 02:47:54','Thanks Mifune it will be nice to have some cheat detection tools :)',NULL,NULL),(48101,6128,70679,'2012-10-23 03:25:10','[quote=knickers,f3128,28099]Normal? Normal?\r\n\r\nI have to enter my password each time i log in now. No idea why, but its changed from before where i just opened mIRC and \'voila\'.[/quote]\r\n\r\nYou need to do a slight change to the script.... I can help ya.',NULL,NULL),(48102,6131,48010,'2012-10-23 14:34:34','as clownius said\r\n+1',NULL,NULL),(48103,6015,48010,'2012-10-23 16:03:19','Forgot one - the search function but ASIMO is looking at it\r\n\r\nI will work on notifications\r\n\r\nthen maybe collages using what forum posts we have already. Seems like that should be enough to make a basic guide ? I dunno\r\n\r\nas to FLS we need to ask Crozz and ASIMO what role they will do then edit as needed. They are both on irc so shouldnt be too difficult to do that',NULL,NULL),(48104,6132,84499,'2012-10-23 17:03:18','\r\nsomewhere to talk about adminy things\r\n\r\nusers with access:\r\nadmin\r\nlanz\r\nj4n\r\nmifune\r\ndave\r\nclownius',NULL,NULL),(48105,6015,84499,'2012-10-23 17:05:03','\r\n\r\ndave there is a better todo list here:http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3061',NULL,NULL),(48106,6015,48010,'2012-10-23 18:20:08','[quote=mifune,f3015,28105]dave there is a better todo list here:http://empornium.mooo.com/forums.php?action=viewthread&threadid=3061[/quote]\r\n\r\ntrue but this is specific to the new site guide',NULL,NULL),(48107,6133,84499,'2012-10-23 18:54:55','\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions about how things work on the new site put them here and we will answer them. I will probably end up using the answers to help write/fill out the staff guide sections in help.',NULL,NULL),(48108,6133,94952,'2012-10-23 18:58:01','I will help out with answers when ever I can.',NULL,NULL);
